g1375.d: διωγμός diōgmós, dee-ogue-mos'; from G1377; persecution:—persecution.
g1375.r: From διώκω (G1377)|English: persecute, follow after, follow, suffer persecution, misc

g1376.d: διώκτης diṓktēs, dee-oke'-tace; from G1377; a persecutor:—persecutor.
g1376.r: From διώκω (G1377)|English: persecute, follow after, follow, suffer persecution, misc

g1377.d:
διώκω diṓkō, dee-o'-ko; a prolonged (and causative) form of a primary verb δίω díō (to flee; 
 compare the base of G1169 and G1249); to pursue (literally or
 figuratively); by implication, to persecute:—ensue, follow (after),
 given to, (suffer) persecute(-ion), press forward.
g1377.r: A prolonged (and causative) form of a primary verb dio (to flee; cf the base of δειλός (G1169) and διάκονος (G1249))|English: fearful

g1378.d:
δόγμα dógma, dog'-mah; from the base of G1380; a law (civil, ceremonial or
 ecclesiastical):—decree, ordinance.
g1378.r: From the base of δοκέω (G1380)|English: think, seem, suppose, seem good, please, misc

g1379.d:
δογματίζω dogmatízō, dog-mat-id'-zo; from G1378; to prescribe by statute, i.e. (reflexively) to submit to,
 ceremonially rule:—be subject to ordinances.

g138.r: Probably akin to αἴρω (G142)|English: take up, take away, take, away with, lift up, bear, misc

g1380.d:
δοκέω dokéō, dok-eh'-o; a prolonged form of a primary verb, δόκω dókō dok'-o (used only in an
 alternate in certain tenses; compare the base of G1166) of the same
 meaning; to think; by implication, to seem (truthfully or
 uncertainly):—be accounted, (of own) please(-ure), be of reputation,
 seem (good), suppose, think, trow.
g1380.r: A prolonged form of a primary verb, doko {dok'-o} (used only in an alternate in certain tenses; cf the base of δεικνύω (G1166)) of the same meaning|English: show

g1381.d:
†δοκιμάζω dokimázō, dok-im-ad'-zo; from G1384; to test (literally or figuratively); by implication, to
 approve:—allow, discern, examine, × like, (ap-)prove, try.

g1382.d:
δοκιμή dokimḗ, dok-ee-may'; from the same as G1384; test (abstractly or concretely); by
 implication, trustiness:—experience(-riment), proof, trial.
g1382.r: From the same as δόκιμος (G1384)|English: approved, tried

g1383.d:
δοκίμιον dokímion, dok-im'-ee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G1382; a testing; by implication,
 trustworthiness:—trial, trying.
g1383.r: A presumed derivative of δοκιμή (G1382)|English: proof, experience, trial, experiment

g1384.d:
δόκιμος dókimos, dok'-ee-mos; from G1380; properly, acceptable (current after assayal), i.e.
 approved:—approved, tried.
g1384.r: From δοκέω (G1380)|English: think, seem, suppose, seem good, please, misc

g1385.d: δοκός dokós, dok-os'; from G1209 (through the idea of holding up); a stick of timber:—beam.
g1385.r: From δέχομαι (G1209) (through the idea of holding up)|English: receive, take, accept, take up

g1386.d: δόλιος dólios, dol'-ee-os; from G1388; guileful:—deceitful.
g1386.r: From δόλος (G1388)|English: guile, subtilty, deceit, craft

g1387.d: δολιόω dolióō, dol-ee-o'-o; from G1386; to be guileful:—use deceit.

g1388.r: From an obsolete primary verb, dello (probably meant to decoy; cf δελεάζω (G1185))|English: entice, beguile, allure

g1389.d:
δολόω dolóō, dol-o'-o; from G1388; to ensnare, i.e. (figuratively) adulterate:—handle
 deceitfully.
g1389.r: From δόλος (G1388)|English: guile, subtilty, deceit, craft

g139.d:
αἵρεσις haíresis, hah'-ee-res-is; from G138; properly, a choice, i.e. (specially) a party or (abstractly)
 disunion:—heresy (which is the Greek word itself), sect.

g1390.d: δόμα dóma, dom'-ah; from the base of G1325; a present:—gift.
g1390.r: From the base of δίδωμι (G1325)|English: give, grant, put, show, deliver, make

g1391.d:
δόξα dóxa, dox'-ah; from the base of G1380; glory (as very apparent), in a wide application
 (literal or figurative, objective or subjective):—dignity,
 glory(-ious), honour, praise, worship.
g1391.r: From the base of δοκέω (G1380)|English: think, seem, suppose, seem good, please, misc

g1392.d:
δοξάζω doxázō, dox-ad'-zo; from G1391; to render (or esteem) glorious (in a wide
 application):—(make) glorify(-ious), full of (have) glory, honour,
 magnify.
g1392.r: From δόξα (G1391)|English: glory, glorious, honour, praise, dignity, worship

g1393.d: Δορκάς Dorkás, dor-kas'; gazelle; Dorcas, a Christian woman:—Dorcas.

g1394.d:
δόσις dósis, dos'-is; from the base of G1325; a giving; by implication, (concretely) a
 gift:—gift, giving.
g1394.r: From the base of δίδωμι (G1325)|English: give, grant, put, show, deliver, make

g1395.d: δότης dótēs, dot'-ace; from the base of G1325; a giver:—giver.
g1395.r: From the base of δίδωμι (G1325)|English: give, grant, put, show, deliver, make

g1396.d:
δουλαγωγέω doulagōgéō, doo-lag-ogue-eh'-o; from a presumed compound of G1401 and G71; to be a slave-driver, i.e. to
 enslave (figuratively, subdue):—bring into subjection.
g1396.r: From a presumed compound of δοῦλος (G1401) and ἄγω (G71)|English: servant, bond, bondman

g1397.d: δουλεία douleía, doo-li'-ah; from G1398; slavery (ceremonially or figuratively):—bondage.
g1397.r: From δουλεύω (G1398)|English: serve, be in bondage, do service

g1398.d:
δουλεύω douleúō, dool-yoo'-o; from G1401; to be a slave to (literal or figurative, involuntary or
 voluntary):—be in bondage, (do) serve(-ice).

g1399.d:
δούλη doúlē, doo'-lay; feminine of G1401; a female slave (involuntarily or
 voluntarily):—handmaid(-en).
g1399.r: Feminine of δοῦλος (G1401)|English: servant, bond, bondman

g14.d: ἀγαθοεργέω agathoergéō, ag-ath-er-gheh'-o; from G18 and G2041; to work good:—do good.
g14.r: From ἀγαθός (G18) and ἔργον (G2041)|English: good, good thing, that which is good, the thing which is good, well, benefit

g140.d: αἱρετίζω hairetízō, hahee-ret-id'-zo; from a derivative of G138; to make a choice:—choose.
g140.r: From a derivative of αἱρέω (G138)|English: choose

g1400.d: δοῦλον doûlon, doo'-lon; neuter of G1401; subservient:—servant.

g1401.r: From δέω (G1210)|English: bind, tie, knit, be in bonds, wind

g1402.d:
δουλόω doulóō, doo-lo'-o; from G1401; to enslave (literally or figuratively):—bring into (be
 under) bondage, × given, become (make) servant.

g1403.d: δοχή dochḗ, dokh-ay'; from G1209; a reception, i.e. convivial entertainment:—feast.
g1403.r: From δέχομαι (G1209)|English: receive, take, accept, take up

g1404.d:
δράκων drákōn, drak'-own; probably from an alternate form of δέρκομαι dérkomai (to look); a fabulous kind
 of serpent (perhaps as supposed to fascinate):—dragon.
g1404.r: Probably from an alternate form of derkomai (to look)|

g1405.d:
δράσσομαι drássomai, dras'-som-ahee; perhaps akin to the base of G1404 (through the idea of capturing); to
 grasp, i.e. (figuratively) entrap:—take.
g1405.r: Perhaps akin to the base of δράκων (G1404) (through the idea of capturing)|English: dragon

g1406.d:
δραχμή drachmḗ, drakh-may'; from G1405; a drachma or (silver) coin (as handled):—piece (of
 silver).

g1407.d:
δρέπανον drépanon, drep'-an-on; from δρέπω drépō (to pluck); a gathering hook (especially for
 harvesting):—sickle.

g1408.d:
δρόμος drómos, drom'-os; from the alternate of G5143; a race, i.e. (figuratively)
 career:—course.
g1408.r: From the alternate of τρέχω (G5143)|English: run, have course

g1409.d:
Δρούσιλλα Droúsilla, droo'-sil-lah; a feminine diminutive of Drusus (a Roman name); Drusilla, a member of
 the Herodian family:—Drusilla.
g1409.r: A diminutive of Drusus (a Roman name)|

g141.d: αἱρετικός hairetikós, hahee-ret-ee-kos'; from the same as G140; a schismatic:—heretic (the Greek word itself).
g141.r: From the same as αἱρετίζω (G140)|English: choose

g1410.d:
δύναμαι dýnamai, doo'-nam-ahee; of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible:—be able, can (do, +
 -not), could, may, might, be possible, be of power.

g1411.d:
δύναμις dýnamis, doo'-nam-is; from G1410; force (literally or figuratively); specially, miraculous
 power (usually by implication, a miracle itself):—ability, abundance,
 meaning, might(-ily, -y, -y deed), (worker of) miracle(-s), power,
 strength, violence, mighty (wonderful) work.
g1411.r: From δύναμαι (G1410)|English: can (could), cannot, be able, may (might), able, misc

g1412.d: δυναμόω dynamóō, doo-nam-o'-o; from G1411; to enable:—strengthen.
g1412.r: From δύναμις (G1411)|English: power, mighty work, strength, miracle, might, virtue, mighty, misc

g1413.d: δυνάστης dynástēs, doo-nas'-tace; from G1410; a ruler or officer:—of great authority, mighty, potentate.
g1413.r: From δύναμαι (G1410)|English: can (could), cannot, be able, may (might), able, misc

g1414.d: δυνατέω dynatéō, doo-nat-eh'-o; from G1415; to be efficient (figuratively):—be mighty.
g1414.r: From δυνατός (G1415)|English: possible, able, mighty, strong, could, power, mighty man

g1415.d:
δυνατός dynatós, doo-nat-os'; from G1410; powerful or capable (literally or figuratively); neuter
 possible:—able, could, (that is) mighty (man), possible, power,
 strong.
g1415.r: From δύναμαι (G1410)|English: can (could), cannot, be able, may (might), able, misc

g1416.r: Prolonged forms of an obsolete primary duo {doo'-o} (to sink)|

g1417.d: δύο dýo, doo'-o; a primary numeral; "two":—both, twain, two.

g1419.d: δυσβάστακτος dysbástaktos, doos-bas'-tak-tos; from G1418 and a derivative of G941; oppressive:—grievous to be borne.
g1419.r: From δυσ- (G1418) and a derivative of βαστάζω (G941)|English: n/a

g142.d:
αἴρω aírō, ah'-ee-ro; a primary root; to lift up; by implication, to take up or away;
 figuratively, to raise (the voice), keep in suspense (the mind),
 specially, to sail away (i.e. weigh anchor); by Hebraism (compare
 H5375) to expiate sin:—away with, bear (up), carry, lift up, loose,
 make to doubt, put away, remove, take (away, up).

g1420.d:
†δυσεντερία dysentería, doos-en-ter-ee'-ah; from G1418 and a comparative of G1787 (meaning a bowel); a
 "dysentery":—bloody flux.
g1420.r: From δυσ- (G1418) and a comparative of ἐντός (G1787) (meaning a bowel)|English: n/a

g1421.d:
δυσερμήνευτος dysermḗneutos, doos-er-mane'-yoo-tos; from G1418 and a presumed derivative of G2059; difficult of
 explanation:—hard to be uttered.
g1421.r: From δυσ- (G1418) and a presumed derivative of ἑρμηνεύω (G2059)|English: n/a

g1422.d:
δύσκολος dýskolos, doo'-kol-os; from G1418 and κόλον kólon (food); properly, fastidious about eating
 (peevish), i.e. (genitive case) impracticable:—hard.

g1423.d: δυσκόλως dyskólōs, doos-kol'-oce; adverb from G1422; impracticably:—hardly.

g1424.d:
δυσμή dysmḗ, doos-may'; from G1416; the sun-set, i.e. (by implication) the western
 region:—west.

g1425.d:
δυσνόητος dysnóētos, doos-no'-ay-tos; from G1418 and a derivative of G3539; difficult of perception:—hard to
 be understood.
g1425.r: From δυσ- (G1418) and a derivative of νοέω (G3539)|English: n/a

g1426.d: δυσφημία dysphēmía, doos-fay-mee'-ah; from a compound of G1418 and G5345; defamation:—evil report.
g1426.r: From a compound of δυσ- (G1418) and φήμη (G5345)|English: n/a

g1427.d: †δώδεκα dṓdeka, do'-dek-ah; from G1417 and G1176; two and ten, i.e. a dozen:—twelve.
g1427.r: From δύο (G1417) and δέκα (G1176)|English: two, twain, both, two and two

g1428.d: δωδέκατος dōdékatos, do-dek'-at-os; from G1427; twelfth:—twelfth.

g1429.d: δωδεκάφυλον dōdekáphylon, do-dek-af'-oo-lon; from G1427 and G5443; the commonwealth of Israel:—twelve tribes.

g143.d:
αἰσθάνομαι aisthánomai, ahee-sthan'-om-ahee; of uncertain derivation; to apprehend (properly, by the
 senses):—perceive.

g1430.d:
δῶμα dōma, do'-mah; from δέμω démō (to build); properly, an edifice, i.e. (specially) a
 roof:—housetop.

g1431.d: δωρεά dōreá, do-reh-ah'; from G1435; a gratuity:—gift.

g1432.d:
δωρεάν dōreán, do-reh-an'; accusative case of G1431 as adverb; gratuitously (literally or
 figuratively):—without a cause, freely, for naught, in vain.
g1432.r: Accusative case of δωρεά (G1431) as adverb|English: gift

g1433.d: δωρέομαι dōréomai, do-reh'-om-ahee; middle voice from G1435; to bestow gratuitously:—give.
g1433.r: Middle voice from δῶρον (G1435)|English: gift, offering

g1434.d: δώρημα dṓrēma, do'-ray-mah; from G1433; a bestowment:—gift.

g1435.d: δῶρον dōron, do'-ron; a present; specially, a sacrifice:—gift, offering.

g1436.d:
ἔα éa, eh'-ah; apparent imperative of G1439; properly, let it be, i.e. (as
 interjection) aha!:—let alone.
g1436.r: Apparent imperative of ἐάω (G1439)|English: suffer, let alone, leave, let, commit

g1437.d:
†ἐάν eán, eh-an'; from G1487 and G302; a conditional particle; in case that, provided,
 etc.; often used in connection with other particles to denote
 indefiniteness or uncertainty:—before, but, except, (and) if, (if)
 so, (what-, whither-)soever, though, when (-soever), whether (or), to
 whom, (who-)so(-ever). See G3361.
g1437.r: From εἰ (G1487) and ἄν (G302)|English: if, whether, that, not tr, misc

g1438.d:
ἑαυτοῦ heautoû, heh-ow-too'; from a reflexive pronoun otherwise obsolete and the genitive case
 (dative case or accusative case) of G846; him- (her-, it-, them-, also
 (in conjunction with the personal pronoun of the other persons) my-,
 thy-, our-, your-) self (selves), etc.:—alone, her (own, -self), (he)
 himself, his (own), itself, one (to) another, our (thine)
 own(-selves), + that she had, their (own, own selves), (of)
 them(-selves), they, thyself, you, your (own, own conceits, own
 selves, -selves).
g1438.r: From a reflexive pronoun otherwise obsolete and the genitive case (dative case or accusative case) of αὐτός (G846)|English: him, his, their, he, her, they, same, himself, misc

g1439.d:
ἐάω eáō, eh-ah'-o; of uncertain affinity; to let be, i.e. permit or leave alone:—commit,
 leave, let (alone), suffer. See also G1436.

g144.d: αἴσθησις aísthēsis, ah'-ee-sthay-sis; from G143; perception, i.e. (figuratively) discernment:—judgment.

g1440.d:
†ἑβδομήκοντα hebdomḗkonta, heb-dom-ay'-kon-tah; from G1442 and a modified form of G1176; seventy:—seventy, three score
 and ten.
g1440.r: From ἕβδομος (G1442) and a modified form of δέκα (G1176)|English: seventh

g1441.d: ἑβδομηκοντάκις hebdomēkontákis, heb-dom-ay-kon-tak-is; multiple adverb from G1440; seventy times:—seventy times.
g1441.r: From ἑβδομήκοντα (G1440)|English: seventy, three score and ten, three score and fifteen

g1442.d: ἕβδομος hébdomos, heb'-dom-os; ordinal from G2033; seventh:—seventh.

g1443.d: Ἐβέρ Ebér, eb-er'; of Hebrew origin (H5677); Eber, a patriarch:—Eber.
g1443.r: Of Hebrew origin עֵבֶר (H5677)|English: Eber, Heber

g1445.d: Ἑβραῖος Hebraîos, heb-rah'-yos; from G1443; a Hebræan (i.e. Hebrew) or Jew:—Hebrew.

g1446.d:
Ἑβραΐς Hebraḯs, heb-rah-is'; from G1443; the Hebraistic (Hebrew) or Jewish (Chaldee)
 language:—Hebrew.

g1447.d:
Ἑβραϊστί Hebraïstí, heb-rah-is-tee'; adverb from G1446; Hebraistically or in the Jewish (Chaldee)
 language:—in (the) Hebrew (tongue).

g1448.d:
ἐγγίζω engízō, eng-id'-zo; from G1451; to make near, i.e. (reflexively) approach:—approach, be at
 hand, come (draw) near, be (come, draw) nigh.
g1448.r: From ἐγγύς (G1451)|English: nigh, at hand, nigh at hand, near, from, nigh unto, ready

g1449.d: ἐγγράφω engráphō, eng-graf'-o; from G1722 and G1125; to "engrave", i.e. inscribe:—write (in).
g1449.r: From ἐν (G1722) and γράφω (G1125)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g145.d:
αἰσθητήριον aisthētḗrion, ahee-sthay-tay'-ree-on; from a derivative of G143; properly, an organ of perception, i.e.
 (figuratively) judgment:—senses.
g145.r: From a derivative of αἰσθάνομαι (G143)|English: perceive

g1450.d:
ἔγγυος éngyos, eng'-goo-os; from G1722 and γυῖον guîon (a limb); pledged (as if articulated by a member),
 i.e. a bondsman:—surety.
g1450.r: From ἐν (G1722) and guion (a limb)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1451.d:
ἐγγύς engýs, eng-goos'; from a primary verb ἄγχω ánchō (to squeeze or throttle; akin to the base of
 G43); near (literally or figuratively, of place or time):—from , at
 hand, near, nigh (at hand, unto), ready.
g1451.r: From a primary verb agcho (to squeeze or throttle; akin to the base of ἀγκάλη (G43))|English: arm

g1453.d:
ἐγείρω egeírō, eg-i'-ro; probably akin to the base of G58 (through the idea of collecting one's
 faculties); to waken (transitively or intransitively), i.e. rouse
 (literally, from sleep, from sitting or lying, from disease, from
 death; or figuratively, from obscurity, inactivity, ruins,
 nonexistence):—awake, lift (up), raise (again, up), rear up, (a-)rise
 (again, up), stand, take up.
g1453.r: Probably akin to the base of ἀγορά (G58) (through the idea of collecting one's faculties)|English: market, marketplace, street

g1454.d: ἔγερσις égersis, eg'-er-sis; from G1453; a resurgence (from death):—resurrection.
g1454.r: From ἐγείρω (G1453)|English: rise, raise, arise, raise up, rise up, rise again, raise again, misc

g1455.d:
ἐγκάθετος enkáthetos, eng-kath'-et-os; from G1722 and a derivative of G2524; subinduced, i.e. surreptitiously
 suborned as a lier-in-wait:—spy.
g1455.r: From ἐν (G1722) and a derivative of καθίημι (G2524)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1456.d:
ἐγκαίνια enkaínia, eng-kah'-ee-nee-ah; neuter plural of a presumed compound from G1722 and G2537; innovatives,
 i.e. (specially) renewal (of religious services after the Antiochian
 interruption):—dedication.
g1456.r: Plural of a presumed compound from ἐν (G1722) and καινός (G2537)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1457.d: ἐγκαινίζω enkainízō, eng-kahee-nid'-zo; from G1456; to renew, i.e. inaugurate:—consecrate, dedicate.

g1458.d:
ἐγκαλέω enkaléō, eng-kal-eh'-o; from G1722 and G2564; to call in (as a debt or demand), i.e. bring to
 account (charge, criminate, etc.):—accuse, call in question, implead,
 lay to the charge.
g1458.r: From ἐν (G1722) and καλέω (G2564)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1459.d:
ἐγκαταλείπω enkataleípō, eng-kat-al-i'-po; from G1722 and G2641; to leave behind in some place, i.e. (in a good
 sense) let remain over, or (in a bad sense) to desert:—forsake,
 leave.
g1459.r: From ἐν (G1722) and καταλείπω (G2641)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g146.d:
αἰσχροκερδής aischrokerdḗs, ahee-skhrok-er-dace'; from G150 and κέρδος kérdos (gain); sordid:—given to (greedy of) filthy
 lucre.

g1460.d:
ἐγκατοικέω enkatoikéō, eng-kat-oy-keh'-o; from G1722 and G2730; to settle down in a place, i.e. reside:—dwell
 among.
g1460.r: From ἐν (G1722) and κατοικέω (G2730)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1461.d:
ἐγκεντρίζω enkentrízō, eng-ken-trid'-zo; from G1722 and a derivative of G2759; to prick in, i.e. ingraft:—graff
 in(-to).
g1461.r: From ἐν (G1722) and a derivative of κέντρον (G2759)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1462.d:
ἔγκλημα énklēma, eng'-klay-mah; from G1458; an accusation, i.e. offence alleged:—crime laid against,
 laid to charge.
g1462.r: From ἐγκαλέω (G1458)|English: accuse, implead, call in question, lay anything to the charge

g1463.d:
ἐγκομβόομαι enkombóomai, eng-kom-bo'-om-ahee; middle voice from G1722 and κομβόω kombóō (to gird); to engirdle oneself (for
 labor), i.e. figuratively (the apron as being a badge of servitude) to
 wear (in token of mutual deference):—be clothed with.
g1463.r: Middle voice from ἐν (G1722) and komboo (to gird)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1464.d: ἐγκοπή enkopḗ, eng-kop-ay'; from G1465; a hindrance:—X hinder.
g1464.r: From ἐγκόπτω (G1465)|English: hinder, be tedious unto

g1465.d:
ἐγκόπτω enkóptō, eng-kop'-to; from G1722 and G2875; to cut into, i.e. (figuratively) impede,
 detain:—hinder, be tedious unto.
g1465.r: From ἐν (G1722) and κόπτω (G2875)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1466.d: ἐγκράτεια enkráteia, eng-krat'-i-ah; from G1468; self-control (especially continence):—temperance.

g1467.d:
ἐγκρατεύομαι enkrateúomai, eng-krat-yoo'-om-ahee; middle voice from G1468; to exercise self-restraint (in diet and
 chastity):—can(-not) contain, be temperate.

g1468.d:
ἐγκρατής enkratḗs, eng-krat-ace'; from G1722 and G2904; strong in a thing (masterful), i.e. (figuratively
 and reflexively) self-controlled (in appetite, etc.):—temperate.
g1468.r: From ἐν (G1722) and κράτος (G2904)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1469.d:
ἐγκρίνω enkrínō, eng-kree'-no; from G1722 and G2919; to judge in, i.e. count among:—make of the
 number.
g1469.r: From ἐν (G1722) and κρίνω (G2919)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g147.d: αἰσχροκερδῶς aischrokerdōs, ahee-skhrok-er-doce'; adverb from G146; sordidly:—for filthy lucre's sake.
g147.r: From αἰσχροκερδής (G146)|English: greedy of filthy lucre, given to filthy lucre

g1470.d: ἐγκρύπτω enkrýptō, eng-kroop'-to; from G1722 and G2928; to conceal in, i.e. incorporate with:—hid in.
g1470.r: From ἐν (G1722) and κρύπτω (G2928)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1471.d:
ἔγκυος énkyos, eng'-koo-os; from G1722 and the base of G2949; swelling inside, i.e. pregnant:—great
 with child.
g1471.r: From ἐν (G1722) and the base of κῦμα (G2949)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1472.d: ἐγχρίω enchríō, eng-khree'-o; from G1722 and G5548; to rub in (oil), i.e. besmear:—anoint.
g1472.r: From ἐν (G1722) and χρίω (G5548)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1473.d:
ἐγώ egṓ, eg-o'; a primary pronoun of the first person I (only expressed when
 emphatic):—I, me. For the other cases and the plural see G1691, G1698,
 G1700, G2248, G2249, G2254, G2257, etc.
g1473.r: A primary pronoun of the first person I (only expressed when emphatic)|

g1474.d: ἐδαφίζω edaphízō, ed-af-id'-zo; from G1475; to raze:—lay even with the ground.

g1475.d: ἔδαφος édaphos, ed'-af-os; from the base of G1476; a basis (bottom), i.e. the soil:—ground.
g1475.r: From the base of ἑδραῖος (G1476)|English: steadfast, settled

g1476.d:
ἑδραῖος hedraîos, hed-rah'-yos; from a derivative of ἕζομαι hézomai (to sit); sedentary, i.e. (by
 implication) immovable:—settled, stedfast.
g1476.r: From a derivative of hezomai (to sit)|

g1477.d:
ἑδραίωμα hedraíōma, hed-rah'-yo-mah; from a derivative of G1476; a support, i.e. (figuratively)
 basis:—ground.
g1477.r: From a derivative of ἑδραῖος (G1476)|English: steadfast, settled

g1478.d:
Ἐζεκίας Ezekías, ed-zek-ee'-as; of Hebrew origin (H2396); Ezekias (i.e. Hezekeiah), an
 Israelite:—Ezekias.
g1478.r: Of Hebrew origin חִזְקִיָּה (H2396)|English: Hezekiah, Hizkiah, Hizkijah

g1479.d:
†ἐθελοθρησκεία ethelothrēskeía, eth-el-oth-race-ki'-ah; from G2309 and G2356; voluntary (arbitrary and unwarranted) piety, i.e.
 sanctimony:—will worship.
g1479.r: From θέλω (G2309) and θρησκεία (G2356)|English: will/would, will/would have, desire, desirous, list, to will, misc

g148.d: αἰσχρολογία aischrología, ahee-skhrol-og-ee'-ah; from G150 and G3056; vile conversation:—filthy communication.

g1480.d:
ἐθίζω ethízō, eth-id'-zo; from G1485; to accustom, i.e. (neuter passive participle)
 customary:—custom.
g1480.r: From ἔθος (G1485)|English: custom, manner, be wont

g1481.d: ἐθνάρχης ethnárchēs, eth-nar'-khace; from G1484 and G746; the governor (not king) of a district:—ethnarch.
g1481.r: From ἔθνος (G1484) and ἀρχή (G746)|English: Gentiles, nation, heathen, people

g1482.d:
ἐθνικός ethnikós, eth-nee-kos'; from G1484; national ("ethnic"), i.e. (specially) a Gentile:—heathen
 (man).
g1482.r: From ἔθνος (G1484)|English: Gentiles, nation, heathen, people

g1483.d: ἐθνικῶς ethnikōs, eth-nee-koce'; adverb from G1482; as a Gentile:—after the manner of Gentiles.

g1484.r: Probably from ἔθω (G1486)|English: be wont, - as his custom was, as his manner was

g1485.d:
ἔθος éthos, eth'-os; from G1486; a usage (prescribed by habit or law):—custom, manner, be
 wont.
g1485.r: From ἔθω (G1486)|English: be wont, - as his custom was, as his manner was

g1487.d:
εἰ ei, i; a primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that,
 etc.:—forasmuch as, if, that, (al-)though, whether. Often used in
 connection or composition with other particles, especially as in G1489,
 G1490, G1499, G1508, G1509, G1512, G1513, G1536, G1537. See also G1437.

g1490.d:
εἰ δὲ μή(γε) ei dè mḗ(ge), i deh may'-(gheh); from G1487, G1161, and G3361 (sometimes with G1065 added); but if
 not:—(or) else, if (not, otherwise), otherwise.
g1490.r: From εἰ (G1487), δέ (G1161), and μή (G3361) (sometimes with γέ (G1065) added)|English: if, whether, that, not tr, misc

g1491.d:
εἶδος eîdos, i'-dos; from G1492; a view, i.e. form (literally or figuratively):—appearance,
 fashion, shape, sight.
g1491.r: From εἴδω (G1492)|English: know, cannot tell, know how, wist, misc, see, behold, look, perceive

g1492.d:
†εἴδω eídō, i'-do; a primary verb; used only in certain past tenses, the others being
 borrowed from the equivalent G3700 and G3708; properly, to see
 (literally or figuratively); by implication, (in the perfect tense
 only) to know:—be aware, behold, × can (+ not tell), consider, (have)
 know(-ledge), look (on), perceive, see, be sure, tell, understand,
 wish, wot. Compare G3700.

g1493.d:
εἰδωλεῖον eidōleîon, i-do-li'-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G1497; an image-fane:—idol's
 temple.
g1493.r: From a presumed derivative of εἴδωλον (G1497)|English: idol

g1494.d:
†εἰδωλόθυτον eidōlóthyton, i-do-loth'-oo-ton; neuter of a compound of G1497 and a presumed derivative of G2380; an
 image-sacrifice, i.e. part of an idolatrous offering:—(meat, thing
 that is) offered (in sacrifice, sacrificed) to (unto) idols.
g1494.r: Neuter of a compound of εἴδωλον (G1497) and a presumed derivative of θύω (G2380)|English: idol

g1495.d:
†εἰδωλολατρεία eidōlolatreía, i-do-lol-at-ri'-ah; from G1497 and G2999; image-worship (literally or
 figuratively):—idolatry.

g1496.d:
εἰδωλολάτρης eidōlolátrēs, i-do-lol-at'-race; from G1497 and the base of G3000; an image- (servant or) worshipper
 (literally or figuratively):—idolater.
g1496.r: From εἴδωλον (G1497) and the base of λατρεύω (G3000)|English: idol

g1497.d:
εἴδωλον eídōlon, i'-do-lon; from G1491; an image (i.e. for worship); by implication, a heathen god,
 or (plural) the worship of such:—idol.
g1497.r: From εἶδος (G1491); an image (i.e. for worship)|English: shape, fashion, sight, appearance

g1498.d:
†εἴην eíēn, i'-ane; optative (i.e. English subjunctive) present of G1510 (including the
 other person); might (could, would, or should) be:—mean, + perish,
 should be, was, were.
g1498.r: Optative (i.e. English subjunctive) present of εἰμί (G1510) (including the other person)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g15.d:
ἀγαθοποιέω agathopoiéō, ag-ath-op-oy-eh'-o; from G17; to be a well-doer (as a favor or a duty):—(when) do good
 (well).

g150.d: αἰσχρός aischrós, ahee-skhros'; from the same as G153; shameful, i.e. base (specially, venal):—filthy.
g150.r: From the same as αἰσχύνω (G153)|English: be ashamed

g1500.d:
εἰκῆ eikē, i-kay'; probably from G1502 (through the idea of failure); idly, i.e. without
 reason (or effect):—without a cause, (in) vain(-ly).
g1500.r: Probably from εἴκω (G1502) (through the idea of failure)|English: give place

g1501.d: εἴκοσι eíkosi, i'-kos-ee; of uncertain affinity; a score:—twenty.

g1502.d:
εἴκω eíkō, i'-ko; apparently a primary verb; properly, to be weak, i.e. yield:—give
 place.

g1504.d:
εἰκών eikṓn, i-kone'; from G1503; a likeness, i.e. (literally) statue, profile, or
 (figuratively) representation, resemblance:—image.

g1505.d:
εἰλικρίνεια eilikríneia, i-lik-ree'-ni-ah; from G1506; clearness, i.e. (by implication) purity
 (figuratively):—sincerity.

g1506.d:
εἰλικρινής eilikrinḗs, i-lik-ree-nace'; from εἵλη heílē (the sun's ray) and G2919; judged by sunlight, i.e. tested
 as genuine (figuratively):—pure, sincere.
g1506.r: From heile (the sun's ray) and κρίνω (G2919)|English: judge, determine, condemn, go to law, call in question, esteem, misc

g151.d: αἰσχρότης aischrótēs, ahee-skhrot'-ace; from G150; shamefulness, i.e. obscenity:—filthiness.

g1510.d:
εἰμί eimí, i-mee'; the first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a
 primary and defective verb; I exist (used only when emphatic):—am,
 have been, × it is I, was. See also G1488, G1498, G1511, G1527, G2258,
 G2071, G2070, G2075, G2076, G2771, G2468, G5600.
g1510.r: The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb|

g1511.d:
εἶναι eînai, i'-nahee; present infinitive from G1510; to exist:—am, was. come, is, × lust
 after, × please well, there is, to be, was.
g1511.r: Present infinitive from εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g1512.d: εἴ περ eí per, i per; from G1487 and G4007; if perhaps:—if so be (that), seeing, though.
g1512.r: From εἰ (G1487) and περ (G4007)|English: if, whether, that, not tr, misc

g1514.d:
εἰρηνεύω eirēneúō, i-rane-yoo'-o; from G1515; to be (act) peaceful:—be at (have, live in) peace, live
 peaceably.
g1514.r: From εἰρήνη (G1515)|English: peace, one, rest, quietness

g1515.d:
εἰρήνη eirḗnē, i-ray'-nay; probably from a primary verb εἴρω eírō (to join); peace (literally or
 figuratively); by implication, prosperity:—one, peace, quietness,
 rest, + set at one again.
g1515.r: Probably from a primary verb eiro (to join)|

g1516.d: εἰρηνικός eirēnikós, i-ray-nee-kos'; from G1515; pacific; by implication, salutary:—peaceable.
g1516.r: From εἰρήνη (G1515)|English: peace, one, rest, quietness

g1517.d:
εἰρηνοποιέω eirēnopoiéō, i-ray-nop-oy-eh'-o; from G1518; to be a peace-maker, i.e. (figuratively) to
 harmonize:—make peace.

g1518.d:
εἰρηνοποιός eirēnopoiós, i-ray-nop-oy-os'; from G1515 and G4160; pacificatory, i.e. (subjectively)
 peaceable:—peacemaker.
g1518.r: From εἰρήνη (G1515) and ποιέω (G4160)|English: peace, one, rest, quietness

g1519.d:
εἰς eis, ice; a primary preposition; to or into (indicating the point reached or
 entered), of place, time, or (figuratively) purpose (result, etc.);
 also in adverbial phrases:—(abundant-)ly, against, among, as, at,
 (back-)ward, before, by, concerning, + continual, + far more
 exceeding, for (intent, purpose), fore,
 + forth, in (among, at, unto, -so much that, -to), to the
 intent that, + of one mind, + never, of, (up-)on, + perish, + set at
 one again, (so) that, therefore(-unto), throughout, til, to (be, the
 end, -ward), (here-)until(-to), …ward, (where-)fore, with.

g152.d:
αἰσχύνη aischýnē, ahee-skhoo'-nay; from G153; shame or disgrace (abstractly or concretely):—dishonesty,
 shame.

g1520.d:
εἷς heîs, hice; a primary numeral; one:—a(-n, -ny,
 certain), + abundantly, man, one (another), only, other, some. See
 also G1527, G3367, G3391, G3762.

g1521.d:
εἰσάγω eiságō, ice-ag'-o; from G1519 and G71; to introduce (literally or figuratively):—bring
 in(-to), (+ was to) lead into.
g1521.r: From εἰς (G1519) and ἄγω (G71)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1522.d: εἰσακούω eisakoúō, ice-ak-oo'-o; from G1519 and G191; to listen to:—hear.
g1522.r: From εἰς (G1519) and ἀκούω (G191)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1523.d: εἰσδέχομαι eisdéchomai, ice-dekh'-om-ahee; from G1519 and G1209; to take into one's favor:—receive.
g1523.r: From εἰς (G1519) and δέχομαι (G1209)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1524.d: εἴσειμι eíseimi, ice'-i-mee; from G1519 and εἶμι eîmi (to go); to enter:—enter (go) into.
g1524.r: From εἰς (G1519) and eimi (to go)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1525.d:
εἰσέρχομαι eisérchomai, ice-er'-khom-ahee; from G1519 and G2064; to enter (literally or figuratively):—X arise,
 come (in, into), enter in(-to), go in (through).
g1525.r: From εἰς (G1519) and ἔρχομαι (G2064)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1526.d:
εἰσί eisí, i-see'; 3rd person plural present indicative of G1510; they are:—agree, are,
 be, dure, × is, were.
g1526.r: Third person plural present indicative of εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g1528.d: εἰσκαλέω eiskaléō, ice-kal-eh'-o; from G1519 and G2564; to invite in:—call in.
g1528.r: From εἰς (G1519) and καλέω (G2564)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1529.d:
εἴσοδος eísodos, ice'-od-os; from G1519 and G3598; an entrance (literally or figuratively):—coming,
 enter(-ing) in (to).
g1529.r: From εἰς (G1519) and ὁδός (G3598)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g153.d:
αἰσχύνομαι aischýnomai, ahee-skhoo'-nom-ahee; from αἶσχος aîschos (disfigurement, i.e. disgrace); to feel shame (for
 oneself):—be ashamed.

g1530.d: †εἰσπηδάω eispēdáō, ice-pay-dah'-o; from G1519 and πηδάω pēdáō (to leap); to rush in:—run (spring) in.
g1530.r: From εἰς (G1519) and pedao (to leap)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1531.d:
εἰσπορεύομαι eisporeúomai, ice-por-yoo'-om-ahee; from G1519 and G4198; to enter (literally or figuratively):—come
 (enter) in, go into.
g1531.r: From εἰς (G1519) and πορεύω (G4198)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1532.d: εἰστρέχω eistréchō, ice-trekh'-o; from G1519 and G5143; to hasten inward:—run in.
g1532.r: From εἰς (G1519) and τρέχω (G5143)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1533.d:
εἰσφέρω eisphérō, ice-fer'-o; from G1519 and G5342; to carry inward (literally or
 figuratively):—bring (in), lead into.
g1533.r: From εἰς (G1519) and φέρω (G5342)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g1534.d:
†εἶτα eîta, i'-tah; of uncertain affinity; a particle of succession (in time or logical
 enumeration), then, moreover:—after that(-ward), furthermore, then. 
 See also G1899.

g1535.d: εἴτε eíte, i'-teh; from G1487 and G5037; if too:—if, or, whether.
g1535.r: From εἰ (G1487) and τέ (G5037)|English: if, whether, that, not tr, misc

g1536.d:
†εἴ τις eí tis, i tis; from G1487 and G5100; if any:—he that, if a(-ny) man('s thing, from
 any, ought), whether any, whosoever.
g1536.r: From εἰ (G1487) and τις (G5100)|English: if, whether, that, not tr, misc

g1537.d:
ἐκ ek, ek; a primary preposition denoting origin (the point whence action or
 motion proceeds), from, out (of place, time, or cause; literal or
 figurative; direct or remote):—after, among, × are, at,
 betwixt(-yond), by (the means of), exceedingly, (+ abundantly above),
 for(- th), from (among, forth, up), + grudgingly, + heartily, X
 heavenly, × hereby, + very highly, in, …ly, (because, by reason) of,
 off (from), on, out among (from, of), over, since, × thenceforth,
 through,
 × unto, × vehemently, with(-out).
g1537.r: A primary preposition denoting origin (the point whence action or motion proceeds), from, out (of place, time, or cause; literal or figurative|

g1538.d:
ἕκαστος hékastos, hek'-as-tos; as if a superlative of ἕκας hékas (afar); each or every:—any, both, each
 (one), every (man, one, woman), particularly.
g1538.r: As if a superlative of hekas (afar)|

g1539.d: ἑκάστοτε hekástote, hek-as'-tot-eh; as if from G1538 and G5119; at every time:—always.
g1539.r: As if from ἕκαστος (G1538) and τότε (G5119)|English: every man, every one, every, misc

g154.d:
αἰτέω aitéō, ahee-teh'-o; of uncertain derivation; to ask (in genitive case):—ask, beg, call
 for, crave, desire, require. Compare G4441.

g1540.d: ἑκατόν hekatón, hek-at-on'; of uncertain affinity; a hundred:—hundred.

g1541.d: †ἑκατονταέτης hekatontaétēs, hek-at-on-tah-et'-ace; from G1540 and G2094; centenarian:—hundred years old.
g1541.r: From ἑκατόν (G1540) and ἔτος (G2094)|English: hundred, hundredfold

g1542.d:

g1624.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and the base of τροπή (G5157)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1625.d:
ἐκτρέφω ektréphō, ek-tref'-o; from G1537 and G5142; to rear up to maturity, i.e. (genitive case) to
 cherish or train:—bring up, nourish.
g1625.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and τρέφω (G5142)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1626.d:
ἔκτρωμα éktrōma, ek'-tro-mah; from a comparative of G1537 and τιτρώσκω titrṓskō (to wound); a miscarriage
 (abortion), i.e. (by analogy) untimely birth:—born out of due time.
g1626.r: From a comparative of ἐκ (G1537) and titrosko (to wound)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1627.d:
ἐκφέρω ekphérō, ek-fer'-o; from G1537 and G5342; to bear out (literally or figuratively):—bear,
 bring forth, carry forth (out).
g1627.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and φέρω (G5342)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1628.d: ἐκφεύγω ekpheúgō, ek-fyoo'-go; from G1537 and G5343; to flee out:—escape, flee.
g1628.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and φεύγω (G5343)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1629.d: ἐκφοβέω ekphobéō, ek-fob-eh'-o; from G1537 and G5399; to frighten utterly:—terrify.
g1629.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and φοβέω (G5399)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g163.d: αἰχμαλωτίζω aichmalōtízō, aheekh-mal-o-tid'-zo; from G164; to make captive:—lead away captive, bring into captivity.

g1630.d:
ἔκφοβος ékphobos, ek'-fob-os; from G1537 and G5401; frightened out of one's wits:—sore afraid,
 exceedingly fear.
g1630.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and φόβος (G5401)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1631.d: ἐκφύω ekphýō, ek-foo'-o; from G1537 and G5453; to sprout up:—put forth.
g1631.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and φύω (G5453)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1632.d:
†ἐκχέω ekchéō, ek-kheh'-o; from G1537 and χέω chéō (to pour); to pour forth; figuratively, to
 bestow:—gush (pour) out, run greedily (out), shed (abroad, forth),
 spill.
g1632.r: From ἐκ (G1537)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1633.d: ἐκχωρέω ekchōréō, ek-kho-reh'-o; from G1537 and G5562; to depart:—depart out.
g1633.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and χωρέω (G5562)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1634.d: ἐκψύχω ekpsýchō, ek-psoo'-kho; from G1537 and G5594; to expire:—give (yield) up the ghost.
g1634.r: From ἐκ (G1537) and ψύχω (G5594)|English: of, from, out of, by, on, with, misc

g1635.d: ἑκών hekṓn, hek-own'; of uncertain affinity; voluntary:—willingly.

g1636.d:
ἐλαία elaía, el-ah'-yah; feminine of a presumed derivative from an obsolete primary; an olive
 (the tree or the fruit):—olive (berry, tree).
g1636.r: From a presumed derivative from an obsolete primary|

g1637.d: ἔλαιον élaion, el'-ah-yon; neuter of the same as G1636; olive oil:—oil.
g1637.r: From the same as ἐλαία (G1636)|English: olives, olive tree, olive berries

g1638.d:
ἐλαιών elaiṓn, el-ah-yone'; from G1636; an olive-orchard, i.e. (specially) the Mount of
 Olives:—Olivet.
g1638.r: From ἐλαία (G1636)|English: olives, olive tree, olive berries

g1639.d: Ἐλαμίτης Elamítēs, el-am-ee'-tace; of Hebrew origin (H5867); an Elamite or Persian:—Elamite.

g164.d:
†αἰχμάλωτος aichmálōtos, aheekh-mal-o-tos'; from αἰχμή aichmḗ (a spear) and a derivative of the same as G259; properly, a
 prisoner of war, i.e. (genitive case) a captive:—captive.
g164.r: From aichme (a spear) and a derivative of the same as ἅλωσις (G259)|English: to be taken

g1640.d:
ἐλάσσων elássōn, el-as'-sone; comparative of the same as G1646; smaller (in size, quantity, age or
 quality):—less, under, worse, younger.
g1640.r: Comparative of the same as ἐλάχιστος (G1646)|English: least, very small, smallest, very little

g1641.d: ἐλαττονέω elattonéō, el-at-ton-eh-o; from G1640; to diminish, i.e. fall short:—have lack.
g1641.r: From ἐλάσσων (G1640)|English: worse, younger, under, less

g1642.d: ἐλαττόω elattóō, el-at-to'-o; from G1640; to lessen (in rank or influence):—decrease, make lower.
g1642.r: From ἐλάσσων (G1640)|English: worse, younger, under, less

g1643.d:
ἐλαύνω elaúnō, el-ow'-no; a prolonged form of a primary verb (obsolete except in certain tenses
 as an alternative of this) of uncertain affinity; to push (as wind,
 oars or dæmonical power):—carry, drive, row.
g1643.r: A prolonged form of a primary verb (obsolete except in certain tenses as an altern. of this) of uncertain affin|

g1644.d: ἐλαφρία elaphría, el-af-ree'-ah; from G1645; levity (figuratively), i.e. fickleness:—lightness.

g1645.d: ἐλαφρός elaphrós, el-af-ros'; probably akin to G1643 and the base of G1640; light, i.e. easy:—light.
g1645.r: Probably akin to ἐλαύνω (G1643) and the base of ἐλάσσων (G1640)|English: row, drive, carry

g1646.d:
ἐλάχιστος eláchistos, el-akh'-is-tos; superlative of ἔλαχυς élachys (short); used as equivalent to G3398; least (in
 size, amount, dignity, etc.):—least, very little (small), smallest.
g1646.r: Superlative of elachus (short); used as equivalent to μικρός (G3398)|English: little, least, small, less

g1648.d: Ἐλεάζαρ Eleázar, el-eh-ad'-zar; of Hebrew origin (H499); Eleazar, an Israelite:—Eleazar.

g1649.d: ἔλεγξις élenxis, el'-eng-xis; from G1651; refutation, i.e. reproof:—rebuke.
g1649.r: From ἐλέγχω (G1651)|English: reprove, rebuke, convince, tell (one's) fault, convict

g165.d:
αἰών aiṓn, ahee-ohn'; from the same as G104; properly, an age; by extension, perpetuity (also
 past); by implication, the world; specially (Jewish) a Messianic
 period (present or future):—age, course, eternal, (for) ever(-more),
 (n-)ever, (beginning of the , while the) world (began, without end). 
 Compare G5550.
g165.r: From the same as ἀεί (G104)|English: alway, always, ever

g1650.d: †ἔλεγχος élenchos, el'-eng-khos; from G1651; proof, conviction:—evidence, reproof.
g1650.r: From ἐλέγχω (G1651)|English: reprove, rebuke, convince, tell (one's) fault, convict

g1651.d:
ἐλέγχω elénchō, el-eng'-kho; of uncertain affinity; to confute, admonish:—convict, convince, tell
 a fault, rebuke, reprove.

g1652.d: ἐλεεινός eleeinós, el-eh-i-nos'; from G1656; pitiable:—miserable.

g1653.d:
†ἐλεέω eleéō, el-eh-eh'-o; from G1656; to compassionate (by word or deed, specially, by divine
 grace):—have compassion (pity on), have (obtain, receive, shew) mercy
 (on).

g1654.d:
ἐλεημοσύνη eleēmosýnē, el-eh-ay-mos-oo'-nay; from G1656; compassionateness, i.e. (as exercised towards the poor)
 beneficence, or (concretely) a benefaction:—alms(-deeds).

g1655.d: ἐλεήμων eleḗmōn, el-eh-ay'-mone; from G1653; compassionate (actively):—merciful.
g1655.r: From ἐλεέω (G1653)|English: have mercy on, obtain mercy, show mercy, have compassion, have compassion on, have pity on, have mercy, have mercy upon, receive mercy

g1656.d:
ἔλεος éleos, el'-eh-os; of uncertain affinity; compassion (human or divine, especially
 active):—(+ tender) mercy.

g1657.d:
ἐλευθερία eleuthería, el-yoo-ther-ee'-ah; from G1658; freedom (legitimate or licentious, chiefly moral or
 ceremonial):—liberty.
g1657.r: From ἐλεύθερος (G1658)|English: free, free woman, at liberty, free man

g1658.d:
ἐλεύθερος eleútheros, el-yoo'-ther-os; probably from the alternate of G2064; unrestrained (to go at pleasure),
 i.e. (as a citizen) not a slave (whether freeborn or manumitted), or
 (genitive case) exempt (from obligation or liability):—free (man,
 woman), at liberty.
g1658.r: Probably from the alternate of ἔρχομαι (G2064)|English: come, go, misc

g1659.d:
ἐλευθερόω eleutheróō, el-yoo-ther-o'-o; from G1658; to liberate, i.e. (figuratively) to exempt (from moral,
 ceremonial or mortal liability):—deliver, make free.
g1659.r: From ἐλεύθερος (G1658)|English: free, free woman, at liberty, free man

g166.d:
αἰώνιος aiṓnios, ahee-o'-nee-os; from G165; perpetual (also used of past time, or past and future as
 well):—eternal, for ever, everlasting, world (began).
g166.r: From αἰών (G165)|English: ever, world, never, evermore, age, eternal, misc

g1660.d: ἔλευσις éleusis, el'-yoo-sis; from the alternate of G2064; an advent:—coming.
g1660.r: From the alternate of ἔρχομαι (G2064)|English: come, go, misc

g1661.d:
ἐλεφάντινος elephántinos, el-ef-an'-tee-nos; from ἔλεφας élephas (an "elephant"); elephantine, i.e. (by implication)
 composed of ivory:—of ivory.

g1662.d: †Ἐλιακείμ Eliakeím, el-ee-ak-ime'; of Hebrew origin (H471); Eliakim, an Israelite:—Eliakim.

g1663.d: Ἐλιέζερ Eliézer, el-ee-ed'-zer; of Hebrew origin (H461); Eliezer, an Israelite:—Eliezer.

g1664.d:
Ἐλιούδ Elioúd, el-ee-ood'; of Hebrew origin (H410 and H1935); God of majesty; Eliud, an
 Israelite:—Eliud.
g1664.r: Of Hebrew origin אֵל (H410) and הוֹד (H1935)|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

g1665.d: Ἐλισάβετ Elisábet, el-ee-sab'-et; of Hebrew origin (H472); Elisabet, an Israelitess:—Elisabeth.

g1666.d: †Ἐλισσαῖος Elissaîos, el-is-sah'-yos; of Hebrew origin (H477); Elissæus, an Israelite:—Elissæus.

g1667.d: ἑλίσσω helíssō, hel-is'-so; a form of G1507; to coil or wrap:—fold up.
g1667.r: A form of εἱλίσσω (G1507)|English: roll together

g1668.d: ἕλκος hélkos, hel'-kos; probably from G1670; an ulcer (as if drawn together):—sore.

g1669.d:
ἑλκόω helkóō, hel-ko'-o; from G1668; to cause to ulcerate, i.e. (passively) be ulcerous:—full
 of sores.

g167.d: ἀκαθαρσία akatharsía, ak-ath-ar-see'-ah; from G169; impurity (the quality), physically or morally:—uncleanness.

g1670.d:
†ἑλκύω helkýō, hel-koo'-o; probably akin to G138; to drag (literally or
 figuratively):—draw. Compare G1667.

g1671.d:
Ἑλλάς Hellás, hel-las'; of uncertain affinity; Hellas (or Greece), a country of
 Europe:—Greece.

g1672.d:
Ἕλλην Héllēn, hel'-lane; from G1671; a Hellen (Grecian) or inhabitant of Hellas; by extension a
 Greek-speaking person, especially a non-Jew:—Gentile, Greek.

g1673.d: Ἑλληνικός Hellēnikós, hel-lay-nee-kos'; from G1672; Hellenic, i.e. Grecian (in language):—Greek.

g1674.d: Ἑλληνίς Hellēnís, hel-lay-nis'; feminine of G1672; a Grecian (i.e. non-Jewish) woman:—Greek.

g1675.d:
Ἑλληνιστής Hellēnistḗs, hel-lay-nis-tace'; from a derivative of G1672; a Hellenist or Greek-speaking
 Jew:—Grecian.
g1675.r: From a derivative of Ἕλλην (G1672)|English: Greek, Gentile

g1676.d:
Ἑλληνιστί Hellēnistí, hel-lay-nis-tee'; adverb from the same as G1675; Hellenistically, i.e. in the Grecian
 language:—Greek.
g1676.r: From the same as Ἑλληνιστής (G1675)|English: Grecians

g1677.d:
†ἐλλογέω ellogéō, el-log-eh'-o; from G1722 and G3056 (in the sense of account); to reckon in, i.e.
 attribute:—impute, put on account.
g1677.r: From ἐν (G1722) and λόγος (G3056) (in the sense of account)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1678.d: †Ἐλμωδάμ Elmōdám, el-mo-dam'; of Hebrew origin (perhaps for H486); Elmodam, an Israelite:—Elmodam.
g1678.r: Of Hebrew origin, perhaps for אַלְמוֹדָד (H486)|English: Almodad

g1679.d: ἐλπίζω elpízō, el-pid'-zo; from G1680; to expect or confide:—(have, thing) hope(-d) (for), trust.

g1680.d:
ἐλπίς elpís, el-pece'; from a primary ἔλπω élpō (to anticipate, usually with pleasure); 
 expectation (abstractly or concretely) or confidence:—faith, hope.
g1680.r: From a primary elpo (to anticipate, usually with pleasure)|

g1681.d: Ἐλύμας Elýmas, el-oo'-mas; of foreign origin; Elymas, a wizard:—Elymas.

g1682.d: †ἐλοΐ eloḯ, el-o-ee'; of Chaldean origin (H426 with pronominal suffix) my God:—Eloi.
g1682.r: Of Aramaic origin, אֱלָהּ (H426) with pronominal suff.|English: God, god

g1683.d:
ἐμαυτοῦ emautoû, em-ow-too'; genitive case compound of G1700 and G846; of myself

 so likewise the dative case
    ἐμαυτῷ emautōi  em-ow-to',

 and accusative case
    ἐμαυτόν emautón  em-ow-ton'

:—me, mine own (self), myself.
g1683.r: Genitive case compound of ἐμοῦ (G1700) and αὐτός (G846)|English: me, my, mine

g1684.d:
ἐμβαίνω embaínō, em-ba'-hee-no; from G1722 and the base of G939; to walk on, i.e. embark (aboard a
 vessel), reach (a pool):—come (get) into, enter (into), go (up) into,
 step in, take ship.
g1684.r: From ἐν (G1722) and the base of βάσις (G939)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1685.d:
ἐμβάλλω embállō, em-bal'-lo; from G1722 and G906; to throw on, i.e. (figuratively) subject to
 (eternal punishment):—cast into.
g1685.r: From ἐν (G1722) and βάλλω (G906)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1686.d:
ἐμβάπτω embáptō, em-bap'-to; from G1722 and G911; to whelm on, i.e. wet (a part of the person, etc.)
 by contact with a fluid:—dip.
g1686.r: From ἐν (G1722) and βάπτω (G911)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1687.d:
ἐμβατεύω embateúō, em-bat-yoo'-o; from G1722 and a presumed derivative of the base of G939; equivalent to
 G1684; to intrude on (figuratively):—intrude into.
g1687.r: From ἐν (G1722) and a presumed derivative of the base of βάσις (G939)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1688.d:
ἐμβιβάζω embibázō, em-bib-ad'-zo; from G1722 and βιβάζω bibázō (to mount; causative of G1684); to place on, i.e.
 transfer (aboard a vessel):—put in.
g1688.r: From ἐν (G1722) and bibazo (to mount, causative of ἐμβαίνω (G1684))|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1689.d:
ἐμβλέπω emblépō, em-blep'-o; from G1722 and G991; to look on, i.e. (relatively) to observe fixedly,
 or (absolutely) to discern clearly:—behold, gaze up, look upon,
 (could) see.
g1689.r: From ἐν (G1722) and βλέπω (G991)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g169.d:
ἀκάθαρτος akáthartos, ak-ath'-ar-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of G2508
 (meaning cleansed); impure (ceremonially, morally (lewd) or specially,
 (demonic)):—foul, unclean.
g169.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of καθαίρω (G2508) (meaning cleansed)|English: Alpha

g1690.d:
ἐμβριμάομαι embrimáomai, em-brim-ah'-om-ahee; from G1722 and βριμάομαι brimáomai (to snort with anger); to have indignation on,
 i.e. (transitively) to blame, (intransitively) to sigh with chagrin,
 (specially) to sternly enjoin:—straitly charge, groan, murmur
 against.
g1690.r: From ἐν (G1722) and brimaomai (to snort with anger)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1692.d: ἐμέω eméō, em-eh'-o; of uncertain affinity; to vomit:—(will) spue.

g1693.d: ἐμμαίνομαι emmaínomai, em-mah'-ee-nom-ahee; from G1722 and G3105; to rave on, i.e. rage at:—be mad against.
g1693.r: From ἐν (G1722) and μαίνομαι (G3105)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1694.d:
Ἐμμανουήλ Emmanouḗl, em-man-oo-ale'; of Hebrew origin (H6005); God with us; Emmanuel, a name of
 Christ:—Emmanuel.

g1695.d:
Ἐμμαούς Emmaoús, em-mah-ooce'; probably of Hebrew origin (compare H3222); Emmaus, a place in
 Palestine:—Emmaus.
g1695.r: Probably of Hebrew origin, cf יֵמִים (H3222)|English: mules

g1696.d:
ἐμμένω emménō, em-men'-o; from G1722 and G3306; to stay in the same place, i.e. (figuratively)
 persevere:—continue.
g1696.r: From ἐν (G1722) and μένω (G3306)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1697.d: †Ἐμμόρ Emmór, em-mor'; of Hebrew origin (H2544); Emmor (i.e. Chamor), a Canaanite:—Emmor.

g1698.d: ἐμοί emoí, em-oy'; a prolonged form of G3427; to me:—I, me, mine, my.
g1698.r: A prolonged form of μοι (G3427)|English: me, my, I, mine

g1699.d:
ἐμός emós, em-os'; from the oblique cases of G1473 (G1698, G1700, G1691); my:—of me, mine
 (own), my.
g1699.r: From the oblique cases of ἐγώ (G1473) (1698, ἐμοῦ (G1700), ἐμέ (G1691))|English: I, my, me, not tr

g17.d: ἀγαθοποιός agathopoiós, ag-ath-op-oy-os'; from G18 and G4160; a well-doer, i.e. virtuous:—them that do well.
g17.r: From ἀγαθός (G18) and ποιέω (G4160)|English: good, good thing, that which is good, the thing which is good, well, benefit

g170.d:
ἀκαιρέομαι akairéomai, ak-ahee-reh'-om-ahee; from a compound of G1 (as a negative particle) and G2540 (meaning
 unseasonable); to be inopportune (for oneself), i.e. to fail of a
 proper occasion:—lack opportunity.
g170.r: From a compound of ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and καιρός (G2540) (meaning unseasonable)|English: Alpha

g1700.d: ἐμοῦ emoû, em-oo'; a prolonged form of G3449; of me:—me, mine, my.
g1700.r: A prolonged form of ἐγώ (G1473)|English: I, my, me, not tr

g1702.d: ἐμπαίζω empaízō, emp-aheed'-zo; from G1722 and G3815; to jeer at, i.e. deride:—mock.
g1702.r: From ἐν (G1722) and παίζω (G3815)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1703.d:
ἐμπαίκτης empaíktēs, emp-aheek-tace'; from G1702; a derider, i.e. (by implication) a false teacher:—mocker,
 scoffer.

g1704.d:
ἐμπεριπατέω emperipatéō, em-per-ee-pat-eh'-o; from G1722 and G4043; to perambulate on a place, i.e. (figuratively) to
 be occupied among persons:—walk in.
g1704.r: From ἐν (G1722) and περιπατέω (G4043)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1705.d:
†ἐμπίπλημι empíplēmi, em-pip'-lay-mee; from G1722 and the base of G4118; to fill in (up), i.e. (by implication)
 to satisfy (literally or figuratively):—fill.
g1705.r: From ἐν (G1722) and the base of πλεῖστος (G4118)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1706.d:
ἐμπίπτω empíptō, em-pip'-to; from G1722 and G4098; to fall on, i.e. (literally) to be entrapped by,
 or (figuratively) be overwhelmed with:—fall among (into).
g1706.r: From ἐν (G1722) and πίπτω (G4098)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1707.d:
ἐμπλέκω emplékō, em-plek'-o; from G1722 and G4120; to entwine, i.e. (figuratively) involve
 with:—entangle (in, self with).
g1707.r: From ἐν (G1722) and πλέκω (G4120)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1708.d: ἐμπλοκή emplokḗ, em-plok-ay'; from G1707; elaborate braiding of the hair:—plaiting.
g1708.r: From ἐμπλέκω (G1707)|English: entangle (one's) self with, entangle therein

g1709.d:
ἐμπνέω empnéō, emp-neh'-o; from G1722 and G4154; to inhale, i.e. (figuratively) to be animated by
 (bent upon):—breathe.
g1709.r: From ἐν (G1722) and πνέω (G4154)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g171.d: ἀκαίρως akaírōs, ak-ah'-ee-roce; adverb from the same as G170; inopportunely:—out of season.
g171.r: From the same as ἀκαιρέομαι (G170)|English: lack of opportunity

g1710.d:
ἐμπορεύομαι emporeúomai, em-por-yoo'-om-ahee; from G1722 and G4198; to travel in (a country as a pedlar), i.e. (by
 implication) to trade:—buy and sell, make merchandise.
g1710.r: From ἐν (G1722) and πορεύω (G4198)|English: in, by, with, among, at, on, through, misc

g1711.d: ἐμπορία emporía, em-por-ee'-ah; feminine from G1713; traffic:—merchandise.

g1712.d: ἐμπόριον empórion, em-por'-ee-on; neuter from G1713; a mart ("emporium"):—merchandise.

g1722.d:
ἐν en, en; a primary preposition denoting (fixed) position (in place, time or

 constructively), i.e. a relation of rest (intermediate between G1519
 and G1537); "in," at, (up-)on, by, etc.:—about, after, against, +
 almost, × altogether, among, × as, at, before, between, (here-)by (+
 all means), for (… sake of), + give self wholly to, (here-)in(-to,
 -wardly), × mightily, (because) of, (up-)on, (open-)ly, × outwardly,
 one, × quickly,
 × shortly, (speedi-)ly, × that, × there(-in, -on),
 through(-out), (un-)to(-ward), under, when, where(-with), while,
 with(-in). Often used in compounds, with substantially the same
 import; rarely with verbs of motion, and then not to indicate
 direction, except (elliptically) by a separate (and different)
 preposition.
g1722.r: A primary preposition denoting (fixed) position (in place, time or state), and (by implication) instrumentality (medially or constructively), i.e. a relation of rest (intermediate between εἰς (G1519) and ἐκ (G1537))|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g2019.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and φωνέω (G5455)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g202.d:
ἀκροατής akroatḗs, ak-ro-at-ace'; from ἀκροάομαι akroáomai (to listen; apparently an intensive of G191); a hearer
 (merely):—hearer.
g202.r: From akroaomai (to listen, apparently an intens. of ἀκούω (G191))|English: hear, hearken, give audience, hearer, misc

g2020.d: ἐπιφώσκω epiphṓskō, ep-ee-foce'-ko; a form of G2017; to begin to grow light:—begin to dawn, × draw on.
g2020.r: A form of ἐπιφαύσκω (G2017)|English: give light

g2021.d:
ἐπιχειρέω epicheiréō, ep-ee-khi-reh'-o; from G1909 and G5495; to put the hand upon, i.e. undertake:—go about,
 take in hand (upon).
g2021.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and χείρ (G5495)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2022.d: ἐπιχέω epichéō, ep-ee-kheh'-o; from G1909 and χέω chéō (to pour);  --to pour upon:—pour in.
g2022.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and cheo (to pour)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2023.d:
ἐπιχορηγέω epichorēgéō, ep-ee-khor-ayg-eh'-o; from G1909 and G5524; to furnish besides, i.e. fully supply,
 (figuratively) aid or contribute:—add, minister (nourishment, unto).
g2023.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and χορηγέω (G5524)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2024.d: ἐπιχορηγία epichorēgía, ep-ee-khor-ayg-ee'-ah; from G2023; contribution:—supply.
g2024.r: From ἐπιχορηγέω (G2023)|English: minister, minister nourishment, add, minister unto

g2025.d: ἐπιχρίω epichríō, ep-ee-khree'-o; from G1909 and G5548; to smear over:—anoint.
g2025.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and χρίω (G5548)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2026.d:
ἐποικοδομέω epoikodoméō, ep-oy-kod-om-eh'-o; from G1909 and G3618; to build upon, i.e. (figuratively) to rear
 up:—build thereon (thereupon, on, upon).
g2026.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and οἰκοδομέω (G3618)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2027.d:
†ἐποκέλλω epokéllō, ep-ok-el'-lo; from G1909 and ὀκέλλω okéllō (to urge); to drive upon the shore, i.e. to beach
 a vessel:—run aground.
g2027.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and okello (to urge)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2028.d: ἐπονομάζω eponomázō, ep-on-om-ad'-zo; from G1909 and G3687; to name further, i.e. denominate:—call.
g2028.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and ὀνομάζω (G3687)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2029.d: ἐποπτεύω epopteúō, ep-opt-yoo'-o; from G1909 and a derivative of G3700; to inspect, i.e. watch:—behold.
g2029.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and a derivative of ὀπτάνομαι (G3700)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g203.d:
ἀκροβυστία akrobystía, ak-rob-oos-tee'-ah; from G206 and probably a modified form of πόσθη pósthē (the penis or male
 sexual organ); the prepuce; by implication, an uncircumcised (i.e.
 gentile, figuratively, unregenerate) state or person:—not
 circumcised, uncircumcised (with G2192), uncircumcision.
g203.r: From ἄκρον (G206) and probably a modified form of posthe (the penis or male sexual organ)|English: uttermost part, one end, other, tip, top

g2030.d:
ἐπόπτης epóptēs, ep-op'-tace; from G1909 and a presumed derivative of G3700; a
 looker-on:—eye-witness.
g2030.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and a presumed derivative of ὀπτάνομαι (G3700)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2031.d: ἔπος épos, ep'-os; from G2036; a word:—X say.
g2031.r: From εἶπον (G2036)|English: say, speak, tell, command, bid, misc

g2032.d: ἐπουράνιος epouránios, ep-oo-ran'-ee-os; from G1909 and G3772; above the sky:—celestial, (in) heaven(-ly), high.
g2032.r: From ἐπί (G1909) and οὐρανός (G3772)|English: on, in, upon, unto, to, misc

g2033.d: ἑπτά heptá, hep-tah'; a primary number; seven:—seven.

g2034.d: ἑπτάκις heptákis, hep-tak-is'; adverb from G2033; seven times:—seven times.

g2035.d: ἑπτακισχίλιοι heptakischílioi, hep-tak-is-khil'-ee-oy; from G2034 and G5507; seven times a thousand:—seven thousand.
g2035.r: From ἑπτάκις (G2034) and χίλιοι (G5507)|English: seven times

g2036.d:
ἔπω épō, ep'-o; a primary verb (used only in the definite past tense, the others being
 borrowed from G2046, G4483, and G5346); to speak or say (by word or
 writing):—answer, bid, bring word, call, command, grant, say (on),
 speak, tell. Compare G3004.
g2036.r: A primary verb (used only in the definite past tense, the others being borrowed from εἶπον (G2046), ῥέω (G4483), and φημί (G5346))|English: say, speak, tell, speak of, call

g2037.d: Ἔραστος Érastos, er'-as-tos; from ἐράω eráō (to love); beloved; Erastus, a Christian:—Erastus.

g2038.d:
ἐργάζομαι ergázomai, er-gad'-zom-ahee; middle voice from G2041; to toil (as a task, occupation, etc.), (by
 implication) effect, be engaged in or with, etc.:—commit, do, labor
 for, minister about, trade (by), work.
g2038.r: Middle voice from ἔργον (G2041)|English: work, deed, doing, labour

g2039.d:
ἐργασία ergasía, er-gas-ee'-ah; from G2040; occupation; by implication, profit, pains:—craft,
 diligence, gain, work.

g204.d: ἀκρογωνιαῖος akrogōniaîos, ak-rog-o-nee-ah'-yos; from G206 and G1137; belonging to the extreme corner:—chief corner.
g204.r: From ἄκρον (G206) and γωνία (G1137)|English: uttermost part, one end, other, tip, top

g2040.d: ἐργάτης ergátēs, er-gat'-ace; from G2041; a toiler; figuratively, a teacher:—labourer, worker(-men).
g2040.r: From ἔργον (G2041)|English: work, deed, doing, labour

g2041.d:
ἔργον érgon, er'-gon; from a primary (but obsolete) ἔργω érgō (to work); toil (as an effort or
 occupation); by implication, an act:—deed, doing, labour, work.
g2041.r: From a primary (but obsolete) ergo (to work)|

g2042.d:
ἐρεθίζω erethízō, er-eth-id'-zo; from a presumed prolonged form of G2054; to stimulate (especially to
 anger):—provoke.
g2042.r: From a presumed prolonged form of ἔρις (G2054)|English: strife, debate, contention, variance

g2043.d:
ἐρείδω ereídō, er-i'-do; of obscure affinity; to prop, i.e. (reflexively) get fast:—stick
 fast.

g2044.d:
ἐρεύγομαι ereúgomai, er-yoog'-om-ahee; of uncertain affinity; to belch, i.e. (figuratively) to speak
 out:—utter.

g2047.d: ἐρημία erēmía, er-ay-mee'-ah; from G2048; solitude (concretely):—desert, wilderness.
g2047.r: From ἔρημος (G2048)|English: wilderness, desert, desolate, solitary

g2048.d:
ἔρημος érēmos, er'-ay-mos; of uncertain affinity; lonesome, i.e. (by implication) waste (usually
 as a noun, G5561 being implied):—desert, desolate, solitary,
 wilderness.

g2049.d:
ἐρημόω erēmóō, er-ay-mo'-o; from G2048; to lay waste (literally or figuratively):—(bring to, make)
 desolate(-ion), come to nought.
g2049.r: From ἔρημος (G2048)|English: wilderness, desert, desolate, solitary

g205.d:
ἀκροθίνιον akrothínion, ak-roth-in'-ee-on; from G206 and θίς thís (a heap); properly (in the plural) the top of the
 heap, i.e. (by implication) best of the booty:—spoils.
g205.r: From ἄκρον (G206) and this (a heap)|English: uttermost part, one end, other, tip, top

g2050.d: ἐρήμωσις erḗmōsis, er-ay'-mo-sis; from G2049; despoliation:—desolation.
g2050.r: From ἐρημόω (G2049)|English: bring to desolation, desolate, come to nought, make desolate

g2051.d: ἐρίζω erízō, er-id'-zo; from G2054; to wrangle:—strive.
g2051.r: From ἔρις (G2054)|English: strife, debate, contention, variance

g2052.d:
ἐριθεία eritheía, er-ith-i'-ah; perhaps as the same as G2042; properly, intrigue, i.e. (by implication)
 faction:—contention(-ious), strife.
g2052.r: Perhaps as the same as ἐρεθίζω (G2042)|English: provoke

g2053.d: ἔριον érion, er'-ee-on; of obscure affinity; wool:—wool.

g2054.d:
ἔρις éris, er'-is; of uncertain affinity; a quarrel, i.e. (by implication)
 wrangling:—contention, debate, strife, variance.

g2055.d:
ἐρίφιον eríphion, er-if'-ee-on; from G2056; a kidling, i.e. (genitive case) goat (symbolically, wicked
 person):—goat.

g2056.d:
ἔριφος ériphos, er'-if-os; perhaps from the same as G2053 (through the idea of hairiness); a kid
 or (genitive case) goat:—goat, kid.
g2056.r: Perhaps from the same as ἔριον (G2053) (through the idea of hairiness)|English: wool

g2057.d: Ἑρμᾶς Hermâs, her-mas'; probably from G2060; Hermas, a Christian:—Hermas.
g2057.r: Probably from Ἑρμῆς (G2060)|English: Mercurius, Hermes a Christian

g2058.d: ἑρμηνεία hermēneía, her-may-ni'-ah; from the same as G2059; translation:—interpretation.
g2058.r: From the same as ἑρμηνεύω (G2059)|English: by interpretation, being interpreted

g2059.d:
ἑρμηνεύω hermēneúō, her-mayn-yoo'-o; from a presumed derivative of G2060 (as the god of language); to
 translate:—interpret.
g2059.r: From a presumed derivative of Ἑρμῆς (G2060) (as the god of language)|English: Mercurius, Hermes a Christian

g206.d:
ἄκρον ákron, ak'-ron; neuter of an adjective probably akin to the base of G188; the
 extremity:—one end… other, tip, top, uttermost participle
g206.r: Neuter of an adj. probably akin to the base of ἀκμήν (G188)|English: yet

g2060.d:
Ἑρμῆς Hermēs, her-mace'; perhaps from G2046; Hermes, the name of the messenger of the Greek
 deities; also of a Christian:—Hermes, Mercury.
g2060.r: Perhaps from εἶπον (G2046)|English: say, speak, tell, speak of, call

g2061.d:
Ἑρμογένης Hermogénēs, her-mog-en'-ace; from G2060 and G1096; born of Hermes; Hermogenes, an apostate
 Christian:—Hermogenes.
g2061.r: From Ἑρμῆς (G2060) and γίνομαι (G1096)|English: Mercurius, Hermes a Christian

g2062.d:
ἑρπετόν herpetón, her-pet-on'; neuter of a derivative of ἕρπω hérpō (to creep); a reptile, i.e. (by
 Hebraism (compare H7431)) a small animal:—creeping thing, serpent.
g2062.r: Neuter of a derivative of herpo (to creep)|

g2063.d: ἐρυθρός erythrós, er-oo-thros'; of uncertain affinity; red, i.e. (with G2281) the Red Sea:—red.

g2064.d:
ἔρχομαι érchomai, er'-khom-ahee; middle voice of a primary verb 

 (used only in the present and imperfect tenses, the others being 
 supplied by a kindred (middle voice)
    
    ἐλεύθομαι eleúthomai  el-yoo'-thom-ahee,  or (active)
    ἔλθω élthō  el'-tho,
    
 which do not otherwise occur); 

 to come or go (in a great variety of applications, literally and 
 figuratively):—accompany, appear, bring, come, enter, fall out, go,
 grow, × light, × next, pass, resort, be set.
g2064.r: Middle voice of a primary verb (used only in the present and imperfect tenses, the others being supplied by a kindred [middle voice] eleuthomai {el-yoo'-thom-ahee}, or [active] eltho {el'-tho}, which do not otherwise occur)|

g2065.d:
ἐρωτάω erōtáō, er-o-tah'-o; apparently from G2046 (compare G2045); to interrogate; by implication,
 to request:—ask, beseech, desire, intreat, pray. Compare G4441.
g2065.r: Apparently from εἶπον (G2046) cf ἐραυνάω (G2045)|English: say, speak, tell, speak of, call

g2066.d: ἐσθής esthḗs, es-thace'; from ἕννυμι hénnymi (to clothe); dress:—apparel, clothing, raiment, robe.

g2068.d:
†ἐσθίω esthíō, es-thee'-o; strengthened for a primary ἔδω édō (to eat); used only in certain tenses,
 the rest being supplied by G5315; to eat (usually literal):—devour,
 eat, live.
g2068.r: Strengthened for a primary edo (to eat); used only in certain tenses, the rest being supplied by φάγω (G5315)|English: eat, meat

g2069.d: Ἐσλί Eslí, es-lee'; of Hebrew origin (probably for H454); Esli, an Israelite:—Esli.
g2069.r: Of Hebrew origin, probably for אֶלְיְהוֹעֵינַי (H454)|English: Elioenai, Elihoenai

g207.d: Ἀκύλας Akýlas, ak-oo'-las; probably for Latin aquila (an eagle); Akulas, an Israelite:—Aquila.

g2070.d:
ἐσμέν esmén, es-men'; first person plural indicative of G1510; we are:—are, be, have our
 being, × have hope, + (the gospel) was (preached unto) us.
g2070.r: From εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g2071.d:
ἔσομαι ésomai, es'-om-ahee; future of G1510; will be:—shall (should) be (have), (shall) come (to
 pass), × may have, × fall, what would follow, × live long, × sojourn.
g2071.r: Future of εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g2072.d:
ἔσοπτρον ésoptron, es'-op-tron; from G1519 and a presumed derivative of G3700; a mirror (for looking
 into):—glass. Compare G2734.
g2072.r: From εἰς (G1519) and a presumed derivative of ὀπτάνομαι (G3700)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g2073.d:
ἑσπέρα hespéra, hes-per'-ah; feminine of an adjective hesperos (evening); the eve (G5610 being
 implied):—evening(-tide).

g2074.d: Ἐσρώμ Esrṓm, es-rome; of Hebrew origin (H2696); Esrom (i.e. Chetsron), an Israelite:—Esrom.

g2075.d:
ἐστέ esté, es-teh'; second person plural present indicative of G1510; ye are:—be, have
 been, belong.
g2075.r: Second person plural present indicative of εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g2076.d:
ἐστί estí, es-tee'; third person singular present indicative of G1510; he (she or it) is;
 also (with neuter plural) they are:—are, be(-long), call, X
 can(-not), come, consisteth, × dure for a while, + follow, × have,
 (that) is (to say), make, meaneth, × must needs, + profit, +
 remaineth, + wrestle.
g2076.r: Third person singular present indicative of εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g2077.r: Second person singular present imperative of εἰμί (G1510), estosan {es'-to-san} third person of the same|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g2078.r: A superlative probably from ἔχω (G2192) (in the sense of contiguity)|English: have, be, need, misc

g2079.d:
ἐσχάτως eschátōs, es-khat'-oce; adverb from G2078; finally, i.e. (with G2192) at the extremity of
 life:—point of death.
g2079.r: From ἔσχατος (G2078)|English: last, lowest, uttermost, last state, ends, latter end

g208.d:
ἀκυρόω akyróō, ak-oo-ro'-o; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G2964; to invalidate:—disannul,
 make of none effect.
g208.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and κυρόω (G2964)|English: Alpha

g2080.d:
ἔσω ésō, es'-o; from G1519; inside (as preposition or adjective):—(with-)in(-ner,
 -to, -ward).
g2080.r: From εἰς (G1519)|English: into, to, unto, for, in, on, toward, against, misc

g2081.d:
ἔσωθεν ésōthen, es'-o-then; from G2080; from inside; also used as equivalent to G2080
 (inside):—inward(-ly), (from) within, without.
g2081.r: From ἔσω (G2080)|English: within, in, into, inward, inner, not tr

g2082.d: ἐσώτερος esṓteros, es-o'-ter-os; comparative of G2080; interior:—inner, within.
g2082.r: Comparative of ἔσω (G2080)|English: within, in, into, inward, inner, not tr

g2083.d: ἑταῖρος hetaîros, het-ah'-ee-ros; from ἔτης étēs (a clansman); a comrade:—fellow, friend.

g2084.d:
ἑτερόγλωσσος heteróglōssos, het-er-og'-loce-sos; from G2087 and G1100; other- tongued, i.e. a foreigner:—man of other
 tongue.
g2084.r: From ἕτερος (G2087) and γλῶσσα (G1100)|English: another, other, other thing, some, next day, misc

g2085.d:
ἑτεροδιδασκαλέω heterodidaskaléō, het-er-od-id-as-kal-eh'-o; from G2087 and G1320; to instruct differently:—teach other
 doctrine(-wise).
g2085.r: From ἕτερος (G2087) and διδάσκαλος (G1320)|English: another, other, other thing, some, next day, misc

g2086.d:
ἑτεροζυγέω heterozygéō, het-er-od-zoog-eh'-o; from a compound of G2087 and G2218; to yoke up differently, i.e.
 (figuratively) to associate discordantly:—unequally yoke together
 with.
g2086.r: From a compound of ἕτερος (G2087) and ζυγός (G2218)|English: another, other, other thing, some, next day, misc

g2087.d:
ἕτερος héteros, het'-er-os; of uncertain affinity; (an-, the) other or different:—altered, else,
 next (day), one, (an-)other, some, strange.

g2088.d: ἑτέρως hetérōs, het-er'-oce; adverb from G2087; differently:—otherwise.
g2088.r: From ἕτερος (G2087)|English: another, other, other thing, some, next day, misc

g2089.d:
ἔτι éti, et'-ee; perhaps akin to G2094; "yet," still (of time or degree):—after that,
 also, ever, (any) further, (t-)henceforth (more), hereafter, (any)
 longer, (any) more(-one), now, still, yet.

g209.d:
ἀκωλύτως akōlýtōs, ak-o-loo'-toce; adverb from a compound of G1 (as a negative particle) and a derivative
 of G2967; in an unhindered manner, i.e. freely:—no man forbidding him.
g209.r: From a compound of ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of κωλύω (G2967)|English: Alpha

g2090.d: ἑτοιμάζω hetoimázō, het-oy-mad'-zo; from G2092; to prepare:—prepare, provide, make ready. Compare G2680.
g2090.r: From ἕτοιμος (G2092)|English: ready, prepared, readiness, make ready to (one's) hand

g2091.d: ἑτοιμασία hetoimasía, het-oy-mas-ee'-ah; from G2090; preparation:—preparation.
g2091.r: From ἑτοιμάζω (G2090)|English: prepare, make ready, provide

g2092.d:
ἕτοιμος hétoimos, het-oy'-mos; from an old noun ἐτεός eteós (fitness); adjusted, i.e. ready:—prepared,
 (made) ready(-iness, to our hand).

g2093.d: ἑτοίμως hetoímōs, het'-oy-moce; adverb from G2092; in readiness:—ready.
g2093.r: From ἕτοιμος (G2092)|English: ready, prepared, readiness, make ready to (one's) hand

g2094.d: ἔτος étos, et'-os; apparently a primary word; a year:—year.

g2095.d:
†εὖ eû, yoo; neuter of a primary εὖς eûs (good); (adverbially) well:—good, well
 (done).

g2096.d:
†Εὖα Eûa, yoo'-ah; of Hebrew origin (H2332); Eua (or Eva, i.e. Chavvah), the first
 woman:—Eve.

g2097.d:
εὐαγγελίζω euangelízō, yoo-ang-ghel-id'-zo; from G2095 and G32; to announce good news ("evangelize") especially the
 gospel:—declare, bring (declare, show) glad (good) tidings, preach
 (the gospel).
g2097.r: From εὖ (G2095) and ἄγγελος (G32)|English: well, well done, good

g2098.d: εὐαγγέλιον euangélion, yoo-ang-ghel'-ee-on; from the same as G2097; a good message, i.e. the gospel:—gospel.
g2098.r: From the same as εὐαγγελίζω (G2097)|English: preach, preach the Gospel, bring good tidings, show glad tidings, bring glad tidings, declare, declare glad tidings, misc

g2099.d: εὐαγγελιστής euangelistḗs, yoo-ang-ghel-is-tace'; from G2097; a preacher of the gospel:—evangelist.
g2099.r: From εὐαγγελίζω (G2097)|English: preach, preach the Gospel, bring good tidings, show glad tidings, bring glad tidings, declare, declare glad tidings, misc

g21.d:
ἀγαλλιάω agalliáō, ag-al-lee-ah'-o; from agan (much) and G242; properly, to jump for joy, i.e. exult:—be
 (exceeding) glad, with exceeding joy, rejoice (greatly).
g21.r: From agan (much) and ἅλλομαι (G242)|English: leap, spring up

g210.d:
ἄκων ákōn, ak'-ohn; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G1635; unwilling:—against the
 will.
g210.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and ἑκών (G1635)|English: Alpha

g2100.d: εὐαρεστέω euarestéō, yoo-ar-es-teh'-o; from G2101; to gratify entirely:—please (well).
g2100.r: From εὐάρεστος (G2101)|English: acceptably, well pleasing, please well, accepted

g2101.d: εὐάρεστος euárestos, yoo-ar'-es-tos; from G2095 and G701; fully agreeable:—acceptable(-ted), wellpleasing.
g2101.r: From εὖ (G2095) and ἀρεστός (G701)|English: well, well done, good

g2102.d: εὐαρέστως euaréstōs, yoo-ar-es'-toce; adverb from G2101; quite agreeably:—acceptably, + please well.
g2102.r: From εὐάρεστος (G2101)|English: acceptably, well pleasing, please well, accepted

g2103.d: Εὔβουλος Eúboulos, yoo'-boo-los; from G2095 and G1014; good-willer; Eubulus, a Christian:—Eubulus.
g2103.r: From εὖ (G2095) and βούλομαι (G1014)|English: well, well done, good

g2104.d:
†εὐγενής eugenḗs, yoog-en'-ace; from G2095 and G1096; well born, i.e. (literally) high in rank, or
 (figuratively) generous:—more noble, nobleman.
g2104.r: From εὖ (G2095) and γίνομαι (G1096)|English: well, well done, good

g2105.d:
εὐδία eudía, yoo-dee'-ah; feminine from G2095 and the alternate of G2203 (as the god of the
 weather); a clear sky, i.e. fine weather:—fair weather.
g2105.r: Feminine from εὖ (G2095) and the alternate of Ζεύς (G2203) (as the god of the weather)|English: well, well done, good

g2106.r: From εὖ (G2095) and δοκέω (G1380)|English: well, well done, good

g2107.d:
εὐδοκία eudokía, yoo-dok-ee'-ah; from a presumed compound of G2095 and the base of G1380; satisfaction,
 i.e. (subjectively) delight, or (objectively) kindness, wish,
 purpose:—desire, good pleasure (will), × seem good.
g2107.r: From a presumed compound of εὖ (G2095) and the base of δοκέω (G1380)|English: well, well done, good

g2108.d:
εὐεργεσία euergesía, yoo-erg-es-ee'-ah; from G2110; beneficence (genitive case or specially):—benefit, good
 deed done.

g2109.d: εὐεργετέω euergetéō, yoo-erg-et-eh'-o; from G2110; to be philanthropic:—do good.

g211.r: From alabastros (of uncertain derivation), the name of a stone|

g2110.d:
εὐεργέτης euergétēs, yoo-erg-et'-ace; from G2095 and the base of G2041; a worker of good, i.e. (specially) a
 philanthropist:—benefactor.
g2110.r: From εὖ (G2095) and the base of ἔργον (G2041)|English: well, well done, good

g2111.d:
εὔθετος eúthetos, yoo'-thet-os; from G2095 and a derivative of G5087; well placed, i.e. (figuratively)
 appropriate:—fit, meet.
g2111.r: From εὖ (G2095) and a derivative of τίθημι (G5087)|English: well, well done, good

g2112.d:
εὐθέως euthéōs, yoo-theh'-oce; adverb from G2117; directly, i.e. at once or soon:—anon, as soon as,
 forthwith, immediately, shortly, straightway.
g2112.r: From εὐθύς (G2117)|English: straight, right, immediately, straightway, anon, by and by, forthwith

g2113.d:
εὐθυδρομέω euthydroméō, yoo-thoo-drom-eh'-o; from G2117 and G1408; to lay a straight course, i.e. sail
 direct:—(come) with a straight course.
g2113.r: From εὐθύς (G2117) and δρόμος (G1408)|English: straight, right, immediately, straightway, anon, by and by, forthwith

g2114.d:
εὐθυμέω euthyméō, yoo-thoo-meh'-o; from G2115; to cheer up, i.e. (intransitively) be cheerful; neuter
 comparative (adverbially) more cheerfully:—be of good cheer (merry).
g2114.r: From εὔθυμος (G2115)|English: of good cheer, more cheerfully

g2115.d:
†εὔθυμος eúthymos, yoo'-thoo-mos; from G2095 and G2372; in fine spirits, i.e. cheerful:—of good cheer,
 the more cheerfully.
g2115.r: From εὖ (G2095) and θυμός (G2372)|English: well, well done, good

g2116.d:
εὐθύνω euthýnō, yoo-thoo'-no; from G2117; to straighten (level); technically, to steer:—governor,
 make straight.
g2116.r: From εὐθύς (G2117)|English: straight, right, immediately, straightway, anon, by and by, forthwith

g2117.d:
†εὐθύς euthýs, yoo-thoos'; perhaps from G2095 and G5087; straight, i.e. (literally) level, or
 (figuratively) true; adverbially (of time) at once:—anon, by and by,
 forthwith, immediately, straightway.
g2117.r: Perhaps from εὖ (G2095) and τίθημι (G5087)|English: well, well done, good

g2118.d: εὐθύτης euthýtēs, yoo-thoo'-tace; from G2117; rectitude:—righteousness.
g2118.r: From εὐθύς (G2117)|English: straight, right, immediately, straightway, anon, by and by, forthwith

g2119.d:
εὐκαιρέω eukairéō, yoo-kahee-reh'-o; from G2121; to have good time, i.e. opportunity or leisure:—have
 leisure (convenient time), spend time.
g2119.r: From εὔκαιρος (G2121)|English: convenient, in time of need

g212.d:
ἀλαζονεία alazoneía, al-ad-zon-i'-a; from G213; braggadocio, i.e. (by implication)
 self-confidence:—boasting, pride.

g2120.d: εὐκαιρία eukairía, yoo-kahee-ree'-ah; from G2121; a favorable occasion:—opportunity.
g2120.r: From εὔκαιρος (G2121)|English: convenient, in time of need

g2121.d:
εὔκαιρος eúkairos, yoo'-kahee-ros; from G2095 and G2540; well-timed, i.e. opportune:—convenient, in time
 of need.
g2121.r: From εὖ (G2095) and καιρός (G2540)|English: well, well done, good

g2122.d: εὐκαίρως eukaírōs, yoo-kah'-ee-roce; adverb from G2121; opportunely:—conveniently, in season.
g2122.r: From εὔκαιρος (G2121)|English: convenient, in time of need

g2123.d:
εὐκοπώτερος eukopṓteros, yoo-kop-o'-ter-os; comparative of a compound of G2095 and G2873; better for toil, i.e. more
 facile:—easier.
g2123.r: Comparative of a compound of εὖ (G2095) and κόπος (G2873)|English: well, well done, good

g2124.d:
εὐλάβεια eulábeia, yoo-lab'-i-ah; from G2126; properly, caution, i.e. (religiously) reverence (piety); by
 implication, dread (concretely):—fear(-ed).

g2125.d:
εὐλαβέομαι eulabéomai, yoo-lab-eh'-om-ahee; middle voice from G2126; to be circumspect, i.e. (by implication) to be
 apprehensive; religiously, to reverence:—(moved with) fear.

g2126.d:
εὐλαβής eulabḗs, yoo-lab-ace'; from G2095 and G2983; taking well (carefully), i.e. circumspect
 (religiously, pious):—devout.
g2126.r: From εὖ (G2095) and λαμβάνω (G2983)|English: well, well done, good

g2127.d:
†εὐλογέω eulogéō, yoo-log-eh'-o; from a compound of G2095 and G3056; to speak well of, i.e. (religiously)
 to bless (thank or invoke a benediction upon, prosper):—bless,
 praise.
g2127.r: From a compound of εὖ (G2095) and λόγος (G3056)|English: well, well done, good

g2128.d: εὐλογητός eulogētós, yoo-log-ay-tos'; from G2127; adorable:—blessed.

g2129.d:
εὐλογία eulogía, yoo-log-ee'-ah; from the same as G2127; fine speaking, i.e. elegance of language;
 commendation ("eulogy"), i.e. (reverentially) adoration; religiously,
 benediction; by implication, consecration; by extension, benefit or
 largess:—blessing (a matter of) bounty (X -tifully), fair speech.
g2129.r: From the same as εὐλογέω (G2127)|English: bless, praise

g213.d: ἀλαζών alazṓn, al-ad-zone'; from ἄλη álē (vagrancy); braggart:—boaster.

g2130.d:
εὐμετάδοτος eumetádotos, yoo-met-ad'-ot-os; from G2095 and a presumed derivative of G3330; good at imparting, i.e.
 liberal:—ready to distribute.
