g2520.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἥκω (G2240)}|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2521.d:
κάθημαι káthēmai, kath'-ay-mahee; from G2596; and ἧμαι hēmai (to sit; akin to the base of G1476); to sit down;
 figuratively, to remain, reside:—dwell, sit (by, down).
g2521.r: From κατά (G2596), and hemai (to sit, akin to the base of ἑδραῖος (G1476))|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2522.d: καθημερινός kathēmerinós, kath-ay-mer-ee-nos'; from G2596 and G2250; quotidian:—daily.
g2522.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἡμέρα (G2250)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2523.d:
καθίζω kathízō, kath-id'-zo; another (active) form for G2516; to seat down, i.e. set (figuratively,
 appoint); intransitively, to sit (down); figuratively, to settle
 (hover, dwell):—continue, set, sit (down), tarry.

g2524.d: καθίημι kathíēmi, kath-ee'-ay-mee; from G2596; and ἵημι híēmi (to send); to lower:—let down.
g2524.r: From κατά (G2596), and hiemi (to send)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2525.d:
καθίστημι kathístēmi, kath-is'-tay-mee; from G2596 and G2476; to place down (permanently), i.e. (figuratively)
 to designate, constitute, convoy:—appoint, be, conduct, make, ordain,
 set.
g2525.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἵστημι (G2476)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2526.d:
†καθό kathó, kath-o'; from G2596 and G3739; according to which thing, i.e. precisely as, in
 proportion as:—according to that, (inasmuch) as.
g2526.r: From κατά (G2596) and ὅς (G3739)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2527.d: καθόλου kathólou, kath-ol'-oo; from G2596 and G3650; on the whole, i.e. entirely:—at all.
g2527.r: From κατά (G2596) and ὅλος (G3650)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2528.d: καθοπλίζω kathoplízō, kath-op-lid'-zo; from G2596; and G3695; to equip fully with armor:—arm.
g2528.r: From κατά (G2596), and ὁπλίζω (G3695)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2529.d:
καθοράω kathoráō, kath-or-ah'-o; from G2596 and G3708; to behold fully, i.e. (figuratively) distinctly
 apprehend:—clearly see.
g2529.r: From κατά (G2596) and ὁράω (G3708)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g253.d:
†ἀλυπότερος alypóteros, al-oo-pot'-er-os; comparative of a compound of G1 (as a negative particle) and G3077; more
 without grief:—less sorrowful.
g253.r: Compound of ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and λύπη (G3077) (only used in the comparative in the NT)|English: Alpha

g2530.d:
καθότι kathóti, kath-ot'-ee; from G2596; and G3739 and G5100; according to which certain thing, i.e.
 as far (or inasmuch) as:—(according, forasmuch) as, because (that).
g2530.r: From κατά (G2596), and ὅς (G3739) and τις (G5100)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2531.d:
καθώς kathṓs, kath-oce'; from G2596 and G5613; just (or inasmuch) as, that:—according to,
 (according, even) as, how, when.
g2531.r: From κατά (G2596) and ὡς (G5613)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2532.d:
καί kaí, kahee; apparently, a primary particle, having a copulative and sometimes also
 a cumulative force; and, also, even, so then, too, etc.; often used in
 connection (or composition) with other particles or small words:—and,
 also, both, but, even, for, if, or, so, that, then, therefore, when,
 yet.
g2532.r: Apparently, a primary particle, having a copulative and sometimes also a cumulative force|

g2533.d:
Καϊάφας Kaïáphas, kah-ee-af'-as; of Chaldee origin; the dell; Caiaphas (i.e. Cajepha), an
 Israelite:—Caiaphas.

g2535.d: Κάϊν Káïn, kah'-in; of Hebrew origin (H7014); Cain, (i.e. Cajin), the son of Adam:—Cain.
g2535.r: Of Hebrew origin קַיִן (H7014)|English: Cain, Kenite

g2536.d:
†Καϊνάν Kaïnán, kah-ee-nan'; of Hebrew origin (H7018); Cainan (i.e. Kenan), the name of two
 patriarchs:—Cainan.
g2536.r: Of Hebrew origin קֵינָן (H7018)|English: Cainan, Kenan

g2537.d:
†καινός kainós, kahee-nos'; of uncertain affinity; new (especially in freshness; while G3501 is
 properly so with respect to age:—new.

g2538.d: καινότης kainótēs, kahee-not'-ace; from G2537; renewal (figuratively):—newness.

g2539.d:
καίπερ kaíper, kah'-ee-per; from G2532 and G4007; and indeed, i.e. nevertheless or
 notwithstanding:—and yet, although.
g2539.r: From καί (G2532) and περ (G4007)|English: and, also, even, both, then, so, likewise, not tr., misc

g254.d: ἅλυσις hálysis, hal'-oo-sis; of uncertain derivation; a fetter or manacle:—bonds, chain.

g2540.d:
καιρός kairós, kahee-ros'; of uncertain affinity; an occasion, i.e. set or proper time:—X
 always, opportunity, (convenient, due) season, (due, short, while)
 time, a while. Compare G5550.

g2541.d: Καῖσαρ Kaîsar, kah'-ee-sar; of Latin origin; Cæsar, a title of the Roman emperor:—Cæsar.

g2542.d: Καισάρεια Kaisáreia, kahee-sar'-i-a; from G2541; Cæsaria, the name of two places in Palestine:—Cæsarea.

g2543.d: καίτοι kaítoi, kah'-ee-toy; from G2532 and G5104; and yet, i.e. nevertheless:—although.
g2543.r: From καί (G2532) and τοι (G5104)|English: and, also, even, both, then, so, likewise, not tr., misc

g2545.d:
καίω kaíō, kah'-yo; apparently a primary verb; to set on fire, i.e. kindle or (by
 implication) consume:—burn, light.

g2546.d:
κἀκεῖ kakeî, kak-i'; from G2532 and G1563; likewise in that place:—and there, there
 (thither) also.
g2546.r: From καί (G2532) and ἐκεῖ (G1563)|English: and, also, even, both, then, so, likewise, not tr., misc

g2547.d:
κἀκεῖθεν kakeîthen, kak-i'-then; from G2532 and G1564; likewise from that place (or time):—and afterward
 (from) (thence), thence also.
g2547.r: From καί (G2532) and ἐκεῖθεν (G1564)|English: and, also, even, both, then, so, likewise, not tr., misc

g2548.d:
κἀκεῖνος kakeînos, kak-i'-nos; from G2532 and G1565; likewise that (or those):—and him (other, them),
 even he, him also, them (also), (and) they.
g2548.r: From καί (G2532) and ἐκεῖνος (G1565)|English: and, also, even, both, then, so, likewise, not tr., misc

g2549.d:
κακία kakía, kak-ee'-ah; from G2556; badness, i.e. (subjectively) depravity, or (actively)
 malignity, or (passively) trouble:—evil, malice(-iousness),
 naughtiness, wickedness.
g2549.r: From κακός (G2556)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g255.d:
ἀλυσιτελής alysitelḗs, al-oo-sit-el-ace'; from G1 (as a negative particle) and the base of G3081; gainless, i.e.
 (by implication) pernicious:—unprofitable.
g255.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and the base of λυσιτελέω (G3081)|English: Alpha

g2550.d:
κακοήθεια kakoḗtheia, kak-o-ay'-thi-ah; from a compound of G2556 and G2239; bad character, i.e. (specially)
 mischievousness:—malignity.
g2550.r: From a compound of κακός (G2556) and ἦθος (G2239)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g2551.d: κακολογέω kakologéō, kak-ol-og-eh'-o; from a compound of G2556 and G3056; to revile:—curse, speak evil of.
g2551.r: From a compound of κακός (G2556) and λόγος (G3056)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g2552.d: κακοπάθεια kakopátheia, kak-op-ath'-i-ah; from a compound of G2256 and G3806; hardship:—suffering affliction.
g2552.r: From a compound of κακός (G2556) and πάθος (G3806)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g2553.d:
κακοπαθέω kakopathéō, kak-op-ath-eh'-o; from the same as G2552; to undergo hardship:—be afflicted, endure
 afflictions (hardness), suffer trouble.
g2553.r: From the same as κακοπάθεια (G2552)|English: suffering affliction

g2554.d:
κακοποιέω kakopoiéō, kak-op-oy-eh'-o; from G2555; to be a bad-doer, i.e. (objectively) to injure, or
 (genitive) to sin:—do(ing) evil.

g2555.d:
κακοποιός kakopoiós, kak-op-oy-os'; from G2556 and G4160; a bad-doer; (specially), a criminal:—evil-doer,
 malefactor.
g2555.r: From κακός (G2556) and ποιέω (G4160)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g2556.d:
κακός kakós, kak-os'; apparently a primary word; worthless (intrinsically, such; whereas
 G4190 properly refers to effects), i.e. (subjectively) depraved, or
 (objectively) injurious:—bad, evil, harm, ill, noisome, wicked.

g2557.d:
κακοῦργος kakoûrgos, kak-oor'-gos; from G2556 and the base of G2041; a wrong-doer, i.e.
 criminal:—evil-doer, malefactor.
g2557.r: From κακός (G2556) and the base of ἔργον (G2041)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g2558.d:
κακουχέω kakouchéō, kak-oo-kheh'-o; from a presumed compound of G2556 and G2192; to maltreat:—which suffer
 adversity, torment.
g2558.r: From a presumed compound of κακός (G2556) and ἔχω (G2192)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g2559.d:
κακόω kakóō, kak-o'-o; from G2556; to injure; figuratively, to exasperate:—make evil
 affected, entreat evil, harm, hurt, vex.
g2559.r: From κακός (G2556)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g256.d: Ἀλφαῖος Alphaîos, al-fah'-yos; of Hebrew origin (compare H2501); Alphæus, an Israelite:—Alpheus.

g2560.d:
κακῶς kakōs, kak-oce'; from G2556; badly (physically or morally):—amiss, diseased, evil,
 grievously, miserably, sick, sore.
g2560.r: From κακός (G2556)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g2561.d: κάκωσις kákōsis, kak'-o-sis; from G2559; maltreatment:—affliction.
g2561.r: From κακόω (G2559)|English: entreat evil, make evil affected, vex, hurt, harm

g2562.d:
καλάμη kalámē, kal-am'-ay; feminine of G2563; a stalk of grain, i.e. (collectively)
 stubble:—stubble.

g2563.d:
κάλαμος kálamos, kal'-am-os; of uncertain affinity; a reed (the plant or its stem, or that of a
 similar plant); by implication, a pen:—pen, reed.

g2564.d:
καλέω kaléō, kal-eh'-o; akin to the base of G2753; to "call" (properly, aloud, but used in a
 variety of applications, directly or otherwise):—bid, call (forth),
 (whose, whose sur-)name (was (called)).
g2564.r: Akin to the base of κελεύω (G2753)|English: command, at (one's) command, give commandment, bid

g2565.d:
καλλιέλαιος kalliélaios, kal-le-el'-ah-yos; from the base of G2566 and G1636; a cultivated olive tree, i.e. a
 domesticated or improved one:—good olive tree.
g2565.r: From the base of καλλίον (G2566) and ἐλαία (G1636)|English: very well

g2567.d: καλοδιδάσκαλος kalodidáskalos, kal-od-id-as'-kal-os; from G2570 and G1320; a teacher of the right:—teacher of good things.
g2567.r: From καλός (G2570) and διδάσκαλος (G1320)|English: good, better, honest, meet, goodly, misc

g2569.d: καλοποιέω kalopoiéō, kal-op-oy-eh'-o; from G2570 and G4160; to do well, i.e. live virtuously:—well doing.
g2569.r: From καλός (G2570) and ποιέω (G4160)|English: good, better, honest, meet, goodly, misc

g257.d:
ἅλων hálōn, hal'-ohn; probably from the base of G1507; a threshing-floor (as rolled hard),
 i.e. (figuratively) the grain (and chaff, as just threshed):—floor.
g257.r: Probably from the base of εἱλίσσω (G1507)|English: roll together

g2570.d:
καλός kalós, kal-os'; of uncertain affinity; properly, beautiful, but chiefly (figuratively)
 good (literally or morally), i.e. valuable or virtuous (for appearance
 or use, and thus distinguished from G18, which is properly
 intrinsic):—X better, fair, good(-ly), honest, meet, well, worthy.

g2571.d: †κάλυμα kályma, kal'-oo-mah; from G2572; a cover, i.e. veil:—vail.

g2572.d:
καλύπτω kalýptō, kal-oop'-to; akin to G2813 and G2928; to cover up (literally or
 figuratively):—cover, hide.
g2572.r: Akin to κλέπτω (G2813) and κρύπτω (G2928)|English: steal

g2573.d:
καλῶς kalōs, kal-oce'; adverb from G2570; well (usually morally):—(in a) good (place),
 honestly, + recover, (full) well.
g2573.r: From καλός (G2570)|English: good, better, honest, meet, goodly, misc

g2574.d: κάμηλος kámēlos, kam'-ay-los; of Hebrew origin (H1581); a "camel":—camel.

g2575.d: κάμινος káminos, kam'-ee-nos; probably from G2545; a furnace:—furnace.
g2575.r: Probably from καίω (G2545)|English: burn, did burn, light

g2576.d:
καμμύω kammýō, kam-moo'-o; from a compound of G2596 and the base of G3466; to shut down, i.e. close
 the eyes:—close.
g2576.r: From a compound of κατά (G2596) and the base of μυστήριον (G3466)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2577.d:
κάμνω kámnō, kam'-no; apparently a primary verb; properly, to toil, i.e. (by implication) to
 tire (figuratively, faint, sicken):—faint, sick, be wearied.

g2578.d: κάμπτω kámptō, kamp'-to; apparently a primary verb; to bend:—bow.

g2579.d:
κἄν kán, kan; from G2532 and G1437; and (or even) if:—and (also) if (so much as), if
 but, at the least, though, yet.
g2579.r: From καί (G2532) and ἐάν (G1437)|English: and, also, even, both, then, so, likewise, not tr., misc

g258.d:
ἀλώπηξ alṓpēx, al-o'-pakes; of uncertain derivation; a fox, i.e. (figuratively) a cunning
 person:—fox.

g2580.d: †Κανᾶ Kanâ, kan-ah'; of Hebrew origin (compare H7071); Cana, a place in Palestine:—Cana.
g2580.r: Of Hebrew origin, cf קָנָה (H7071)|English: Kanah

g2582.d: Κανδάκη Kandákē, kan-dak'-ay; of foreign origin; Candacè, an Egyptian queen:—Candace.

g2583.d:
κανών kanṓn, kan-ohn'; from κάνη kánē (a straight reed, i.e. rod); a rule ("canon"), i.e.
 (figuratively) a standard (of faith and practice); by implication, a
 boundary, i.e. (figuratively) a sphere (of activity):—line, rule.
g2583.r: From kane (a straight reed, i.e. rod)|

g2585.d:
καπηλεύω kapēleúō, kap-ale-yoo'-o; from κάπηλος kápēlos (a huckster); to retail, i.e. (by implication) to
 adulterate (figuratively):—corrupt.

g2586.d: καπνός kapnós, kap-nos'; of uncertain affinity; smoke:—smoke.

g2587.d: Καππαδοκία Kappadokía, kap-pad-ok-ee'-ah; of foreign origin; Cappadocia, a region of Asia Minor:—Cappadocia.

g2588.d:
καρδία kardía, kar-dee'-ah; prolonged from a primary κάρ kár (Latin cor, "heart"); the heart, i.e.
 (figuratively) the thoughts or feelings (mind); also (by analogy) the
 middle:—(+ broken-)heart(-ed).
g2588.r: Prolonged from a primary kar (Latin, cor,|

g2589.d: καρδιογνώστης kardiognṓstēs, kar-dee-og-noce'-tace; from G2588 and G1097; a heart-knower:—which knowest the hearts.
g2589.r: From καρδία (G2588) and γινώσκω (G1097)|English: heart, broken hearted

g259.d: ἅλωσις hálōsis, hal'-o-sis; from a collateral form of G138; capture, be taken.
g259.r: From a collateral form of αἱρέω (G138)|English: choose

g2590.d:
καρπός karpós, kar-pos'; probably from the base of G726; fruit (as plucked), literally or
 figuratively:—fruit.
g2590.r: Probably from the base of ἁρπάζω (G726)|English: catch up, take by force, catch away, pluck, catch, pull

g2591.d: Κάρπος Kárpos, kar'-pos; perhaps for G2590; Carpus, probably a Christian:—Carpus.

g2592.d:
καρποφορέω karpophoréō, kar-pof-or-eh'-o; from G2593; to be fertile (literally or figuratively):—be (bear, bring
 forth) fruit(-ful).

g2593.d: καρποφόρος karpophóros, kar-pof-or'-os; from G2590 and G5342; fruitbearing (figuratively):—fruitful.

g2594.d:
καρτερέω karteréō, kar-ter-eh'-o; from a derivative of G2904 (transposed); to be strong, i.e.
 (figuratively) steadfast (patient):—endure.
g2594.r: From a derivative of κράτος (G2904) (transp.)|English: power, dominion, strength, mighty

g2595.d: κάρφος kárphos, kar'-fos; from κάρφω kárphō (to wither); a dry twig or straw:—mote.

g2596.d:
κατά katá, kat-ah'; a primary particle; (prepositionally) down (in place or time), in
 varied relations (according to the case (genitive, dative or
 accusative) with which it is joined):—about, according as (to),
 after, against, (when they were) × alone, among, and, × apart, (even,
 like) as (concerning, pertaining to touching), × aside, at, before,
 beyond, by, to the charge of, (charita-)bly, concerning, + covered,
 (dai-)ly, down, every, (+ far more) exceeding, × more excellent, for,
 from … to, godly, in(-asmuch, divers, every, -to, respect of), …
 by, after the manner of, + by any means, beyond (out of) measure, X
 mightily, more, × natural, of (up-)on (X part), out (of every), over
 against, (+ your) × own, + particularly, so, through(-oughout,
 -oughout every), thus, (un-)to(-gether, -ward), × uttermost,
 where(-by), with.

g2597.d:
καταβαίνω katabaínō, kat-ab-ah'-ee-no; from G2596 and the base of G939; to descend (literally or
 figuratively):—come (get, go, step) down, fall (down).
g2597.r: From κατά (G2596) and the base of βάσις (G939)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2598.d: καταβάλλω katabállō, kat-ab-al'-lo; from G2596 and G906; to throw down:—cast down, lay.
g2598.r: From κατά (G2596) and βάλλω (G906)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2599.d: καταβαρέω katabaréō, kat-ab-ar-eh'-o; from G2596 and G916; to impose upon:—burden.
g2599.r: From κατά (G2596) and βαρέω (G916)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g26.d:
ἀγάπη agápē, ag-ah'-pay; from G25; love, i.e. affection or benevolence; specially (plural) a
 love-feast:—(feast of) charity(-ably), dear, love.

g260.d:
ἅμα háma, ham'-ah; a primary particle; properly, at the "same" time, but freely used as a
 preposition or adverb denoting close association:—also, and,
 together, with(-al).
g260.s: absolute state masculine plural intensive noun

g2600.d: κατάβασις katábasis, kat-ab'-as-is; from G2597; a declivity:—descent.
g2600.r: From καταβαίνω (G2597)|English: come down, descend, go down, fall down, step down, get down, fall

g2601.d:
καταβιβάζω katabibázō, kat-ab-ib-ad'-zo; from G2596 and a derivative of the base of G939; to cause to go down,
 i.e. precipitate:—bring (thrust) down.
g2601.r: From κατά (G2596) and a derivative of the base of βάσις (G939)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2602.d:
καταβολή katabolḗ, kat-ab-ol-ay'; from G2598; a deposition, i.e. founding; figuratively,
 conception:—conceive, foundation.

g2603.d:
καταβραβεύω katabrabeúō, kat-ab-rab-yoo'-o; from G2596 and G1018 (in its original sense); to award the price
 against, i.e. (figuratively) to defraud (of salvation):—beguile of
 reward.
g2603.r: From κατά (G2596) and βραβεύω (G1018) (in its original sense)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2604.d: καταγγελεύς katangeleús, kat-ang-gel-yooce'; from G2605; a proclaimer:—setter forth.
g2604.r: From καταγγέλλω (G2605)|English: preach, show, declare, teach, speak of

g2605.d:
καταγγέλλω katangéllō, kat-ang-gel'-lo; from G2596 and the base of G32; to proclaim, promulgate:—declare,
 preach, shew, speak of, teach.
g2605.r: From κατά (G2596) and the base of ἄγγελος (G32)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2606.d: καταγελάω katageláō, kat-ag-el-ah'-o; to laugh down, i.e. deride:—laugh to scorn.
g2606.r: From κατά (G2596) and γελάω (G1070)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2607.d:
καταγινώσκω kataginṓskō, kat-ag-in-o'-sko; from G2596 and G1097; to note against, i.e. find fault with:—blame,
 condemn.
g2607.r: From κατά (G2596) and γινώσκω (G1097)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2608.d:
κατάγνυμι katágnymi, kat-ag'-noo-mee; from G2596 and the base of G4486; to rend in pieces, i.e. crack
 apart:—break.
g2608.r: From κατά (G2596) and the base of ῥήγνυμι (G4486)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2609.d:
κατάγω katágō, kat-ag'-o; from G2596 and G71; to lead down; specially, to moor a vessel:—bring
 (down, forth), (bring to) land, touch.
g2609.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἄγω (G71)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g261.d: ἀμαθής amathḗs, am-ath-ace'; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3129; ignorant:—unlearned.
g261.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and μανθάνω (G3129)|English: Alpha

g2610.d:
καταγωνίζομαι katagōnízomai, kat-ag-o-nid'-zom-ahee; from G2596 and G75; to struggle against, i.e. (by implication) to
 overcome:—subdue.
g2610.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἀγωνίζομαι (G75)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2611.d: καταδέω katadéō, kat-ad-eh'-o; from G2596 and G1210; to tie down, i.e. bandage (a wound):—bind up.
g2611.r: From κατά (G2596) and δέω (G1210)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2612.d: κατάδηλος katádēlos, kat-ad'-ay-los; from G2596 intensive and G1212; manifest:—far more evident.
g2612.r: From κατά (G2596) intensive and δῆλος (G1212)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2613.d:
καταδικάζω katadikázō, kat-ad-ik-ad'-zo; from G2596 and a derivative of G1349; to adjudge against, i.e. pronounce
 guilty:—condemn.
g2613.r: From κατά (G2596) and a derivative of δίκη (G1349)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2614.d: καταδιώκω katadiṓkō, kat-ad-ee-o'-ko; from G2596 and G1377; to hunt down, i.e. search for:—follow after.
g2614.r: From κατά (G2596) and διώκω (G1377)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2615.d: καταδουλόω katadoulóō, kat-ad-oo-lo'-o; from G2596 and G1402; to enslave utterly:—bring into bondage.
g2615.r: From κατά (G2596) and δουλόω (G1402)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2616.d:
καταδυναστεύω katadynasteúō, kat-ad-oo-nas-tyoo'-o; from G2596 and a derivative of G1413; to exercise dominion against, i.e.
 oppress:—oppress.
g2616.r: From κατά (G2596) and a derivative of δυνάστης (G1413)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2617.d:
καταισχύνω kataischýnō, kat-ahee-skhoo'-no; from G2596 and G153; to shame down, i.e. disgrace or (by implication)
 put to the blush:—confound, dishonour, (be a-, make a-)shame(-d).
g2617.r: From κατά (G2596) and αἰσχύνω (G153)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2618.d:
κατακαίω katakaíō, kat-ak-ah'-ee-o; from G2596 and G2545; to burn down (to the ground), i.e. consume
 wholly:—burn (up, utterly).
g2618.r: From κατά (G2596) and καίω (G2545)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2619.d: κατακαλύπτω katakalýptō, kat-ak-al-oop'-to; from G2596 and G2572; to cover wholly, i.e. veil:—cover, hide.
g2619.r: From κατά (G2596) and καλύπτω (G2572)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g262.d:
ἀμαράντινος amarántinos, am-ar-an'-tee-nos; from G263; "amaranthine", i.e. (by implication) fadeless:—that fadeth
 not away.
g262.r: From ἀμάραντος (G263)|English: that fadeth not away

g2620.d:
†κατακαυχάομαι katakaucháomai, kat-ak-ow-khah'-om-ahee; from G2596 and G2744; to exult against (i.e. over):—boast (against),
 glory, rejoice against.
g2620.r: From κατά (G2596) and καυχάομαι (G2744)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2621.d:
κατάκειμαι katákeimai, kat-ak'-i-mahee; from G2596 and G2749; to lie down, i.e. (by implication) be sick;
 specially, to recline at a meal:—keep, lie, sit at meat (down).
g2621.r: From κατά (G2596) and κεῖμαι (G2749)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2622.d: κατακλάω katakláō, kat-ak-lah'-o; from G2596 and G2806; to break down, i.e. divide:—break.
g2622.r: From κατά (G2596) and κλάω (G2806)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2623.d:
κατακλείω katakleíō, kat-ak-li'-o; from G2596 and G2808; to shut down (in a dungeon), i.e.
 incarcerate:—shut up.
g2623.r: From κατά (G2596) and κλείω (G2808)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2624.d:
†κατακληροδοτέω kataklērodotéō, kat-ak-lay-rod-ot-eh'-o; from G2596 and a derivative of a compound of G2819 and G1325; to be a
 giver of lots to each, i.e. (by implication) to apportion an
 estate:—divide by lot.
g2624.r: From κατά (G2596) and a derivative of a compound of κλῆρος (G2819) and δίδωμι (G1325)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2625.d:
κατακλίνω kataklínō, kat-ak-lee'-no; from G2596 and G2827; to recline down, i.e. (specially) to take a place
 at table:—(make) sit down (at meat).
g2625.r: From κατά (G2596) and κλίνω (G2827)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2626.d:
κατακλύζω kataklýzō, kat-ak-lood'-zo; from G2596 and the base of G2830; to dash (wash) down, i.e. (by
 implication) to deluge:—overflow.
g2626.r: From κατά (G2596) and the base of κλύδων (G2830)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2627.d: κατακλυσμός kataklysmós, kat-ak-looce-mos'; from G2626; an inundation:—flood.

g2628.d: κατακολουθέω katakolouthéō, kat-ak-ol-oo-theh'-o; from G2596 and G190; to accompany closely:—follow (after).
g2628.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἀκολουθέω (G190)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2629.d: κατακόπτω katakóptō, kat-ak-op'-to; from G2596 and G2875; to chop down, i.e. mangle:—cut.
g2629.r: From κατά (G2596) and κόπτω (G2875)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g263.d:
ἀμάραντος amárantos, am-ar'-an-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of G3133; 
 unfading, i.e. (by implication) perpetual:—that fadeth not away.
g263.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of μαραίνω (G3133)|English: Alpha

g2630.d:
κατακρημνίζω katakrēmnízō, kat-ak-rame-nid'-zo; from G2596 and a derivative of G2911; to precipitate down:—cast down
 headlong.
g2630.r: From κατά (G2596) and a derivative of κρημνός (G2911)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2631.d: κατάκριμα katákrima, kat-ak'-ree-mah; from G2632; an adverse sentence (the verdict):—condemnation.

g2632.d: κατακρίνω katakrínō, kat-ak-ree'-no; from G2596 and G2919; to judge against, i.e. sentence:—condemn, damn.
g2632.r: From κατά (G2596) and κρίνω (G2919)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2633.d: κατάκρισις katákrisis, kat-ak'-ree-sis; from G2632; sentencing adversely (the act):—condemn(-ation).

g2634.d:
κατακυριεύω katakyrieúō, kat-ak-oo-ree-yoo'-o; from G2596 and G2961; to lord against, i.e. control,
 subjugate:—exercise dominion over (lordship), be lord over, overcome.
g2634.r: From κατά (G2596) and κυριεύω (G2961)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2635.d:
καταλαλέω katalaléō, kat-al-al-eh'-o; from G2637; to be a traducer, i.e. to slander:—speak against (evil
 of).

g2636.d: †καταλαλία katalalía, kat-al-al-ee'-ah; from G2637; defamation:—backbiting, evil speaking.

g2637.d:
κατάλαλος katálalos, kat-al'-al-os; from G2596 and the base of G2980; talkative against, i.e. a
 slanderer:—backbiter.
g2637.r: From κατά (G2596) and the base of λαλέω (G2980)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2638.d:
καταλαμβάνω katalambánō, kat-al-am-ban'-o; from G2596 and G2983; to take eagerly, i.e. seize, possess, etc.
 (literally or figuratively):—apprehend, attain, come upon,
 comprehend, find, obtain, perceive, (over-)take.
g2638.r: From κατά (G2596) and λαμβάνω (G2983)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2639.d:
καταλέγω katalégō, kat-al-eg'-o; from G2596 and G3004 (in its original meaning); to lay down, i.e.
 (figuratively) to enrol:—take into the number.

g2715.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἐξουσιάζω (G1850)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2716.d:
κατεργάζομαι katergázomai, kat-er-gad'-zom-ahee; from G2596 and G2038; to work fully, i.e. accomplish; by implication, to
 finish, fashion:—cause, to (deed), perform, work (out).
g2716.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἐργάζομαι (G2038)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2718.d:
κατέρχομαι katérchomai, kat-er'-khom-ahee; from G2596 and G2064 (including its alternate); to come (or go) down
 (literally or figuratively):—come (down), depart, descend, go down,
 land.
g2718.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἔρχομαι (G2064) (including its alternate)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2719.d:
κατεσθίω katesthíō, kat-es-thee'-o; from G2596 and G2068 (including its alternate); to eat down, i.e. devour
 (literally or figuratively):—devour.
g2719.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἐσθίω (G2068) (including its alternate)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g272.d:
ἀμελέω ameléō, am-el-eh'-o; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3199; to be careless of:—make
 light of, neglect, be negligent, no regard.
g272.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and μέλει (G3199)|English: Alpha

g2720.d:
κατευθύνω kateuthýnō, kat-yoo-thoo'-no; from G2596 and G2116; to straighten fully, i.e. (figuratively)
 direct:—guide, direct.
g2720.r: From κατά (G2596) and εὐθύνω (G2116)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2721.d:
κατεφίστημι katephístēmi, kat-ef-is'-tay-mee; from G2596 and G2186; to stand over against, i.e. rush upon
 (assault):—make insurrection against.
g2721.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἐφίστημι (G2186)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2722.d:
κατέχω katéchō, kat-ekh'-o; from G2596 and G2192; to hold down (fast), in various applications
 (literally or figuratively):—have, hold (fast), keep (in memory),
 let, × make toward, possess, retain, seize on, stay, take, withhold.
g2722.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἔχω (G2192)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2723.d:
κατηγορέω katēgoréō, kat-ay-gor-eh'-o; from G2725; to be a plaintiff, i.e. to charge with some
 offence:—accuse, object.

g2724.d:
κατηγορία katēgoría, kat-ay-gor-ee'-ah; from G2725; a complaint ("category"), i.e. criminal charge:—accusation
 (X -ed).

g2725.d:
†κατήγορος katḗgoros, kat-ay'-gor-os; from G2596 and G58; against one in the assembly, i.e. a complainant at
 law; specially, Satan:—accuser.
g2725.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἀγορά (G58)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2726.d:
κατήφεια katḗpheia, kat-ay'-fi-ah; from a compound of G2596 and perhaps a derivative of the base of G5316
 (meaning downcast in look); demureness, i.e. (by implication)
 sadness:—heaviness.
g2726.r: From a compound of κατά (G2596) and perhaps a derivative of the base of φαίνω (G5316) (meaning downcast in look)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2727.d:
κατηχέω katēchéō, kat-ay-kheh'-o; from G2596 and G2279; to sound down into the ears, i.e. (by implication)
 to indoctrinate ("catechize") or (genitive case) to apprise
 of:—inform, instruct, teach.
g2727.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἦχος (G2279)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2728.d:
κατιόω katióō, kat-ee-o'-o; from G2596 and a derivative of G2447; to rust down, i.e.
 corrode:—canker.
g2728.r: From κατά (G2596) and a derivative of ἰός (G2447)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2729.d: κατισχύω katischýō, kat-is-khoo'-o; from G2596 and G2480; to overpower:—prevail (against).
g2729.r: From κατά (G2596) and ἰσχύω (G2480)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g273.d:
ἄμεμπτος ámemptos, am'-emp-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a derivative of G3201; 
 irreproachable:—blameless, faultless, unblamable.
g273.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of μέμφομαι (G3201)|English: Alpha

g2730.d:
†κατοικέω katoikéō, kat-oy-keh'-o; from G2596 and G3611; to house permanently, i.e. reside (literally or
 figuratively):—dwell(-er), inhabitant(-ter).
g2730.r: From κατά (G2596) and οἰκέω (G3611)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2731.d:
κατοίκησις katoíkēsis, kat-oy'-kay-sis; from G2730; residence (properly, the act; but by implication,
 concretely, the mansion):—dwelling.
g2731.r: From κατοικέω (G2730)|English: dwell, dweller, inhabitor, inhabitant

g2732.d: κατοικητήριον katoikētḗrion, kat-oy-kay-tay'-ree-on; from a derivative of G2730; a dwelling-place:—habitation.
g2732.r: From a derivative of κατοικέω (G2730)|English: dwell, dweller, inhabitor, inhabitant

g2733.d:
κατοικία katoikía, kat-oy-kee'-ah; residence (properly, the condition; but by implication, the
 abode itself):—habitation.

g2734.d:
†κατοπτρίζομαι katoptrízomai, kat-op-trid'-zom-ahee; middle voice from a compound of G2596 and a derivative of G3700 (compare
 G2072); to mirror oneself, i.e. to see reflected
 (figuratively):—behold as in a glass.
g2734.r: Middle voice from a compound of κατά (G2596) and a derivative of ὀπτάνομαι (G3700) [cf ἔσοπτρον (G2072)]|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2736.d:
†κάτω kátō, kat'-o; (compare G2737); adverb from G2596; downwards:—beneath, bottom, down,
 under.
g2736.r: From κατά (G2596)|English: according to, after, against, in, by, daily, as, misc

g2737.d: κατώτερος katṓteros, kat-o'-ter-os; comparative from G2736; inferior (locally, of Hades):—lower.
g2737.r: Comparative from κάτω (G2736)|English: down, beneath, bottom, under

g2738.d:
καῦμα kaûma, kow'-mah; from G2545; properly, a burn (concretely), but used (abstractly) of a
 glow:—heat.
g2738.r: From καίω (G2545)|English: burn, did burn, light

g2739.d: καυματίζω kaumatízō, kow-mat-id'-zo; from G2738; to burn:—scorch.

g274.d: ἀμέμπτως amémptōs, am-emp'-toce; adverb from G273; faultlessly:—blameless, unblamably.

g2740.d: καῦσις kaûsis, kow'-sis; from G2545; burning (the act):—be burned.
g2740.r: From καίω (G2545)|English: burn, did burn, light

g2741.d: †καυσόω kausóō, kow-so'-o; from G2740; to set on fire:—fervent heat.

g2742.d: καύσων kaúsōn, kow'-sone; from G2741; a glare:—(burning) heat.

g2744.r: From some (obsolete) base akin to that of aucheo (to boast) and εὔχομαι (G2172)|English: wish, pray, can wish, I would

g2745.d:
καύχημα kaúchēma, kow'-khay-mah; from G2744; a boast (properly, the object; by implication, the act) in
 a good or a bad sense:—boasting, (whereof) to glory (of), glorying,
 rejoice(-ing).
g2745.r: From καυχάομαι (G2744)|English: glory, boast, rejoice, make boast, joy

g2746.d:
καύχησις kaúchēsis, kow'-khay-sis; from G2744; boasting (properly, the act; by implication, the object),
 in a good or a bad sense:—boasting, whereof I may glory, glorying,
 rejoicing.
g2746.r: From καυχάομαι (G2744)|English: glory, boast, rejoice, make boast, joy

g2747.d:
†Κεγχρεαί Kenchreaí, keng-khreh-a'-hee; probably from kegchros (millet); Cenchreæ, a port of
 Corinth:—Cencrea.

g2748.d:
†Κεδρών Kedrṓn, ked-rone'; of Hebrew origin (H6939); Cedron (i.e. Kidron), a brook near
 Jerusalem:—Cedron.

g2749.d:
κεῖμαι keîmai, ki'-mahee; middle voice of a primary verb; to lie outstretched (literally or
 figuratively):—be (appointed, laid up, made, set), lay, lie. Compare
 G5087.
g2749.r: Middle voice of a primary verb|

g275.d:
ἀμέριμνος amérimnos, am-er'-im-nos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3308; not anxious:—without
 care(-fulness), secure.
g275.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and μέριμνα (G3308)|English: Alpha

g2750.d: κειρία keiría, ki-ree'-ah; of uncertain affinity; a swathe, i.e. winding-sheet:—graveclothes.

g2751.d: κείρω keírō, ki'-ro; a primary verb; to shear:—shear(-er).

g2752.d: †κέλευμα kéleuma, kel'-yoo-mah; from G2753; a cry of incitement:—shout.
g2752.r: From κελεύω (G2753)|English: command, at (one's) command, give commandment, bid

g2753.d:
κελεύω keleúō, kel-yoo'-o; from a primary κέλλω kéllō (to urge on); "hail"; to incite by word, i.e.
 order:—bid, (at, give) command(-ment).
g2753.r: From a primary kello (to urge on)|

g2754.d: κενοδοξία kenodoxía, ken-od-ox-ee'-ah; from G2755; empty glorying, i.e. self-conceit:—vain-glory.
g2754.r: From κενόδοξος (G2755)|English: desirous of vain glory

g2755.d:
κενόδοξος kenódoxos, ken-od'-ox-os; from G2756 and G1391; vainly glorifying, i.e. self-conceited:—desirous
 of vain-glory.
g2755.r: From κενός (G2756) and δόξα (G1391)|English: vain, in vain, empty, vain things

g2756.d:
κενός kenós, ken-os'; apparently a primary word; empty (literally or figuratively):—empty,
 (in) vain.

g2757.d:
κενοφωνία kenophōnía, ken-of-o-nee'-ah; from a presumed compound of G2756 and G5456; empty sounding, i.e.
 fruitless discussion:—vain.
g2757.r: From a presumed compound of κενός (G2756) and φωνή (G5456)|English: vain, in vain, empty, vain things

g2758.d:
κενόω kenóō, ken-o'-o; from G2756; to make empty, i.e. (figuratively) to abase, neutralize,
 falsify:—make (of none effect, of no reputation, void), be in vain.
g2758.r: From κενός (G2756)|English: vain, in vain, empty, vain things

g2759.d:
κέντρον kéntron, ken'-tron; from κεντέω kentéō (to prick); a point ("centre"), i.e. a sting
 (figuratively, poison) or goad (figuratively, divine impulse):—prick,
 sting.

g276.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of μετατίθημι (G3346)|English: Alpha

g2760.d:
κεντυρίων kentyríōn, ken-too-ree'-ohn; of Latin origin; a centurion, i.e. captain of one hundred
 soldiers:—centurion.

g2761.d: κενῶς kenōs, ken-oce'; adverb from G2756; vainly, i.e. to no purpose:—in vain.
g2761.r: From κενός (G2756)|English: vain, in vain, empty, vain things

g2762.d:
κεραία keraía, ker-ah'-yah; feminine of a presumed derivative of the base of G2768; something
 horn-like, i.e. (specially) the apex of a Hebrew letter (figuratively,
 the least particle):—tittle.
g2762.r: From a presumed derivative of the base of κέρας (G2768)|English: horn

g2763.d: κεραμεύς kerameús, ker-am-yooce'; from G2766; a potter:—potter.

g2764.d: κεραμικός keramikós, ker-am-ik-os'; from G2766; made of clay, i.e. earthen:—of a potter.

g2765.d:
κεράμιον kerámion, ker-am'-ee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G2766; an earthenware vessel, i.e.
 jar:—pitcher.
g2765.r: From a presumed derivative of κέραμος (G2766)|English: tiling

g2766.d:
κέραμος kéramos, ker'-am-os; probably from the base of G2767 (through the idea of mixing clay and
 water); earthenware, i.e. a tile (by analogy, a thin roof or
 awning):—tiling.
g2766.r: Probably from the base of κεράννυμι (G2767) (through the idea of mixing clay and water)|English: fill, pour out

g2767.d:
κεράννυμι keránnymi, ker-an'-noo-mee; prolonged form of a more primary κεράω keráō ker-ah'-o (which is used in
 certain tenses); to mingle, i.e. (by implication) to pour out (for
 drinking):—fill, pour out. Compare G3396.
g2767.r: A prolonged form of a more primary kerao {ker-ah'-o} (which is used in certain tenses)|

g2768.d:
κέρας kéras, ker'-as; from a primary κάρ kár (the hair of the head); a horn (literally or
 figuratively):—horn.
g2768.r: From a primary kar (the hair of the head)|

g2769.d:
κεράτιον kerátion, ker-at'-ee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G2768; something horned, i.e.
 (specially) the pod of the carob-tree:—husk.
g2769.r: From a presumed derivative of κέρας (G2768)|English: horn

g277.d:
ἀμετακίνητος ametakínētos, am-et-ak-in'-ay-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a derivative of G3334; 
 immovable:—unmovable.
g277.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of μετακινέω (G3334)|English: Alpha

g2770.d: κερδαίνω kerdaínō, ker-dah'-ee-no; from G2771; to gain (literally or figuratively):—(get) gain, win.

g2771.d:
κέρδος kérdos, ker'-dos; of uncertain affinity; gain (pecuniary or genitive case):—gain,
 lucre.

g2772.d: κέρμα kérma, ker'-mah; from G2751; a clipping (bit), i.e. (specially) a coin:—money.

g2773.d:
κερματιστής kermatistḗs, ker-mat-is-tace'; from a derivative of G2772; a handler of coins, i.e.
 money-broker:—changer of money.
g2773.r: From a derivative of κέρμα (G2772)|English: money

g2774.d:
κεφάλαιον kephálaion, kef-al'-ah-yon; neuter of a derivative of G2776; a principal thing, i.e. main point;
 specially, an amount (of money):—sum.
g2774.r: From a derivative of κεφαλή (G2776)|English: head

g2776.d:
κεφαλή kephalḗ, kef-al-ay'; from the primary κάπτω káptō (in the sense of seizing); the head (as the
 part most readily taken hold of), literally or figuratively:—head.
g2776.r: From the primary kapto (in the sense of seizing)|

g2777.d:
κεφαλίς kephalís, kef-al-is'; from G2776; properly, a knob, i.e. (by implication) a roll (by
 extension from the end of a stick on which the manuscript was
 rolled):—volume.

g2778.d:
κῆνσος kēnsos, kane'-sos; of Latin origin; properly, an enrollment ("census"), i.e. (by
 implication) a tax:—tribute.

g2779.d: κῆπος kēpos, kay'-pos; of uncertain affinity; a garden:—garden.

g278.d:
ἀμεταμέλητος ametamélētos, am-et-am-el'-ay-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of G3338; 
 irrevocable:—without repentance, not to be repented of.
g278.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of μεταμέλομαι (G3338)|English: Alpha

g2780.d:
κηπουρός kēpourós, kay-poo-ros'; from G2779 and οὖρος oûros (a warden); a garden-keeper, i.e.
 gardener:—gardener.
g2780.r: From κῆπος (G2779) and ouros (a warden)|English: garden

g2782.d:
κήρυγμα kḗrygma, kay'-roog-mah; from G2784; a proclamation (especially of the gospel; by implication,
 the gospel itself):—preaching.
g2782.r: From κηρύσσω (G2784)|English: preach, publish, proclaim, preached, preacher

g2783.d:
κῆρυξ kēryx, kay'-roox; from G2784; a herald, i.e. of divine truth (especially of the
 gospel):—preacher.
g2783.r: From κηρύσσω (G2784)|English: preach, publish, proclaim, preached, preacher

g2784.d:
κηρύσσω kērýssō, kay-roos'-so; of uncertain affinity; to herald (as a public crier), especially
 divine truth (the gospel):—preacher(-er), proclaim, publish.

g2785.d:
κῆτος kētos, kay'-tos; probably from the base of G5490; a huge fish (as gaping for
 prey):—whale.
g2785.r: Probably from the base of χάσμα (G5490)|English: gulf

g2786.d:
Κηφᾶς Kēphâs, kay-fas'; of Chaldee origin (compare H3710); the Rock; Cephas (i.e. Kepha), a
 surname of Peter:—Cephas.
g2786.r: Of Aramaic origin cf כְּף (H3710)|English: rock

g2787.d:
κιβωτός kibōtós, kib-o-tos'; of uncertain derivation; a box, i.e. the sacred ark and that of
 Noah:—ark.

g2788.d: κιθάρα kithára, kith-ar'-ah; of uncertain affinity; a lyre:—harp.

g2789.d: κιθαρίζω kitharízō, kith-ar-id'-zo; from G2788; to play on a lyre:—harp.

g279.d:
ἀμετανόητος ametanóētos, am-et-an-o'-ay-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of G3340; 
 unrepentant:—impenitent.
g279.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of μετανοέω (G3340)|English: Alpha

g2790.d:
κιθαρῳδός kitharōidós, kith-ar-o'-dos; from G2788 and a derivative of the same as G5603; a
 lyre-singer(-player), i.e. harpist:—harper.
g2790.r: From κιθάρα (G2788) and a derivative of the same as ᾠδή (G5603)|English: harp

g2791.d: Κιλικία Kilikía, kil-ik-ee'-ah; probably of foreign origin; Cilicia, a region of Asia Minor:—Cilicia.

g2793.d: κινδυνεύω kindyneúō, kin-doon-yoo'-o; from G2794; to undergo peril:—be in danger, be (stand) in jeopardy.

g2794.d: κίνδυνος kíndynos, kin'-doo-nos; of uncertain derivation; danger:—peril.

g2795.d:
κινέω kinéō, kin-eh'-o; from κίω kíō (poetic for εἶμι eîmi, to go); to stir (transitively), literally
 or figuratively:—(re-)move(-r), way.
g2795.r: From kio (poetic for eimi, to go)|

g2796.d: κίνησις kínēsis, kin'-ay-sis; from G2795; a stirring:—moving.
g2796.r: From κινέω (G2795)|English: move, wag, remove, mover

g2797.d: Κίς Kís, kis; of Hebrew origin (H7027); Cis (i.e. Kish), an Israelite:—Cis.

g2798.d: κλάδος kládos, klad'-os; from G2806; a twig or bough (as if broken off):—branch.

g2799.d: κλαίω klaíō, klah'-yo; of uncertain affinity; to sob, i.e. wail aloud (whereas G1145 is rather to cry silently):—bewail, weep.

g28.d: †Ἄγαρ Ágar, ag'-ar; of Hebrew origin (H1904); Hagar, the concubine of Abraham:—Hagar.

g280.d:
ἄμετρος ámetros, am'-et-ros; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3358; immoderate:—(thing) without
 measure.
g280.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and μέτρον (G3358)|English: Alpha

g2800.d: κλάσις klásis, klas'-is; from G2806; fracture (the act):—breaking.

g2801.d: κλάσμα klásma, klas'-mah; from G2806; a piece (bit):—broken, fragment.

g2803.d: Κλαυδία Klaudía, klow-dee'-ah; feminine of G2804; Claudia, a Christian woman:—Claudia.

g2804.d: Κλαύδιος Klaúdios, klow'-dee-os; of Latin origin; Claudius, the name of two Romans:—Claudius.

g2805.d: κλαυθμός klauthmós, klowth-mos'; from G2799; lamentation:—wailing, weeping, × wept.

g2806.d: κλάω kláō, klah'-o; a primary verb; to break (specially, of bread):—break.

g2807.d:
κλείς kleís, klice; from G2808; a key (as shutting a lock), literally or
 figuratively:—key.

g2808.d: κλείω kleíō, kli'-o; a primary verb; to close (literally or figuratively):—shut (up).

g2809.d:
κλέμμα klémma, klem'-mah; from G2813; stealing (properly, the thing stolen, but used of the
 act):—theft.

g281.d:
ἀμήν amḗn, am-ane'; of Hebrew origin (H543); properly, firm, i.e. (figuratively)
 trustworthy; adverbially, surely (often as interjection, so be
 it):—amen, verily.
g281.r: Of Hebrew origin אָמֵן (H543)|English: amen truly, so be it

g2810.d:
Κλεόπας Kleópas, kleh-op'-as; probably contracted from Κλεόπατρος Kleópatros (compound of G2811 and G3962); 
 Cleopas, a Christian:—Cleopas.
g2810.r: Probably contracted from Kleopatros (compound of κλέος (G2811) and πατήρ (G3962))|English: glory

g2811.d: κλέος kléos, kleh'-os; from a shorter form of G2564; renown (as if being called):—glory.
g2811.r: From a shorter form of καλέω (G2564)|English: call, bid, be so named, named, misc

g2812.d:
κλέπτης kléptēs, klep'-tace; from G2813; a stealer (literally or figuratively):—thief. Compare
 G3027.

g2813.d: κλέπτω kléptō, klep'-to; a primary verb; to filch:—steal.

g2814.d: κλῆμα klēma, kaly'-mah; from G2806; a limb or shoot (as if broken off):—branch.

g2815.d:
Κλήμης Klḗmēs, klay'-mace; of Latin origin; merciful; Clemes (i.e. Clemens), a
 Christian:—Clement.

g2816.d:
κληρονομέω klēronoméō, klay-ron-om-eh'-o; from G2818; to be an heir to (literally or figuratively):—be heir,
 (obtain by) inherit(-ance).

g2817.d:
κληρονομία klēronomía, klay-ron-om-ee'-ah; from G2818; heirship, i.e. (concretely) a patrimony or (genitive case)
 a possession:—inheritance.

g2818.d:
κληρονόμος klēronómos, klay-ron-om'-os; from G2819 and the base of G3551 (in its original sense of partitioning,
 i.e. (reflexively) getting by apportionment); a sharer by lot, i.e.
 inheritor (literally or figuratively); by implication, a
 possessor:—heir.
g2818.r: From κλῆρος (G2819) and the base of νόμος (G3551) (in its original sense of partitioning, i.e. [reflexively] getting by apportionment)|English: lot, part, inheritance, heritage

g2819.d:
κλῆρος klēros, klay'-ros; probably from G2806 (through the idea of using bits of wood, etc., for
 the purpose; a die (for drawing chances); by implication, a portion
 (as if so secured); by extension, an acquisition (especially a
 patrimony, figuratively):—heritage, inheritance, lot, part.
g2819.r: Probably from κλάω (G2806) (through the idea of using bits of wood, etc., for the purpose)|English: break

g282.d:
ἀμήτωρ amḗtōr, am-ay'-tore; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3384; motherless, i.e. of unknown
 maternity:—without mother.
g282.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and μήτηρ (G3384)|English: Alpha

g2820.d:
κληρόω klēróō, klay-ro'-o; from G2819; to allot, i.e. (figuratively) to assign (a
 privilege):—obtain an inheritance.
g2820.r: From κλῆρος (G2819)|English: lot, part, inheritance, heritage

g2821.d: κλῆσις klēsis, klay'-sis; from a shorter form of G2564; an invitation (figuratively):—calling.
g2821.r: From a shorter form of καλέω (G2564)|English: call, bid, be so named, named, misc

g2822.d:
κλητός klētós, klay-tos'; from the same as G2821; invited, i.e. appointed, or (specially), a
 saint:—called.
g2822.r: From the same as κλῆσις (G2821)|English: calling, vocation

g2823.d: κλίβανος klíbanos, klib'-an-os; of uncertain derivation; an earthen pot used for baking in:—oven.

g2824.d:
κλίμα klíma, klee'-mah; from G2827; a slope, i.e. (specially) a "clime" or tract of
 country:—part, region.
g2824.r: From κλίνω (G2827)|English: lay, bow, bow down, be far spent, turn to fight, wear away

g2825.d:
†κλίνη klínē, klee'-nay; from G2827; a couch (for sleep, sickness, sitting or eating):—bed,
 table.
g2825.r: From κλίνω (G2827)|English: lay, bow, bow down, be far spent, turn to fight, wear away

g2826.d:
κλινίδιον klinídion, klin-id'-ee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G2825; a pallet or little
 couch:—bed.
g2826.r: From a presumed derivative of κλίνη (G2825)|English: bed, table

g2827.d:
κλίνω klínō, klee'-no; a primary verb; to slant or slope, i.e. incline or recline (literally
 or figuratively):—bow (down), be far spent, lay, turn to flight, wear
 away.

g2828.d:
κλισία klisía, klee-see'-ah; from a derivative of G2827; properly, reclination, i.e. (concretely and
 specially), a party at a meal:—company.
g2828.r: From a derivative of κλίνω (G2827)|English: lay, bow, bow down, be far spent, turn to fight, wear away

g2829.d: κλοπή klopḗ, klop-ay'; from G2813; stealing:—theft.

g283.d:
ἀμίαντος amíantos, am-ee'-an-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a derivative of G3392; unsoiled,
 i.e. (figuratively) pure:—undefiled.
g283.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of μιαίνω (G3392)|English: Alpha

g2830.d:
κλύδων klýdōn, kloo'-dohn; from κλύζω klýzō (to billow or dash over); a surge of the sea (literally or
 figuratively):—raging, wave.
g2830.r: From kluzo (to billow or dash over)|

g2831.d:
κλυδωνίζομαι klydōnízomai, kloo-do-nid'-zom-ahee; middle voice from G2830; to surge, i.e. (figuratively) to
 fluctuate:—toss to and fro.
g2831.r: Middle voice from κλύδων (G2830)|English: raging, wave

g2832.d:
Κλωπᾶς Klōpâs, klo-pas'; of Chaldee origin (corresponding to H256); Clopas, an
 Israelite:—Cleophas.
g2832.r: Of Aramaic origin (corresponding to אַחְאָב (H256))|English: Ahab

g2833.d:
κνήθω knḗthō, knay'-tho; from a primary κνάω knáō (to scrape); to scratch, i.e. (by implication) to
 tickle:—X itching.

g2834.d: Κνίδος Knídos, knee'-dos; probably of foreign origin; Cnidus, a place in Asia Minor:—Cnidus.

g2835.d: κοδράντης kodrántēs, kod-ran'-tace; of Latin origin; a quadrans, i.e. the fourth part of an as:—farthing.

g2836.d:
κοιλία koilía, koy-lee'-ah; from κοῖλος koîlos ("hollow"); a cavity, i.e. (especially) the abdomen; by
 implication, the matrix; figuratively, the heart:—belly, womb.

g2837.d:
κοιμάω koimáō, koy-mah'-o; from G2749; to put to sleep, i.e. (passively or reflexively) to
 slumber; figuratively, to decease:—(be a-, fall a-, fall on) sleep,
 be dead.
g2837.r: From κεῖμαι (G2749)|English: lie, be laid, be set, be appointed, be, be made, laid up, there

g2838.d: κοίμησις koímēsis, koy'-may-sis; from G2837; sleeping, i.e. (by implication) repose:—taking of rest.
g2838.r: From κοιμάω (G2837)|English: sleep, fall asleep, be asleep, fall on sleep, be dead

g2839.d:
κοινός koinós, koy-nos'; probably from G4862; common, i.e. (literally) shared by all or several,
 or (ceremonially) profane:—common, defiled, unclean, unholy.
g2839.r: Probably from σύν (G4862)|English: with, beside, accompany

g284.d: Ἀμιναδάβ Aminadáb, am-ee-nad-ab'; of Hebrew origin (H5992); Aminadab, an Israelite:—Aminadab.

g2840.d:
κοινόω koinóō, koy-no'-o; from G2839; to make (or consider) profane (ceremonially):—call common,
 defile, pollute, unclean.
g2840.r: From κοινός (G2839)|English: common, unclean, defiled, unholy

g2841.d:
κοινωνέω koinōnéō, koy-no-neh'-o; from G2844; to share with others (objectively or
 subjectively):—communicate, distribute, be partaker.
g2841.r: From κοινωνός (G2844)|English: partaker, partner, fellowship, companion

g2842.d:
κοινωνία koinōnía, koy-nohn-ee'-ah; from G2844; partnership, i.e. (literally) participation, or (social)
 intercourse, or (pecuniary) benefaction:—(to) communicate(-ation),
 communion, (contri-)distribution, fellowship.
g2842.r: From κοινωνός (G2844)|English: partaker, partner, fellowship, companion

g2843.d:
κοινωνικός koinōnikós, koy-no-nee-kos'; from G2844; communicative, i.e. (pecuniarily) liberal:—willing to
 communicate.
g2843.r: From κοινωνός (G2844)|English: partaker, partner, fellowship, companion

g2844.d:
κοινωνός koinōnós, koy-no-nos'; from G2839; a sharer, i.e. associate:—companion, × fellowship,
 partaker, partner.
g2844.r: From κοινός (G2839)|English: common, unclean, defiled, unholy

g2845.d:
κοίτη koítē, koy'-tay; from G2749; a couch; by extension, cohabitation; by implication, the
 male sperm:—bed, chambering, × conceive.
g2845.r: From κεῖμαι (G2749)|English: lie, be laid, be set, be appointed, be, be made, laid up, there

g2846.d: κοιτών koitṓn, koy-tone'; from G2845; a bedroom:—+ chamberlain.

g2847.d:
κόκκινος kókkinos, kok'-kee-nos; from G2848 (from the kernel-shape of the insect); 
 crimson-colored:—scarlet (colour, coloured).
g2847.r: From κόκκος (G2848) (from the kernel-shape of the insect)|English: grain, corn

g2848.d: κόκκος kókkos, kok'-kos; apparently a primary word; a kernel of seed:—corn, grain.

g2849.d:
κολάζω kolázō, kol-ad'-zo; from κόλος kólos (dwarf); properly, to curtail, i.e. (figuratively) to
 chastise (or reserve for infliction):—punish.

g285.d: ἄμμος ámmos, am'-mos; perhaps from G260; sand (as heaped on the beach):—sand.
g285.r: Perhaps from ἅμα (G260)|English: together, withal, with, and, misc

g2850.d: κολακεία kolakeía, kol-ak-i'-ah; from a derivative of κόλαξ kólax (a fawner); flattery:—× flattering.
g2850.r: From a derivative of kolax (a fawner)|

g2851.d: κόλασις kólasis, kol'-as-is; from G2849; penal infliction:—punishment, torment.

g2852.d: κολαφίζω kolaphízō, kol-af-id'-zo; from a derivative of the base of G2849; to rap with the fist:—buffet.
g2852.r: From a derivative of the base of κολάζω (G2849)|English: punish

g2853.d:
κολλάω kolláō, kol-lah'-o; from κόλλα kólla ("glue"); to glue, i.e. (passively or reflexively) to stick
 (figuratively):—cleave, join (self), keep company.

g2854.d:
†κολλούριον kolloúrion, kol-loo'-ree-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of κολλύρα kollýra (a cake; prob akin to the
 base of G2853); properly, a poultice (as made of or in the form of
 crackers), i.e. (by analogy) a plaster:—eyesalve.
g2854.r: From a presumed derivative of kollura (a cake - prob akin to the base of κολλάω (G2853))|English: join (one's) self, cleave, be joined, keep company, vr reach

g2855.d:
κολλυβιστής kollybistḗs, kol-loo-bis-tace'; from a presumed derivative of κόλλυβος kóllybos (a small coin; probably akin to
 G2854); a coin-dealer:—(money-)changer.
g2855.r: From a presumed derivative of kollubos (a small coin - probably akin to κολλούριον (G2854))|English: eyesalve

g2856.d:
κολοβόω kolobóō, kol-ob-o'-o; from a derivative of the base of G2849; to dock, i.e. (figuratively)
 abridge:—shorten.
g2856.r: From a derivative of the base of κολάζω (G2849)|English: punish

g2857.d:
†Κολοσσαί Kolossaí, kol-os-sah'-ee; apparently feminine plural of kolossos ("colossal"); Colossæ, a place
 in Asia Minor:—Colosse.

g2859.d:
κόλπος kólpos, kol'-pos; apparently a primary word; the bosom; by analogy, a bay:—bosom,
 creek.

g286.d: ἀμνός amnós, am-nos'; apparently a primary word; a lamb:—lamb.

g2860.d: κολυμβάω kolymbáō, kol-oom-bah'-o; from κόλυμβος kólymbos (a diver); to plunge into water:—swim.

g2861.d:
κολυμβήθρα kolymbḗthra, kol-oom-bay'-thrah; from G2860; 

 a diving-place, i.e. pond for bathing (or swimming):—pool.

g2862.d: κολωνία kolōnía, kol-o-nee'-ah; of Latin origin; a Roman "colony" for veterans:—colony.

g2863.d: κομάω komáō, kom-ah'-o; from G2864; to wear tresses of hair:—have long hair.

g2864.d:
κόμη kómē, kom'-ay; apparently from the same as G2865; the hair of the head (locks, as
 ornamental, and thus differing from G2359; which properly denotes
 merely the scalp):—hair.
g2864.r: Apparently from the same as κομίζω (G2865)|English: receive, bring

g2865.r: From a primary komeo (to tend, i.e. take care of)|

g2866.d:
κομψότερον kompsóteron, komp-sot'-er-on; neuter comparative of a derivative of the base of 2865 (meaning,
 properly, well dressed, i.e. nice); figuratively, convalescent:—+
 began to amend.
g2866.r: Neuter comparative of a derivative of the base of κομίζω (G2865) (meaning properly, well dressed, i.e. nice)|English: receive, bring

g2867.d: κονιάω koniáō, kon-ee-ah'-o; from κονία konía (dust; by analogy, lime); to whitewash:—whiten.

g2868.d:
κονιορτός koniortós, kon-ee-or-tos'; from the base of G2867 and ornumi (to "rouse"); pulverulence (as blown
 about):—dust.
g2868.r: From the base of κονιάω (G2867) and ornumi (to "rouse")|English: whited

g2869.d: κοπάζω kopázō, kop-ad'-zo; from G2873; to tire, i.e. (figuratively) to relax:—cease.

g287.d: ἀμοιβή amoibḗ, am-oy-bay'; from ἀμείβω ameíbō (to exchange); requital:—requite.

g2870.d: κοπετός kopetós, kop-et-os'; from G2875; mourning (properly, by beating the breast):—lamentation.
g2870.r: From κόπτω (G2875)|English: bewail, lament, cut down, wail, mourn

g2871.d: κοπή kopḗ, kop-ay'; from G2875; cutting, i.e. carnage:—slaughter.
g2871.r: From κόπτω (G2875)|English: bewail, lament, cut down, wail, mourn

g2872.d:
κοπιάω kopiáō, kop-ee-ah'-o; from a derivative of G2873; to feel fatigue; by implication, to work
 hard:—(bestow) labour, toil, be wearied.
g2872.r: From a derivative of κόπος (G2873)|English: labour, trouble, weariness

g2873.d:
κόπος kópos, kop'-os; from G2875; a cut, i.e. (by analogy) toil (as reducing the strength),
 literally or figuratively; by implication, pains:—labour, + trouble,
 weariness.
g2873.r: From κόπτω (G2875)|English: bewail, lament, cut down, wail, mourn

g2874.d: †κοπρία kopría, kop-ree'-ah; from κόπρος kópros (ordure; perhaps akin to G2875); manure:—dung(-hill).
g2874.r: From kopros (ordure, perhaps akin to κόπτω (G2875))|English: bewail, lament, cut down, wail, mourn

g2875.d:
κόπτω kóptō, kop'-to; a primary verb; to "chop"; specially, to beat the breast in
 grief:—cut down, lament, mourn, (be-)wail. Compare the base of G5114.

g2876.d: κόραξ kórax, kor'-ax; perhaps from G2880; a crow (from its voracity):—raven.
g2876.r: Perhaps from κορέννυμι (G2880)|English: eat enough, full

g2877.d:
κοράσιον korásion, kor-as'-ee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of κόρη kórē (a maiden); a (little)
 girl:—damsel, maid.
g2877.r: From a presumed derivative of kore (a maiden)|

g2878.d:
†κορβᾶν korbân, kor-ban'; of Hebrew and Chaldee origin respectively (H7133); a votive offering
 and the offering; a consecrated present (to the Temple fund); by
 extension (the latter term) the Treasury itself, i.e. the room where
 the contribution boxes stood:—Corban, treasury.
g2878.r: Of Hebrew and Aramaic origin respectively קָרְבָּן (H7133)|English: offering, oblation, offered, sacrifice

g2879.d: Κορέ Koré, kor-eh'; of Hebrew origin (H7141); Core (i.e. Korach), an Israelite:—Core.

g288.d:
ἄμπελος ámpelos, am'-pel-os; probably from the base of G297 and that of G257; a vine (as coiling
 about a support):—vine.
g288.r: Probably from the base of ἀμφότεροι (G297) and that of ἅλων (G257)|English: both

g2880.d: κορέννυμι korénnymi, kor-en'-noo-mee; a primary verb; to cram, i.e. glut or sate:—eat enough, full.

g2881.d: Κορίνθιος Korínthios, kor-in'-thee-os; from G2882; a Corinthian, i.e. inhabitant of Corinth:—Corinthian.

g2882.d: Κόρινθος Kórinthos, kor'-in-thos; of uncertain derivation; Corinthus, a city of Greece:—Corinth.

g2883.d: Κορνήλιος Kornḗlios, kor-nay'-lee-os; of Latin origin; Cornelius, a Roman:—Cornelius.

g2884.d: κόρος kóros, kor'-os; of Hebrew origin (H3734); a cor, i.e. a specific measure:—measure.
g2884.r: Of Hebrew origin כֹּר (H3734)|English: measure, cor

g2885.d:
κοσμέω kosméō, kos-meh'-o; from G2889; to put in proper order, i.e. decorate (literally or
 figuratively); specially, to snuff (a wick):—adorn, garnish, trim.

g2886.d:
κοσμικός kosmikós, kos-mee-kos'; from G2889 (in its secondary sense); terrene ("cosmic"), literally
 (mundane) or figuratively (corrupt):—worldly.
g2886.r: From κόσμος (G2889) (in its secondary sense)|English: world, adorning

g2887.d:
κόσμιος kósmios, kos'-mee-os; from G2889 (in its primary sense); orderly, i.e. decorous:—of good
 behaviour, modest.
g2887.r: From κόσμος (G2889) (in its primary sense)|English: world, adorning

g2888.d: κοσμοκράτωρ kosmokrátōr, kos-mok-fat'-ore; from G2889 and G2902; a world-ruler, an epithet of Satan:—ruler.
g2888.r: From κόσμος (G2889) and κρατέω (G2902)|English: world, adorning

g2889.r: Probably from the base of κομίζω (G2865)|English: receive, bring

g289.d: ἀμπελουργός ampelourgós, am-pel-oor-gos'; from G288 and G2041; a vine-worker, i.e. pruner:—vine-dresser.

g2890.d: Κούαρτος Koúartos, koo'-ar-tos; of Latin origin (fourth); Quartus, a Christian:—Quartus.

g2891.d: †κοῦμι koûmi, koo'-mee; of Chaldee origin (H6966); cumi (i.e. rise!):—cumi.
g2891.r: Of Aramaic origin קוּם (H6966)|English: set up, arise, stand, set, establish, rise up, appointeth, stood by, made, rise

g2892.d: κουστωδία koustōdía, koos-to-dee'-ah; of Latin origin; "custody", i.e. a Roman sentry:—watch.

g2893.d: κουφίζω kouphízō, koo-fid'-zo; from κοῦφος koûphos (light in weight); to unload:—lighten.

g2894.d: κόφινος kóphinos, kof'-ee-nos; of uncertain derivation; a (small) basket:—basket.

g2895.d: †κράββατος krábbatos, krab'-bat-os; probably of foreign origin; a mattress:—bed.

g2896.d:
κράζω krázō, krad'-zo; a primary verb; properly, to "croak" (as a raven) or scream, i.e.
 (genitive case) to call aloud (shriek, exclaim, intreat):—cry (out).

g2897.d:
κραιπάλη kraipálē, krahee-pal'-ay; probably from the same as G726; properly, a headache (as a seizure of
 pain) from drunkenness, i.e. (by implication) a debauch (by analogy, a
 glut):—surfeiting.
g2897.r: Probably from the same as ἁρπάζω (G726)|English: catch up, take by force, catch away, pluck, catch, pull

g2898.d:
κρανίον kraníon, kran-ee'-on; diminutive of a derivative of the base of G2768; a skull
 ("cranium"):—Calvary, skull.
g2898.r: Diminutive of a derivative of the base of κέρας (G2768)|English: horn

g2899.d:
κράσπεδον kráspedon, kras'-ped-on; of uncertain derivation; a margin, i.e. (specially), a fringe or
 tassel:—border, hem.

g29.d:
ἀγγαρεύω angareúō, ang-ar-yew'-o; of foreign origin (compare H104); properly, to be a courier, i.e. (by
 implication) to press into public service:—compel (to go).
g29.r: Of foreign origin, cf אִגְּרָא (H104)|English: letter

g290.d: ἀμπελών ampelṓn, am-pel-ohn'; from G288; a vineyard:—vineyard.

g2900.d: κραταιός krataiós, krat-ah-yos'; from G2904; powerful:—mighty.
g2900.r: From κράτος (G2904)|English: power, dominion, strength, mighty

g2901.d:
κραταιόω krataióō, krat-ah-yo'-o; from G2900; to empower, i.e. (passively) increase in vigor:—be
 strengthened, be (wax) strong.

g2902.d:
κρατέω kratéō, krat-eh'-o; from G2904; to use strength, i.e. seize or retain (literally or
 figuratively):—hold (by, fast), keep, lay hand (hold) on, obtain,
 retain, take (by).
g2902.r: From κράτος (G2904)|English: power, dominion, strength, mighty

g2903.d:
κράτιστος krátistos, krat'-is-tos; superlative of a derivative of G2904; strongest, i.e. (in dignity) very
 honorable:—most excellent (noble).
g2903.r: Superlative of a derivative of κράτος (G2904)|English: power, dominion, strength, mighty

g2904.d:
κράτος krátos, krat'-os; perhaps a primary word; vigor ("great") (literally or
 figuratively):—dominion, might(-ily), power, strength.

g2905.d: κραυγάζω kraugázō, krow-gad'-zo; from G2906; to clamor:—cry out.

g2906.d:
κραυγή kraugḗ, krow-gay'; from G2896; an outcry (in notification, tumult or grief):—clamour,
 cry(-ing).

g2907.d: κρέας kréas, kreh'-as; perhaps a primary word; (butcher's) meat:—flesh.

g2909.d:
κρείττων kreíttōn, krite'-tohn; comparative of a derivative of G2904; stronger, i.e. (figuratively)
 better, i.e. nobler:—best, better.
g2909.r: Comparative of a derivative of κράτος (G2904)|English: power, dominion, strength, mighty

g291.d:
†Ἀμπλίας Amplías, am-plee'-as; contracted for Latin ampliatus (enlarged); Amplias, a Roman
 Christian:—Amplias.

g2910.d: κρεμάννυμι kremánnymi, krem-an'-noo-mee; a prolonged form of a primary verb; to hang:—hang.
g2910.r: A prolonged form of a primary verb|

g2911.d: κρημνός krēmnós, krame-nos'; from G2910; overhanging, i.e. a precipice:—steep place.

g2912.d: Κρής Krḗs, krace; from G2914; a Cretan, i.e. inhabitant of Crete:—Crete, Cretian.

g2913.d:
Κρήσκης Krḗskēs, krace'-kace; of Latin origin; growing; Cresces (i.e. Crescens), a
 Christian:—Crescens.

g2914.d:
Κρήτη Krḗtē, kray'-tay; of uncertain derivation; Crete, an island in the
 Mediterranean:—Crete.

g2915.d: κριθή krithḗ, kree-thay'; of uncertain derivation; barley:—barley.

g2916.d: κρίθινος kríthinos, kree'-thee-nos; from G2915; consisting of barley:—barley.

g2917.d:
κρίμα kríma, kree'-mah; from G2919; a decision (the function or the effect, for or against
 ("crime")):—avenge, condemned, condemnation, damnation, + go to law,
 judgment.
g2917.r: From κρίνω (G2919)|English: judge, determine, condemn, go to law, call in question, esteem, misc

g2918.d: κρίνον krínon, kree'-non; perhaps a prim word; a lily:—lily.

g2919.d:
κρίνω krínō, kree'-no; properly, to distinguish, i.e. decide (mentally or judicially); by
 implication, to try, condemn, punish:—avenge, conclude, condemn,
 damn, decree, determine, esteem, judge, go to (sue at the) law,
 ordain, call in question, sentence to, think.

g292.d:
†ἀμύνομαι amýnomai, am-oo'-nom-ahee; middle voice of a primary verb; to ward off (for oneself), i.e.
 protect:—defend.
g292.r: Middle voice of a primary verb|

g2920.d:
κρίσις krísis, kree'-sis; decision (subjectively or objectively, for or against); by
 extension, a tribunal; by implication, justice (especially, divine
 law):—accusation, condemnation, damnation, judgment.

g2921.d: Κρίσπος Kríspos, kris'-pos; of Latin origin; "crisp"; Crispus, a Corinthian:—Crispus.

g2922.d:
κριτήριον kritḗrion, kree-tay'-ree-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G2923; a rule of judging
 ("criterion"), i.e. (by implication) a tribunal:—to judge, judgment
 (seat).
g2922.r: From a presumed derivative of κριτής (G2923)|English: judge, Judge

g2923.d: κριτής kritḗs, kree-tace'; from G2919; a judge (genitive case or specially):—judge.
g2923.r: From κρίνω (G2919)|English: judge, determine, condemn, go to law, call in question, esteem, misc

g2924.d: κριτικός kritikós, krit-ee-kos'; from G2923; decisive ("critical"), i.e. discriminative:—discerner.

g2925.d: κρούω kroúō, kroo'-o; apparently a primary verb; to rap:—knock.

g2926.d: κρύπτη krýptē, kroop-tay'; feminine of G2927; a hidden place, i.e. cellar ("crypt"):—secret.
g2926.r: From κρυπτός (G2927)|English: secret, hid, hidden, inwardly

g2927.d: κρυπτός kryptós, kroop-tos'; from G2928; concealed, i.e. private:—hid(-den), inward(-ly), secret.
g2927.r: From κρύπτω (G2928)|English: hide, hide (one's) self, keep secret, secretly, hidden

g2928.d:
κρύπτω krýptō, kroop'-to; a primary verb; to conceal (properly, by covering):—hide (self), keep
 secret, secret(-ly).

g2929.d:
κρυσταλλίζω krystallízō, kroos-tal-lid'-zo; from G2930; to make (i.e. intransitively, resemble) ice
 ("crystallize"):—be clear as crystal.

g293.d:
ἀμφίβληστρον amphíblēstron, am-fib'-lace-tron; from a compound of the base of G297 and G906; a (fishing) net (as thrown
 about the fish):—net.
g293.r: From a compound of the base of ἀμφότεροι (G297) and βάλλω (G906)|English: both

g2930.d:
κρύσταλλος krýstallos, kroos'-tal-los; from a derivative of κρύος krýos (frost); ice, i.e. (by analogy) rock
 "crystal":—crystal.

g2931.d: κρυφῆ kryphē, kroo-fay'; adverb from G2928; privately:—in secret.
g2931.r: From κρύπτω (G2928)|English: hide, hide (one's) self, keep secret, secretly, hidden

g2932.d:
κτάομαι ktáomai, ktah'-om-ahee; a primary verb; to get, i.e. acquire (by any means; own):—obtain,
 possess, provide, purchase.

g2933.d: κτῆμα ktēma, ktay'-mah; from G2932; an acquirement, i.e. estate:—possession.
g2933.r: From κτάομαι (G2932)|English: possess, purchase, provide, obtain

g2934.d: κτῆνος ktēnos, ktay'-nos; from G2932; property, i.e. (specially) a domestic animal:—beast.
g2934.r: From κτάομαι (G2932)|English: possess, purchase, provide, obtain

g2935.d: κτήτωρ ktḗtōr, ktay'-tore; from G2932; an owner:—possessor.
g2935.r: From κτάομαι (G2932)|English: possess, purchase, provide, obtain

g2936.d:
κτίζω ktízō, ktid'-zo; probably akin to G2932 (through the idea of proprietorship of the
 manufacturer); to fabricate, i.e. found (form originally):—create,
 Creator, make.
g2936.r: Probably akin to κτάομαι (G2932) (through the idea of proprietor-ship of the manufacturer)|English: possess, purchase, provide, obtain

g2937.d:
κτίσις ktísis, ktis'-is; from G2936; original formation (properly, the act; by implication, the
 thing, literally or figuratively):—building, creation, creature,
 ordinance.

g2938.d:
κτίσμα ktísma, ktis'-mah; from G2936; an original formation (concretely), i.e. product (created
 thing):—creature.

g2939.d: †κτίστης ktístēs, ktis-tace'; from G2936; a founder, i.e. God (as author of all things):—Creator.

g294.d: †ἀμφιέννυμι amphiénnymi, am-fee-en'-noo-mee; from the base of G297 and ἕννυμι hénnymi (to invest); to enrobe:—clothe.
g294.r: From the base of ἀμφότεροι (G297) and hennumi (to invest)|English: both

g2940.d:
κυβεία kybeía, koo-bi'-ah; from κύβος kýbos (a "cube", i.e. die for playing); gambling, i.e.
 (figuratively) artifice or fraud:—sleight.
g2940.r: From kubos (a "cube", i.e. die for playing)|

g2941.d:
κυβέρνησις kybérnēsis, koo-ber'-nay-sis; from κυβερνάω kybernáō (of Latin origin, to steer); pilotage, i.e.
 (figuratively) directorship (in the church):—government.
g2941.r: From kubernao (of Latin origin, to steer)|

g2942.d:
κυβερνήτης kybernḗtēs, koo-ber-nay'-tace; from the same as G2941; helmsman, i.e. (by implication)
 captain:—(ship) master.
g2942.r: From the same as κυβέρνησις (G2941)|English: government

g2943.d:
κυκλόθεν kyklóthen, koo-kloth'-en; adverb from the same as G2945; from the circle, i.e. all
 around:—(round) about.
g2943.r: From the same as κύκλῳ (G2945)|English: round about, round

g2944.d:
†κυκλόω kyklóō, koo-klo'-o; from the same as G2945; to encircle, i.e. surround:—compass (about),
 come (stand) round about.
g2944.r: From the same as κύκλῳ (G2945)|English: round about, round

g2945.d:
†κύκλῳ kýklōi, koo'-klo; as if dative case of κύκλος kýklos (a ring, "cycle"; akin to G2947); i.e. in a
 circle (by implication, of G1722), i.e. (adverbially) all
 around:—round about.
g2945.r: As if dative case of kuklos (a ring, "cycle" - akin to κυλίω (G2947))|English: wallow

g2946.d: †κύλισμα kýlisma, koo'-lis-mah; from G2947; a wallow (the effect of rolling), i.e. filth:—wallowing.

g2947.d:
†κυλιόω kylióō, koo-lee-o'-o; from the base of G2949 (through the idea of circularity; compare G2945,
 G1507); to roll about:—wallow.
g2947.r: From base of κῦμα (G2949) (through the idea of circularity, cf κύκλῳ (G2945), εἱλίσσω (G1507))|English: wave

g2948.d:
κυλλός kyllós, kool-los'; from the same as G2947; rocking about, i.e. crippled (maimed, in feet
 or hands):—maimed.
g2948.r: From the same as κυλίω (G2947)|English: wallow

g2949.d:
κῦμα kŷma, koo'-mah; from κύω kýō (to swell (with young), i.e. bend, curve); a billow (as
 bursting or toppling):—wave.
g2949.r: From kuo (to swell [with young], i.e bend, curve)|

g295.d:
Ἀμφίπολις Amphípolis, am-fip'-ol-is; from the base of G297 and G4172; a city surrounded by a river;
 Amphipolis, a place in Macedonia:—Amphipolis.
g295.r: From the base of ἀμφότεροι (G297) and πόλις (G4172)|English: both

g2950.d:
κύμβαλον kýmbalon, koom'-bal-on; from a derivative of the base of G2949; a "cymbal" (as
 hollow):—cymbal.
g2950.r: From a derivative of the base of κῦμα (G2949)|English: wave

g2951.d: κύμινον kýminon, koo'-min-on; of foreign origin (compare H3646); dill or fennel ("cummin"):—cummin.
g2951.r: Of foreign origin, cf כַּמֹּן (H3646)|English: cummin

g2952.d: κυνάριον kynárion, koo-nar'-ee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G2965; a puppy:—dog.
g2952.r: From a presumed derivative of κύων (G2965)|English: dog

g2953.d: Κύπριος Kýprios, koo'-pree-os; from G2954; a Cyprian (Cypriot), i.e. inhabitant of Cyprus:—of Cyprus.

g2954.d: Κύπρος Kýpros, koo'-pros; of uncertain origin; Cyprus, an island in the Mediterranean:—Cyprus.

g2955.d: †κύπτω kýptō, koop'-to; probably from the base of G2949; to bend forward:—stoop (down).
g2955.r: Probably from the base of κῦμα (G2949)|English: wave

g2956.d:
Κυρηναῖος Kyrēnaîos, koo-ray-nah'-yos; from G2957; i.e. Cyrenæan, i.e. inhabitant of Cyrene:—of Cyrene,
 Cyrenian.

g2957.d: Κυρήνη Kyrḗnē, koo-ray'-nay; of uncertain derivation; Cyrene, a region of Africa:—Cyrene.

g2958.d: Κυρήνιος Kyrḗnios, koo-ray'-nee-os; of Latin origin; Cyrenius (i.e. Quirinus), a Roman:—Cyrenius.

g2959.d: Κυρία Kyría, koo-ree'-ah; feminine of G2962; Cyria, a Christian woman:—lady.
g2959.r: From κύριος (G2962)|English: Lord, lord, master, sir, Sir, misc

g296.d:
ἄμφοδον ámphodon, am'-fod-on; from the base of G297 and G3598; a fork in the road:—where two ways
 meet.
g296.r: From the base of ἀμφότεροι (G297) and ὁδός (G3598)|English: both

g2960.d: κυριακός kyriakós, koo-ree-ak-os'; from G2962; belonging to the Lord (Jehovah or Jesus):—Lord's.
g2960.r: From κύριος (G2962)|English: Lord, lord, master, sir, Sir, misc

g2961.d:
κυριεύω kyrieúō, ko-ree-yoo'-o; from G2962; to rule:—have dominion over, lord, be lord of, exercise
 lordship over.
g2961.r: From κύριος (G2962)|English: Lord, lord, master, sir, Sir, misc

g2962.d:
κύριος kýrios, koo'-ree-os; from κῦρος kŷros (supremacy); supreme in authority, i.e. (as noun)
 controller; by implication, Master (as a respectful title):—God,
 Lord, master, Sir.

g2963.d:
κυριότης kyriótēs, koo-ree-ot'-ace; from G2962; mastery, i.e. (concretely and collectively)
 rulers:—dominion, government.
g2963.r: From κύριος (G2962)|English: Lord, lord, master, sir, Sir, misc

g2964.d: κυρόω kyróō, koo-ro'-o; from the same as G2962; to make authoritative, i.e. ratify:—confirm.
g2964.r: From the same as κύριος (G2962)|English: Lord, lord, master, sir, Sir, misc

g2965.d: κύων kýōn, koo'-ohn; a primary word; a dog ("hound") (literally or figuratively):—dog.

g2966.d: κῶλον kōlon, ko'-lon; from the base of G2849; a limb of the body (as if lopped):—carcase.
g2966.r: From the base of κολάζω (G2849)|English: punish

g2967.d:
κωλύω kōlýō, ko-loo'-o; from the base of G2849; to estop, i.e. prevent (by word or
 act):—forbid, hinder, keep from, let, not suffer, withstand.
g2967.r: From the base of κολάζω (G2849)|English: punish

g2968.d: κώμη kṓmē, ko'-may; from G2749; a hamlet (as if laid down):—town, village.
g2968.r: From κεῖμαι (G2749)|English: lie, be laid, be set, be appointed, be, be made, laid up, there

g2969.d: κωμόπολις kōmópolis, ko-mop'-ol-is; from G2968 and G4172; an unwalled city:—town.
g2969.r: From κώμη (G2968) and πόλις (G4172)|English: village, town

g297.d: ἀμφότερος amphóteros, am-fot'-er-os; comparative of ἀμφί amphí (around); (in plural) both:—both.

g2970.d: κῶμος kōmos, ko'-mos; from G2749; a carousal (as if letting loose):—revelling, rioting.
g2970.r: From κεῖμαι (G2749)|English: lie, be laid, be set, be appointed, be, be made, laid up, there

g2971.d:
κώνωψ kṓnōps, ko'-nopes; apparently a derivative of the base of G2759 and a derivative of G3700; 
 a mosquito (from its stinging proboscis):—gnat.
g2971.r: Apparently a derivative of the base of κέντρον (G2759) and a derivative of ὀπτάνομαι (G3700)|English: sting, prick

g2972.d: Κώς Kṓs, koce; of uncertain origin; Cos, an island in the Mediterranean:—Cos.

g2973.d:
Κωσάμ Kōsám, ko-sam'; of Hebrew origin (compare H7081); Cosam (i.e. Kosam) an
 Israelite:—Cosam.
g2973.r: Of Hebrew origin cf קֶסֶם (H7081)|English: divination, witchcraft, divine sentence

g2974.d:
κωφός kōphós, ko-fos'; from G2875; blunted, i.e. (figuratively) of hearing (deaf) or speech
 (dumb):—deaf, dumb, speechless.
g2974.r: From κόπτω (G2875)|English: bewail, lament, cut down, wail, mourn

g2975.d:
λαγχάνω lanchánō, lang-khan'-o; a prolonged form of a primary verb, which is only used as an alternate
 in certain tenses; to lot, i.e. determine (by implication, receive)
 especially by lot:—his lot be, cast lots, obtain.
g2975.r: A prolonged form of a primary verb, which is only used as an alternate in certain tenses|

g2976.d:
Λάζαρος Lázaros, lad'-zar-os; probably of Hebrew origin (H499); Lazarus (i.e. Elazar), the name of
 two Israelites (one imaginary):—Lazarus.
g2976.r: Probably of Hebrew origin אֶלְעָזָר (H499)|English: Eleazar

g2977.d: †λάθρα láthra, lath'-rah; adverb from G2990; privately:—privily, secretly.
g2977.r: From λανθάνω (G2990)|English: be hid, be ignorant of, unawares

g2978.d: λαῖλαψ laîlaps, lah'-ee-laps; of uncertain derivation; a whirlwind (squall):—storm, tempest.

g2979.d: λακτίζω laktízō, lak-tid'-zo; from adverb λάξ láx (heelwise); to recalcitrate:—kick.

g298.d:
ἀμώμητος amṓmētos, am-o'-may-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a derivative of G3469; 
 unblamable:—blameless.
g298.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of μωμάομαι (G3469)|English: Alpha

g2980.d:
λαλέω laléō, lal-eh'-o; a prolonged form of an otherwise obsolete verb; to talk, i.e. utter
 words:—preach, say, speak (after), talk, tell, utter. Compare G3004.
g2980.r: A prolonged form of an otherwise obsolete verb|

g2981.d: λαλιά laliá, lal-ee-ah'; from G2980; talk:—saying, speech.
g2981.r: From λαλέω (G2980)|English: speak, say, tell, talk, preach, utter, misc

g2982.d:
†λαμά lamá, lam-ah'; of Hebrew origin (H4100 with prepositional prefix); 
 lama (i.e. why):—lama.

g2983.d:
λαμβάνω lambánō, lam-ban'-o; a prolonged form of a primary verb, which is use only as an alternate
 in certain tenses; to take (in very many applications, literally and
 figuratively (properly objective or active, to get hold of; whereas
 G1209 is rather subjective or passive, to have offered to one; while
 G138 is more violent, to seize or remove)):—accept, + be amazed,
 assay, attain, bring, × when I call, catch, come on (X unto), +
 forget, have, hold, obtain, receive (X after), take (away, up).
g2983.r: A prolonged form of a primary verb, which is use only as an alternate in certain tenses|

g2984.d: Λάμεχ Lámech, lam'-ekh; of Hebrew origin (H3929); Lamech (i.e. Lemek), a patriarch:—Lamech.

g2985.d: λαμπάς lampás, lam-pas'; from G2989; a "lamp" or flambeau:—lamp, light, torch.

g2986.d:
λαμπρός lamprós, lam-pros'; from the same as G2985; radiant; by analogy, limpid; figuratively,
 magnificent or sumptuous (in appearance):—bright, clear, gay, goodly,
 gorgeous, white.
g2986.r: From the same as λαμπάς (G2985)|English: lamp, torch, light

g2987.d: λαμπρότης lamprótēs, lam-prot'-ace; from G2986; brilliancy:—brightness.
g2987.r: From λαμπρός (G2986)|English: bright, goodly, white, gorgeous, gay, clear

g2988.d:
λαμπρῶς lamprōs, lam-proce'; adverb from G2986; brilliantly, i.e. figuratively,
 luxuriously:—sumptuously.
g2988.r: From λαμπρός (G2986)|English: bright, goodly, white, gorgeous, gay, clear

g2989.d:
λάμπω lámpō, lam'-po; a primary verb; to beam, i.e. radiate brilliancy (literally or
 figuratively):—give light, shine.

g299.d:
†ἄμωμος ámōmos, am'-o-mos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3470; unblemished (literally or
 figuratively):—without blame (blemish, fault, spot), faultless,
 unblamable.
g299.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and μῶμος (G3470)|English: Alpha

g2990.d:
λανθάνω lanthánō, lan-than'-o; a prolonged form of a primary verb, which is used only as an alternate
 in certain tenses; to lie hid (literally or figuratively); often used
 adverbially, unwittingly:—be hid, be ignorant of, unawares.
g2990.r: A prolonged form of a primitive verb, which is used only as an alt. in certain tenses|

g2991.d:
λαξευτός laxeutós, lax-yoo-tos'; from a compound of λᾶς lâs (a stone) and the base of G3584 (in its original
 sense of scraping); rock-quarried:—hewn in stone.
g2991.r: From a compound of las (a stone) and the base of ξηρός (G3584) (in its original sense of scraping)|English: withered, dry, dry land, land

g2992.d:
