στῆθος stēthos, stay'-thos; from G2476 (as standing prominently); the (entire external) bosom, i.e.
 chest:—breast.
g4738.r: From ἵστημι (G2476) (as standing prominently)|English: stand, set, establish, stand still, stand by, misc

g4739.d:
στήκω stḗkō, stay'-ko; from the perfect tense of G2476; to be stationary, i.e. (figuratively)
 to persevere:—stand (fast).
g4739.r: From the perfect tense of ἵστημι (G2476)|English: stand, set, establish, stand still, stand by, misc

g474.d: ἀντιβάλλω antibállō, an-tee-bal'-lo; from G473 and G906; to bandy:—have.
g474.r: From ἀντί (G473) and βάλλω (G906)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4740.d: στηριγμός stērigmós, stay-rig-mos'; from G4741; stability (figuratively):—stedfastness.
g4740.r: From στηρίζω (G4741)|English: stablish, establish, strengthen, fix, stedfastly set

g4741.d:
στηρίζω stērízō, stay-rid'-zo; from a presumed derivative of G2476 (like G4731); to set fast, i.e.
 (literally) to turn resolutely in a certain direction, or
 (figuratively) to confirm:—fix, (e-)stablish, stedfastly set,
 strengthen.
g4741.r: From a presumed derivative of ἵστημι (G2476) (like στερεός (G4731))|English: stand, set, establish, stand still, stand by, misc

g4742.d:
στίγμα stígma, stig'-mah; from a primary στίζω stízō (to "stick", i.e. prick); a mark incised or
 punched (for recognition of ownership), i.e. (figuratively) scar of
 service:—mark.
g4742.r: From a primary stizo (to "stick", i.e. prick)|

g4743.d: στιγμή stigmḗ, stig-may'; feminine of G4742; a point of time, i.e. an instant:—moment.

g4744.d: στίλβω stílbō, stil'-bo; apparently a primary verb; to gleam, i.e. flash intensely:—shining.

g4745.d: στοά stoá, sto-ah'; probably from G2476; a colonnade or interior piazza:—porch.
g4745.r: Probably from ἵστημι (G2476)|English: stand, set, establish, stand still, stand by, misc

g4747.d:
στοιχεῖον stoicheîon, stoy-khi'-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of the base of G4748; something orderly
 in arrangement, i.e. (by implication) a serial (basal, fundamental,
 initial) constituent (literally), proposition
 (figuratively):—element, principle, rudiment.
g4747.r: From a presumed derivative of the base of στοιχέω (G4748)|English: walk, walk orderly

g4748.d:
στοιχέω stoichéō, stoy-kheh'-o; from a derivative of στείχω steíchō (to range in regular line); to march in
 (military) rank (keep step), i.e. (figuratively) to conform to virtue
 and piety:—walk (orderly).
g4748.r: From a derivative of steicho (to range in regular line)|

g4749.d:
στολή stolḗ, stol-ay'; from G4724; equipment, i.e. (specially), a "stole" or long-fitting gown
 (as a mark of dignity):—long clothing (garment), (long) robe.

g475.d:
ἀντιδιατίθεμαι antidiatíthemai, an-tee-dee-at-eeth'-em-ahee; from G473 and G1303; to set oneself opposite, i.e. be 
 disputatious:—that oppose themselves.
g475.r: From ἀντί (G473) and διατίθημι (G1303)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4750.d:
στόμα stóma, stom'-a; probably strengthened from a presumed derivative of the base of G5114; 
 the mouth (as if a gash in the face); by implication, language (and
 its relations); figuratively, an opening (in the earth); specially,
 the front or edge (of a weapon):—edge, face, mouth.
g4750.r: Probably strengthened from a presumed derivative of the base of τομός (G5114)|English: sharper

g4751.d:
στόμαχος stómachos, stom'-akh-os; from G4750; an orifice (the gullet), i.e. (specially), the
 "stomach":—stomach.

g4752.d:
στρατεία strateía, strat-i'-ah; from G4754; military service, i.e. (figuratively) the apostolic career
 (as one of hardship and danger):—warfare.
g4752.r: From στρατεύω (G4754)|English: war, goeth a warfare, soldier

g4753.d:
στράτευμα stráteuma, strat'-yoo-mah; from G4754; an armament, i.e. (by implication) a body of troops (more
 or less extensive or systematic):—army, soldier, man of war.
g4753.r: From στρατεύω (G4754)|English: war, goeth a warfare, soldier

g4754.d:
†στρατεύομαι strateúomai, strat-yoo'-om-ahee; middle voice from the base of G4756; to serve in a military campaign;
 figuratively, to execute the apostolate (with its arduous duties and
 functions), to contend with carnal inclinations:—soldier, (go to)
 war(-fare).
g4754.r: Middle voice from the base of στρατιά (G4756)|English: host

g4755.d:
στρατηγός stratēgós, strat-ay-gos'; from the base of G4756 and G71 or G2233; a general, i.e. (by implication
 or analogy) a (military) governor (prætor), the chief (præfect) of
 the (Levitical) temple-wardens:—captain, magistrate.
g4755.r: From the base of στρατιά (G4756) and ἄγω (G71) or ἡγέομαι (G2233)|English: host

g4756.d:
στρατιά stratiá, strat-ee'-ah; feminine of a derivative of στρατός stratós (an army; from the base of G4766,
 as encamped); camp-likeness, i.e. an army, i.e. (figuratively) the
 angels, the celestial luminaries:—host.
g4756.r: From a derivative of stratos (an army from the base of στρωννύω (G4766), as encamped)|English: spread, straw, furnish, make (one's) bed

g4757.d:
στρατιώτης stratiṓtēs, strat-ee-o'-tace; from a presumed derivative of the same as G4756; a camper-out, i.e. a
 (common) warrior (literally or figuratively):—soldier.
g4757.r: From a presumed derivative of the same as στρατιά (G4756)|English: host

g4758.r: From a compound of the base of στρατιά (G4756) and λέγω (G3004) (in its original sense)|English: host

g476.d:
ἀντίδικος antídikos, an-tid'-ee-kos; from G473 and G1349; an opponent (in a lawsuit); specially, Satan (as
 the arch-enemy):—adversary.
g476.r: From ἀντί (G473) and δίκη (G1349)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4760.d:
στρατόπεδον stratópedon, strat-op'-ed-on; from the base of G4756 and the same as G3977; a camping-ground, i.e. (by
 implication) a body of troops:—army.
g4760.r: From the base of στρατιά (G4756) and the same as πεδινός (G3977)|English: host

g4761.d:
στρεβλόω streblóō, streb-lo'-o; from a derivative of G4762; to wrench, i.e. (specially), to torture (by
 the rack), but only figuratively, to pervert:—wrest.
g4761.r: From a derivative of στρέφω (G4762)|English: turn, turn (one's) self, turn (one), turn again, turn back again, turn (one) about, be converted

g4762.d:
στρέφω stréphō, stref'-o; strengthened from the base of G5157; to twist, i.e. turn quite around
 or reverse (literally or figuratively):—convert, turn (again, back
 again, self, self about).
g4762.r: Strengthened from the base of τροπή (G5157)|English: turning

g4763.d:
στρηνιάω strēniáō, stray-nee-ah'-o; from a presumed derivative of G4764; to be luxurious:—live
 deliciously.
g4763.r: From a presumed derivative of στρῆνος (G4764)|English: delicacy

g4764.d:
στρῆνος strēnos, stray'-nos; akin to G4731; a "straining", "strenuousness" or "strength", i.e.
 (figuratively) luxury (voluptuousness):—delicacy.
g4764.r: Akin to στερεός (G4731)|English: strong, sure, stedfast

g4765.d: στρουθίον strouthíon, stroo-thee'-on; diminutive of στρουθός strouthós (a sparrow); a little sparrow:—sparrow.

g4766.d:
στρώννυμι strṓnnymi, strone'-noo-mee; prolongation from a still simpler
    στρόω stróō  stro'-o, (used only as an alternate in certain tenses)
 (probably akin to G4731 through the idea of positing); to "strew," i.e.
 spread (as a carpet or couch):—make bed, furnish, spread, strew.
g4766.r: Prolongation from a still simpler stroo {stro'-o} (used only as an alternate in certain tenses, probably akin to στερεός (G4731) through the idea of positing)|English: strong, sure, stedfast

g4767.d:
†στυγνητός stygnētós, stoog-nay-tos'; from a derivative of an obsolete apparently primary στύγω stýgō (to hate); 
 hated, i.e. odious:—hateful.
g4767.r: From a derivative of an obsolete apparently primary stugo (to hate)|

g4768.d:
στυγνάζω stygnázō, stoog-nad'-zo; from the same as G4767; to render gloomy, i.e. (by implication) glower
 (be overcast with clouds, or sombreness of speech):—lower, be sad.
g4768.r: From the same as στυγητός (G4767)|English: hateful

g4769.d:
†στῦλος stŷlos, stoo'-los; from στύω stýō (to stiffen; properly akin to the base of G2476); a post
 ("style"), i.e. (figuratively) support:—pillar.
g4769.r: From stuo (to stiffen, properly akin to the base of ἵστημι (G2476))|English: stand, set, establish, stand still, stand by, misc

g477.d:
ἀντίθεσις antíthesis, an-tith'-es-is; from a compound of G473 and G5087; opposition, i.e. a conflict (of
 theories):—opposition.
g477.r: From a compound of ἀντί (G473) and τίθημι (G5087)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4770.d:
†Στωϊκός Stōïkós, sto-ik-os'; from G4745; a "Stoic" (as occupying a particular porch in Athens), i.e.
 adherent of a certin philosophy:—Stoick.

g4771.d:
σύ sý, soo; the personal pronoun of the second person singular; thou:—thou. See
 also G4571, G4671, G4675; and for the plural G5209, G5210, G5213, G5216.
g4771.r: Personal pronoun of the second person singular|

g4772.d: συγγένεια syngéneia, soong-ghen'-i-ah; from G4773; relationship, i.e. (concretely) relatives:—kindred.
g4772.r: From συγγενής (G4773)|English: kinsman, cousin, kinsfolk, kin

g4773.d:
†συγγενής syngenḗs, soong-ghen-ace'; from G4862 and G1085; a relative (by blood); by extension, a fellow
 countryman:—cousin, kin(-sfolk, -sman).
g4773.r: From σύν (G4862) and γένος (G1085)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4774.d:
συγγνώμη syngnṓmē, soong-gno'-may; from a compound of G4862 and G1097; fellow knowledge, i.e.
 concession:—permission.
g4774.r: From a compound of σύν (G4862) and γινώσκω (G1097)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4775.d: συγκάθημαι synkáthēmai, soong-kath'-ay-mahee; from G4862 and G2521; to seat oneself in company with:—sit with.
g4775.r: From σύν (G4862) and κάθημαι (G2521)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4776.d:
συγκαθίζω synkathízō, soong-kath-id'-zo; from G4862 and G2523; to give (or take) a seat in company with:—(make)
 sit (down) together.
g4776.r: From σύν (G4862) and καθίζω (G2523)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4777.d:
συγκακοπαθέω synkakopathéō, soong-kak-op-ath-eh'-o; from G4862 and G2553; to suffer hardship in company with:—be partaker
 of afflictions.
g4777.r: From σύν (G4862) and κακοπαθέω (G2553)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4778.d:
†συγκακουχέω synkakouchéō, soong-kak-oo-kheh'-o; from G4862 and G2558; to maltreat in company with, i.e. (passively)
 endure persecution together:—suffer affliction with.
g4778.r: From σύν (G4862) and κακουχέω (G2558)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4779.d: συγκαλέω synkaléō, soong-kal-eh'-o; from G4862 and G2564; to convoke:—call together.
g4779.r: From σύν (G4862) and καλέω (G2564)|English: with, beside, accompany

g478.d:
ἀντικαθίστημι antikathístēmi, an-tee-kath-is'-tay-mee; from G473 and G2525; to set down (troops) against, i.e.
 withstand:—resist.
g478.r: From ἀντί (G473) and καθίστημι (G2525)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4780.d: συγκαλύπτω synkalýptō, soong-kal-oop'-to; from G4862 and G2572; to conceal altogether:—cover.
g4780.r: From σύν (G4862) and καλύπτω (G2572)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4781.d:
συγκάμπτω synkámptō, soong-kamp'-to; from G4862 and G2578; to bend together, i.e. (figuratively) to
 afflict:—bow down.
g4781.r: From σύν (G4862) and κάμπτω (G2578)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4782.d: συγκαταβαίνω synkatabaínō, soong-kat-ab-ah'-ee-no; from G4862 and G2597; to descend in company with:—go down with.
g4782.r: From σύν (G4862) and καταβαίνω (G2597)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4783.d:
συγκατάθεσις synkatáthesis, soong-kat-ath'-es-is; from G4784; a deposition (of sentiment) in company with, i.e.
 (figuratively) accord with:—agreement.

g4784.d:
†συγκατατίθεμαι synkatatíthemai, soong-kat-at-ith'-em-ahee; middle from G4862 and G2698; to deposit (one's vote or opinion) in company
 with, i.e. (figuratively) to accord with:—consent.
g4784.r: Mid from σύν (G4862) and κατατίθημι (G2698)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4785.d:
συγκαταψηφίζω synkatapsēphízō, soong-kat-aps-ay-fid'-zo; from G4862 and a compound of G2596 and G5585; to count down in company
 with, i.e. enroll among:—number with.
g4785.r: From σύν (G4862) and a compound of κατά (G2596) and ψηφίζω (G5585)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4786.d:
συγκεράννυμι synkeránnymi, soong-ker-an'-noo-mee; from G4862 and G2767; to commingle, i.e. (figuratively) to combine or
 assimilate:—mix with, temper together.
g4786.r: From σύν (G4862) and κεράννυμι (G2767)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4787.d:
συγκινέω synkinéō, soong-kin-eh'-o; from G4682 and G2795; to move together, i.e. (specially), to excite as a
 mass (to sedition):—stir up.
g4787.r: From σπαράσσω (G4682) and κινέω (G2795)|English: tear, rend

g4788.d:
συγκλείω synkleíō, soong-kli'-o; from G4862 and G2808; to shut together, i.e. include or (figuratively)
 embrace in a common subjection to:—conclude, inclose, shut up.
g4788.r: From σύν (G4862) and κλείω (G2808)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4789.d:
συγκληρονόμος synklēronómos, soong-klay-ron-om'-os; from G4862 and G2818; a co-heir, i.e. (by analogy) participant in
 common:—fellow (joint)-heir, heir together, heir with.
g4789.r: From σύν (G4862) and κληρονόμος (G2818)|English: with, beside, accompany

g479.d: ἀντικαλέω antikaléō, an-tee-kal-eh'-o; from G473 and G2564; to invite in return:—bid again.
g479.r: From ἀντί (G473) and καλέω (G2564)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4790.d:
συγκοινωνέω synkoinōnéō, soong-koy-no-neh'-o; from G4862 and G2841; to share in company with, i.e. co-participate
 in:—communicate (have fellowship) with, be partaker of.
g4790.r: From σύν (G4862) and κοινωνέω (G2841)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4791.d:
συγκοινωνός synkoinōnós, soong-koy-no-nos'; from G4862 and G2844; a co-participant:—companion, partake(-r, -r
 with).
g4791.r: From σύν (G4862) and κοινωνός (G2844)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4792.d:
συγκομίζω synkomízō, soong-kom-id'-zo; from G4862 and G2865; to convey together, i.e. collect or bear away in
 company with others:—carry.
g4792.r: From σύν (G4862) and κομίζω (G2865)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4793.d:
συγκρίνω synkrínō, soong-kree'-no; from G4862 and G2919; to judge of one thing in connection with another,
 i.e. combine (spiritual ideas with appropriate expressions) or collate
 (one person with another by way of contrast or resemblance):—compare
 among (with).
g4793.r: From σύν (G4862) and κρίνω (G2919)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4794.d:
συγκύπτω synkýptō, soong-koop'-to; from G4862 and G2955; to stoop altogether, i.e. be completely overcome
 by:—bow together.
g4794.r: From σύν (G4862) and κύπτω (G2955)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4795.d:
συγκυρία synkyría, soong-koo-ree'-ah; from a comparative of G4862 and κυρέω kyréō (to light or happen; from the
 base of G2962); concurrence, i.e. accident:—chance.
g4795.r: From a comparative of σύν (G4862) and kureo (to light or happen; from the base of κύριος (G2962))|English: with, beside, accompany

g4796.d:
συγχαίρω synchaírō, soong-khah'-ee-ro; from G4862 and G5463; to sympathize in gladness, congratulate:—rejoice
 in (with).
g4796.r: From σύν (G4862) and χαίρω (G5463)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4797.d:
†συγχέω synchéō, soong-kheh'-o; from G4862 and χέω chéō (to pour) or its alternate; to commingle
 promiscuously, i.e. (figuratively) to throw (an assembly) into
 disorder, to perplex (the mind):—confound, confuse, stir up, be in an
 uproar.
g4797.r: From σύν (G4862) and cheo (to pour) or its alternate|English: with, beside, accompany

g4798.d:
συγχράομαι synchráomai, soong-khrah'-om-ahee; from G4862 and G5530; to use jointly, i.e. (by implication) to hold
 intercourse in common:—have dealings with.
g4798.r: From σύν (G4862) and χράομαι (G5530)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4799.d:
σύγχυσις sýnchysis, soong'-khoo-sis; from G4797; commixture, i.e. (figuratively) riotous
 disturbance:—confusion.
g4799.r: From συγχέω (G4797)|English: confound, confuse, be in an uproar, stir up

g48.d:
ἁγνίζω hagnízō, hag-nid'-zo; from G53; to make clean, i.e. (figuratively) sanctify (ceremonially or
 morally):—purify (self).

g480.d:
ἀντίκειμαι antíkeimai, an-tik'-i-mahee; from G473 and G2749; to lie opposite, i.e. be adverse (figuratively,
 repugnant) to:—adversary, be contrary, oppose.
g480.r: From ἀντί (G473) and κεῖμαι (G2749)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4800.d:
συζάω syzáō, sood-zah'-o; from G4862 and G2198; to continue to live in common with, i.e.
 co-survive (literally or figuratively):—live with.
g4800.r: From σύν (G4862) and ζάω (G2198)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4801.d:
συζεύγνυμι syzeúgnymi, sood-zyoog'-noo-mee; from G4862 and the base of G2201; to yoke together, i.e. (figuratively)
 conjoin (in marriage):—join together.
g4801.r: From σύν (G4862) and the base of ζεῦγος (G2201)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4802.d:
συζητέω syzētéō, sood-zay-teh'-o; from G4862 and G2212; to investigate jointly, i.e. discuss, controvert,
 cavil:—dispute (with), enquire, question (with), reason (together).
g4802.r: From σύν (G4862) and ζητέω (G2212)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4804.d: συζητητής syzētētḗs, sood-zay-tay-tace'; from G4802; a disputant, i.e. sophist:—disputer.
g4804.r: From συζητέω (G4802)|English: question with, question, question one with another, enquire, dispute with, dispute, reason together, reason

g4805.d:
σύζυγος sýzygos, sood'-zoo-gos; from G4801; co-yoked, i.e. (figuratively) as noun, a colleague;
 probably rather as a proper name; Syzygus, a Christian:—yokefellow.

g4806.d:
συζωοποιέω syzōopoiéō, sood-zo-op-oy-eh'-o; from G4862 and G2227; to reanimate conjointly with
 (figuratively):—quicken together with.
g4806.r: From σύν (G4862) and ζῳοποιέω (G2227)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4807.d:
συκάμινος sykáminos, soo-kam'-ee-nos; of Hebrew origin (H8256) in imitation of G4809; a sycamore-fig
 tree:—sycamine tree.
g4807.r: Of Hebrew origin שִׁקְמָה (H8256) in imitation of συκομορέα (G4809)|English: sycamore tree, sycamore, sycamore fruit

g4808.d: συκῆ sykē, soo-kay'; from G4810; a fig-tree:—fig tree.

g4809.d:
†συκομωραία sykomōraía, soo-kom-o-rah'-yah; from G4810 and μόρον móron (the mulberry); the "sycamore"-fig tree:—sycamore
 tree. Compare G4807.
g4809.r: From σῦκον (G4810) and moron (the mulberry)|English: fig

g481.d: †ἀντικρύ antikrý, an-tee-kroo'; prolonged from G473; opposite:—over against.
g481.r: Prob. from ἀντί (G473)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4810.d: σῦκον sŷkon, soo'-kon; apparently a primary word; a fig:—fig.

g4811.d:
συκοφαντέω sykophantéō, soo-kof-an-teh'-o; from a compound of G4810 and a derivative of G5316; to be a fig-informer
 (reporter of the law forbidding the exportation of figs from Greece),
 "sycophant", i.e. (genitive and by extension) to defraud (exact
 unlawfully, extort):—accuse falsely, take by false accusation.
g4811.r: From a compound of σῦκον (G4810) and a derivative of φαίνω (G5316)|English: fig

g4812.d:
συλαγωγέω sylagōgéō, soo-lag-ogue-eh'-o; from the base of G4813 and (the reduplicated form of) G71; to lead away
 as booty, i.e. (figuratively) seduce:—spoil.
g4812.r: From the base of συλάω (G4813) and (the reduplicated form of) ἄγω (G71)|English: rob

g4813.d:
συλάω syláō, soo-lah'-o; from a derivative of σύλλω sýllō (to strip; probably akin to G138; compare
 G4661); to despoil:—rob.
g4813.r: From a derivative of sullo (to strip, probably akin to αἱρέω (G138), cf σκῦλον (G4661))|English: choose

g4814.d:
συλλαλέω syllaléō, sool-lal-eh'-o; from G4862 and G2980; to talk together, i.e. converse:—commune (confer,
 talk) with, speak among.
g4814.r: From σύν (G4862) and λαλέω (G2980)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4815.d:
συλλαμβάνω syllambánō, sool-lam-ban'-o; from G4862 and G2983; to clasp, i.e. seize (arrest, capture); specially,
 to conceive (literally or figuratively); by implication, to
 aid:—catch, conceive, help, take.
g4815.r: From σύν (G4862) and λαμβάνω (G2983)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4816.d:
συλλέγω syllégō, sool-leg'-o; from G4862 and G3004 in its original sense; to collect:—gather
 (together, up).
g4816.r: From σύν (G4862) and λέγω (G3004) in its original sense|English: with, beside, accompany

g4817.d:
συλλογίζομαι syllogízomai, sool-log-id'-zom-ahee; from G4862 and G3049; to reckon together (with oneself), i.e.
 deliberate:—reason with.
g4817.r: From σύν (G4862) and λογίζομαι (G3049)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4818.d:
†συλλυπέω syllypéō, sool-loop-eh'-o; from G4862 and G3076; to afflict jointly, i.e. (passive) sorrow at (on
 account of) someone:—be grieved.
g4818.r: From σύν (G4862) and λυπέω (G3076)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4819.d:
συμβαίνω symbaínō, soom-bah'-ee-no; from G4862 and the base of G939; to walk (figuratively, transpire)
 together, i.e. concur (take place):—be(-fall), happen (unto).
g4819.r: From σύν (G4862) and the base of βάσις (G939)|English: with, beside, accompany

g482.d:
†ἀντιλαμβάνομαι antilambánomai, an-tee-lam-ban'-om-ahee; from G473 and the middle voice of G2983; to take hold of in turn, i.e.
 succor; also to participate:—help, partaker, support.
g482.r: From ἀντί (G473) and the middle voice of λαμβάνω (G2983)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4820.d:
συμβάλλω symbállō, soom-bal'-lo; from G4862 and G906; to combine, i.e. (in speaking) to converse,
 consult, dispute, (mentally) to consider, (by implication) to aid,
 (personally) to join, attack:—confer, encounter, help, make, meet
 with, ponder.
g4820.r: From σύν (G4862) and βάλλω (G906)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4821.d: συμβασιλεύω symbasileúō, soom-bas-il-yoo'-o; from G4862 and G936; to be co-regent (figuratively):—reign with.
g4821.r: From σύν (G4862) and βασιλεύω (G936)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4822.d:
συμβιβάζω symbibázō, soom-bib-ad'-zo; from G4862 and βιβάζω bibázō (to force; causative (by reduplication) of the
 base of G939); to drive together, i.e. unite (in association or
 affection), (mentally) to infer, show, teach:—compact, assuredly
 gather, intrust, knit together, prove.
g4822.r: From σύν (G4862) and bibazo (to force, causative [by reduplication] of the base of βάσις (G939))|English: with, beside, accompany

g4823.d:
συμβουλεύω symbouleúō, soom-bool-yoo'-o; from G4862 and G1011; to give (or take) advice jointly, i.e. recommend,
 deliberate or determine:—consult, (give, take) counsel (together).
g4823.r: From σύν (G4862) and βουλεύω (G1011)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4824.d:
συμβούλιον symboúlion, soom-boo'-lee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G4825; advisement; specially, a
 deliberative body, i.e. the provincial assessors or
 lay-court:—consultation, counsel, council.
g4824.r: From a presumed derivative of σύμβουλος (G4825)|English: counsellor

g4825.d: σύμβουλος sýmboulos, soom'-boo-los; from G4862 and G1012; a consultor, i.e. adviser:—counsellor.
g4825.r: From σύν (G4862) and βουλή (G1012)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4826.d:
†Συμεών Symeṓn, soom-eh-one'; from the same as G4613; Symeon (i.e. Shimon), the name of five
 Israelites:—Simeon, Simon.
g4826.r: From the same as Σίμων (G4613)|English: Simon (Peter), Simon (Zelotes), Simon (father of Judas), Simon (Magus), Simon (the tanner), Simon (the Pharisee), Simon (of Cyrene), Simon (brother of Jesus), Simon (the leper)

g4827.d:
συμμαθητής symmathētḗs, soom-math-ay-tace'; from a compound of G4862 and G3129; a co-learner (of
 Christianity):—fellow disciple.
g4827.r: From a compound of σύν (G4862) and μανθάνω (G3129)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4828.d:
συμμαρτυρέω symmartyréō, soom-mar-too-reh'-o; from G4862 and G3140; to testify jointly, i.e. corroborate by
 (concurrent) evidence:—testify unto, (also) bear witness (with).
g4828.r: From σύν (G4862) and μαρτυρέω (G3140)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4829.d:
συμμερίζομαι symmerízomai, soom-mer-id'-zom-ahee; middle voice from G4862 and G3307; to share jointly, i.e. participate
 in:—be partaker with.
g4829.r: Middle voice from σύν (G4862) and μερίζω (G3307)|English: with, beside, accompany

g483.d:
†ἀντιλέγω antilégō, an-til'-eg-o; from G473 and G3004; to dispute, refuse:—answer again, contradict,
 deny, gainsay(-er), speak against.
g483.r: From ἀντί (G473) and λέγω (G3004)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4830.d: συμμέτοχος symmétochos, soom-met'-okh-os; from G4862 and G3353; a co-participant:—partaker.
g4830.r: From σύν (G4862) and μέτοχος (G3353)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4831.d:
συμμιμητής symmimētḗs, soom-mim-ay-tace'; from a presumed compound of G4862 and G3401; a co-imitator, i.e. fellow
 votary:—follower together.
g4831.r: From a presumed compound of σύν (G4862) and μιμέομαι (G3401)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4832.d:
σύμμορφος sýmmorphos, soom-mor-fos'; from G4862 and G3444; jointly formed, i.e. (figuratively)
 similar:—conformed to, fashioned like unto.
g4832.r: From σύν (G4862) and μορφή (G3444)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4834.d:
συμπαθέω sympathéō, soom-path-eh'-o; from G4835; to feel "sympathy" with, i.e. (by implication) to
 commiserate:—have compassion, be touched with a feeling of.
g4834.r: From συμπαθής (G4835)|English: having compassion one of another

g4835.d:
συμπαθής sympathḗs, soom-path-ace'; from G4841; having a fellow-feeling ("sympathetic"), i.e. (by
 implication) mutually commiserative:—having compassion one of
 another.

g4836.d:
συμπαραγίνομαι symparagínomai, soom-par-ag-in'-om-ahee; from G4862 and G3854; to be present together, i.e. to convene; by
 implication, to appear in aid:—come together, stand with.
g4836.r: From σύν (G4862) and παραγίνομαι (G3854)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4837.d: συμπαρακαλέω symparakaléō, soom-par-ak-al-eh'-o; from G4862 and G3870; to console jointly:—comfort together.
g4837.r: From σύν (G4862) and παρακαλέω (G3870)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4838.d: συμπαραλαμβάνω symparalambánō, soom-par-al-am-ban'-o; from G4862 and G3880; to take along in company:—take with.
g4838.r: From σύν (G4862) and παραλαμβάνω (G3880)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4840.d:
συμπάρειμι sympáreimi, soom-par'-i-mee; from G4862 and G3918; to be at hand together, i.e. now present:—be here
 present with.
g4840.r: From σύν (G4862) and πάρειμι (G3918)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4841.d:
συμπάσχω sympáschō, soom-pas'-kho; from G4862 and G3958 (including its alternate); to experience pain
 jointly or of the same kind (specially, persecution; to
 "sympathize"):—suffer with.
g4841.r: From σύν (G4862) and πάσχω (G3958) (including its alternate)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4842.d: συμπέμπω sympémpō, soom-pem'-po; from G4862 and G3992; to despatch in company:—send with.
g4842.r: From σύν (G4862) and πέμπω (G3992)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4843.d:
συμπεριλαμβάνω symperilambánō, soom-per-ee-lam-ban'-o; from G4862 and a compound of G4012 and G2983; to take by enclosing
 altogether, i.e. earnestly throw the arms about one:—embrace.
g4843.r: From σύν (G4862) and a compound of περί (G4012) and λαμβάνω (G2983)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4844.d: συμπίνω sympínō, soom-pee'-no; from G4862 and G4095; to partake a beverage in company:—drink with.
g4844.r: From σύν (G4862) and πίνω (G4095)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4845.d:
συμπληρόω symplēróō, soom-play-ro'-o; from G4862 and G4137; to implenish completely, i.e. (of space) to swamp
 (a boat), or (of time) to accomplish (passive, be complete):—(fully)
 come, fill up.
g4845.r: From σύν (G4862) and πληρόω (G4137)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4846.d:
συμπνίγω sympnígō, soom-pnee'-go; from G4862 and G4155; to strangle completely, i.e. (literally) to drown,
 or (figuratively) to crowd:—choke, throng.
g4846.r: From σύν (G4862) and πνίγω (G4155)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4847.d:
συμπολίτης sympolítēs, soom-pol-ee'-tace; from G4862 and G4177; a native of the same town, i.e. (figuratively)
 co-religionist (fellow-Christian):—fellow- citizen.
g4847.r: From σύν (G4862) and πολίτης (G4177)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4848.d:
συμπορεύομαι symporeúomai, soom-por-yoo'-om-ahee; from G4862 and G4198; to journey together; by implication, to
 assemble:—go with, resort.
g4848.r: From σύν (G4862) and πορεύω (G4198)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4849.d:
συμπόσιον sympósion, soom-pos'-ee-on; neuter of a derivative of the alternate of G4844; a drinking-party
 ("symposium"), i.e. (by extension) a room of guests:—company.
g4849.r: From a derivative of the alternate of συμπίνω (G4844)|English: drink with

g485.d:
ἀντιλογία antilogía, an-tee-log-ee'-ah; from a derivative of G483; dispute, disobedience:—contradiction,
 gainsaying, strife.
g485.r: From a derivative of ἀντιλέγω (G483)|English: speak against, deny, contradict, gainsay, gainsayer, answer again

g4850.d: συμπρεσβύτερος sympresbýteros, soom-pres-boo'-ter-os; from G4862 and G4245; a co-presbyter:—presbyter, also an elder.
g4850.r: From σύν (G4862) and πρεσβύτερος (G4245)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4851.d:
†συμφέρω symphérō, soom-fer'-o; from G4862 and G5342 (including its alternate); to bear together
 (contribute), i.e. (literally) to collect, or (figuratively) to
 conduce; especially (neuter participle as a noun) advantage:—be
 better for, bring together, be expedient (for), be good, (be)
 profit(-able for).
g4851.r: From σύν (G4862) and φέρω (G5342) (including its alternate)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4852.d: σύμφημι sýmphēmi, soom'-fay-mee; from G4862 and G5346; to say jointly, i.e. assent to:—consent unto.
g4852.r: From σύν (G4862) and φημί (G5346)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4853.d:
συμφυλέτης symphylétēs, soom-foo-let'-ace; from G4862 and a derivative of G5443; a co-tribesman, i.e. native of the
 same country:—countryman.
g4853.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of φυλή (G5443)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4854.d:
σύμφυτος sýmphytos, soom'-foo-tos; from G4862 and a derivative of G5453; grown along with (connate), i.e.
 (figuratively) closely united to:—planted together.
g4854.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of φύω (G5453)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4855.d: συμφύω symphýō, soom-foo'-o; from G4862 and G5453; passive, to grow jointly:—spring up with.
g4855.r: From σύν (G4862) and φύω (G5453)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4856.d:
συμφωνέω symphōnéō, soom-fo-neh'-o; from G4859; to be harmonious, i.e. (figuratively) to accord (be
 suitable, concur) or stipulate (by compact):—agree (together, with).

g4857.d: συμφώνησις symphṓnēsis, soom-fo'-nay-sis; from G4856; accordance:—concord.
g4857.r: From συμφωνέω (G4856)|English: agree, agree with, agree together

g4858.d:
συμφωνία symphōnía, soom-fo-nee'-ah; from G4859; unison of sound ("symphony"), i.e. a concert of instruments
 (harmonious note):—music.

g4859.d:
σύμφωνος sýmphōnos, soom'-fo-nos; from G4862 and G5456; sounding together (alike), i.e. (figuratively)
 accordant (neuter as noun, agreement):—consent.
g4859.r: From σύν (G4862) and φωνή (G5456)|English: with, beside, accompany

g486.d: ἀντιλοιδορέω antiloidoréō, an-tee-loy-dor-eh'-o; from G473 and G3058; to rail in reply:—revile again.
g486.r: From ἀντί (G473) and λοιδορέω (G3058)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4860.d: συμψηφίζω sympsēphízō, soom-psay-fid'-zo; from G4862 and G5585; to compute jointly:—reckon.
g4860.r: From σύν (G4862) and ψηφίζω (G5585)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4861.d:
σύμψυχος sýmpsychos, soom'-psoo-khos; from G4862 and G5590; co-spirited, i.e. similar in
 sentiment:—like-minded.
g4861.r: From σύν (G4862) and ψυχή (G5590)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4862.d:
σύν sýn, soon; a primary preposition denoting union; with or together (but much
 closer than G3326 or G3844), i.e. by association, companionship,
 process, resemblance, possession, instrumentality, addition,
 etc.:—beside, with. In composition it has similar applications,
 including completeness.

g4863.d:
συνάγω synágō, soon-ag'-o; from G4862 and G71; to lead together, i.e. collect or convene;
 specially, to entertain (hospitably):—+ accompany, assemble (selves,
 together), bestow, come together, gather (selves together, up,
 together), lead into, resort, take in.
g4863.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἄγω (G71)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4864.r: From (the reduplicated form of) συνάγω (G4863)|English: gather, be gathered together, gather together, come together, be gathered, be assembled, take in, misc

g4865.d:
συναγωνίζομαι synagōnízomai, soon-ag-o-nid'-zom-ahee; from G4862 and G75; to struggle in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to
 be a partner (assistant):—strive together with.
g4865.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀγωνίζομαι (G75)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4866.d:
συναθλέω synathléō, soon-ath-leh'-o; from G4862 and G118; to wrestle in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to
 seek jointly:—labour with, strive together for.
g4866.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀθλέω (G118)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4867.d:
†συναθροίζω synathroízō, soon-ath-royd'-zo; from G4862 and ἀθροίζω athroízō (to hoard); to convene:—call (gather)
 together.
g4867.r: From σύν (G4862) and athroizo (to hoard)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4868.d:
συναίρω synaírō, soon-ah'-ee-ro; from G4862 and G142; to make up together, i.e. (figuratively) to compute
 (an account):—reckon, take.
g4868.r: From σύν (G4862) and αἴρω (G142)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4869.d: συναιχμάλωτος synaichmálōtos, soon-aheekh-mal'-o-tos; from G4862 and G164; a co-captive:—fellowprisoner.
g4869.r: From σύν (G4862) and αἰχμάλωτος (G164)|English: with, beside, accompany

g487.d: ἀντίλυτρον antílytron, an-til'-oo-tron; from G473 and G3083; a redemption-price:—ransom.
g487.r: From ἀντί (G473) and λύτρον (G3083)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4870.d: συνακολουθέω synakolouthéō, soon-ak-ol-oo-theh'-o; from G4862 and G190; to accompany:—follow.
g4870.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀκολουθέω (G190)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4871.d:
συναλίζω synalízō, soon-al-id'-zo; from G4862 and ἁλίζω halízō (to throng); to accumulate, i.e.
 convene:—assemble together.
g4871.r: From σύν (G4862) and halizo (to throng)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4872.d: συναναβαίνω synanabaínō, soon-an-ab-ah'-ee-no; from G4862 and G305; to ascend in company with:—come up with.
g4872.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀναβαίνω (G305)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4873.d:
συνανάκειμαι synanákeimai, soon-an-ak'-i-mahee; from G4862 and G345; to recline in company with (at a meal):—sit (down,
 at the table, together) with (at meat).
g4873.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀνάκειμαι (G345)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4874.d:
συναναμίγνυμι synanamígnymi, soon-an-am-ig'-noo-mee; from G4862 and a compound of G303 and G3396; to mix up together, i.e.
 (figurative) associate with:—(have, keep) company (with).
g4874.r: From σύν (G4862) and a compound of ἀνά (G303) and μίγνυμι (G3396)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4875.d:
συναναπαύομαι synanapaúomai, soon-an-ap-ow'-om-ahee; middle from G4862 and G373; to recruit oneself in company with:—refresh
 with.
g4875.r: Middle from σύν (G4862) and ἀναπαύω (G373)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4876.d:
συναντάω synantáō, soon-an-tah'-o; from G4862 and a derivative of G473; to meet with; figuratively, to
 occur:—befall, meet.
g4876.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derived from ἀντί (G473)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4878.d:
συναντιλαμβάνομαι synantilambánomai, soon-an-tee-lam-ban'-om-ahee; from G4862 and G482; to take hold of opposite together, i.e. co-operate
 (assist):—help.
g4878.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀντιλαμβάνω (G482)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4879.d:
συναπάγω synapágō, soon-ap-ag'-o; from G4862 and G520; to take off together, i.e. transport with (seduce,
 passively, yield):—carry (lead) away with, condescend.
g4879.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀπάγω (G520)|English: with, beside, accompany

g488.d: ἀντιμετρέω antimetréō, an-tee-met-reh'-o; from G473 and G3354; to mete in return:—measure again.
g488.r: From ἀντί (G473) and μετρέω (G3354)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4880.d:
†συναποθνήσκω synapothnḗskō, soon-ap-oth-nace'-ko; from G4862 and G599; to decease (literally) in company with, or
 (figuratively), similarly to:—be dead (die) with.
g4880.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀποθνῄσκω (G599)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4881.d:
συναπόλλυμι synapóllymi, soon-ap-ol'-loo-mee; from G4862 and G622; to destroy (middle voice or passively, be slain) in
 company with:—perish with.
g4881.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀπόλλυμι (G622)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4882.d:
συναποστέλλω synapostéllō, soon-ap-os-tel'-lo; from G4862 and G649; to despatch (on an errand) in company with:—send
 with.
g4882.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἀποστέλλω (G649)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4883.d:
συναρμολογέω synarmologéō, soon-ar-mol-og-eh'-o; from G4862 and a derivative of a compound of G719 and G3004 (in its
 original sense of laying); to render close-jointed together, i.e.
 organize compactly:—be fitly framed (joined) together.
g4883.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of a compound of ἁρμός (G719) and λέγω (G3004) (in its original sense of laying)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4884.d: συναρπάζω synarpázō, soon-ar-pad'-zo; from G4862 and G726; to snatch together, i.e. seize:—catch.
g4884.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἁρπάζω (G726)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4885.d: †συναυξάνω synauxánō, soon-owx-an'-o; from G4862 and G837; to increase (grow up) together:—grow together.
g4885.r: From σύν (G4862) and αὐξάνω (G837)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4886.d:
σύνδεσμος sýndesmos, soon'-des-mos; from G4862 and G1199; a joint tie, i.e. ligament, (figuratively) uniting
 principle, control:—band, bond.
g4886.r: From σύν (G4862) and δεσμός (G1199)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4887.d:
συνδέω syndéō, soon-deh'-o; from G4862 and G1210; to bind with, i.e. (passively) be a
 fellow-prisoner (figuratively):—be bound with.
g4887.r: From σύν (G4862) and δέω (G1210)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4888.d:
συνδοξάζω syndoxázō, soon-dox-ad'-zo; from G4862 and G1392; to exalt to dignity in company (i.e. similarly)
 with:—glorify together.
g4888.r: From σύν (G4862) and δοξάζω (G1392)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4889.d:
σύνδουλος sýndoulos, soon'-doo-los; from G4862 and G1401; a co-slave, i.e. servitor or ministrant of the
 same master (human or divine):—fellowservant.
g4889.r: From σύν (G4862) and δοῦλος (G1401)|English: with, beside, accompany

g489.d:
ἀντιμισθία antimisthía, an-tee-mis-thee'-ah; from a compound of G473 and G3408; requital,
 correspondence:—recompense.
g489.r: From a compound of ἀντί (G473) and μισθός (G3408)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4890.d:
συνδρομή syndromḗ, soon-drom-ay'; from (the alternate of) G4936; a running together, i.e. (riotous)
 concourse:—run together.
g4890.r: From (the alternate of) συντρέχω (G4936)|English: run, run together, run with

g4891.d:
συνεγείρω synegeírō, soon-eg-i'-ro; from G4862 and G1453; to rouse (from death) in company with, i.e.
 (figuratively) to revivify (spirtually) in resemblance to:—raise up
 together, rise with.
g4891.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἐγείρω (G1453)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4892.d:
συνέδριον synédrion, soon-ed'-ree-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of a compound of G4862 and the base of
 G1476; a joint session, i.e. (specially), the Jewish Sanhedrin; by
 analogy, a subordinate tribunal:—council.
g4892.r: From a presumed derivative of a compound of σύν (G4862) and the base of ἑδραῖος (G1476)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4893.d:
συνείδησις syneídēsis, soon-i'-day-sis; from a prolonged form of G4894; co-perception, i.e. moral
 consciousness:—conscience.
g4893.r: From a prolonged form of συνοράω (G4894)|English: by privy, consider, be ware of, know

g4895.d:
σύνειμι sýneimi, soon'-i-mee; from G4862 and G1510 (including its various inflections); to be in
 company with, i.e. present at the time:—be with.
g4895.r: From σύν (G4862) and εἰμί (G1510) (including its various inflections)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4897.d:
συνεισέρχομαι syneisérchomai, soon-ice-er'-khom-ahee; from G4862 and G1525; to enter in company with:—go in with, go with
 into.
g4897.r: From σύν (G4862) and εἰσέρχομαι (G1525)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4898.d:
συνέκδημος synékdēmos, soon-ek'-day-mos; from G4862 and the base of G1553; a co-absentee from home, i.e.
 fellow-traveller:—companion in travel, travel with.
g4898.r: From σύν (G4862) and the base of ἐκδημέω (G1553)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4899.d:
συνεκλεκτός syneklektós, soon-ek-lek-tos'; from a compound of G4862 and G1586; chosen in company with, i.e.
 co-elect (fellow Christian):—elected together with.
g4899.r: From a compound of σύν (G4862) and ἐκλέγομαι (G1586)|English: with, beside, accompany

g49.d:
ἁγνισμός hagnismós, hag-nis-mos'; from G48; a cleansing (the act), i.e. (ceremonially)
 lustration:—purification.

g490.d: Ἀντιόχεια Antiócheia, an-tee-okh'-i-ah; from Ἀντίοχυς Antíochys (a Syrian king); Antiochia, a place in Syria:—Antioch.

g4901.d:
συνεπιμαρτυρέω synepimartyréō, soon-ep-ee-mar-too-reh'-o; from G4862 and G1957; to testify further jointly, i.e. unite in adding
 evidence:—also bear witness.
g4901.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἐπιμαρτυρέω (G1957)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4902.d:
συνέπομαι synépomai, soon-ep'-om-ahee; middle voice from G4862 and a primary ἕπω hépō (to follow); to attend
 (travel) in company with:—accompany.
g4902.r: Middle voice from σύν (G4862) and a primary hepo (to follow)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4903.d:
συνεργέω synergéō, soon-erg-eh'-o; from G4904; to be a fellow-worker, i.e. co-operate:—help (work) with,
 work(-er) together.
g4903.r: From συνεργός (G4904)|English: fellowlabourer, helper, fellowhelper, fellowworkers, workfellow, labourer together with, companion in labour

g4904.d:
συνεργός synergós, soon-er-gos'; from a presumed compound of G4862 and the base of G2041; a co-laborer,
 i.e. coadjutor:—companion in labour, (fellow-)helper(-labourer,
 -worker), labourer together with, workfellow.
g4904.r: From a presumed compound of σύν (G4862) and the base of ἔργον (G2041)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4905.d:
συνέρχομαι synérchomai, soon-er'-khom-ahee; from G4862 and G2064; to convene, depart in company with, associate
 with, or (specially), cohabit (conjugally):—accompany, assemble
 (with), come (together), come (company, go) with, resort.
g4905.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἔρχομαι (G2064)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4906.d:
συνεσθίω synesthíō, soon-es-thee'-o; from G4862 and G2068 (including its alternate); to take food in company
 with:—eat with.
g4906.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἐσθίω (G2068) (including its alternate)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4907.d:
σύνεσις sýnesis, soon'-es-is; from G4920; a mental putting together, i.e. intelligence or
 (concretely) the intellect:—knowledge, understanding.
g4907.r: From συνίημι (G4920)|English: understand, consider, be wise

g4908.d:
συνετός synetós, soon-et'-os; from G4920; mentally put (or putting) together, i.e.
 sagacious:—prudent. Compare G5429.
g4908.r: From συνίημι (G4920)|English: understand, consider, be wise

g4909.d:
συνευδοκέω syneudokéō, soon-yoo-dok-eh'-o; from G4862 and G2106; to think well of in common, i.e. assent to, feel
 gratified with:—allow, assent, be pleased, have pleasure.
g4909.r: From σύν (G4862) and εὐδοκέω (G2106)|English: with, beside, accompany

g491.d: Ἀντιοχεύς Antiocheús, an-tee-okh-yoos'; from G490; an Antiochian or inhabitant of Antiochia:—of Antioch.

g4910.d:
†συνευωχέω syneuōchéō, soon-yoo-o-kheh'-o; from G4862 and a derivative of a presumed compound of G2095 and a
 derivative of G2192 (meaning to be in good condition, i.e. (by
 implication) to fare well, or feast); to entertain sumptuously in
 company with, i.e. (middle voice or passive) to revel together:—feast
 with.
g4910.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of a presumed compound of εὖ (G2095) and a derivative of ἔχω (G2192) (meaning to be in good condition, i.e. [by implication] to fare well, or feast)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4911.d:
συνεφίστημι synephístēmi, soon-ef-is'-tay-mee; from G4862 and G2186; to stand up together, i.e. to resist (or assault)
 jointly:—rise up together.
g4911.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἐφίστημι (G2186)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4912.d:
συνέχω synéchō, soon-ekh'-o; from G4862 and G2192; to hold together, i.e. to compress (the ears, with
 a crowd or siege) or arrest (a prisoner); figuratively, to compel,
 perplex, afflict, preoccupy:—constrain, hold, keep in, press, lie
 sick of, stop, be in a strait, straiten, be taken with, throng.
g4912.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἔχω (G2192)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4913.d:
συνήδομαι synḗdomai, soon-ay'-dom-ahee; middle voice from G4862 and the base of G2237; to rejoice in with
 oneself, i.e. feel satisfaction concerning:—delight.
g4913.r: Middle voice from σύν (G4862) and the base of ἡδονή (G2237)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4914.d:
συνήθεια synḗtheia, soon-ay'-thi-ah; from a compound of G4862 and G2239; mutual habituation, i.e.
 usage:—custom.
g4914.r: From a compound of σύν (G4862) and ἦθος (G2239)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4915.d:
συνηλικιώτης synēlikiṓtēs, soon-ay-lik-ee-o'-tace; from G4862 and a derivative of G2244; a co-aged person, i.e. alike in
 years:—equal.
g4915.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of ἡλικία (G2244)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4916.d:
συνθάπτω syntháptō, soon-thap'-to; from G4862 and G2290; to inter in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to
 assimilate spiritually (to Christ by a sepulture as to sin):—bury
 with.
g4916.r: From σύν (G4862) and θάπτω (G2290)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4917.d:
συνθλάω synthláō, soon-thlah'-o; from G4862 and thlao (to crush); to dash together, i.e.
 shatter:—break.
g4917.r: From σύν (G4862) and thlao (to crush)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4918.d: συνθλίβω synthlíbō, soon-thlee'-bo; from G4862 and G2346; to compress, i.e. crowd on all sides:—throng.
g4918.r: From σύν (G4862) and θλίβω (G2346)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4919.d:
συνθρύπτω synthrýptō, soon-throop'-to; from G4862 and θρύπτω thrýptō (to crumble); to crush together, i.e.
 (figuratively) to dispirit:—break.
g4919.r: From σύν (G4862) and thrupto (to crumble)|English: with, beside, accompany

g492.d: ἀντιπαρέρχομαι antiparérchomai, an-tee-par-er'-khom-ahee; from G473 and G3928; to go along opposite:—pass by on the other side.
g492.r: From ἀντί (G473) and παρέρχομαι (G3928)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4920.d:
συνίημι syníēmi, soon-ee'-ay-mee; from G4862 and ἵημι híēmi (to send); to put together, i.e. (mentally) to
 comprehend; by implication, to act piously:—consider, understand, be
 wise.
g4920.r: From σύν (G4862) and hiemi (to send)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4921.d:
συνιστάω synistáō, soon-is-tah'-o; from G4862 and G2476 (including its collateral forms); to set together,
 i.e. (by implication) to introduce (favorably), or (figuratively) to
 exhibit; intransitively, to stand near, or (figuratively) to
 constitute:—approve, commend, consist, make, stand (with).
g4921.r: From σύν (G4862) and ἵστημι (G2476) (including its collat. forms)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4922.d: συνοδεύω synodeúō, soon-od-yoo'-o; from G4862 and G3593; to travel in company with:—journey with.
g4922.r: From σύν (G4862) and ὁδεύω (G3593)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4923.d:
συνοδία synodía, soon-od-ee'-ah; from a compound of G4862 and G3598 ("synod"); companionship on a
 journey, i.e. (by implication), a caravan:—company.
g4923.r: From a compound of σύν (G4862) and ὁδός (G3598) ("synod")|English: with, beside, accompany

g4924.d: συνοικέω synoikéō, soon-oy-keh'-o; from G4862 and G3611; to reside together (as a family):—dwell together.
g4924.r: From σύν (G4862) and οἰκέω (G3611)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4925.d:
συνοικοδομέω synoikodoméō, soon-oy-kod-om-eh'-o; from G4862 and G3618; to construct, i.e. (passively) to compose (in
 company with other Christians, figuratively):—build together.
g4925.r: From σύν (G4862) and οἰκοδομέω (G3618)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4926.d: συνομιλέω synomiléō, soon-om-il-eh'-o; from G4862 and G3656; to converse mutually:—talk with.
g4926.r: From σύν (G4862) and ὁμιλέω (G3656)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4927.d:
συνομορέω synomoréō, soon-om-or-eh'-o; from G4862 and a derivative of a compound of the base of 3674 and the
 base of G3725; to border together, i.e. adjoin:—join hard.
g4927.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of a compound of the base of ὁμοῦ (G3674) and the base of ὅριον (G3725)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4928.d: συνοχή synochḗ, soon-okh-ay'; from G4912; restraint, i.e. (figuratively) anxiety:—anguish, distress.
g4928.r: From συνέχω (G4912)|English: be taken with, throng, straiten, keep in, hold, stop, press, lie sick of, constrain, be in a strait

g4929.d:
συντάσσω syntássō, soon-tas-so; from G4862 and G5021; to arrange jointly, i.e. (figuratively) to
 direct:—appoint.
g4929.r: From σύν (G4862) and τάσσω (G5021)|English: with, beside, accompany

g493.d:
Ἀντίπας Antípas, an-tee'-pas; contracted for a compound of G473 and a derivative of G3962; Antipas, a
 Christian:—Antipas.
g493.r: Contracted for a compound of ἀντί (G473) and a derivative of πατήρ (G3962)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4930.d:
συντέλεια syntéleia, soon-tel'-i-ah; from G4931; entire completion, i.e. consummation (of a
 dispensation):—end.
g4930.r: From συντελέω (G4931)|English: end, fulfil, finish, make

g4931.d:
συντελέω synteléō, soon-tel-eh'-o; from G4862 and G5055; to complete entirely; generally, to execute
 (literally or figuratively):—end, finish, fulfil, make.
g4931.r: From σύν (G4862) and τελέω (G5055)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4932.d:
συντέμνω syntémnō, soon-tem'-no; from G4862 and the base of G5114; to contract by cutting, i.e.
 (figuratively) do concisely (speedily):—(cut) short.
g4932.r: From σύν (G4862) and the base of τομός (G5114)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4933.d:
συντηρέω syntēréō, soon-tay-reh'-o; from G4862 and G5083; to keep closely together, i.e. (by implication) to
 conserve (from ruin); mentally, to remember (and obey):—keep,
 observe, preserve.
g4933.r: From σύν (G4862) and τηρέω (G5083)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4934.d:
†συντίθεμαι syntíthemai, soon-tith'-em-ahee; middle voice from G4862 and G5087; to place jointly, i.e. (figuratively)
 to consent (bargain, stipulate), concur:—agree, assent, covenant.
g4934.r: Middle voice from σύν (G4862) and τίθημι (G5087)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4935.d: συντόμως syntómōs, soon-tom'-oce; adverb from a derivative of G4932; concisely (briefly):—a few words.
g4935.r: From a derivative of συντέμνω (G4932)|English: cut short, short

g4936.d:
συντρέχω syntréchō, soon-trekh'-o; from G4862 and G5143 (including its alternate); to rush together
 (hastily assemble) or headlong (figuratively):—run (together, with).
g4936.r: From σύν (G4862) and τρέχω (G5143) (including its alternate)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4937.d:
συντρίβω syntríbō, soon-tree'-bo; from G4862 and the base of G5147; to crush completely, i.e. to shatter
 (literally or figuratively):—break (in pieces), broken to shivers (+
 -hearted), bruise.
g4937.r: From σύν (G4862) and the base of τρίβος (G5147)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4938.d:
σύντριμμα sýntrimma, soon-trim'-mah; from G4937; concussion or utter fracture (properly, concretely), i.e.
 complete ruin:—destruction.
g4938.r: From συντρίβω (G4937)|English: bruise, break, broken to shivers, brokenhearted, break in pieces

g4939.d:
σύντροφος sýntrophos, soon'-trof-os; from G4862 and G5162 (in a passive sense); a fellow-nursling, i.e.
 comrade:—brought up with.
g4939.r: From σύν (G4862) and τροφός (G5162) (in a passive sense)|English: with, beside, accompany

g494.d: Ἀντιπατρίς Antipatrís, an-tip-at-rece'; from the same as G493; Antipatris, a place in Palestine:—Antipatris.
g494.r: From the same as Ἀντίπας (G493)|English: Antipas

g4940.d:
συντυγχάνω syntynchánō, soon-toong-khan'-o; from G4862 and G5177; to chance together, i.e. meet with (reach):—come
 at.
g4940.r: From σύν (G4862) and τυγχάνω (G5177)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4941.d: Συντύχη Syntýchē, soon-too'-khay; from G4940; an accident; Syntyche, a Christian female:—Syntyche.

g4942.d:
συνυποκρίνομαι synypokrínomai, soon-oo-pok-rin'-om-ahee; from G4862 and G5271; to act hypocritically in concert with:—dissemble
 with.
g4942.r: From σύν (G4862) and ὑποκρίνομαι (G5271)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4943.d:
συνυπουργέω synypourgéō, soon-oop-oorg-eh'-o; from G4862 and a derivative of a compound of G5259 and the base of G2041; 
 to be a co-auxiliary, i.e. assist:—help together.
g4943.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of a compound of ὑπό (G5259) and the base of ἔργον (G2041)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4944.d:
συνωδίνω synōdínō, soon-o-dee'-no; from G4862 and G5605; to have (parturition) pangs in company (concert,
 simultaneously) with, i.e. (figuratively) to sympathize (in
 expectation of relief from suffering):—travail in pain together.
g4944.r: From σύν (G4862) and ὠδίνω (G5605)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4945.d:
συνωμοσία synōmosía, soon-o-mos-ee'-ah; from a compound of G4862 and G3660; a swearing together, i.e. (by
 implication) a plot:—comspiracy.
g4945.r: From a compound of σύν (G4862) and ὀμνύω (G3660)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4946.d:
Συράκουσαι Syrákousai, soo-rak'-oo-sahee; plural of uncertain derivation; Syracuse, the capital of
 Sicily:—Syracuse.

g4947.d:
Συρία Syría, soo-ree'-ah; probably of Hebrew origin (H6865); Syria (i.e. Tsyria or Tyre), a
 region of Asia:—Syria.
g4947.r: Probably of Hebrew origin צֹר (H6865)|English: Tyrus, Tyre

g4948.d:
Σύρος Sýros, soo'-ros; from the same as G4947; a Syran (i.e. probably Tyrian), a native of
 Syria:—Syrian.
g4948.r: From the same as Συρία (G4947)|English: Syria

g4949.d:
†Συροφοίνισσα Syrophoínissa, soo-rof-oy'-nis-sah; feminine of a compound of G4948 and the same as G5403; a Syro-phœnician
 woman, i.e. a female native of Phœnicia in Syria:—Syrophenician.
g4949.r: From a compound of Σύρος (G4948) and the same as Φοινίκη (G5403)|English: Syrian

g495.d: †ἀντιπέραν antipéran, an-tee-per'-an; from G473 and G4008; on the opposite side:—over against.
g495.r: From ἀντί (G473) and πέραν (G4008)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4950.d:
σύρτις sýrtis, soor'-tis; from G4951; a shoal (from the sand drawn thither by the waves), i.e.
 the Syrtis Major or great bay on the north coast of
 Africa:—quicksands.

g4951.d: σύρω sýrō, soo'-ro; probably akin to G138; to trail:—drag, draw, hale.
g4951.r: Probably akin to αἱρέω (G138); to trail|English: choose

g4952.d:
συσπαράσσω sysparássō, soos-par-as'-so; from G4862 and G4682; to rend completely, i.e. (by analogy) to convulse
 violently:—throw down.
g4952.r: From σύν (G4862) and σπαράσσω (G4682)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4953.d:
σύσσημον sýssēmon, soos'-say-mon; neuter of a compound of G4862 and the base of G4591; a sign in common,
 i.e. preconcerted signal:—token.
g4953.r: From a compound of σύν (G4862) and the base of σημαίνω (G4591)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4954.d:
σύσσωμος sýssōmos, soos'-so-mos; from G4862 and G4983; of a joint body, i.e. (figuratively) a
 fellow-member of the Christian community:—of the same body.
g4954.r: From σύν (G4862) and σῶμα (G4983)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4956.d:
συστατικός systatikós, soos-tat-ee-kos'; from a derivative of G4921; introductory, i.e. recommendatory:—of
 commendation.
g4956.r: From a derivative of συνίστημι (G4921)|English: commend, approve, consist, make, stand, stand with

g4957.d:
συσταυρόω systauróō, soos-tow-ro'-o; from G4862 and G4717; to impale in company with (literally or
 figuratively):—crucify with.
g4957.r: From σύν (G4862) and σταυρόω (G4717)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4958.d:
συστέλλω systéllō, soos-tel'-lo; from G4862 and G4724; to send (draw) together, i.e. enwrap (enshroud a
 corpse for burial), contract (an interval):—short, wind up.
g4958.r: From σύν (G4862) and στέλλω (G4724)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4959.d:
συστενάζω systenázō, soos-ten-ad'-zo; from G4862 and G4727; to moan jointly, i.e. (figuratively) experience a
 common calamity:—groan together.
g4959.r: From σύν (G4862) and στενάζω (G4727)|English: with, beside, accompany

g496.d: ἀντιπίπτω antipíptō, an-tee-pip'-to; from G473 and G4098 (including its alternate); to oppose:—resist.
g496.r: From ἀντί (G473) and πίπτω (G4098) (including its alternate)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4960.d:
συστοιχέω systoichéō, soos-toy-kheh'-o; from G4862 and G4748; to file together (as soldiers in ranks), i.e.
 (figuratively) to correspond to:—answer to.
g4960.r: From σύν (G4862) and στοιχέω (G4748)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4961.d:
συστρατιώτης systratiṓtēs, soos-trat-ee-o'-tace; from G4862 and G4757; a co-campaigner, i.e. (figuratively) an associate
 in Christian toil:—fellowsoldier.
g4961.r: From σύν (G4862) and στρατιώτης (G4757)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4962.d:
συστρέφω systréphō, soos-tref'-o; from G4862 and G4762; to twist together, i.e. collect (a bundle, a
 crowd):—gather.
g4962.r: From σύν (G4862) and στρέφω (G4762)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4963.d:
συστροφή systrophḗ, soos-trof-ay'; from G4962; a twisting together, i.e. (figuratively) a secret
 coalition, riotous crowd:—+ band together, concourse.

g4964.d:
συσχηματίζω syschēmatízō, soos-khay-mat-id'-zo; from G4862 and a derivative of G4976; to fashion alike, i.e. conform to
 the same pattern (figuratively):—conform to, fashion self according
 to.
g4964.r: From σύν (G4862) and a derivative of σχῆμα (G4976)|English: with, beside, accompany

g4965.d:
Συχάρ Sychár, soo-khar'; of Hebrew origin (H7941); Sychar (i.e. Shekar), a place in
 Palestine:—Sychar.
g4965.r: Of Hebrew origin שֵׁכָר (H7941)|English: strong drink, strong wine, drunkard

g4966.d:
†Συχέμ Sychém, soo-khem'; of Hebrew origin (H7927); Sychem (i.e. Shekem), the name of a Canaanite
 and of a place in Palestine:—Sychem.
g4966.r: Of Hebrew origin שְׁכֶם (H7927)|English: Shechem, Sichem, Strong's synonym for consent

g4967.d:
σφαγή sphagḗ, sfag-ay'; from G4969; butchery (of animals for food or sacrifice, or
 (figuratively) of men (destruction)):—slaughter.

g4968.d: σφάγιον sphágion, sfag'-ee-on; neuter of a derivative of G4967; a victim (in sacrifice):—slain beast.
g4968.r: From a derivative of σφαγή (G4967)|English: slaughter

g4969.d:
σφάζω spházō, sfad'-zo; a primary verb; to butcher (especially an animal for food or in
 sacrifice) or (generally) to slaughter, or (specially), to maim
 (violently):—kill, slay, wound.

g497.d:
ἀντιστρατεύομαι antistrateúomai, an-tee-strat-yoo'-om-ahee; from G473 and G4754; (figuratively) to attack, i.e. (by implication)
 destroy:—war against.
g497.r: From ἀντί (G473) and στρατεύω (G4754)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4970.d:
σφόδρα sphódra, sfod'-rah; neuter plural of σφοδρός sphodrós (violent; of uncertain derivation) as
 adverb; vehemently, i.e. in a high degree, much:—exceeding(-ly),
 greatly, sore, very.
g4970.r: Neuter plural of sphodros (violent, of uncertain derivation) as adverb|

g4971.d: σφοδρῶς sphodrōs, sfod-roce'; adverb from the same as G4970; very much:—exceedingly.
g4971.r: From the same as σφόδρα (G4970)|English: exceeding, very, greatly, exceedingly, sore

g4972.d:
σφραγίζω sphragízō, sfrag-id'-zo; from G4973; to stamp (with a signet or private mark) for security or
 preservation (literally or figuratively); by implication, to keep
 secret, to attest:—(set a, set to) seal up, stop.

g4973.d:
σφραγίς sphragís, sfrag-ece'; probably strengthened from G5420; a signet (as fencing in or protecting
 from misappropriation); by implication, the stamp impressed (as a mark
 of privacy, or genuineness), literally or figuratively:—seal.

g4974.d:
†σφυρόν sphyrón, sfoo-ron'; neuter of a presumed derivative probably of the same as
 σφαῖρα sphaîra (a ball, "sphere"; compare the feminine σφῦρα sphŷra, a
 hammer); the ankle (as globular):—ancle bone.
g4974.r: From a presumed derivative probably of the same as sphaira (a ball, "sphere", cf the feminine sphura, a hammer)|

g4975.d:
σχεδόν schedón, skhed-on'; neuter of a presumed derivative of the alternate of G2192 as adverb; 
 nigh, i.e. nearly:—almost.
g4975.r: Neuter of a presumed derivative of the alternate of ἔχω (G2192) as adverb|English: have, be, need, misc

g4976.d:
σχῆμα schēma, skhay'-mah; from the alternate of G2192; a figure (as a mode or circumstance), i.e.
 (by implication) external condition:—fashion.
g4976.r: From the alternate of ἔχω (G2192)|English: have, be, need, misc

g4977.d:
σχίζω schízō, skhid'-zo; apparently a primary verb; to split or sever (literally or
 figuratively):—break, divide, open, rend, make a rent.

g4978.d:
σχίσμα schísma, skhis'-mah; from G4977; a split or gap ("schism"), literally or
 figuratively:—division, rent, schism.
g4978.r: From σχίζω (G4977)|English: rend, divide, open, break, make a rent

g4979.d:
σχοινίον schoiníon, skhoy-nee'-on; diminutive of σχοῖνος schoînos (a rush or flag-plant; of uncertain
 derivation); a rushlet, i.e. grass-withe or tie (generally):—small
 cord, rope.
g4979.r: Diminutive of schoinos (a rush or flag-plant, of uncertain derivation)|

g498.d:
†ἀντιτάσσομαι antitássomai, an-tee-tas'-som-ahee; from G473 and the middle voice of G5021; to range oneself against, i.e.
 oppose:—oppose themselves, resist.
g498.r: From ἀντί (G473) and the middle voice of τάσσω (G5021)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4980.d:
σχολάζω scholázō, skhol-ad'-zo; from G4981; to take a holiday, i.e. be at leisure for (by implication,
 devote oneself wholly to); figuratively, to be vacant (of a
 house):—empty, give self.

g4981.d:
σχολή scholḗ, skhol-ay'; probably feminine of a presumed derivative of the alternate of G2192; 
 properly, loitering (as a withholding of oneself from work) or
 leisure, i.e. (by implication) a "school" (as vacation from physical
 employment):—school.
g4981.r: Probably feminine of a presumed derivative of the alternate of ἔχω (G2192)|English: have, be, need, misc

g4982.d:
†σώζω sṓzō, sode'-zo; from a primary σῶς sōs (contraction for obsolete σάος sáos, "safe"); to save,
 i.e. deliver or protect (literally or figuratively):—heal, preserve,
 save (self), do well, be (make) whole.
g4982.r: From a primary sos (contraction for obsolete saoz, "safe")|

g4983.d:
σῶμα sōma, so'-mah; from G4982; the body (as a sound whole), used in a very wide
 application, literally or figuratively:—bodily, body, slave.
g4983.r: From σῴζω (G4982)|English: save, make whole, heal, be whole, misc

g4984.d: σωματικός sōmatikós, so-mat-ee-kos'; from G4983; corporeal or physical:—bodily.

g4985.d: σωματικῶς sōmatikōs, so-mat-ee-koce'; adverb from G4984; corporeally or physically:—bodily.

g4986.d:
Σώπατρος Sṓpatros, so'-pat-ros; from the base of G4982 and G3962; of a safe father; Sopatrus, a
 Christian:—Sopater. Compare G4989.
g4986.r: From the base of σῴζω (G4982) and πατήρ (G3962)|English: save, make whole, heal, be whole, misc

g4987.d:
σωρεύω sōreúō, sore-yoo'-o; from another form of G4673; to pile up (literally or
 figuratively):—heap, load.
g4987.r: From another form of σορός (G4673)|English: bier

g4988.d:
Σωσθένης Sōsthénēs, soce-then'-ace; from the base of G4982 and that of G4599; of safe strength; Sosthenes, a
 Christian:—Sosthenes.
g4988.r: From the base of σῴζω (G4982) and that of σθενόω (G4599)|English: save, make whole, heal, be whole, misc

g4989.d: Σωσίπατρος Sōsípatros, so-sip'-at-ros; prolongation for G4986; Sosipatrus, a Christian:—Sosipater.

g499.d:
†ἀντίτυπον antítypon, an-teet'-oo-pon; neuter of a compound of G473 and G5179; corresponding ("antitype"), i.e.
 a representative, counterpart:—(like) figure (whereunto).
g499.r: Neuter of a compound of ἀντί (G473) and τύπος (G5179)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g4990.d: σωτήρ sōtḗr, so-tare'; from G4982; a deliverer, i.e. God or Christ:—saviour.
g4990.r: From σῴζω (G4982)|English: save, make whole, heal, be whole, misc

g4991.d:
σωτηρία sōtēría, so-tay-ree'-ah; feminine of a derivative of G4990 as (properly, abstract) noun; rescue
 or safety (physically or morally):—deliver, health, salvation, save,
 saving.
g4991.r: Feminine of a derivative of σωτήρ (G4990) as (properly, abstract) noun|English: Saviour

g4992.d:
†σωτήριον sōtḗrion, so-tay'-ree-on; neuter of the same as G4991 as (properly, concretely) noun; defender or
 (by implication) defence:—salvation.
g4992.r: Neuter of the same as σωτηρία (G4991) as (properly, concretely) noun|English: salvation, the (one) be saved, deliver, health, saving, that (one) be saved

g4993.d:
σωφρονέω sōphronéō, so-fron-eh'-o; from G4998; to be of sound mind, i.e. sane, (figuratively)
 moderate:—be in right mind, be sober (minded), soberly.

g4994.d:
σωφρονίζω sōphronízō, so-fron-id'-zo; from G4998; to make of sound mind, i.e. (figuratively) to discipline or
 correct:—teach to be sober.

g4995.d: σωφρονισμός sōphronismós, so-fron-is-mos'; from G4994; discipline, i.e. self-control:—sound mind.
g4995.r: From σωφρονίζω (G4994)|English: teach to be sober

g4996.d: σωφρόνως sōphrónōs, so-fron'-oce; adverb from G4998; with sound mind, i.e. moderately:—soberly.

g4997.d:
σωφροσύνη sōphrosýnē, so-fros-oo'-nay; from G4998; soundness of mind, i.e. (literally) sanity or
 (figuratively) self-control:—soberness, sobriety.

g4998.d:
σώφρων sṓphrōn, so'-frone; from the base of G4982 and that of G5424; safe (sound) in mind, i.e.
 self-controlled (moderate as to opinion or passion):—discreet, sober,
 temperate.
g4998.r: From the base of σῴζω (G4982) and that of φρήν (G5424)|English: save, make whole, heal, be whole, misc

g4999.d:
†Ταβέρναι Tabérnai, tab-er'-nahee; plural of Latin origin; huts or wooden-walled buildings;
 Tabernæ:—taverns.

g5.d: Ἀββᾶ Abbâ, ab-bah'; of Chaldee origin (H2); father as a vocative:—Abba.

g50.d:
ἀγνοέω agnoéō, ag-no-eh'-o; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3539; not to know (through lack of
 information or intelligence); by implication, to ignore (through
 disinclination):—(be) ignorant(-ly), not know, not understand,
 unknown.
g50.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and νοέω (G3539)|English: Alpha

g500.d: ἀντίχριστος antíchristos, an-tee'-khris-tos; from G473 and G5547; an opponent of the Messiah:—antichrist.
g500.r: From ἀντί (G473) and Χριστός (G5547)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g5000.d:
Ταβιθά Tabithá, tab-ee-thah'; of Chaldee origin (compare H6646); the gazelle; Tabitha (i.e.
 Tabjetha), a Christian female:—Tabitha.
g5000.r: Of Aramaic origin cf צְבִיָּה (H6646)|English: roe

g5001.d:
τάγμα tágma, tag'-mah; from G5021; something orderly in arrangement (a troop), i.e.
 (figuratively) a series or succession:—order.
g5001.r: From τάσσω (G5021)|English: appoint, ordain, set, determine, addict

g5002.d: τακτός taktós, tak-tos'; from G5021; arranged, i.e. appointed or stated:—set.
g5002.r: From τάσσω (G5021)|English: appoint, ordain, set, determine, addict

g5003.d:
ταλαιπωρέω talaipōréō, tal-ahee-po-reh'-o; from G5005; to be wretched, i.e. realize one's own misery:—be
 afflicted.

g5004.d: ταλαιπωρία talaipōría, tal-ahee-po-ree'-ah; from G5005; wretchedness, i.e. calamity:—misery.

g5005.d:
ταλαίπωρος talaípōros, tal-ah'-ee-po-ros; from the base of G5007 and a derivative of the base of G3984; enduring
 trial, i.e. miserable:—wretched.
g5005.r: From the base of τάλαντον (G5007) and a derivative of the base of πεῖρα (G3984)|English: talent

g5006.d: ταλαντιαῖος talantiaîos, tal-an-tee-ah'-yos; from G5007; talent-like in weight:—weight of a talent.

g5007.d:
τάλαντον tálanton, tal'-an-ton; neuter of a presumed derivative of the original form of τλάω tláō (to bear; 
 equivalent to G5342); a balance (as supporting weights), i.e. (by
 implication) a certain weight (and thence a coin or rather sum of
 money) or "talent":—talent.
g5007.r: From a presumed derivative of the original form of tlao (to bear, equivalent to φέρω (G5342))|English: bring, bear, bring forth, come, reach, endure, carry, misc

g5008.d:
ταλιθά talithá, tal-ee-thah'; of Chaldee origin (compare H2924); the fresh, i.e. young girl; talitha
 (O maiden):—talitha.
g5008.r: Of Aramaic origin cf טָלֶה (H2924)|English: lamb

g5009.d:
ταμεῖον tameîon, tam-i'-on; neuter contraction of a presumed derivative of ταμίας tamías (a dispenser or
 distributor; akin to τέμνω témnō, to cut); a dispensary or magazine, i.e. a
 chamber on the ground-floor or interior of an Oriental house
 (generally used for storage or privacy, a spot for
 retirement):—secret chamber, closet, storehouse.
g5009.r: Contraction of a presumed derivative of tamias (a dispenser or distributor|

g501.d:
ἀντλέω antléō, ant-leh-o; from ἄντλος ántlos (the hold of a ship); to bale up (properly, bilge water),
 i.e. dip water (with a bucket, pitcher, etc.):—draw (out).
g501.r: From antlos (the hold of a ship)|

g5010.d:
τάξις táxis, tax'-is; from G5021; regular arrangement, i.e. (in time) fixed succession (of
 rank or character), official dignity:—order.
g5010.r: From τάσσω (G5021)|English: appoint, ordain, set, determine, addict

g5011.d:
ταπεινός tapeinós, tap-i-nos'; of uncertain derivation; depressed, i.e. (figuratively) humiliated (in
 circumstances or disposition):—base, cast down, humble, of low degree
 (estate), lowly.

g5012.d:
ταπεινοφροσύνη tapeinophrosýnē, tap-i-nof-ros-oo'-nay; from a compound of G5011 and the base of G5424; humiliation of mind,
 i.e. modesty:—humbleness of mind, humility (of mind, loneliness (of
 mind).
g5012.r: From a compound of ταπεινός (G5011) and the base of φρήν (G5424)|English: of low degree, humble, base, cast down, of low estate, lowly

g5013.d:
ταπεινόω tapeinóō, tap-i-no'-o; from G5011; to depress; figuratively, to humiliate (in condition or
 heart):—abase, bring low, humble (self).
g5013.r: From ταπεινός (G5011)|English: of low degree, humble, base, cast down, of low estate, lowly

g5014.d:
ταπείνωσις tapeínōsis, tap-i'-no-sis; from G5013; depression (in rank or feeling):—humiliation, be made low,
 low estate, vile.
g5014.r: From ταπεινόω (G5013)|English: humble, abase, humble (one's) self, bring low

g5015.d: ταράσσω tarássō, tar-as'-so; of uncertain affinity; to stir or agitate (roil water):—trouble.

g5017.d: τάραχος tárachos, tar'-akh-os; masculine from G5015; a disturbance, i.e. (popular) tumult:—stir.

g5018.d: Ταρσεύς Tarseús, tar-syoos'; from G5019; a Tarsean, i.e. native of Tarsus:—of Tarsus.

g5019.d:
Ταρσός Tarsós, tar-sos'; perhaps the same as ταρσός tarsós (a flat basket); Tarsus, a place in Asia
 Minor:—Tarsus.
g5019.r: Perhaps the same as tarsos (a flat basket)|

g502.d: ἄντλημα ántlēma, ant'-lay-mah; from G501; a baling-vessel:—thing to draw with.

g5020.d:
ταρταρόω tartaróō, tar-tar-o'-o; from Τάρταρος Tártaros (the deepest abyss of Hades); to incarcerate in eternal
 torment:—cast down to hell.
g5020.r: From Tartaros (the deepest abyss of Hell)|

g5021.d:
τάσσω tássō, tas'-so; a prolonged form of a primary verb (which latter appears only in
 certain tenses); to arrange in an orderly manner, i.e. assign or
 dispose (to a certain position or lot):—addict, appoint, determine,
 ordain, set.
g5021.r: A prolonged form of a primary verb (which latter appears only in certain tenses)|

g5022.d:
ταῦρος taûros, tow'-ros; apparently a primary word (compare H8450, "steer"); a bullock:—bull,
 ox.

g5023.d:
ταῦτα taûta, tow'-tah; nominative or accusative case neuter plural of G3778; these things:—+
 afterward, follow, + hereafter, × him, the same, so, such, that, then,
 these, they, this, those, thus.
g5023.r: Nominative or accusative case neuter plural of οὗτος (G3778)|English: this, these, he, the same, this man, she, they, misc

g5027.d: ταφή taphḗ, taf-ay'; feminine from G2290; burial (the act):—X bury.

g5028.d:
τάφος táphos, taf'-os; masculine from G2290; a grave (the place of interment):—sepulchre,
 tomb.

g5029.d:
τάχα tácha, takh'-ah; as if neuter plural of G5036 (adverbially); shortly, i.e.
 (figuratively) possibly:—peradventure(-haps).
g5029.r: As if neuter plural of ταχύς (G5036) (adverbially)|English: swift

g503.d: ἀντοφθαλμέω antophthalméō, ant-of-thal-meh'-o; from a compound of G473 and G3788; to face:—bear up into.
g503.r: From a compound of ἀντί (G473) and ὀφθαλμός (G3788)|English: for, because, for ... cause, therefore, in the room of

g5030.d:
ταχέως tachéōs, takh-eh'-oce; adverb from G5036; briefly, i.e. (in time) speedily, or (in manner)
 rapidly:—hastily, quickly, shortly, soon, suddenly.

g5031.d: ταχινός tachinós, takh-ee-nos'; from G5034; curt, i.e. impending:—shortly, swift.

g5032.d:
τάχιον táchion, takh'-ee-on; neuter singular of the comparative of G5036 (as adverb); more swiftly,
 i.e. (in manner) more rapidly, or (in time) more speedily:—out (run),
 quickly, shortly, sooner.
g5032.r: Comparative of ταχέως (G5030)|English: shortly, quickly, soon, hastily, suddenly

g5034.d:
τάχος táchos, takh'-os; from the same as G5036; a brief space (of time), i.e. (with G1722
 prefixed) in haste:—+ quickly, + shortly, + speedily.
g5034.r: From the same as ταχύς (G5036)|English: swift

g5035.d:
ταχύ tachý, takh-oo'; neuter singular of G5036 (as adverb); shortly, i.e. without delay,
 soon, or (by surprise) suddenly, or (by implication, of ease)
 readily:—lightly, quickly.
g5035.r: Neuter singular of ταχύς (G5036) (as adverb)|English: swift

g5036.d:
ταχύς tachýs, takh-oos'; of uncertain affinity; fleet, i.e. (figuratively) prompt or
 ready:—swift.

g5037.d:
τέ té, teh; a primary particle (enclitic) of connection or addition; both or also
 (properly, as correlation of G2532):—also, and, both, even, then,
 whether. Often used in composition, usually as the latter participle.
g5037.r: A primary particle (enclitic) of connection or addition|

g5038.d: τεῖχος teîchos, ti'-khos; akin to the base of G5088; a wall (as formative of a house):—wall.
g5038.r: Akin to the base of τίκτω (G5088)|English: bring forth, be delivered, be born, be in travail, bear

g5039.d:
τεκμήριον tekmḗrion, tek-may'-ree-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of τεκμάρ tekmár (a goal or fixed limit); a
 token (as defining a fact), i.e. criterion of certainty:—infallible
 proof.
g5039.r: From a presumed derivative of tekmar (a goal or fixed limit)|

g504.d:
ἄνυδρος ánydros, an'-oo-dros; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G5204; waterless, i.e. dry:—dry,
 without water.
g504.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and ὕδωρ (G5204)|English: Alpha

g5040.d:
τεκνίον tekníon, tek-nee'-on; diminutive of G5043; an infant, i.e. (plural figuratively) darlings
 (Christian converts):—little children.
g5040.r: Diminutive of τέκνον (G5043)|English: child, son, daughter

g5041.d:
τεκνογονέω teknogonéō, tek-nog-on-eh'-o; from a compound of G5043 and the base of G1096; to be a child-bearer,
 i.e. parent (mother):—bear children.
g5041.r: From a compound of τέκνον (G5043) and the base of γίνομαι (G1096)|English: child, son, daughter

g5042.d:
τεκνογονία teknogonía, tek-nog-on-ee'-ah; from the same as G5041; childbirth (parentage), i.e. (by implication)
 maternity (the performance of maternal duties):—childbearing.
g5042.r: From the same as τεκνογονέω (G5041)|English: bear children

g5043.d: τέκνον téknon, tek'-non; from the base of G5098; a child (as produced):—child, daughter, son.
g5043.r: From the base of τιμωρία (G5098)|English: punishment

g5044.d:
τεκνοτροφέω teknotrophéō, tek-not-rof-eh'-o; from a compound of G5043 and G5142; to be a childrearer, i.e. fulfil the
 duties of a female parent:—bring up children.
g5044.r: From a compound of τέκνον (G5043) and τρέφω (G5142)|English: child, son, daughter

g5045.d:
τέκτων téktōn, tek'-tone; from the base of G5098; an artificer (as producer of fabrics), i.e.
 (specially), a craftsman in wood:—carpenter.
g5045.r: From the base of τιμωρία (G5098)|English: punishment

g5046.d:
τέλειος téleios, tel'-i-os; from G5056; complete (in various applications of labor, growth, mental
 and moral character, etc.); neuter (as noun, with G3588)
 completeness:—of full age, man, perfect.
g5046.r: From τέλος (G5056)|English: end, custom, uttermost, finally, ending, by (one's) continual

g5047.d:
τελειότης teleiótēs, tel-i-ot'-ace; from G5046; (the state) completeness (mentally or
 morally):—perfection(-ness).
g5047.r: From τέλειος (G5046)|English: perfect, man, of full age

g5048.d:
τελειόω teleióō, tel-i-o'-o; from G5046; to complete, i.e. (literally) accomplish, or (figuratively)
 consummate (in character):—consecrate, finish, fulfil, make) perfect.
g5048.r: From τέλειος (G5046)|English: perfect, man, of full age

g5049.d:
τελείως teleíōs, tel-i'-oce; adverb from G5046; completely, i.e. (of hope) without wavering:—to the
 end.
g5049.r: From τέλειος (G5046)|English: perfect, man, of full age

g505.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of ὑποκρίνομαι (G5271)|English: Alpha

g5050.d:
τελείωσις teleíōsis, tel-i'-o-sis; from G5448; (the act) completion, i.e. (of prophecy) verification, or
 (of expiation) absolution:—perfection, performance.
g5050.r: From τελειόω (G5048)|English: make perfect, perfect, finish, fulfil, be perfect, consecrate

g5051.d: τελειωτής teleiōtḗs, tel-i-o-tace'; from G5048; a completer, i.e. consummater:—finisher.
g5051.r: From τελειόω (G5048)|English: make perfect, perfect, finish, fulfil, be perfect, consecrate

g5052.d:
τελεσφορέω telesphoréō, tel-es-for-eh'-o; from a compound of G5056 and G5342; to be a bearer to completion
 (maturity), i.e. to ripen fruit (figuratively):—bring fruit to
 perfection.
g5052.r: From a compound of τέλος (G5056) and φέρω (G5342)|English: end, custom, uttermost, finally, ending, by (one's) continual

g5053.d:
τελευτάω teleutáō, tel-yoo-tah'-o; from a presumed derivative of G5055; to finish life (by implication, of
 G979), i.e. expire (demise):—be dead, decease, die.
g5053.r: From a presumed derivative of τελέω (G5055)|English: finish, fulfil, accomplish, pay, perform, expire, misc

g5054.d: τελευτή teleutḗ, tel-yoo-tay'; from G5053; decease:—death.
g5054.r: From τελευτάω (G5053)|English: die, be dead, decrease

g5055.d:
τελέω teléō, tel-eh'-o; from G5056; to end, i.e. complete, execute, conclude, discharge (a
 debt):—accomplish, make an end, expire, fill up, finish, go over,
 pay, perform.
g5055.r: From τέλος (G5056)|English: end, custom, uttermost, finally, ending, by (one's) continual

g5056.r: From a primary tello (to set out for a definite point or goal)|

g5057.d:
τελώνης telṓnēs, tel-o'-nace; from G5056 and G5608; a tax-farmer, i.e. collector of public
 revenue:—publican.
g5057.r: From τέλος (G5056) and ὠνέομαι (G5608)|English: end, custom, uttermost, finally, ending, by (one's) continual

g5058.d:
τελώνιον telṓnion, tel-o'-nee-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of G5057; a tax-gatherer's place of
 business:—receipt of custom.
g5058.r: From a presumed derivative of τελώνης (G5057)|English: publican

g5059.d: τέρας téras, ter'-as; of uncertain affinity; a prodigy or omen:—wonder.

g506.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of ὑποτάσσω (G5293)|English: Alpha

g5060.d: Τέρτιος Tértios, ter'-tee-os; of Latin origin; third; Tertius, a Christian:—Tertius.

g5061.d: Τέρτυλλος Tértyllos, ter'-tool-los; of uncertain derivation; Tertullus, a Roman:—Tertullus.

g5064.d: τέσσαρες téssares, tes'-sar-es; a plural number; four:—four.

g5065.d: τεσσαρεσκαιδέκατος tessareskaidékatos, tes-sar-es-kahee-dek'-at-os; from G5064 and G2532 and G1182; fourteenth:—fourteenth.
