φοβερός phoberós, fob-er-os'; from G5401; frightful, i.e. (objectively) formidable:—fearful,
 terrible.

g5399.d:
φοβέω phobéō, fob-eh'-o; from G5401; to frighten, i.e. (passively) to be alarmed; by analogy, to
 be in awe of, i.e. revere:—be (+ sore) afraid, fear (exceedingly),
 reverence.

g54.d:
ἁγνότης hagnótēs, hag-not'-ace; from G53; cleanness (the state), i.e. (figuratively)
 blamelessness:—pureness.

g540.d:
ἀπάτωρ apátōr, ap-at'-ore; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3962; fatherless, i.e. of
 unrecorded paternity:—without father.
g540.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and πατήρ (G3962)|English: Alpha

g5400.d:
φόβητρον phóbētron, fob'-ay-tron; neuter of a derivative of G5399; a frightening thing, i.e. terrific
 portent:—fearful sight.
g5400.r: From a derivative of φοβέω (G5399)|English: fear, be afraid, be afraid of, reverence, misc

g5401.d:
φόβος phóbos, fob'-os; from a primary φέβομαι phébomai (to be put in fear); alarm or fright:—be
 afraid, + exceedingly, fear, terror.
g5401.r: From a primary phebomai (to be put in fear)|

g5402.d:
Φοίβη Phoíbē, foy'-bay; feminine of φοῖβος phoîbos (bright; probably akin to the base of G5457);
 Phœbe, a Christian woman:—Phebe.
g5402.r: From phoibos (bright, probably akin to the base of φῶς (G5457))|English: light, fire

g5403.d:
Φοινίκη Phoiníkē, foy-nee'-kay; from G5404; palm-country; Phœnice (or Phœnicia), a region of
 Palestine:—Phenice, Phenicia.

g5404.d: †φοῖνιξ phoînix, foy'-nix; of uncertain derivation; a palm-tree:—palm (tree).

g5405.d: Φοῖνιξ Phoînix, foy'-nix; probably the same as G5404; Phœnix, a place in Crete:—Phenice.
g5405.r: Probably the same as φοῖνιξ/φοίνιξ (G5404)|English: palm tree, palm

g5406.d:
φονεύς phoneús, fon-yooce'; from G5408; a murderer (always of criminal (or at least intentional)
 homicide; which G443 does not necessarily imply; while G4607 is a
 special term for a public bandit):—murderer.
g5406.r: From φόνος (G5408)|English: murder, slaughter, be slain

g5407.d: φονεύω phoneúō, fon-yoo'-o; from G5406; to be a murderer (of):—kill, do murder, slay.

g5408.d:
φόνος phónos, fon'-os; from an obsolete primary φένω phénō (to slay); murder:—murder, + be slain
 with, slaughter.
g5408.r: From an obsolete primary pheno (to murder)|

g5409.d:
φορέω phoréō, for-eh'-o; from G5411; to have a burden, i.e. (by analogy) to wear as clothing or
 a constant accompaniment:—bear, wear.

g541.d:
ἀπαύγασμα apaúgasma, ap-ow'-gas-mah; from a compound of G575 and G826; an off-flash, i.e.
 effulgence:—brightness.
g541.r: From a compound of ἀπό (G575) and αὐγάζω (G826)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5411.d:
φόρος phóros, for'-os; from G5342; a load (as borne), i.e. (figuratively) a tax (properly, an
 individual assessment on persons or property; whereas G5056 is usually
 a general toll on goods or travel):—tribute.
g5411.r: From φέρω (G5342)|English: bring, bear, bring forth, come, reach, endure, carry, misc

g5412.d:
φορτίζω phortízō, for-tid'-zo; from G5414; to load up (properly, as a vessel or animal), i.e.
 (figuratively) to overburden with ceremony (or spiritual
 anxiety):—lade, by heavy laden.

g5413.d:
φορτίον phortíon, for-tee'-on; diminutive of G5414; an invoice (as part of freight), i.e.
 (figuratively) a task or service:—burden.

g5415.d: Φορτουνᾶτος Phortounâtos, for-too-nat'-os; of Latin origin; "fortunate"; Fortunatus, a Christian:—Fortunatus.

g5416.d:
φραγέλλιον phragéllion, frag-el'-le-on; neuter of a derivative from the base of G5417; a whip, i.e. Roman lash
 as a public punishment:—scourge.
g5416.r: From a derivative from the base of φραγελλόω (G5417)|English: scourge

g5417.d:
φραγελλόω phragellóō, frag-el-lo'-o; from a presumed equivalent of the Latin flagellum; to whip, i.e. lash
 as a public punishment:—scourge.
g5417.r: From a presumed equivalent of the Latin flagellum|

g5418.d:
φραγμός phragmós, frag-mos'; from G5420; a fence, or inclosing barrier (literally or
 figuratively):—hedge (+ round about), partition.

g5419.d:
φράζω phrázō, frad'-zo; probably akin to G5420 through the idea of defining; to indicate (by
 word or act), i.e. (specially), to expound:—declare.
g5419.r: Probably akin to φράσσω (G5420) through the idea of defining|English: stop

g5420.d:
φράσσω phrássō, fras'-so; apparently a strengthening form of the base of G5424; to fence or
 inclose, i.e. (specially), to block up (figuratively, to
 silence):—stop.
g5420.r: Apparently a strengthening form of the base of φρήν (G5424)|English: understanding

g5422.d: φρεναπατάω phrenapatáō, fren-ap-at-ah'-o; from G5423; to be a mind-misleader, i.e. delude:—deceive.

g5423.d: φρεναπάτης phrenapátēs, fren-ap-at'-ace; from G5424 and G539; a mind-misleader, i.e. seducer:—deceiver.

g5424.d:
φρήν phrḗn, frane; probably from an obsolete φράω phráō (to rein in or curb; compare G5420); 
 the midrif (as a partition of the body), i.e. (figuratively and by
 implication, of sympathy) the feelings (or sensitive nature; by
 extension (also in the plural) the mind or cognitive
 faculties):—understanding.
g5424.r: Probably from an obsolete phrao (to rein in or curb, cf φράσσω (G5420))|English: stop

g5425.d:
φρίσσω phríssō, fris'-so; apparently a primary verb; to "bristle" or chill, i.e. shudder
 (fear):—tremble.

g5426.d:
φρονέω phronéō, fron-eh'-o; from G5424; to exercise the mind, i.e. entertain or have a sentiment or
 opinion; by implication, to be (mentally) disposed (more or less
 earnestly in a certain direction); intensively, to interest oneself in
 (with concern or obedience):—set the affection on, (be) care(-ful),
 (be like-, + be of one, + be of the same, + let this) mind(-ed),
 regard, savour, think.

g5427.d:
φρόνημα phrónēma, fron'-ay-mah; from G5426; (mental) inclination or purpose:—(be, + be carnally, + be
 spiritually) mind(-ed).
g5427.r: From φρονέω (G5426)|English: think, regard, mind, be minded, savour, be of the same mind, be like minded, misc

g5428.d:
φρόνησις phrónēsis, fron'-ay-sis; from G5426; mental action or activity, i.e. intellectual or moral
 insight:—prudence, wisdom.
g5428.r: From φρονέω (G5426)|English: think, regard, mind, be minded, savour, be of the same mind, be like minded, misc

g5429.d:
φρόνιμος phrónimos, fron'-ee-mos; from G5424; thoughtful, i.e. sagacious or discreet (implying a cautious
 character; while G4680 denotes practical skill or acumen; and G4908
 indicates rather intelligence or mental acquirement); in a bad sense
 conceited (also in the comparative):—wise(-r).

g543.d:
ἀπείθεια apeítheia, ap-i'-thi-ah; from G545; disbelief (obstinate and rebellious):—disobedience,
 unbelief.

g5430.d: φρονίμως phronímōs, fron-im'-oce; adverb from G5429; prudently:—wisely.

g5431.d:
φροντίζω phrontízō, fron-tid'-zo; from a derivative of G5424; to exercise thought, i.e. be anxious:—be
 careful.
g5431.r: From a derivative of φρήν (G5424)|English: understanding

g5432.d:
φρουρέω phrouréō, froo-reh'-o; from a compound of G4253 and G3708; to be a watcher in advance, i.e. to
 mount guard as a sentinel (post spies at gates); figuratively, to hem
 in, protect:—keep (with a garrison). Compare G5083.
g5432.r: From a compound of πρό (G4253) and ὁράω (G3708)|English: before, above, above ... ago, or ever

g5433.d:
φρυάσσω phryássō, froo-as'-so; akin to G1032, G1031; to snort (as a spirited horse), i.e.
 (figuratively) to make a tumult:—rage.
g5433.r: Akin to βρύω (G1032), βρύχω (G1031)|English: send forth

g5434.d:
φρύγανον phrýganon, froo'-gan-on; neuter of a presumed derivative of φρύγω phrýgō (to roast or parch; akin to
 the base of G5395); something desiccated, i.e. a dry twig:—stick.
g5434.r: From a presumed derivative of phrugo (to roast or parch, akin to the base of φλόξ (G5395))|English: flame, flaming

g5435.d: Φρυγία Phrygía, froog-ee'-ah; probably of foreign origin; Phrygia, a region of Asia Minor:—Phrygia.

g5436.d:
†Φύγελλος Phýgellos, foog'-el-los; probably from G5343; fugitive; Phygellus, an apostate
 Christian:—Phygellus.
g5436.r: Probably from φεύγω (G5343)|English: flee, escape, flee away

g5437.d: φυγή phygḗ, foog-ay'; from G5343; a fleeing, i.e. escape:—flight.
g5437.r: From φεύγω (G5343)|English: flee, escape, flee away

g5438.d:
φυλακή phylakḗ, foo-lak-ay'; from G5442; a guarding or (concretely, guard), the act, the person;
 figuratively, the place, the condition, or (specially), the time (as a
 division of day or night), literally or figuratively:—cage, hold,
 (im-)prison(-ment), ward, watch.
g5438.r: From φυλάσσω (G5442)|English: keep, observe, beware, keep (one's) self, save, be ... ware

g5439.d: φυλακίζω phylakízō, foo-lak-id'-zo; from G5441; to incarcerate:—imprison.

g544.d:
ἀπειθέω apeithéō, ap-i-theh'-o; from G545; to disbelieve (wilfully and perversely):—not believe,
 disobedient, obey not, unbelieving.

g5440.d:
φυλακτήριον phylaktḗrion, foo-lak-tay'-ree-on; neuter of a derivative of G5442; a guard-case, i.e. "phylactery" for
 wearing slips of Scripture texts:—phylactery.
g5440.r: Neuter of a derivative of φυλάσσω (G5442)|English: keep, observe, beware, keep (one's) self, save, be ... ware

g5441.d: φύλαξ phýlax, foo'-lax; from G5442; a watcher or sentry:—keeper.
g5441.r: From φυλάσσω (G5442)|English: keep, observe, beware, keep (one's) self, save, be ... ware

g5442.d:
φυλάσσω phylássō, foo-las'-so; probably from G5443 through the idea of isolation; to watch, i.e. be on
 guard (literally of figuratively); by implication, to preserve, obey,
 avoid:—beward, keep (self), observe, save. Compare G5083.
g5442.r: Probably from φυλή (G5443) through the idea of isolation|English: tribe, kindred

g5443.d:
φυλή phylḗ, foo-lay'; from G5453 (compare G5444); an offshoot, i.e. race or clan:—kindred,
 tribe.
g5443.r: From φύω (G5453) (cf φύλλον (G5444))|English: spring up, spring, as soon as it be sprung up

g5444.d: φύλλον phýllon, fool'-lon; from the same as G5443; a sprout, i.e. leaf:—leaf.
g5444.r: From the same as φυλή (G5443)|English: tribe, kindred

g5445.d:
φύραμα phýrama, foo'-ram-ah; from a prolonged form of φύρω phýrō (to mix a liquid with a solid; perhaps
 akin to G5453 through the idea of swelling in bulk), mean to knead; a
 mass of dough:—lump.
g5445.r: From a prolonged form of phuro (to mix a liquid with a solid, perhaps akin to φύω (G5453) through the idea of swelling in bulk), mean to knead|English: spring up, spring, as soon as it be sprung up

g5446.d:
φυσικός physikós, foo-see-kos'; from G5449; "physical", i.e. (by implication) instinctive:—natural. 
 Compare G5591.
g5446.r: From φύσις (G5449)|English: nature, natural, kind, mankind

g5447.d:
φυσικῶς physikōs, foo-see-koce'; adverb from G5446; "physically", i.e. (by implication)
 instinctively:—naturally.

g5448.d:
φυσιόω physióō, foo-see-o'-o; from G5449 in the primary sense of blowing; to inflate, i.e.
 (figuratively) make proud (haughty):—puff up.
g5448.r: From φύσις (G5449) in the primary sense of blowing|English: nature, natural, kind, mankind

g5449.d:
φύσις phýsis, foo'-sis; from G5453; growth (by germination or expansion), i.e. (by implication)
 natural production (lineal descent); by extension, a genus or sort;
 figuratively, native disposition, constitution or usage:—(man-)kind,
 nature(-al).
g5449.r: From φύω (G5453)|English: spring up, spring, as soon as it be sprung up

g545.d:
ἀπειθής apeithḗs, ap-i-thace'; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3982; unpersuadable, i.e.
 contumacious:—disobedient.
g545.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and πείθω (G3982)|English: Alpha

g5450.d: φυσίωσις physíōsis, foo-see'-o-sis; from G5448; inflation, i.e. (figuratively) haughtiness:—swelling.

g5451.d:
φυτεία phyteía, foo-ti'-ah; from G5452; trans-planting, i.e. (concretely) a shrub or
 vegetable:—plant.

g5452.d:
φυτεύω phyteúō, foot-yoo'-o; from a derivative of G5453; to set out in the earth, i.e. implant;
 figuratively, to instil doctrine:—plant.
g5452.r: From a derivative of φύω (G5453)|English: spring up, spring, as soon as it be sprung up

g5453.d:
φύω phýō, foo'-o; a primary verb; probably originally, to "puff" or blow, i.e. to swell
 up; but only used in the implied sense, to germinate or grow (sprout,
 produce), literally or figuratively:—spring (up).
g5453.r: A primary verb, probably originally, to "puff" or blow, i.e. to swell up|

g5454.d: φωλεός phōleós, fo-leh-os'; of uncertain derivative; a burrow or lurking-place:—hole.

g5455.d:
φωνέω phōnéō, fo-neh'-o; from G5456; to emit a sound (animal, human or instrumental); by
 implication, to address in words or by name, also in imitation:—call
 (for), crow, cry.
g5455.r: From φωνή (G5456)|English: voice, sound, be noised abroad, noise

g5456.d:
φωνή phōnḗ, fo-nay'; probably akin to G5316 through the idea of disclosure; a tone
 (articulate, bestial or artificial); by implication, an address (for
 any purpose), saying or language:—noise, sound, voice.
g5456.r: Probably akin to φαίνω (G5316) through the idea of disclosure|English: appear, shine, be seen, seem, think

g5457.d:
φῶς phōs, foce; from an obsolete φάω pháō (to shine or make manifest, especially by rays; 
 compare G5316, G5346); luminousness (in the widest application, natural
 or artificial, abstract or concrete, literal or figurative):—fire,
 light.
g5457.r: From an obsolete phao (to shine or make manifest, especially by rays, cf φαίνω (G5316), φημί (G5346))|English: appear, shine, be seen, seem, think

g5458.d:
φωστήρ phōstḗr, foce-tare'; from G5457; an illuminator, i.e. (concretely) a luminary, or
 (abstractly) brilliancy:—light.

g5459.d:
φωσφόρος phōsphóros, foce-for'-os; from G5457 and G5342; light-bearing ("phosphorus"), i.e. (specially),
 the morning-star (figuratively):—day star.
g5459.r: From φῶς (G5457) and φέρω (G5342)|English: light, fire

g546.d:
ἀπειλέω apeiléō, ap-i-leh'-o; of uncertain derivation; to menace; by implication, to
 forbid:—threaten.

g5460.d:
φωτεινός phōteinós, fo-ti-nos'; from G5457; lustrous, i.e. transparent or well-illuminated
 (figuratively):—bright, full of light.

g5461.d:
φωτίζω phōtízō, fo-tid'-zo; from G5457; to shed rays, i.e. to shine or (transitively) to brighten
 up (literally or figuratively):—enlighten, illuminate, (bring to,
 give) light, make to see.

g5462.d: φωτισμός phōtismós, fo-tis-mos'; from G5461; illumination (figuratively):—light.
g5462.r: From φωτίζω (G5461)|English: give light, bring to light, lighten, enlighten, light, illuminate, make to see

g5463.d:
χαίρω chaírō, khah'-ee-ro; a primary verb; to be "cheer"ful, i.e. calmly happy or well-off;
 impersonally, especially as salutation (on meeting or parting), be
 well:—farewell, be glad, God speed, greeting, hail, joy(- fully),
 rejoice.

g5464.d: χάλαζα chálaza, khal'-ad-zah; probably from G5465; hail:—hail.
g5464.r: Probably from χαλάω (G5465)|English: let down, strike

g5465.d: χαλάω chaláō, khal-ah'-o; from the base of G5490; to lower (as into a void):—let down, strike.
g5465.r: From the base of χάσμα (G5490)|English: gulf

g5466.d:
Χαλδαῖος Chaldaîos, khal-dah'-yos; probably of Hebrew or (H3778); a Chaldæan (i.e. Kasdi), or native or
 the region of the lower Euphrates:—Chaldæan.
g5466.r: Probably of Hebrew or כַּשְׂדִּימָה (H3778)|English: Chaldeans, Chaldees, Chaldea

g5467.r: Perhaps from χαλάω (G5465) through the idea of reducing the strength|English: let down, strike

g5468.d:
χαλιναγωγέω chalinagōgéō, khal-in-ag-ogue-eh'-o; from a compound of G5469 and the reduplicated form of G71; to be a
 bit-leader, i.e. to curb (figuratively):—bridle.
g5468.r: From a compound of χαλινός (G5469) and the reduplicated form of ἄγω (G71)|English: bit, bridle

g5469.d: χαλινός chalinós, khal-ee-nos'; from G5465; a curb or head-stall (as curbing the spirit):—bit, bridle.

g547.d: ἀπειλή apeilḗ, ap-i-lay'; from G546; a menace:—X straitly, threatening.

g5471.d: χαλκεύς chalkeús, khalk-yooce'; from G5475; a copper-worker or brazier:—coppersmith.

g5472.d:
χαλκηδών chalkēdṓn, khal-kay-dohn'; from G5475 and perhaps G1491; copper-like, i.e.
 "chalcedony":—chalcedony.
g5472.r: From χαλκός (G5475) and perhaps εἶδος (G1491)|English: brass, money

g5473.d: χαλκίον chalkíon, khal-kee'-on; diminutive from G5475; a copper dish:—brazen vessel.

g5474.d:
χαλκολίβανον chalkolíbanon, khal-kol-ib'-an-on; neuter of a compound of G5475 and G3030 (in the implied mean of
 whiteness or brilliancy); burnished copper, an alloy of copper (or
 gold) and silver having a brilliant lustre:—fine brass.
g5474.r: From a compound of χαλκός (G5475) and λίβανος (G3030) (in the implied mean of whiteness or brilliancy)|English: brass, money

g5475.d:
χαλκός chalkós, khal-kos'; perhaps from G5465 through the idea of hollowing out as a vessel (this
 metal being chiefly used for that purpose); copper (the substance, or
 some implement or coin made of it):—brass, money.
g5475.r: Perhaps from χαλάω (G5465) through the idea of hollowing out as a vessel (this metal being chiefly used for that purpose)|English: let down, strike

g5476.d:
χαμαί chamaí, kham-ah'-ee; adverb perhaps from the base of G5490 through the idea of a fissure in
 the soil; earthward, i.e. prostrate:—on (to) the ground.
g5476.r: Perhaps from the base of χάσμα (G5490) through the idea of a fissure in the soil|English: gulf

g5477.d:
Χαναάν Chanaán, khan-ah-an'; of Hebrew origin (H3667); Chanaan (i.e. Kenaan), the early name of
 Palestine:—Chanaan.
g5477.r: Of Hebrew origin כְּנַעַן (H3667)|English: Canaan, merchant, traffick, traffickers

g5478.d:
†Χανααναῖος Chanaanaîos, khan-ah-an-ah'-yos; from G5477; a Chanaanæan (i.e. Kenaanite), or native of gentile
 Palestine:—of Canaan.

g5479.d:
χαρά chará, khar-ah'; from G5463; cheerfulness, i.e. calm delight:—gladness, × greatly, (X
 be exceeding) joy(-ful, -fully, -fulness, -ous).
g5479.r: From χαίρω (G5463)|English: rejoice, be glad, joy, hail, greeting, God speed, all hail, joyfully, farewell

g548.d: ἄπειμι ápeimi, ap'-i-mee; from G575 and G1510; to be away:—be absent. Compare G549.
g548.r: From ἀπό (G575) and εἰμί (G1510)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5480.d:
χάραγμα cháragma, khar'-ag-mah; from the same as G5482; a scratch or etching, i.e. stamp (as a badge of
 servitude), or scupltured figure (statue):—graven, mark.
g5480.r: From the same as χάραξ (G5482)|English: trench

g5481.d:
χαρακτήρ charaktḗr, khar-ak-tare'; from the same as G5482; a graver (the tool or the person), i.e. (by
 implication) engraving (("character"), the figure stamped, i.e. an
 exact copy or (figuratively) representation):—express image.
g5481.r: From the same as χάραξ (G5482)|English: trench

g5482.d:
χάραξ chárax, khar'-ax; from χαράσσω charássō (to sharpen to a point; akin to G1125 through the idea of
 scratching); a stake, i.e. (by implication) a palisade or rampart
 (military mound for circumvallation in a siege):—trench.
g5482.r: From charasso (to sharpen to a point, akin to γράφω (G1125) through the idea of scratching)|English: write, writing, describe

g5483.d:
χαρίζομαι charízomai, khar-id'-zom-ahee; middle voice from G5485; to grant as a favor, i.e. gratuitously, in
 kindness, pardon or rescue:—deliver, (frankly) forgive, (freely)
 give, grant.
g5483.r: Middle voice from χάρις (G5485)|English: grace, favour, thanks, thank, thank, pleasure, misc

g5484.d:
χάριν chárin, khar'-in; accusative case of G5485 as preposition; through favor of, i.e. on
 account of:—be-(for) cause of, for sake of,
 +…fore, × reproachfully.
g5484.r: Accusative case of χάρις (G5485) as preposition|English: grace, favour, thanks, thank, thank, pleasure, misc

g5485.d:
χάρις cháris, khar'-ece; from G5463; graciousness (as gratifying), of manner or act (abstract or
 concrete; literal, figurative or spiritual; especially the divine
 influence upon the heart, and its reflection in the life; including
 gratitude):—acceptable, benefit, favour, gift, grace(- ious), joy,
 liberality, pleasure, thank(-s, -worthy).
g5485.r: From χαίρω (G5463)|English: rejoice, be glad, joy, hail, greeting, God speed, all hail, joyfully, farewell

g5486.d:
χάρισμα chárisma, khar'-is-mah; from G5483; a (divine) gratuity, i.e. deliverance (from danger or
 passion); (specially), a (spiritual) endowment, i.e. (subjectively)
 religious qualification, or (objectively) miraculous faculty:—(free)
 gift.
g5486.r: From χαρίζομαι (G5483)|English: forgive, give, freely give, deliver, grant, frankly forgive

g5487.d:
χαριτόω charitóō, khar-ee-to'-o; from G5485; to grace, i.e. indue with special honor:—make accepted, be
 highly favoured.
g5487.r: From χάρις (G5485)|English: grace, favour, thanks, thank, thank, pleasure, misc

g5488.d:
Χαῤῥάν Charrhán, khar-hran'; of Hebrew origin (H2771); Charrhan (i.e. Charan), a place in
 Mesopotamia:—Charran.

g5489.d:
χάρτης chártēs, khar'-tace; from the same as G5482; a sheet ("chart") of writing-material (as to be
 scribbled over):—paper.
g5489.r: From the same as χάραξ (G5482)|English: trench

g5490.d:
χάσμα chásma, khas'-mah; from a form of an obsolete primary χάω cháō (to "gape" or "yawn"); a
 "chasm" or vacancy (impassable interval):—gulf.
g5490.r: From a form of an obsolete prim chao (to "gape" or "yawn")|

g5491.d:
χεῖλος cheîlos, khi'-los; from a form of the same as G5490; a lip (as a pouring place);
 figuratively, a margin (of water):—lip, shore.
g5491.r: From a form of the same as χάσμα (G5490)|English: gulf

g5492.d:
χειμάζω cheimázō, khi-mad'-zo; from the same as G5494; to storm, i.e. (passively) to labor under a
 gale:—be tossed with tempest.
g5492.r: From the same as χειμών (G5494)|English: winter, tempest, foul weather

g5493.d:
χείμαῤῥος cheímarrhos, khi'-mar-hros; from the base of G5494 and G4482; a storm-runlet, i.e.
 winter-torrent:—brook.
g5493.r: From the base of χειμών (G5494) and ῥέω (G4482)|English: winter, tempest, foul weather

g5494.d: χειμών cheimṓn, khi-mone'; from a derivative of χέω chéō (to pour; akin to the base of G5490 through the idea of a channel), meaning a storm (as pouring rain); by implication, the rainy season, i.e. winter:—tempest, foul weather, winter.
g5494.r: From a derivative of cheo (to pour, akin to the base of χάσμα (G5490) through the idea of a channel), meaning a storm (as pouring rain)|English: gulf

g5495.d:
χείρ cheír, khire; perhaps from the base of G5494 in the sense of its congener the base of
 G5490 (through the idea of hollowness for grasping); the hand
 (literally or figuratively (power); especially (by Hebraism) a means
 or instrument):—hand.
g5495.r: Perhaps from the base of χειμών (G5494) in the sense of its congener the base of χάσμα (G5490) (through the idea of hollowness for grasping)|English: winter, tempest, foul weather

g5496.d:
χειραγωγέω cheiragōgéō, khi-rag-ogue-eh'-o; from G5497; to be a hand-leader, i.e. to guide (a blind person):—lead
 by the hand.
g5496.r: From χειραγωγός (G5497)|English: some to lead by the hand

g5497.d:
χειραγωγός cheiragōgós, khi-rag-o-gos'; from G5495 and a reduplicated form of G71; a hand-leader, i.e. personal
 conductor (of a blind person):—some to lead by the hand.
g5497.r: From χείρ (G5495) and a reduplicated form of ἄγω (G71)|English: hand, not tr

g5498.d:
χειρόγραφον cheirógraphon, khi-rog'-raf-on; neuter of a compound of G5495 and G1125; something hand-written
 ("chirograph"), i.e. a manuscript (specially, a legal document or bond
 (figuratively)):—handwriting.
g5498.r: From a compound of χείρ (G5495) and γράφω (G1125)|English: hand, not tr

g5499.d:
χειροποίητος cheiropoíētos, khi-rop-oy'-ay-tos; from G5495 and a derivative of G4160; manufactured, i.e. of human
 construction:—made by (make with) hands.
g5499.r: From χείρ (G5495) and a derivative of ποιέω (G4160)|English: hand, not tr

g55.d: ἁγνῶς hagnōs, hag-noce'; adverb from G53; purely, i.e. honestly:—sincerely.

g550.d:
†ἀπειπόμην apeipómēn, ap-i-pom'-ane; reflexive past of a compound of G575 and G2036; to say off for oneself,
 i.e. disown:—renounce.
g550.r: Reflexive past of a compound of ἀπό (G575) and εἶπον (G2036)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5500.d:
χειροτονέω cheirotonéō, khi-rot-on-eh'-o; from a comparative of G5495 and τείνω teínō (to stretch); to be a
 hand-reacher or voter (by raising the hand), i.e. (generally) to
 select or appoint:—choose, ordain.
g5500.r: From a comparative of χείρ (G5495) and teino (to stretch)|English: hand, not tr

g5501.d:
χείρων cheírōn, khi'-rone; irregular comparative of G2556; from an obsolete equivalent
 χέρης chérēs (of uncertain derivation); more evil or aggravated
 (physically, mentally or morally):—sorer, worse.
g5501.r: Irregular comparative of κακός (G2556)|English: evil, evil things, harm, that which is evil, wicked, ill, bad, noisome

g5502.d:
†χερουβίμ cheroubím, kher-oo-beem'; plural of Hebrew origin (H3742); "cherubim" (i.e. cherubs or
 kerubim):—cherubims.
g5502.r: Plural of Hebrew origin כְּרוּב (H3742)|English: cherubims, cherub

g5503.d:
χήρα chḗra, khay'-rah; feminine of a presumed derivative apparently from the base of G5490
 through the idea of deficiency; a widow (as lacking a husband),
 literally or figuratively:—widow.
g5503.r: Feminine of a presumed derivative apparently from the base of χάσμα (G5490) through the idea of deficiency|English: gulf

g5505.d: χιλιάς chiliás, khil-ee-as'; from G5507; one thousand ("chiliad"):—thousand.

g5506.d:
†χιλίαρχος chilíarchos, khil-ee'-ar-khos; from G5507 and G757; the commander of a thousand soldiers ("chiliarch";
 i.e. colonel:—(chief, high) captain.

g5507.d: χίλιοι chílioi, khil'-ee-oy; plural of uncertain affinity; a thousand:—thousand.

g5508.d:
Χίος Chíos, khee'-os; of uncertain derivation; Chios, an island in the
 Mediterranean:—Chios.

g5509.d: χιτών chitṓn, khee-tone'; of foreign origin (H3801); a tunic or shirt:—clothes, coat, garment.
g5509.r: Of foreign origin כֻּתֹּנֶת (H3801)|English: coat, garment, robe

g551.d:
ἀπείραστος apeírastos, ap-i'-ras-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of G3987; 
 untried, i.e. not temptable:—not to be tempted.
g551.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of πειράω (G3987)|English: Alpha

g5510.d:
χιών chiṓn, khee-one'; perhaps akin to the base of G5490 (G5465) or G5494 (as descending or
 empty); snow:—snow.
g5510.r: Perhaps akin to the base of χάσμα (G5490) (5465) or χειμών (G5494) (as descending or empty)|English: gulf

g5511.d: χλαμύς chlamýs, khlam-ooce'; of uncertain derivation; a military cloak:—robe.

g5512.d:
†χλευάζω chleuázō, khlyoo-ad'-zo; from a derivative probably of G5491; to throw out the lip, i.e. jeer
 at:—mock.
g5512.r: From a derivative probably of χεῖλος (G5491)|English: lip, shore

g5513.d: χλιαρός chliarós, khlee-ar-os'; from χλίω chlíō (to warm); tepid:—lukewarm.

g5514.d:
Χλόη Chlóē, khlo'-ay; feminine of apparently a primary word; "green"; Chloë, a Christian
 female:—Chloe.

g5515.d:
χλωρός chlōrós, khlo-ros'; from the same as G5514; greenish, i.e. verdant, dun-colored:—green,
 pale.
g5515.r: From the same as Χλόη (G5514)|English: Chloe

g5517.d:
χοϊκός choïkós, kho-ik-os'; from G5522; dusty or dirty (soil-like), i.e. (by implication)
 terrene:—earthy.

g5518.d: χοῖνιξ choînix, khoy'-nix; of uncertain derivation; a chœnix or certain dry measure:—measure.

g5519.d: χοῖρος choîros, khoy'-ros; of uncertain derivation; a hog:—swine.

g552.d:
ἄπειρος ápeiros, ap'-i-ros; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G3984; inexperienced, i.e.
 ignorant:—unskilful.
g552.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and πεῖρα (G3984)|English: Alpha

g5520.d:
χολάω choláō, khol-ah'-o; from G5521; to be bilious, i.e. (by implication) irritable (enraged,
 "choleric"):—be angry.

g5521.d:
χολή cholḗ, khol-ay'; feminine of an equivalent perhaps akin to the same as 5514 (from the
 greenish hue); "gall" or bile, i.e. (by analogy) poison or an anodyne
 (wormwood, poppy, etc.):—gall.
g5521.r: From an equivalent perhaps akin to the same as Χλόη (G5514) (from the greenish hue)|English: Chloe

g5523.d: †Χοραζίν Chorazín, khor-ad-zin'; of uncertain derivation; Chorazin, a place in Palestine:—Chorazin.

g5524.d:
χορηγέω chorēgéō, khor-ayg-eh'-o; from a compound of G5525 and G71; to be a dance-leader, i.e. (generally)
 to furnish:—give, minister.
g5524.r: From a compound of χορός (G5525) and ἄγω (G71)|English: dancing

g5525.d: χορός chorós, khor-os'; of uncertain derivation; a ring, i.e. round dance ("choir":—dancing.

g5526.d:
χορτάζω chortázō, khor-tad'-zo; from G5528; to fodder, i.e. (generally) to gorge (supply food in
 abundance):—feed, fill, satisfy.

g5527.d: χόρτασμα chórtasma, khor'-tas-mah; from G5526; forage, i.e. food:—sustenance.
g5527.r: From χορτάζω (G5526)|English: fill, be full, satisfy, feed

g5528.d:
χόρτος chórtos, khor'-tos; apparently a primary word; a "court" or "garden", i.e. (by
 implication, of pasture) herbage or vegetation:—blade, grass, hay.

g5529.d: Χουζᾶς Chouzâs, khood-zas'; of uncertain origin; Chuzas, an officer of Herod:—Chuza.

g553.d: ἀπεκδέχομαι apekdéchomai, ap-ek-dekh'-om-ahee; from G575 and G1551; to expect fully:—look (wait) for.
g553.r: From ἀπό (G575) and ἐκδέχομαι (G1551)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5530.r: Middle voice of a primary verb (perhaps rather from χείρ (G5495), to handle)|English: hand, not tr

g5532.d:
χρεία chreía, khri'-ah; from the base of G5530 or G5534; employment, i.e. an affair; also (by
 implication) occasion, demand, requirement or destitution:—business,
 lack, necessary(-ity), need(-ful), use, want.
g5532.r: From the base of χράομαι (G5530) or χρή (G5534)|English: use, entreat

g5533.d:
†χρεωφειλέτης chreōpheilétēs, khreh-o-fi-let'-ace; from a derivative of G5531 and G3781; a loan-ower, i.e. indebted
 person:—debtor.
g5533.r: From a derivative of κίχρημι (G5531) and ὀφειλέτης (G3781)|English: lend

g5534.d:
χρή chrḗ, khray; third person singular of the same as G5530 or G5531 used impersonally; 
 it needs (must or should) be:—ought.
g5534.r: Third person singular of the same as χράομαι (G5530) or κίχρημι (G5531) used impersonally|English: use, entreat

g5535.d:
χρῄζω chrḗizō, khrade'-zo; from G5532; to make (i.e. have) necessity, i.e. be in want of:—(have)
 need.
g5535.r: From χρεία (G5532)|English: need, need, necessity, use, needful, necessary, business, lack, wants

g5536.d: χρῆμα chrēma, khray'-mah; something useful or needed, i.e. wealth, price:—money, riches.

g5537.d:
χρηματίζω chrēmatízō, khray-mat-id'-zo; from G5536; to utter an oracle (compare the original sense of G5530),
 i.e. divinely intimate; by implication, (compare the secular sense of
 G5532) to constitute a firm for business, i.e. (generally) bear as a
 title:—be called, be admonished (warned) of God, reveal, speak.

g5538.d: χρηματισμός chrēmatismós, khray-mat-is-mos'; from G5537; a divine response or revelation:—answer of God.
g5538.r: From χρηματίζω (G5537)|English: be warned of God, call, be admonished of God, reveal, speak, be warned from God

g5539.d: χρήσιμος chrḗsimos, khray'-see-mos; from G5540; serviceable:—profit.

g554.d:
ἀπεκδύομαι apekdýomai, ap-ek-doo'-om-ahee; middle voice from G575 and G1562; to divest wholly oneself, or (for
 oneself) despoil:—put off, spoil.
g554.r: Middle voice from ἀπό (G575) and ἐκδύω (G1562)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5540.d:
χρῆσις chrēsis, khray'-sis; from G5530; employment, i.e. (specially), sexual intercourse (as an
 occupation of the body):—use.

g5541.d:
χρηστεύομαι chrēsteúomai, khraste-yoo'-om-ahee; middle voice from G5543; to show oneself useful, i.e. act
 benevolently:—be kind.
g5541.r: Middle voice from χρηστός (G5543)|English: kind, easy, better, goodness, good, gracious

g5542.d:
χρηστολογία chrēstología, khrase-tol-og-ee'-ah; from a compound of G5543 and G3004; fair speech, i.e.
 plausibility:—good words.
g5542.r: From a compound of χρηστός (G5543) and λέγω (G3004)|English: kind, easy, better, goodness, good, gracious

g5543.d:
χρηστός chrēstós, khrase-tos'; from G5530; employed, i.e. (by implication) useful (in manner or
 morals):—better, easy, good(-ness), gracious, kind.

g5544.d:
χρηστότης chrēstótēs, khray-stot'-ace; from G5543; usefulness, i.e. morally, excellence (in character or
 demeanor):—gentleness, good(-ness), kindness.
g5544.r: From χρηστός (G5543)|English: kind, easy, better, goodness, good, gracious

g5545.d:
χρῖσμα chrîsma, khris'-mah; from G5548; an unguent or smearing, i.e. (figuratively) the special
 endowment ("chrism") of the Holy Spirit:—anointing, unction.

g5546.d: Χριστιανός Christianós, khris-tee-an-os'; from G5547; a Christian, i.e. follower of Christ:—Christian.

g5547.d: Χριστός Christós, khris-tos'; from G5548; anointed, i.e. the Messiah, an epithet of Jesus:—Christ.

g5548.d:
χρίω chríō, khree'-o; probably akin to G5530 through the idea of contact; to smear or rub
 with oil, i.e. (by implication) to consecrate to an office or
 religious service:—anoint.
g5548.r: Probably akin to χράομαι (G5530) through the idea of contact|English: use, entreat

g5549.d: χρονίζω chronízō, khron-id'-zo; from G5550; to take time, i.e. linger:—delay, tarry.
g5549.r: From χρόνος (G5550)|English: time, season, while, a while, space, oftentimes, not tr, misc

g555.d: ἀπέκδυσις apékdysis, ap-ek'-doo-sis; from G554; divestment:—putting off.

g5550.d:
χρόνος chrónos, khron'-os; of uncertain derivation; a space of time (in general, and thus
 properly distinguished from G2540, which designates a fixed or special
 occasion; and from G165, which denotes a particular period) or
 interval; by extension, an individual opportunity; by implication,
 delay:—+ years old, season, space, (X often-)time(-s), (a) while.

g5551.d:
χρονοτριβέω chronotribéō, khron-ot-rib-eh'-o; from a presumed compound of G5550 and the base of G5147; to be a
 time-wearer, i.e. to procrastinate (linger):—spend time.
g5551.r: From a presumed compound of χρόνος (G5550) and the base of τρίβος (G5147)|English: time, season, while, a while, space, oftentimes, not tr, misc

g5552.d: χρύσεος chrýseos, khroo'-seh-os; from G5557; made of gold:—of gold, golden.

g5553.d:
χρυσίον chrysíon, khroo-see'-on; diminutive of G5557; a golden article, i.e. gold plating, ornament, or
 coin:—gold.

g5554.d:
χρυσοδακτύλιος chrysodaktýlios, khroo-sod-ak-too'-lee-os; from G5557 and G1146; gold-ringed, i.e. wearing a golden finger-ring or
 similar jewelry:—with a gold ring.

g5555.d:
χρυσόλιθος chrysólithos, khroo-sol'-ee-thos; from G5557 and G3037; gold-stone, i.e. a yellow gem
 ("chrysolite"):—chrysolite.

g5556.d:
χρυσόπρασος chrysóprasos, khroo-sop'-ras-os; from G5557 and πράσον práson (a leek); a greenish-yellow gem
 ("chrysoprase"):—chrysoprase.
g5556.r: From χρυσός (G5557) and prason (a leek)|English: gold

g5557.d:
χρυσός chrysós, khroo-sos'; perhaps from the base of G5530 (through the idea of the utility of the
 metal); gold; by extension, a golden article, as an ornament or
 coin:—gold.
g5557.r: Perhaps from the base of χράομαι (G5530) (through the idea of the utility of the metal), gold|English: use, entreat

g5558.d: χρυσόω chrysóō, khroo-so'-o; from G5557; to gild, i.e. bespangle with golden ornaments:—deck.

g5559.d:
χρώς chrṓs, khroce; probably akin to the base of G5530 through the idea of handling; the
 body (properly, its surface or skin):—body.
g5559.r: Probably akin to the base of χράομαι (G5530) through the idea of handling|English: use, entreat

g556.d: ἀπελαύνω apelaúnō, ap-el-ow'-no; from G575 and G1643; to dismiss:—drive.
g556.r: From ἀπό (G575) and ἐλαύνω (G1643)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5560.d: χωλός chōlós, kho-los'; apparently a primary word; "halt", i.e. limping:—cripple, halt, lame.

g5561.d:
χώρα chṓra, kho'-rah; feminine of a derivative of the base of G5490 through the idea of empty
 expanse; room, i.e. a space of territory (more or less extensive;
 often including its inhabitants):—coast, county, fields, ground,
 land, region. Compare G5117.
g5561.r: From a derivative of the base of χάσμα (G5490) through the idea of empty expanse|English: gulf

g5562.d:
χωρέω chōréō, kho-reh'-o; from G5561; to be in (give) space, i.e. (intransitively) to pass,
 enter, or (transitively) to hold, admit (literally or
 figuratively):—come, contain, go, have place, (can, be room to)
 receive.
g5562.r: From χώρα (G5561)|English: country, region, land, field, ground, coast

g5563.d:
χωρίζω chōrízō, kho-rid'-zo; from G5561; to place room between, i.e. part; reflexively, to go
 away:—depart, put asunder, separate.
g5563.r: From χώρα (G5561)|English: country, region, land, field, ground, coast

g5564.d:
χωρίον chōríon, kho-ree'-on; diminutive of G5561; a spot or plot of ground:—field, land, parcel of
 ground, place, possession.
g5564.r: Diminutive of χώρα (G5561)|English: country, region, land, field, ground, coast

g5565.d:
χωρίς chōrís, kho-rece'; adverb from G5561; at a space, i.e. separately or apart from (often as
 preposition):—beside, by itself, without.
g5565.r: From χώρα (G5561)|English: country, region, land, field, ground, coast

g5566.d: χῶρος chōros, kho'-ros; of Latin origin; the north-west wind:—north west.

g5567.d:
ψάλλω psállō, psal'-lo; probably strengthened from ψάω psáō (to rub or touch the surface; compare
 G5597); to twitch or twang, i.e. to play on a stringed instrument
 (celebrate the divine worship with music and accompanying odes):—make
 melody, sing (psalms).
g5567.r: Probably strengthened from psao (to rub or touch the surface, cf ψώχω (G5597))|English: rub

g5568.d:
ψαλμός psalmós, psal-mos'; from G5567; a set piece of music, i.e. a sacred ode (accompanied with
 the voice, harp or other instrument; a "psalm"); collectively, the
 book of the Psalms:—psalm. Compare G5603.
g5568.r: From ψάλλω (G5567)|English: sing, sing psalms, make melody

g5569.d:
ψευδάδελφος pseudádelphos, psyoo-dad'-el-fos; from G5571 and G80; a spurious brother, i.e. pretended associate:—false
 brethren.
g5569.r: From ψευδής (G5571) and ἀδελφός (G80)|English: liar, false

g557.d:
ἀπελεγμός apelegmós, ap-el-eg-mos'; from a compound of G575 and G1651; refutation, i.e. (by implication)
 contempt:—nought.
g557.r: From a compound of ἀπό (G575) and ἐλέγχω (G1651)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5570.d:
ψευδαπόστολος pseudapóstolos, psyoo-dap-os'-tol-os; from G5571 and G652; a spurious apostle, i.e. pretended pracher:—false
 teacher.
g5570.r: From ψευδής (G5571) and ἀπόστολος (G652)|English: liar, false

g5571.d: ψευδής pseudḗs, psyoo-dace'; from G5574; untrue, i.e. erroneous, deceitful, wicked:—false, liar.

g5572.d:
ψευδοδιδάσκαλος pseudodidáskalos, psyoo-dod-id-as'-kal-os; from G5571 and G1320; a spurious teacher, i.e. propagator of erroneous
 Christian doctrine:—false teacher.
g5572.r: From ψευδής (G5571) and διδάσκαλος (G1320)|English: liar, false

g5573.d:
ψευδολόγος pseudológos, psyoo-dol-og'-os; from G5571 and G3004; mendacious, i.e. promulgating erroneous Christian
 doctrine:—speaking lies.
g5573.r: From ψευδής (G5571) and λέγω (G3004)|English: liar, false

g5574.d:
†ψεύδομαι pseúdomai, psyoo'-dom-ahee; middle voice of an apparently primary verb; to utter an untruth or
 attempt to deceive by falsehood:—falsely, lie.
g5574.r: Middle voice of an apparently primary verb|

g5576.d:
ψευδομαρτυρέω pseudomartyréō, psyoo-dom-ar-too-reh'-o; from G5575; to be an untrue testifier, i.e. offer falsehood in
 evidence:—be a false witness.

g5577.d: ψευδομαρτυρία pseudomartyría, psyoo-dom-ar-too-ree'-ah; from G5575; untrue testimony:—false witness.

g5578.d:
ψευδοπροφήτης pseudoprophḗtēs, psyoo-dop-rof-ay'-tace; from G5571 and G4396; a spurious prophet, i.e. pretended foreteller or
 religious impostor:—false prophet.
g5578.r: From ψευδής (G5571) and προφήτης (G4396)|English: liar, false

g5579.d: ψεῦδος pseûdos, psyoo'-dos; from G5574; a falsehood:—lie, lying.

g558.d: ἀπελεύθερος apeleútheros, ap-el-yoo'-ther-os; from G575 and G1658; one freed away, i.e. a freedman:—freeman.
g558.r: From ἀπό (G575) and ἐλεύθερος (G1658)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5580.d: ψευδόχριστος pseudóchristos, psyoo-dokh'-ris-tos; from G5571 and G5547; a spurious Messiah:—false Christ.
g5580.r: From ψευδής (G5571) and Χριστός (G5547)|English: liar, false

g5581.d: ψευδώνυμος pseudṓnymos, psyoo-do'-noo-mos; from G5571 and G3686; untruly named:—falsely so called.
g5581.r: From ψευδής (G5571) and ὄνομα (G3686)|English: liar, false

g5582.d: ψεῦσμα pseûsma, psyoos'-mah; from G5574; a fabrication, i.e. falsehood:—lie.

g5583.d: ψεύστης pseústēs, psyoos-tace'; from G5574; a falsifier:—liar.

g5584.d:
ψηλαφάω psēlapháō, psay-laf-ah'-o; from the base of G5567 (compare G5586); to manipulate, i.e. verify by
 contact; figuratively, to search for:—feel after, handle, touch.
g5584.r: From the base of ψάλλω (G5567) (cf ψῆφος (G5586))|English: sing, sing psalms, make melody

g5585.d:
ψηφίζω psēphízō, psay-fid'-zo; from G5586; to use pebbles in enumeration, i.e. (generally) to
 compute:—count.

g5586.d:
ψῆφος psēphos, psay'-fos; from the same as G5584; a pebble (as worn smooth by handling), i.e. (by
 implication, of use as a counter or ballot) a verdict (of acquittal)
 or ticket (of admission); a vote:—stone, voice.
g5586.r: From the same as ψηλαφάω (G5584)|English: handle, feel after, touch

g5587.r: From a derivative of psithos (a whisper; by implication, a slander, probably akin to ψεύδομαι (G5574))|English: lie, falsely

g5588.d: ψιθυριστής psithyristḗs, psith-oo-ris-tace'; from the same as G5587; a secret calumniator:—whisperer.
g5588.r: From the same as ψιθυρισμός (G5587)|English: whispering

g5589.d:
ψιχίον psichíon, psikh-ee'-on; diminutive from a derivative of the base of G5567 (meaning a crumb); a
 little bit or morsel:—crumb.
g5589.r: Diminutive from a derivative of the base of ψάλλω (G5567) (meaning a crumb)|English: sing, sing psalms, make melody

g559.d: Ἀπελλῆς Apellēs, ap-el-lace'; of Latin origin; Apelles, a Christian:—Apelles.

g5590.d:
ψυχή psychḗ, psoo-khay'; from G5594; breath, i.e. (by implication) spirit, abstractly or
 concretely (the animal sentient principle only; thus distinguished on
 the one hand from G4151, which is the rational and immortal soul; and
 on the other from G2222, which is mere vitality, even of plants: these
 terms thus exactly correspond respectively to the Hebrew H5315, H7307
 and H2416):—heart (+ -ily), life, mind, soul, + us, + you.

g5591.d:
ψυχικός psychikós, psoo-khee-kos'; from G5590; sensitive, i.e. animate (in distinction on the one hand
 from G4152, which is the higher or renovated nature; and on the other
 from G5446, which is the lower or bestial nature):—natural, sensual.
g5591.r: From ψυχή (G5590)|English: soul, life, mind, heart, heartily, not tr

g5592.d: ψύχος psýchos, psoo'-khos; from G5594; coolness:—cold.

g5593.d: ψυχρός psychrós, psoo-chros'; from G5592; chilly (literally or figuratively):—cold.

g5594.d:
ψύχω psýchō, psoo'-kho; a primary verb; to breathe (voluntarily but gently, thus differing on
 the one hand from G4154, which denotes properly a forcible respiration;
 and on the other from the base of G109, which refers properly to an
 inanimate breeze), i.e. (by implication, of reduction of temperature
 by evaporation) to chill (figuratively):—wax cold.

g5595.d:
ψωμίζω psōmízō, pso-mid'-zo; from the base of G5596; to supply with bits, i.e. (generally) to
 nourish:—(bestow to) feed.
g5595.r: From the base of ψωμίον (G5596)|English: sop

g5596.d:
ψωμίον psōmíon, pso-mee'-on; diminutive from a derivative of the base of G5597; a crumb or morsel
 (as if rubbed off), i.e. a mouthful:—sop.
g5596.r: Diminutive from a derivative of the base of ψώχω (G5597)|English: rub

g5597.d:
ψώχω psṓchō, pso'-kho; prolongation from the same base as G5567; to triturate, i.e. (by
 analogy) to rub out (kernels from husks with the fingers or
 hand):—rub.
g5597.r: Prolongation from the same base as ψάλλω (G5567)|English: sing, sing psalms, make melody

g5598.d:
Ω Ō, o'-meg-ah; the last letter of the Greek alphabet, i.e. (figuratively) the
 finality:—Omega.

g5599.d:
ὦ ō, o; a primary interjection; as a sign of the vocative case, O; as a note
 of exclamation, oh:—O.

g56.d:
ἀγνωσία agnōsía, ag-no-see'-ah; from G1 (as negative particle) and G1108; ignorance (properly, the
 state):—ignorance, not the knowledge.
g56.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as negative particle) and γνῶσις (G1108)|English: Alpha

g560.d: ἀπελπίζω apelpízō, ap-el-pid'-zo; from G575 and G1679; to hope out, i.e. fully expect:—hope for again.
g560.r: From ἀπό (G575) and ἐλπίζω (G1679)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5600.d:
ὦ ō, o; the subjunctive of G1510; (may, might, can, could, would, should, must,
 etc.; also with G1487 and its comparative, as well as with other
 particles) be:—+ appear, are, (may, might, should) be, × have, is, +
 pass the flower of her age, should stand, were.
g5600.r: The subjunctive of εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g5601.d: †Ὠβήδ Ōbḗd, o-bade'; of Hebrew origin (H5744); Obed, an Israelite:—Obed.

g5602.d:
ὧδε hōde, ho'-deh; from an adverb form of G3592; in this same spot, i.e. here or
 hither:—here, hither, (in) this place, there.
g5602.r: From an adverb form of ὅδε (G3592)|English: these things, thus, after this manner, he, she, such

g5603.d:
ᾠδή ōidḗ, o-day'; from G103; a chant or "ode" (the general term for any words sung; while
 G5215 denotes especially a religious metrical composition, and G5568
 still more specially, a Hebrew cantillation):—song.

g5604.d:
ὠδίν ōdín, o-deen'; akin to G3601; a pang or throe, especially of childbirth:—pain,
 sorrow, travail.

g5605.d:
ὠδίνω ōdínō, o-dee'-no; from G5604; to experience the pains of parturition (literally or
 figuratively):—travail in (birth).

g5606.d:
ὦμος ōmos, o'-mos; perhaps from the alternate of G5342; the shoulder (as that on which
 burdens are borne):—shoulder.
g5606.r: Perhaps from the alternate of φέρω (G5342)|English: bring, bear, bring forth, come, reach, endure, carry, misc

g5607.d: ὤν ṓn, oan; present participle of G1510; being:—be, come, have.
g5607.r: Present participle of εἰμί (G1510)|English: I am, am, it is I, be, I was, have been, not tr

g5608.d:
ὠνέομαι ōnéomai, o-neh'-om-ahee; middle voice from an apparently primary ὦνος ōnos (a sum or price); to
 purchase (synonymous with the earlier G4092):—buy.
g5608.r: Middle voice from an apparently primary onos (a sum or price)|

g5609.d: ὠόν ōón, o-on'; apparently a primary word; an "egg":—egg.

g561.d:
ἀπέναντι apénanti, ap-en'-an-tee; from G575 and G1725; from in front, i.e. opposite, before or
 against:—before, contrary, over against, in the presence of.
g561.r: From ἀπό (G575) and ἔναντι (G1725)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g5610.d:
ὥρα hṓra, ho'-rah; apparently a primary word; an "hour" (literally or
 figuratively):—day, hour, instant, season, × short, (even-)tide,
 (high) time.

g5611.d:
ὡραῖος hōraîos, ho-rah'-yos; from G5610; belonging to the right hour or season (timely), i.e. (by
 implication) flourishing (beauteous (figuratively)):—beautiful.
g5611.r: From ὥρα (G5610)|English: hour, time, season, misc

g5612.d: ὠρύομαι ōrýomai, o-roo'-om-ahee; middle voice of an apparently primary verb; to "roar":—roar.
g5612.r: Middle voice of an apparently primary verb|

g5613.d:
ὡς hōs, hoce; probably adverb of comparative from G3739; which how, i.e. in that
 manner (very variously used, as follows):—about, after (that),
 (according) as (it had been, it were), as soon (as), even as (like),
 for, how (greatly), like (as, unto), since, so (that), that, to wit,
 unto, when(-soever), while, × with all speed.
g5613.r: Probably from comparative from ὅς (G3739)|English: which, whom, that, who, whose, what, that which, whereof, misc

g5614.d:
ὡσαννά hōsanná, ho-san-nah'; of Hebrew origin (H3467 and H4994); oh save!; hosanna (i.e. hoshia-na),
 an exclamation of adoration:—hosanna.
g5614.r: Of Hebrew origin יָשַׁע (H3467) and נָא (H4994)|English: save, saviour, deliver, help, preserved, salvation, avenging, at all, avenged, defend, rescue, safe, victory

g5615.d:
ὡσαύτως hōsaútōs, ho-sow'-toce; from G5613 and an adverb from G846; as thus, i.e. in the same way:—even
 so, likewise, after the same (in like) manner.
g5615.r: From ὡς (G5613) and an adverb from αὐτός (G846)|English: as, when, how, as it were, about, misc

g5616.d:
ὡσεί hōseí, ho-si'; from G5613 and G1487; as if:—about, as (it had been, it were), like
 (as).
g5616.r: From ὡς (G5613) and εἰ (G1487)|English: as, when, how, as it were, about, misc

g5617.d: Ὡσηέ Hōsēé, ho-say-eh'; of Hebrew origin (H1954); Hosee (i.e. Hoshea), an Israelite:—Osee.
g5617.r: Of Hebrew origin הוֹשֵׁעַ (H1954)|English: Hoshea, Hosea, Oshea

g5618.d: ὥσπερ hṓsper, hoce'-per; from G5613 and G4007; just as, i.e. exactly like:—(even, like) as.
g5618.r: From ὡς (G5613) and περ (G4007)|English: as, when, how, as it were, about, misc

g5619.d: ὡσπερεί hōspereí, hoce-per-i'; from G5618 and G1487; just as if, i.e. as it were:—as.
g5619.r: From ὥσπερ (G5618) and εἰ (G1487)|English: as, even as, like as

g562.d:
ἀπέραντος apérantos, ap-er'-an-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a secondary derivative of G4008; 
 unfinished, i.e. (by implication) interminable:—endless.
g562.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a secondary derivative of πέραν (G4008)|English: Alpha

g5620.d:
ὥστε hṓste, hoce'-teh; from G5613 and G5037; so too, i.e. thus therefore (in various relations
 of consecution, as follow):—(insomuch) as, so that (then), (insomuch)
 that, therefore, to, wherefore.
g5620.r: From ὡς (G5613) and τέ (G5037)|English: as, when, how, as it were, about, misc

g5621.d:
ὠτίον ōtíon, o-tee'-on; diminutive of G3775; an earlet, i.e. one of the ears, or perhaps the
 lobe of the ear:—ear.

g5622.d:
ὠφέλεια ōphéleia, o-fel'-i-ah; from a derivative of the base of G5624; usefulness, i.e.
 benefit:—advantage, profit.
g5622.r: From a derivative of the base of ὠφέλιμος (G5624)|English: profitable, profit

g5623.d:
ὠφελέω ōpheléō, o-fel-eh'-o; from the same as G5622; to be useful, i.e. to benefit:—advantage,
 better, prevail, profit.
g5623.r: From the same as ὠφέλεια (G5622)|English: profit, advantage

g5624.d:
ὠφέλιμος ōphélimos, o-fel'-ee-mos; from a form of G3786; helpful or serviceable, i.e.
 advantageous:—profit(-able).
g5624.r: From a form of ὄφελος (G3786)|English: it profiteth, it advantageth

g563.d:
ἀπερισπάστως aperispástōs, ap-er-is-pas-toce'; adverb from a compound of G1 (as a negative participle) and a presumed
 derivative of G4049; undistractedly, i.e. free from (domestic)
 solicitude:—without distraction.
g563.r: From a compound of ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative participle) and a presumed derivative of περισπάω (G4049)|English: Alpha

g564.d:
ἀπερίτμητος aperítmētos, ap-er-eet'-may-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of G4059; 
 uncircumcised (figuratively):—uncircumcised.
g564.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of περιτέμνω (G4059)|English: Alpha

g565.d:
ἀπέρχομαι apérchomai, ap-erkh'-om-ahee; from G575 and G2064; to go off (i.e. depart), aside (i.e. apart) or
 behind (i.e. follow), literally or figuratively:—come, depart, go
 (aside, away, back, out, … ways), pass away, be past.
g565.r: From ἀπό (G575) and ἔρχομαι (G2064)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g568.r: From ἀπό (G575) and ἔχω (G2192)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g569.d:
ἀπιστέω apistéō, ap-is-teh'-o; from G571; to be unbelieving, i.e. (transitively) disbelieve, or (by
 implication) disobey:—believe not.
g569.r: From ἄπιστος (G571)|English: that believe not, unbelieving, faithless, unbeliever, infidel, thing incredible, which believe not

g57.d: ἄγνωστος ágnōstos, ag'-noce-tos'; from G1 (as negative particle) and G1110; unknown:—unknown.
g57.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as negative particle) and γνωστός (G1110)|English: Alpha

g570.d:
ἀπιστία apistía, ap-is-tee'-ah; from G571; faithlessness, i.e. (negatively) disbelief (lack of
 Christian faith), or (positively) unfaithfulness
 (disobedience):—unbelief.
g570.r: From ἄπιστος (G571)|English: that believe not, unbelieving, faithless, unbeliever, infidel, thing incredible, which believe not

g571.d:
ἄπιστος ápistos, ap'-is-tos; from G1 (as a negative particle) and G4103; (actively) disbelieving,
 i.e. without Christian faith (specially, a heathen); (passively)
 untrustworthy (person), or incredible (thing):—that believeth not,
 faithless, incredible thing, infidel, unbeliever(-ing).
g571.r: From ἄλφα (G1) (as a negative particle) and πιστός (G4103)|English: Alpha

g572.d:
ἁπλότης haplótēs, hap-lot'-ace; from G573; singleness, i.e. (subjectively) sincerity (without
 dissimulation or self-seeking), or (objectively) generosity (copious
 bestowal):—bountifulness, liberal(-ity), simplicity, singleness.

g573.d:
ἁπλοῦς haploûs, hap-looce'; probably from G1 (as a particle of union) and the base of G4120; 
 properly, folded together, i.e. single (figuratively, clear):—single.
g573.r: Probably from ἄλφα (G1) (as a particle of union) and the base of πλέκω (G4120)|English: Alpha

g574.d:
ἁπλῶς haplōs, hap-loce'; adverb from G573 (in the objective sense of G572); bountifully;
 --liberally.
g574.r: From ἁπλοῦς (G573) (in the objective sense of ἁπλότης (G572))|English: single

g575.d:
ἀπό apó, apo'; a primary particle; "off," i.e. away (from something near), in various
 senses (of place, time, or relation; literal or figurative):—(X
 here-)after, ago, at, because of, before, by (the space of), for(-th),
 from, in, (out) of, off, (up-)on(-ce), since, with.

g576.d:
ἀποβαίνω apobaínō, ap-ob-ah'-ee-no; from G575 and the base of G939; literally, to disembark; figuratively,
 to eventuate:—become, go out, turn.
g576.r: From ἀπό (G575) and the base of βάσις (G939)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g577.d: ἀποβάλλω apobállō, ap-ob-al'-lo; from G575 and G906; to throw off; figuratively, to lose:—cast away.
g577.r: From ἀπό (G575) and βάλλω (G906)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g578.d:
ἀποβλέπω apoblépō, ap-ob-lep'-o; from G575 and G991; to look away from everything else, i.e.
 (figuratively) intently regard:—have respect.
g578.r: From ἀπό (G575) and βλέπω (G991)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g579.d:
ἀπόβλητος apóblētos, ap-ob'-lay-tos; from G577; cast off, i.e. (figuratively) such as to be rejected:—be
 refused.

g58.d:
ἀγορά agorá, ag-or-ah'; from ἀγείρω ageírō (to gather; probably akin to G1453); properly, the
 town-square (as a place of public resort); by implication, a market or
 thoroughfare:—market(-place), street.
g58.r: From ageiro (to gather, probably akin to ἐγείρω (G1453))|English: rise, raise, arise, raise up, rise up, rise again, raise again, misc

g580.d: ἀποβολή apobolḗ, ap-ob-ol-ay'; from G577; rejection; figuratively, loss:—casting away, loss.

g581.d:
†ἀπογενόμενος apogenómenos, ap-og-en-om'-en-os; past participle of a compound of G575 and G1096; absent, i.e. deceased
 (figuratively, renounced):—being dead.
g581.r: Past participle of a compound of ἀπό (G575) and γίνομαι (G1096)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g582.d: ἀπογραφή apographḗ, ap-og-raf-ay'; from G583; an enrollment; by implication, an assessment:—taxing.

g583.d:
ἀπογράφω apográphō, ap-og-raf'-o; from G575 and G1125; to write off (a copy or list), i.e. enrol:—tax,
 write.
g583.r: From ἀπό (G575) and γράφω (G1125)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g584.d:
ἀποδείκνυμι apodeíknymi, ap-od-ike'-noo-mee; from G575 and G1166; to show off, i.e. exhibit; figuratively, to
 demonstrate, i.e. accredit:—(ap-)prove, set forth, shew.
g584.r: From ἀπό (G575) and δεικνύω (G1166)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g585.d: ἀπόδειξις apódeixis, ap-od'-ike-sis; from G584; manifestation:—demonstration.
g585.r: From ἀποδείκνυμι (G584)|English: approve, prove, set forth, show

g586.d:
†ἀποδεκατόω apodekatóō, ap-od-ek-at-o'-o; from G575 and G1183; to tithe (as debtor or creditor):—(give, pay,
 take) tithe.
g586.r: From ἀπό (G575) and δεκατόω (G1183)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g587.d: ἀπόδεκτος apódektos, ap-od'-ek-tos; from G588; accepted, i.e. agreeable:—acceptable.
g587.r: From ἀποδέχομαι (G588)|English: receive, receive gladly, accept

g588.d:
ἀποδέχομαι apodéchomai, ap-od-ekh'-om-ahee; from G575 and G1209; to take fully, i.e. welcome (persons), approve
 (things):—accept, receive (gladly).
g588.r: From ἀπό (G575) and δέχομαι (G1209)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g589.d:
ἀποδημέω apodēméō, ap-od-ay-meh'-o; from G590; to go abroad, i.e. visit a foreign land:—go (travel) into a
 far country, journey.
g589.r: From ἀπόδημος (G590)|English: taking a far journey

g59.d:
ἀγοράζω agorázō, ag-or-ad'-zo; from G58; properly, to go to market, i.e. (by implication) to purchase;
 specially, to redeem:—buy, redeem.

g590.d:
ἀπόδημος apódēmos, ap-od'-ay-mos; from G575 and G1218; absent from one's own people, i.e. a foreign
 traveller:—taking a far journey.
g590.r: From ἀπό (G575) and δῆμος (G1218)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g591.d:
ἀποδίδωμι apodídōmi, ap-od-eed'-o-mee; from G575 and G1325; to give away, i.e. up, over, back, etc. (in various
 applications):—deliver (again), give (again), (re-)pay(-ment be
 made), perform, recompense, render, requite, restore, reward, sell,
 yield.
g591.r: From ἀπό (G575) and δίδωμι (G1325)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g592.d:
ἀποδιορίζω apodiorízō, ap-od-ee-or-id'-zo; from G575 and a compound of G223 and G3724; to disjoin (by a boundary,
 figuratively, a party):—separate.
g592.r: From ἀπό (G575) and a compound of διά (G1223) and ὁρίζω (G3724)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g593.d:
ἀποδοκιμάζω apodokimázō, ap-od-ok-ee-mad'-zo; from G575 and G1381; to disapprove, i.e. (by implication) to
 repudiate:—disallow, reject.
g593.r: From ἀπό (G575) and δοκιμάζω (G1381)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g594.d: ἀποδοχή apodochḗ, ap-od-okh-ay'; from G588; acceptance:—acceptation.
g594.r: From ἀποδέχομαι (G588)|English: receive, receive gladly, accept

g595.d:
ἀπόθεσις apóthesis, ap-oth'-es-is; from G659; a laying aside (literally or figuratively):—putting away
 (off).
g595.r: From ἀποτίθημι (G659)|English: put off, lay aside, lay down, cast off, put away, lay apart

g596.d: ἀποθήκη apothḗkē, ap-oth-ay'-kay; from G659; a repository, i.e. granary:—barn, garner.
g596.r: From ἀποτίθημι (G659)|English: put off, lay aside, lay down, cast off, put away, lay apart

g597.d: ἀποθησαυρίζω apothēsaurízō, ap-oth-ay-sow-rid'-zo; from G575 and G2343; to treasure away:—lay up in store.
g597.r: From ἀπό (G575) and θησαυρίζω (G2343)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g598.d: ἀποθλίβω apothlíbō, ap-oth-lee'-bo; from G575 and G2346; to crowd (from every side):—press.
g598.r: From ἀπό (G575) and θλίβω (G2346)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g599.d:
†ἀποθνήσκω apothnḗskō, ap-oth-nace'-ko; from G575 and G2348; to die off (literally or figuratively):—be dead,
 death, die, lie a-dying, be slain (X with).
g599.r: From ἀπό (G575) and θνῄσκω (G2348)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g6.d: †Ἄβελ Ábel, ab'-el; of Hebrew origin (H1893); Abel, the son of Adam:—Abel.

g60.d:
ἀγοραῖος agoraîos, ag-or-ah'-yos; from G58; relating to the market-place, i.e. forensic (times); by
 implication, vulgar:—baser sort, low.

g600.d:
ἀποκαθίστημι apokathístēmi, ap-ok-ath-is'-tay-mee; from G575 and G2525; to reconstitute (in health, home or
 organization):—restore (again).
g600.r: From ἀπό (G575) and καθίστημι (G2525)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g601.d: ἀποκαλύπτω apokalýptō, ap-ok-al-oop'-to; from G575 and G2572; to take off the cover, i.e. disclose:—reveal.
g601.r: From ἀπό (G575) and καλύπτω (G2572)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g602.d:
ἀποκάλυψις apokálypsis, ap-ok-al'-oop-sis; from G601; disclosure:—appearing, coming, lighten, manifestation, be
 revealed, revelation.

g603.d:
ἀποκαραδοκία apokaradokía, ap-ok-ar-ad-ok-ee'-ah; from a comparative of G575 and a compound of κάρα kára (the head) and G1380
 (in the sense of watching); intense anticipation:—earnest
 expectation.
g603.r: From a comparative of ἀπό (G575) and a compound of kara (the head) and δοκέω (G1380) (in the sense of watching)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g604.d: ἀποκαταλλάσσω apokatallássō, ap-ok-at-al-las'-so; from G575 and G2644; to reconcile fully:—reconcile.
g604.r: From ἀπό (G575) and καταλλάσσω (G2644)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g605.d: ἀποκατάστασις apokatástasis, ap-ok-at-as'-tas-is; from G600; reconstitution:—restitution.

g606.d:
ἀπόκειμαι apókeimai, ap-ok'-i-mahee; from G575 and G2749; to be reserved; figuratively, to await:—be
 appointed, (be) laid up.
g606.r: From ἀπό (G575) and κεῖμαι (G2749)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g6063.r: See εἴδω (G1492)|English: know, cannot tell, know how, wist, misc, see, behold, look, perceive

g607.d: ἀποκεφαλίζω apokephalízō, ap-ok-ef-al-id'-zo; from G575 and G2776; to decapitate:—behead.

g608.d: ἀποκλείω apokleíō, ap-ok-li'-o; from G575 and G2808; to close fully:—shut up.
g608.r: From ἀπό (G575) and κλείω (G2808)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g609.d:
ἀποκόπτω apokóptō, ap-ok-op'-to; from G575 and G2875; to amputate; reflexively (by irony) to mutilate

g611.d:

 address is expected):—answer.
g611.r: From ἀπό (G575) and krino|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g612.d: ἀπόκρισις apókrisis, ap-ok'-ree-sis; from G611; a response:—answer.

g613.d:
ἀποκρύπτω apokrýptō, ap-ok-roop'-to; from G575 and G2928; to conceal away (i.e. fully); figuratively, to keep
 secret:—hide.
g613.r: From ἀπό (G575) and κρύπτω (G2928)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g614.d: ἀπόκρυφος apókryphos, ap-ok'-roo-fos; from G613; secret; by implication, treasured:—hid, kept secret.

g615.d:
†ἀποκτείνω apokteínō, ap-ok-ti'-no; from G575 and κτείνω kteínō (to slay); to kill outright; figuratively, to

g628.d:
ἀπολούω apoloúō, ap-ol-oo'-o; from G575 and G3068; to wash fully, i.e. (figuratively) have remitted
 (reflexively):—wash (away).
g628.r: From ἀπό (G575) and λούω (G3068)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g629.d:
ἀπολύτρωσις apolýtrōsis, ap-ol-oo'-tro-sis; from a compound of G575 and G3083; (the act) ransom in full, i.e.

 salvation:—deliverance, redemption.
g629.r: From a compound of ἀπό (G575) and λύτρον (G3083)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.

g658.d: ἀποτελέω apoteléō, ap-ot-el-eh'-o; from G575 and G5055; to complete entirely, i.e. consummate:—finish.
g658.r: From ἀπό (G575) and τελέω (G5055)|English: from, of, out of, for, off, by, at, in, since, on, not tr., misc.
