h1155.d: בֹּסֶר bôçer, bo'ser; from the same as H1154:—sour grape.
h1155.r: From the same as בֵּסֶר (H1154)|English: unripe grape

h1156.d: בְּעָא bᵉʻâʼ, beh-aw'; (Aramaic) or בְּעָה bᵉʻâh; (Aramaic), corresponding to H1158;  to seek or ask:—ask, desire, make (petition), pray, request, seek.
h1156.r: Corresponding to בָּעָה (H1158)|English: enquire, boil, sought up, swelling out

h1157.d: בְּעַד bᵉʻad, beh-ad'; from H5704 with prepositional prefix;  in up to or over against; generally at, beside, among, behind, for, etc.:—about, at by (means of), for, over, through, up (-on), within.
h1157.r: From עַד (H5704) with prepositional prefix|English: by, as long, hitherto, when, how long, as yet

h1158.d: בָּעָה bâʻâh, baw-aw'; a primitive root;  to gush over, i.e. to swell; (figuratively) to desire earnestly; by implication to ask:—cause, inquire, seek up, swell out.

h116.d: אֱדַיִן ʼĕdayin, ed-ah'-yin; (Aramaic) of uncertain derivation;  then (of time):—now, that time, then.

h1162.d: בֹּעַז Bôʻaz, bo'-az; from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  Boaz, the ancestor of David; also the name of a pillar in front of the temple:—Boaz.
h1162.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h1166.d: בָּעַל bâʻal, baw-al'; a primitive root; also as denominative from H1167  to be master; hence, to marry:—have dominion (over), be husband, marry(-ried, × wife).

h1167.d: בַּעַל baʻal, bah'-al; from H1166;  a master; hence, a husband, or (figuratively) owner (often used with another noun in modifications of this latter sense):—  archer,   babbler,   bird, captain, chief man,   confederate,   have to do,   dreamer, those to whom it is due,   furious, those that are given to it, great,   hairy, he that hath it, have,   horseman, husband, lord, man,   married, master, person,   sworn, they of.
h1167.r: From בָּעַל (H1166)|English: marry, husband, dominion, wife, married wife, Beulah

h1168.d: בַּעַל Baʻal, bah'-al; the same as H1167;  Baal, a Phoenician deity:—Baal, (plural) Baalim.
h1168.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h1168.r: The same as בַּעַל (H1167)|English: man, owner, husband, have, master, man given, adversary, archers, babbler, bird, captain, confederate, misc

h117.d: אַדִּיר ʼaddîyr, ad-deer'; from H142;  wide or (generally) large; figuratively, powerful:—excellent, famous, gallant, glorious, goodly, lordly, mighty(-ier one), noble, principal, worthy.

h1170.d: בַּעַל בְּרִית Baʻal Bᵉrîyth, bah'-al ber-eeth'; from H1168 and H1285; Baal of (the) covenant;  Baal-Berith, a special deity of the Shechemites:—Baal-berith.
h1170.r: From בַּעַל (H1168) and בְּרִית (H1285)|English: Baal, Baalim

h1173.d: בַּעֲלָה Baʻălâh, bah-al-aw'; the same as H1172;  Baalah, the name of three places in Palestine:—Baalah.
h1173.r: The same as בַּעֲלָה (H1172)|English: mistress, hath (a familiar spirit)

h1177.d: בַּעַל חָנָן Baʻal Chânân, bah'-al khaw-nawn'; from H1167 and H2603; possessor of grace;  Baal-Chanan, the name of an Edomite, also of an Israelite:—Baal-hanan.
h1177.r: From בַּעַל (H1167) and חָנַן (H2603)|English: man, owner, husband, have, master, man given, adversary, archers, babbler, bird, captain, confederate, misc

h1179.d: בַּעַל חֶרְמוֹן Baʻal Chermôwn, bah'-al kher-mone'; from H1167 and H2768; possessor of Hermon;  Baal-Chermon, a place in Palestine:—Baal-hermon.
h1179.r: From בַּעַל (H1167) and חֶרְמוֹן (H2768)|English: man, owner, husband, have, master, man given, adversary, archers, babbler, bird, captain, confederate, misc

h118.d: אֲדַלְיָא ʼĂdalyâʼ, ad-al-yaw'; of Persian derivation;  Adalja, a son of Haman:—Adalia.

h1181.d: בַּעֲלֵי בָּמוֹת Baʻălêy Bâmôwth, bah-al-ay' baw-moth'; from the plural of H1168 and the plural of H1116; Baals of (the) heights;  Baale-Bamoth, a place East of the Jordan:—lords of the high places.
h1181.r: From the pl. of בַּעַל (H1168) and the pl. of בָּמָה (H1116)|English: Baal, Baalim

h1182.d: בְּעֶלְיָדָע Bᵉʻelyâdâʻ, beh-el-yaw-daw'; from H1168 and H3045; Baal has known;  Beeljada, an Israelite:—Beeliada.
h1182.r: From בַּעַל (H1168) and יָדַע (H3045)|English: Baal, Baalim

h1183.d: בְּעַלְיָה Bᵉʻalyâh, beh-al-yaw'; from H1167 and H3050; Jah (is) master;  Bealjah, an Israelite:—Bealiah.
h1183.r: From בַּעַל (H1167) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: man, owner, husband, have, master, man given, adversary, archers, babbler, bird, captain, confederate, misc

h1186.d: בַּעַל מְעוֹן Baʻal Mᵉʻôwn, bah-al meh-one'; from H1168 and H4583; Baal of (the) habitation (of) (compare H1010);  Baal-Meon, a place East of the Jordan:—Baal-meon.
h1186.r: From בַּעַל (H1168) and מָעוֹן (H4583)|English: Baal, Baalim

h1187.d: בַּעַל פְּעוֹר Baʻal Pᵉʻôwr, bah'-al peh-ore'; from H1168 and H6465; Baal of Peor;  Baal-Peor, a Moabitish deity:—Baal-peor.
h1187.r: From בַּעַל (H1168) and פְעוֹר (H6465)|English: Baal, Baalim

h1188.d: בַּעַל פְּרָצִים Baʻal Pᵉrâtsîym, bah'-al per-aw-tseem'; from H1167 and the plural of H6556; possessor of breaches;  Baal-Peratsim, a place in Palestine:—Baal-perazim.
h1188.r: From בַּעַל (H1167) and the pl. of פֶּרֶץ (H6556)|English: man, owner, husband, have, master, man given, adversary, archers, babbler, bird, captain, confederate, misc

h1189.d: בַּעַל צְפוֹן Baʻal Tsᵉphôwn, bah'-al tsef-one'; from H1168 and H6828 (in the sense of cold) (according to others an Egyptian form of Typhon, the destroyer); Baal of winter;  Baal-Tsephon, a place in Eqypt:—Baal-zephon.
h1189.r: From בַּעַל (H1168) and צָפוֹן (H6828)|English: Baal, Baalim

h119.d: אָדַם ʼâdam, aw-dam'; to show blood (in the face), i.e. flush or turn rosy:—be (dyed, made) red (ruddy).

h1195.d: בַּעֲנָא Baʻănâʼ, bah-an-aw'; the same as H1196;  Baana, the name of four Israelite:—Baana, Baanah.

h1196.d: בַּעֲנָה Baʻănâh, bah-an-aw'; from a derivative of H6031 with prepositional prefix; in affliction  Baanah, the name of four Israelites:—Baanah.
h1196.r: From a derivative of עָנָה (H6031) with prepositional prefix|English: afflict, humble, force, exercised, sing, Leannoth, troubled, weakened, misc

h1197.d: בָּעַר bâʻar, baw-ar'; a primitive root; also as denominative from H1198  to kindle, i.e. consume (by fire or by eating); to be (-come) brutish:—be brutish, bring (put, take) away, burn, (cause to) eat (up), feed, heat, kindle, set (on fire), waste.

h1198.d: בַּעַר baʻar, bah'-ar; from H1197;  properly, foot (as consumed); i.e. (by exten.) of cattle brutishness; (concretely) stupid:—brutish (person), foolish.
h1198.r: From בָּעַר (H1197)|English: burn, ... away, kindle, brutish, eaten, set, burn up, eat up, feed, heated, took, wasted

h120.d: אָדַם ʼâdam, aw-dam'; from H119;  ruddy i.e. a human being (an individual or the species, mankind, etc.):—× another,   hypocrite,   common sort, × low, man (mean, of low degree), person.
h120.r: From אָדַם (H119)|English: dyed red, red ruddy

h1201.d: בַּעְשָׁא Baʻshâʼ, bah-shaw'; from an unused root meaning to stink; offensiveness;  Basha, a king of Israel:—Baasha.
h1201.r: From an unused root meaning to stink|

h1204.d: בָּעַת bâʻath, baw-ath'; a primitive root;  to fear:—affright, be (make) afraid, terrify, trouble.

h1205.d: בְּעָתָה bᵉʻâthâh, beh-aw-thaw'; from H1204;  fear:—trouble.
h1205.r: From בָּעַת (H1204)|English: afraid, terrify, affrighted, trouble

h1209.d: בֵּצַי Bêtsay, bay-tsah'-ee; perhaps the same as H1153;  Betsai, the name of two Israelites:—Bezai.
h1209.r: Perhaps the same as בֵּסַי (H1153)|English: Besai

h121.d: אָדָם ʼÂdâm, aw-dawm'; the same as H120;  Adam the name of the first man, also of a place in Palestine:—Adam.
h121.r: The same as אָדָם (H120)|English: man, men, Adam, person(s), common sort, hypocrite

h1212.d: בְּצַלְאֵל Bᵉtsalʼêl, bets-al-ale'; probably from H6738 and H410 with a prepositional prefix; in (the) shadow (i.e. protection) of God;  Betsalel, the name of two Israelites:—Bezaleel.
h1212.r: Probably from צֵל (H6738) and אֵל (H410) with a prepositional prefix|English: shadow, defence, shade

h1214.d: בָּצַע bâtsaʻ, baw-tsah'; a primitive root  to break off, i.e. (usually) plunder; figuratively, to finish, or (intransitively) stop:—(be) covet(-ous), cut (off), finish, fulfill, gain (greedily), get, be given to (covetousness), greedy, perform, be wounded.

h1215.d: בֶּצַע betsaʻ, beh'-tsah; from H1214;  plunder; by extension, gain (usually unjust):—covetousness, (dishonest) gain, lucre, profit.
h1215.r: From בָּצַע (H1214)|English: cut me off, gained, given, greedy, coveteth, covetous, cut, finish, fulfilled, get, performed, wounded

h1216.d: בָּצֵק bâtsêq, baw-tsake'; a primitive root;  perhaps to swell up, i.e. blister:—swell.

h1217.d: בָּצֵק bâtsêq, baw-tsake'; from H1216;  dough (as swelling by fermentation):—dough, flour.

h1219.d: בָּצַר bâtsar, baw-tsar'; a primitive root; to clip off; specifically (as denominative from H1210)  to gather grapes; also to be isolated (i.e. inaccessible by height or fortification):—cut off, (de-) fenced, fortify, (grape) gather(-er), mighty things, restrain, strong, wall (up), withhold.

h122.d: אָדֹם ʼâdôm, aw-dome'; from H119;  rosy:—red, ruddy.
h122.r: From אָדַם (H119)|English: dyed red, red ruddy

h1220.d: בֶּצֶר betser, beh'-tser; from H1219;  strictly a clipping, i.e. gold (as dug out):—gold defence.
h1220.r: From בָּצַר (H1219)|English: fenced, defenced, gather, grapegatherers, fortify, cut off, restrained, strong, mighty things, walled up, fenced up, walled, withholden, non translated variant

h1221.d: בֶּצֶר Betser, beh'-tser; the same as H1220, an inaccessible spot;  Betser, a place in Palestine; also an Israelite:—Bezer.
h1221.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h1221.r: The same as בֶּצֶר (H1220)|English: gold, defence

h1224.d: בׇּצְרָה Botsrâh, bots-raw'; the same as H1223;  Botsrah, a place in Edom:—Bozrah.

h1229.d: בַּקְבֻּקְיָה Baqbuqyâh, bak-book-yaw'; from H1228 and H3050; emptying (i.e. wasting) of Jah;  Bakbukjah, an Israelite:—Bakbukiah.
h1229.r: From בַּקְבּוּק (H1228) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: bottle cruse

h123.d: אֱדֹם ʼĔdôm, ed-ome'; or (fully) אֱדוֹם ʼĔdôwm ; from H122; red (see Genesis 25:25);  Edom, the elder twin-brother of Jacob; hence the region (Idumaea) occupied by him:—Edom, Edomites, Idumea.

h1231.d: בֻּקִּי Buqqîy, book-kee'; from H1238; wasteful;  Bukki, the name of two Israelites:—Bukki.
h1231.r: From בָּקַק (H1238)|English: empty, make void, emptiers, fail, utterly (inf for emphasis

h1232.d: בֻּקִּיָּה Buqqîyâh, book-kee-yaw'; from H1238 and H3050; wasting of Jah;  Bukkijah, an Israelite:—Bukkiah.
h1232.r: From בָּקַק (H1238) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: empty, make void, emptiers, fail, utterly (inf for emphasis

h1234.d: בָּקַע bâqaʻ, baw-kah'; a primitive root;  to cleave; generally, to rend, break, rip or open:—make a breach, break forth (into, out, in pieces, through, up), be ready to burst, cleave (asunder), cut out, divide, hatch, rend (asunder), rip up, tear, win.

h1237.d: בִּקְעָה biqʻâh, bik-aw'; from H1234;  properly, a split, i.e. a wide level valley between mountains:—plain, valley.
h1237.r: From בָּקַע (H1234)|English: cleave, ...up, divide, rent, ... out, break through, rend, breach, asunder, hatch, brake, burst, cleft, break forth, pieces, tare, tear, win

h1238.d: בָּקַק bâqaq, baw-kah'; a primitive root;  to pour out, i.e. to empty, figuratively, to depopulate; by analogy, to spread out (as a fruitful vine):—(make) empty (out), fail, × utterly, make void.

h1241.d: בָּקָר bâqâr, baw-kawr'; from H1239;  a beeve or an animal of the ox family of either gender (as used for plowing); collectively, a herd:—beeve, bull (+ -ock), + calf, + cow, great (cattle), + heifer, herd, kine, ox.

h1242.d: בֹּקֶר bôqer, bo'-ker; from H1239; properly, dawn (as the break of day); generally, morning:—(+) day, early, morning, morrow.

h1245.d: בָּקַשׁ bâqash, baw-kash'; a primitive root;  to search out (by any method, specifically in worship or prayer); by implication, to strive after:—ask, beg, beseech, desire, enquire, get, make inquisition, procure, (make) request, require, seek (for).

h1246.d: בַּקָּשָׁה baqqâshâh, bak-kaw-shaw'; from H1245;  a petition:—request.
h1246.r: From בָּקַשׁ (H1245)|English: seek, require, request, seek out, enquired, besought, ask, sought for, begging, desire, get, inquisition, procureth

h125.d: אֲדַמְדָּם ʼădamdâm, ad-am-dawm'; reduplicated from H119;  reddish:—(somewhat) reddish.
h125.r: Reduplicated from אָדַם (H119)|English: dyed red, red ruddy

h1250.d: בָּר bâr, bawr; or בַּר bar; from H1305 (in the sense of winnowing);  grain of any kind (even while standing in the field); by extension the open country:—corn, wheat.
h1250.r: From בָּרַר (H1305) (in the sense of winnowing)|English: pure, choice, chosen, clean, clearly, manifest, bright, purge out, polished, purge, purified

h1254.d: בָּרָא bârâʼ, baw-raw'; a primitive root;  (absolutely) to create; (qualified) to cut down (a wood), select, feed (as formative processes):—choose, create (creator), cut down, dispatch, do, make (fat).

h1256.d: בְּרָאיָה Bᵉrâʼyâh, ber-aw-yaw'; from H1254 and H8050; Jah has created;  Berajah, an Israelite:—Beraiah.
h1256.r: From בָּרָא (H1254) and שְׁמוּאֵל (H8050)|English: create, creator, choose, make, cut down, dispatch, done, make fat

h1257.d: בַּרְבֻּר barbur, bar-boor'; by reduplication from H1250;  a fowl (as fattened on grain):—fowl.
h1257.r: By reduplication from בַּר (H1250)|English: corn, wheat

h1259.d: בָּרָד bârâd, baw-rawd'; from H1258;  hail:—hail(stones).

h126.d: אַדְמָה ʼAdmâh, ad-maw'; contracted for H127; earthy;  Admah, a place near the Dead Sea:—Admah.
h126.r: Contracted for אֲדָמָה (H127)|English: land(s), earth, ground, country, husbandman, husbandry

h1261.d: בָּרֹד bârôd, baw-rode'; from H1258;  spotted (as if with hail):—grisled.

h1262.d: בָּרָה bârâh, baw-raw'; a primitive root; to select; also (as denominative from H1250) to feed; also (as equivalent to H1305) to render clear (Ecclesiastes 3:18)  to select; to feed; to render clear:—choose, (cause to) eat, manifest, (give) meat.

h1263.d: בָּרוּךְ Bârûwk, baw-rook'; passive participle from H1288; blessed;  Baruk, the name of three Israelites:—Baruch.
h1263.r: Pass. participle from בָּרַךְ (H1288)|English: bless, salute, curse, blaspheme, blessing, praised, kneel down, congratulate, kneel, make to kneel, misc

h1265.d: בְּרוֹשׁ bᵉrôwsh, ber-osh'; of uncertain derivation;  a cypress (?) tree; hence, a lance or a musical instrument (as made of that wood):—fir (tree).

h1268.d: בֵּרוֹתָה Bêrôwthâh, bay-ro-thaw'; or בֵּרֹתַי Bêrôthay; probably from H1266; cypress or cypresslike;  Berothah or Berothai, a place north of Palestine:—Berothah, Berothai.

h127.d: אֲדָמָה ʼădâmâh, ad-aw-maw'; from H119;  soil (from its general redness):—country, earth, ground, husband(-man) (-ry), land.
h127.r: From אָדַם (H119)|English: dyed red, red ruddy

h1270.d: בַּרְזֶל barzel, bar-zel'; perhaps from the root of H1269;  iron (as cutting); by extension, an iron implement:—(ax) head, iron.
h1270.r: Perhaps from the root of בִּרְזוֹת (H1269)|English: Birzavith

h1271.d: בַּרְזִלַּי Barzillay, bar-zil-lah'-ee; from H1270; iron-hearted;  Barzillai, the name of three Israelites:—Barzillai.

h1272.d: בָּרַח bârach, baw-rakh'; a primitive root;  to bolt, i.e. figuratively, to flee suddenly:—chase (away); drive away, fain, flee (away), put to flight, make haste, reach, run away, shoot.

h1275.d: בֵּרִי Bêrîy, bay-ree'; probably by contraction from H882;  Beri, an Israelite:—Beri.
h1275.r: Probably by contraction from בְּאֵרִי (H882)|English: Beeri

h1277.d: בָּרִיא bârîyʼ, baw-ree'; from H1254 (in the sense of H1262);  fatted or plump:—fat ((fleshed), -ter), fed, firm, plenteous, rank.
h1277.r: From בָּרָא (H1254) (in the sense of בָּרָה (H1262))|English: create, creator, choose, make, cut down, dispatch, done, make fat

h1278.d: בְּרִיאָה bᵉrîyʼâh, ber-ee-aw'; feminine from H1254;  a creation, i.e. a novelty:—new thing.
h1278.r: From בָּרָא (H1254)|English: create, creator, choose, make, cut down, dispatch, done, make fat

h1279.d: בִּרְיָה biryâh, beer-yaw'; feminine from H1262;  food:—meat.
h1279.r: From בָּרָה (H1262)|English: eat, choose, give, cause to eat

h1280.d: בְּרִיחַ bᵉrîyach, ber-ee'-akh; from H1272;  a bolt:—bar, fugitive.
h1280.r: From בָּרַח (H1272)|English: flee, ...away, chased, fain (inf. for emphasis), flight, make haste, reach, shoot

h1282.d: בָּרִיחַ Bârîyach, baw-ree'-akh; the same as H1281;  Bariach, an Israelite:—Bariah.
h1282.r: The same as בָּרִחַ (H1281)|English: crooked, piercing, nobles

h1283.d: בְּרִיעָה Bᵉrîyʻâh, ber-ee'-aw; apparently from the feminine of H7451 with a prepositional prefix; in trouble;  Beriah, the name of four Israelites:—Beriah.
h1283.r: Apparently from the fem. of רַע (H7451) with a prepositional prefix|English: evil, wickedness, wicked, mischief, hurt, bad, trouble, sore, affliction, ill, adversity, favoured, harm, naught, noisome, grievous, sad

h1285.d: בְּרִית bᵉrîyth, ber-eeth'; from H1262 (in the sense of cutting [like H1254]);  a compact (because made by passing between pieces of flesh):—confederacy, (con-) feder(-ate), covenant, league.
h1285.r: From בָּרָה (H1262) (in the sense of cutting [like בָּרָא (H1254)])|English: eat, choose, give, cause to eat

h1287.d: בֹּרִית bôrîyth, bo-reeth'; feminine of H1253;  vegetable alkali:—sope.
h1287.r: From בֹּר (H1253)|English: purely, non translated variant

h1288.d: בָּרַךְ bârak, baw-rak'; a primitive root;  to kneel; by implication to bless God (as an act of adoration), and (vice-versa) man (as a benefit); also (by euphemism) to curse (God or the king, as treason):—× abundantly, × altogether, × at all, blaspheme, bless, congratulate, curse, × greatly, × indeed, kneel (down), praise, salute, × still, thank.

h1289.d: בְּרַךְ bᵉrak, ber-ak'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1288:—bless, kneel.
h1289.r: Corresponding to בָּרַךְ (H1288)|English: bless, salute, curse, blaspheme, blessing, praised, kneel down, congratulate, kneel, make to kneel, misc

h1290.d: בֶּרֶךְ berek, beh'-rek; from H1288;  a knee:—knee.
h1290.r: From בָּרַךְ (H1288)|English: bless, salute, curse, blaspheme, blessing, praised, kneel down, congratulate, kneel, make to kneel, misc

h1293.d: בְּרָכָה Bᵉrâkâh, ber-aw-kaw'; from H1288;  benediction; by implication prosperity:—blessing, liberal, pool, present.
h1293.r: From בָּרַךְ (H1288)|English: bless, salute, curse, blaspheme, blessing, praised, kneel down, congratulate, kneel, make to kneel, misc

h1295.d: בְּרֵכָה bᵉrêkâh, ber-ay-kaw'; from H1288;  a reservoir (at which camels kneel as a resting-place):—(fish-) pool.
h1295.r: From בָּרַךְ (H1288)|English: bless, salute, curse, blaspheme, blessing, praised, kneel down, congratulate, kneel, make to kneel, misc

h1296.d: בֶּרֶכְיָה Berekyâh, beh-rek-yaw'; or בֶּרֶכְיָהוּ Berekyâhûw; from H1290 and H3050; knee (i.e. blessing) of Jah;  Berekjah, the name of six Israelites:—Berachiah, Berechiah.

h1297.d: בְּרַם bᵉram, ber-am'; (Aramaic) perhaps from H7313 with a prepositional prefix;  properly, highly, i.e. surely; but used adversatively, however:—but, nevertheless, yet.
h1297.r: Perhaps from רוּם (H7313) with a prepositional prefix|English: lift up, extol, set up

h1298.d: בֶּרַע Beraʻ, beh'-rah; of uncertain derivation;  Bera, a Sodomitish king:—Bera.

h1299.d: בָּרַק bâraq, baw-rak'; a primitive root;  to lighten (lightning):—cast forth.

h130.d: אֱדֹמִי ʼĔdômîy, ed-o-mee'; or (fully) אֱדוֹמִי ʼĔdôwmîy ; patronymic from H123; See H726.  an Edomite, or descendants from (or inhabitants of) Edom:—Edomite.
h130.r: Patronymic from אֱדֹם (H123)|English: Edom, Edomites, Idumea

h1300.d: בָּרָק bârâq, baw-rawk'; from H1299;  lightning; by analogy, a gleam; concretely, a flashing sword:—bright, glitter(-ing sword), lightning.

h1301.d: בָּרָק Bârâq, baw-rawk'; the same as H1300;  Barak, an Israelite:—Barak.
h1301.r: The same as בָּרָק (H1300)|English: lightning, glittering, bright, glitter, glittering sword

h1305.d: בָּרַר bârar, baw-rar'; a primitive root;  to clarify (i.e. brighten), examine, select:—make bright, choice, chosen, cleanse (be clean), clearly, polished, (shew self) pure(-ify), purge (out).

h1308.d: בְּשׂוֹר Bᵉsôwr, bes-ore'; from H1319; cheerful;  Besor, a stream of Palestine:—Besor.
h1308.r: From בָּשַׂר (H1319)|English: tidings, show forth, publish, messenger, preached

h1309.d: בְּשׂוֹרָה bᵉsôwrâh, bes-o-raw'; or (shortened) בְּשֹׂרָה bᵉsôrâh; feminine from H1319;  glad tidings; by implication, reward for good news:—reward for tidings.
h1309.r: From בָּשַׂר (H1319)|English: tidings, show forth, publish, messenger, preached

h1310.d: בָּשַׁל bâshal, baw-shal'; a primitive root;  properly, to boil up; hence, to be done in cooking; figuratively to ripen:—bake, boil, bring forth, roast, seethe, sod (be sodden).

h1312.d: בִּשְׁלָם Bishlâm, bish-lawm'; of foreign derivation;  Bishlam, a Persian:—Bishlam.

h1314.d: בֶּשֶׂם besem, beh'-sem; or בֹּשֶׂם bôsem; from the same as H1313;  fragrance; by implication, spicery; also the balsam plant:—smell, spice, sweet (odour).
h1314.r: From the same as בָּשָׂם (H1313)|English: spice

h1315.d: בׇּשְׂמַת Bosmath, bos-math'; feminine of H1314 (the second form); fragrance;  Bosmath, the name of a wife of Esau, and of a daughter of Solomon:—Bashemath, Basmath.
h1315.r: From בֶּשֶׂם (H1314) (the second form); fragrance|English: spice, sweet odours, sweet, sweet smell

h1316.d: בָּשָׁן Bâshân, baw-shawn'; of uncertain derivation;  Bashan (often with the article), a region East of the Jordan:—Bashan.

h1317.d: בׇּשְׁנָה boshnâh, bosh-naw'; feminine from H954;  shamefulness:—shame.
h1317.r: From בּוּשׁ (H954)|English: ashamed, confounded, shame, all (inf. for emphasis), confusion, delayed, dry, long, shamed

h1319.d: בָּשַׂר bâsar, baw-sar'; a primitive root;  properly, to be fresh, i.e. full (rosy, figuratively cheerful); to announce (glad news):—messenger, preach, publish, shew forth, (bear, bring, carry, preach, good, tell good) tidings.

h132.d: אַדְמֹנִי ʼadmônîy, ad-mo-nee'; or (fully) אַדְמוֹנִי ʼadmôwnîy ; from H119;  reddish (of the hair or the complexion):—red, ruddy.
h132.r: From אָדַם (H119)|English: dyed red, red ruddy

h1320.d: בָּשָׂר bâsâr, baw-sawr'; from H1319;  flesh (from its freshness); by extension, body, person; also (by euphemistically) the pudenda of a man:—body, (fat, lean) flesh(-ed), kin, (man-) kind,   nakedness, self, skin.
h1320.r: From בָּשַׂר (H1319)|English: tidings, show forth, publish, messenger, preached

h1321.d: בְּשַׁר bᵉshar, bes-ar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1320:—flesh.
h1321.r: Corresponding to בָּשָׂר (H1320)|English: flesh, body, fatfleshed, leanfleshed, kin, leanfleshed, mankind, myself, nakedness, skin

h1322.d: בֹּשֶׁת bôsheth, bo'-sheth; from H954;  shame (the feeling and the condition, as well as its cause); by implication (specifically) an idol:—ashamed, confusion,   greatly, (put to) shame(-ful thing).
h1322.r: From בּוּשׁ (H954)|English: ashamed, confounded, shame, all (inf. for emphasis), confusion, delayed, dry, long, shamed

h1323.d: בַּת bath, bath; from H1129 (as feminine of H1121);  a daughter (used in the same wide sense as other terms of relationship, literally and figuratively):—apple (of the eye), branch, company, daughter, × first, × old,   owl, town, village.
h1323.r: From בָּנָה (H1129) and בֵּן (H1121)|English: build, build up, builder, made, built again, repair, set up, have children, obtain children, surely (inf. for emphasis)

h1324.d: בַּת bath, bath; probably from the same as H1327;  a bath or Hebrew measure (as a means of division) of liquids:—bath.
h1324.r: Probably from the same as בַּתָּה (H1327)|English: desolate

h1325.d: בַּת bath, bath; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1324:—bath.

h1328.d: בְּתוּאֵל Bᵉthûwʼêl, beth-oo-ale'; apparently from the same as H1326 and H410; destroyed of God;  Bethuel, the name of a nephew of Abraham, and of a place in Palestine:—Bethuel. Compare 1329.
h1328.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h1328.r: Apparently from the same as בָּתָה (H1326) and אֵל (H410)|English: waste

h133.d: אַדְמָתָא ʼAdmâthâʼ, ad-maw-thaw'; probably of Persian derivation;  Admatha, a Persian nobleman:—Admatha.

h1330.d: בְּתוּלָה bᵉthûwlâh, beth-oo-law'; feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to separate;  a virgin (from her privacy); sometimes (by continuation) a bride; also (figuratively) a city or state:—maid, virgin.
h1330.r: Pass. participle of an unused root meaning to separate|

h1331.d: בְּתוּלִים bᵉthûwlîym, beth-oo-leem'; masculine plural of the same as H1330;  (collectively and abstractly) virginity; by implication and concretely, the tokens of it:—× maid, virginity.
h1331.r: Masculine plural of the same as בְּתוּלָה (H1330)|English: virgin, maid, maiden

h1335.d: בֶּתֶר bether, beh'-ther; from H1334;  a section:—part, piece.

h1338.d: בִּתְרוֹן Bithrôwn, bith-rone'; from H1334; (with the article) the craggy spot;  Bithron, a place East of the Jordan:—Bithron.

h1339.d: בַּת־שֶׁבַע Bath-Shebaʻ, bath-sheh'-bah; from H1323 and H7651 (in the sense of H7650); daughter of an oath;  Bath-Sheba, the mother of Solomon:—Bath-sheba.
h1339.r: From בַּת (H1323) and שֶׁבַע (H7651) (in the sense of שָׁבַע (H7650))|English: daughter, town, village, owl, first, apple, branches, children, company, daughter, eye, old

h1341.d: גֵּא gêʼ, gay'; for H1343;  haughty:—proud.

h1342.d: גָּאָה gâʼâh, gaw-aw'; a primitive root;  to mount up; hence, in general, to rise, (figuratively) be majestic:—gloriously, grow up, increase, be risen, triumph.

h1343.d: גֵּאֶה gêʼeh, gay-eh'; from H1342;  lofty; figuratively, arrogant:—proud.
h1343.r: From גָּאָה (H1342)|English: triumph, gloriously, risen, grow up, increase

h1344.d: גֵּאָה gêʼâh, gay-aw'; feminine from H1342;  arrogance:—pride.
h1344.r: From גָּאָה (H1342)|English: triumph, gloriously, risen, grow up, increase

h1345.d: גְּאוּאֵל Gᵉʼûwʼêl, gheh-oo-ale'; from H1342 and H410; majesty of God;  Geuel, an Israelite:—Geuel.
h1345.r: From גָּאָה (H1342) and אֵל (H410)|English: triumph, gloriously, risen, grow up, increase

h1346.d: גַּאֲוָה gaʼăvâh, gah-av-aw'; from H1342;  arrogance or majesty; by implication, (concretely) ornament:—excellency, haughtiness, highness, pride, proudly, swelling.
h1346.r: From גָּאָה (H1342)|English: triumph, gloriously, risen, grow up, increase

h1347.d: גָּאוֹן gâʼôwn, gaw-ohn'; from H1342;  the same as H1346:—arrogancy, excellency(-lent), majesty, pomp, pride, proud, swelling.
h1347.r: From גָּאָה (H1342)|English: triumph, gloriously, risen, grow up, increase

h135.d: אַדָּן ʼAddân, ad-dawn'; intensive from the same as H134; firm;  Addan, an Israelite:—Addan.
h135.r: Intensive from the same as אֶדֶן (H134)|English: socket(s), foundations

h1350.d: גָּאַל gâʼal, gaw-al'; a primitive root,  to redeem (according to the Oriental law of kinship), i.e. to be the next of kin (and as such to buy back a relative's property, marry his widow, etc.):—× in any wise, × at all, avenger, deliver, (do, perform the part of near, next) kinsfolk(-man), purchase, ransom, redeem(-er), revenger.

h1351.d: גָּאַל gâʼal, gaw-al'; a primitive root, (rather identified with H1350, through the idea of freeing, i.e. repudiating);  to soil or (figuratively) desecrate:—defile, pollute, stain.

h1353.d: גְּאֻלָּה gᵉʼullâh, gheh-ool-law'; feminine passive participle of H1350;  redemption (including the right and the object); by implication, relationship:—kindred, redeem, redemption, right.
h1353.r: Pass. participle of גָּאַל (H1350)|English: redeem, redeemer, kinsman, revenger, avenger, ransom, at all, deliver, kinsfolks, kinsman's part, purchase, stain, wise

h1356.d: גֵּב gêb, gabe; from H1461;  a log (as cut out); also well or cistern (as dug):—beam, ditch, pit.

h1358.d: גֹּב gôb, gobe; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H1461;  a pit (for wild animals) (as cut out):—den.
h1358.r: From a root corresponding to גּוּב (H1461)|English: husbandman

h136.d: אֲדֹנָי ʼĂdônây, ad-o-noy'; an emphatic form of H113;  the Lord (used as a proper name of God only):—(my) Lord.
h136.r: Am emphatic form of אָדוֹן (H113)|English: lord, master(s), Lord, owner, sir

h1361.d: גָּבַהּ gâbahh, gaw-bah'; a primitive root;  to soar, i.e. be lofty; figuratively, to be haughty:—exalt, be haughty, be (make) high(-er), lift up, mount up, be proud, raise up great height, upward.

h1363.d: גֹּבַהּ gôbahh, go'-bah; from H1361;  elation, grandeur, arrogance:—excellency, haughty, height, high, loftiness, pride.
h1363.r: From גָּבַהּ (H1361)|English: exalt, ... up, haughty, higher, high, above, height, proud, upward

h1364.d: גָּבֹהַּ gâbôahh, gaw-bo'-ah; or גָּבוֹהַּ gâbôwahh; (fully) from H1361;  elevated (or elated), powerful, arrogant:—haughty, height, high(-er), lofty, proud, × exceeding proudly.
h1364.r: From גָּבַהּ (H1361)|English: exalt, ... up, haughty, higher, high, above, height, proud, upward

h1366.d: גְּבוּל gᵉbûwl, gheb-ool'; or גְּבֻל gᵉbul; (shortened) from H1379;  properly, a cord (as twisted), i.e. (by implication) a boundary; by extension the territory inclosed:—border, bound, coast, × great, landmark, limit, quarter, space.
h1366.r: From גָּבַל (H1379)|English: border set bounds, set

h1368.d: גִּבּוֹר gibbôwr, ghib-bore'; or גִּבֹּר gibbôr; (shortened) intensive from the same as H1397;  powerful; by implication, warrior, tyrant:—champion, chief, × excel, giant, man, mighty (man, one), strong (man), valiant man.
h1368.r: Intensive from גָּבַר (H1396)|English: prevail, strengthen, great, confirm, exceeded, mighty, put, stronger, valiant

h1369.d: גְּבוּרָה gᵉbûwrâh, gheb-oo-raw'; feminine passive participle from the same as H1368;  force (literally or figuratively); by implication, valor, victory:—force, mastery, might, mighty (act, power), power, strength.
h1369.r: Pass. participle from the same as גִּבּוֹר (H1368)|English: mighty, mighty man, strong, valiant, .... ones, mighties, man, valiant men, strong man, upright man , champion, chief, excel, giant, men's, mightiest, strongest

h137.d: אֲדֹנִי־בֶזֶק ʼĂdônîy-Bezeq, ad-o''-nee-beh'-zek; from H113 and H966; lord of Bezek;  Adoni-Bezek; a Canaanitish king:—Adonibezek.
h137.r: From אָדוֹן (H113) and בֶּזֶק (H966)|English: lord, master(s), Lord, owner, sir

h1372.d: גַּבַּחַת gabbachath, gab-bakh'-ath; from the same as H1371;  baldness in the forehead; by analogy, a bare spot on the right side of cloth:—bald forehead, × without.
h1372.r: From the same as גִּבֵּחַ (H1371)|English: forehead bald

h1375.d: גְּבִיעַ gᵉbîyaʻ, gheb-ee'-ah; from an unused root (meaning to be convex);  a goblet; by analogy, the calyx of a flower:—house, cup, pot.

h1376.d: גְּבִיר gᵉbîyr, gheb-eer'; from H1396;  a master:—lord.
h1376.r: From גָּבַר (H1396)|English: prevail, strengthen, great, confirm, exceeded, mighty, put, stronger, valiant

h1377.d: גְּבִירָה gᵉbîyrâh, gheb-ee-raw'; feminine of H1376;  a mistress:—queen.

h1379.d: גָּבַל gâbal, gaw-bal'; a primitive root; also as a denominative from H1366  properly, to twist as a rope; to bound (as by a line):—be border, set (bounds about).

h138.d: אֲדֹנִיָּה ʼĂdônîyâh, ad-o-nee-yaw'; original (prolonged) אֲדֹנִיָּהוּ ʼĂdônîyâhûw ; from H113 and H3050; lord (i.e. worshipper) of Jah;  Adonijah, the name of three Israelites:—Adonijah.
h138.r: From אָדוֹן (H113) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: lord, master(s), Lord, owner, sir

h1381.d: גְּבָל Gᵉbâl, gheb-awl'; the same as H1380;  Gebal, a region in Idumaea:—Gebal.

h1387.d: גֶּבַע Gebaʻ, gheh'-bah; from the same as H1375, a hillock;  Geba, a place in Palestine:—Gaba, Geba, Gibeah.
h1387.r: From the same as גָּבִיעַ (H1375)|English: bowl, cup, pot

h1389.d: גִּבְעָה gibʻâh, ghib-aw'; feminine from the same as H1387;  a hillock:—hill, little hill.
h1389.r: From the same as גֶּבַע (H1387)|English: Geba, Gibeah, Gaba

h1390.d: גִּבְעָה Gibʻâh, ghib-aw'; the same as H1389;  Gibah; the name of three places in Palestine:—Gibeah, the hill.

h1391.d: גִּבְעוֹן Gibʻôwn, ghib-ohn'; from the same as H1387; hilly;  Gibon, a place in Palestine:—Gibeon.
h1391.r: From the same as גֶּבַע (H1387)|English: Geba, Gibeah, Gaba

h1396.d: גָּבַר gâbar, gaw-bar'; a primitive root;  to be strong; by implication, to prevail, act insolently:—exceed, confirm, be great, be mighty, prevail, put to more (strength), strengthen, be stronger, be valiant.

h1397.d: גֶּבֶר geber, gheh'-ber; from H1396;  properly, a valiant man or warrior; generally, a person simply:—every one, man, × mighty.
h1397.r: From גָּבַר (H1396)|English: prevail, strengthen, great, confirm, exceeded, mighty, put, stronger, valiant

h1398.d: גֶּבֶר Geber, gheh'-ber; the same as H1397;  Geber, the name of two Israelites:—Geber.
h1398.r: The same as גֶּבֶר (H1397)|English: man, mighty, man child, every one

h1399.d: גְּבַר gᵉbar, gheb-ar'; from H1396; the same as H1397;  a person:—man.
h1399.r: From גָּבַר (H1396)|English: prevail, strengthen, great, confirm, exceeded, mighty, put, stronger, valiant

h14.d: אָבָה ʼâbâh, aw-baw'; a primitive root;  to breathe after, i.e. (figuratively) to be acquiescent:—consent, rest content will, be willing.

h1400.d: גְּבַר gᵉbar, gheb-ar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1399:—certain, man.

h1401.d: גִּבָּר gibbâr, ghib-bawr'; (Aramaic) intensive of H1400;  valiant, or warrior:—mighty.

h1403.d: גַּבְרִיאֵל Gabrîyʼêl, gab-ree-ale'; from H1397 and H410; man of God;  Gabriel, an archangel:—Garbriel.
h1403.r: From גֶּבֶר (H1397) and אֵל (H410)|English: man, mighty, man child, every one

h1405.d: גִּבְּתוֹן Gibbᵉthôwn, ghib-beth-one'; intensive from H1389; a hilly spot;  Gibbethon, a place in Palestine:—Gibbethon.

h1406.d: גָּג gâg, gawg; probably by reduplication from H1342;  a roof; by analogy, the top of an altar:—roof (of the house), (house) top (of the house).
h1406.r: Probably by reduplication from גָּאָה (H1342)|English: triumph, gloriously, risen, grow up, increase

h1410.d: גָּד Gâd, gawd; from H1464;  Gad, a son of Jacob, including his tribe and its territory; also a prophet:—Gad.
h1410.r: From גּוּד (H1464)|English: overcome, invade with troops

h1413.d: גָּדַד gâdad, gaw-dad'; a primitive root (compare H1464);  to crowd; also to gash (as if by pressing into):—assemble (selves by troops), gather (selves together, self in troops), cut selves.
h1413.r: A primitive root [compare גּוּד (H1464)]|English: overcome, invade with troops

h1414.d: גְּדַד gᵉdad, ghed-ad'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1413;  to cut down:—hew down.
h1414.r: Corresponding to גָּדַד (H1413)|English: cut, gather together, assemble by troop, gather

h1416.d: גְּדוּד gᵉdûwd, ghed-ood'; from H1413;  a crowd (especially of soldiers):—army, band (of men), company, troop (of robbers).
h1416.r: From גָּדַד (H1413)|English: cut, gather together, assemble by troop, gather

h1419.d: גָּדוֹל gâdôwl, gaw-dole'; or גָּדֹל gâdôl; (shortened) from H1431;  great (in any sense); hence, older; also insolent:—  aloud, elder(-est),   exceeding(-ly),   far, (man of) great (man, matter, thing,-er,-ness), high, long, loud, mighty, more, much, noble, proud thing, × sore, (×) very.
h1419.r: From גָּדַל (H1431)|English: magnify, great, grow, nourish up, grow up, greater, misc

h1420.d: גְּדוּלָה gᵉdûwlâh, ghed-oo-law'; or גְּדֻלָּה gᵉdullâh; (shortened) or (less accurately) גְּדוּלָּה gᵉdûwllâh; feminine of H1419;  greatness; (concretely) mighty acts:—dignity, great things(-ness), majesty.
h1420.r: From גָּדוֹל (H1419)|English: great, high, greater, loud, greatest, elder, great man, mighty, eldest, misc

h1423.d: גְּדִי gᵉdîy, ghed-ee'; from the same as H1415;  a young goat (from browsing):—kid.
h1423.r: From the same as גָּדָה (H1415)|English: bank

h1426.d: גַּדִּי Gaddîy, gad-dee'; intensive for H1424;  Gaddi, an Israelite:—Gaddi.

h1427.d: גַּדִּיאֵל Gaddîyʼêl, gad-dee-ale'; from H1409 and H410; fortune of God;  Gaddiel, an Israelite:—Gaddiel.

h1429.d: גְּדִיָּה gᵉdîyâh, ghed-ee-yaw'; feminine of H1423;  a young female goat:—kid.

h143.d: אֲדָר ʼĂdâr, ad-awr'; probably of foreign derivation; perhaps meaning fire;  Adar, the 12th Hebrew month:—Adar.

h1431.d: גָּדַל gâdal, gaw-dal'; a primitive root; properly, to twist (compare H1434), i.e.  to be (causatively make) large (in various senses, as in body, mind, estate or honor, also in pride):—advance, boast, bring up, exceed, excellent, be(-come, do, give, make, wax), great(-er, come to... estate,   things), grow(up), increase, lift up, magnify(-ifical), be much set by, nourish (up), pass, promote, proudly (spoken), tower.

h1433.d: גֹּדֶל gôdel, go'-del; from H1431;  magnitude (literally or figuratively):—greatness, stout(-ness).
h1433.r: From גָּדַל (H1431)|English: magnify, great, grow, nourish up, grow up, greater, misc

h1436.d: גְּדַּלְיָה Gᵉdalyâh, ghed-al-yaw'; or (prolonged) גְּדַלְיָהוּ Gᵉdalyâhûw; from H1431 and H3050; Jah has become great;  Gedaljah, the name of five Israelites:—Gedaliah.
h1436.r: From גָּדַל (H1431) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: magnify, great, grow, nourish up, grow up, greater, misc

h1437.d: גִּדַּלְתִּי Giddaltîy, ghid-dal'-tee; from H1431; I have made great;  Giddalti, an Israelite:—Giddalti.
h1437.r: From גָּדַל (H1431)|English: magnify, great, grow, nourish up, grow up, greater, misc

h1438.d: גָּדַע gâdaʻ, gaw-dah'; a primitive root;  to fell a tree; generally, to destroy anything:—cut (asunder, in sunder, down, off), hew down.

h1439.d: גִּדְעוֹן Gidʻôwn, ghid-ohn'; from H1438; feller (i.e. warrior);  Gidon, an Israelite:—Gideon.
h1439.r: From גָּדַע (H1438)|English: ... down, cut off, asunder, cut in sunder

h144.d: אֲדָר ʼĂdâr, ad-awr'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H143:—Adar.

h1444.d: גֶּדֶר geder, gheh'-der; from H1443;  a circumvallation:—wall.
h1444.r: From גָּדַר (H1443)|English: make, mason, repairer, close up, fenced up, hedged, inclosed

h1446.d: גְדֹר Gᵉdôr, ghed-ore'; or (fully) גְּדוֹר Gᵉdôwr; from H1443; inclosure;  Gedor, a place in Palestine; also the name of three Israelites:—Gedor.
h1446.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h1446.r: From גָּדַר (H1443)|English: make, mason, repairer, close up, fenced up, hedged, inclosed

h1447.d: גָּדֵר gâdêr, gaw-dare'; from H1443;  a circumvallation; by implication, an inclosure:—fence, hedge, wall.
h1447.r: From גָּדַר (H1443)|English: make, mason, repairer, close up, fenced up, hedged, inclosed

h1448.d: גְּדֵרָה gᵉdêrâh, ghed-ay-raw'; feminine of H1447;  inclosure (especially for flocks):—(sheep-) cote (fold) hedge, wall.

h1450.d: גְּדֵרוֹת Gᵉdêrôwth, ghed-ay-rohth'; plural of H1448; walls;  Gederoth, a place in Palestine:—Gederoth.
h1450.r: Plural of גְּדֵרָה (H1448)|English: hedge, fold, wall, sheepfold, sheepcote

h1454.d: גֵּה gêh, gay; probably a clerical error for H2088;  this:—this.
h1454.r: Probably a clerical error for זֶה (H2088)|English: this, thus, these, such, very, hath, hence, side, same

h1456.d: גֵּהָה gêhâh, gay-haw'; from H1455;  a cure:—medicine.

h1457.d: גָּהַר gâhar, gaw-har'; a primitive root;  to prostrate oneself:—cast self down, stretch self.

h1459.d: גַּו gav, gav; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1460;  the middle:—midst, same, there-(where-) in.
h1459.r: Corresponding to גֵּו (H1460)|English: back, among, body

h146.d: אַדָּר ʼAddâr, ad-dawr'; intensive from H142; ample;  Addar, a place in Palestine; also an Israelite:—Addar.

h1460.d: גֵּו gêv, gave; from H1342 (corresponding to H1354);  the back; by analogy, the middle:—  among, back, body.
h1460.r: From גָּאָה (H1342) [corresponding to גַּב (H1354)]|English: triumph, gloriously, risen, grow up, increase

h1463.d: גּוֹג Gôwg, gohg; of uncertain derivation;  Gog, the name of an Israelite, also of some northern nation:—Gog.

h1466.d: גֵּוָה gêvâh, gay-vaw'; the same as H1465;  exaltation; (figuratively) arrogance:—lifting up, pride.

h1469.d: גּוֹזָל gôwzâl, go-zawl'; or (shortened) גֹזָל gôzâllemma גזָל missing vowel, corrected to גֹזָל; from H1497;  a nestling (as being comparatively nude of feathers):—young (pigeon).
h1469.r: From גָּזַל (H1497)|English: spoil, take away, rob, pluck, caught, consume, exercised, force, pluck off, torn, violence

h1470.d: גּוֹזָן Gôwzân, go-zawn'; probably from H1468; a quarry (as a place of cutting stones);  Gozan, a province of Assyria:—Gozan.
h1470.r: Probably from גּוּז (H1468)|English: cut off, brought

h1471.d: גּוֹי gôwy, go'-ee; rarely (shortened) גֹּי gôy; apparently from the same root as H1465 (in the sense of massing);  a foreign nation; hence, a Gentile; also (figuratively) a troop of animals, or a flight of locusts:—Gentile, heathen, nation, people.
h1471.r: Apparently from the same root as גֵּוָה (H1465)|English: body

h1472.d: גְּוִיָּה gᵉvîyâh, ghev-ee-yaw'; prolonged for H1465;  a body, whether alive or dead:—(dead) body, carcase, corpse.

h1473.d: גּוֹלָה gôwlâh, go-law'; or (shortened) גֹּלָה gôlâh; active participle feminine of H1540;  exile; concretely and collectively exiles:—(carried away), captive(-ity), removing.
h1473.r: Active participle of גָּלָה (H1540)|English: uncover, discover, captive, carry away, reveal, open, captivity, shew, remove, appear, misc

h1474.d: גּוֹלָן Gôwlân, go-lawn'; from H1473; captive;  Golan, a place east of the Jordan:—Golan.
h1474.r: From גּוֹלָה (H1473)|English: captivity, carry away, captive, removing, remove, captivity

h1476.d: גּוּנִי Gûwnîy, goo-nee'; probably from H1598; protected;  Guni, the name of two Israelites:—Guni.

h1478.d: גָּוַע gâvaʻ, gaw-vah'; a primitive root;  to breathe out, i.e. (by implication) expire:—die, be dead, give up the ghost, perish.

h1481.d: גּוּר gûwr, goor; a primitive root;  properly, to turn aside from the road (for a lodging or any other purpose), i.e. sojourn (as a guest); also to shrink, fear (as in a strange place); also to gather for hostility (as afraid):—abide, assemble, be afraid, dwell, fear, gather (together), inhabitant, remain, sojourn, stand in awe, (be) stranger, × surely.

h1482.d: גּוּר gûwr, goor; or (shortened) גֻּר gur; perhaps from H1481;  a cub (as still abiding in the lair), especially of the lion:—whelp, young one.
h1482.r: Perhaps from גּוּר (H1481)|English: sojourn, dwell, afraid, stranger, gather together, fear, abide, assemble, stand in awe, gathered, inhabitant, remain, sojourners, surely

h1484.d: גּוֹר gôwr, gore; or (feminine) גֹּרָה gôrâh; a variation of H1482:—whelp.
h1484.r: A variation of גּוּר (H1482)|English: whelp, young one

h1486.d: גּוֹרָל gôwrâl, go-rawl'; or (shortened) גֹּרָל gôrâl; from an unused root meaning to be rough (as stone);  properly, a pebble, i.e. a lot (small stones being used for that purpose); figuratively, a portion or destiny (as if determined by lot):—lot.
h1486.r: From an unused root meaning to be rough (as stone)|

h1488.d: גֵּז gêz, gaze; from H1494;  a fleece (as shorn); also mown grass:—fleece, mowing, mown grass.
h1488.r: From גָּזַז (H1494)|English: shear, sheepshearer, shearers, cut off, poll, shave, cut down

h1494.d: גָּזַז gazâz, gaw-zaz'; a primitive root (akin to H1468);  to cut off; specifically to shear a flock or shave the hair; figuratively to destroy an enemy:—cut off (down), poll, shave, (sheep-) shear(-er).
h1494.r: A primitive root [akin to גּוּז (H1468)]|English: cut off, brought

h1495.d: גָּזֵז Gâzêz, gaw-zaze'; from H1494; shearer;  Gazez, the name of two Israelites:—Gazez.
h1495.r: From גָּזַז (H1494)|English: shear, sheepshearer, shearers, cut off, poll, shave, cut down

h1496.d: גָּזִית gâzîyth, gaw-zeeth'; from H1491;  something cut, i.e. dressed stone:—hewed, hewn stone, wrought.

h1497.d: גָּזַל gâzal, gaw-zal'; a primitive root;  to pluck off; specifically to flay, strip or rob:—catch, consume, exercise (robbery), pluck (off), rob, spoil, take away (by force, violence), tear.

h1498.d: גָּזֵל gâzêl, gaw-zale'; from H1497;  robbery, or (concretely) plunder:—robbery, thing taken away by violence.
h1498.r: From גָּזַל (H1497)|English: spoil, take away, rob, pluck, caught, consume, exercised, force, pluck off, torn, violence

h150.d: אֲדַרְכֹּן ʼădarkôn, ad-ar-kone'; of Persian origin;  a daric or Persian coin:—dram.

h1500.d: גְּזֵלָה gᵉzêlâh, ghez-ay-law'; feminine of H1498 and meaning the same:—that (he had robbed) (which he took violently away), spoil, violence.
h1500.r: From גָּזֵל (H1498)|English: robbery, taken away by violence

h1501.d: גָּזָם gâzâm, gaw-zawm'; from an unused root meaning to devour;  a kind of locust:—palmer-worm.
h1501.r: From an unused root meaning to devour|

h1504.d: גָּזַר gâzar, gaw-zar'; a primitive root;  to cut down or off; (figuratively) to destroy, divide, exclude, or decide:—cut down (off), decree, divide, snatch.

h1506.d: גֶּזֶר gezer, gheh'-zer; from H1504;  something cut off; a portion:—part, piece.
h1506.r: From גָּזַר (H1504)|English: cut off, divide, decree, cut down, snatch

h1507.d: גֶּזֶר Gezer, gheh'-zer; the same as H1506;  Gezer, a place in Palestine:—Gazer, Gezer.
h1507.r: The same as גֶּזֶר (H1506)|English: piece, part

h151.d: אֲדֹרָם ʼĂdôrâm, ad-o-rawm'; contracted for H141;  Adoram (or Adoniram), an Israelite:—Adoram.
h151.r: Shortened form of אֲדֹנִירָם (H141), Adoniram|English: Adoniram

h1513.d: גֶּחֶל gechel, geh'-khel; or (feminine) גַּחֶלֶת gacheleth; from an unused root meaning to glow or kindle;  an ember:—(burning) coal.

h1516.d: גַּיְא gayʼ, gah'-ee; or (shortened) גַּי gay; probably (by transmutation) from the same root as H1466 (abbreviated);  a gorge (from its lofty sides; hence, narrow, but not a gully or winter-torrent):—valley.
h1516.r: Probably from the same root as גֵּוָה (H1466) (abbreviated)|English: pride, lifting up

h1517.d: גִּיד gîyd, gheed; probably from H1464;  a thong (as compressing); by analogy, a tendon:—sinew.
h1517.r: Probably from גּוּד (H1464)|English: overcome, invade with troops

h1518.d: גִּיחַ gîyach, ghee'-akh; or (shortened) גֹּחַ gôach; a primitive root;  to gush forth (as water), generally to issue:—break forth, labor to bring forth, come forth, draw up, take out.

h1520.d: גִּיחַ Gîyach, ghee'-akh; from H1518; a fountain;  Giach, a place in Palestine:—Giah.
h1520.r: From גִּיחַ (H1518)|English: come forth, take, bring forth, draw up

h1522.d: גֵּיחֲזִי Gêychăzîy, gay-khah-zee'; or גֵּחֲזִי Gêchăzîy; apparently from H1516 and H2372; valley of a visionary;  Gechazi, the servant of Elisha:—Gehazi.
h1522.r: Apparently from גַּיְא (H1516) and חָזָה (H2372)|English: valley

h1523.d: גִּיל gîyl, gheel; or (by permutation) גּוּל gûwl; a primitive root;  properly, to spin round (under the influence of any violent emotion), i.e. usually rejoice, or (as cringing) fear:—be glad, joy, be joyful, rejoice.

h1524.d: גִּיל gîyl, gheel; from H1523;  a revolution (of time, i.e. an age); also joy:—× exceedingly, gladness, × greatly, joy, rejoice(-ing), sort.
h1524.r: From גִּיל (H1523)|English: rejoice, glad, joyful, joy, delight

h1528.d: גִּיר gîyr, gheer; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1615;  lime:—plaster.

h1529.d: גֵּישָׁן Gêyshân, gay-shawn'; from the same as H1487; lumpish;  Geshan, an Israelite:—Geshan.
h1529.r: From the same as גּוּשׁ (H1487)|English: clod

h1530.d: גַּל gal, gal; from H1556;  something rolled, i.e. a heap of stone or dung (plural ruins), by analogy, a spring of water (plural waves):—billow, heap, spring, wave.
h1530.r: From גָּלַל (H1556)|English: roll, roll ..., seek occasion, wallow, trust, commit, remove, run down

h1533.d: גִּלְבֹּעַ Gilbôaʻ, ghil-bo'-ah; from H1530 and H1158; fountain of ebullition;  Gilboa, a mountain of Palestine:—Gilboa.
h1533.r: From גַּל (H1530) and בָּעָה (H1158)|English: heap, wave, spring, billow, of

h1534.d: גַּלְגַּל galgal, gal-gal'; by reduplication from H1556;  a wheel; by analogy, a whirlwind; also dust (as whirled):—heaven, rolling thing, wheel.
h1534.r: By reduplication from גָּלַל (H1556)|English: roll, roll ..., seek occasion, wallow, trust, commit, remove, run down

h1537.d: גִּלְגָּל Gilgâl, ghil-gawl'; the same as H1536 (with the article as a properly, noun);  Gilgal, the name of three places in Palestine:—Gilgal. See also H1019.

h1540.d: גָּלָה gâlâh, gaw-law'; a primitive root;  to denude (especially in a disgraceful sense); by implication, to exile (captives being usually stripped); figuratively, to reveal:—  advertise, appear, bewray, bring, (carry, lead, go) captive (into captivity), depart, disclose, discover, exile, be gone, open, × plainly, publish, remove, reveal, × shamelessly, shew, × surely, tell, uncover.

h1541.d: גְּלָה gᵉlâh, ghel-aw'; (Aramaic) or גְּלָא gᵉlâʼ; (Aramaic), corresponding to H1540:—bring over, carry away, reveal.
h1541.r: Corresponding to גָּלָה (H1540)|English: uncover, discover, captive, carry away, reveal, open, captivity, shew, remove, appear, misc

h1542.d: גִּלֹה Gilôh, ghee-lo'; or (fully) גִּילֹה Gîylôh; from H1540; open;  Giloh, a place in Palestine:—Giloh.
h1542.r: From גָּלָה (H1540)|English: uncover, discover, captive, carry away, reveal, open, captivity, shew, remove, appear, misc

h1543.d: גֻּלָּה gullâh, gool-law'; feminine from H1556;  a fountain, bowl or globe (all as round):—bowl, pommel, spring.
h1543.r: From גָּלַל (H1556)|English: roll, roll ..., seek occasion, wallow, trust, commit, remove, run down

h1544.d: גִּלּוּל gillûwl, ghil-lool'; or (shortened) גִּלֻּל gillul; from H1556;  properly, a log (as round); by implication, an idol:—idol.
h1544.r: From גָּלַל (H1556)|English: roll, roll ..., seek occasion, wallow, trust, commit, remove, run down

h1545.d: גְּלוֹם gᵉlôwm, ghel-ome'; from H1563;  clothing (as wrapped):—clothes.

h1546.d: גָּלוּת gâlûwth, gaw-looth'; feminine from H1540;  captivity; concretely, exiles (collectively):—(they that are carried away) captives(-ity).
h1546.r: From גָּלָה (H1540)|English: uncover, discover, captive, carry away, reveal, open, captivity, shew, remove, appear, misc

h1548.d: גָּלַח gâlach, gaw-lakh'; a primitive root;  properly, to be bald, i.e. (causatively) to shave; figuratively to lay waste:—poll, shave (off).

h1549.d: גִּלָּיוֹן gillâyôwn, ghil-law-yone'; or גִּלְיוֹן gilyôwn; from H1540;  a tablet for writing (as bare); by analogy, a mirror (as a plate):—glass, roll.
h1549.r: From גָּלָה (H1540)|English: uncover, discover, captive, carry away, reveal, open, captivity, shew, remove, appear, misc

h1551.d: גָּלִיל Gâlîyl, gaw-leel'; or (prolonged) גָּלִילָה Gâlîylâh; the same as H1550; a circle (with the article);  Galil (as a special circuit) in the North of Palestine:—Galilee.
h1551.r: The same as גָּלִיל (H1550)|English: folding, ring

h1552.d: גְלִילָה gᵉlîylâh, ghel-ee-law'; feminine of H1550;  a circuit or region:—border, coast, country.

h1554.d: גַּלִּים Gallîym, gal-leem'; plural of H1530; springs;  Gallim, a place in Palestine:—Gallim.
h1554.r: Plural of גַּל (H1530)|English: heap, wave, spring, billow, of

h1555.d: גׇּלְיַת Golyath, gol-yath'; perhaps from H1540; exile;  Goljath, a Philistine:—Goliath.
h1555.r: Perhaps from גָּלָה (H1540)|English: uncover, discover, captive, carry away, reveal, open, captivity, shew, remove, appear, misc

h1556.d: גָּלַל gâlal, gaw-lal'; a primitive root;  to roll (literally or figuratively):—commit, remove, roll (away, down, together), run down, seek occasion, trust, wallow.

h1557.d: גָּלָל gâlâl, gaw-lawl'; from H1556;  dung (as in balls):—dung.
h1557.r: From גָּלַל (H1556)|English: roll, roll ..., seek occasion, wallow, trust, commit, remove, run down

h1558.d: גָּלָל gâlâl, gaw-lawl'; from H1556;  a circumstance (as rolled around); only used adverbially, on account of:—because of, for (sake).
h1558.r: From גָּלַל (H1556)|English: roll, roll ..., seek occasion, wallow, trust, commit, remove, run down

h1561.d: גֵּלֶל gêlel, gay'-lel; a variation of H1557;  dung (plural balls of dung):—dung.

h1562.d: גִּלֲלַי Gilălay, ghe-lal-ah'-ee; from H1561; dungy;  Gilalai, an Israelite:—Gilalai.

h1567.d: גַּלְעֵד Galʻêd, gal-ade'; from H1530 and H5707; heap of testimony;  Galed, a memorial cairn East of the Jordan:—Galeed.
h1567.r: From גַּל (H1530) and עֵד (H5707)|English: heap, wave, spring, billow, of

h1568.d: גִּלְעָד Gilʻâd, ghil-awd'; probably from H1567;  Gilad, a region East of the Jordan; also the name of three Israelites:—Gilead, Gileadite.
h1568.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h157.d: אָהַב ʼâhab, aw-hab'; or אָהֵב ʼâhêb ; a primitive root;  to have affection for (sexually or otherwise):—(be-) love(-d, -ly, -r), like, friend.

h1571.d: גַּם gam, gam; by contraction from an unused root meaning to gather;  properly, assemblage; used only adverbially also, even, yea, though; often repeated as correl. both...and:—again, alike, also, (so much) as (soon), both (so)...and, but, either...or, even, for all, (in) likewise (manner), moreover, nay...neither, one, then(-refore), though, what, with, yea.
h1571.r: By contraction from an unused root|

h1576.d: גְּמוּל gᵉmûwl, ghem-ool'; from H1580;  treatment, i.e. an act (of good or ill); by implication, service or requital:—  as hast served, benefit, desert, deserving, that which he hath given, recompense, reward.
h1576.r: From גָּמַל (H1580)|English: wean, reward, dealt bountifully, do, bestowed, recompense, weaned child, do good, requite, ripening, served, yielded

h1578.d: גְּמוּלָה gᵉmûwlâh, ghem-oo-law'; feminine of H1576;  meaning the same:—deed, recompense, such a reward.
h1578.r: From גְּמוּל (H1576)|English: recompense, reward, benefit, given, serve, deserve

h1579.d: גִּמְזוֹ Gimzôw, ghim-zo'; of uncertain derivation;  Gimzo, a place in Palestine:—Gimzo.

h158.d: אַהַב ʼahab, ah'-hab; from H157;  affection (in a good or a bad sense):—love(-r).
h158.r: From אָהַב (H157)|English: love, lover(s), friend(s), beloved, liketh, lovely, loving
