h1731.r: From the same as דּוֹד (H1730)|English: beloved, uncle, love(s), father's brother, wellbeloved

h1732.d: דָּוִד Dâvid, daw-veed'; rarely (fully); דָּוִיד Dâvîyd; from the same as H1730; loving;  David, the youngest son of Jesse:—David.
h1732.r: From the same as דּוֹד (H1730)|English: beloved, uncle, love(s), father's brother, wellbeloved

h1736.d: דּוּדַי dûwday, doo-dah'-ee; from H1731;  a boiler or basket; also the mandrake (as an aphrodisiac):—basket, mandrake.
h1736.r: From דּוּד (H1731)|English: basket, pot, kettle, caldron

h1737.d: דּוֹדַי Dôwday, do-dah'ee; formed like H1736; amatory;  Dodai, an Israelite:—Dodai.

h1739.d: דָּוֶה dâveh, daw-veh'; from H1738;  sick (especially in menstruation):—faint, menstruous cloth, she that is sick, having sickness.

h174.d: אֲהָלִים ʼăhâlîym, a-haw-leem'; or (feminine) אֲהָלוֹת ʼăhâlôwth (only used thus in the plural); of foreign origin;  aloe wood (i.e. sticks):—(tree of lign-) aloes.

h1742.d: דַּוָּי davvây, dav-voy'; from H1739;  sick; figuratively, troubled:—faint.
h1742.r: From דָּוֶה (H1739)|English: faint, sick, sickness, menstruous cloth

h1743.d: דּוּךְ dûwk, dook; a primitive root;  to bruise in a mortar:—beat.

h1746.d: דּוּמָה Dûwmâh, doo-maw'; the same as H1745;  Dumah, a tribe and region of Arabia:—Dumah.
h1746.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h1747.d: דּוּמִיָּה dûwmîyâh, doo-me-yaw'; from H1820;  stillness; adverbially, silently; abstractly quiet, trust:—silence, silent, waiteth.
h1747.r: From דָּמָה (H1820)|English: cut off, cease, perish, bring to silence, liken, destroy, undone, utterly, cut down

h175.d: אַהֲרוֹן ʼAhărôwn, a-har-one'; of uncertain derivation;  Aharon, the brother of Moses:—Aaron.

h1752.d: דּוּר dûwr, dure; a primitive root;  properly, to gyrate (or move in a circle), i.e. to remain:—dwell.

h1753.d: דּוּר dûwr, dure; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1752;  to reside:—dwell.

h1754.d: דּוּר dûwr, dure; from H1752;  a circle, ball or pile:—ball, turn, round about.

h1755.d: דּוֹר dôwr, dore; or (shortened) דֹּר dôr; from H1752;  properly, a revolution of time, i.e. an age or generation; also a dwelling:—age, × evermore, generation, (n-) ever, posterity.

h1756.d: דּוֹר Dôwr, dore; or (by permutation) דֹּאר Dôʼr; (Joshua 17:11; 1 Kings 4:11), from H1755; dwelling;  Dor, a place in Palestine:—Dor.
h1756.r: From דּוֹר (H1755)|English: generation, all, many, misc

h1758.d: דּוּשׁ dûwsh, doosh; or דּוֹשׁ dôwsh; or דִּישׁ dîysh; a primitive root;  to trample or thresh:—break, tear, thresh, tread out (down), at grass (Jeremiah 50:11, by mistake for H1877).

h176.d: אוֹ ʼôw, o; presumed to be the 'constructive' or genitival form of אַו ʼav ; short for H185;  desire (and so probably in Proverbs 31:4); hence (by way of alternative) or, also if:—also, and, either, if, at the least, × nor, or, otherwise, then, whether.
h176.r: Short for אַוָּה (H185)|English: desire, lust after, pleasure

h1760.d: דָּחָה dâchâh, daw-khaw'; or דָּחַח dâchach; (Jeremiah 23:12), a primitive root;  to push down:—chase, drive away (on), overthrow, outcast, × sore, thrust, totter.

h1763.d: דְּחַל dᵉchal, deh-khal'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2119;  to slink, i.e. (by implication) to fear, or (causatively) be formidable:—make afraid, dreadful, fear, terrible.
h1763.r: Corresponding to זָחַל (H2119)|English: afraid, serpents, worms

h1764.d: דֹּחַן dôchan, do'-khan; of uncertain derivation;  millet:—millet.

h1765.d: דָּחַף dâchaph, daw-khaf'; a primitive root;  to urge, i.e. hasten:—(be) haste(-ned), pressed on.

h1767.d: דַּי day, dahee; of uncertain derivation;  enough (as noun or adverb), used chiefly with preposition in phrases:—able, according to, after (ability), among, as (oft as), (more than) enough, from, in, since, (much as is) sufficient(-ly), too much, very, when.

h1768.d: דִּי dîy, dee; (Aramaic) apparently for H1668;  that, used as relative conjunction, and especially (with a preposition) in adverbial phrases; also as preposition of:—× as, but, for(-asmuch  ),   now, of, seeing, than, that, therefore, until,   what (-soever), when, which, whom, whose.
h1768.r: Apparently from דָּא (H1668)|English: this, one, another

h1769.d: דִּיבוֹן Dîybôwn, dee-bome'; or (shortened) דִּיבֹן Dîybôn; from H1727; pining:— Dibon, the name of three places in Palestine:—Dibon. (Also, with H1410 added, Dibon-gad.)

h177.d: אוּאֵל ʼÛwʼêl, oo-ale'; from H176 and H410; wish of God;  Uel, and Israelite:—Uel.
h177.r: From אַו (H176) and אֵל (H410)|English: also, and, desire, either, least, nor, or, otherwise, should, then, whether

h1771.d: דַּיָּג dayâg, dah-yawg'; from H1770;  a fisherman:—fisher.

h1777.d: דִּין dîyn, deen; or (Genesis 6:3) דּוּן dûwn; a primitive root;  to rule; by implication to judge (as umpire); also to strive (as at law):—contend contend execute (judgment) judge minister judgment plead (the cause) at strife strive.
h1777.r: A primitive root [comp. אָדוֹן (H113)]|English: lord, master(s), Lord, owner, sir

h1779.d: דִּין dîyn, deen; or (Job 19:29) דּוּן dûwn; from H1777;  judgement (the suit, justice, sentence or tribunal); by implication also strife:—cause, judgement, plea, strife.
h1779.r: From דִּין (H1777)|English: judge, plead the cause, contend, execute, plead, strife

h178.d: אוֹב ʼôwb, obe; from the same as H1 (apparently through the idea of prattling a father's name);  properly, a mumble, i.e. a water-skin (from its hollow sound); hence a necromancer (ventriloquist, as from a jar):—bottle, familiar spirit.
h178.r: From the same as אָב (H1) (apparently through the idea of prattling a father's name)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h1780.d: דִּין dîyn, deen; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1779:—judgement.
h1780.r: Corresponding to דִּין (H1779)|English: judgment, cause, plea, strife

h1783.d: דִּינָה Dîynâh, dee-naw'; feminine of H1779; justice;  Dinah, the daughter of Jacob:—Dinah.
h1783.r: From דִּין (H1779)|English: judgment, cause, plea, strife

h1787.d: דִּישׁוֹן Dîyshôwn, dee-shone'; Diyshon, the same as H1788;  Dishon, the name of two Edomites:—Dishon.

h1789.d: דִּישָׁן Dîyshân, dee-shawn'; another form of H1787  Dishan, an Edomite:—Dishan, Dishon.

h179.d: אוֹבִיל ʼôwbîyl, o-beel'; probably from H56; mournful;  Obil, an Ishmaelite:—Obil.

h1791.d: דֵּךְ dêk, dake; (Aramaic) or דָּךְ dâk; (Aramaic), prolonged from H1668;  this:—the same, this.
h1791.r: Prolonged from דָּא (H1668)|English: this, one, another

h1792.d: דָּכָא dâkâʼ, daw-kaw'; a primitive root (compare H1794);  to crumble; transitively, to bruise (literally or figuratively):—beat to pieces, break (in pieces), bruise, contrite, crush, destroy, humble, oppress, smite.
h1792.r: A primitive root (compare דָּכָה (H1794))|English: break, contrite, crouch

h1794.d: דָּכָה dâkâh, daw-kaw'; a primitive root (compare H1790, H1792);  to collapse (phys. or mentally):—break (sore), contrite, crouch.
h1794.r: A primitive root (compare דַּךְ (H1790), דָּכָא (H1792))|English: oppressed, afflicted

h1797.d: דִּכֵּן dikkên, dik-kane'; (Aramaic) prolonged from H1791;  this:—same, that, this.

h1798.d: דְּכַר dᵉkar, dek-ar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2145;  properly, a male, i.e. of sheep:—ram.
h1798.r: Corresponding to זָכָר (H2145)|English: male, man, child, mankind, him

h18.d: אֵבוּס ʼêbûwç, ay-booce'; from H75;  a manger or stall:—crib.

h1800.d: דַּל dal, dal; from H1809;  properly, dangling, i.e. (by implication) weak or thin:—lean, needy, poor (man), weaker.
h1800.r: From דָּלַל (H1809)|English: brought low, dried up, not equal, emptied, fail, impoverished, made thin

h1801.d: דָּלַג dâlag, daw-lag'; a primitive root;  to spring:—leap.

h1802.d: דָּלָה dâlâh, daw-law'; a primitive root (compare H1809);  properly, to dangle, i.e. to let down a bucket (for drawing out water); figuratively, to deliver:—draw (out), × enough, lift up.
h1802.r: A primitive root (compare דָּלַל (H1809))|English: brought low, dried up, not equal, emptied, fail, impoverished, made thin

h1803.d: דַּלָּה dallâh, dal-law'; from H1802;  properly, something dangling, i.e. a loose thread or hair; figuratively, indigent:—hair, pining sickness, poor(-est sort).
h1803.r: From דָּלָה (H1802)|English: draw, enough, lifted me

h1804.d: דָּלַח dâlach, daw-lakh'; a primitive root;  to roil water:—trouble.

h1806.d: דְּלָיָה Dᵉlâyâh, del-aw-yaw'; or (prolonged) דְּלָיָהוּ Dᵉlâyâhûwxlit Dᵉlâyâhhûw corrected to Dᵉlâyâhûw; from H1802 and H3050; Jah has delivered;  Delajah, the name of five Israelites:—Dalaiah, Delaiah.
h1806.r: From דָּלָה (H1802) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: draw, enough, lifted me

h1807.d: דְּלִילָה Dᵉlîylâh, del-ee-law'; from H1809; languishing  Delilah, a Philistine woman:—Delilah.
h1807.r: From דָּלַל (H1809)|English: brought low, dried up, not equal, emptied, fail, impoverished, made thin

h1809.d: דָּלַל dâlal, daw-lal'; a primitive root (compare H1802);  to slacken or be feeble; figuratively, to be oppressed:—bring low, dry up, be emptied, be not equal, fail, be impoverished, be made thin.
h1809.r: A primitive root (compare דָּלָה (H1802))|English: draw, enough, lifted me

h181.d: אוּד ʼûwd, ood; from an unused root meaning to rake together;  a poker (for turning or gathering embers):—(fire-) brand.
h181.r: From an unused root meaning to rake together|

h1811.d: דָּלַף dâlaph, daw-laf'; a primitive root;  to drip; by implication, to weep:—drop through, melt, pour out.

h1812.d: דֶּלֶף deleph, deh'-lef; from H1811;  a dripping:—dropping.
h1812.r: From דָּלַף (H1811)|English: pour out, melt, drop through

h1813.d: דַּלְפוֹן Dalphôwn, dal-fone'; from H1811; dripping;  Dalphon, a son of Haman:—Dalphon.
h1813.r: From דָּלַף (H1811)|English: pour out, melt, drop through

h1814.d: דָּלַק dâlaq, daw-lak'; a primitive root;  to flame (literally or figuratively):—burning, chase, inflame, kindle, persecute(-or), pursue hotly.

h1817.d: דֶּלֶת deleth, deh'-leth; from H1802;  something swinging, i.e. the valve of a door:—door (two-leaved), gate, leaf, lid. (Psalm 141:3).
h1817.r: From דָּלָה (H1802)|English: draw, enough, lifted me

h1818.d: דָּם dâm, dawm; from H1826 (compare H119);  blood (as that which when shed causes death) of man or an animal; by analogy, the juice of the grape; figuratively (especially in the plural) bloodshed (i.e. drops of blood):—blood(-y, -guiltiness), (-thirsty), + innocent.
h1818.r: From דָּמָם (H1826) (compare אָדַם (H119))|English: silence, still, silent, cut off, cut down, rest, cease, forbear, peace, quieted, tarry, wait

h1819.d: דָּמָה dâmâh, daw-maw'; a primitive root;  to compare; by implication, to resemble, liken, consider:—compare, devise, (be) like(-n), mean, think, use similitudes.

h182.d: אוֹדוֹת ʼôwdôwth, o-doth'; or (shortened) אֹדוֹת ʼôdôwth (only thus in the plural); from the same as H181;  turnings (i.e. occasions); (adverb) on account of:—(be-) cause, concerning, sake.
h182.r: From the same as אוּד (H181)|English: firebrand(s), brand

h1820.d: דָּמָה dâmâh, daw-mam'; a primitive root;  to be dumb or silent; hence, to fail or perish; trans. to destroy:—cease, be cut down (off), destroy, be brought to silence, be undone, × utterly.

h1821.d: דְּמָה dᵉmâh, dem-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1819;  to resemble:—be like.
h1821.r: Corresponding to דָּמָה (H1819)|English: like, liken, thought, compared, devised, meaneth, similitudes

h1823.d: דְּמוּת dᵉmûwth, dem-ooth'; from H1819;  resemblance; concretely, model, shape; adverbially, like:—fashion, like (-ness, as), manner, similitude.
h1823.r: From דָּמָה (H1819)|English: like, liken, thought, compared, devised, meaneth, similitudes

h1824.d: דְּמִי dᵉmîy, dem-ee'; or דֳּמִי dŏmîy; from H1820;  quiet:—cutting off, rest, silence.
h1824.r: From דָּמָה (H1820)|English: cut off, cease, perish, bring to silence, liken, destroy, undone, utterly, cut down

h1826.d: דָּמַם dâmam, daw-man'; a primitive root (compare H1724, H1820);  to be dumb; by implication, to be astonished, to stop; also to perish:—cease, be cut down (off), forbear, hold peace, quiet self, rest, be silent, keep (put to) silence, be (stand) still, tarry, wait.
h1826.r: A prim root [compare דָּהַם (H1724), דָּמָה (H1820)]|English: astonied

h1829.d: דִּמְנָה Dimnâh, dim-naw'; feminine from the same as H1828; a dung-heap;  Dimnah, a place in Palestine:—Dimnah.
h1829.r: Feminine from the same as דֹּמֶן (H1828)|English: dung

h183.d: אָוָה ʼâvâh, aw-vaw'; a primitive root;  to wish for:—covet, (greatly) desire, be desirous, long, lust (after).

h1830.d: דָּמַע dâmaʻ, daw-mah'; a primitive root;  to weep:—× sore, weep.

h1832.d: דִּמְעָה dimʻâh, dim-aw'; feminine of H1831;  weeping:—tears.

h1834.d: דַּמֶּשֶׂק Dammeseq, dam-meh'-sek; or דּוּמֶשֶׂק Dûwmeseq; or דַּרְמֶשֶׂק Darmeseq; of foreign origin;  Damascus, a city of Syria:—Damascus.

h1835.d: דָּן Dân, dawn; from H1777; judge;  Dan, one of the sons of Jacob; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory; likewise a place in Palestine colonized by them:—Daniel
h1835.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h1835.r: From דִּין (H1777)|English: judge, plead the cause, contend, execute, plead, strife

h1836.d: דֵּן dên, dane; (Aramaic) an orthographical variation of H1791;  this:—(afore-) time,   after this manner, here (-after), one...another, such, there(-fore), these, this (matter),   thus, where(-fore), which.
h1836.r: An orthographical variation of דֵּךְ (H1791)|English: this, same

h1840.d: דָנִיֵּאל Dânîyêʼl, daw-nee-yale'; in Ezekiel it is; דָּנִאֵל Dâniʼêl; from H1835 and H410; judge of God;  Daniel or Danijel, the name of two Israelites:—Daniel.
h1840.r: From דָּן (H1835) and אֵל (H410)|English: Dan, variant

h1841.d: דָּנִיֵּאל Dânîyêʼl, daw-nee-yale'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1840;  Danijel, the Hebrew prophet:—Daniel.

h1844.d: דֵּעָה dêʻâh, day-aw'; feminine of H1843;  knowledge:—knowledge.

h1847.d: דַּעַת daʻath, dah'-ath; from H3045;  knowledge:—cunning, (ig-) norantly, know(-ledge), (un-) awares (wittingly).
h1847.r: From יָדַע (H3045)|English: know, known, knowledge, perceive, shew, tell, wist, understand, certainly, acknowledge, acquaintance, consider, declare, teach, misc

h1849.d: דָּפַק dâphaq, daw-fak'; a primitive root;  to knock; by analogy, to press severely:—beat, knock, overdrive.

h1851.d: דַּק daq, dak; from H1854;  crushed, i.e. (by implication) small or thin:—dwarf, lean(-fleshed), very little thing, small, thin.
h1851.r: From דָּקַק (H1854)|English: beat small, powder, stamp, stamp small, bruise, small, made dust, beat in pieces

h1853.d: דִּקְלָה Diqlâh, dik-law'; of foreign origin;  Diklah, a region of Arabia:—Diklah.
h1853.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h1854.d: דָּקַק dâqaq, daw-kak'; a primitive root (compare H1915);  to crush (or intransitively) crumble:—beat in pieces (small), bruise, make dust, (into) × powder, (be, very) small, stamp (small).
h1854.r: A primitive root [compare הָדַךְ (H1915)]|English: tread down

h1855.d: דְּקַק dᵉqaq, dek-ak'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1854;  to crumble or (trans.) crush:—break to pieces.
h1855.r: Corresponding to דָּקַק (H1854)|English: beat small, powder, stamp, stamp small, bruise, small, made dust, beat in pieces

h1856.d: דָּקַר dâqar, daw-kar'; a primitive root;  to stab; by analogy, to starve; figuratively, to revile:—pierce, strike (thrust) through, wound.

h1858.d: דַּר dar, dar; apparently from the same as H1865;  properly, a pearl (from its sheen as rapidly turned); by analogy, pearl-stone, i.e. mother-of-pearl or alabaster:—× white.
h1858.r: Apparently from the same as דְּרוֹר (H1865)|English: liberty, pure

h1859.d: דָּר dâr, dawr; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1755;  an age:—generation.
h1859.r: Corresponding to דּוֹר (H1755)|English: generation, all, many, misc

h1860.d: דְּרָאוֹן dᵉrâʼôwn, der-aw-one'; or דֵּרָאוֹן dêrâʼôwn; from an unused root (meaning to repulse);  an object of aversion:—abhorring, contempt.
h1860.r: From an unused root (meaning to repulse)|

h1865.d: דְּרוֹר dᵉrôwr, der-ore'; from an unused root (meaning to move rapidly);  freedom; hence, spontaneity of outflow, and so clear:—liberty, pure.
h1865.r: From an unused root (meaning to move rapidly)|

h1867.d: דָּֽרְיָוֵשׁ Dârᵉyâvêsh, daw-reh-yaw-vaysh'; of Persian origin;  Darejavesh, a title (rather than name) of several Persian kings:—Darius.

h1868.d: דָּֽרְיָוֵשׁ Dârᵉyâvêsh, daw-reh-yaw-vaysh'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1867:—Darius.

h1869.d: דָּרַךְ dârak, daw-rak'; a primitive root;  to tread; by implication, to walk; also to string a bow (by treading on it in bending):—archer, bend, come, draw, go (over), guide, lead (forth), thresh, tread (down), walk.

h187.d: אוּזָל ʼÛwzâl, oo-zawl'; of uncertain derivation;  Uzal, a son of Joktan:—Uzal.

h1870.d: דֶּרֶךְ derek, deh'-rek; from H1869;  a road (as trodden); figuratively, a course of life or mode of action, often adverb:—along, away, because of,   by, conversation, custom, (east-) ward, journey, manner, passenger, through, toward, (high-) (path-) way(-side), whither(-soever).
h1870.r: From דָּרַךְ (H1869)|English: tread, bend, bent, lead, archer, tread down, come, go, treader, tread upon, walk, drew, lead forth, guide, tread out, go over, shoot, thresh

h1875.d: דָּרַשׁ dârash, daw-rash'; a primitive root;  properly, to tread or frequent; usually to follow (for pursuit or search); by implication, to seek or ask; specifically to worship:—ask, × at all, care for, × diligently, inquire, make inquisition, (necro-) mancer, question, require, search, seek (for, out), × surely.

h1876.d: דָּשָׁא dâshâʼ, daw-shaw'; a primitive root;  to sprout:—bring forth, spring.

h1877.d: דֶּשֶׁא desheʼ, deh'-sheh; from H1876;  a sprout; by analogy, grass:—(tender) grass, green, (tender) herb.

h1878.d: דָּשֵׁן dâshên, daw-shane'; a primitive root; also denominatively (from H1880)  to be fat; transitively, to fatten (or regard as fat); specifically to anoint; figuratively, to satisfy; to remove (fat) ashes (of sacrifices):—accept, anoint, take away the (receive) ashes (from), make (wax) fat.

h188.d: אוֹי ʼôwy, o'-ee; probably from H183 (in the sense of crying out after);  lamentation; also interjectionally Oh!:—alas, woe.
h188.r: Probably from אָוָה (H183) (in the sense of crying out after)|English: desire, lust, longed, covet

h1881.d: דָּת dâth, dawth; of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation;  a royal edict or statute:—commandment, commission, decree, law, manner.

h1882.d: דָּת dâth, dawth; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1881;:—decree, law.
h1882.r: Corresponding to דָּת (H1881)|English: law, decree, commandment, manner, commission

h1883.d: דֶּתֶא detheʼ, deh'-thay; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1877:—tender grass.
h1883.r: Corresponding to דֶּשֶׁא (H1877)|English: grass, herb, green

h1885.d: דָּתָן Dâthân, daw-thawn'; of uncertain derivation;  Dathan, an Israelite:—Dathan.

h1887.d: הֵא hêʼ, hay; a primitive particle;  lo!:—behold, lo.

h1889.d: הֶאָח heʼâch, heh-awkh'; from H1887 and H253;  aha!:—ah, aha, ha.
h1889.r: From הֵא (H1887) and אָח (H253)|English: lo, behold

h189.d: אֱוִי ʼĔvîy, ev-ee'; probably from H183; desirous;  Evi, a Midianitish chief:—Evi.
h189.r: Probably from אָוָה (H183)|English: desire, lust, longed, covet

h1891.d: הָבַל hâbal, haw-bal'; a primitive root;  to be vain in act, word, or expectation; specifically to lead astray:—be (become, make) vain.

h1892.d: הֶבֶל hebel, heh'bel; or (rarely in the abs.) הֲבֵל hăbêl; from H1891;  emptiness or vanity; figuratively, something transitory and unsatisfactory; often used as an adverb:—× altogether, vain, vanity.
h1892.r: From הָבַל (H1891)|English: become vain, make vain

h1893.d: הֶבֶל Hebel, heh'-bel; the same as H1892;  Hebel, the son of Adam:—Abel.
h1893.r: The same as הֶבֶל (H1892)|English: vanity, vain, altogether

h1896.d: הֵגֵא Hêgêʼ, hay-gay'; or (by permutation) הֵגַי Hêgay; probably of Persian origin;  Hege or Hegai, a eunuch of Xerxes:—Hegai, Hege.

h1897.d: הָגָה hâgâh, haw-gaw'; a primitive root (compare H1901);  to murmur (in pleasure or anger); by implication, to ponder:—imagine, meditate, mourn, mutter, roar, × sore, speak, study, talk, utter.
h1897.r: A primitive root [compare הָגִיג (H1901)]|English: meditation, musing

h1898.d: הָגָה hâgâh, haw-gaw'; a primitive root;  to remove:—stay, stay away.

h1899.d: הֶגֶה hegeh, heh'-geh; from H1897;  a muttering (in sighing, thought, or as thunder):—mourning, sound, tale.
h1899.r: From הָגָה (H1897)|English: meditate, mourn, speak, imagine, study, mutter, utter, roaring, sore, talk

h190.d: אוֹיָה ʼôwyâh, o-yaw'; feminine of H188:—woe.

h1902.d: הִגָּיוֹן higgâyôwn, hig-gaw-yone'; intensive from H1897;  a murmuring sound, i.e. a musical notation (probably similar to the modern affettuoso to indicate solemnity of movement); by implication, a machination:—device, Higgaion, meditation, solemn sound.
h1902.r: Intensive from הָגָה (H1897)|English: meditate, mourn, speak, imagine, study, mutter, utter, roaring, sore, talk

h1904.d: הָגָר Hâgâr, haw-gawr'; of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation;  Hagar, the mother of Ishmael:—Hagar.

h1906.d: הֵד hêd, hade; for H1959;  a shout:—sounding again.

h1907.d: הַדָּבָר haddâbâr, had-daw-bawr'; (Aramaic) probably of foreign origin;  a vizier:—counsellor.

h1908.d: הֲדַד Hădad, had-ad'; probably of foreign origin (compare H111);  Hadad, the name of an idol, and of several kings of Edom:—Hadad.
h1908.r: Probably of foreign origin [compare אֲדַד (H111)]|English: Hadad

h1909.d: הֲדַדְעֶזֶר Hădadʻezer, had-ad-eh'-zer; from H1908 and H5828; Hadad (is his) help;  Hadadezer, a Syrian king:—Hadadezer. Compare H1928.

h191.d: אֱוִיל ʼĕvîyl, ev-eel'; from an unused root (meaning to be perverse);  (figuratively) silly:—fool(-ish) (man).
h191.r: From an unused root (meaning to be perverse)|

h1913.d: הֲדוֹרָם Hădôwrâm, had-o-rawm'; or הֲדֹרָם Hădôrâm; probably of foreign derivation;  Hadoram, a son of Joktan, and the tribe descended from him:—Hadoram.

h1914.d: הִדַּי Hidday, hid-dah'ee; of uncertain derivation;  Hiddai, an Israelite:—Hiddai.

h1915.d: הָדַךְ hâdak, haw-dak'; a primitive root (compare H1854);  to crush with the foot:—tread down.
h1915.r: A primitive root [compare דָּקַק (H1854)]|English: beat small, powder, stamp, stamp small, bruise, small, made dust, beat in pieces

h1918.d: הֲדַס hădaç, had-as'; of uncertain derivation;  the myrtle:—myrtle (tree).

h1919.d: הֲדַסָּה Hădaççâh, had-as-saw'; feminine of H1918;  Hadassah (or Esther):—Hadassah.
h1919.r: From of הֲדַס (H1918)|English: myrtle tree, myrtle

h1921.d: הָדַר hâdar, haw-dar'; a primitive root;  to swell up (literally or figuratively, active or passive); by implication, to favor or honour, be high or proud:—countenance, crooked place, glorious, honour, put forth.

h1926.d: הָדָר hâdâr, haw-dawr'; from H1921;  magnificence, i.e. ornament or splendor:—beauty, comeliness, excellency, glorious, glory, goodly, honour, majesty.
h1926.r: From הָדַר (H1921)|English: honour, countenance, crooked places, glorious, put forth

h1927.d: הֲדָרָה hădârâh, had-aw-raw'; feminine of H1926;  decoration:—beauty, honour.
h1927.r: From הָדָר (H1926)|English: glory, majesty, honour, beauty, comeliness, excellency, glorious, goodly

h1929.d: הָהּ hâhh, haw; a shortened form of H162;  ah! expressing grief:—woe worth.
h1929.r: A shortened form of אֲהָהּ (H162)|English: Ah, Alas, O

h193.d: אוּל ʼûwl, ool; from an unused root meaning to twist, i.e. (by implication) be strong;  the body (as being rolled together); also powerful:—mighty, strength.
h193.r: From an unused root meaning to twist, i.e. (by implication) be strong|

h1930.d: הוֹ hôw, ho; by permutation from H1929;  oh!:—alas.
h1930.r: By permutation from הָהּ (H1929)|English: Woe worth

h1931.d: הוּא hûwʼ, hoo; of which the feminine (beyond the Pentateuch) is הִיא hîyʼ; he a primitive word, the third person pronoun singular;  he (she or it); only expressed when emphatic or without a verb; also (intensively) self, or (especially with the article) the same; sometimes (as demonstrative) this or that; occasionally (instead of copula) as or are:—he, as for her, him(-self), it, the same, she (herself), such, that (...it), these, they, this, those, which (is), who.
h1931.s: demonstrative pronoun, third person singular personal pronoun

h1932.d: הוּא hûwʼ, hoo; (Aramaic) or (feminine) הִיא hîyʼ; (Aramaic), corresponding to H1931:—× are, it, this.
h1932.r: Corresponding to הוּא (H1931)|English: that, him, same, this, he, which, who, such, wherein

h1933.d: הָוָא hâvâʼ, haw-vaw'; or הָוָה hâvâh; a primitive root (compare H183, H1961) supposed to mean properly, to breathe;  to be (in the sense of existence):—be, × have.
h1933.r: A primitive root [compare אָוָה (H183), הָיָה (H1961)]|English: desire, lust, longed, covet

h1934.d: הָוָא hâvâʼ, hav-aw'; (Aramaic) or הָוָה hâvâh; (Aramaic), corresponding to H1933;  to exist; used in a great variety of applications (especially in connection with other words):—be, become,   behold,   came (to pass),   cease,   cleave,   consider,   do,   give,   have,   judge,   keep,   labour,   mingle (self),   put,   see,   seek,   set,   slay,   take heed, tremble,   walk,   would.
h1934.r: Corresponding to הָוָה (H1933)|English: be thou, be, shall be, may be, hath

h1935.d: הוֹד hôwd, hode; from an unused root;  grandeur (i.e. an imposing form and appearance):—beauty, comeliness, excellency, glorious, glory, goodly, honour, majesty.

h1936.d: הוֹד Hôwd, hode; the same as H1935;  Hod, an Israelite:—Hod.
h1936.r: The same as הוֹד (H1935)|English: glory, honour, majesty, beauty, comeliness, glorious, goodly, honourable

h1938.d: הוֹדַוְיָה Hôwdavyâh, ho-dav-yaw'; from H1935 and H3050; majesty of Jah;  Hodavjah, the name of three Israelites:—Hodaviah.
h1938.r: From הוֹד (H1935) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: glory, honour, majesty, beauty, comeliness, glorious, goodly, honourable

h194.d: אוּלַי ʼûwlay, oo-lah'ee; or (shortened) אֻלַי ʼulay; from H176;  if not; hence perhaps:—if so be, may be, peradventure, unless.
h194.r: From אַו (H176)|English: also, and, desire, either, least, nor, or, otherwise, should, then, whether

h1940.d: הוֹדִיָּה Hôwdîyâh, ho-dee-yaw'; a form for the feminine of H3064;  a Jewess:—Hodiah.
h1940.r: A form for the fem. of יְהוּדִי (H3064)|English: Jew, Jew, Judah

h1941.d: הוֹדִיָּה Hôwdîyâh, ho-dee-yaw'; a form of H1938;  Hodijah, the name of three Israelites:—Hodijah.

h1942.d: הַוָּה havvâh, hav-vaw'; from H1933 (in the sense of eagerly coveting and rushing upon;  by implication, of falling); desire; also ruin:—calamity, iniquity, mischief, mischievous (thing), naughtiness, naughty, noisome, perverse thing, substance, very wickedness.
h1942.r: From הָוָה (H1933)|English: be thou, be, shall be, may be, hath

h1943.d: הֹוָה hôvâh, ho-vaw'; another form for H1942;  ruin:—mischief.
h1943.r: Another form for הַוָּה (H1942)|English: calamity, wickedness, perverse thing, mischief, noisome, iniquity, substance, naughtiness, naughty, mischievous

h1945.d: הוֹי hôwy, hoh'ee; a prolonged form of H1930 (akin to H188);  oh!:—ah, alas, ho, O, woe.
h1945.r: A prolonged form of הוֹ (H1930) [akin to אוֹי (H188)]|English: Alas

h1946.d: הוּךְ hûwk, hook; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1981;  to go; causatively, to bring:—bring again, come, go (up).

h1947.d: הוֹלֵלָה hôwlêlâh, ho-lay-law'; feminine active participle of H1984;  folly:—madness.
h1947.r: Act. participle of הָלַל (H1984)|English: praise, glory, boast, mad, shine, foolish, fools, commended, rage, celebrate, give, marriage, renowned

h1948.d: הוֹלֵלוּת hôwlêlûwth, ho-lay-looth'; from active participle of H1984;  folly:—madness.
h1948.r: From act. participle of הָלַל (H1984)|English: praise, glory, boast, mad, shine, foolish, fools, commended, rage, celebrate, give, marriage, renowned

h1949.d: הוּם hûwm, hoom; a primitive root (compare H2000);  to make an uproar, or agitate greatly:—destroy, move, make a noise, put, ring again.
h1949.r: A primitive root [compare הָמַם (H2000)]|English: discomfit, destroy, vex, crush, break, consume trouble

h1952.d: הוֹן hôwn, hone; from the same as H1951 in the sense of H202;  wealth; by implication, enough:—enough,   for nought, riches, substance, wealth.
h1952.r: From the same as הוּן (H1951) in the sense of אוֹן (H202)|English: ready

h1953.d: הוֹשָׁמָע Hôwshâmâʻ, ho-shaw-maw'; from H3068 and H8085; Jehovah has heard;  Hoshama, an Israelite:—Hoshama.
h1953.r: From יְהֹוָה (H3068) and שָׁמַע (H8085)|English: LORD, GOD, JEHOVAH, variant

h1954.d: הוֹשֵׁעַ Hôwshêaʻ, ho-shay'-ah; from H3467; deliverer;  Hoshea, the name of five Israelites:—Hosea, Hoshea, Oshea.
h1954.r: From יָשַׁע (H3467)|English: save, saviour, deliver, help, preserved, salvation, avenging, at all, avenged, defend, rescue, safe, victory

h1955.d: הוֹשַׁעְיָה Hôwshaʻyâh, ho-shah-yaw'; from H3467 and H3050; Jah has saved;  Hoshajah, the name of two Israelites:—Hoshaiah.
h1955.r: From יָשַׁע (H3467) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: save, saviour, deliver, help, preserved, salvation, avenging, at all, avenged, defend, rescue, safe, victory

h1956.d: הוֹתִיר Hôwthîyr, ho-theer'; from H3498; he has caused to remain;  Hothir, an Israelite:—Hothir.
h1956.r: From יָתַר (H3498)|English: leave, remain, rest, remainder, remnant, reserved, residue, plenteous, behind, excel, much, preserve

h1958.d: הִי hîy, he; for H5092;  lamentation:—woe. (For hiyr, see H1931, H1932.)

h1961.d: הָיָה hâyâh, haw-yaw; a primitive root (compare H1933);  to exist, i.e. be or become, come to pass (always emphatic, and not a mere copula or auxiliary):—beacon, × altogether, be(-come), accomplished, committed, like), break, cause, come (to pass), do, faint, fall,   follow, happen, × have, last, pertain, quit (one-) self, require, × use.
h1961.r: A primitive root [compare הָוָה (H1933)]|English: be thou, be, shall be, may be, hath

h1963.d: הֵיךְ hêyk, hake; another form for H349;  how?:—how.
h1963.r: Another form for אֵיךְ (H349)|English: how, what, where

h1964.d: הֵיכָל hêykâl, hay-kawl'; probably from H3201 (in the sense of capacity);  a large public building, such as a palace or temple:—palace, temple.
h1964.r: Probably from יָכֹל (H3201) (in the sense of capacity)|English: could, able, cannot, prevail, may, can, canst, endure, might, misc

h1965.d: הֵיכַל hêykal, hay-kal'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1964:—palace, temple.

h1968.d: הֵימָן Hêymân, hay-mawn'; probably from H539; faithful;  Heman, the name of at least two Israelites:—Heman.
h1968.r: Probably from אָמַן (H539)|English: believe, assurance, faithful, sure, established, trust, verified, stedfast, continuance, father, bring up, nurse, be nursed, surely be, stand fast, fail, trusty

h1969.d: הִין hîyn, heen; probably of Egyptian origin;  a hin or liquid measure:—hin.

h197.d: אוּלָם ʼûwlâm, oo-lawm'; or (shortened), אֻלָם ʼulâm ; from H481 (in the sense of tying);  a vestibule (as bound to the building):—porch.
h197.r: From אָלַם (H481) (in the sense of tying)|English: dumb, put to silence, binding

h1973.d: הָלְאָה hâlᵉʼâh, haw-leh-aw'; from the primitive form of the article (hal);  to the distance, i.e. far away; also (of time) thus far:—back, beyond, (hence,-) forward, hitherto, thence, forth, yonder.
h1973.r: From the primitive form of the article [hal]|

h1975.d: הַלָּז hallâz, hal-lawz'; from H1976;  this or that:—side, that, this.

h1976.d: הַלָּזֶה hallâzeh, hal-law-zeh'; from the article (see H1973) and H2088;  this very:—this.
h1976.r: From the article [see הָֽלְאָה (H1973)] and זֶה (H2088)|English: beyond, forward, hitherto, back thenceforth, henceforth, yonder

h1977.d: הַלֵּזוּ hallêzûw, hal-lay-zoo'; another form of H1976;  that:—this.

h1980.d: הָלַךְ hâlak, haw-lak'; akin to H3212; a primitive root;  to walk (in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively):—(all) along, apace, behave (self), come, (on) continually, be conversant, depart,   be eased, enter, exercise (self),   follow, forth, forward, get, go (about, abroad, along, away, forward, on, out, up and down),   greater, grow, be wont to haunt, lead, march, × more and more, move (self), needs, on, pass (away), be at the point, quite, run (along),   send, speedily, spread, still, surely,   tale-bearer,   travel(-ler), walk (abroad, on, to and fro, up and down, to places), wander, wax, (way-) faring man, × be weak, whirl.
h1980.r: Akin to יָלַךְ (H3212), a primitive root|English: go, walk, come, depart, ...away, follow, get, lead, brought, carry, bring, misc

h1981.d: הֲלַךְ hălak, hal-ak'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H1980 (compare H1946);  to walk:—walk.
h1981.r: Corresponding to הָלַךְ (H1980) [compare הוּךְ (H1946)]|English: go, walk, come, ...away, ...along, misc

h1984.d: הָלַל hâlal, haw-lal'; a primitive root;  to be clear (orig. of sound, but usually of color); to shine; hence, to make a show, to boast; and thus to be (clamorously) foolish; to rave; causatively, to celebrate; also to stultify:—(make) boast (self), celebrate, commend, (deal, make), fool(-ish, -ly), glory, give (light), be (make, feign self) mad (against), give in marriage, (sing, be worthy of) praise, rage, renowned, shine.

h1986.d: הָלַם hâlam, haw-lam'; a primitive root;  to strike down; by implication, to hammer, stamp, conquer, disband:—beat (down), break (down), overcome, smite (with the hammer).

h1987.d: הֶלֶם Helem, hay'-lem; from H1986; smiter;  Helem, the name of two Israelites:—Helem.
h1987.r: From הָלַם (H1986)|English: smite, break down, break, beat down, beat, overcome

h1988.d: הֲלֹם hălôm, hal-ome'; from the article (see H1973);  hither:—here, hither(-to), thither.
h1988.r: From the article [see הָֽלְאָה (H1973)]|English: beyond, forward, hitherto, back thenceforth, henceforth, yonder

h199.d: אוּלָם ʼûwlâm, oo-lawm'; apparently a variation of H194;  however or on the contrary:—as for, but, howbeit, in very deed, surely, truly, wherefore.
h199.r: Apparently a variation of אוּלַי (H194)|English: if (so be), may (be), peradventure, unless

h1992.d: הֵם hêm, haym; or (prolonged) הֵמָּה hêmmâh; masculine plural from H1931;  they (only used when emphatic):—it, like, × (how, so) many (soever, more as) they (be), (the) same, × so, × such, their, them, these, they, those, which, who, whom, withal, ye.
h1992.s: third person plural masculine personal pronoun

h1993.d: הָמָה hâmâh, haw-maw'; a primitive root (compare H1949);  to make a loud sound (like English 'hum'); by implication, to be in great commotion or tumult, to rage, war, moan, clamor:—clamorous, concourse, cry aloud, be disquieted, loud, mourn, be moved, make a noise, rage, roar, sound, be troubled, make in tumult, tumultuous, be in an uproar.
h1993.r: A primitive root [compare הוּם (H1949)]|English: rang again, make a noise, moved, destroy

h1994.d: הִמּוֹ himmôw, him-mo'; (Aramaic) or (prolonged) הִמּוֹן himmôwn; (Aramaic), corresponding to H1992;  they:—× are, them, those.
h1994.r: Corresponding to הֵם (H1992)|English: they, them, themselves, these, those, as many more as, ye, same

h1995.d: הָמוֹן hâmôwn, haw-mone'; or הָמֹן hâmôn; (Ezekiel 5:7), from H1993;  a noise, tumult, crowd; also disquietude, wealth:—abundance, company, many, multitude, multiply, noise, riches, rumbling, sounding, store, tumult.
h1995.r: From הָמָֽה (H1993)|English: roar, noise, disquieted, sound, troubled, aloud, loud, clamorous, concourse, mourning, moved, raged, raging, tumult, tumultuous, uproar

h200.d: אִוֶּלֶת ʼivveleth, iv-veh'-leth; from the same as H191;  silliness:—folly, foolishly(-ness).
h200.r: From the same as אֱוִיל (H191)|English: fool(s), foolish (man)

h2000.d: הָמַם hâmam, haw-mam'; a primitive root (compare H1949, H1993);  properly, to put in commotion; by implication, to disturb, drive, destroy:—break, consume, crush, destroy, discomfit, trouble, vex.
h2000.r: A primitive root [compare הוּם (H1949), הָמָֽה (H1993)]|English: rang again, make a noise, moved, destroy

h2001.d: הָמָן Hâmân, haw-mawn'; of foreign derivation;  Haman, a Persian vizier:—Haman.

h2004.d: הֵן hên, hane; feminine plural from H1931;  they (only used when emphatic):—× in, such like, (with) them, thereby, therein, (more than) they, wherein, in which, whom, withal.
h2004.r: From הוּא (H1931)|English: that, him, same, this, he, which, who, such, wherein

h2005.d: הֵן hên, hane; a primitive particle;  lo!; also (as expressing surprise) if:—behold, if, lo, though.

h2006.d: הֵן hên, hane; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2005;  lo! also there(-fore), (un-) less, whether, but, if:—(that) if, or, whether.
h2006.r: Corresponding to הֵן (H2005)|English: lo, behold, if, or if, though

h2007.d: הֵנָּה hênnâh, hane'-naw; prolongation for H2004;  themselves (often used emphatic for the copula, also in indirect relation):—× in, × such (and such things), their, (into) them, thence, therein, these, they (had), on this side, whose, wherein.
h2007.s: third person plural feminine personal pronoun
h2007.r: Prolongation for הֵן (H2004)|English: therein, withal, which, they, for, like, them, thereby, wherein

h2008.d: הֵנָּה hênnâh, hane'-naw; from H2004;  hither or thither (but used both of place and time):—here, hither(-to), now, on this (that) side,   since, this (that) way, thitherward,   thus far, to...fro,   yet.
h2008.r: From הֵן (H2004)|English: therein, withal, which, they, for, like, them, thereby, wherein

h2009.d: הִנֵּה hinnêh, hin-nay'; prolongation for H2005;  lo!:—behold, lo, see.
h2009.r: Prolongation for הֵן (H2005)|English: lo, behold, if, or if, though

h201.d: אוֹמָר ʼÔwmâr, o-mawr'; from H559; talkative;  Omar, a grandson of Esau:—Omar.

h205.r: From an unused root perhaps meaning properly, to pant (hence, to exert oneself, usually in vain|

h2167.d: זָמַר zâmar, zaw-mar'; a primitive root (perhaps identical with H2168 through the idea of striking with the fingers);  properly, to touch the strings or parts of a musical instrument, i.e. play upon it; to make music, accompanied by the voice; hence to celebrate in song and music:—give praise, sing forth praises, psalms.
h2167.r: A primitive root [perhaps ident. with זָמַר (H2168) through the idea of striking with the fingers]|English: prune

h2168.d: זָמַר zâmar, zaw-mar'; a primitive root (compare H2167, H5568, H6785);  to trim (a vine):—prune.
h2168.r: A primitive root [compare זָמַר (H2167), סָמַר (H5568), צֶמֶר (H6785)]|English: praise, sing, sing psalms, sing forth

h217.d: אוּר ʼûwr, oor; from H215;  flame; hence (in the plural) the East (as being the region of light):—fire, light. See also H224.
h217.r: From אוֹר (H215)|English: light, shine, enlighten, break of day, fire, give, glorious, kindle

h2170.d: זְמָר zᵉmâr, zem-awr'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H2167;  instrumental music:—musick.
h2170.r: From a root corresponding to זָמַר (H2167)|English: praise, sing, sing psalms, sing forth

h2171.d: זַמָּר zammâr, zam-mawr'; (Aramaic) from the same as H2170;  an instrumental musician:—singer.
h2171.r: From the same as זְמָר (H2170)|English: musick

h2174.d: זִמְרִי Zimrîy, zim-ree'; from H2167; musical;  Zimri, the name of five Israelites, and of an Arabian tribe:—Zimri.
h2174.r: From זָמַר (H2167)|English: praise, sing, sing psalms, sing forth

h2175.d: זִמְרָן Zimrân, zim-rawn'; from H2167; musical;  Zimran, a son of Abraham by Keturah:—Zimran.
h2175.r: From זָמַר (H2167)|English: praise, sing, sing psalms, sing forth

h2177.d: זַן zan, zan; from H2109;  properly, nourished (or fully developed), i.e. a form or sort:—divers kinds, × all manner of store.

h2180.d: זָנָב zânâb, zaw-nawb'; from H2179 (in the original sense of flapping);  the tail (literally or figuratively):—tail.
h2180.r: From זָנָב (H2179) (in the original sense of flapping)|English: smite the hindmost

h2181.d: זָנָה zânâh, zaw-naw'; a primitive root [highly fed and therefore wanton];  to commit adultery (usually of the female, and less often of simple fornication, rarely of involuntary ravishment); figuratively, to commit idolatry (the Jewish people being regarded as the spouse of Jehovah):—(cause to) commit fornication, × continually, × great, (be an, play the) harlot, (cause to be, play the) whore, (commit, fall to) whoredom, (cause to) go a-whoring, whorish.
h2181.r: A primitive root [highly-fed and therefore wanton]|

h2182.d: זָנוֹחַ Zânôwach, zaw-no'-akh; from H2186; rejected;  Zanoach, the name of two places in Palestine:—Zanoah.
h2182.r: From זָנַח (H2186)|English: cast...off, cast away, turn...away, removed...far off

h2186.d: זָנַח zânach, zaw-nakh'; a primitive root meaning to push aside, i.e.  reject, forsake, fail:—cast away (off), remove far away (off).
h2186.r: A primitive root meaning to push aside|

h219.d: אוֹרָה ʼôwrâh, o-raw'; feminine of H216;  luminousness, i.e. (figuratively) prosperity; also a plant (as being bright):—herb, light.
h219.r: Fem. of אוֹר (H216)|English: light(s), day, bright, clear, flood, herbs, lightning, morning, sun

h2190.d: זַעֲוָן Zaʻăvân, zah-av-awn'; from H2111; disquiet;  Zaavan, an Idumaean:—Zaavan.

h2192.d: זְעֵיר zᵉʻêyr, zeh-ayr'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2191:—little.

h2194.d: זָעַם zâʻam, zaw-am'; a primitive root;  properly, to foam at the mouth, i.e. to be enraged:—abhor, abominable, (be) angry, defy, (have) indignation.

h2196.d: זָעַף zâʻaph, zaw-af'; a primitive root;  properly, to boil up, i.e. (figuratively) to be peevish or angry:—fret, sad, worse liking, be wroth.

h2197.d: זַעַף zaʻaph, zah'-af; from H2196;  anger:—indignation, rage(-ing), wrath.
h2197.r: From זָעַף (H2196)|English: wroth, sad, fretteth, worse liking

h2199.d: זָעַק zâʻaq, zaw-ak'; a primitive root;  to shriek (from anguish or danger); by analogy, (as a herald) to announce or convene publicly:—assemble, call (together), (make a) cry (out), come with such a company, gather (together), cause to be proclaimed.

h22.d: אֲבִיאֵל ʼĂbîyʼêl, ab-ee-ale'; from H1 and H410; father (i.e. possessor) of God;  Abiel, the name of two Israelites:—Abiel.
h22.r: From אָב (H1) and אֵל (H410)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h2201.d: זַעַק zaʻaq, zah'-ak; and (feminine) זְעָקָה zᵉʻâqâhxlit zᵉâqâh corrected to zᵉʻâqâh; from H2199;  a shriek or outcry:—cry(-ing).
h2201.r: From זָעַק (H2199)|English: cry, cry out, assemble, called, gathered together, gathered, company, proclaimed

h2203.d: זֶפֶת zepheth, zeh'-feth; from an unused root (meaning to liquify);  asphalt (from its tendency to soften in the sun):—pitch.
h2203.r: From an unused root (meaning to liquify)|

h2204.d: זָקֵן zâqên, zaw-kane'; a primitive root;  to be old:—aged man, be (wax) old (man).

h2205.d: זָקֵן zâqên, zaw-kane'; from H2204;  old:—aged, ancient (man), elder(-est), old (man, men and...women), senator.

h2206.d: זָקָן zâqân, zaw-kawn'; from H2204;  the beard (as indicating age):—beard.

h2208.d: זָקֻן zâqun, zaw-koon'; properly, passive participle of H2204 (used only in the plural as a noun);  old age:—old age.
h2208.r: Properly, passive participle of זָקֵן (H2204) (used only in the plural as a noun)|English: ...old, aged

h2209.d: זִקְנָה ziqnâh, zik-naw'; feminine of H2205;  old age:—old (age).
h2209.r: From זָקֵן (H2205)|English: elders, old, old man, ancient, aged, eldest, ancient man, senators, old women

h221.d: אוּרִי ʼÛwrîy, oo-ree'; from H217; fiery;  Uri, the name of three Israelites:—Uri.

h2212.d: זָקַק zâqaq, zaw-kak'; a primitive root;  to strain, (figuratively) extract, clarify:—fine, pour down, purge, purify, refine.

h2213.d: זֵר zêr, zare; from H2237 (in the sense of scattering);  a chaplet (as spread around the top), i.e. (specifically) a border moulding:—crown.
h2213.r: From זָרַר (H2237) (in the sense of scattering)|English: sneeze

h2214.d: זָרָא zârâʼ, zaw-raw'; from H2114 (in the sense of estrangement) (compare H2219);  disgust:—loathsome.
h2214.r: From זוּר (H2114) (sense of estrangement) [compare זָרָה (H2219)]|English: stranger, strange, estranged, stranger, another, strange woman, gone away, fanners, another place

h2216.d: זְרֻבָּבֶל Zᵉrubbâbel, zer-oob-baw-bel'; from H2215 and H894; descended of (i.e. from) Babylon, i.e. born there;  Zerubbabel, an Israelite:—Zerubbabel.
h2216.r: From זָרַב (H2215) and בָּבֶל (H894)|English: wax warm

h2217.d: זְרֻבָּבֶל Zᵉrubbâbel, zer-oob-baw-bel'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2216:—Zerubbabel.

h2218.d: זֶרֶד Zered, zeh'-red; from an unused root meaning to be exuberant in growth; lined with shrubbery;  Zered, a brook East of the Dead Sea:—Zared, Zered.
h2218.r: From an unused root meaning to be exuberant in growth|

h2219.d: זָרָה zârâh, zaw-raw'; a primitive root (compare H2114);  to toss about; by implication, to diffuse, winnow:—cast away, compass, disperse, fan, scatter (away), spread, strew, winnow.
h2219.r: A primitive root [compare זוּר (H2114)]|English: stranger, strange, estranged, stranger, another, strange woman, gone away, fanners, another place

h222.d: אוּרִיאֵל ʼÛwrîyʼêl, oo-ree-ale'; from H217 and H410; flame of God;  Uriel, the name of two Israelites:—Uriel.
h222.r: From אוּר (H217) and אֵל (H410)|English: fire(s), light

h2220.d: זְרוֹעַ zᵉrôwaʻ, zer-o'-ah; or (shortened) זְרֹעַ zᵉrôaʻ; and (feminine) זְרוֹעָה zᵉrôwʻâh; or זְרֹעָה zᵉrôʻâh; from H2232;  the arm (as stretched out), or (of animals) the foreleg; figuratively, force:—arm,   help, mighty, power, shoulder, strength.
h2220.r: From זָרַע (H2232)|English: sow, yielding, sower, bearing, conceive, seed, set

h2221.d: זֵרוּעַ zêrûwaʻ, zay-roo'-ah; from H2232;  something sown, i.e. a plant:—sowing, thing that is sown.
h2221.r: From זָרַע (H2232)|English: sow, yielding, sower, bearing, conceive, seed, set

h2224.d: זָרַח zârach, zaw-rakh'; a primitive root;  properly, to irradiate (or shoot forth beams), i.e. to rise (as the sun); specifically, to appear (as a symptom of leprosy):—arise, rise (up), as soon as it is up.

h2226.d: זֶרַח Zerach, zeh'-rakh; the same as H2225;  Zerach, the name of three Israelites, also of an Idumaean and an Ethiopian prince:—Zarah, Zerah.

h2228.d: זְרַחְיָה Zᵉrachyâh, zer-akh-yaw'; from H2225 and H3050; Jah has risen;  Zerachjah, the name of two Israelites:—Zerahiah.

h2229.d: זָרַם zâram, zaw-ram'; a primitive root;  to gush (as water):—carry away as with a flood, pour out.

h223.d: אוּרִיָּה ʼÛwrîyâh, oo-ree-yaw'; or (prolonged) אוּרִיָּהוּ ʼÛwrîyâhûw ; from H217 and H3050; flame of Jah;  Urijah, the name of one Hittite and five Israelites:—Uriah, Urijah.
h223.r: From אוּר (H217) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: fire(s), light

h2232.d: זָרַע zâraʻ, zaw-rah'; a primitive root;  to sow; figuratively, to disseminate, plant, fructify:—bear, conceive seed, set with sow(-er), yield.

h2233.d: זֶרַע zeraʻ, zeh'-rah; from H2232;  seed; figuratively, fruit, plant, sowing-time, posterity:—× carnally, child, fruitful, seed(-time), sowing-time.
h2233.r: From זָרַע (H2232)|English: sow, yielding, sower, bearing, conceive, seed, set

h2235.d: זֵרֹעַ zêrôaʻ, zay-ro'-ah; or זֵרָעֹן zêrâʻôn; from H2232;  something sown (only in the plural), i.e. a vegetable (as food):—pulse.
h2235.r: From זָרַע (H2232)|English: sow, yielding, sower, bearing, conceive, seed, set

h2236.d: זָרַק zâraq, zaw-rak'; a primitive root;  to sprinkle (fluid or solid particles):—be here and there, scatter, sprinkle, strew.

h2237.d: זָרַר zârar, zaw-rar'; a primitive root (compare H2114);  perhaps to diffuse, i.e. (specifically) to sneeze:—sneeze.
h2237.r: A primitive root [compare זוּר (H2114)]|English: stranger, strange, estranged, stranger, another, strange woman, gone away, fanners, another place

h2238.d: זֶרֶשׁ Zeresh, zeh'-resh; of Persian origin;  Zeresh, Haman's wife:—Zeresh.

h2239.d: זֶרֶת zereth, zeh'-reth; from H2219;  the spread of the fingers, i.e. a span:—span.
h2239.r: From זָרָה (H2219)|English: scatter, disperse, fan, spread, winnowed, cast away, scatter away, compass, strawed

h2240.d: זַתּוּא Zattûwʼ, zat-too'; of uncertain derivation;  Zattu, an Israelite:—Zattu.

h2241.d: זֵתָם Zêthâm, zay-thawm'; apparently a variation for H2133;  Zetham, an Israelite:—Zetham.
h2241.r: Apparently a variation for זֵיתָן (H2133)|English: Zethan

h2242.d: זֵתַר Zêthar, zay-thar'; of Persian origin;  Zethar, a eunuch of Xerxes:—Zethar.

h2244.d: חָבָא châbâʼ, khaw-baw'; a primitive root (compare H2245);  to secrete:—× held, hide (self), do secretly.

h2246.d: חֹבָב Chôbâb, kho-bawb'; from H2245; cherished;  Chobab, father-in-law of Moses:—Hobab.

h2249.d: חָבוֹר Châbôwr, khaw-bore'; from H2266; united;  Chabor, a river of Assyria:—Habor.
h2249.r: From חָבַר (H2266)|English: couple, join, couple together, join together, compact, charmer, charming, have fellowship, league, heap up

h225.d: אוּת ʼûwth, ooth; a primitive root;  properly, to come, i.e. (implied) to assent:—consent.

h2250.d: חַבּוּרָה chabbûwrâh, khab-boo-raw'; or חַבֻּרָה chabburâh; or חֲבֻרָה chăburâh; from H2266;  properly, bound (with stripes), i.e. a weal (or black-and-blue mark itself):—blueness, bruise, hurt, stripe, wound.
h2250.r: From חָבַר (H2266)|English: couple, join, couple together, join together, compact, charmer, charming, have fellowship, league, heap up

h2254.d: חָבַל châbal, khaw-bal'; a primitive root;  to wind tightly (as a rope), i.e. to bind; specifically, by a pledge; figuratively, to pervert, destroy; also to writhe in pain (especially of parturition):—× at all, band, bring forth, (deal) corrupt(-ly), destroy, offend, lay to (take a) pledge, spoil, travail, × very, withhold.

h2256.d: חֶבֶל chebel, kheh'-bel; or חֵבֶל chêbel; from H2254;  a rope (as twisted), especially a measuring line; by implication, a district or inheritance (as measured); or a noose (as of cords); figuratively, a company (as if tied together); a throe (especially of parturition); also ruin:—band, coast, company, cord, country, destruction, line, lot, pain, pang, portion, region, rope, snare, sorrow, tackling.
h2256.r: From חָבַל (H2254)|English: destroy, take a pledge, pledge, bands, brought forth, at all, corrupt, corruptly, offend, spoil, travaileth, very, withholden

h226.d: אוֹת ʼôwth, oth; probably from H225 (in the sense of appearing);  a signal (literally or figuratively), as a flag, beacon, monument, omen, prodigy, evidence, etc.:—mark, miracle, (en-) sign, token.
h226.r: Probably from אוֹת (H225) (in the sense of appearing)|English: consent

h2263.d: חָבַק châbaq, khaw-bak'; a primitive root;  to clasp (the hands or in embrace):—embrace, fold.

h2264.d: חִבֻּק chibbuq, khib-book'; from H2263;  a clasping of the hands (in idleness):—fold.

h2265.d: חֲבַקּוּק Chăbaqqûwq, khab-ak-kook'; by reduplication from H2263; embrace;  Chabakkuk, the prophet:—Habakkuk.
h2265.r: By reduplication from חָבַק (H2263)|English: embrace, fold

h2266.d: חָבַר châbar, khaw-bar'; a primitive root;  to join (literally or figuratively); specifically (by means of spells) to fascinate:—charm(-er), be compact, couple (together), have fellowship with, heap up, join (self, together), league.

h2267.d: חֶבֶר cheber, kheh'-ber; from H2266;  a society; also a spell:—  charmer(-ing), company, enchantment, × wide.
h2267.r: From חָבַר (H2266)|English: couple, join, couple together, join together, compact, charmer, charming, have fellowship, league, heap up

h2268.d: חֶבֶר Cheber, kheh'-ber; the same as H2267; community;  Cheber, the name of a Kenite and of three Israelites:—Heber.
h2268.r: The same as חֶבֶר (H2267)|English:  wide, enchantment, company, charmer, charming

h227.d: אָז ʼâz, awz; a demonstrative adverb;  at that time or place; also as a conjunction, therefore:—beginning, for, from, hitherto, now, of old, once, since, then, at which time, yet.

h2270.d: חָבֵר châbêr, khaw-bare'; from H2266;  an associate:—companion, fellow, knit together.
h2270.r: From חָבַר (H2266)|English: couple, join, couple together, join together, compact, charmer, charming, have fellowship, league, heap up

h2274.d: חֶבְרָה chebrâh, kheb-raw'; feminine of H2267;  association:—company.
h2274.r: From חֶבֶר (H2267)|English:  wide, enchantment, company, charmer, charming

h2275.d: חֶבְרוֹן Chebrôwn, kheb-rone'; from H2267; seat of association;  Chebron, a place in Palestine, also the name of two Israelites:—Hebron.
h2275.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h2275.r: From חֶבֶר (H2267)|English:  wide, enchantment, company, charmer, charming

h2279.d: חֹבֶרֶת chôbereth, kho-beh'-reth; feminine active participle of H2266;  a joint:—which coupleth, coupling.
h2279.r: Act. participle of חָבַר (H2266)|English: couple, join, couple together, join together, compact, charmer, charming, have fellowship, league, heap up

h228.d: אֲזָא ʼăzâʼ, az-zaw'; (Aramaic) or אֲזָה ʼăzâh (Aramaic);  to kindle; (by implication) to heat:—heat, hot.

h2280.d: חָבַשׁ châbash, khaw-bash'; a primitive root;  to wrap firmly (especially a turban, compress, or saddle); figuratively, to stop, to rule:—bind (up), gird about, govern, healer, put, saddle, wrap about.

h2282.d: חַג chag, khag; or חָג châg; from H2287;  a festival, or a victim therefor:—(solemn) feast (day), sacrifice, solemnity.
h2282.r: From חָגַג (H2287)|English: keep, ...feast, celebrate, keep a solemn feast, dancing, holyday, reel to and fro

h2287.d: חָגַג châgag, khaw-gag'; a primitive root (compare H2283, H2328);  properly, to move in a circle, i.e. (specifically) to march in a sacred procession, to observe a festival; by implication, to be giddy:—celebrate, dance, (keep, hold) a (solemn) feast (holiday), reel to and fro.
h2287.r: A primitive root [compare חָגָּא (H2283), חוּג (H2328)]|English: terrors

h2292.d: חַגַּי Chaggay, khag-gah'-ee; from H2282; festive;  Chaggai, a Hebrew prophet:—Haggai.
h2292.r: From חָג (H2282)|English: feast, sacrifice, feast days, solemnity

h2293.d: חַגִּיָּה Chaggîyâh, khag-ghee-yaw'; from H2282 and H3050; festival of Jah;  Chaggijah, an Israelite:—Haggiah.
h2293.r: From חָג (H2282) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: feast, sacrifice, feast days, solemnity

h2295.d: חׇגְלָה Choglâh, khog-law'; of uncertain derivation; probably a partridge;  Choglah, an Israelitess:—Hoglah. See also H1031.

h2296.d: חָגַר châgar, khaw-gar'; a primitive root;  to gird on (as a belt, armor, etc.):—be able to put on, be afraid, appointed, gird, restrain, × on every side.

h2298.d: חַד chad, khad; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2297;  as card. one; as article single; as an ordinal, first; adverbially, at once:—a, first, one, together.

h2299.d: חַד chad, khad; from H2300;  sharp:—sharp.

h2300.d: חָדַד châdad, khaw-dad'; a primitive root;  to be (causatively, make) sharp or (figuratively) severe:—be fierce, sharpen.

h2301.d: חֲדַד Chădad, khad-ad'; from H2300; fierce;  Chadad, an Ishmaelite:—Hadad.

h2302.d: חָדָה châdâh, khaw-daw'; a primitive root;  to rejoice:—make glad, be joined, rejoice.

h2307.d: חָדִיד Châdîyd, khaw-deed'; from H2300; a peak;  Chadid, a place in Palestine:—Hadid.

h2308.d: חָדַל châdal, khaw-dal'; a primitive root;  properly, to be flabby, i.e. (by implication) desist; (figuratively) be lacking or idle:—cease, end, fall, forbear, forsake, leave (off), let alone, rest, be unoccupied, want.

h231.d: אֵזוֹב ʼêzôwb, ay-zobe'; probably of foreign derivation;  hyssop:—hyssop.

h2315.d: חֶדֶר cheder, kheh'-der; from H2314;  an apartment (usually literal):—((bed) inner) chamber, innermost(-ward) part, parlour,   south, × within.

h2318.d: חָדַשׁ châdash, khaw-dash'; a primitive root;  to be new; causatively, to rebuild:—renew, repair.

h2319.d: חָדָשׁ châdâsh, khaw-dawsh'; from H2318;  new:—fresh, new thing.

h2320.d: חֹדֶשׁ chôdesh, kho'-desh; from H2318;  the new moon; by implication, a month:—month(-ly), new moon.

h2330.d: חוּד chûwd, khood; a primitive root;  properly, to tie a knot, i.e. (figuratively) to propound a riddle:—put forth.

h2331.d: חָוָה châvâh, khaw-vah'; a primitive root; (compare H2324, H2421);  properly, to live; by implication (intensively) to declare or show:—show.
h2331.r: A primitive root [compare חֲוָא (H2324), חָיָה (H2421)]|English: show

h2332.d: חַוָּה Chavvâh, khav-vaw'; causatively from H2331; life-giver;  Chavvah (or Eve), the first woman:—Eve.

h2334.d: חַוּוֹת יָעִיר Chavvôwth Yâʻîyr, khav-vothe' yaw-eer'; from the plural of H2333 and a modification of H3265;  hamlets of Jair, a region of Palestine:—(Bashan-) Havoth-jair.
h2334.r: From the plural of חַוָּה (H2333) and a modification of יָעוּר (H3265)|English: town

h2339.d: חוּט chûwṭ, khoot; from an unused root probably meaning to sew;  a string; by implication, a measuring tape:—cord, fillet, line, thread.
h2339.r: From an unused root probably meaning to sew|

h234.d: אַזְכָּרָה ʼazkârâh, az-kaw-raw'; from H2142;  a reminder; specifically remembrance-offering:—memorial.
h234.r: From זָכַר (H2142)|English: remember, mention, remembrance, recorder, mindful, think, bring to remembrance, record, misc

h2340.d: חִוִּי Chivvîy, khiv-vee'; perhaps from H2333; a villager;  a Chivvite, one of the aboriginal tribes of Palestine:—Hivite.

h2341.d: חֲוִילָה Chăvîylâh, khav-ee-law'; probably from H2342; circular;  Chavilah, the name of two or three eastern regions; also perhaps of two men:—Havilah.
h2341.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h2341.r: Probably from חוּל (H2342)|English: pain, formed, bring forth, pained, tremble, travail, dance, calve, grieved, grievous, wounded, shake, misc

h2342.d: חוּל chûwl, khool; or חִיל chîyl; a primitive root;  properly, to twist or whirl (in a circular or spiral manner), i.e. (specifically) to dance, to writhe in pain (especially of parturition) or fear; figuratively, to wait, to pervert:—bear, (make to) bring forth, (make to) calve, dance, drive away, fall grievously (with pain), fear, form, great, grieve, (be) grievous, hope, look, make, be in pain, be much (sore) pained, rest, shake, shapen, (be) sorrow(-ful), stay, tarry, travail (with pain), tremble, trust, wait carefully (patiently), be wounded.

h2343.d: חוּל Chûwl, khool; from H2342; a circle;  Chul, a son of Aram; also the region settled by him:—Hul.
h2343.r: From חוּל (H2342)|English: pain, formed, bring forth, pained, tremble, travail, dance, calve, grieved, grievous, wounded, shake, misc

h2345.d: חוּם chûwm, khoom; from an unused root meaning to be warm, i.e. (by implication)  sunburnt or swarthy (blackish):—brown.
h2345.r: From an unused root meaning to be warm|

h2346.d: חוֹמָה chôwmâh, kho-maw'; feminine active participle of an unused root apparently meaning to join;  a wall of protection:—wall, walled.
h2346.r: Act. participle of an unused root apparently meaning to join|

h2347.d: חוּס chûwç, khoos; a primitive root;  properly, to cover, i.e. (figuratively) to compassionate:—pity, regard, spare.

h235.d: אָזַל ʼâzal, aw-zal'; a primitive root;  to go away, hence, to disappear:—fail, gad about, go to and fro (but in Ezekiel 27:19 the word is rendered by many 'from Uzal,' by others 'yarn'), be gone (spent).

h2351.d: חוּץ chûwts, khoots; or (shortened) חֻץ chuts; (both forms feminine in the plural) from an unused root meaning to sever;  properly, separate by a wall, i.e. outside, outdoors:—abroad, field, forth, highway, more, out(-side, -ward), street, without.
h2351.r: (both forms fem. in the pl.) from an unused root meaning to sever|

h2353.d: חוּר chûwr, khoor; from H2357;  white linen:—white.

h2354.d: חוּר Chûwr, khoor; the same as H2353 or H2352;  Chur, the name of four Israelites and one Midianite:—Hur.
h2354.r: The same as חוּר (H2353) or חוּר (H2352)|English: white

h2356.d: חוֹר chôwr, khore; or (shortened) חֹר chôr; the same as H2352;  a cavity, socket, den:—cave, hole.

h2357.d: חָוַר châvar, khaw-var'; a primitive root;  to blanch (as with shame):—wax pale.

h236.d: אֲזַל ʼăzal, az-al'; (Aramaic) the same as H235;  to depart:—go (up).
h236.r: The same as אָזַל (H235)|English: gone, fail, gaddest about, to and fro, spent

h2360.d: חוּרַי Chûwray, khoo-rah'ee; probably an orthographical variation for H2359;  Churai, an Israelite:—Hurai.
h2360.r: Probably an orthographical variation for חוּרִי (H2359)|English: Huri

h2361.d: חוּרָם Chûwrâm, khoo-rawm'; probably from H2353; whiteness, i.e. noble;  Churam, the name of an Israelite and two Syrians:—Huram. Compare H2438.

h2362.d: חַוְרָן Chavrân, khav-rawn'; apparently from H2357 (in the sense of H2352); cavernous;  Chavran, a region East of the Jordan:—Hauran.
h2362.r: Apparently from חָוַר (H2357) (in the sense of חוּר (H2352))|English: wax pale

h2363.d: חוּשׁ chûwsh, koosh; a primitive root;  to hurry; figuratively, to be eager with excitement or enjoyment:—(make) haste(-n), ready.

h2365.d: חוּשַׁי Chûwshay, khoo-shah'-ee; from H2363; hasty;  Chushai, an Israelite:—Hushai.

h2366.d: חוּשִׁים Chûwshîym, khoo-sheem'; or חֻשִׁים Chushîym; or חֻשִׁם Chushim; plural from H2363; hasters;  Chushim, the name of three Israelites:—Hushim.
h2366.s: proper feminine noun, proper masculine noun

h2367.d: חוּשָׁם Chûwshâm, khoo-shawm'; or חֻשָׁם Chushâm; from H2363; hastily;  Chusham, an Idumaean:—Husham.

h2368.d: חוֹתָם chôwthâm, kho-thawm'; or חֹתָם chôthâm; from H2856;  a signature-ring:—seal, signet.
h2368.r: From חָתַם (H2856)|English: seal, seal up, marked, stopped, variant

h2370.d: חֲזָא chăzâʼ, khaz-aw'; (Aramaic) or חֲזָה chăzâh; (Aramaic), corresponding to H2372;  to gaze upon; mentally to dream, be usual (i.e. seem):—behold, have (a dream), see, be wont.
h2370.r: Corresponding to חָזָה (H2372)|English: see, behold, look, prophesy, provide

h2371.d: חֲזָאֵל Chăzâʼêl, khaz-aw-ale'; or חֲזָהאֵל Chăzâhʼêl; from H2372 and H410; God has seen;  Chazael, a king of Syria:—Hazael.
h2371.r: From חָזָה (H2372) and אֵל (H410)|English: see, behold, look, prophesy, provide

h2372.d: חָזָה châzâh, khaw-zaw'; a primitive root;  to gaze at; mentally to perceive, contemplate (with pleasure); specifically, to have a vision of:—behold, look, prophesy, provide, see.

h2373.d: חָזֶה châzeh, khaw-zeh'; from H2372;  the breast (as most seen in front):—breast.
h2373.r: From חָזָה (H2372)|English: see, behold, look, prophesy, provide

h2374.d: חֹזֶה chôzeh, kho-zeh'; active participle of H2372;  a beholder in vision; also a compact (as looked upon with approval):—agreement, prophet, see that, seer, (star-) gazer.
h2374.r: Active participle of חָזָה (H2372)|English: see, behold, look, prophesy, provide

h2376.d: חֵזֵו chêzêv, khay'-zev; (Aramaic) from H2370;  a sight:—look, vision.
h2376.r: From חֲזָא (H2370)|English: see, saw, beheld, had, wont, beheld

h2377.d: חָזוֹן châzôwn, khaw-zone'; from H2372;  a sight (mentally), i.e. a dream, revelation, or oracle:—vision.
h2377.r: From חָזָה (H2372)|English: see, behold, look, prophesy, provide

h238.d: אָזַן ʼâzan, aw-zan'; a primitive root; probably to expand; but used only as a denominative from H241;  to broaden out the ear (with the hand), i.e. (by implication) to listen:—give (perceive by the) ear, hear(-ken). See H239.

h2380.d: חָזוּת châzûwth, khaw-zooth'; from H2372;  a look; hence (figuratively) striking appearance, revelation, or (by implication) compact:—agreement, notable (one), vision.
h2380.r: From חָזָה (H2372)|English: see, behold, look, prophesy, provide

h2384.d: חִזָּיוֹן chizzâyôwn, khiz-zaw-yone'; from H2372;  a revelation, expectation by dream:—vision.
h2384.r: From חָזָה (H2372)|English: see, behold, look, prophesy, provide

h2385.d: חֲזִיז chăzîyz, khaw-zeez'; from an unused root meaning to glare;  a flash of lightning:—bright cloud, lightning.
h2385.r: From an unused root meaning to glare|

h2386.d: חֲזִיר chăzîyr, khaz-eer'; from an unused root probably meaning to inclose;  a hog (perhaps as penned):—boar, swine.
h2386.r: From an unused root probably meaning to enclose|

h2387.d: חֵזִיר Chêzîyr, khay-zeer'; from the same as H2386; perhaps protected;  Chezir, the name of two Israelites:—Hezir.
h2387.r: From the same as חֲזִיר (H2386)|English: swine, boar

h2388.d: חָזַק châzaq, khaw-zak'; a primitive root;  to fasten upon; hence, to seize, be strong (figuratively, courageous, causatively strengthen, cure, help, repair, fortify), obstinate; to bind, restrain, conquer:—aid, amend, × calker, catch, cleave, confirm, be constant, constrain, continue, be of good (take) courage(-ous, -ly), encourage (self), be established, fasten, force, fortify, make hard, harden, help, (lay) hold (fast), lean, maintain, play the man, mend, become (wax) mighty, prevail, be recovered, repair, retain, seize, be (wax) sore, strengthen (self), be stout, be (make, shew, wax) strong(-er), be sure, take (hold), be urgent, behave self valiantly, withstand.

h2389.d: חָזָק châzâq, khaw-zawk'; from H2388;  strong (usu. in a bad sense, hard, bold, violent):—harder, hottest,   impudent, loud, mighty, sore, stiff(-hearted), strong(-er).
h2389.r: From חָזַק (H2388)|English: strong, repair, hold, strengthened, strengthen, harden, prevail, encourage, take, courage, caught, stronger, hold, misc

h2393.d: חֶזְקָה chezqâh, khez-kaw'; feminine of H2391;  prevailing power:—strength(-en self), (was) strong.

h2394.d: חׇזְקָה chozqâh, khoz-kaw'; feminine of H2392;  vehemence (usually in a bad sense):—force, mightily, repair, sharply.

h2395.d: חִזְקִי Chizqîy, khiz-kee'; from H2388; strong;  Chizki, an Israelite:—Hezeki.
h2395.r: From חָזַק (H2388)|English: strong, repair, hold, strengthened, strengthen, harden, prevail, encourage, take, courage, caught, stronger, hold, misc

h2396.d: חִזְקִיָּה Chizqîyâh, khiz-kee-yaw'; or חִזְקִיָּהוּ Chizqîyâhûw; also יְחִזְקִיָּה Yᵉchizqîyâh; or יְחִזְקִיָּהוּ Yᵉchizqîyâhûw; from H2388 and H3050; strengthened of Jah;  Chizkijah, a king of Judah, also the name of two other Israelites:—Hezekiah, Hizkiah, Hizkijah. Compare H3169.
h2396.r: From חָזַק (H2388) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: strong, repair, hold, strengthened, strengthen, harden, prevail, encourage, take, courage, caught, stronger, hold, misc

h2397.d: חָח châch, khawkh; once (Ezekiel 29:4) חָחִי châchîy; from the same as H2336;  a ring for the nose (or lips):—bracelet, chain, hook.
h2397.r: From the same as חוֹחַ (H2336)|English: thistle(s), thorn(s), brambles

h2398.d: חָטָא châṭâʼ, khaw-taw'; a primitive root;  properly, to miss; hence (figuratively and generally) to sin; by inference, to forfeit, lack, expiate, repent, (causatively) lead astray, condemn:—bear the blame, cleanse, commit (sin), by fault, harm he hath done, loss, miss, (make) offend(-er), offer for sin, purge, purify (self), make reconciliation, (cause, make) sin(-ful, -ness), trespass.

h2399.d: חֵטְא chêṭᵉʼ, khate; from H2398;  a crime or its penalty:—fault, × grievously, offence, (punishment of) sin.
h2399.r: From חָטָא (H2398)|English: sin, purify, cleanse, sinner, committed, offended, blame, done, fault, harm, loss, miss, offender, purge, reconciliation, sinful, trespass

h24.d: אָבִיב ʼâbîyb, aw-beeb'; from an unused root (meaning to be tender);  green, i.e. a young ear of grain; hence, the name of the month Abib or Nisan:—Abib, ear, green ears of corn (not maize).
h24.r: From an unused root (meaning to be tender)|

h2400.d: חַטָּא chaṭṭâʼ, khat-taw'; intensively from H2398;  a criminal, or one accounted guilty:—offender, sinful, sinner.
h2400.r: Intensively from חָטָא (H2398)|English: sin, purify, cleanse, sinner, committed, offended, blame, done, fault, harm, loss, miss, offender, purge, reconciliation, sinful, trespass

h2401.d: חֲטָאָה chăṭâʼâh, khat-aw-aw'; feminine of H2399;  an offence, or a sacrifice for it:—sin (offering).
h2401.r: From חֵטְא (H2399)|English: sin, faults, grievously, offences

h2403.d: חַטָּאָה chaṭṭâʼâh, khat-taw-aw'; or חַטָּאת chaṭṭâʼth; from H2398;  an offence (sometimes habitual sinfulness), and its penalty, occasion, sacrifice, or expiation; also (concretely) an offender:—punishment (of sin), purifying(-fication for sin), sin(-ner, offering).
h2403.r: From חָטָא (H2398)|English: sin, purify, cleanse, sinner, committed, offended, blame, done, fault, harm, loss, miss, offender, purge, reconciliation, sinful, trespass

h2406.d: חִטָּה chiṭṭâh, khit-taw'; of uncertain derivation;  wheat, whether the grain or the plant:—wheat(-en).

h2407.d: חַטּוּשׁ Chaṭṭûwsh, khat-toosh'; from an unused root of uncertain signification;  Chattush, the name of four or five Israelites:—Hattush.
h2407.r: From an unused root of uncertain signification|

h2409.d: חֲטָּיָא chăṭṭâyâʼ, khat-taw-yaw'; (Aramaic) from the same as H2408;  an expiation:—sin offering.
h2409.r: From the same as חֲטָי (H2408)|English: sin

h241.d: אֹזֶן ʼôzen, o'-zen; from H238;  broadness. i.e. (concrete) the ear (from its form in man):—  advertise, audience,   displease, ear, hearing,   show.
h241.r: From אָזַן (H238)|English: give ear, hearken, hear, perceived by the ear

h2416.d: חַי chay, khah'-ee; from H2421;  alive; hence, raw (flesh); fresh (plant, water, year), strong; also (as noun, especially in the feminine singular and masculine plural) life (or living thing), whether literally or figuratively:—  age, alive, appetite, (wild) beast, company, congregation, life(-time), live(-ly), living (creature, thing), maintenance,   merry, multitude,   (be) old, quick, raw, running, springing, troop.
h2416.r: From חָיָה (H2421)|English: live, alive, save, quicken, revive, surely, life, recover, misc

h2417.d: חַי chay, khah'-ee; (Aramaic) from H2418;  alive; also (as noun in plural) life:—life, that liveth, living.

h2418.d: חֲיָא chăyâʼ, khah-yaw'; (Aramaic) or חֲיָה chăyâh; (Aramaic), corresponding to H2421;  to live:—live, keep alive.
h2418.r: Corresponding to חָיָה (H2421)|English: live, alive, save, quicken, revive, surely, life, recover, misc

h2419.d: חִיאֵל Chîyʼêl, khee-ale'; from H2416 and H410; living of God;  Chiel, an Israelite:—Hiel.
h2419.r: From חַי (H2416) and אֵל (H410)|English: live, life, beast, alive, creature, running, living thing, raw, misc

h2420.d: חִידָה chîydâh, khee-daw'; from H2330;  a puzzle, hence, a trick, conundrum, sententious maxim:—dark saying (sentence, speech), hard question, proverb, riddle.

h2421.d: חָיָה châyâh, khaw-yaw'; a primitive root (compare H2331, H2421);  to live, whether literally or figuratively; causatively, to revive:—keep (leave, make) alive, × certainly, give (promise) life, (let, suffer to) live, nourish up, preserve (alive), quicken, recover, repair, restore (to life), revive, (× God) save (alive, life, lives), × surely, be whole.
h2421.r: A primitive root [compare חָוָה (H2331), חָיָה (H2421)]|English: shew

h2423.d: חֵיוָא chêyvâʼ, khay-vaw'; (Aramaic) from H2418;  an animal:—beast.

h2424.d: חַיּוּת chayûwth, khah-yooth'; from H2421;  life:—× living.
h2424.r: From חָיָה (H2421)|English: live, alive, save, quicken, revive, surely, life, recover, misc

h2425.d: חָיַי châyay, khaw-yah'-ee; a primitive root (compare H2421);  to live; causatively to revive:—live, save life.
h2425.r: A primitive root [compare חָיָה (H2421)]|English: live, alive, save, quicken, revive, surely, life, recover, misc

h2426.d: חֵיל chêyl, khale; or (shortened) חֵל chêl; a collateral form of H2428;  an army; also (by analogy,) an intrenchment:—army, bulwark, host, + poor, rampart, trench, wall.
h2426.r: A collateral form of חַיִל (H2428)|English: army, man of valour, host, forces, valiant, strength, riches, wealth, power, substance, might, strong, misc

h2427.d: חִיל chîyl, kheel; and (feminine) חִילָה chîylâh; from H2342;  a throe (expectant of childbirth):—pain, pang, sorrow.
h2427.r: From חוּל (H2342)|English: pain, formed, bring forth, pained, tremble, travail, dance, calve, grieved, grievous, wounded, shake, misc

h2428.d: חַיִל chayil, khah'-yil; from H2342;  probably a force, whether of men, means or other resources; an army, wealth, virtue, valor, strength:—able, activity, ( ) army, band of men (soldiers), company, (great) forces, goods, host, might, power, riches, strength, strong, substance, train, ( ) valiant(-ly), valour, virtuous(-ly), war, worthy(-ily).
h2428.r: From חוּל (H2342)|English: pain, formed, bring forth, pained, tremble, travail, dance, calve, grieved, grievous, wounded, shake, misc

h2429.d: חַיִל chayil, khah'-yil; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2428;  an army, or strength:—aloud, army, × most (mighty), power.
h2429.r: Corresponding to חַיִל (H2428)|English: army, man of valour, host, forces, valiant, strength, riches, wealth, power, substance, might, strong, misc

h2432.d: חִילֵן Chîylên, khee-lane'; from H2428; fortress;  Chilen, a place in Palestine:—Hilen.
h2432.r: From חַיִל (H2428)|English: army, man of valour, host, forces, valiant, strength, riches, wealth, power, substance, might, strong, misc

h2436.d: חֵיק chêyq, khake; or חֵק chêq; and חוֹק chôwq; from an unused root, apparently meaning to inclose;  the bosom (literally or figuratively):—bosom, bottom, lap, midst, within.
h2436.r: From an unused root, apparently meaning to inclose|

h2437.d: חִירָה Chîyrâh, khee-raw'; from H2357 in the sense of splendor;  Chirah, an Adullamite:—Hirah.
h2437.r: From חָוַר (H2357) in the sense of splendour|English: wax pale

h2438.d: חִירָם Chîyrâm, khee-rawm'; or חִירוֹם Chîyrôwmlemma חִירֹם missing vav, corrected to חִירוֹם; another form of H2361;  Chiram or Chirom, the name of two Tyrians:—Hiram, Huram.
h2438.r: Another form of חוּרָם (H2361)|English: Huram, variant

h2442.d: חָכָה châkâh, khaw-kaw'; a primitive root (apparently akin to H2707 through the idea of piercing);  properly, to adhere to; hence, to await:—long, tarry, wait.
h2442.r: A primitive root [apparently akin to חָקָה (H2707) through the idea of piercing]|English: portrayed, carved work, set a print

h2445.d: חַכִּים chakkîym, khak-keem'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H2449;  wise, i.e. a Magian:—wise.
h2445.r: From a root corresponding to חָכַם (H2449)|English: ..wise, ..wiser, ..wisely, teach wisdom, exceeding

h2449.d: חָכַם châkam, khaw-kam'; a primitive root,  to be wise (in mind, word or act):—× exceeding, teach wisdom, be (make self, shew self) wise, deal (never so) wisely, make wiser.

h2450.d: חָכָם châkâm, khaw-kawm'; from H2449;  wise, (i.e. intelligent, skillful or artful):—cunning (man), subtle, (un-), wise((hearted), man).

h2451.d: חׇכְמָה chokmâh, khok-maw'; from H2449;  wisdom (in a good sense):—skilful, wisdom, wisely, wit.

h2452.d: חׇכְמָה chokmâh, khok-maw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2451;  wisdom:—wisdom.
h2452.r: Corresponding to חָכְמָה (H2451)|English: wisdom, wisely, skilful man, wits

h2454.d: חׇכְמוֹת chokmôwth, khok-moth'; or חַכְמוֹת chakmôwth; collateral forms of H2451;  wisdom:—wisdom, every wise (woman).
h2454.r: Collateral forms of חָכְמָה (H2451)|English: wisdom, wisely, skilful man, wits

h2455.d: חֹל chôl, khole; from H2490;  properly, exposed; hence, profane:—common, profane (place), unholy.
h2455.r: From חָלַל (H2490)|English: begin, profane, pollute, defile, break, wounded, eat, slay, first, gather grapes, inheritance, began men, piped, players, prostitute, sorrow, stain, eat as common things

h2456.d: חָלָא châlâʼ, khaw-law'; a primitive root (compare H2470);  to be sick:—be diseased.
h2456.r: A primitive root [compare חָלָה (H2470)]|English: ...sick, beseech, be weak, grievous, be diseased, wounded, pray, intreat, grief, grieved, sore, pain, infirmity, intreated, laid, prayer, sorry, make suit, supplication, travail

h2595.d: חֲנִית chănîyth, khan-eeth'; from H2583;  a lance (for thrusting, like pitching a tent):—javelin, spear.
h2595.r: From חָנָה (H2583)|English: pitch, encamp, camp, pitch ... tent, abide, dwelt, lie, rested, grows to an end

h2596.d: חָנַךְ chânak, khaw-nak'; a primitive root; (compare H2614)  properly, to narrow; figuratively, to initiate or discipline:—dedicate, train up.

h26.d: אֲבִיגַיִל ʼĂbîygayil, ab-ee-gah'-yil; or shorter אֲבִיגַל ʼĂbîygal; from H1 and H1524; father (i.e. source) of joy;  Abigail or Abigal, the name of two Israelitesses:—Abigal.
h26.r: From אָב (H1) and גִּיל (H1524)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h260.d: אָחוּ ʼâchûw, aw'-khoo; of uncertain (perhaps Egyptian) derivation;  a bulrush or any marshy grass (particularly that along the Nile):—flag, meadow.

h2600.d: חִנָּם chinnâm, khin-nawm'; from H2580;  gratis, i.e. devoid of cost, reason or advantage:—without a cause (cost, wages), causeless, to cost nothing, free(-ly), innocent, for nothing (nought), in vain.
h2600.r: From חֵן (H2580)|English: grace, favour, gracious, pleasant, precious, wellfavoured

h2601.d: חֲנַמְאֵל Chănamʼêl, khan-am-ale'; probably by orthographical variation for H2606;  Chanamel, an Israelite:—Hanameel.
h2601.r: Probably by orthographical variation for חֲנַנְאֵל (H2606)|English: Hananeel

h2603.d: חָנַן chânan, khaw-nan'; a primitive root (compare H2583);  properly, to bend or stoop in kindness to an inferior; to favor, bestow; causatively to implore (i.e. move to favor by petition):—beseech, × fair, (be, find, shew) favour(-able), be (deal, give, grant (gracious(-ly), intreat, (be) merciful, have (shew) mercy (on, upon), have pity upon, pray, make supplication, × very.
h2603.r: A primitive root [compare חָנָה (H2583)]|English: pitch, encamp, camp, pitch ... tent, abide, dwelt, lie, rested, grows to an end

h2604.d: חֲנַן chănan, khan-an'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2603;  to favor or (causatively) to entreat:—shew mercy, make supplication.
h2604.r: Corresponding to חָנַן (H2603)|English: mercy, gracious, merciful, supplication, favour, besought, pity, fair, favourable, favoured, misc

h2605.d: חָנָן Chânân, khaw-nawn'; from H2603; favor;  Chanan, the name of seven Israelites:—Canan.
h2605.r: From חָנַן (H2603)|English: mercy, gracious, merciful, supplication, favour, besought, pity, fair, favourable, favoured, misc

h2607.d: חֲנָנִי Chănânîy, khan-aw-nee'; from H2603; gracious;  Chanani, the name of six Israelites:—Hanani.
h2607.r: From חָנַן (H2603)|English: mercy, gracious, merciful, supplication, favour, besought, pity, fair, favourable, favoured, misc

h2608.d: חֲנַנְיָה Chănanyâh, khan-an-yaw'; or חֲנַנְיָהוּ Chănanyâhûw; from H2603 and H3050; Jah has favored;  Chananjah, the name of thirteen Israelites:—Hananiah.
h2608.r: From חָנַן (H2603) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: mercy, gracious, merciful, supplication, favour, besought, pity, fair, favourable, favoured, misc

h2610.d: חָנֵף chânêph, khaw-nafe'; a primitive root;  to soil, especially in a moral sense:—corrupt, defile, × greatly, pollute, profane.

h2611.d: חָנֵף chânêph, khaw-nafe'; from H2610;  soiled (i.e. with sin), impious:—hypocrite(-ical).
h2611.r: From חָנֵף (H2610)|English: pollute, defile, greatly, corrupt, profane

h2612.d: חֹנֶף chôneph, kho'-nef; from H2610;  moral filth, i.e. wickedness:—hypocrisy.
h2612.r: From חָנֵף (H2610)|English: pollute, defile, greatly, corrupt, profane

h2617.d: חֶסֶד cheçed, kheh'-sed; from H2616;  kindness; by implication (towards God) piety; rarely (by opposition) reproof, or (subjectively) beauty:—favour, good deed(-liness, -ness), kindly, (loving-) kindness, merciful (kindness), mercy, pity, reproach, wicked thing.
h2617.r: From חָסַד (H2616)|English: show thyself merciful, put to shame

h2619.d: חֲסַדְיָה Chăçadyâh, khas-ad-yaw'; from H2617 and H3050; Jah has favored;  Chasadjah, an Israelite:—Hasadiah.
h2619.r: From חֶסֶד (H2617) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: mercy, kindness, lovingkindness, goodness, kindly, merciful, favour, good, goodliness, pity, reproach, wicked thing

h2620.d: חָסָה châçâh, khaw-saw'; a primitive root; (compare H982)  to flee for protection; figuratively, to confide in:—have hope, make refuge, (put) trust.

h2623.d: חָסִיד châçîyd, khaw-seed'; from H2616;  properly, kind, i.e. (religiously) pious (a saint):—godly (man), good, holy (one), merciful, saint, (un-) godly.
h2623.r: From חָסַד (H2616)|English: show thyself merciful, put to shame

h2627.d: חַסִּיר chaççîyr, khas-seer'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H2637;  deficient:—wanting.
