h2631.d: חֲסַן chăçan, khas-an'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2630;  to hold in occupancy:—possess.

h2632.d: חֵסֶן chêçen, khay'-sen; (Aramaic) from H2631;  strength:—power.

h2633.d: חֹסֶן chôçen, kho'-sen; from H2630;  wealth:—riches, strength, treasure.

h2635.d: חֲסַף chăçaph, khas-af'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of H2636;  a clod:—clay.
h2635.r: From a root corresponding to that of חַסְפַּס (H2636)|English: round thing

h2636.d: חַסְפַּס chaçpaç, khas-pas'; reduplicated from an unused root meaning apparently to peel;  a shred or scale:—round thing.

h2637.d: חָסֵר châçêr, khaw-sare'; a primitive root;  to lack; by implication, to fail, want, lessen:—be abated, bereave, decrease, (cause to) fail, (have) lack, make lower, want.

h2638.d: חָסֵר châçêr, khaw-sare'; from H2637;  lacking; hence, without:—destitute, fail, lack, have need, void, want.
h2638.r: From חָסֵר (H2637)|English: want, lack, fail, decreased, abated, have need, made lower, bereave

h2644.d: חָפָא châphâʼ, khaw-faw'; an orthographical variation of H2645;  properly, to cover, i.e. (in a sinister sense) to act covertly:—do secretly.
h2644.r: An orthographical variation of חָפָה (H2645)|English: covered, overlaid, cieled

h2645.d: חָפָה châphâh, khaw-faw'; a primitive root (compare H2644, H2653);  to cover; by implication, to veil, to encase, protect:—ceil, cover, overlay.
h2645.r: A primitive root (compare חָפָא (H2644), חָפַף (H2653))|English: did secretly

h265.d: אֲחוֹחַ ʼĂchôwach, akh-o'-akh; by reduplication from H251; brotherly;  Achoach, an Israelite:—Ahoah.
h265.r: By reduplication from אָח (H251)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2652.d: חׇפְנִי Chophnîy, khof-nee'; from H2651; perhaps pugilist;  Chophni, an Israelite:—Hophni.

h2654.d: חָפֵץ châphêts, khaw-fates'; a primitive root;  properly, to incline to; by implication (literally but rarely) to bend; figuratively, to be pleased with, desire:—× any at all, (have, take) delight, desire, favour, like, move, be (well) pleased, have pleasure, will, would.

h2655.d: חָפֵץ châphêts, khaw-fates'; from H2654;  pleased with:—delight in, desire, favour, please, have pleasure, whosoever would, willing, wish.
h2655.r: From חָפֵץ (H2654)|English: delight, please, desire, will, pleasure, favour, like, moveth, would, at all

h2656.d: חֵפֶץ chêphets, khay'-fets; from H2654;  pleasure; hence (abstractly) desire; concretely, a valuable thing; hence (by extension) a matter (as something in mind):—acceptable, delight(-some), desire, things desired, matter, pleasant(-ure), purpose, willingly.
h2656.r: From חָפֵץ (H2654)|English: delight, please, desire, will, pleasure, favour, like, moveth, would, at all

h2658.d: חָפַר châphar, khaw-far'; a primitive root;  properly, to pry into; by implication, to delve, to explore:—dig, paw, search out, seek.

h2660.d: חֵפֶר Chêpher, khay'-fer; from H2658 or H2659; a pit of shame;  Chepher, a place in Palestine; also the name of three Israelites:—Hepher.
h2660.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h2660.r: From חָפַר (H2658) or חָפֵר (H2659)|English: dig, search out, paweth, seeketh

h2664.d: חָפַשׂ châphas, khaw-fas'; a primitive root;  to seek; causatively, to conceal oneself (i.e. let be sought), or mask:—change, (make) diligent (search), disquise self, hide, search (for, out).

h2665.d: חֵפֶשׂ chêphes, khay'-fes; from H2664;  something covert, i.e. a trick:—search.
h2665.r: From חָפַשׂ (H2664)|English: search, disguise, search out, changed, diligent, hidden

h2669.d: חׇפְשׁוּת chophshûwth, khof-shooth'; and חׇפְשִׁית chophshîyth; from H2666; (with H1004, a hospital)  prostration by sickness:—several.

h267.d: אֲחוּמַי ʼĂchûwmay, akh-oo-mah'-ee; perhaps from H251 and H4325; brother (i.e. neighbour) of water;  Achumai, an Israelite:—Ahumai.
h267.r: Perhaps from אָח (H251) and מַיִם (H4325)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2670.d: חׇפְשִׁי chophshîy, khof-shee'; from H2666;  exempt (from bondage, tax or care):—free, liberty.

h2671.d: חֵץ chêts, khayts; from H2686; also by interchange for H6086  properly, a piercer, i.e. an arrow; by implication, a wound; figuratively, (of God) thunder-bolt; the shaft of a spear:—  archer, arrow, dart, shaft, staff, wound.
h2671.r: From חָצַץ (H2686)|English: bands, archers, cut off in the midst

h2672.d: חָצַב châtsab, khaw-tsab'; or חָצֵב châtsêb; a primitive root;  to cut or carve (wood, stone or other material); by implication, to hew, split, square, quarry, engrave:—cut, dig, divide, grave, hew (out, -er), made, mason.

h2673.d: חָצָה châtsâh, khaw-tsaw'; a primitive root (compare H2086);  to cut or split in two; to halve:—divide, × live out half, reach to the midst, participle
h2673.r: A primitive root [compare חָצַץ (H2686)])|English: bands, archers, cut off in the midst

h2674.d: חָצוֹר Châtsôwr, khaw-tsore'; a collective form of H2691; village;  Chatsor, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine and of one in Arabia:—Hazor.

h2677.d: חֵצִי chêtsîy, khay-tsee'; from H2673;  the half or middle:—half, middle, mid(-night), midst, part, two parts.

h2678.d: חִצִּי chitstsîy, khits-tsee'; or חֵצִי chêtsîy; prolongation from H2671;  an arrow:—arrow.

h2682.d: חָצִיר châtsîyr, khaw-tseer'; perhaps originally the same as H2681, from the greenness of a courtyard;  grass; also a leek (collectively):—grass, hay, herb, leek.

h2689.d: חֲצֹצְרָה chătsôtsᵉrâh, khats-o-tser-aw'; by reduplication from H2690;  a trumpet (from its sundered or quavering note):—trumpet(-er).
h2689.r: By reduplication from חָצַר (H2690)|English: sounded, blow, sounding, trumpeters, sounded, variant

h269.d: אָחוֹת ʼâchôwth, aw-khoth'; irregular feminine of H251;  a sister (used very widely [like H251 number H250, corrected to H251], literally and figuratively):—(an-) other, sister, together.

h2691.d: חָצֵר châtsêr, khaw-tsare'; (masculine and feminine); from H2690 in its original sense;  a yard (as inclosed by a fence); also a hamlet (as similarly surrounded with walls):—court, tower, village.
h2691.r: From חָצַר (H2690) in its original sense|English: sounded, blow, sounding, trumpeters, sounded, variant

h2694.d: חֲצַר הַתִּיכוֹן Chătsar hat-Tîykôwn, khats-ar' hat-tee-kone'; from H2691 and H8484 with the article interposed; village of the middle;  Chatsar-hat-Tikon, a place in Palestine:—Hazar-hatticon.
h2694.r: From חָצֵר (H2691) and תִּיכוֹן (H8484) with the article interposed|English: court, villages, towns

h2695.d: חֶצְרוֹ Chetsrôw, khets-ro'; by an orthographical variation for H2696; enclosure;  Chetsro, an Israelite:—Hezro, Hezrai.
h2695.r: By an orthographical variation for חֶצְרוֹן (H2696)|English: Hezron

h2696.d: חֶצְרוֹן Chetsrôwn, khets-rone'; from H2691; court-yard;  Chetsron, the name of a place in Palestine; also of two Israelites:—Hezron.
h2696.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h27.d: אֲבִידָן ʼĂbîydân, ab-ee-dawn'; from H1 and H1777; father of judgment (i.e. judge);  Abidan, an Israelite:—Abidan.
h27.r: From אָב (H1) and דִּין (H1777)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h270.d: אָחַז ʼâchaz, aw-khaz'; a primitive root;  to seize (often with the accessory idea of holding in possession):—  be affrighted, bar, (catch, lay, take) hold (back), come upon, fasten, handle, portion, (get, have or take) possess(-ion).

h2700.d: חֲצַרְמָוֶת Chătsarmâveth, khats-ar-maw'-veth; from H2691 and H4194; village of death;  Chatsarmaveth, a place in Arabia:—Hazarmaveth.
h2700.r: From חָצֵר (H2691) and מָוֶת (H4194)|English: court, villages, towns

h2702.d: חֲצַר סוּסִים Chătsar Çûwçîym, khats-ar' soo-seem'; from H2691 and the plural of H5483; village of horses;  Chatsar-Susim, a place in Palestine:—Hazar-susim.
h2702.r: From חָצֵר (H2691) and the plural of סוּס (H5483)|English: court, villages, towns

h2706.d: חֹק chôq, khoke; from H2710;  an enactment; hence, an appointment (of time, space, quantity, labor or usage):—appointed, bound, commandment, convenient, custom, decree(-d), due, law, measure, × necessary, ordinance(-nary), portion, set time, statute, task.
h2706.r: From חָקַק (H2710)|English: lawgiver, governor, decree, to grave, portray, law, printed, set, note, appoint

h2707.d: חָקָה châqâh, khaw-kaw'; a primitive root;  to carve; by implication, to delineate; also to entrench:—carved work, portrayed, set a print.

h2708.d: חֻקָּה chuqqâh, khook-kaw'; feminine of H2706, and meaning substantially the same:—appointed, custom, manner, ordinance, site, statute.
h2708.r: From חֹק (H2706)|English: statute, ordinance, decree, due, law, portion, bounds, custom, appointed, commandments, misc

h271.d: אָחָז ʼÂchâz, aw-khawz'; from H270; possessor;  Achaz, the name of a Jewish king and of an Israelite:—Ahaz.
h271.r: From אָחַז (H270)|English: hold, take, possess, caught, fastened, misc

h2710.d: חָקַק châqaq, khaw-kak'; a primitive root;  properly, to hack, i.e. engrave (Judges 5:14, to be a scribe simply); by implication, to enact (laws being cut in stone or metal tablets in primitive times) or (generally) prescribe:—appoint, decree, governor, grave, lawgiver, note, pourtray, print, set.

h2711.d: חֵקֶק chêqeq, khay'-kek; from H2710;  an enactment, a resolution:—decree, thought.
h2711.r: From חָקַק (H2710)|English: lawgiver, governor, decree, to grave, portray, law, printed, set, note, appoint

h2712.d: חֻקֹּק Chuqqôq, Khook-koke'; or (fully) חוּקֹק Chûwqôq; from H2710; appointed;  Chukkok or Chukok, a place in Palestine:—Hukkok, Hukok.
h2712.r: From חָקַק (H2710)|English: lawgiver, governor, decree, to grave, portray, law, printed, set, note, appoint

h2713.d: חָקַר châqar, khaw-kar'; a primitive root;  properly, to penetrate; hence, to examine intimately:—find out, (make) search (out), seek (out), sound, try.

h2714.d: חֵקֶר chêqer, khay'-ker; from H2713;  examination, enumeration, deliberation:—finding out, number, (un-) search(-able, -ed, out, -ing).
h2714.r: From חָקַר (H2713)|English: search, search out, found out, seek out, seek, sounded, try

h2717.d: חָרַב chârab, khaw-rab'; or חֲרֵב chărêb; a primitive root;  to parch (through drought) i.e. (by analogy,) to desolate, destroy, kill:—decay, (be) desolate, destroy(-er), (be) dry (up), slay, × surely, (lay, lie, make) waste.

h2718.d: חֲרַב chărab, khar-ab'; (Aramaic) a root corresponding to H2717;  to demolish:—destroy.
h2718.r: A root corresponding to חָרַב (H2717)|English: waste, dry, dry up, desolate, slay, decayeth, destroyed, destroyer, surely, utterly

h2719.d: חֶרֶב chereb, kheh'-reb; from H2717;  drought; also a cutting instrument (from its destructive effect), as a knife, sword, or other sharp implement:—axe, dagger, knife, mattock, sword, tool.
h2719.r: From חָרַב (H2717)|English: waste, dry, dry up, desolate, slay, decayeth, destroyed, destroyer, surely, utterly

h272.d: אֲחֻזָּה ʼăchuzzâh, akh-ooz-zaw'; feminine passive participle from H270;  something seized, i.e. a possession (especially of land):—possession.
h272.r: From passive participle from אָחַז (H270)|English: hold, take, possess, caught, fastened, misc

h2722.d: חֹרֵב Chôrêb, kho-rabe'; from H2717; desolate;  Choreb, a (generic) name for the Sinaitic mountains:—Horeb.
h2722.r: From חָרַב (H2717)|English: waste, dry, dry up, desolate, slay, decayeth, destroyed, destroyer, surely, utterly

h2723.d: חׇרְבָּה chorbâh, khor-baw'; feminine of H2721;  properly, drought, i.e. (by implication) a desolation:—decayed place, desolate (place, -tion), destruction, (laid) waste (place).
h2723.r: From חֹרֶב (H2721)|English: heat, dry, drought, waste, desolation, utterly

h2724.d: חָרָבָה chârâbâh, khaw-raw-baw'; feminine of H2720;  a desert:—dry (ground, land).

h2725.d: חֲרָבוֹן chărâbôwn, khar-aw-bone'; from H2717;  parching heat:—drought.
h2725.r: From חָרַב (H2717)|English: waste, dry, dry up, desolate, slay, decayeth, destroyed, destroyer, surely, utterly

h2726.d: חַרְבוֹנָא Charbôwnâʼ, khar-bo-naw'; or חַרְבוֹנָה Charbôwnâh; of Persian origin;  Charbona or Charbonah, a eunuch of Xerxes:—Harbona, Harbonah.

h2727.d: חָרַג chârag, khaw-rag'; a primitive root;  properly, to leap suddenly, i.e. (by implication) to be dismayed:—be afraid.

h2729.d: חָרַד chârad, khaw-rad'; a primitive root;  to shudder with terror; hence, to fear; also to hasten (with anxiety):—be (make) afraid, be careful, discomfit, fray (away), quake, tremble.

h2730.d: חָרֵד chârêd, khaw-rade'; from H2729;  fearful; also reverential:—afraid, trembling.
h2730.r: From חָרֵד (H2729)|English: afraid, tremble, fray away, careful, discomfited, fray, quaked

h2734.d: חָרָה chârâh, khaw-raw'; a primitive root (compare H2787);  to glow or grow warm; figuratively (usually) to blaze up, of anger, zeal, jealousy:—be angry, burn, be displeased, × earnestly, fret self, grieve, be (wax) hot, be incensed, kindle, × very, be wroth. See H8474.
h2734.r: A primitive root [compare חָרַר (H2787)]|English: burn, dried, angry, kindle

h274.d: אֲחַזְיָה ʼĂchazyâh, akh-az-yaw'; or (prolonged) אֲחַזְיָהוּ ʼĂchazyâhûw ; from H270 and H3050; Jah has seized;  Achazjah, the name of a Jewish and an Israelite king:—Ahaziah.
h274.r: From אָחַז (H270) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: hold, take, possess, caught, fastened, misc

h2740.d: חָרוֹן chârôwn, khaw-rone'; or (shortened) חָרֹן chârôn; from H2734;  a burning of anger:—sore displeasure, fierce(-ness), fury, (fierce) wrath(-ful).

h2742.d: חֲרוּץ chărûwts, khaw-roots'; or חָרֻץ châruts; passive participle of H2782;  properly, incised or (active) incisive; hence (as noun masculine or feminine) a trench (as dug), gold (as mined), a threshing-sledge (having sharp teeth); (figuratively) determination; also eager:—decision, diligent, (fine) gold, pointed things, sharp, threshing instrument, wall.
h2742.r: Pass. participle of חָרַץ (H2782)|English: determined, move, decide, bestir, maim, decreed

h2747.d: חֶרֶט chereṭ, kheh'-ret; from a primitive root meaning to engrave;  a chisel or graver; also a style for writing:—graving tool, pen.
h2747.r: From a primitive root meaning to engrave|

h2749.d: חַרְטֹם charṭôm, khar-tome'; (Aramaic) the same as H2748:—magician.

h2754.d: חָרִיט chârîyṭ, khaw-reet'; or חָרִט châriṭ; from the same as H2747;  properly, cut out (or hollow), i.e. (by implication) a pocket:—bag, crisping pin.

h2763.d: חָרַם châram, khaw-ram'; a primitive root;  to seclude; specifically (by a ban) to devote to religious uses (especially destruction); physical and reflexive, to be blunt as to the nose:—make accursed, consecrate, (utterly) destroy, devote, forfeit, have a flat nose, utterly (slay, make away).

h2764.d: חֵרֶם chêrem, khay'-rem; or (Zechariah 14:11) חֶרֶם cherem; from H2763;  physical (as shutting in) a net (either literally or figuratively); usually a doomed object; abstractly extermination:—(ac-) curse(-d, -d thing), dedicated thing, things which should have been utterly destroyed, (appointed to) utter destruction, devoted (thing), net.
h2764.r: From חָרַם (H2763)|English: destroy, utterly, devote, accursed, consecrate, forfeited, flat nose, utterly to make away, slay

h2765.d: חֳרֵם Chŏrêm, khor-ame'; from H2763; devoted;  Chorem, a place in Palestine:—Horem.
h2765.r: From חָרַם (H2763)|English: destroy, utterly, devote, accursed, consecrate, forfeited, flat nose, utterly to make away, slay

h2766.d: חָרִם Chârim, khaw-reem'; from H2763; snub-nosed;  Charim, an Israelite:—Harim.

h2767.d: חׇרְמָה Chormâh, khor-maw'; from H2763; devoted;  Chormah, a place in Palestine:—Hormah.

h2768.d: חֶרְמוֹן Chermôwn, kher-mone'; from H2763; abrupt;  Chermon, a mount of Palestine:—Hermon.
h2768.r: From חָרַם (H2763)|English: destroy, utterly, devote, accursed, consecrate, forfeited, flat nose, utterly to make away, slay

h2771.d: חָרָן Chârân, kaw-rawn'; from H2787; parched;  Charan, the name of a man and also of a place:—Haran.
h2771.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h2771.r: From חָרַר (H2787)|English: burn, dried, angry, kindle

h2774.d: חַרְנֶפֶר Charnepher, khar-neh'fer; of uncertain derivation;  Charnepher, an Israelite:—Harnepher.

h2775.d: חֶרֶס chereç, kheh'-res; or (with a directive enclitic) חַרְסָה charçâh; from an unused root meaning to scrape; also perhaps from the mediating idea of H2777  the sun:—sun.
h2775.r: From an unused root meaning to scrape|

h2776.d: חֶרֶס Chereç, kheh'-res; the same as H2775; shining;  Cheres, a mountain in Palestine:—Heres.

h2778.d: חָרַף châraph, khaw-raf'; a primitive root; also denominative (from H2779)  to pull off, i.e. (by implication) to expose (as by stripping); specifically, to betroth (as if a surrender); figuratively, to carp at, i.e. defame; to spend the winter:—betroth, blaspheme, defy, jeopard, rail, reproach, upbraid.

h2779.d: חֹרֶף chôreph, kho'-ref; from H2778;  properly, the crop gathered, i.e. (by implication) the autumn (and winter) season; figuratively, ripeness of age:—cold, winter (-house), youth.
h2779.r: From חָרַף (H2778)|English: reproach, defy, betrothed, blasphemed, jeoparded, rail, upbraid, winter

h278.r: Probably the same as אֲחִי (H277)|English: Ahi

h2780.d: חָרֵף Chârêph, khaw-rafe'; from H2778; reproachful;  Chareph, an Israelite:—Hareph.
h2780.r: From חָרַף (H2778)|English: reproach, defy, betrothed, blasphemed, jeoparded, rail, upbraid, winter

h2781.d: חֶרְפָּה cherpâh, kher-paw'; from H2778;  contumely, disgrace, the pudenda:—rebuke, reproach(-fully), shame.
h2781.r: From חָרַף (H2778)|English: reproach, defy, betrothed, blasphemed, jeoparded, rail, upbraid, winter

h2787.d: חָרַר chârar, khaw-rar'; a primitive root;  to glow, i.e. literally (to melt, burn, dry up) or figuratively (to show or incite passion):—be angry, burn, dry, kindle.

h2789.d: חֶרֶשׂ cheres, kheh'-res; a collateral form mediating between H2775 and H2791;  a piece of pottery:—earth(-en), (pot-) sherd,   stone.

h279.d: אֲחִיאָם ʼĂchîyʼâm, akh-ee-awm'; from H251 and H517; brother of the mother (i.e. uncle);  Achiam, an Israelite:—Ahiam.
h279.r: From אָח (H251) and אֵם (H517)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2790.d: חָרַשׁ chârash, khaw-rash'; a primitive root;  to scratch, i.e. (by implication) to engrave, plough; hence (from the use of tools) to fabricate (of any material); figuratively, to devise (in a bad sense); hence (from the idea of secrecy) to be silent, to let alone; hence (by implication) to be deaf (as an accompaniment of dumbness):—× altogether, cease, conceal, be deaf, devise, ear, graven, imagine, leave off speaking, hold peace, plow(-er, man), be quiet, rest, practise secretly, keep silence, be silent, speak not a word, be still, hold tongue, worker.

h2791.d: חֶרֶשׁ cheresh, kheh'-resh; from H2790;  magical craft; also silence:—cunning, secretly.
h2791.r: From חָרַשׁ (H2790)|English: ...peace, plow, devise, keep ... silence, hold...tongue, altogether, plowman, cease, conceal, deaf, to ear, graven, imagine, misc

h2792.d: חֶרֶשׁ Cheresh, kheh'-resh; the same as H2791  Cheresh, a Levite:—Heresh.
h2792.r: The same as חֶרֶשׁ (H2791)|English: craftsmen, artificer, secretly

h2795.d: חֵרֵשׁ chêrêsh, khay-rashe'; from H2790;  deaf (whether literally or spiritual):—deaf.

h2796.d: חָרָשׁ chârâsh, khaw-rawsh'; from H2790;  a fabricator or any material:—artificer, (+) carpenter, craftsman, engraver, maker,   mason, skilful, (+) smith, worker, workman, such as wrought.
h2796.r: From חָרַשׁ (H2790)|English: ...peace, plow, devise, keep ... silence, hold...tongue, altogether, plowman, cease, conceal, deaf, to ear, graven, imagine, misc

h28.d: אֲבִידָע ʼĂbîydâʻ, ab-ee-daw'; from H1 and H3045; father of knowledge (i.e. knowing);  Abida, a son of Abraham by Keturah:—Abida, Abidah.
h28.r: From אָב (H1) and יָדַע (H3045)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h2805.d: חֵשֶׁב chêsheb, khay'-sheb; from H2803;  a belt or strap (as being interlaced):—curious girdle.
h2805.r: From חָשַׁב (H2803)|English: count, devise, think, imagine, cunning, reckon, purpose, esteem, account, impute, forecast, regard, workman, conceived, misc

h2806.r: From חָשַׁב (H2803) and דִּין (H1777)|English: count, devise, think, imagine, cunning, reckon, purpose, esteem, account, impute, forecast, regard, workman, conceived, misc

h2811.r: From חָשַׁב (H2803) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: count, devise, think, imagine, cunning, reckon, purpose, esteem, account, impute, forecast, regard, workman, conceived, misc

h2823.r: From חָשַׁךְ (H2821)|English: darken, dark, blacker, darkness, dim, hideth, variant

h2825.r: From חָשַׁךְ (H2821)|English: darken, dark, blacker, darkness, dim, hideth, variant

h2837.d: חֵשֶׁק chêsheq, khay'-shek; from H2836;  delight:—desire, pleasure.

h2842.d: חָשַׁשׁ châshash, khaw-shash'; by variation for H7179;  dry grass:—chaff.

h2844.d: חַת chath, khath; from H2865;  concretely, crushed; also afraid; abstractly, terror:—broken, dismayed, dread, fear.
h2844.r: From חָתַת (H2865)|English: dismayed, afraid, break in pieces, broken, break down, abolished, affrighted, amazed, chapt, confound, discouraged, go down, beaten down, scarest, terrify

h2847.r: From חָתַת (H2865)|English: dismayed, afraid, break in pieces, broken, break down, abolished, affrighted, amazed, chapt, confound, discouraged, go down, beaten down, scarest, terrify

h2850.d: חִתִּי Chittîy, khit-tee'; patronymically from H2845;  a Chittite, or descendant of Cheth:—Hittite, Hittities.

h2851.d: חִתִּית chittîyth, khit-teeth'; from H2865;  fear:—terror.
h2851.r: From חָתַת (H2865)|English: dismayed, afraid, break in pieces, broken, break down, abolished, affrighted, amazed, chapt, confound, discouraged, go down, beaten down, scarest, terrify

h2856.d: חָתַם châtham, khaw-tham'; a primitive root;  to close up; especially to seal:—make an end, mark, seal (up), stop.

h2857.d: חֲתַם chătham, khath-am'; (Aramaic) a root corresponding to H2856;  to seal:—seal.
h2857.r: A root corresponding to חָתַם (H2856)|English: seal, seal up, marked, stopped, variant

h2860.d: חָתָן châthân, khaw-thawn'; from H2859;  a relative by marriage (especially through the bride); figuratively, a circumcised child (as a species of religious espousal):—bridegroom, husband, son in law.

h2862.d: חָתַף châthaph, khaw-thaf'; a primitive root;  to clutch:—take away.

h2864.d: חָתַר châthar, khaw-thar'; a primitive root;  to force a passage, as by burglary; figuratively, with oars:—dig (through), row.

h2865.d: חָתַת châthath, khaw-thath'; a primitive root;  properly, to prostrate; hence, to break down, either (literally) by violence, or (figuratively) by confusion and fear:—abolish, affright, be (make) afraid, amaze, beat down, discourage, (cause to) dismay, go down, scare, terrify.

h2867.d: חֲתַת Chăthath, khath-ath'; the same as H2866;  Chathath, an Israelite:—cathath.

h2868.d: טְאֵב ṭᵉʼêb, teh-abe'; (Aramaic) a primitive root;  to rejoice:—be glad.

h2870.d: טָבְאֵל ṭâbᵉʼêl, taw-beh-ale'; from H2895 and H410; pleasing (to) God;  Tabeel, the name of a Syrian and of a Persian:—Tabeal, Tabeel.

h2871.d: טָבוּל ṭâbûwl, taw-bool'; passive participle of H2881;  properly, dyed, i.e. a turban (probably as of colored stuff):—dyed attire.
h2871.r: Pass. participle of טָבַל (H2881)|English: dip, plunge

h2873.d: טָבַח ṭâbach, taw-bakh'; a primitive root;  to slaughter (animals or men):—kill, (make) slaughter, slay.

h2874.d: טֶבַח ṭebach, teh'-bakh; from H2873;  properly, something slaughtered; hence, a beast (or meat, as butchered); abstractly butchery (or concretely, a place of slaughter):—× beast, slaughter, × slay, × sore.
h2874.r: From טָבַח (H2873)|English: kill, slaughter, slay, slain

h2875.d: טֶבַח Ṭebach, teh'-bakh; the same as H2874; massacre;  Tebach, the name of a Mesopotamian and of an Israelite:—Tebah.
h2875.r: The same as טֶבַח (H2874)|English: slaughter, slay, sore, beast

h2877.d: טַבָּח ṭabbâch, tab-bawkh'; (Aramaic) the same as H2876;  a lifeguardsman:—guard.
h2877.r: The same as טַבָּח (H2876)|English: guard, cook

h288.d: אֲחִימֶלֶךְ ʼĂchîymelek, akh-ee-meh'-lek; from H251 and H4428; brother of (the) king;  Achimelek, the name of an Israelite and of a Hittite:—Ahimelech.
h288.r: From אָח (H251) and מֶלֶךְ (H4428)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2882.d: טְבַלְיָהוּ Ṭᵉbalyâhûw, teb-al-yaw'-hoo; from H2881 and H3050; Jah has dipped;  Tebaljah, an Israelite:—Tebaliah.
h2882.r: From טָבַל (H2881) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: dip, plunge

h2883.d: טָבַע ṭâbaʻ, taw-bah'; a primitive root;  to sink:—drown, fasten, settle, sink.

h2885.d: טַבַּעַת ṭabbaʻath, tab-bah'-ath; from H2883;  properly, a seal (as sunk into the wax), i.e. signet (for sealing); hence (generally) a ring of any kind:—ring.
h2885.r: From טָבַע (H2883)|English: sink, drown, settle, fasten

h2887.d: טֵבֶת Ṭêbeth, tay'-beth; probably of foreign derivation;  Tebeth, the tenth Hebrew month:—Tebeth.

h2889.d: טָהוֹר ṭâhôwr, taw-hore'; or טָהֹר ṭâhôr; from H2891;  pure (in a physical, chemical, ceremonial or moral sense):—clean, fair, pure(-ness).
h2889.r: From טָהֵר (H2891)|English: clean, purify, purge, pure, purifier

h289.d: אֲחִימַן ʼĂchîyman, akh-ee-man'; or אֲחִימָן ʼĂchîymân ; from H251 and H4480; brother of a portion (i.e. gift);  Achiman, the name of an Anakite and of an Israelite:—Ahiman.
h289.r: From אָח (H251) and מִן (H4480)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2891.d: טָהֵר ṭâhêr, taw-hare'; a primitive root; properly, to be bright; i.e. (by implication)  to be pure (physical sound, clear, unadulterated; Levitically, uncontaminated; morally, innocent or holy):—be (make, make self, pronounce) clean, cleanse (self), purge, purify(-ier, self).

h2895.d: טוֹב ṭôwb, tobe; a primitive root,  to be (transitively, do or make) good (or well) in the widest sense:—be (do) better, cheer, be (do, seem) good, (make) goodly, × please, (be, do, go, play) well.

h2896.d: טוֹב ṭôwb, tobe; from H2895;  good (as an adjective) in the widest sense; used likewise as a noun, both in the masculine and the feminine, the singular and the plural (good, a good or good thing, a good man or woman; the good, goods or good things, good men or women), also as an adverb (well):—beautiful, best, better, bountiful, cheerful, at ease, × fair (word), (be in) favour, fine, glad, good (deed, -lier, -liest, -ly, -ness, -s), graciously, joyful, kindly, kindness, liketh (best), loving, merry, × most, pleasant,   pleaseth, pleasure, precious, prosperity, ready, sweet, wealth, welfare, (be) well(-favoured).
h2896.r: From טוֹב (H2895)|English: ...well, good, please, goodly, better, cheer, comely, do, pleased

h2898.d: טוּב ṭûwb, toob; from H2895;  good (as a noun), in the widest sense, especially goodness (superlative concretely, the best), beauty, gladness, welfare:—fair, gladness, good(-ness, thing, -s), joy, go well with.
h2898.r: From טוֹב (H2895)|English: ...well, good, please, goodly, better, cheer, comely, do, pleased

h29.d: אֲבִיָּה ʼĂbîyâh, ab-ee-yaw'; or prolonged אֲבִיָּהוּ ʼĂbîyâhûw ; from H1 and H3050; father (i.e. worshipper) of Jah;  Abijah, the name of several Israelite men and two Israelitesses:—Abiah, Abijah.
h29.r: From אָב (H1) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h290.d: אֲחִימַעַץ ʼĂchîymaʻats, akh-ee-mah'-ats; from H251 and the equivalent of H4619; brother of anger;  Achimaats, the name of three Israelites:—Ahimaaz.
h290.r: From אָח (H251) and the equivalent of מַעַץ (H4619)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2900.d: טוֹבִיָּה Ṭôwbîyâh, to-bee-yaw'; or טוֹבִיָּהוּ Ṭôwbîyâhûw; from H2896 and H3050; goodness of Jehovah;  Tobijah, the name of three Israelites and of one Samaritan:—Tobiah, Tobijah.
h2900.r: From טוֹב (H2896) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: good, better, well, goodness, goodly, best, merry, fair, prosperity, precious, fine, wealth, beautiful, fairer, favour, glad, misc

h2901.d: טָוָה ṭâvâh, taw-vaw'; a primitive root;  to spin:—spin.

h2904.d: טוּל ṭûwl, tool; a primitive root;  to pitch over or reel; hence (transitively) to cast down or out:—carry away, (utterly) cast (down, forth, out), send out.

h2905.d: טוּר ṭûwr, toor; from an unused root meaning to range in a regular manner;  a row; hence, a wall:—row.
h2905.r: From an unused root meaning to range in a regular manner|

h2906.d: טוּר ṭûwr, toor; (Aramaic) corresponding to H6697;  a rock or hill:—mountain.
h2906.r: Corresponding to צוּר (H6697)|English: rock, strength, sharp, God, beauty, edge, stones, mighty One, strong

h2908.d: טְוָת ṭᵉvâth, tev-awth'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H2901;  hunger (as twisting):—fasting.
h2908.r: From a root corresponding to טָוָה (H2901)|English: spin

h2912.d: טָחַן ṭâchan, taw-khan'; a primitive root;  to grind meal; hence, to be a concubine (that being their employment):—grind(-er).

h2914.d: טְחֹר ṭᵉchôr, tekh-ore'; from an unused root meaning to burn;  a boil or ulcer (from the inflammation), especially a tumor in the anus or pudenda (the piles):—emerod.
h2914.r: From an unused root meaning to burn|

h2916.d: טִיט ṭîyṭ, teet; from an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky (rather perhaps a demonstrative); from H2894, through the idea of dirt to be swept away);  mud or clay; figuratively, calamity:—clay, dirt, mire.
h2916.r: From an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky [rath perb. a demon. From טוּא (H2894), through the idea of dirt to be swept away]|English: sweep

h2919.d: טַל ṭal, tal; from H2926;  dew (as covering vegetation):—dew.

h292.d: אֲחִינָדָב ʼĂchîynâdâb, akh-ee-naw-dawb'; from H251 and H5068; brother of liberality;  Achinadab, an Israelite:—Ahinadab.
h292.r: From אָח (H251) and נָדַב (H5068)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2924.d: טָלֶה ṭâleh, taw-leh'; by variation for H2922;  a lamb:—lamb.

h2927.d: טְלַל ṭᵉlal, tel-al'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H2926;  to cover with shade:—have a shadow.

h2928.d: טֶלֶם Ṭelem, teh'-lem; from an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently; oppression;  Telem, the name of a place in Idumaea, also of a temple doorkeeper:—Telem.
h2928.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h2928.r: From an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently|

h2929.d: טַלְמוֹן Ṭalmôwn, tal-mone'; from the same as H2728; oppressive;  Talmon, a temple doorkeeper:—Talmon.
h2929.r: From the same as חַרְגֹּל (H2728)|English: beetle

h293.d: אֲחִינֹעַם ʼĂchîynôʻam, akh-ee-no'-am; from H251 and H5278; brother of pleasantness;  Achinoam, the name of two Israelitesses:—Ahinoam.
h293.r: From אָח (H251) and נֹעַם (H5278)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2930.d: טָמֵא ṭâmêʼ, taw-may'; a primitive root;  to be foul, especially in a ceremial or moral sense (contaminated):—defile (self), pollute (self), be (make, make self, pronounce) unclean, × utterly.

h2931.d: טָמֵא ṭâmêʼ, taw-may'; from H2930;  foul in a religious sense:—defiled,   infamous, polluted(-tion), unclean.
h2931.r: From טָמֵא (H2930)|English: unclean, defile, pollute, uncleanness, utterly

h2932.d: טֻמְאָה ṭumʼâh, toom-aw'; from H2930;  religious impurity:—filthiness, unclean(-ness).
h2932.r: From טָמֵא (H2930)|English: unclean, defile, pollute, uncleanness, utterly

h2934.d: טָמַן ṭâman, taw-man'; a primitive root;  to hide (by covering over):—hide, lay privily, in secret.

h2938.d: טָעַם ṭâʻam, taw-am'; a primitive root;  to taste; figuratively, to perceive:—× but, perceive, taste.

h2940.d: טַעַם ṭaʻam, tah'-am; from H2938;  properly, a taste, i.e. (figuratively) perception; by implication, intelligence; transitively, a mandate:—advice, behaviour, decree, discretion, judgment, reason, taste, understanding.

h2942.d: טְעֵם ṭᵉʻêm, teh-ame'; (Aramaic) from H2939, and equivalent to H2941;  properly, flavor; figuratively, judgment (both subjective and objective); hence, account (both subjectively and objectively):—  chancellor,   command, commandment, decree,   regard, taste, wisdom.
h2942.r: From טְעַם (H2939), and equivalent to טַעַם (H2941)|English: make to eat, feed

h2943.d: טָעַן ṭâʻan, taw-an'; a primitive root;  to load a beast:—lade.

h2945.d: טַף ṭaph, taf; from H2952 (perhaps referring to the tripping gait of children);  a family (mostly used collectively in the singular):—(little) children (ones), families.
h2945.r: From טָפַף (H2952) (perhaps referring to the tripping gait of children)|English: mincing

h2946.d: טָפַח ṭâphach, taw-fakh'; a primitive root; or perhaps a denominative from H2947, from dandling on the palms  to flatten out or extend (as a tent); figuratively, to nurse a child (as promotive of growth);:—span, swaddle.

h2948.d: טֹפַח ṭôphach, to'-fakh; from H2946  (the same as 2947):—hand-breadth (broad).
h2948.r: From טָפַח (H2946) (the same as טֶפַח (H2947))|English: span, swaddle

h295.d: אֲחִיעֶזֶר ʼĂchîyʻezer, akh-ee-eh'-zer; from H251 and H5828; brother of help;  Achiezer, the name of two Israelites:—Ahiezer.
h295.r: From אָח (H251) and עֵזֶר (H5828)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2958.d: טְרוֹם ṭᵉrôwm, ter-ome'; a variation of H2962;  not yet:—before.
h2958.r: A variation of טֶרֶם (H2962)|English: before, ere, not yet, neither

h296.d: אֲחִיקָם ʼĂchîyqâm, akh-ee-kawm'; from H251 and H6965; brother of rising (i.e. high);  Achikam, an Israelite:—Ahikam.
h296.r: From אָח (H251) and קוּם (H6965)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2962.d: טֶרֶם ṭerem, teh'-rem; from an unused root apparently meaning to interrupt or suspend;  properly, non-occurrence; used adverbially, not yet or before:—before, ere, not yet.
h2962.r: From an unused root apparently meaning to interrupt or suspend|

h2963.d: טָרַף ṭâraph, taw-raf'; a primitive root;  to pluck off or pull to pieces; causatively to supply with food (as in morsels):—catch, × without doubt, feed, ravin, rend in pieces, × surely, tear (in pieces).

h2964.d: טֶרֶף ṭereph, teh'-ref; from H2963;  something torn, i.e. a fragment, e.g. a fresh leaf, prey, food:—leaf, meat, prey, spoil.
h2964.r: From טָרַף (H2963)|English: tear, tear in pieces, ravening, catch, doubt, feed, rent in pieces, prey, ravin, surely, not translated, torn

h2966.d: טְרֵפָה ṭᵉrêphâh, ter-ay-faw'; feminine (collectively) of H2964;  prey, i.e. flocks devoured by animals:—ravin, (that which was) torn (of beasts, in pieces).
h2966.r: From (collectively) טֶרֶף (H2964)|English: prey, meat, leaves, spoil

h2970.d: יַאֲזַנְיָה Yaʼăzanyâh, yah-az-an-yaw'; or יַאֲזַנְיָהוּ Yaʼăzanyâhûw; from H238 and H3050; heard of Jah;  Jaazanjah, the name of four Israelites:—Jaazaniah. Compare H3153.
h2970.r: From אָזַן (H238) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: give ear, hearken, hear, perceived by the ear

h2971.d: יָאִיר Yâʼîyr, yaw-ere'; from H215; enlightener;  Jair, the name of four Israelites:—Jair.
h2971.r: From אוֹר (H215)|English: light, shine, enlighten, break of day, fire, give, glorious, kindle

h2973.d: יָאַל yâʼal, yaw-al'; a primitive root;  properly, to be slack, i.e. (figuratively) to be foolish:—dote, be (become, do) foolish(-ly).

h2974.d: יָאַל yâʼal, yaw-al'; a primitive root (probably rather the same as H2973 through the idea of mental weakness);  properly, to yield, especially assent; hence (positive) to undertake as an act of volition:—assay, begin, be content, please, take upon, × willingly, would.
h2974.r: A primitive root [probably rather the same as יָאַל (H2973) through the idea of mental weakness]|English: foolishly, fool, foolish, dote

h2977.d: יֹאשִׁיָּה Yôʼshîyâh, yo-shee-yaw'; or יֹאשִׁיָּהוּ Yôʼshîyâhûw; from the same root as H803 and H3050; founded of Jah;  Joshijah, the name of two Israelites:—Josiah.
h2977.r: From the same root as אָשְׁיָה (H803) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: foundation

h2979.d: יְאָתְרַי yᵉʼâthᵉray, yeh-aw-ther-ah'ee; from the same as H871; stepping;  Jeatherai, an Israelite:—Jeaterai.
h2979.r: From the same as אֲתָרִים (H871)|English: spies

h2981.d: יְבוּל yᵉbûwl, yeb-ool'; from H2986;  produce, i.e. a crop or (figuratively) wealth:—fruit, increase.
h2981.r: From יָבַל (H2986)|English: bring, carry, bring forth, lead forth, lead

h2982.d: יְבוּס Yᵉbûwç, yeb-oos'; from H947; trodden, i.e. threshing-place;  Jebus, the original name of Jerusalem:—Jebus.

h2984.d: יִבְחַר Yibchar, yib-khar'; from H977; choice;  Jibchar, an Israelite:—Ibhar.
h2984.r: From בָּחַר (H977)|English: choose, chosen, choice, choose...out, acceptable, appoint, excellent, chosen men, rather, require, not translated

h2985.d: יָבִין Yâbîyn, yaw-bene'; from H995; intelligent;  Jabin, the name of two Canaanitish kings:—Jabin.
h2985.r: From בִּין (H995)|English: understand, understanding, consider, prudent, perceive, regard, discern, instruct, misc.

h2986.d: יָבַל yâbal, yaw-bal'; a primitive root;  properly, to flow; causatively, to bring (especially with pomp):—bring (forth), carry, lead (forth).

h2988.d: יָבָל yâbâl, yaw-bawl'; from H2986;  a stream:—(water-) course, stream.
h2988.r: From יָבַל (H2986)|English: bring, carry, bring forth, lead forth, lead

h2989.d: יָבָל Yâbâl, yaw-bawl'; the same as H2988;  Jabal, an antediluvian:—Jabal.
h2989.r: The same as יָבָל (H2988)|English: stream, course

h299.d: אֲחִירַע ʼĂchîyraʻ, akh-ee-rah'; from H251 and H7451; brother of wrong;  Achira, an Israelite:—Ahira.
h299.r: From אָח (H251) and רַע (H7451)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h2999.d: יַבֹּק Yabbôq, yab-boke'; probably from H1238; pouring forth;  Jabbok, a river east of the Jordan:—Jabbok.
h2999.r: Probably from בָּקַק (H1238)|English: empty, make void, emptiers, fail, utterly (inf for emphasis

h30.d: אֲבִיהוּא ʼĂbîyhûwʼ, ab-ee-hoo'; from H1 and H1931; father (i.e. worshipper) of Him (i.e. God);  Abihu, a son of Aaron:—Abihu.
h30.r: From אָב (H1) and הוּא (H1931)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h3001.d: יָבֵשׁ yâbêsh, yaw-bashe'; a primitive root;  to be ashamed, confused or disappointed; also (as failing) to dry up (as water) or wither (as herbage):—be ashamed, clean, be confounded, (make) dry (up), (do) shame(-fully), × utterly, wither (away).

h3002.d: יָבֵשׁ yâbêsh, yaw-bashe'; from H3001;  dry:—dried (away), dry.
h3002.r: From יָבֵשׁ (H3001)|English: dry up, withered, confounded, ashamed, dry, wither away, clean, shamed, shamefully, utterly

h3003.d: יָבֵשׁ Yâbêsh, yaw-bashe'; the same as H3002 (also יָבֵישׁ Yâbêysh; often with the addition of H1568, i.e. Jabesh of Gilad);  Jobesh, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine:—Jobesh (-Gilead).
h3003.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h3003.r: The same as יָבֵשׁ (H3002) (also Yabeysh {yaw-bashe'})|English: dry

h3004.d: יַבָּשָׁה yabbâshâh, yab-baw-shaw'; from H3001;  dry ground:—dry (ground, land).
h3004.r: From יָבֵשׁ (H3001)|English: dry up, withered, confounded, ashamed, dry, wither away, clean, shamed, shamefully, utterly

h3005.d: יִבְשָׂם Yibsâm, yib-sawm'; from the same as H1314; fragrant;  Jibsam, an Israelite:—Jibsam.
h3005.r: From the same as בֶּשֶׂם (H1314)|English: spice, sweet odours, sweet, sweet smell

h3006.d: יַבֶּשֶׁת yabbesheth, yab-beh'-sheth; a variation of H3004;  dry ground:—dry land.
h3006.r: A variation of יַבָּשָׁה (H3004)|English: dry, dry land, dry ground, land

h3008.d: יִגְאָל Yigʼâl, yig-awl'; from H1350; avenger;  Jigal, the name of three Israelites:—Igal, Igeal.
h3008.r: From גָּאַל (H1350)|English: redeem, redeemer, kinsman, revenger, avenger, ransom, at all, deliver, kinsfolks, kinsman's part, purchase, stain, wise

h3013.d: יָגָה yâgâh, yaw-gaw'; a primitive root;  to grieve:—afflict, cause grief, grieve, sorrowful, vex.

h3015.d: יָגוֹן yâgôwn, yaw-gohn'; from H3013;  affliction:—grief, sorrow.
h3015.r: From יָגָה (H3013)|English: afflict, grieve, cause grief, sorrowful, vex

h302.d: אֲחִיתֹפֶל ʼĂchîythôphel, akh-ee-tho'-fel; from H251 and H8602; brother of folly;  Achithophel, an Israelite:—Ahithophel.
h302.r: From אָח (H251) and תָּפֵל (H8602)|English: brethren, brother, another, brotherly, kindred, like, another, other

h3021.d: יָגַע yâgaʻ, yaw-gah'; a primitive root;  properly, to gasp; hence, to be exhausted, to tire, to toil:—faint, (make to) labour, (be) weary.

h3028.d: יַד yad, yad; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3027:—hand, power.

h3384.d: יָרָה yârâh, yaw-raw'; or (2 Chronicles 26:15) יָרָא yârâʼ; a primitive root;  properly, to flow as water (i.e. to rain); transitively, to lay or throw (especially an arrow, i.e. to shoot); figuratively, to point out (as if by aiming the finger), to teach:—(+) archer, cast, direct, inform, instruct, lay, shew, shoot, teach(-er,-ing), through.

h3387.d: יָרוֹק yârôwq, yaw-roke'; from H3417;  green, i.e. an herb:—green thing.

h3389.d: יְרוּשָׁלִַ͏ם Yᵉrûwshâlaim, yer-oo-shaw-lah'-im; rarely יְרוּשָׁלַיִם Yᵉrûwshâlayim; a dual (in allusion to its two main hills (the true pointing, at least of the former reading, seems to be that of H3390)); probably from (the passive participle of) H3384 and H7999; founded peaceful;  Jerushalaim or Jerushalem, the capital city of Palestine:—Jerusalem.
h3389.r: A dual (in allusion to its two main hills [the true pointing, at least of the former reading, seems to be that of יְרוּשְׁלֵם (H3390)]), probably from (the passive participle of) יָרָה (H3384) and שָׁלַם (H7999)|English: Jerusalem

h339.d: אִי ʼîy, ee; from H183;  properly, a habitable spot (as desirable); dry land, a coast, an island:—country, isle, island.

h3390.d: יְרוּשָׁלֵם Yᵉrûwshâlêm, yer-oo-shaw-lame' (Chaldee) corresponding to H3389:—Jerusalem.

h3391.d: יֶרַח yerach, yeh'-rakh; from an unused root of uncertain significance; a lunation, i.e. month:—month, moon.

h3392.d: יֶרַח Yerach, yeh'-rakh; the same as H3391;  Jerach, an Arabian patriarch:—Jerah.

h3393.d: יְרַח yᵉrach, yeh-rakh'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3391;  a month:—month.

h3426.d: יֵשׁ yêsh, yaysh; perhaps from an unused root meaning to stand out, or exist; entity; used adverbially or as a copula for the substantive verb (H1961);  there is or are (or any other form of the verb to be, as may suit the connection):—(there) are, (he, it, shall, there, there may, there shall, there should) be, thou do, had, hast, (which) hath, (I, shalt, that) have, (he, it, there) is, substance, it (there) was, (there) were, ye will, thou wilt, wouldest.
h3426.r: Perhaps from an unused root meaning to stand out, or exist|
