h3485.d: יִשָּׂשכָר Yissâˢkâr, yis-saw-kawr'; (strictly yis-saws-kawr'); from H5375 and H7939; he will bring a reward;  Jissaskar, a son of Jacob:—Issachar.
h3485.s: proper collective noun, proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h3485.r: From נָשָׂא (H5375) and שָׂכָר (H7939)|English: (bare, lift, etc...) up, bear, take, bare, carry, (take, carry)..away, borne, armourbearer, forgive, accept, exalt, regard, obtained, respect

h3487.d: יַת yath, yath; (Aramaic) corresponding to H853;  a sign of the object of a verb:—  whom.

h3488.d: יְתִב yᵉthib, yeth-eeb'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3427;  to sit or dwell:—dwell, (be) set, sit.
h3488.r: Corresponding to יָשַׁב (H3427)|English: dwell, inhabitant, sit, abide, inhabit, down, remain, in, tarry, set, continue, place, still, taken, misc

h3489.d: יָתֵד yâthêd, yaw-thade'; from an unused root meaning to pin through or fast;  a peg:—nail, paddle, pin, stake.
h3489.r: From an unused root meaning to pin through or fast|

h349.d: אֵיךְ ʼêyk, ake; also אֵיכָה ʼêykâh ; and אֵיכָכָה ʼêykâkâh ; prolonged from H335;  how? or how!; also where:—how, what.
h349.r: Prolonged from אַי (H335)|English: where, what, whence

h3490.d: יָתוֹם yâthôwm, yaw-thome'; from an unused root meaning to be lonely;  a bereaved person:—fatherless (child), orphan.
h3490.r: From an unused root meaning to be lonely|

h3492.d: יַתִּיר Yattîyr, yat-teer'; from H3498; redundant;  Jattir, a place in Palestine:—Jattir.
h3492.r: From יָתַר (H3498)|English: leave, remain, rest, remainder, remnant, reserved, residue, plenteous, behind, excel, much, preserve

h3493.d: יַתִּיר yattîyr, yat-teer'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3492;  preeminent; as an adverb, very:—exceeding(-ly), excellent.

h3496.d: יַתְנִיאֵל Yathnîyʼêl, yath-nee-ale'; from an unused root meaning to endure, and H410; continued of God;  Jathniel, an Israelite:—Jathniel.
h3496.r: From an unused root meaning to endure, and אֵל (H410)|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

h3498.d: יָתַר yâthar, yaw-thar'; a primitive root;  to jut over or exceed; by implication, to excel; (intransitively) to remain or be left; causatively to leave, cause to abound, preserve:—excel, leave (a remnant), left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve, (be, let) remain(-der, -ing, -nant), reserve, residue, rest.

h3499.d: יֶתֶר yether, yeh'-ther; from H3498;  properly, an overhanging, i.e. (by implication) an excess, superiority, remainder; also a small rope (as hanging free):—  abundant, cord, exceeding, excellancy(-ent), what they leave, that hath left, plentifully, remnant, residue, rest, string, with.
h3499.r: From יָתַר (H3498)|English: leave, remain, rest, remainder, remnant, reserved, residue, plenteous, behind, excel, much, preserve

h350.d: אִי־כָבוֹד ʼÎy-kâbôwd, ee-kaw-bode'; from H336 and H3519; (there is) no glory, i.e. inglorious;  Ikabod, a son of Phineas:—I-chabod.

h3500.d: יֶתֶר Yether, yeh'-ther; the same as H3499;  Jether, the name of five or six Israelites and of one Midianite:—Jether, Jethro. Compare H3503.
h3500.r: The same as יֶתֶר (H3499)|English: rest, remnant, residue, leave, excellency, withs, cord, exceeding, excellent, more, plentifully, string

h3503.d: יִתְרוֹ Yithrôw, yith-ro'; from H3499 with pron. suffix; his excellence;  Jethro, Moses' father-in-law:—Jethro. Compare H3500.
h3503.r: From יֶתֶר (H3499) with pron. suffix|English: rest, remnant, residue, leave, excellency, withs, cord, exceeding, excellent, more, plentifully, string

h3506.d: יִתְרָן Yithrân, yith-rawn'; from H3498; excellent;  Jithran, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite:—Ithran.
h3506.r: From יָתַר (H3498)|English: leave, remain, rest, remainder, remnant, reserved, residue, plenteous, behind, excel, much, preserve

h3507.d: יִתְרְעָם Yithrᵉʻâm, yith-reh-awm'; from H3499 and H5971; excellence of people;  Jithream, a son of David:—Ithream.
h3507.r: From יֶתֶר (H3499) and עַם (H5971)|English: rest, remnant, residue, leave, excellency, withs, cord, exceeding, excellent, more, plentifully, string

h3509.d: יְתֵת Yᵉthêth, yeh-thayth'; of uncertain derivation;  Jetheth, an Edomite:—Jetheth.

h351.d: אֵיכֹה ʼêykôh, ay-ko; probably a variation for H349, but not as an interogative;  where:—where.
h351.r: Probably a variation for אֵיךְ (H349), but not as an interrogative|English: how, what, where

h3511.d: כְּאֵב kᵉʼêb, keh-abe'; from H3510;  suffering (physical or mental), adversity:—grief, pain, sorrow.
h3511.r: From כָּאַב (H3510)|English: sorrowful, sore, have pain, made sad, mar, make sore, grieving

h3513.d: כָּבַד kâbad, kaw-bad'; or כָּבֵד kâbêd; a primitive root;  to be heavy, i.e. in a bad sense (burdensome, severe, dull) or in a good sense (numerous, rich, honorable); causatively, to make weighty (in the same two senses):—abounding with, more grievously afflict, boast, be chargeable, × be dim, glorify, be (make) glorious (things), glory, (very) great, be grievous, harden, be (make) heavy, be heavier, lay heavily, (bring to, come to, do, get, be had in) honour (self), (be) honourable (man), lade, × more be laid, make self many, nobles, prevail, promote (to honour), be rich, be (go) sore, stop.

h3515.d: כָּבֵד kâbêd, kaw-bade'; from H3513;  heavy; figuratively in a good sense (numerous) or in a bad sense (severe, difficult, stupid):—(so) great, grievous, hard(-ened), (too) heavy(-ier), laden, much, slow, sore, thick.
h3515.r: From כָּבַד (H3513)|English: honour, glorify, honourable, heavy, harden, glorious, sore, made heavy, chargeable, great, many, heavier, promote, misc

h3518.d: כָּבָה kâbâh, kaw-baw'; a primitive root;  to expire or (causatively) to extinguish (fire, light, anger):—go (put) out, quench.

h3519.d: כָּבוֹד kâbôwd, kaw-bode'; rarely כָּבֹד kâbôd; from H3513;  properly, weight, but only figuratively in a good sense, splendor or copiousness:—glorious(-ly), glory, honour(-able).
h3519.r: From כָּבַד (H3513)|English: honour, glorify, honourable, heavy, harden, glorious, sore, made heavy, chargeable, great, many, heavier, promote, misc

h352.d: אַיִל ʼayil, ah'-yil; from the same as H193;  properly, strength; hence, anything strong; specifically a chief (politically); also a ram (from his strength); a pilaster (as a strong support); an oak or other strong tree:—mighty (man), lintel, oak, post, ram, tree.
h352.r: From the same as אוּל (H193)|English: mighty, strength

h3524.d: כַּבִּיר kabbîyr, kab-beer'; from H3527;  vast, whether in extent (figuratively, of power, mighty; of time, aged), or in number, many:—  feeble, mighty, most, much, strong, valiant.

h3526.d: כָּבַס kâbaç, kaw-bas'; a primitive root;  to trample; hence, to wash (properly, by stamping with the feet), whether literal (including the fulling process) or figurative:—fuller, wash(-ing).

h3528.d: כְּבָר kᵉbâr, keb-awr'; from H3527;  properly, extent of time, i.e. a great while; hence, long ago, formerly, hitherto:—already, (seeing that which), now.

h3529.d: כְּבָר Kᵉbâr, keb-awr'; the same as H3528; length;  Kebar, a river of Mesopotamia:—Chebar. Compare H2249.
h3529.r: The same as כְּבָר (H3528)|English: already, now

h353.d: אֱיָל ʼĕyâl, eh-yawl'; a variation of H352;  strength:—strength.
h353.r: A variation of אַיִל (H352)|English: ram(s), post(s), mighty (men), trees, lintel, oaks

h3532.d: כֶּבֶשׂ kebes, keh-bes'; from an unused root meaning to dominate;  a ram (just old enough to butt):—lamb, sheep.
h3532.r: From an unused root meaning to dominate|

h3533.d: כָּבַשׁ kâbash, kaw-bash'; a primitive root;  to tread down; hence, negatively, to disregard; positively, to conquer, subjugate, violate:—bring into bondage, force, keep under, subdue, bring into subjection.

h3535.d: כִּבְשָׂה kibsâh, kib-saw'; or כַּבְשָׂה kabsâh; feminine of H3532;  a ewe:—(ewe) lamb.

h3538.d: כְּדַב kᵉdab, ked-ab'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H3576;  false:—lying.
h3538.r: From a root corresponding to כָּזַב (H3576)|English: lie, liar, vain, fail

h354.d: אַיָּל ʼayâl, ah-yawl'; an intensive form of H352 (in the sense of ram);  a stag or male deer:—hart.
h354.r: An intensive form of אַיִל (H352) (in the sense of ram)|English: ram(s), post(s), mighty (men), trees, lintel, oaks

h3540.d: כְּדׇרְלָעֹמֶר Kᵉdorlâʻômer, ked-or-law-o'-mer; of foreign origin;  Kedorlaomer, an early Persian king:—Chedorlaomer.

h3541.d: כֹּה kôh, ko; from the prefix k and H1931;  properly, like this, i.e. by implication, (of manner) thus (or so); also (of place) here (or hither); or (of time) now:—also, here,   hitherto, like, on the other side, so (and much), such, on that manner, (on) this (manner, side, way, way and that way),   mean while, yonder.
h3541.r: From the prefix k and הוּא (H1931)|English: that, him, same, this, he, which, who, such, wherein

h3543.d: כָּהָה kâhâh, kaw-haw'; a primitive root;  to be weak, i.e. (figuratively) to despond (causatively, rebuke), or (of light, the eye) to grow dull:—darken, be dim, fail, faint, restrain, × utterly.

h3547.d: כָּהַן kâhan, kaw-han'; a primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services; but used only as denominative from H3548;  to officiate as a priest; figuratively, to put on regalia:—deck, be (do the office of a, execute the, minister in the) priest('s office).
h3547.r: A primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services|

h3548.d: כֹּהֵן kôhên, ko-hane'; active participle of H3547;  literally one officiating, a priest; also (by courtesy) an acting priest (although a layman):—chief ruler, × own, priest, prince, principal officer.
h3548.r: Active participle of כָּהַן (H3547)|English: priest's office, decketh, office of a priest, priest

h3550.d: כְּהֻנָּה kᵉhunnâh, keh-hoon-naw'; from H3547;  priesthood:—priesthood, priest's office.
h3550.r: From כָּהַן (H3547)|English: priest's office, decketh, office of a priest, priest

h3553.d: כּוֹבַע kôwbaʻ, ko'-bah; from an unused root meaning to be high or rounded;  a helmet (as arched):—helmet. Compare H6959.
h3553.r: From an unused root meaning to be high or rounded|

h3555.d: כְּוִיָּה kᵉvîyâh, kev-ee-yaw'; from H3554;  a branding:—burning.

h3556.d: כּוֹכָב kôwkâb, ko-kawb'; probably from the same as H3522 (in the sense of rolling) or H3554 (in the sense of blazing);  a star (as round or as shining); figuratively, a prince:—star(-gazer).
h3556.r: Probably from the same as כַּבּוֹן (H3522) (in the sense of rolling) or כָּוָה (H3554) (in the sense of blazing)|English: Cabbon

h3557.d: כּוּל kûwl, kool; a primitive root;  properly, to keep in; hence, to measure; figuratively, to maintain (in various senses):—(be able to, can) abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide, hold(-ing in), nourish(-er), be present, make provision, receive, sustain, provide sustenance (victuals).

h3558.d: כּוּמָז kûwmâz, koo-mawz'; from an unused root meaning to store away;  a jewel (probably gold beads):—tablet.
h3558.r: From an unused root meaning to store away|

h3559.d: כּוּן kûwn, koon; a primitive root;  properly, to be erect (i.e. stand perpendicular); hence (causatively) to set up, in a great variety of applications, whether literal (establish, fix, prepare, apply), or figurative (appoint, render sure, proper or prosperous):—certain(-ty), confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted, be fixed, frame, be meet, ordain, order, perfect, (make) preparation, prepare (self), provide, make provision, (be, make) ready, right, set (aright, fast, forth), be stable, (e-) stablish, stand, tarry, × very deed.

h3561.d: כַּוָּן kavvân, kav-vawn'; from H3559;  something prepared, i.e. a sacrificial wafer:—cake.
h3561.r: From כּוּן (H3559)|English: prepare, establish, ready, stablish, provide, right, fixed, set, direct, order, fashion, variant, certain, confirmed, firm, preparation, misc

h3562.d: כּוֹנַנְיָהוּ Kôwnanyâhûw, ko-nan-yaw'-hoo; from H3559 and H3050; Jah has sustained;  Conanjah, the name of two Israelites:—Conaniah, Cononiah. Compare H3663.
h3562.r: From כּוּן (H3559) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: prepare, establish, ready, stablish, provide, right, fixed, set, direct, order, fashion, variant, certain, confirmed, firm, preparation, misc

h3563.d: כּוֹס kôwç, koce; from an unused root meaning to hold together;  a cup (as a container), often figuratively, a lot (as if a potion); also some unclean bird, probably an owl (perhaps from the cup-like cavity of its eye):—cup, (small) owl. Compare H3599.
h3563.r: From an unused root meaning to hold together|

h3564.d: כּוּר kûwr, koor; from an unused root meaning properly, to dig through;  a pot or furnace (as if excavated):—furnace. Compare H3600.
h3564.r: From an unused root meaning properly, to dig through|

h3566.d: כּוֹרֶשׁ Kôwresh, ko'-resh; or (Ezra 1:1-2 (last time)) כֹּרֶשׁ Kôresh; from the Persian;  Koresh (or Cyrus), the Persian king:—Cyrus.

h3567.d: כּוֹרֶשׁ Kôwresh, ko'-resh; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3566:—Cyrus.

h3568.d: כּוּשׁ Kûwsh, koosh; probably of foreign origin;  Cush (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite:—Chush, Cush, Ethiopia.
h3568.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h357.d: אַיָּלוֹן ʼAyâlôwn, ah-yaw-lone'; from H354; deer-field;  Ajalon, the name of five places in Palestine:—Aijalon, Ajalon.

h3573.d: כּוּשַׁן רִשְׁעָתַיִם Kûwshan Rishʻâthayim, koo-shan' rish-awthah'-yim; apparently from H3572 and the dual of H7564; Cushan of double wickedness;  Cushan-Rishathajim, a Mesopotamian king:—Chushan-rishathayim.
h3573.r: Apparently from כּוּשָׁן (H3572) and the dual of רִשְׁעָה (H7564)|English: Cushan

h3576.d: כָּזַב kâzab, kaw-zab'; a primitive root;  to lie (i.e. deceive), literally or figuratively:—fail, (be found a, make a) liar, lie, lying, be in vain.

h3577.d: כָּזָב kâzâb, kaw-zawb'; from H3576;  falsehood; literally (untruth) or figuratively (idol):—deceitful, false, leasing,   liar, lie, lying.
h3577.r: From כָּזַב (H3576)|English: lie, liar, vain, fail

h3581.d: כֹּחַ kôach, ko'-akh; or (Daniel 11:6) כּוֹחַ kôwach; from an unused root meaning to be firm;  vigor, literally (force, in a good or a bad sense) or figuratively (capacity, means, produce); also (from its hardiness) a large lizard:—ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, power(-ful), strength, substance, wealth.
h3581.r: From an unused root meaning to be firm|

h3582.d: כָּחַד kâchad, kaw-khad'; a primitive root;  to secrete, by act or word; hence (intensively) to destroy:—conceal, cut down (off), desolate, hide.

h3583.d: כָּחַל kâchal, kaw-khal'; a primitive root;  to paint (with stibium):—paint.

h3584.d: כָּחַשׁ kâchash, kaw-khash'; a primitive root;  to be untrue, in word (to lie, feign, disown) or deed (to disappoint, fail, cringe):—deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-) lie, lying, submit selves.

h3586.d: כֶּחָשׁ kechâsh, kekh-awsh'; from H3584;  faithless:—lying.
h3586.r: From כָּחַשׁ (H3584)|English: lie, submit, deny, fail, denied, belied, deceive, dissembled, deal falsely, liars, submitted

h3588.d: כִּי kîy, kee; a primitive particle (the full form of the prepositional prefix) indicating causal relations of all kinds, antecedent or consequent;  (by implication) very widely used as a relative conjunction or adverb (as below); often largely modified by other particles annexed:—and,   (forasmuch, inasmuch, where-) as, assured(-ly),   but, certainly, doubtless,   else, even,   except, for, how, (because, in, so, than) that,   nevertheless, now, rightly, seeing, since, surely, then, therefore,   (al-) though,   till, truly,   until, when, whether, while, whom, yea, yet.

h359.d: אֵילוֹת ʼÊylôwth, ay-loth'; or אֵילַת ʼÊylath ; from H352; trees or a grove (i.e. palms);  Eloth or Elath, a place on the Red Sea:—Elath, Eloth.
h359.r: From אַיִל (H352)|English: ram(s), post(s), mighty (men), trees, lintel, oaks

h3591.d: כִּידוֹן kîydôwn, kee-dohn'; from the same as H3589; (perhaps smaller than H2595)  properly, something to strike with, i.e. a dart:—lance, shield, spear, target.
h3591.r: From the same as כִּיד (H3589)|English: destruction

h3595.d: כִּיּוֹר kîyôwr, kee-yore'; or כִּיֹּר kîyôr; from the same as H3564;  properly, something round (as excavated or bored), i.e. a chafing-dish for coals or a caldron for cooking; hence (from similarity of form) a washbowl; also (for the same reason) a pulpit or platform:—hearth, laver, pan, scaffold.
h3595.r: From the same as כּוּר (H3564)|English: furnace

h3599.d: כִּיס kîyç, keece; a form for H3563;  a cup; also a bag for money or weights:—bag, cup, purse.
h3599.r: A form for כּוֹס (H3563)|English: cup, owl

h36.d: אֲבִיטוּב ʼĂbîyṭûwb, ab-ee-toob'; from H1 and H2898; father of goodness (i.e. good);  Abitub, an Israelite:—Abitub.
h36.r: From אָב (H1) and טוּב (H2898)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h3602.d: כָּכָה kâkâh, kaw'-kaw; from H3541;  just so, referring to the previous or following context:—after that (this) manner, this matter, (even) so, in such a case, thus.
h3602.r: From כֹּה (H3541)|English: thus, so...also, like, hitherto, while, on this manner

h3603.d: כִּכָּר kikkâr, kik-kawr'; from H3769;  a circle, i.e. (by implication) a circumjacent tract or region, especially the Ghor or valley of the Jordan; also a (round) loaf; also a talent (or large [round] coin):—loaf, morsel, piece, plain, talent.

h3604.d: כִּכֵּר kikkêr, kik-kare'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3603;  a talent:—talent.
h3604.r: Corresponding to כִּכָּר (H3603)|English: talent, plain, loaf, piece, country, morsel

h3605.d: כֹּל kôl, kole; or (Jeremiah 33:8) כּוֹל kôwl; from H3634;  properly, the whole; hence, all, any or every (in the singular only, but often in a plural sense):—(in) all (manner, (ye)), altogether, any (manner), enough, every (one, place, thing), howsoever, as many as, (no-) thing, ought, whatsoever, (the) whole, whoso(-ever).

h3606.d: כֹּל kôl, kole; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3605:—all, any,   (forasmuch) as,   be-(for this) cause, every,   no (manner, -ne),   there (where) -fore,   though, what (where, who) -soever, (the) whole.
h3606.r: Corresponding to כֹּל (H3605)|English: every thing, all, whosoever, whatsoever, nothing, yet

h3609.d: כִּלְאָב Kilʼâb, kil-awb'; apparently from H3607 and H1; restraint of (his) father;  Kilab, an Israelite:—Chileab.
h3609.r: Apparently from כָּלָא (H3607) and אָב (H1)|English: shut up, stayed, refrained, restrained, withhold, keep back, finish, forbid, kept, retain

h3610.d: כִּלְאַיִם kilʼayim, kil-ah'-yim; dual of H3608 in the original sense of separation;  two heterogeneities:—divers seeds (-e kinds), mingled (seed).
h3610.r: Dual of כֶּלֶא (H3608) in the original sense of separation|English: prison

h3611.d: כֶּלֶב keleb, keh'-leb; from an unused root means. to yelp, or else to attack;  a dog; hence (by euphemism) a male prostitute:—dog.
h3611.r: From an unused root means. to yelp, or else to attack|

h3612.d: כָּלֵב Kâlêb, kaw-labe'; perhaps a form of H3611, or else from the same root in the sense of forcible;  Caleb, the name of three Israelites:—Caleb.
h3612.r: Perhaps a form of כֶּלֶב (H3611), or else from the same root in the sense of forcible|English: dog

h3615.d: כָּלָה kâlâh, kaw-law'; a primitive root;  to end, whether intransitive (to cease, be finished, perish) or transitive (to complete, prepare, consume):—accomplish, cease, consume (away), determine, destroy (utterly), be (when... were) done, (be an) end (of), expire, (cause to) fail, faint, finish, fulfil, × fully, × have, leave (off), long, bring to pass, wholly reap, make clean riddance, spend, quite take away, waste.

h3617.d: כָּלָה kâlâh, kaw-law'; from H3615;  a completion; adverb, completely; also destruction:—altogether, (be, utterly) consume(-d), consummation(-ption), was determined, (full, utter) end, riddance.
h3617.r: From כָּלָה (H3615)|English: consume, end, finish, fail, accomplish, done, spend, ended, determined, away, fulfil, fainteth, destroy, left, waste, misc

h3618.d: כַּלָּה kallâh, kal-law'; from H3634;  a bride (as if perfect); hence, a son's wife:—bride, daughter-in-law, spouse.

h362.d: אֵילִם ʼÊylim, ay-leem'; plural of H352; palm-trees;  Elim, a place in the Desert:—Elim.
h362.r: Plural of אַיִל (H352)|English: ram(s), post(s), mighty (men), trees, lintel, oaks

h3620.d: כְּלוּב Kᵉlûwb, kel-oob'; the same as H3619;  Kelub, the name of two Israelites:—Chelub.
h3620.r: The same as כְּלוּב (H3619)|English: cage, basket

h3622.d: כְּלוּהַי Kᵉlûwhay, kel-oo-hah'-ee; from H3615; completed;  Keluhai, an Israelite:—Chelluh.
h3622.r: From כָּלָה (H3615)|English: consume, end, finish, fail, accomplish, done, spend, ended, determined, away, fulfil, fainteth, destroy, left, waste, misc

h3627.d: כְּלִי kᵉlîy, kel-ee'; from H3615;  something prepared, i.e. any apparatus (as an implement, utensil, dress, vessel or weapon):—armour(-bearer), artillery, bag, carriage,   furnish, furniture, instrument, jewel, that is made of, × one from another, that which pertaineth, pot,   psaltery, sack, stuff, thing, tool, vessel, ware, weapon,   whatsoever.
h3627.r: From כָּלָה (H3615)|English: consume, end, finish, fail, accomplish, done, spend, ended, determined, away, fulfil, fainteth, destroy, left, waste, misc

h3628.d: כְּלִיא kᵉlîyʼ, kel-ee'; or כְּלוּא kᵉlûwʼ; from H3627 (compare H3608);  a prison:—prison.
h3628.r: From כָּלָא (H3607) [compare כֶּלֶא (H3608)]|English: shut up, stayed, refrained, restrained, withhold, keep back, finish, forbid, kept, retain

h3629.d: כִּלְיָה kilyâh, kil-yaw'; feminine of H3627 (only in the plural);  a kidney (as an essential organ); figuratively, the mind (as the interior self):—kidneys, reins.
h3629.r: From כְּלִי (H3627) (only pl.)|English: vessel, instrument, weapon, jewel, armourbearer, stuff, thing, armour, furniture, carriage, bag, misc

h3631.d: כִּלָּיוֹן killâyôwn, kil-law-yone'; from H3615;  pining, destruction:—consumption, failing.
h3631.r: From כָּלָה (H3615)|English: consume, end, finish, fail, accomplish, done, spend, ended, determined, away, fulfil, fainteth, destroy, left, waste, misc

h3632.d: כָּלִיל kâlîyl, kaw-leel'; from H3634;  complete; as noun, the whole (specifically, a sacrifice entirely consumed); as adverb, fully:—all, every whit, flame, perfect(-ion), utterly, whole burnt offering (sacrifice), wholly.

h3633.d: כַּלְכֹּל Kalkôl, kal-kole'; from H3557; sustenance;  Calcol, an Israelite:—Calcol, Chalcol.
h3633.r: From כּוּל (H3557)|English: contain, feed, sustain, abide, nourish, hold, receive, victual, bear, comprehended, misc

h3634.d: כָּלַל kâlal, kaw-lal'; a primitive root;  to complete:—(make) perfect.

h3635.d: כְּלַל kᵉlal, kel-al'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3634;  to complete:—finish, make (set) up.
h3635.r: Corresponding to כָּלַל (H3634)|English: perfected, made perfect

h3636.d: כְּלָל Kᵉlâl, kel-awl'; from H3634; complete;  Kelal, an Israelite:—Chelal.

h3637.d: כָּלַם kâlam, kaw-lawm'; a primitive root;  properly, to wound; but only figuratively, to taunt or insult:—be (make) ashamed, blush, be confounded, be put to confusion, hurt, reproach, (do, put to) shame.

h3639.d: כְּלִמָּה kᵉlimmâh, kel-im-maw'; from H3637;  disgrace:—confusion, dishonour, reproach, shame.
h3639.r: From כָּלַם (H3637)|English: ashamed, confounded, shame, blush, hurt, reproach, confusion

h3640.d: כְּלִמּוּת kᵉlimmûwth, kel-im-mooth'; from H3639;  disgrace:—shame.
h3640.r: From כְּלִמָּה (H3639)|English: shame, confusion, dishonour, reproach

h3643.d: כִּמְהָם Kimhâm, kim-hawm'; from H3642; pining;  Kimham, an Israelite:—Chimham.
h3643.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h3644.d: כְּמוֹ kᵉmôw, kem-o'; or כָּמוֹ kâmôw; a form of the prefix k, but used separately [compare H3651];  as, thus, so:—according to, (such) as (it were, well as), in comparison of, like (as, to, unto), thus, when, worth.

h3645.d: כְּמוֹשׁ Kᵉmôwsh, kem-oshe'; or (Jeremiah 48:7) כְּמִישׁ Kᵉmîysh; from an unused root meaning to subdue; the powerful;  Kemosh, the god of the Moabites:—Chemosh.
h3645.s: proper noun with reference to deity
h3645.r: From an unused root meaning to subdue|

h3648.d: כָּמַר kâmar, kaw-mar'; a primitive root;  properly, to intertwine or contract, i.e. (by implication) to shrivel (as with heat); figuratively, to be deeply affected with passion (love or pity):—be black, be kindled, yearn.

h3649.d: כָּמָר kâmâr, kaw-mawr'; from H3648;  properly, an ascetic (as if shrunk with self-maceration), i.e. an idolatrous priest (only in plural):—Chemarims (idolatrous) priests.

h3651.d: כֵּן kên, kane; from H3559;  properly, set upright; hence (figuratively as adjective) just; but usually (as adverb or conjunction) rightly or so (in various applications to manner, time and relation; often with other particles):—  after that (this, -ward, -wards), as... as,   (for-) asmuch as yet,   be (for which) cause,   following, howbeit, in (the) like (manner, -wise), × the more, right, (even) so, state, straightway, such (thing), surely,   there (where) -fore, this, thus, true, well, × you.
h3651.r: From כּוּן (H3559)|English: prepare, establish, ready, stablish, provide, right, fixed, set, direct, order, fashion, variant, certain, confirmed, firm, preparation, misc

h3652.d: כֵּן kên, kane; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3651;  so:—thus.
h3652.r: Corresponding to כֵּן (H3651)|English: so, thus, like manner, well, such thing, howbeit, state, after that, following, after this, therefore, wherefore, surely

h3654.d: כֵּן kên, kane; from H3661 in the sense of fastening; (from infixing its sting; used only in plural (and irregular in Exodus 8:17,18; Hebrews 13:14))  a gnat:—lice, × manner.
h3654.r: From כָּנַן (H3661) in the sense of fastening|English: vineyard

h3656.d: כַּנֶּה Kanneh, kan-neh'; for H3641;  Canneh, a place in Assyria:—Canneh.

h3658.d: כִּנּוֹר kinnôwr, kin-nore'; from a unused root meaning to twang;  a harp:—harp.
h3658.r: From a unused root meaning to twang|

h3659.d: כׇּנְיָהוּ Konyâhûw, kon-yaw'-hoo; for H3204;  Conjah, an Israelite king:—Coniah.

h3660.d: כְּנֵמָא kᵉnêmâʼ, ken-ay-maw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3644;  so or thus:—so, (in) this manner (sort), thus.
h3660.r: Corresponding to כְּמוֹ (H3644)|English: and when, as thyself, like me, according to it, worth

h3662.d: כְּנָנִי Kᵉnânîy, ken-aw-nee'; from H3661; planted;  Kenani, an Israelite:—Chenani.

h3663.d: כְּנַנְיָה Kᵉnanyâh, ken-an-yaw'; or כְּנַנְיָהוּ Kᵉnanyâhûw; from H3661 and H3050; Jah has planted;  Kenanjah, an Israelite:—Chenaniah.

h3664.d: כָּנַס kânaç, kaw-nas'; a primitive root;  to collect; hence, to enfold:—gather (together), heap up, wrap self.

h3665.d: כָּנַע kânaʻ, kaw-nah'; a primitive root;  properly, to bend the knee; hence, to humiliate, vanquish:—bring down (low), into subjection, under, humble (self), subdue.

h3667.d: כְּנַעַן Kᵉnaʻan, ken-ah'-an; from H3665; humiliated;  Kenaan, a son a Ham; also the country inhabited by him:—Canaan, merchant, traffick.
h3667.s: masculine noun, proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h3667.r: From כָּנַע (H3665)|English: humble, subdue, bring low, bring down, subjection, misc

h3668.d: כְּנַעֲנָה Kᵉnaʻănâh, ken-ah-an-aw'; feminine of H3667;  Kenaanah, the name of two Israelites:—Chenaanah.
h3668.r: From כְּנַעַן (H3667)|English: Canaan, merchant, traffick, traffickers

h3669.d: כְּנַעַנִי Kᵉnaʻanîy, ken-ah-an-ee'; patrial from H3667;  a Kenaanite or inhabitant of Kenaan; by implication, a pedlar (the Canaanites standing for their neighbors the Ishmaelites, who conducted mercantile caravans):—Canaanite, merchant, trafficker.
h3669.r: Patrial from כְּנַעַן (H3667)|English: Canaan, merchant, traffick, traffickers

h367.d: אֵימָה ʼêymâh, ay-maw'; or (shortened) אֵמָה ʼêmâh; from the same as H366;  fright; concrete, an idol (as a bugbear):—dread, fear, horror, idol, terrible, terror.
h367.r: From the same as אָיֹם (H366)|English: terrible

h3670.d: כָּנַף kânaph, kaw-naf'; a primitive root;  properly, to project laterally, i.e. probably (reflexive) to withdraw:—be removed.

h3671.d: כָּנָף kânâph, kaw-nawf'; from H3670;  an edge or extremity; specifically (of a bird or army) a wing, (of a garment or bedclothing) a flap, (of the earth) a quarter, (of a building) a pinnacle:—  bird, border, corner, end, feather(-ed), × flying,   (one an-) other, overspreading, × quarters, skirt, × sort, uttermost part, wing(-ed).
h3671.r: From כָּנַף (H3670)|English: be removed into a corner

h3672.d: כִּנְּרוֹת Kinnᵉrôwth, kin-ner-oth'; or כִּנֶּרֶת Kinnerethlemma כִּנֶרֶת missing dagesh, corrected to כִּנֶּרֶת; respectively plural and singular feminine from the same as H3658; perhaps harp-shaped;  Kinneroth or Kinnereth, a place in Palestine:—Chinnereth, Chinneroth, Cinneroth.
h3672.r: Respectively pl. and sing. fem. from the same as כִּנּוֹר (H3658)|English: harp

h3673.d: כָּנַשׁ kânash, kaw-nash'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3664;  to assemble:—gather together.
h3673.r: Corresponding to כָּנַס (H3664)|English: gather, gather together, heap up, wrap

h3677.d: כֶּסֶא keçeʼ, keh'-seh; or כֶּסֶה keçeh; apparently from H3680;  properly, fulness or the full moon, i.e. its festival:—(time) appointed.
h3677.r: Apparently from כָּסָה (H3680)|English: cover, hide, conceal, covering, overwhelmed, clad, closed, clothed

h3678.d: כִּסֵּא kiççêʼ, kis-say'; or כִּסֵּה kiççêh; from H3680;  properly, covered, i.e. a throne (as canopied):—seat, stool, throne.
h3678.r: From כָּסָה (H3680)|English: cover, hide, conceal, covering, overwhelmed, clad, closed, clothed

h3680.d: כָּסָה kâçâh, kaw-saw'; a primitive root;  properly, to plump, i.e. fill up hollows; by implication, to cover (for clothing or secrecy):—clad self, close, clothe, conceal, cover (self), (flee to) hide, overwhelm. Compare H3780.

h3682.d: כְּסוּת kᵉçûwth, kes-ooth'; from H3680;  a cover (garment); figuratively, a veiling:—covering, raiment, vesture.
h3682.r: From כָּסָה (H3680)|English: cover, hide, conceal, covering, overwhelmed, clad, closed, clothed

h3683.d: כָּסַח kâçach, kaw-sakh'; a primitive root;  to cut off:—cut down (up).

h3685.d: כְּסִיל Kᵉçîyl, kes-eel'; the same as H3684;  any notable constellation; specifically Orion (as if a burly one):—constellation, Orion.
h3685.r: The same as כְּסִיל (H3684)|English: fool, foolish

h3689.d: כֶּסֶל keçel, keh'-sel; from H3688;  properly, fatness, i.e. by implication (literally) the loin (as the seat of the leaf fat) or (generally) the viscera; also (figuratively) silliness or (in a good sense) trust:—confidence, flank, folly, hope, loin.

h369.d: אַיִן ʼayin, ah'-yin; as if from a primitive root meaning to be nothing or not exist;  a nonentity; generally used as a negative particle:—else, except, fail, (father-) less, be gone, in(-curable), neither, never, no (where), none, nor, (any, thing), not, nothing, to nought, past, un(-searchable), well-nigh, without. Compare H370.
h369.r: As if from a primitive root meaning to be nothing or not exist|

h3691.d: כִּסְלֵו Kiçlêv, kis-lave'; probably of foreign origin;  Kisleu, the 9th Hebrew month:—Chisleu.

h3697.d: כָּסַם kâçam, kaw-sam'; a primitive root; to shear:—× only, poll. Compare H3765.

h370.d: אַיִן ʼayin, ah-yin'; probably identical with H369 in the sense of query (compare H336)  where? (only in connection with prepositional prefix, whence):—whence, where.
h370.r: Probably identical with אִין (H369) in the sense of query (compare אִי (H336))|English: except, faileth, fatherless, incurable, infinite, innumerable, neither, never, no, none, not, nothing, nought, without

h3700.d: כָּסַף kâçaph, kaw-saf'; a primitive root;  properly, to become pale, i.e. (by implication) to pine after; also to fear:—(have) desire, be greedy, long, sore.

h3701.d: כֶּסֶף keçeph, keh'-sef; from H3700;  silver (from its pale color); by implication, money:—money, price, silver(-ling).
h3701.r: From כָּסַף (H3700)|English: desire, long, greedy, sore

h3702.d: כְּסַף kᵉçaph, kes-af'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3701:—money, silver.
h3702.r: Corresponding to כֶּסֶף (H3701)|English: silver, money, price, silverlings

h3703.d: כָּסִפְיָא Kâçiphyâʼ, kaw-sif-yaw'; perhaps from H3701; silvery;  Casiphja, a place in Babylon:—Casiphia.
h3703.r: Perhaps from כֶּסֶף (H3701)|English: silver, money, price, silverlings

h3705.d: כְּעַן kᵉʻan, keh-an'; (Aramaic) probably from H3652;  now:—now.

h3707.d: כַּעַס kaʻaç, kaw-as'; a primitive root;  to trouble; by implication, to grieve, rage, be indignant:—be angry, be grieved, take indignation, provoke (to anger, unto wrath), have sorrow, vex, be wroth.

h3708.d: כַּעַס kaʻaç, kah'-as; or (in Job) כַּעַשׂ kaʻas; from H3707;  vexation:—anger, angry, grief, indignation, provocation, provoking, × sore, sorrow, spite, wrath.
h3708.r: From כָּעַס (H3707)|English: anger, provoked, angry, grieved, indignation, sorrow, vex, wrath, wroth

h3709.d: כַּף kaph, kaf; from H3721;  the hollow hand or palm (so of the paw of an animal, of the sole, and even of the bowl of a dish or sling, the handle of a bolt, the leaves of a palm-tree); figuratively, power:—branch,   foot, hand((-ful), -dle, (-led)), hollow, middle, palm, paw, power, sole, spoon.

h371.d: אִין ʼîyn, een; apparently a shortened form of H369; but (like H370) an interrogative;  is it not?:—not.
h371.r: Apparently a shortened form of אִין (H369)|English: except, faileth, fatherless, incurable, infinite, innumerable, neither, never, no, none, not, nothing, nought, without

h3712.d: כִּפָּה kippâh, kip-paw'; feminine of H3709;  a leaf of a palmtree:—branch.
h3712.r: From כַּף (H3709)|English: hand, spoon, sole, palm, hollow, handful, apiece, branches, breadth, clouds, misc

h3713.d: כְּפוֹר kᵉphôwr, kef-ore'; from H3722;  properly, a cover, i.e. (by implication) a tankard (or covered goblet); also white frost (as covering the ground):—bason, hoar(-y) frost.
h3713.r: From כָּפַר (H3722)|English: atonement, purge, reconciliation, reconcile, forgive, purge away, pacify, atonement...made, merciful, cleansed, disannulled, appease, put off, pardon, pitch

h3715.d: כְּפִיר kᵉphîyr, kef-eer'; from H3722;  a village (as covered in by walls); also a young lion (perhaps as covered with a mane):—(young) lion, village. Compare H3723.
h3715.r: From כָּפַר (H3722)|English: atonement, purge, reconciliation, reconcile, forgive, purge away, pacify, atonement...made, merciful, cleansed, disannulled, appease, put off, pardon, pitch

h3716.d: כְּפִירָה Kᵉphîyrâh, kef-ee-raw'; feminine of H3715; the village (always with the art.);  Kephirah, a place in Palestine:—Chephirah.
h3716.r: Feminine of כְּפִיר (H3715)|English: lion, villages, young

h3717.d: כָּפַל kâphal, kaw-fal'; a primitive root;  to fold together; figuratively, to repeat:—double.

h3718.d: כֶּפֶל kephel, keh'-fel; from H3717;  a duplicate:—double.

h3719.d: כָּפַן kâphan, kaw-fan'; a primitive root;  to bend:—bend.

h3721.d: כָּפַף kâphaph, kaw-faf'; a primitive root;  to curve:—bow down (self).

h3722.d: כָּפַר kâphar, kaw-far'; a primitive root;  to cover (specifically with bitumen); figuratively, to expiate or condone, to placate or cancel:—appease, make (an atonement, cleanse, disannul, forgive, be merciful, pacify, pardon, purge (away), put off, (make) reconcile(-liation).

h3724.d: כֹּפֶר kôpher, ko'-fer; from H3722;  properly, a cover, i.e. (literally) a village (as covered in); (specifically) bitumen (as used for coating), and the henna plant (as used for dyeing); figuratively, a redemption-price:—bribe, camphire, pitch, ransom, satisfaction, sum of money, village.
h3724.r: From כָּפַר (H3722)|English: atonement, purge, reconciliation, reconcile, forgive, purge away, pacify, atonement...made, merciful, cleansed, disannulled, appease, put off, pardon, pitch

h3729.d: כְּפַת kᵉphath, kef-ath'; (Aramaic) a root of uncertain correspondence;  to fetter:—bind.

h3733.d: כַּר kar, kar; from H3769 in the sense of plumpness;  a ram (as full-grown and fat), including a battering-ram (as butting); hence, a meadow (as for sheep); also a pad or camel's saddle (as puffed out):—captain, furniture, lamb, (large) pasture, ram. See also H1033, H3746.
h3733.r: From כָּרַר (H3769) in the sense of plumpness|English: dance

h3738.d: כָּרָה kârâh, kaw-raw'; a primitive root;  properly, to dig; figuratively, to plot; generally, to bore or open:—dig, × make (a banquet), open.

h3739.d: כָּרָה kârâh, kaw-raw'; usually assigned as a primitive root, but probably only a special application of H3738 (through the common idea of planning implied in a bargain);  to purchase:—buy, prepare.
h3739.r: Usually assigned as a primitive root, but probably only a special application of כָּרָה (H3738) (through the common idea of planning implied in a bargain)|English: dig, make, pierce, open

h374.d: אֵיפָה ʼêyphâh, ay-faw'; or (shortened) אֵפָה ʼêphâh ; of Egyptian derivation;  an ephah or measure for grain; hence, a measure in general:—ephah, (divers) measure(-s).

h3740.d: כֵּרָה kêrâh, kay-raw'; from H3739;  a purchase:—provision.

h3742.d: כְּרוּב kᵉrûwb, ker-oob'; of uncertain derivation;  a cherub or imaginary figure:—cherub, (plural) cherubims.

h3743.d: כְּרוּב Kᵉrûwb, ker-oob'; the same as H3742;  Kerub, a place in Babylon:—Cherub.
h3743.r: The same as כְּרוּב (H3742)|English: cherubims, cherub

h3747.d: כְּרִית Kᵉrîyth, ker-eeth'; from H3772; a cut;  Kerith, a brook of Palestine:—Cherith.
h3747.r: From כָּרַת (H3772)|English: cut off, make, cut down, cut, fail, destroy, want, covenanted, hew, misc

h375.d: אֵיפֹה ʼêyphôh, ay-fo'; from H335 and H6311;  what place?; also (of time) when?; or (of means) how?:—what manner, where.
h375.r: From אַי (H335) and פֹּה (H6311)|English: where, what, whence

h3754.d: כֶּרֶם kerem, keh'-rem; from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  a garden or vineyard:—vines, (increase of the) vineyard(-s), vintage. See also H1021.
h3754.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h3756.d: כַּרְמִי Karmîy, kar-mee'; from H3754; gardener;  Karmi, the name of three Israelites:—Carmi.

h3758.d: כַּרְמִיל karmîyl, kar-mele'; probably of foreign origin;  carmine, a deep red:—crimson.

h3759.d: כַּרְמֶל karmel, kar-mel'; from H3754;  a planted field (garden, orchard, vineyard or park); by implication, garden produce:—full (green) ears (of corn), fruitful field (place), plentiful (field).

h376.d: אִישׁ ʼîysh, eesh; contracted for H582 (or perhaps rather from an unused root meaning to be extant);  a man as an individual or a male person; often used as an adjunct to a more definite term (and in such cases frequently not expressed in translation):—also, another, any (man), a certain,   champion, consent, each, every (one), fellow, (foot-, husband-) man, (good-, great, mighty) man, he, high (degree), him (that is), husband, man(-kind),   none, one, people, person,   steward, what (man) soever, whoso(-ever), worthy. Compare H802.
h376.r: Contracted for אֱנוֹשׁ (H582) [or perhaps rather from an unused root meaning to be extant]|English: man, certain, husbands, some, merchantmen, persons, misc

h3760.d: כַּרְמֶל Karmel, kar-mel'; the same as H3759;  Karmel, the name of a hill and of a town in Palestine:—Carmel, fruitful (plentiful) field, (place).
h3760.r: The same as כַּרְמֶל (H3759)|English: fruitful field, plentiful field, full ear, green ear, full ears of corn, plentiful

h3764.d: כׇּרְסֵא korçêʼ, kor-say'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3678;  a throne:—throne.
h3764.r: Corresponding to כִּסֵּא (H3678)|English: throne, seat, stool

h3766.d: כָּרַע kâraʻ, kaw-rah'; a primitive root;  to bend the knee; by implication, to sink, to prostrate:—bow (down, self), bring down (low), cast down, couch, fall, feeble, kneeling, sink, smite (stoop) down, subdue, × very.

h3767.d: כָּרָע kârâʻ, kaw-raw'; from H3766;  the leg (from the knee to the ankle) of men or locusts (only in the dual):—leg.
h3767.r: From כָּרַע (H3766)|English: bow, ...down, fell, subdued, brought low, couched, feeble, kneeling, very

h3768.d: כַּרְפַּס karpaç, kar-pas'; of foreign origin;  byssus or fine vegetable wool:—green.

h3769.d: כָּרַר kârar, kaw-rar'; a primitive root;  to dance (i.e. whirl):—dance(-ing).

h3772.d: כָּרַת kârath, kaw-rath'; a primitive root;  to cut (off, down or asunder); by implication, to destroy or consume; specifically, to covenant (i.e. make an alliance or bargain, originally by cutting flesh and passing between the pieces):—be chewed, be con-(feder-) ate, covenant, cut (down, off), destroy, fail, feller, be freed, hew (down), make a league (covenant), × lose, perish, × utterly, × want.

h3773.d: כָּרֻתָה kâruthâh, kaw-rooth-aw'; passive participle feminine of H3772;  something cut, i.e. a hewn timber:—beam.
h3773.r: Passive participle of כָּרַת (H3772)|English: cut off, make, cut down, cut, fail, destroy, want, covenanted, hew, misc

h3778.d: כַּשְׂדִּי Kasdîy, kas-dee'; (occasionally with enclitic) כַּשְׂדִּימָה Kasdîymâh; towards the Kasdites into Chaldea), patronymically from H3777 (only in the plural);  a Kasdite, or descendant of Kesed; by implication, a Chaldaean (as if so descended); also an astrologer (as if proverbial of that people:—Chaldeans, Chaldees, inhabitants of Chaldea).

h3779.d: כַּשְׂדַּי Kasday, kas-dah'-ee; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3778;  a Chaldaean or inhabitant of Chaldaea; by implication, a Magian or professional astrologer:—Chaldean.
h3779.r: Corresponding to כַּשְׂדִּימָה (H3778)|English: Chaldeans, Chaldees, Chaldea

h378.d: אִישׁ־בֹּשֶׁת ʼÎysh-Bôsheth, eesh-bo'-sheth; from H376 and H1322; man of shame;  Ish-Bosheth, a son of King Saul:—Ish-bosheth.
h378.r: From אִישׁ (H376) and בּשֶׁת (H1322)|English: man, men, one, husband, any, misc

h3782.d: כָּשַׁל kâshal, kaw-shal'; a primitive root;  to totter or waver (through weakness of the legs, especially the ankle); by implication, to falter, stumble, faint or fall:—bereave (from the margin), cast down, be decayed, (cause to) fail, (cause, make to) fall (down, -ing), feeble, be (the) ruin(-ed, of), (be) overthrown, (cause to) stumble, × utterly, be weak.

h3784.d: כָּשַׁף kâshaph, kaw-shaf'; a primitive root;  properly, to whisper a spell, i.e. to inchant or practise magic:—sorcerer, (use) witch(-craft).

h3785.d: כֶּשֶׁף kesheph, keh'-shef; from H3784;  magic:—sorcery, witchcraft.

h3788.d: כִּשְׁרוֹן kishrôwn, kish-rone'; from H3787;  success, advantage:—equity, good, right.

h3789.d: כָּתַב kâthab, kaw-thab'; a primitive root;  to grave, by implication, to write (describe, inscribe, prescribe, subscribe):—describe, record, prescribe, subscribe, write(-ing, -ten).

h379.d: אִישְׁהוֹד ʼÎyshᵉhôwd, eesh-hode'; from H376 and H1935; man of renown;  Ishod, an Israelite:—Ishod.
h379.r: From אִישׁ (H376) and הוֹד (H1935)|English: man, men, one, husband, any, misc

h3790.d: כְּתַב kᵉthab, keth-ab'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3789:—write(-ten).
h3790.r: Corresponding to כָּתַב (H3789)|English: write, describe, subscribe, recorded, write up

h3791.d: כָּתָב kâthâb, kaw-thawb'; from H3789;  something written, i.e. a writing, record or book:—register, scripture, writing.
h3791.r: From כָּתַב (H3789)|English: write, describe, subscribe, recorded, write up

h3792.d: כְּתָב kᵉthâb, keth-awb'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3791:—prescribing, writing(-ten).
h3792.r: Corresponding to כְּתָב (H3791)|English: writing, register, scripture

h3793.d: כְּתֹבֶת kᵉthôbeth, keth-o'-beth; from H3789;  a letter or other mark branded on the skin:—× any (mark).
h3793.r: From כָּתַב (H3789)|English: write, describe, subscribe, recorded, write up

h3794.d: כִּתִּי Kittîy, kit-tee'; or כִּתִּיִּי Kittîyîy; patrial from an unused name denoting Cyprus (only in the plural);  a Kittite or Cypriote; hence, an islander in general, i.e. the Greeks or Romans on the shores opposite Palestine:—Chittim, Kittim.
h3794.r: Patrial from an unused name denoting Cyprus (only in the pl.)|

h3795.d: כָּתִית kâthîyth, kaw-theeth'; from H3807;  beaten, i.e. pure (oil):—beaten.
h3795.r: From כָּתַת (H3807)|English: beat, destroyed, beat down, break in pieces, smite, beat in pieces, discomfited, crushed, stamped

h38.d: אֲבִיָּם ʼĂbîyâm, ab-ee-yawm'; from H1 and H3220; father of (the) sea (i.e. seaman);  Abijam (or Abijah), a king of Judah:—Abijam.
h38.r: From אָב (H1) and יָם (H3220)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h3800.d: כֶּתֶם kethem, keh'-them; from H3799;  properly, something carved out, i.e. ore; hence, gold (pure as originally mined):—((most) fine, pure) gold(-en wedge).

h3801.d: כְּתֹנֶת kᵉthôneth, keth-o'-neth; or כֻּתֹּנֶת kuttôneth; from an unused root meaning to cover (compare H3802);  a shirt:—coat, garment, robe.
h3801.r: From an unused root meaning to cover [compare כָּתֵף (H3802)]|English: side, shoulders, shoulderpieces, undersetters, corner, arm

h3802.d: כָּתֵף kâthêph, kaw-thafe'; from an unused root meaning to clothe;  the shoulder (proper, i.e. upper end of the arm; as being the spot where the garments hang); figuratively, side-piece or lateral projection of anything:—arm, corner, shoulder(-piece), side, undersetter.
h3802.r: From an unused root meaning to clothe|

h3803.d: כָּתַר kâthar, kaw-thar'; a primitive root;  to enclose; hence (in a friendly sense) to crown, (in a hostile one) to besiege; also to wait (as restraining oneself):—beset round, compass about, be crowned, inclose round, suffer.

h3804.d: כֶּתֶר kether, keh'-ther; from H3803;  properly, a circlet, i.e. a diadem:—crown.
h3804.r: From כָּתַר (H3803)|English: compass (about), inclosed, beset me round, suffer, crowned

h3805.d: כֹתֶרֶת kôthereth, ko-theh'-reth; feminine active participle of H3803;  the capital of a column:—chapiter.
h3805.r: Act. participle of כָּתַר (H3803)|English: compass (about), inclosed, beset me round, suffer, crowned

h3807.d: כָּתַת kâthath, kaw-thath'; a primitive root;  to bruise or violently strike:—beat (down, to pieces), break in pieces, crushed, destroy, discomfit, smite, stamp.

h3808.d: לֹא lôʼ, lo; or לוֹא lôwʼ; or לֹה lôh; (Deuteronomy 3:11), a primitive particle; + not (the simple or abstract negation); by implication, no; often used with other particles:—× before, + or else, ere, + except, ig(-norant), much, less, nay, neither, never, no((-ne), -r, (-thing)), (× as though...,(can-), for) not (out of), of nought, otherwise, out of, + surely, + as truly as, + of a truth, + verily, for want, + whether, without.

h3809.d: לָא lâʼ, law; (Aramaic) or לָה lâh; (Aramaic) (Daniel 4:32), corresponding to H3808:—or even, neither, no(-ne, -r), (can-) not, as nothing, without.
h3809.r: Corresponding to לֹא (H3808)|English: not, no, none, nay, never, neither, ere, otherwise, before

h3811.d: לָאָה lâʼâh, law-aw'; a primitive root;  to tire; (figuratively) to be (or make) disgusted:—faint, grieve, lothe, (be, make) weary (selves).

h3812.d: לֵאָה Lêʼâh, lay-aw'; from H3811; weary;  Leah, a wife of Jacob:—Leah.
h3812.r: From לָאָה (H3811)|English: weary, grieve, faint, loath

h3813.d: לָאַט lâʼaṭ, law-at'; a primitive root;  to muffle:—cover.

h3814.d: לָאט lâʼṭ, lawt; from H3813 (or perhaps for active participle of H3874);  properly, muffled, i.e. silently:—softly.
h3814.r: From לָאַט (H3813) (or perhaps for act. participle of לוּט (H3874))|English: covered

h3816.d: לְאֹם lᵉʼôm, leh-ome'; or לְאוֹם lᵉʼôwm; from an unused root meaning to gather;  a community:—nation, people.
h3816.r: From an unused root meaning to gather|

h3820.d: לֵב lêb, labe; a form of H3824; the heart; also used (figuratively) very widely for the feelings, the will and even the intellect; likewise for the centre of anything:—care for, comfortably, consent, × considered, courag(-eous), friend(-ly), ((broken-), (hard-), (merry-), (stiff-), (stout-), double) heart(-ed), × heed, × I, kindly, midst, mind(-ed), × regard(-ed), × themselves, × unawares, understanding, × well, willingly, wisdom.
h3820.r: A form of לֵבָב (H3824)|English: heart, consider, mind, understanding, misc

h3823.d: לָבַב lâbab, law-bab'; a primitive root;  properly, to be enclosed (as if with fat); by implication (as denominative from H3824); to unheart; i.e. (in a good sense) transport (with love), or (in a bad sense) stultify; to make cakes:—make cakes, ravish, be wise.

h3824.d: לֵבָב lêbâb, lay-bawb'; from H3823; used also like H3820  the heart (as the most interior organ);:—  bethink themselves, breast, comfortably, courage, (faint), (tender-) heart(-ed), midst, mind, × unawares, understanding.
h3824.r: From לָבַב (H3823)|English: ravished my heart, make, made cakes, be wise

h3825.d: לְבַב lᵉbab, leb-ab'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3824:—heart.
h3825.r: Corresponding to לֵבָב (H3824)|English: heart, consider, mind, understanding, misc

h3828.d: לְבוֹנָה lᵉbôwnâh, leb-o-naw'; or לְבֹנָה lᵉbônâh; from H3836;  frankincense (from its whiteness or perhaps that of its smoke):—(frank-) incense.

h383.d: אִיתַי ʼîythay, ee-thah'ee; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3426;  properly, entity; used only as a particle of affirmation, there is:—art thou, can, do ye, have, it be, there is (are), × we will not.
h383.r: Corresponding to יֵשׁ (H3426)|English: is, be, have, there, misc

h3830.d: לְבוּשׁ lᵉbûwsh, leb-oosh'; or לְבֻשׁ lᵉbush; from H3847;  a garment (literally or figuratively); by implication (euphemistically) a wife:—apparel, clothed with, clothing, garment, raiment, vestment, vesture.
h3830.r: From לָבַשׁ (H3847)|English: clothe, put on, put, array, wear, armed, came, apparel, apparelled, clothed them, came upon, variant

h3833.d: לָבִיא lâbîyʼ, law-bee'; or (Ezekiel 19:2) לְבִיָּא lᵉbîyâʼ; irregular masculine plural לְבָאִים lᵉbâʼîym; irregular feminine plural לְבָאוֹת lᵉbâʼôwth; from an unused root meaning to roar; compare H738  a lion (properly, a lioness as the fiercer (although not a roarer;)):—(great, old, stout) lion, lioness, young (lion).
h3833.r: From an unused root men. to roar|

h3835.d: לָבַן lâban, law-ban'; a primitive root; also as denominative from H3843  to be (or become) white; to make bricks:—make brick, be (made, make) white(-r).

h3836.d: לָבָן lâbân, law-bawn'; or (Genesis 49:12) לָבֵן lâbên; from H3835;  white:—white.
h3836.r: From לָבַן (H3835)|English: make white, make, make brick, be white, be whiter

h3837.d: לָבָן Lâbân, law-bawn'; the same as H3836;  Laban, a Mesopotamian; also a place in the Desert:—Laban.
h3837.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h3839.d: לִבְנֶה libneh, lib-neh'; from H3835;  some sort of whitish tree, perhaps the storax:—poplar.
h3839.r: From לָבַן (H3835)|English: make white, make, make brick, be white, be whiter

h384.d: אִיתִיאֵל ʼÎythîyʼêl, eeth-ee-ale'; perhaps from H837 and H410; God has arrived;  Ithiel, the name of an Israelite, also of a symbolical person:—Ithiel.
h384.r: Perhaps from אשֶׁר (H837) and אֵל (H410)|English: happy

h3841.d: לִבְנָה Libnâh, lib-naw'; the same as H3839;  Libnah, a place in the Desert and one in Palestine:—Libnah.

h3842.d: לְבָנָה lᵉbânâh, leb-aw-naw'; from H3835;  properly, (the) white, i.e. the moon:—moon. See also H3838.
h3842.r: From לָבַן (H3835)|English: make white, make, make brick, be white, be whiter

h3843.d: לְבֵנָה lᵉbênâh, leb-ay-naw'; from H3835;  a brick (from the whiteness of the clay):—(altar of) brick, tile.
h3843.r: From לָבַן (H3835)|English: make white, make, make brick, be white, be whiter

h3844.d: לְבָנוֹן Lᵉbânôwn, leb-aw-nohn'; from H3825; (the) white mountain (from its snow);  Lebanon, a mountain range in Palestine:—Lebanon.
h3844.r: From לָבַן (H3835)|English: make white, make, make brick, be white, be whiter

h3845.d: לִבְנִי Libnîy, lib-nee'; from H3835; white;  Libni, an Israelite:—Libni.
h3845.r: From לָבַן (H3835)|English: make white, make, make brick, be white, be whiter

h3847.d: לָבַשׁ lâbash, law-bash'; or לָבֵשׁ lâbêsh; a primitive root;  properly, wrap around, i.e. (by implication) to put on a garment or clothe (oneself, or another), literally or figuratively:—(in) apparel, arm, array (self), clothe (self), come upon, put (on, upon), wear.

h3849.d: לֹג lôg, lohg; from an unused root apparently meaning to deepen or hollow (like H3537);  a log or measure for liquids:—log (of oil).
h3849.r: From an unused root apparently meaning to deepen or hollow [like כַּד (H3537)]|English: pitcher, barrel

h3850.d: לֹד Lôd, lode; from an unused root of uncertain signification;  Lod, a place in Palestine:—Lod.
h3850.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h3850.r: From an unused root of uncertain signification|

h3851.d: לַהַב lahab, lah'-hab; from an usused root meaning to gleam;  a flash; figuratively, a sharply polished blade or point of a weapon:—blade, bright, flame, glittering.
h3851.r: From an unused root meaning to gleam|

h3852.d: לֶהָבָה lehâbâh, leh-aw-baw'; or לַהֶבֶת lahebeth; feminine of H3851, and meaning the same:—flame(-ming), head (of a spear).
h3852.r: From לַהַב (H3851), and meaning the same|English: flame, blade, glittering, bright

h3854.d: לַהַג lahag, lah'-hag; from an unused root meaning to be eager;  intense mental application:—study.
h3854.r: From an unused root meaning to be eager|

h3856.d: לָהַהּ lâhahh, law-hah'; a primitive root meaning properly, to burn, i.e. (by implication)  to be rabid (figuratively, insane); also (from the exhaustion of frenzy) to languish:—faint, mad.

h3857.d: לָהַט lâhaṭ, law-hat'; a primitive root;  properly, to lick, i.e. (by implication) to blaze:—burn (up), set on fire, flaming, kindle.

h3859.d: לָהַם lâham, law-ham'; a primitive root;  properly, to burn in, i.e. (figuratively) to rankle:—wound.

h386.d: אֵיתָן ʼêythân, ay-thawn'; or (shortened) אֵתָן ʼêthân ; from an unused root (meaning to continue);  permanence; hence (concrete) permanent; specifically a chieftain:—hard, mighty, rough, strength, strong.
h386.r: From an unused root (meaning to continue)|

h3861.d: לָהֵן lâhên, law-hane'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3860;  therefore; also except:—but, except, save, therefore, wherefore.

h3863.d: לוּא lûwʼ, loo; or לֻא luʼ; or לוּ lûw;  a conditional particle; if; by implication (interj. as a wish) would that!:—if (haply), peradventure, I pray thee, though, I would, would God (that).

h3864.d: לוּבִי Lûwbîy, loo-bee'; or לֻבִּי Lubbîy; (Daniel 11:43), partrial from a name probably derived from an unused root meaning to thirst, i.e. a dry region; apparently  a Libyan or inhabitant of interior Africa (only in plural):—Lubim(-s), Libyans.
h3864.r: Partrial from a name probably derived from an unused root meaning to thirst|

h3865.d: לוּד Lûwd, lood; probably of foreign derivation;  Lud, the name of two nations:—Lud, Lydia.

h3866.d: לוּדִי Lûwdîy, loo-dee'; or לוּדִיִּי Lûwdîyîy; patrial from H3865;  a Ludite or inhabitants of Lud (only in plural):—Ludim. Lydians.

h3867.d: לָוָה lâvâh, law-vaw'; a primitive root;  properly, to twine, i.e. (by implication) to unite, to remain; also to borrow (as a form of obligation) or (causatively) to lend:—abide with, borrow(-er), cleave, join (self), lend(-er).

h3869.d: לוּז lûwz, looz; probably of foreign origin;  some kind of nut-tree, perhaps the almond:—hazel.

h387.d: אֵיתָן ʼÊythân, ay-thawn'; the same as H386; permanent;  Ethan, the name of four Israelites:—Ethan.
h387.r: The same as אֵיתָן (H386)|English: strong, mighty, strength, hard, rough

h3871.d: לוּחַ lûwach, loo'-akh; or לֻחַ luach; from a primitive root;  probably meaning to glisten; a tablet (as polished), of stone, wood or metal:—board, plate, table.

h3873.d: לוֹחֵשׁ Lôwchêsh, lo-khashe'; active participle of H3907; (the) enchanter;  Lochesh, an Israelite:—Hallohesh, Haloshesh (including the article).
h3873.r: Active participle of לָחַשׁ (H3907)|English: whisper, charmer

h3876.d: לוֹט Lôwṭ, lote; the same as H3875;  Lot, Abraham's nephew:—Lot.

h3877.d: לוֹטָן Lôwṭân, lo-tawn'; from H3875; covering;  Lotan, an Idumaean:—Lotan.

h3878.d: לֵוִי Lêvîy, lay-vee'; from H3867; attached;  Levi, a son of Jacob:—Levi. See also H3879, H3881.
h3878.r: From לָוָה (H3867)|English: join, lend, borrow, borrower, abide, cleave, lender, lender

h3879.d: לֵוִי Lêvîy, lay-vee'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3880:—Levite.

h388.d: אֵיתָנִים ʼÊythânîym, ay-thaw-neem'; plural of H386; always with the article; the permanent brooks;  Ethanim, the name of a month:—Ethanim.
h388.r: Plural of אֵיתָן (H386)|English: strong, mighty, strength, hard, rough

h3881.d: לֵוִיִּי Lêvîyîy, lay-vee-ee'; or לֵוִי Lêvîy; patronymically from H3878;  a Levite or descendant of Levi:—Leviite.

h3882.d: לִוְיָתָן livyâthân, liv-yaw-thawn'; from H3867;  a wreathed animal, i.e. a serpent (especially the crocodile or some other large sea-monster); figuratively, the constellation of the dragon; also as a symbol of Babylon:—leviathan, mourning.
h3882.r: From לָוָה (H3867)|English: join, lend, borrow, borrower, abide, cleave, lender, lender

h3883.d: לוּל lûwl, lool; from an unused root meaning to fold back;  a spiral step:—winding stair. Compare H3924.
h3883.r: From an unused root meaning to fold back|

h3884.d: לוּלֵא lûwlêʼ, loo-lay'; or לוּלֵי lûwlêy; from H3863 and H3808;  if not:—except, had not, if (...not), unless, were it not that.
h3884.r: From לוּא (H3863) and לֹא (H3808)|English: if, would God, O that, Oh, would it might be, if haply, peradventure, Oh that, pray thee, Though, would

h3885.d: לוּן lûwn, loon; or לִין lîyn; a primitive root;  to stop (usually over night); by implication, to stay permanently; hence (in a bad sense) to be obstinate (especially in words, to complain):—abide (all night), continue, dwell, endure, grudge, be left, lie all night, (cause to) lodge (all night, in, -ing, this night), (make to) murmur, remain, tarry (all night, that night).

h3886.d: לוּעַ lûwaʻ, loo'-ah; a primitive root;  to gulp; figuratively, to be rash:—swallow down (up).

h3887.d: לוּץ lûwts, loots; a primitive root;  properly, to make mouths at, i.e. to scoff; hence (from the effort to pronounce a foreign language) to interpret, or (generally) intercede:—ambassador, have in derision, interpreter, make a mock, mocker, scorn(-er, -ful), teacher.

h3888.d: לוּשׁ lûwsh, loosh; a primitive root;  to knead:—knead.

h3889.d: לוּשׁ Lûwsh, loosh; from H3888; kneading;  Lush, a place in Palestine:—Laish (from the margin). Compare H3919.

h389.d: אַךְ ʼak, ak; akin to H403;  a particle of affirmation, surely; hence (by limitation) only:—also, in any wise, at least, but, certainly, even, howbeit, nevertheless, notwithstanding, only, save, surely, of a surety, truly, verily,   wherefore, yet (but).
h389.r: Akin to אָכֵן (H403)|English: surely, but, verily, truly, certainly, nevertheless

h3891.d: לְזוּת lᵉzûwth, lez-ooth'; from H3868;  perverseness:—perverse.
h3891.r: From לוּז (H3868)|English: froward, depart, perverse, perverseness

h3892.d: לַח lach, lakh; from an unused root meaning to be new;  fresh, i.e. unused or undried:—green, moist.
h3892.r: From an unused root meaning to be new|

h3895.d: לְחִי lᵉchîy, lekh-ee'; from an unused root meaning to be soft;  the cheek (from its fleshiness); hence, the jaw-bone:—cheek (bone), jaw (bone).
h3895.r: From an unused root meaning to be soft|

h3897.d: לָחַךְ lâchak, law-khak'; a primitive root;  to lick:—lick (up).

h3898.d: לָחַם lâcham, law-kham'; a primitive root;  to feed on; figuratively, to consume; by implication, to battle (as destruction):—devour, eat, × ever, fight(-ing), overcome, prevail, (make) war(-ring).

h3899.d: לֶחֶם lechem, lekh'-em; from H3898; See also H1036  food (for man or beast), especially bread, or grain (for making it):—(shew-) bread, × eat, food, fruit, loaf, meat, victuals.
h3899.r: From לָחַם (H3898)|English: fight, to war, make war, eat, overcome, devoured, ever, prevail

h39.d: אֲבִימָאֵל ʼĂbîymâʼêl, ab-ee-maw-ale'; from H1 and an elsewhere unused (probably foreign) word; father of Mael (apparently some Arab tribe);  Abimael, a son of Joktan:—Abimael.
h39.r: From אָב (H1) and an elsewhere unused (probably foreign) word|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h3900.d: לְחֶם lᵉchem, lekh-em'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3899:—feast.
h3900.r: Corresponding to לֶחֶם (H3899)|English: bread, food, meat, shewbread, loaves, shewbread, shewbread, victuals, eat, feast, fruit, provision

h3901.d: לָחֶם lâchem, law-khem'; from H3898,  battle:—war.
h3901.r: From לָחַם (H3898)|English: fight, to war, make war, eat, overcome, devoured, ever, prevail

h3902.d: לַחְמִי Lachmîy, lakh-mee'; from H3899; foodful; (or perhaps erroneous transcription) for H1022  Lachmi, an Israelite; or rather probably a brief form:—Lahmi. See also H3433.
h3902.r: From לֶחֶם (H3899)|English: bread, food, meat, shewbread, loaves, shewbread, shewbread, victuals, eat, feast, fruit, provision

h3905.d: לָחַץ lâchats, law-khats'; a primitive root;  properly, to press, i.e. (figuratively) to distress:—afflict, crush, force, hold fast, oppress(-or), thrust self.

h3908.d: לַחַשׁ lachash, lakh'-ash; from H3907;  properly, a whisper, i.e. by implication, (in a good sense) a private prayer, (in a bad one) an incantation; concretely, an amulet:—charmed, earring, enchantment, orator, prayer.

h3909.d: לָט lâṭ, lawt; a form of H3814 or else participle from H3874;  properly, covered, i.e. secret; by implication, incantation; also secrecy or (adverb) covertly:—enchantment, privily, secretly, softly.
h3909.r: A form of לָאט (H3814) or else participle from לוּט (H3874)|English: softly

h3915.d: לַיִל layil, lah'-yil; or (Isaiah 21:11) לֵיל lêyl; also לַיְלָה laylâh; from the same as H3883;  properly, a twist (away of the light), i.e. night; figuratively, adversity:—(mid-)night (season).
h3915.r: From the same as לוּל (H3883)|English: winding stair

h3916.d: לֵילְיָא lêylᵉyâʼ, lay-leh-yaw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3815:—night.

h3919.d: לַיִשׁ Layish, lah'-yish; the same as H3918;  Laish, the name of two places in Palestine:—Laish. Compare H3889.
h3919.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h3919.r: The same as לַיִשׁ (H3918)|English: old lion, lion

h3920.d: לָכַד lâkad, law-kad'; a primitive root;  to catch (in a net, trap or pit); generally, to capture or occupy; also to choose (by lot); figuratively, to cohere:—× at all, catch (self), be frozen, be holden, stick together, take.

h3923.d: לָכִישׁ Lâkîysh, law-keesh'; from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  Lakish, a place in Palestine:—Lachish.
h3923.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h3924.d: לֻלָאָה lulâʼâh, loo-law-aw'; from the same as H3883;  a loop:—loop.
h3924.r: From the same as לוּל (H3883)|English: winding stair

h3925.d: לָמַד lâmad, law-mad'; a primitive root;  properly, to goad, i.e. (by implication) to teach (the rod being an Oriental incentive):—(un-) accustomed, × diligently, expert, instruct, learn, skilful, teach(-er, -ing).

h3927.d: לְמוּאֵל Lᵉmûwʼêl, lem-oo-ale'; or לְמוֹאֵל Lᵉmôwʼêl; from H3926 and H410; (belonging) to God;  Lemuel or Lemoel, a symbolic name of Solomon:—Lemuel.
h3927.r: From לְמוֹ (H3926) and אֵל (H410)|English: for, at, to, upon

h3928.d: לִמּוּד limmûwd, lim-mood'; or לִמֻּד limmud; from H3925;  instructed:—accustomed, disciple, learned, taught, used.
h3928.r: From לָמַד (H3925)|English: teach, learn, instruct, diligently, expert, skilful, teachers, unaccustomed

h3929.d: לֶמֶךְ Lemek, leh'-mek; from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  Lemek, the name of two antediluvian patriarchs:—Lamech.
h3929.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h393.d: אַכְזָר ʼakzâr, ak-zawr'; from an unused root (apparently meaning to act harshly);  violent; by implication deadly; also (in a good sense) brave:—cruel, fierce.
h393.r: From an unused root (apparently meaning to act harshly)|

h3932.d: לָעַג lâʻag, law-ag'; a primitive root;  to deride; by implication (as if imitating a foreigner) to speak unintelligibly:—have in derision, laugh (to scorn), mock (on), stammering.

h3934.d: לָעֵג lâʻêg, law-ayg'; from H3932;  a buffoon; also a foreigner:—mocker, stammering.
h3934.r: From לָעַג (H3932)|English: mock, scorn, laugh, have in derision, laugh to scorn, stammering

h3936.d: לַעְדָּן Laʻdân, lah-dawn'; from the same as H3935;  Ladan, the name of two Israelites:—Laadan.
h3936.r: From the same as לַעְדָּה (H3935)|English: Laadah

h3937.d: לָעַז lâʻaz, law-az'; a primitive root;  to speak in a foreign tongue:—strange language.

h394.d: אַכְזָרִי ʼakzârîy, ak-zawr-ree'; from H393;  terrible:—cruel (one).

h3940.d: לַפִּיד lappîyd, lap-peed'; or לַפִּד lappid; from an unused root probably meaning to shine;  a flambeau, lamp or flame:—(fire-) brand, (burning) lamp, lightning, torch.
h3940.r: From an unused root probably meaning to shine|

h3943.d: לָפַת lâphath, law-fath'; a primitive root;  properly, to bend, i.e. (by implication) to clasp; also (reflexively) to turn around or aside:—take hold, turn aside (self).

h3947.d: לָקַח lâqach, law-kakh'; a primitive root;  to take (in the widest variety of applications):—accept, bring, buy, carry away, drawn, fetch, get, infold, × many, mingle, place, receive(-ing), reserve, seize, send for, take (away, -ing, up), use, win.

h3948.d: לֶקַח leqach, leh'-kakh; from H3947;  properly, something received, i.e. (mentally) instruction (whether on the part of the teacher or hearer); also (in an active and sinister sense) inveiglement:—doctrine, learning, fair speech.
h3948.r: From לָקַח (H3947)|English: take, receive, take away, fetch, bring, get, take out, carry away, married, buy, misc

h3950.d: לָקַט lâqaṭ, law-kat'; a primitive root;  properly, to pick up, i.e. (generally) to gather; specifically, to glean:—gather (up), glean.

h3952.d: לָקַק lâqaq, law-kak'; a primitive root;  to lick or lap:—lap, lick.

h3955.d: לְשַׁד lᵉshad, lesh-ad'; from an unused root of uncertain meaning; apparently juice, i.e.  (figuratively) vigor; also a sweet or fat cake:—fresh, moisture.
h3955.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h3956.d: לָשׁוֹן lâshôwn, law-shone'; or לָשֹׁן lâshôn; also (in plural) feminine לְשֹׁנָה lᵉshônâh; from H3960;  the tongue (of man or animals), used literally (as the instrument of licking, eating, or speech), and figuratively (speech, an ingot, a fork of flame, a cove of water):—  babbler, bay,   evil speaker, language, talker, tongue, wedge.

h3957.d: לִשְׁכָּה lishkâh, lish-kaw'; from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  a room in a building (whether for storage, eating, or lodging):—chamber, parlour. Compare H5393.
h3957.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h3959.d: לֶשֶׁם Leshem, leh'-shem; the same as H3958;  Leshem, a place in Palestine:—Leshem.

h3960.d: לָשַׁן lâshan, law-shan'; a primitive root; properly, to lick; but used only as a denominative from H3956;  to wag the tongue, i.e. to calumniate:—accuse, slander.

h3964.d: מָא mâʼ, maw; (Aramaic) corresponding to H4100;  (as indefinitely) that:—+ what.
h3964.r: Corresponding to מָה (H4100)|English: what, how, why, whereby, wherein, how long, how oft, to what end

h3966.d: מְאֹד mᵉʼôd, meh-ode'; from the same as H181;  properly, vehemence, i.e. (with or without preposition) vehemently; by implication, wholly, speedily, etc. (often with other words as an intensive or superlative; especially when repeated):—diligently, especially, exceeding(-ly), far, fast, good, great(-ly), × louder and louder, might(-ily, -y), (so) much, quickly, (so) sore, utterly, very (  much, sore), well.
h3966.r: From the same as אוּד (H181)|English: firebrand(s), brand

h3967.d: מֵאָה mêʼâh, may-aw'; or מֵאיָה mêʼyâh; properly, a primitive numeral  a hundred; also as a multiplicative and a fraction:—hundred((-fold), -th),   sixscore.
h3967.r: Properly, a primitive numeral; a hundred|

h3969.d: מְאָה mᵉʼâh, meh-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H3967; properly, a primitive numeral  a hundred; also as a multiplicative and a fraction}:—hundred.
h3969.r: Corresponding to מֵאָה (H3967)|English: hundred, eleven hundred, hundredth, hundredfold, sixscore, hundred times

h397.d: אֲכִישׁ ʼĂkîysh, aw-keesh'; of uncertain derivation;  Akish, a Philistine king:—Achish.

h3971.d: מאוּם mʼûwm, moom; usually מוּם mûwm; as if passive participle from an unused root probably meaning to stain  a blemish (physically or morally):—blemish, blot, spot.
h3971.r: As if passive participle from an unused root|

h3972.d: מְאוּמָה mᵉʼûwmâh, meh-oo'-maw; apparently a form of H3971;  properly, a speck or point, i.e. (by implication) something; with negative, nothing:—fault,   no(-ught), ought, somewhat, any (no-)thing.
h3972.r: Apparently a form of מְאוּם (H3971)|English: blemish, spot, blot, variant

h3974.d: מָאוֹר mâʼôwr, maw-ore'; or מָאֹר mâʼôr; also (in plural) feminine מְאוֹרָה mᵉʼôwrâh; or מְאֹרָה mᵉʼôrâh; from H215;  properly, a luminous body or luminary, i.e. (abstractly) light (as an element); figuratively, brightness, i.e.cheerfulness; specifically, a chandelier:—bright, light.
h3974.r: From אוֹר (H215)|English: light, shine, enlighten, break of day, fire, give, glorious, kindle

h3975.d: מְאוּרָה mᵉʼûwrâh, meh-oo-raw'; feminine passive participle of H215;  something lighted, i.e. an aperture; by implication, a crevice or hole (of a serpent):—den.
h3975.r: Pass. participle of אוֹר (H215)|English: light, shine, enlighten, break of day, fire, give, glorious, kindle

h3976.d: מֹאזֵן môʼzên, mo-zane'; from H239;  (only in the dual) a pair of scales:—balances.

h3978.d: מַאֲכָל maʼăkâl, mah-ak-awl'; from H398;  an eatable (includ. provender, flesh and fruit):—food, fruit, (bake-)meat(-s), victual.
h3978.r: From אָכַל (H398)|English: eat, devour, consume, misc

h398.d: אָכַל ʼâkal, aw-kal'; a primitive root;  to eat (literally or figuratively):—× at all, burn up, consume, devour(-er, up), dine, eat(-er, up), feed (with), food, × freely, × in...wise(-deed, plenty), (lay) meat, × quite.

h3980.d: מַאֲכֹלֶת maʼăkôleth, mah-ak-o'-leth; from H398;  something eaten (by fire), i.e. fuel:—fuel.
h3980.r: From אָכַל (H398)|English: eat, devour, consume, misc

h3984.d: מָאן mâʼn, mawn; (Aramaic) probably from a root corresponding to H579 in the sense of an inclosure by sides;  a utensil:—vessel.
h3984.r: Probably from a root corresponding to אָנָה (H579) in the sense of an inclosure by sides|English: deliver, befall, happen, seeketh a quarrel

h3985.d: מָאֵן mâʼên, maw-ane'; a primitive root;  to refuse:—refuse, × utterly.

h3987.d: מֵאֵן mêʼên, may-ane'; from H3985;  refractory:—refuse.

h3988.d: מָאַס mâʼaç, maw-as'; a primitive root;  to spurn; also (intransitively) to disappear:—abhor, cast away (off), contemn, despise, disdain, (become) loathe(some), melt away, refuse, reject, reprobate, × utterly, vile person.

h3989.d: מַאֲפֶה maʼăpheh, mah-af-eh'; from H644;  something baked, i.e. a batch:—baken.

h399.d: אֲכַל ʼăkal, ak-al'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H398:—  accuse, devour, eat.
h399.r: Corresponding to אָכַל (H398)|English: eat, devour, consume, misc

h3990.d: מַאֲפֵל maʼăphêl, mah-af-ale'; from the same as H651;  something opaque:—darkness.
h3990.r: From the same as אָפֵל (H651)|English: very dark

h3991.d: מַאְפֵלְיָה maʼphêlᵉyâh, mah-af-ay-leh-yaw'; prolonged feminine of H3990;  opaqueness:—darkness.

h3993.d: מַאֲרָב maʼărâb, mah-ar-awb'; from H693;  an ambuscade:—lie in ambush, ambushment, lurking place, lying in wait.
h3993.r: From אָרַב (H693)|English: lay in wait, liers in wait, ambush

h3995.d: מִבְדָּלָה mibdâlâh, mib-daw-law'; from H914;  a separation, i.e. (concretely) a separate place:—separate.
h3995.r: From בָּדַל (H914)|English: separate, divide, difference, asunder, severed, sever out, separation, utterly (inf. for emphasis)

h3996.d: מָבוֹא mâbôwʼ, maw-bo'; from H935; (with or without H8121)  an entrance (the place or the act); specifically sunset or the west; also (adverb with preposition) towards:—by which came, as cometh, in coming, as men enter into, entering, entrance into, entry, where goeth, going down,   westward. Compare H4126.
h3996.r: From בּוֹא (H935)|English: come, bring, ... in, enter, go, carry, ...down, pass, ...out, misc

h40.d: אֲבִימֶלֶךְ ʼĂbîymelek, ab-ee-mel'-ek; from H1 and H4428; father of (the) king;  Abimelek, the name of two Philistine kings and of two Israelites:—Abimelech.
h40.r: From אָב (H1) and מֶלֶךְ (H4428)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h400.d: אֹכֶל ʼôkel, o'-kel; from H398;  food:—eating, food, meal(-time), meat, prey, victuals.
h400.r: From אָכַל (H398)|English: eat, devour, consume, misc

h4002.d: מַבּוּעַ mabbûwaʻ, mab-boo'-ah; from H5042;  a fountain:—fountain, spring.
h4002.r: From נָבַע (H5042)|English: utter, pour out, send forth, flowing, belch out

h4004.d: מִבְחוֹר mibchôwr, mib-khore'; from H977;  select, i.e. well fortified:—choice.
h4004.r: From בָּחַר (H977)|English: choose, chosen, choice, choose...out, acceptable, appoint, excellent, chosen men, rather, require, not translated

h4006.d: מִבְחָר Mibchâr, mib-khawr'; the same as H4005;  Mibchar, an Israelite:—Mibhar.
h4006.r: The same as מִבְחָר (H4005)|English: choice, chosen, choicest

h4009.d: מִבְטָח mibṭâch, mib-tawkh'; from H982;  properly, a refuge, i.e. (objective) security, or (subjective) assurance:—confidence, hope, sure, trust.
h4009.r: From בָּטַח (H982)|English: trust, confidence, secure, confident, bold, careless, hope, hoped, ones, sure, women

h4012.d: מְבֻנַּי Mᵉbunnay, meb-oon-hah'-ee; from H1129; built up;  Mebunnai, an Israelite:—Mebunnai.
h4012.r: From בָּנָה (H1129)|English: build, build up, builder, made, built again, repair, set up, have children, obtain children, surely (inf. for emphasis)

h4013.d: מִבְצָר mibtsâr, mib-tsawr'; also (in plural) feminine (Daniel 11:l5) מִבְצָרָה mibtsârâh; from H1219;  a fortification, castle, or fortified city; figuratively, a defender:—(de-, most) fenced, fortress, (most) strong (hold).
h4013.r: From בָּצַר (H1219)|English: fenced, defenced, gather, grapegatherers, fortify, cut off, restrained, strong, mighty things, walled up, fenced up, walled, withholden, non translated variant

h4014.d: מִבְצָר Mibtsâr, mib-tsawr'; the same as H4013;  Mibtsar, an Idumaean:—Mibzar.
h4014.r: The same as מִבְצָר (H4013)|English: hold, fenced, fortress, defenced, strong

h4017.d: מִבְשָׂם Mibsâm, mib-sawm'; from the same as H1314; fragrant;  Mibsam, the name of an Ishmaelite and of an Israelite:—Mibsam.
h4017.r: From the same as בֶּשֶׂם (H1314)|English: spice, sweet odours, sweet, sweet smell

h402.d: אׇכְלָה ʼoklâh, ok-law'; feminine of H401;  food:—consume, devour, eat, food, meat.

h4021.d: מִגְבָּעָה migbâʻâh, mig-baw-aw'; from the same as H1389;  a cap (as hemispherical):—bonnet.
h4021.r: From the same as גִּבְעָה (H1389)|English: hill

h4022.d: מֶגֶד meged, meh'-ghed; from an unused root probably meaning to be eminent;  properly, a distinguished thing; hence something valuable, as a product or fruit:—pleasant, precious fruit (thing).
h4022.r: From an unused root probably meaning to be eminent|

h4023.d: מְגִדּוֹן Mᵉgiddôwn, meg-id-done'; (Zechariah H12) or מְגִדּוֹ Mᵉgiddôw; from H1413; rendezvous;  Megiddon or Megiddo, a place in Palestine:—Megiddo, Megiddon.
h4023.r: From גָּדַד (H1413)|English: cut, gather together, assemble by troop, gather

h4024.d: מִגְדּוֹל Migdôwl, mig-dole'; or מִגְדֹּל Migdôl; probably of Egyptian origin;  Migdol, a place in Egypt:—Migdol, tower.

h4025.d: מַגְדִּיאֵל Magdîyʼêl, mag-dee-ale'; from H4022 and H410; preciousness of God;  Magdiel, an Idumaean:—Magdiel.
h4025.r: From מֶגֶד (H4022) and אֵל (H410)|English: precious things, pleasant, precious fruit

h4026.d: מִגְדָּל migdâl, mig-dawl'; also (in plural) feminine מִגְדָּלָה migdâlâh; from H1431;  a tower (from its size or height); by analogy, a rostrum; figuratively, a (pyramidal) bed of flowers:—castle, flower, tower. Compare the names following.
h4026.r: From גָּדַל (H1431)|English: magnify, great, grow, nourish up, grow up, greater, misc
