h4960.d: מִשְׁתֶּה mishteh, mish-teh'; from H8354;  drink, by implication, drinking (the act); also (by implication) a banquet or (generally) feast:—banquet, drank, drink, feast((-ed), -ing).
h4960.r: From שָׁתָה (H8354)|English: drink, drinkers, drunkards, banquet, misc

h4962.d: מַת math, math; from the same as H4970;  properly, an adult (as of full length); by implication, a man (only in the plural):—  few, × friends, men, persons, × small.
h4962.r: From the same as מָתַי (H4970)|English: when, long

h4966.d: מָתוֹק mâthôwq, maw-thoke'; or מָתוּק mâthûwq; from H4985;  sweet:—sweet(-er, -ness).

h4968.d: מְתוּשֶׁלַח Mᵉthûwshelach, meth-oo-sheh'-lakh; from H4962 and H7973; man of a dart;  Methushelach, an antediluvian patriarch:—Methuselah.
h4968.r: From מַת (H4962) and שֶׁלַח (H7973)|English: men, few, few, friends, number, persons, small, with

h497.d: אֶלְעָדָה ʼElʻâdâh, el-aw-daw'; from H410 and H5710; God has decked;  Eladah, an Israelite:—Eladah.
h497.r: From אֵל (H410) and עָדָה (H5710)|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

h4970.d: מָתַי mâthay, maw-thah'ee; from an unused root meaning to extend;  properly, extent (of time); but used only adverbially (especially with other particle prefixes), when (either relative or interrogative):—long, when.
h4970.r: From an unused root meaning to extend|

h4973.d: מְתַלְּעָה mᵉthallᵉʻâh, meth-al-leh-aw'; contr. from H3216;  properly, a biter, i.e. a tooth:—cheek (jaw) tooth, jaw.

h4974.d: מְתֹם mᵉthôm, meth-ohm'; from H8552;  wholesomeness; also (adverb) completely:—men (by reading H4962), soundness.
h4974.r: From תָּמַם (H8552)|English: consume, end, finished, clean, upright, spent, perfect, done, failed, accomplish, misc

h4975.d: מֹתֶן môthen, mo'-then; from an unused root meaning to be slender;  properly, the waist or small of the back; only in plural the loins:—  greyhound, loins, side.
h4975.r: From an unused root meaning to be slender|

h4976.d: מַתָּן mattân, mat-tawn'; from H5414;  a present:—gift, to give, reward.
h4976.r: From נָתַן (H5414)|English: give, put, deliver, made, set, up, lay, grant, suffer, yield, bring, cause, utter, laid, send, recompense, appoint, shew

h4977.d: מַתָּן Mattân, mat-tawn'; the same as H4976;  Mattan, the name of a priest of Baal, and of an Israelite:—Mattan.

h4978.d: מַתְּנָא mattᵉnâʼ, mat-ten-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H4979:—gift.
h4978.r: Corresponding to מַתָּנָה (H4979)|English: gifts, as he is able

h4979.d: מַתָּנָה mattânâh, mat-taw-naw'; feminine of H4976;  a present; specifically (in a good sense), a sacrificial offering, (in a bad sense) a bribe:—gift.

h498.d: אֶלְעוּזַי ʼElʻûwzay, el-oo-zah'ee; from H410 and H5756 (in the sense of H5797); God (is) defensive;  Eluzai, an Israelite:—Eluzai.
h498.r: From אֵל (H410) and עוּז (H5756) (in the sense of עֹז (H5797))|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

h4982.d: מַתְּנַי Mattᵉnay, mat-ten-ah'ee; from H4976; liberal;  Mattenai, the name of three Israelites:—Mattenai.

h4983.d: מַתַּנְיָה Mattanyâh, mat-tan-yaw'; or מַתַּנְיָהוּ Mattanyâhûw; from H4976 and H3050; gift of Jah;  Mattanjah, the name of ten Israelites:—Mattaniah.

h4985.d: מָתַק mâthaq, maw-thak'; a primitive root;  to suck, by implication, to relish, or (intransitively) be sweet:—be (made, × take) sweet.

h499.d: אֶלְעָזָר ʼElʻâzâr, el-aw-zawr'; from H410 and H5826; God (is) helper;  Elazar, the name of seven Israelites:—Eleazar.
h499.r: From אֵל (H410) and עָזַר (H5826)|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

h4990.d: מִתְרְדָת Mithrᵉdâth, mith-red-awth'; of Persian origin;  Mithredath, the name of two Persians:—Mithredath.

h4992.d: מַתַּתָּה Mattattâh, mat-tat-taw'; for H4993; gift of Jah;  Mattattah, an Israelite:—Mattathah.

h4993.d: מַתִּתְיָה Mattithyâh, mat-tith-yaw'; or מַתִּתְיָהוּ Mattithyâhûw; from H4991 and H3050; gift of Jah; Mattithjah, the name of four Israelites:—Mattithiah.
h4993.r: From מַתַּת (H4991) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: gift,give, reward

h4994.d: נָא nâʼ, naw; a primitive particle of incitement and entreaty, which may usually be rendered;  'I pray', 'now', or 'then'; added mostly to verbs (in the Imperative or Future), or to interjections, occasionally to an adverb or conjunction:—I beseech (pray) thee (you), go to, now, oh.
h4994.r: A primitive particle of incitement and entreaty, which may usually be rendered: "I pray," "now," or "then"|

h4996.d: נֹא Nôʼ, no; of Egyptian origin;  No (i.e. Thebes), the capital of Upper Egypt:—No. Compare H528.

h4997.d: נֹאד nôʼd, node; or נאוֹד nʼôwdlemma נֹאוד vowel, corrected to נאוֹדxlit nôʼwd corrected to nʼôwd; also (feminine) נֹאדָה nôʼdâh; from an unused root of uncertain signification;  a (skin or leather) bag (for fluids):—bottle.
h4997.r: From an unused root of uncertain signification|

h4998.d: נָאָה nâʼâh, naw-aw'; a primitive root;  properly, to be at home, i.e. (by implication) to be pleasant (or suitable), i.e. beautiful:—be beautiful, become, be comely.

h4999.d: נָאָה nâʼâh, naw-aw'; from H4998;  a home; figuratively, a pasture:—habitation, house, pasture, pleasant place.

h5.d: אֲבַגְתָא ʼĂbagthâʼ, ab-ag-thaw'; of foreign origin;  Abagtha, a eunuch of Xerxes:—Abagtha.

h50.d: אֲבִישׁוּעַ ʼĂbîyshûwaʻ, ab-ee-shoo'-ah; from H1 and H7771; father of plenty (i.e. prosperous);  Abishua, the name of two Israelites:—Abishua.
h50.r: From אָב (H1) and שׁוֹעַ (H7771)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h500.d: אֶלְעָלֵא ʼElʻâlêʼ, el-aw-lay'; or (more properly) אֶלְעָלֵה ʼElʻâlêh; from H410 and H5927; God (is) going up;  Elale or Elaleh, a place east of the Jordan:—Elealeh.
h500.r: From אֵל (H410) and עָלָה (H5927)|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

h5002.d: נְאֻם nᵉʼum, neh-oom'; from H5001;  an oracle:—(hath) said, saith.

h5003.d: נָאַף nâʼaph, naw-af'; a primitive root;  to commit adultery; figuratively, to apostatize:—adulterer(-ess), commit(-ing) adultery, woman that breaketh wedlock.

h5006.d: נָאַץ nâʼats, naw-ats'; a primitive root;  to scorn; or (in Ecclesiastes 12:5), by interchange for H5132, to bloom:—abhor, (give occasion to) blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, × great, provoke.

h5007.d: נְאָצָה nᵉʼâtsâh, neh-aw-tsaw'; or נֶאָצָה neʼâtsâh; from H5006;  scorn:—blasphemy.
h5007.r: From נָאַץ (H5006)|English: despise, provoke, abhor, blaspheme, contemn, flourish, great occasion to blaspheme

h5008.d: נָאַק nâʼaq, naw-ak'; a primitive root;  to groan:—groan.

h501.d: אֶלְעָשָׂה ʼElʻâsâh, el-aw-saw'; from H410 and H6213; God has made;  Elasah, the name of four Israelites:—Elasah, Eleasah.
h501.r: From אֵל (H410) and עָשָׂה (H6213)|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

h5011.d: נֹב Nôb, nobe; the same as H5108; fruit;  Nob, a place in Palestine:—Nob.

h5012.d: נָבָא nâbâʼ, naw-baw'; a primitive root;  to prophesy, i.e. speak (or sing) by inspiration (in prediction or simple discourse):—prophesy(-ing), make self a prophet.

h5013.d: נְבָא nᵉbâʼ, neb-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5012:—prophesy.
h5013.r: Corresponding to נָבָא (H5012)|English: prophesy, prophesying, prophet

h5015.d: נְבוֹ Nᵉbôw, neb-o'; probably of foreign derivation;  Nebo, the name of a Babylonian deity, also of a mountain in Moab, and of a place in Palestine:—Nebo.
h5015.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h5018.d: נְבוּזַרְאֲדָן Nᵉbûwzarʼădân, neb-oo-zar-ad-awn'; of foreign origin;  Nebuzaradan, a Babylonian general:—Nebuzaradan.

h5019.d: נְבוּכַדְנֶאצַּר Nᵉbûwkadneʼtstsar, neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar'; or נְבֻּכַדְנֶאצַּר Nᵉbukadneʼtstsar; (2 Kings 24:1,10), or נְבוּכַדְנֶצַּר Nᵉbûwkadnetstsar; (Esther 2:6; Daniel 1:18), or נְבוּכַדְרֶאצַּר Nᵉbûwkadreʼtstsar; or נְבוּכַדְרֶאצּוֹר Nᵉbûwkadreʼtstsôwr; (Ezra 2:1; Jeremiah 49:28), or foreign derivation;  Nebukadnetstsar (or -retstsar, or -retstsor), king of Babylon:—Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar.

h502.d: אָלַף ʼâlaph, aw-lof'; a primitive root, to associate with;  hence, to learn (and causatively to teach):—learn, teach, utter.
h502.r: A primitive root, to associate with|

h5020.d: נְבוּכַדְנֶצַּר Nᵉbûwkadnetstsar, neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5019:—Nebuchadnezzar.

h5022.d: נָבוֹת Nâbôwth, naw-both'; feminine plural from the same as H5011; fruits;  Naboth, an Israelite:—Naboth.
h5022.r: From the same as נֹב (H5011)|English: Nob

h5024.d: נָבַח nâbach, naw-bakh'; a primitive root;  to bark (as a dog):—bark.

h5025.d: נֹבַח Nôbach, no'-bach; from H5024; a bark;  Nobach, the name of an Israelite, and of a place East of the Jordan:—Nobah.
h5025.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h5026.d: נִבְחַז Nibchaz, nib-khaz'; of foreign origin;  Nibchaz, a deity of the Avites:—Nibhaz.

h5027.d: נָבַט nâbaṭ, naw-bat'; a primitive root;  to scan, i.e. look intently at; by implication, to regard with pleasure, favor or care:—(cause to) behold, consider, look (down), regard, have respect, see.

h5029.d: נְבִיא nᵉbîyʼ, neb-ee'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5030;  a prophet:—prophet.
h5029.r: Corresponding to נָבִיא (H5030)|English: prophet, prophecy, them that prophesy, prophet, variant

h503.d: אָלַף ʼâlaph, aw-laf'; denominative from H505;  causative, to make a thousandfold:—bring forth thousands.
h503.r: Denominative from אֶלֶף (H505)|English: thousand, eleven hundred, variant, twelve hundred

h5030.d: נָבִיא nâbîyʼ, naw-bee'; from H5012;  a prophet or (generally) inspired man:—prophecy, that prophesy, prophet.

h5032.d: נְבָיוֹת Nᵉbâyôwth, neb-aw-yoth'; or נְבָיֹת Nᵉbâyôth; feminine plural from H5107; fruitfulnesses;  Nebajoth, a son of Ismael, and the country settled by him:—Nebaioth, Nebajoth.
h5032.r: From נוּב (H5107)|English: bring forth, increase, make cheerful

h5034.d: נָבֵל nâbêl, naw-bale'; a primitive root;  to wilt; generally, to fall away, fail, faint; figuratively, to be foolish or (morally) wicked; causatively, to despise, disgrace:—disgrace, dishounour, lightly esteem, fade (away, -ing), fall (down, -ling, off), do foolishly, come to nought, × surely, make vile, wither.

h5035.d: נֶבֶל nebel, neh'-bel; or נֵבֶל nêbel; from H5034;  a skin-bag for liquids (from collapsing when empty); hence, a vase (as similar in shape when full); also a lyre (as having a body of like form):—bottle, pitcher, psaltery, vessel, viol.
h5035.r: From נָבֵל (H5034)|English: fade, fade away, wear away, wither, disgrace, surely, dishonoureth, fall down, esteemed, falling, foolishly, come to nought, fall off, surely, make vile

h5036.d: נָבָל nâbâl, naw-bawl'; from H5034;  stupid; wicked (especially impious):—fool(-ish, -ish man, -ish woman), vile person.
h5036.r: From נָבֵל (H5034)|English: fade, fade away, wear away, wither, disgrace, surely, dishonoureth, fall down, esteemed, falling, foolishly, come to nought, fall off, surely, make vile

h5037.d: נָבָל Nâbâl, naw-bawl'; the same as H5036; dolt;  Nabal, an Israelite:—Nabal.
h5037.r: The same as נָבָל (H5036)|English: fool, foolish, vile person, foolish man, foolish women

h5038.d: נְבֵלָה nᵉbêlâh, neb-ay-law'; from H5034;  a flabby thing, i.e. a carcase or carrion (human or bestial, often collectively); figuratively, an idol:—(dead) body, (dead) carcase, dead of itself, which died, (beast) that (which) dieth of itself.
h5038.r: From נָבֵל (H5034)|English: fade, fade away, wear away, wither, disgrace, surely, dishonoureth, fall down, esteemed, falling, foolishly, come to nought, fall off, surely, make vile

h5039.d: נְבָלָה nᵉbâlâh, neb-aw-law'; feminine of H5036;  foolishness, i.e. (morally) wickedness; concretely, a crime; by extension, punishment:—folly, vile, villany.
h5039.r: From נָבָל (H5036)|English: fool, foolish, vile person, foolish man, foolish women

h504.d: אֶלֶף ʼeleph, eh'-lef; from H502;  a family; also (from the sense of yoking or taming) an ox or cow:—family, kine, oxen.

h5041.d: נְבַלָּט Nᵉballâṭ, neb-al-lawt'; apparently from H5036 and H3909; foolish secrecy;  Neballat, a place in Palestine:—Neballat.
h5041.r: Apparently from נָבָל (H5036) and לָט (H3909)|English: fool, foolish, vile person, foolish man, foolish women

h5042.d: נָבַע nâbaʻ, naw-bah'; a primitive root;  to gush forth; figuratively, to utter (good or bad words); specifically, to emit (a foul odor):—belch out, flowing, pour out, send forth, utter (abundantly).

h5045.d: נֶגֶב negeb, neh'-gheb; from an unused root meaning to be parched;  the south (from its drought); specifically, the Negeb or southern district of Judah, occasionally, Egypt (as south to Palestine):—south (country, side, -ward).
h5045.r: From an unused root meaning to be parched|

h5046.d: נָגַד nâgad, naw-gad'; a primitive root;  properly, to front, i.e. stand boldly out opposite; by implication (causatively), to manifest; figuratively, to announce (always by word of mouth to one present); specifically, to expose, predict, explain, praise:—bewray, × certainly, certify, declare(-ing), denounce, expound, × fully, messenger, plainly, profess, rehearse, report, shew (forth), speak, × surely, tell, utter.

h5047.d: נְגַד nᵉgad, neg-ad'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5046;  to flow (through the idea of clearing the way):—issue.
h5047.r: Corresponding to נָגַד (H5046)|English: tell, declare, shew, utter, shew forth, expound, messenger, report, misc

h5048.d: נֶגֶד neged, neh'-ghed; from H5046;  a front, i.e. part opposite; specifically a counterpart, or mate; usually (adverbial, especially with preposition) over against or before:—about, (over) against, × aloof, × far (off), × from, over, presence, × other side, sight, × to view.
h5048.r: From נָגַד (H5046)|English: tell, declare, shew, utter, shew forth, expound, messenger, report, misc

h5049.d: נֶגֶד neged, neh'-ghed; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5048;  opposite:—toward.
h5049.r: Corresponding to נֶגֶד (H5048)|English: before, against, in the presence, about

h505.d: אֶלֶף ʼeleph, eh'-lef; prop, the same as H504;  hence (the ox's head being the first letter of the alphabet, and this eventually used as a numeral) a thousand:—thousand.
h505.r: Prop, the same as אֶלֶף (H504)|English: kine, oxen, family

h5050.d: נָגַהּ nâgahh, naw-gah'; a primitive root;  to glitter; causatively, to illuminate:—(en-) lighten, (cause to) shine.

h5051.d: נֹגַהּ nôgahh, no'-gah; from H5050;  brilliancy (literally or figuratively):—bright(-ness), light, (clear) shining.

h5052.d: נֹגַהּ Nôgahh, no'-gah; the same as H5051;  Nogah, a son of David:—Nogah.
h5052.r: The same as נֹגַהּ (H5051)|English: brightness, shining, bright, light

h5055.d: נָגַח nâgach, naw-gakh'; a primitive root;  to butt with the horns; figuratively, to war against:—gore, push (down, -ing).

h5057.d: נָגִיד nâgîyd, naw-gheed'; or נָגִד nâgid; from H5046;  a commander (as occupying the front), civil, military or religious; generally (abstractly, plural), honorable themes:—captain, chief, excellent thing, (chief) governor, leader, noble, prince, (chief) ruler.
h5057.r: From נָגַד (H5046)|English: tell, declare, shew, utter, shew forth, expound, messenger, report, misc

h5059.d: נָגַן nâgan, naw-gan'; a primitive root;  properly, to thrum, i.e. beat a tune with the fingers; expectation. to play on a stringed instrument; hence (generally), to make music:—player on instruments, sing to the stringed instruments, melody, ministrel, play(-er, -ing).

h506.d: אֲלַף ʼălaph, al-af'; (Aramaic) or אֶלֶף ʼeleph; (Aramaic), corresponding to H505:—thousand.
h506.r: Corresponding to אֶלֶף (H505)|English: thousand, eleven hundred, variant, twelve hundred

h5060.d: נָגַע nâgaʻ, naw-gah'; a primitive root;  properly, to touch, i.e. lay the hand upon (for any purpose; euphemistically, to lie with a woman); by implication, to reach (figuratively, to arrive, acquire); violently, to strike (punish, defeat, destroy, etc.):—beat, (× be able to) bring (down), cast, come (nigh), draw near (nigh), get up, happen, join, near, plague, reach (up), smite, strike, touch.

h5061.d: נֶגַע negaʻ, neh'-gah; from H5060;  a blow (figuratively, infliction); also (by implication) a spot (concretely, a leprous person or dress):—plague, sore, stricken, stripe, stroke, wound.
h5061.r: From נָגַע (H5060)|English: touch, came, reach, bring, near, smite, nigh, plagued, happeneth, strike, beaten, cast, reach up, brought down, join, laid, get up

h5062.d: נָגַף nâgaph, naw-gaf'; a primitive root;  to push, gore, defeat, stub (the toe), inflict (a disease):—beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite (down), strike, stumble, × surely, put to the worse.

h5063.d: נֶגֶף negeph, neh'-ghef; from H5062;  a trip (of the foot); figuratively, an infliction (of disease):—plague, stumbling.
h5063.r: From נָגַף (H5062)|English: smite, put to the worse, smitten down, plague, hurt, slain, struck, stumble, beaten, dash, surely

h5064.d: נָגַר nâgar, naw-gar'; a primitive root;  to flow; figuratively, to stretch out; causatively, to pour out or down; figuratively, to deliver over:—fall, flow away, pour down (out), run, shed, spilt, trickle down.

h5065.d: נָגַשׂ nâgas, naw-gas'; a primitive root;  to drive (an animal, a workman, a debtor, an army); by implication, to tax, harass, tyrannize:—distress, driver, exact(-or), oppress(-or), × raiser of taxes, taskmaster.

h5066.d: נָגַשׁ nâgash, naw-gash'; a primitive root;  to be or come (causatively, bring) near (for any purpose); euphemistically, to lie with a woman; as an enemy, to attack; religious to worship; causatively, to present; figuratively, to adduce an argument; by reversal, to stand back:—(make to) approach (nigh), bring (forth, hither, near), (cause to) come (hither, near, nigh), give place, go hard (up), (be, draw, go) near (nigh), offer, overtake, present, put, stand.

h5067.d: נֵד nêd, nade; from H5110 in the sense of piling up;  a mound, i.e. wave:—heap.
h5067.r: From נוּד (H5110) in the sense of piling up|English: bemoan, remove, vagabond, flee, get, mourn, move, pity, shaken, skippedst, sorry, wag, wandering

h5068.d: נָדַב nâdab, naw-dab'; a primitive root;  to impel; hence, to volunteer (as a soldier), to present spontaneously:—offer freely, be (give, make, offer self) willing(-ly).

h5069.d: נְדַב nᵉdab, ned-ab'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5068;  be (or give) liberal(-ly):—(be minded of...own) freewill (offering), offer freely (willingly).
h5069.r: Corresponding to נָדַב (H5068)|English: offered willingly, willingly offered, willing, offered, willing, offered freely, give willingly

h5070.d: נָדָב Nâdâb, naw-dawb'; from H5068; liberal;  Nadab, the name of four Israelites:—Nadab.
h5070.r: From נָדַב (H5068)|English: offered willingly, willingly offered, willing, offered, willing, offered freely, give willingly

h5071.d: נְדָבָה nᵉdâbâh, ned-aw-baw'; from H5068;  properly (abstractly) spontaneity, or (adjectively) spontaneous; also (concretely) a spontaneous or (by inference, in plural) abundant gift:—free(-will) offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary(-ily, offering), willing(-ly), offering).
h5071.r: From נָדַב (H5068)|English: offered willingly, willingly offered, willing, offered, willing, offered freely, give willingly

h5073.d: נִדְבָּךְ nidbâk, nid-bawk'; (Aramaic) from a root meaning to stick;  a layer (of building materials):—row.
h5073.r: From a root meaning to stick|

h5074.d: נָדַד nâdad, naw-dad'; a primitive root;  properly, to wave to and fro (rarely to flap up and down); figuratively, to rove, flee, or (causatively) to drive away:—chase (away), × could not, depart, flee (× apace, away), (re-) move, thrust away, wander (abroad, -er, -ing).

h5075.d: נְדַד nᵉdad, ned-ad'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5074;  to depart:—go from.
h5075.r: Corresponding to נָדַד (H5074)|English: flee, wander, ....away, wandereth abroad, flee apace, chased, misc

h5076.d: נָדֻד nâdud, naw-dood'; passive participle of H5074;  properly, tossed; abstractly, a rolling (on the bed):—tossing to and fro.
h5076.r: Pass participle of נָדַד (H5074)|English: flee, wander, ....away, wandereth abroad, flee apace, chased, misc

h5077.d: נָדָה nâdâh, naw-daw'; or נָדָא nâdâʼ; (2 Kings 17:21), a primitive root;  properly, to toss; figuratively, to exclude, i.e. banish, postpone, prohibit:—cast out, drive, put far away.

h5078.d: נֵדֶה nêdeh, nay'-deh; from H5077 in the sense of freely flinging money;  a bounty (for prostitution):—gifts.
h5078.r: From נָדָה (H5077) in the sense of freely flinging money|English: cast you out, put far away, drive

h5079.d: נִדָּה niddâh, nid-daw'; from H5074;  properly, rejection; by implication, impurity, especially personal (menstruation) or moral (idolatry, incest):—× far, filthiness, × flowers, menstruous (woman), put apart, × removed (woman), separation, set apart, unclean(-ness, thing, with filthiness).
h5079.r: From נָדַד (H5074)|English: flee, wander, ....away, wandereth abroad, flee apace, chased, misc

h5080.d: נָדַח nâdach, naw-dakh'; a primitive root;  to push off; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (to expel, mislead, strike, inflict, etc.):—banish, bring, cast down (out), chase, compel, draw away, drive (away, out, quite), fetch a stroke, force, go away, outcast, thrust away (out), withdraw.

h5081.d: נָדִיב nâdîyb, naw-deeb'; from H5068;  properly, voluntary, i.e. generous; hence, magnanimous; as noun, a grandee (sometimes a tyrant):—free, liberal (things), noble, prince, willing (hearted).
h5081.r: From נָדַב (H5068)|English: offered willingly, willingly offered, willing, offered, willing, offered freely, give willingly

h5082.d: נְדִיבָה nᵉdîybâh, ned-ee-baw'; feminine of H5081;  properly, nobility, i.e. reputation:—soul.
h5082.r: From נָדִיב (H5081)|English: prince, nobles, willing, free, liberal, liberal things

h5086.d: נָדַף nâdaph, naw-daf'; a primitive root;  to shove asunder, i.e. disperse:—drive (away, to and fro), thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro.

h5087.d: נָדַר nâdar, naw-dar'; a primitive root;  to promise (pos., to do or give something to God):—(make a) vow.

h5088.d: נֶדֶר neder, neh'-der; or נֵדֶר nêder; from H5087;  a promise (to God); also (concretely) a thing promised:—vow(-ed).

h5090.d: נָהַג nâhag, naw-hag'; a primitive root;  to drive forth (a person, an animal or chariot), i.e. lead, carry away; reflexively, to proceed (i.e. impel or guide oneself); also (from the panting induced by effort), to sigh:—acquaint, bring (away), carry away, drive (away), lead (away, forth), (be) guide, lead (away, forth).

h5091.d: נָהָה nâhâh, naw-haw'; a primitive root;  to groan, i.e. bewail; hence (through the idea of crying aloud), to assemble (as if on proclamation):—lament, wail.

h5092.d: נְהִי nᵉhîy, neh-hee'; from H5091;  an elegy:—lamentation, wailing.

h5094.d: נְהִיר nᵉhîyr, neh-heere'; (Aramaic) or נְהִירוּ nᵉhîyrûw; (Aramaic), from the same as H5105;  illumination, i.e. (figuratively) wisdom:—light.
h5094.r: From the same as נְהָרָה (H5105)|English: light

h5096.d: נַהֲלָל Nahălâl, nah-hal-awl'; or נַהֲלֹל Nahălôl; the same as H5097;  Nahalal or Nahalol, a place in Palestine:—Nahalal, Nahallal, Nahalol.

h5101.d: נָהַק nâhaq, naw-hak'; a primitive root;  to bray (as an ass), scream (from hunger):—bray.

h5103.d: נְהַר nᵉhar, neh-har'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H5102;  a river, especially the Euphrates:—river, stream.
h5103.r: From a root corresponding to נָהַר (H5102)|English: flow together, flow, lightened

h5104.d: נָהָר nâhâr, naw-hawr'; from H5102;  a stream (including the sea; expectation the Nile, Euphrates, etc.); figuratively, prosperity:—flood, river.
h5104.r: From נָהַר (H5102)|English: flow together, flow, lightened

h5105.d: נְהָרָה nᵉhârâh, neh-haw-raw'; from H5102 in its original sense;  daylight:—light.
h5105.r: From נָהַר (H5102) in its original sense|English: flow together, flow, lightened

h5106.d: נוּא nûwʼ, noo; a primitive root;  to refuse, forbid, dissuade, or neutralize:—break, disallow, discourage, make of none effect.

h5107.d: נוּב nûwb, noob; a primitive root;  to germinate, i.e. (figuratively) to (causatively, make) flourish; also (of words), to utter:—bring forth (fruit), make cheerful, increase.

h5109.d: נוֹבַי Nôwbay, no-bah'ee; from H5108; fruitful;  Nobai, an Israelite:—Nebai (from the margin).

h511.d: אֶלְקָנָה ʼElqânâh, el-kaw-naw'; from H410 and H7069; God has obtained;  Elkanah, the name of several Israelites:—Elkanah.
h511.r: From אֵל (H410) and קָנָה (H7069)|English: God, god, power, mighty, goodly, great, idols, Immanuel, might, strong

h5110.d: נוּד nûwd, nood; a primitive root;  to nod, i.e. waver; figuratively, to wander, flee, disappear; also (from shaking the head in sympathy), to console, deplore, or (from tossing the head in scorn) taunt:—bemoan, flee, get, mourn, make to move, take pity, remove, shake, skip for joy, be sorry, vagabond, way, wandering.

h5111.d: נוּד nûwd, nood; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5116;  to flee:—get away.
h5111.r: Corresponding to נָוֶה (H5116)|English: habitation, fold, dwelling, sheepcote, comely, stable, dwelling place, pleasant place, tarried

h5116.d: נָוֶה nâveh, naw-veh'; or (feminine) נָוָה nâvâh; from H5115;  (adjectively) at home; hence (by implication of satisfaction) lovely; also (noun) a home, of God (temple), men (residence), flocks (pasture), or wild animals (den):—comely, dwelling (place), fold, habitation, pleasant place, sheepcote, stable, tarried.
h5116.r: From נָוָה (H5115)|English: keep at home, prepare an habitation

h5117.d: נוּחַ nûwach, noo'-akh; a primitive root;  to rest, i.e. settle down; used in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, intransitive, transitive and causative (to dwell, stay, let fall, place, let alone, withdraw, give comfort, etc.):—cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down. Compare H3241.

h5119.d: נוֹחָה Nôwchâh, no-chaw'; feminine of H5118; quietude;  Nochah, an Israelite:—Nohah.

h5123.d: נוּם nûwm, noom; a primitive root;  to slumber (from drowsiness):—sleep, slumber.

h5127.d: נוּס nûwç, noos; a primitive root;  to flit, i.e. vanish away (subside, escape; causatively, chase, impel, deliver):—× abate, away, be displayed, (make to) flee (away, -ing), put to flight, × hide, lift up a standard.

h5128.d: נוּעַ nûwaʻ, noo'-ah; a primitive root;  to waver, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (as subjoined):—continually, fugitive, × make, to (go) up and down, be gone away, (be) move(-able, -d), be promoted, reel, remove, scatter, set, shake, sift, stagger, to and fro, be vagabond, wag, (make) wander (up and down).

h5129.d: נוֹעַדְיָה Nôwʻadyâh, no-ad-yaw'; from H3259 and H3050; convened of Jah;  Noadjah, the name of an Israelite, and a false prophetess:—Noadiah.
h5129.s: proper feminine noun, proper masculine noun
h5129.r: From יָעַד (H3259) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: meet, together, assemble, appointed, set, time, betrothed, agreed, appointment, gather

h5130.d: נוּף nûwph, noof; a primitive root;  to quiver (i.e. vibrate up and down, or rock to and fro); used in a great variety of applications (including sprinkling, beckoning, rubbing, bastinadoing, sawing, waving, etc.):—lift up, move, offer, perfume, send, shake, sift, strike, wave.

h5132.d: נוּץ nûwts, noots; a primitive root;  properly, to flash; also, to fly away (from the quickness of motion):—flee away, bud (forth).

h5133.d: נוֹצָה nôwtsâh, no-tsaw'; or נֹצָה nôtsâh; feminine active participle of H5327 in the sense of flying;  a pinion (or wing feather); often (collectively) plumage:—feather(-s), ostrich.
h5133.r: From נָצָה (H5327) in the sense of flying|English: strive, strive together, laid waste,

h5135.d: נוּר nûwr, noor; (Aramaic) from an unused root (corresponding to that of H5216) meaning to shine;  fire:—fiery, fire.
h5135.r: From an unused root (corresponding to that of נִיר (H5216)) meaning to shine|English: lamp, candle, light

h5137.d: נָזָה nâzâh, naw-zaw'; a primitive root;  to spirt, i.e. besprinkle (especially in expiation):—sprinkle.

h5138.d: נָזִיד nâzîyd, naw-zeed'; from H2102;  something boiled, i.e. soup:—pottage.
h5138.r: From זוּד (H2102)|English: deal proudly, presumptuously, presume, proud, sod

h5139.d: נָזִיר nâzîyr, naw-zeer'; or נָזִר nâzir; from H5144;  separate, i.e. consecrated (as prince, a Nazirite); hence (figuratively from the latter) an unpruned vine (like an unshorn Nazirite):—Nazarite (by a false alliteration with Nazareth), separate(-d), vine undressed.

h514.d: אֶלְתְּקֵא ʼEltᵉqêʼ, el-te-kay'; or (more properly) אֶלְתְּקֵה ʼEltᵉqêh; of uncertain derivation;  Eltekeh or Elteke, a place in Palestine:—Eltekeh.

h5140.d: נָזַל nâzal, naw-zal'; a primitive root;  to drip, or shed by trickling:—distil, drop, flood, (cause to) flow(-ing), gush out, melt, pour (down), running water, stream.

h5141.d: נֶזֶם nezem, neh'-zem; from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  a nose-ring:—earring, jewel.
h5141.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h5142.d: נְזַק nᵉzaq, nez-ak'; (Aramaic) corresponding to the root of H5143;  to suffer (causatively, inflict) loss:—have (en-) damage, hurt(-ful).
h5142.r: Corresponding to the root of נֶזֶק (H5143)|English: damage

h5145.d: נֶזֶר nezer, neh'-zer; or נֵזֶר nêzer; from H5144;  properly, something set apart, i.e. (abstractly) dedication (of a priet or Nazirite); hence (concretely) unshorn locks; also (by implication) a chaplet (especially of royalty):—consecration, crown, hair, separation.

h5146.d: נֹחַ Nôach, no'-akh; the same as H5118; rest;  Noach, the patriarch of the flood:—Noah.
h5146.r: The same as נוּחַ (H5118)|English: rest, resting place

h5147.d: נַחְבִּי Nachbîy, nakh-bee'; from H2247; occult;  Nachbi, an Israelite:—Nakbi.

h5148.d: נָחָה nâchâh, naw-khaw'; a primitive root;  to guide; by implication, to transport (into exile, or as colonists):—bestow, bring, govern, guide, lead (forth), put, straiten.

h5149.d: נְחוּם Nᵉchûwm, neh-khoom'; from H5162; comforted;  Nechum, an Israelite:—Nehum.
h5149.r: From נָחַם (H5162)|English: comfort, repent, comforter, ease

h5150.d: נִחוּם nichûwm, nee-khoom'; or נִחֻם nichum; from H5162;  properly, consoled; abstractly, solace:—comfort(-able), repenting.
h5150.r: From נָחַם (H5162)|English: comfort, repent, comforter, ease

h5152.d: נָחוֹר Nâchôwr, naw-khore'; from the same as H5170; snorer;  Nachor, the name of the grandfather and a brother of Abraham:—Nahor.
h5152.r: From the same as נַחַר (H5170)|English: nostril, snorting

h5153.d: נָחוּשׁ nâchûwsh, naw-khoosh'; apparently passive participle of H5172 (perhaps in the sense of ringing), i.e. bell-metal; or from the red color of the throat of a serpent (H5175, as denominative) when hissing);  coppery, i.e. (figuratively) hard:—of brass.
h5153.r: Apparently pass participle of נָחַשׁ (H5172) (perhaps in the sense of ringing, i.e. bell-metal|English: enchantment, divine, enchanter, indeed, certainly, learn by experience, diligently observe

h5154.d: נְחוּשָׁה nᵉchûwshâh, nekh-oo-shaw'; or נְחֻשָׁה nᵉchushâh; feminine of H5153;  copper:—brass, steel. Compare H5176.

h5157.d: נָחַל nâchal, naw-khal'; a primitive root;  to inherit (as a (figurative) mode of descent), or (generally) to occupy; causatively, to bequeath, or (generally) distribute, instate:—divide, have (inheritance), take as a heritage, (cause to, give to, make to) inherit, (distribute for, divide (for, for an, by), give for, have, leave for, take (for)) inheritance, (have in, cause to, be made to) possess(-ion).

h5158.d: נַחַל nachal, nakh'-al; or (feminine) נַחְלָה nachlâh; (Psalm 124:4), or נַחֲלָה nachălâh; (Ezekiel 47:19; Ezekiel 48:28), from H5157 in its original sense;  a stream, especially a winter torrent; (by implication) a (narrow) valley (in which a brook runs); also a shaft (of a mine):—brook, flood, river, stream, valley.
h5158.r: From נָחַל (H5157) in its original sense|English: inherit, inheritance, possess, have, divide, heritage, possession, strong's synonym

h5159.d: נַחֲלָה nachălâh, nakh-al-aw'; from H5157 (in its usual sense);  properly, something inherited, i.e. (abstractly) occupancy, or (concretely) an heirloom; generally an estate, patrimony or portion:—heritage, to inherit, inheritance, possession. Compare H5158.
h5159.r: From נָחַל (H5157) (in its usual sense)|English: inherit, inheritance, possess, have, divide, heritage, possession, strong's synonym

h5162.d: נָחַם nâcham, naw-kham'; a primitive root;  properly, to sigh, i.e. breathe strongly; by implication, to be sorry, i.e. (in a favorable sense) to pity, console or (reflexively) rue; or (unfavorably) to avenge (oneself):—comfort (self), ease (one's self), repent(-er,-ing, self).

h5164.d: נֹחַם nôcham, no'-kham; from H5162;  ruefulness, i.e. desistance:—repentance.
h5164.r: From נָחַם (H5162)|English: comfort, repent, comforter, ease

h5166.d: נְחֶמְיָה Nᵉchemyâh, nekh-em-yaw'; from H5162 and H3050; consolation of Jah;  Nechemjah, the name of three Israelites:—Nehemiah.
h5166.r: From נָחַם (H5162) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: comfort, repent, comforter, ease

h5167.d: נַחֲמָנִי Nachămânîy, nakh-am-aw-nee'; from H5162; consolatory;  Nachamani, an Israelite:—Nahamani.
h5167.r: From נָחַם (H5162)|English: comfort, repent, comforter, ease

h5168.d: נַחְנוּ nachnûw, nakh-noo'; for H587;  we:—we.

h517.d: אֵם ʼêm, ame; a primitive word;  a mother (as the bond of the family); in a wide sense (both literally and figuratively [like father]):—dam, mother, × parting.

h5170.d: נַחַר nachar, nakh'-ar; and (feminine) נַחֲרָה nachărâh; from an unused root meaning to snort or snore;  a snorting:—nostrils, snorting.
h5170.r: From an unused root meaning to snort or snore|

h5171.d: נַחֲרַי Nachăray, nakh-ar-ah'-ee; or נַחְרַי Nachray; from the same as H5170; snorer;  Nacharai or Nachrai, an Israelite:—Naharai, Nahari.
h5171.r: From the same as נַחַר (H5170)|English: nostril, snorting

h5172.d: נָחַשׁ nâchash, naw-khash'; a primitive root;  properly, to hiss, i.e. whisper a (magic) spell; generally, to prognosticate:—× certainly, divine, enchanter, (use) × enchantment, learn by experience, × indeed, diligently observe.

h5173.d: נַחַשׁ nachash, nakh'-ash; from H5172;  an incantation or augury:—enchantment.
h5173.r: From נָחַשׁ (H5172)|English: enchantment, divine, enchanter, indeed, certainly, learn by experience, diligently observe

h5174.d: נְחָשׁ nᵉchâsh, nekh-awsh'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5154;  copper:—brass.

h5175.d: נָחָשׁ nâchâsh, naw-khawsh'; from H5172;  a snake (from its hiss):—serpent.
h5175.r: From נָחַשׁ (H5172)|English: enchantment, divine, enchanter, indeed, certainly, learn by experience, diligently observe

h5177.d: נַחְשׁוֹן Nachshôwn, nakh-shone'; from H5172; enchanter;  Nachshon, an Israelite:—Naashon, Nahshon.
h5177.r: From נָחַשׁ (H5172)|English: enchantment, divine, enchanter, indeed, certainly, learn by experience, diligently observe

h5178.d: נְחֹשֶׁת nᵉchôsheth, nekh-o'-sheth; for H5154;  copper, hence, something made of that metal, i.e. coin, a fetter; figuratively, base (as compared with gold or silver):—brasen, brass, chain, copper, fetter (of brass), filthiness, steel.

h518.d: אִם ʼim, eem; a primitive particle;  used very widely as demonstrative, lo!; interrogative, whether?; or conditional, if, although; also Oh that!, when; hence, as a negative, not:—(and, can-, doubtless, if, that) (not), + but, either, + except, + more(-over if, than), neither, nevertheless, nor, oh that, or, + save (only, -ing), seeing, since, sith, + surely (no more, none, not), though, + of a truth, + unless, + verily, when, whereas, whether, while, + yet.

h5180.d: נְחֻשְׁתָּן Nᵉchushtân, nekh-oosh-tawn'; from H5178;  something made of copper, i.e. the copper serpent of the Desert:—Nehushtan.
h5180.r: From נְחשֶׁת (H5178)|English: brass, brasen, fetters, chain, copper, filthiness, steel

h5181.d: נָחַת nâchath, naw-khath'; a primitive root;  to sink, i.e. descend; causatively, to press or lead down:—be broken, (cause to) come down, enter, go down, press sore, settle, stick fast.

h5183.d: נַחַת Nachath, nakh'-ath; from H5182; also (intransitively; perhaps from H5117)  a descent, i.e. imposition, unfavorable (punishment) or favorable (food); restfulness:—lighting down, quiet(-ness), to rest, be set on.
h5183.r: From נְחַת (H5182)|English: come down, carry, place, laid up, deposed

h5184.d: נַחַת Nachath, nakh'-ath; the same as H5183; quiet;  Nachath, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites:—Nahath.
h5184.r: The same as נַחַת (H5183)|English: rest, set on, quietness, quiet, lighting down

h5185.d: נָחֵת nâchêth, naw-khayth'; from H5181;  descending:—come down.
h5185.r: From נָחַת (H5181)|English: broken, come down, enter, stick fast, settle, press sore, strong's synonym

h5186.d: נָטָה nâṭâh, naw-taw'; a primitive root;  to stretch or spread out; by implication, to bend away (including moral deflection); used in a great variety of application (as follows):—  afternoon, apply, bow (down, -ing), carry aside, decline, deliver, extend, go down, be gone, incline, intend, lay, let down, offer, outstretched, overthrown, pervert, pitch, prolong, put away, shew, spread (out), stretch (forth, out), take (aside), turn (aside, away), wrest, cause to yield.

h5189.d: נְטִישָׁה nᵉṭîyshâh, net-ee-shaw'; from H5203;  a tendril (as an offshoot):—battlement, branch, plant.
h5189.r: From נָטַשׁ (H5203)|English: forsake, leave, spread, spread abroad, drawn, fall, joined, lie, loosed, cast off, misc

h519.d: אָמָה ʼâmâh, aw-maw'; apparently a primitive word;  a maid-servant or female slave:—(hand-) bondmaid(-woman), maid(-servant).

h5192.d: נֵטֶל nêṭel, nay'-tel; from H5190;  a burden:—weighty.

h5193.d: נָטַע nâṭaʻ, naw-tah'; a primitive root;  properly, to strike in, i.e. fix; specifically, to plant (literally or figuratively):—fastened, plant(-er).

h5194.d: נֶטַע neṭaʻ, neh'-tah; from H5193;  a plant; collectively, a plantation; abstractly, a planting:—plant.

h5195.d: נָטִיעַ nâṭîyaʻ, naw-tee'-ah; from H5193;  a plant:—plant.

h5197.d: נָטַף nâṭaph, naw-taf'; a primitive root;  to ooze, i.e. distil gradually; by implication, to fall in drops; figuratively, to speak by inspiration:—drop(-ping), prophesy(-et).

h5198.d: נָטָף nâṭâph, naw-tawf'; from H5197;  a drop; specifically, an aromatic gum (probably stacte):—drop, stacte.
h5198.r: From נָטַף (H5197)|English: drop, prophesy, prophet, down

h52.d: אֲבִישַׁי ʼĂbîyshay, ab-ee-shah'ee; or (shorter) אַבְשַׁי ʼAbshay ; from H1 and H7862; father of a gift (i.e. probably generous);  Abishai, an Israelite:—Abishai.
h52.r: From אָב (H1) and שַׁי (H7862)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h520.d: אַמָּה ʼammâh, am-maw'; prolonged from H517;  properly, a mother (i.e. unit of measure, or the fore-arm (below the elbow), i.e. a cubit; also a door-base (as a bond of the entrance):—cubit, + hundred (by exchange for H3967), measure, post.
h520.r: Prolonged from אֵם (H517)|English: mother, dam, parting

h5203.d: נָטַשׁ nâṭash, naw-tash'; a primitive root;  properly, to pound, i.e. smite; by implication (as if beating out, and thus expanding) to disperse; also, to thrust off, down, out or upon (inclusively, reject, let alone, permit, remit, etc.):—cast off, drawn, let fall, forsake, join (battle), leave (off), lie still, loose, spread (self) abroad, stretch out, suffer.

h5208.d: נִיחוֹחַ nîychôwach, nee-kho'-akh; (Aramaic) or נִיחֹחַ nîychôach; (shorter) (Aramaic), corresponding to H5207;  pleasure:—sweet odour (savour).
h5208.r: Corresponding to נִיחֹחַ (H5207)|English: sweet, sweet odours

h5209.d: נִין nîyn, neen; from H5125;  progeny:—son.

h521.d: אַמָּה ʼammâh, am-maw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H520:—cubit.
h521.r: Corresponding to אַמָּה (H520)|English: cubit, measure, post, not translated

h5210.d: נִינְוֵה Nîynᵉvêh, nee-nev-ay'; of foreign origin;  Nineveh, the capital of Assyria:—Nineveh.

h5212.d: נִיסָן Nîyçân, nee-sawn'; probably of foreign origin;  Nisan, the first month of the Jewish sacred year:—Nisan.

h5214.d: נִיר nîyr, neer; a root probably identical with that of H5216, through the idea of the gleam of a fresh furrow;  to till the soil:—break up.
h5214.r: A root probably identical with that of נִיר (H5216), through the idea of the gleam of a fresh furrow|English: lamp, candle, light

h5215.d: נִיר nîyr, neer; or נִר nir; from H5214;  properly, plowing, i.e. (concretely) freshly plowed land:—fallow ground, plowing, tillage.

h5216.d: נִיר nîyr, neer; or נִר nir; also נֵיר nêyr; or נֵר nêr; or (feminine) נֵרָה nêrâh; from a primitive root (see H5214; H5135) properly, meaning to glisten;  a lamp (i.e. the burner) or light (literally or figuratively):—candle, lamp, light.
h5216.r: From a primitive root [see נִיר (H5214); נוּר (H5135)] properly, meaning to glisten|English: break up

h5218.d: נָכֵא nâkêʼ, naw-kay'; or נָכָא nâkâʼ; from H5217;  smitten, i.e. (figuratively) afflicted:—broken, stricken, wounded.

h5219.d: נְכֹאת nᵉkôʼth, nek-ohth'; from H5218;  properly, a smiting, i.e. (concretely) an aromatic gum (perhaps styrax) (as powdered):—spicery(-ces).

h5221.d: נָכָה nâkâh, naw-kaw'; a primitive root;  to strike (lightly or severely, literally or figuratively):—beat, cast forth, clap, give (wounds), × go forward, × indeed, kill, make (slaughter), murderer, punish, slaughter, slay(-er, -ing), smite(-r, -ing), strike, be stricken, (give) stripes, × surely, wound.

h5223.d: נָכֶה nâkeh, naw-keh';   smitten, i.e. (literally) maimed, or (figuratively) dejected:—contrite, lame.

h5224.d: נְכוֹ Nᵉkôw, nek-o'; probably of Egyptian origin;  Neko, an Egyptian king:—Necho. Compare H6549.

h5227.d: נֹכַח nôkach, no'-kakh; from the same as H5226;  properly, the front part; used adverbially (especially with preposition), opposite, in front of, forward, in behalf of:—(over) against, before, direct(-ly), for, right (on).
h5227.r: From the same as נֵכַח (H5226)|English: before, against

h5229.d: נְכֹחָה nᵉkôchâh, nek-o-khaw'; feminine of H5228;  properly, straightforwardness, i.e. (figuratively) integrity, or (concretely) a truth:—equity, right (thing), uprightness.

h523.d: אֻמַּה ʼummah, oom-maw'; from the same as H517;  a collection, i.e. community of persons:—nation, people.
h523.r: From the same as אֵם (H517)|English: mother, dam, parting

h5230.d: נָכַל nâkal, naw-kal'; a primitive root;  to defraud, i.e. act treacherously:—beguile, conspire, deceiver, deal subtilly.

h5233.d: נֶכֶס nekeç, neh'-kes; from an unused root meaning to accumulate;  treasure:—riches, wealth.
h5233.r: From an unused root meaning to accumulate|

h5234.d: נָכַר nâkar, naw-kar'; a primitive root;  properly, to scrutinize, i.e. look intently at; hence (with recognition implied), to acknowledge, be acquainted with, care for, respect, revere, or (with suspicion implied), to disregard, ignore, be strange toward, reject, resign, dissimulate (as if ignorant or disowning):—acknowledge, × could, deliver, discern, dissemble, estrange, feign self to be another, know, take knowledge (notice), perceive, regard, (have) respect, behave (make) self strange(-ly).

h5236.d: נֵכָר nêkâr, nay-kawr'; ' from H5234;  foreign, or (concretely) a foreigner, or (abstractly) heathendom:—alien, strange (+ -er).
h5236.r: From נָכַר (H5234)|English: know, acknowledge, discern, respect, knowledge, known, feign to another, misc

h5237.d: נׇכְרִי nokrîy, nok-ree'; from H5235 (second form);  strange, in a variety of degrees and applications (foreign, non-relative, adulterous, different, wonderful):—alien, foreigner, outlandish, strange(-r, woman).

h524.d: אֻמָּה ʼummâh, oom-maw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H523:—nation.

h5241.d: נְמוּאֵל Nᵉmûwʼêl, nem-oo-ale'; apparently for H3223;  Nemuel, the name of two Israelites:—Nemuel.

h5246.d: נָמֵר nâmêr, naw-mare'; from an unused root meaning properly, to filtrate, i.e. be limpid (comp H5247 and H5249); and thus to spot or stain as if by dripping;  a leopard (from its stripes):—leopard.
h5246.r: From an unused root meaning properly, to filtrate, i.e. be limpid [comp נִמְרָה (H5247) and נִמְרִים (H5249)]|English: Nimrah

h5247.d: נִמְרָה Nimrâh, nim-raw'; from the same as H5246; clear water;  Nimrah, a place East of the Jordan:—Nimrah. See also H1039, H5249.
h5247.r: From the same as נָמֵר (H5246)|English: leopard

h5248.d: נִמְרוֹד Nimrôwd, nim-rode'; or נִמְרֹד Nimrôd; probably of foreign origin;  Nimrod, a son of Cush:—Nimrod.

h525.d: אָמוֹן ʼâmôwn, aw-mone'; from H539, probably in the sense of training; like H542  skilled, i.e. an architect:—one brought up.
h525.r: From אָמַן (H539), probably in the sense of training|English: believe, assurance, faithful, sure, established, trust, verified, stedfast, continuance, father, bring up, nurse, be nursed, surely be, stand fast, fail, trusty

h5254.d: נָסָה nâçâh, naw-saw'; a primitive root;  to test; by implication, to attempt:—adventure, assay, prove, tempt, try.

h5255.d: נָסַח nâçach, naw-sakh'; a primitive root;  to tear away:—destroy, pluck, root.

h5257.d: נְסִיךְ nᵉçîyk, nes-eek'; from H5258;  properly, something poured out, i.e. a libation; also a molten image; by implication, a prince (as anointed):—drink offering, duke, prince(-ipal).
h5257.r: From נָסַךְ (H5258)|English: pour out, pour, cover, offer, melteth, molten, set, set up

h5258.d: נָסַךְ nâçak, naw-sak'; a primitive root;  to pour out, especially a libation, or to cast (metal); by analogy, to anoint a king:—cover, melt, offer, (cause to) pour (out), set (up).

h526.d: אָמוֹן ʼÂmôwn, aw-mone'; the same as H525;  Amon, the name of three Israelites:—Amon.
h526.r: The same as אָמוֹן (H525)|English: one brought up

h5261.d: נְסַךְ nᵉçak, nes-ak'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5262;  a libation:—drink offering.
h5261.r: Corresponding to נֶסֶךְ (H5262)|English: offering, image, cover withal

h5262.d: נֶסֶךְ neçek, neh'-sek; or נֵסֶךְ nêçek; from H5258;  a libation; also a cast idol:—cover, drink offering, molten image.
h5262.r: From נָסַךְ (H5258)|English: pour out, pour, cover, offer, melteth, molten, set, set up

h5263.d: נָסַס nâçaç, naw-sas'; a primitive root;  to wane, i.e. be sick:—faint.

h5265.d: נָסַע nâçaʻ, naw-sah'; a primitive root;  properly, to pull up, especially the tent-pins, i.e. start on a journey:—cause to blow, bring, get, (make to) go (away, forth, forward, onward, out), (take) journey, march, remove, set aside (forward), × still, be on his (go their) way.

h5267.d: נְסַק nᵉçaq, nes-ak'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5266:—take up.

h5270.d: נֹעָה Nôʻâh, no-aw'; from H5128; movement;  Noah, an Israelitess:—Noah.
h5270.r: From נוּעַ (H5128)|English: shake, wander, move, promoted, fugitive, sift, stagger, wag, misc

h5273.d: נָעִים nâʻîym, naw-eem'; from H5276;  delightful (objective or subjective, literal or figurative):—pleasant(-ure), sweet.
h5273.r: From נָעֵם (H5276)|English: pleasant, sweet, beauty, delight

h5274.d: נָעַל nâʻal, naw-al'; a primitive root; also denominative from H5275  properly, to fasten up, i.e. with a bar or cord; hence, to sandal, i.e. furnish with slippers:—bolt, inclose, lock, shoe, shut up.

h5275.d: נַעַל naʻal, nah'-al; or (feminine) נַעֲלָה naʻălâh; from H5274;  properly, a sandal tongue; by extension a sandal or slipper (sometimes as a symbol of occupancy, a refusal to marry, or of something valueless):—dryshod, (pair of) shoe((-latchet), -s).
h5275.r: From נָעַל (H5274)|English: lock, bolt, shod, inclosed, shut up

h5276.d: נָעֵם nâʻêm, naw-ame'; a primitive root;  to be agreeable (literally or figuratively):—pass in beauty, be delight, be pleasant, be sweet.

h5278.d: נֹעַם nôʻam, no'-am; from H5276;  agreeableness, i.e. delight, suitableness, splendor or grace:—beauty, pleasant(-ness).
h5278.r: From נָעֵם (H5276)|English: pleasant, sweet, beauty, delight

h528.d: אָמוֹן ʼÂmôwn, aw-mone'; of Egyptian derivation; used only as an adjunct of H4996  Amon (i.e. Ammon or Amn), a deity of Egypt:—multitude, populous.

h5281.d: נׇעֳמִי Noʻŏmîy, no-om-ee'; from H5278; pleasant;  Noömi, an Israelitess:—Naomi.

h5282.d: נַעֲמָן naʻămân, nah-am-awn'; from H5276;  pleasantness (plural as concrete):—pleasant.
h5282.r: From נָעֵם (H5276)|English: pleasant, sweet, beauty, delight

h5283.d: נַעֲמָן Naʻămân, nah-am-awn'; the same as H5282;  Naaman, the name of an Israelite and of a Damascene:—Naaman.

h5287.d: נָעַר nâʻar, naw-ar'; a primitive root (probably identical with H5286, through the idea of the rustling of mane, which usually accompanies the lion's roar);  to tumble about:—shake (off, out, self), overthrow, toss up and down.
h5287.r: A primitive root [probably identical with נָעַר (H5286), through the idea of the rustling of mane, which usually accompanies the lion's roar]|English: yell

h5288.d: נַעַר naʻar, nah'-ar; from H5287;  (concretely) a boy (as active), from the age of infancy to adolescence; by implication, a servant; also (by interch. of sex), a girl (of similar latitude in age):—babe, boy, child, damsel (from the margin), lad, servant, young (man).
h5288.r: From נָעַר (H5287)|English: shake, shake out, overthrow, toss to and fro, shake off

h529.d: אֵמוּן ʼêmûwn, ay-moon'; from H539;  established, i.e. (figuratively) trusty; also (abstractly) trustworthiness:—faith(-ful), truth.
h529.r: From אָמַן (H539)|English: believe, assurance, faithful, sure, established, trust, verified, stedfast, continuance, father, bring up, nurse, be nursed, surely be, stand fast, fail, trusty

h5291.d: נַעֲרָה naʻărâh, nah-ar-aw'; feminine of H5288;  a girl (from infancy to adolescence):—damsel, maid(-en), young (woman).
h5291.r: From נַעַר (H5288)|English: young man, servant, child, lad, young, children, youth, babe, boys, young

h5292.d: נַעֲרָה Naʻărâh, nah-ar-aw'; the same as H5291;  Naarah, the name of an Israelitess, and of a place in Palestine:—Naarah, Naarath.
h5292.s: proper feminine noun, proper locative noun
h5292.r: The same as נַעֲרָה (H5291)|English: damsel, maiden, maid, young, young woman

h5293.d: נַעֲרַי Naʻăray, nah-ar-ah'-ee; from H5288; youthful;  Naarai, an Israelite:—Naarai.
h5293.r: From נַעַר (H5288)|English: young man, servant, child, lad, young, children, youth, babe, boys, young

h5294.d: נְעַרְיָה Nᵉʻaryâh, neh-ar-yaw'; from H5288 and H3050; servant of Jah;  Nearjah, the name of two Israelites:—Neariah.
h5294.r: From נַעַר (H5288) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: young man, servant, child, lad, young, children, youth, babe, boys, young

h5295.d: נַעֲרָן Naʻărân, nah-ar-awn'; from H5288; juvenile;  Naaran, a place in Palestine:—Naaran.
h5295.r: From נַעַר (H5288)|English: young man, servant, child, lad, young, children, youth, babe, boys, young

h5296.d: נְעֹרֶת nᵉʻôreth, neh-o'-reth; from H5287;  something shaken out, i.e. tow (as the refuse of flax):—tow.
h5296.r: From נָעַר (H5287)|English: shake, shake out, overthrow, toss to and fro, shake off

h5297.d: נֹף Nôph, nofe; a variation of H4644;  Noph, the capital of Upper Egypt:—Noph.

h5298.d: נֶפֶג Nepheg, neh'-feg; from an unused root probably meaning to spring forth; a sprout;  Nepheg, the name of two Israelites:—Nepheg.
h5298.r: From an unused root probably meaning to spring forth|

h53.d: אֲבִישָׁלוֹם ʼĂbîyshâlôwm, ab-ee-shaw-lome'; or (shortened) אַבְשָׁלוֹם ʼAbshâlôwm ; from H1 and H7965; father of peace (i.e. friendly);  Abshalom, a son of David; also (the fuller form) a later Israelite:—Abishalom, Absalom.
h53.r: From אָב (H1) and שָׁלוֹם (H7965)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h530.d: אֱמוּנָה ʼĕmûwnâh, em-oo-naw'; or (shortened) אֱמֻנָה ʼĕmunâh; feminine of H529;  literally firmness; figuratively security; morally fidelity:—faith(-ful, -ly, -ness, (man)), set office, stability, steady, truly, truth, verily.

h5304.d: נְפִיסִים Nᵉphîyçîym, nef-ee-seem'; plural from an unused root meaning to scatter; expansions;  Nephisim, a Temple-servant:—Nephusim (from the margin).
h5304.r: From an unused root meaning to scatter|

h5305.d: נָפִישׁ Nâphîysh, naw-feesh'; from H5314; refreshed;  Naphish, a son of Ishmael, and his posterity:—Naphish.

h5306.d: נֹפֶךְ nôphek, no'-fek; from an unused root meaning to glisten;  shining; a gem, probably the garnet:—emerald.
h5306.r: From an unused root meaning to glisten|

h5307.d: נָפַל nâphal, naw-fal'; a primitive root;  to fall, in a great variety of applications (intransitive or causative, literal or figurative):—be accepted, cast (down, self, (lots), out), cease, die, divide (by lot), (let) fail, (cause to, let, make, ready to) fall (away, down, -en, -ing), fell(-ing), fugitive, have (inheritance), inferior, be judged (by mistake for 6419), lay (along), (cause to) lie down, light (down), be (× hast) lost, lying, overthrow, overwhelm, perish, present(-ed, -ing), (make to) rot, slay, smite out, × surely, throw down.

h5308.d: נְפַל nᵉphal, nef-al'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5307:—fall (down), have occasion.
h5308.r: Corresponding to נָפַל (H5307)|English: fail, fall down, cast, cast down, fall away, divide, overthrow, present, lay, rot, accepted, lie down, inferior, lighted, lost, misc

h5310.d: נָפַץ nâphats, naw-fats'; a primitive root;  to dash to pieces, or scatter:—be beaten in sunder, break (in pieces), broken, dash (in pieces), cause to be discharged, dispersed, be overspread, scatter.

h5312.d: נְפַק nᵉphaq, nef-ak'; (Aramaic) a primitive root;  to issue; causatively, to bring out:—come (go, take) forth (out).

h5313.d: נִפְקָא niphqâʼ, nif-kaw'; (Aramaic) from H5312;  an outgo, i.e. expense:—expense.
h5313.r: From נְפַק (H5312)|English: take out, come forth, go forth, take forth,

h5315.d: נֶפֶשׁ nephesh, neh'-fesh; from H5314;  properly, a breathing creature, i.e. animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental):—any, appetite, beast, body, breath, creature, × dead(-ly), desire, × (dis-) contented, × fish, ghost,   greedy, he, heart(-y), (hath, × jeopardy of) life (× in jeopardy), lust, man, me, mind, mortally, one, own, person, pleasure, (her-, him-, my-, thy-) self, them (your) -selves,   slay, soul,   tablet, they, thing, (× she) will, × would have it.

h5317.d: נֹפֶת nôpheth, no'-feth; from H5130 in the sense of shaking to pieces;  a dripping i.e. of honey (from the comb):—honeycomb.
h5317.r: From נוּף (H5130) in the sense of shaking to pieces|English: wave, shake, offer, lift up, move, perfumed, send, sift, strike

h5321.d: נַפְתָּלִי Naphtâlîy, naf-taw-lee'; from H6617; my wrestling;  Naphtali, a son of Jacob, with the tribe descended from him, and its territory:—Naphtali.
h5321.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h5321.r: From פָּתַל (H6617)|English: froward, shew..froward, wrestle, shew unsavoury

h5324.d: נָצַב nâtsab, naw-tsab'; a primitive root;  to station, in various applications (literally or figuratively):—appointed, deputy, erect, establish, × Huzzah (by mistake for a proper name), lay, officer, pillar, present, rear up, set (over, up), settle, sharpen, establish, (make to) stand(-ing, still, up, upright), best state.

h5327.d: נָצָה nâtsâh, naw-tsaw'; a primitive root;  properly, to go forth, i.e. (by implication) to be expelled, and (consequently) desolate; causatively, to lay waste; also (specifically), to quarrel:—be laid waste, runinous, strive (together).

h5329.d: נָצַח nâtsach, naw-tsakh'; a primitive root; also as denominative from H5331  properly, to glitter from afar, i.e. to be eminent (as a superintendent, especially of the Temple services and its music); to be permanent:—excel, chief musician (singer), oversee(-r), set forward.

h5331.d: נֶצַח netsach, neh'-tsakh; or נֵצַח nêtsach; from H5329;  properly, a goal, i.e. the bright object at a distance travelled towards; hence (figuratively), splendor, or (subjectively) truthfulness, or (objectively) confidence; but usually (adverbially), continually (i.e. to the most distant point of view):—alway(-s), constantly, end, (+ n-) ever(more), perpetual, strength, victory.
h5331.r: From נָצַח (H5329)|English: Musician, set forward, overseers, excel, oversee, perpetual, chief singer

h5333.d: נְצִיב nᵉtsîyb, nets-eeb'; or נְצִב nᵉtsib; from H5324;  something stationary, i.e. a prefect, a military post, a statue:—garrison, officer, pillar.
h5333.r: From נָצַב (H5324)|English: stand, set, officers, set up, upright, appointed, deputy, erected, establish, Huzzab, misc

h5337.d: נָצַל nâtsal, naw-tsal'; a primitive root;  to snatch away, whether in a good or a bad sense:—× at all, defend, deliver (self), escape, × without fail, part, pluck, preserve, recover, rescue, rid, save, spoil, strip, × surely, take (out).

h534.d: אָמִיר ʼâmîyr, aw-meer'; apparently from H559 (in the sense of self-exaltation);  a summit (of a tree or mountain):—bough, branch.
h534.r: Apparently from אָמַר (H559) (sense of self-exaltation)|English: said, speak, answer, command, tell, call, promised, misc.

h5340.d: נָצַץ nâtsats, naw-tsats'; a primitive root;  to glare, i.e. be bright-colored:—sparkle.

h5341.d: נָצַר nâtsar, naw-tsar'; a primitive root;  to guard, in a good sense (to protect, maintain, obey, etc.) or a bad one (to conceal, etc.):—besieged, hidden thing, keep(-er, -ing), monument, observe, preserve(-r), subtil, watcher(-man).

h5342.d: נֵצֶר nêtser, nay'-tser; from H5341 in the sense of greenness as a striking color;  a shoot; figuratively, a descendant:—branch.
h5342.r: From נָצַר (H5341) in the sense of greenness as a striking colour|English: keep, preserve, watchmen, besieged, keeper, monuments, observe, preserver, subtil, hidden things, watchers

h5344.d: נָקַב nâqab, naw-kab'; a primitive root;  to puncture, literally (to perforate, with more or less violence) or figuratively (to specify, designate, libel):—appoint, blaspheme, bore, curse, express, with holes, name, pierce, strike through.

h5347.d: נְקֵבָה nᵉqêbâh, nek-ay-baw'; from H5344;  female (from the sexual form):—female.
h5347.r: From נָקַב (H5344)|English: curse, expressed, blaspheme, bore, name, pierce, Appoint, holes, pierce through, strike through

h5348.d: נָקֹד nâqôd, naw-kode'; from an unused root meaning to mark (by puncturing or branding);  spotted:—speckled.
h5348.r: From an unused root meaning to mark (by puncturing or branding)|

h535.d: אָמַל ʼâmal, aw-mal'; a primitive root;  to droop; by implication to be sick, to mourn:—languish, be weak, wax feeble.

h5352.d: נָקָה nâqâh, naw-kaw'; a primitive root;  to be (or make) clean (literally or figuratively); by implication (in an adverse sense) to be bare, i.e. extirpated:—acquit × at all, × altogether, be blameless, cleanse, (be) clear(-ing), cut off, be desolate, be free, be (hold) guiltless, be (hold) innocent, × by no means, be quit, be (leave) unpunished, × utterly, × wholly.

h5355.d:
נָקִי nâqîy, naw-kee'; or נָקִיא nâqîyʼ; (Joel 4:19 [Joel 3:19][1]; Jonah 1:14), from H5352;  innocent:—blameless, clean, clear, exempted, free, guiltless, innocent, quit.


    
    
        1. Edited by BLB [Strong's references Joel 4:19 in the Hebrew Bible]
h5355.r: From נָקָה (H5352)|English: unpunished, guiltless, innocent, clear, cleanse, free, by no means, acquit, altogether, cut off, at all, blameless, desolate, quit, utterly, wholly

h5356.d: נִקָּיוֹן niqqâyôwn, nik-kaw-yone'; or נִקָּיֹן niqqâyôn; from H5352;  clearness (literally or figuratively):—cleanness, innocency.
h5356.r: From נָקָה (H5352)|English: unpunished, guiltless, innocent, clear, cleanse, free, by no means, acquit, altogether, cut off, at all, blameless, desolate, quit, utterly, wholly

h5358.d: נָקַם nâqam, naw-kam'; a primitive root;  to grudge, i.e. avenge or punish:—avenge(-r, self), punish, revenge (self), × surely, take vengeance.

h5359.d: נָקָם nâqâm, naw-kawm'; from H5358;  revenge:—  avenged, quarrel, vengeance.
h5359.r: From נָקַם (H5358)|English: avenge, vengeance, revenge, take, avenger, punished, surely

h5360.d: נְקָמָה nᵉqâmâh, nek-aw-maw'; feminine of H5359;  avengement, whether the act or the passion:—  avenge, revenge(-ing), vengeance.

h5362.d: נָקַף nâqaph, naw-kaf'; a primitive root;  to strike with more or less violence (beat, fell, corrode); by implication (of attack) to knock together, i.e. surround or circulate:—compass (about, -ing), cut down, destroy, go round (about), inclose, round.

h5367.d: נָקַשׁ nâqash, naw-kash'; a primitive root;  to entrap (with a noose), literally or figuratively:—catch (lay a) snare.

h5369.d: נֵר Nêr, nare; the same as H5216; lamp;  Ner, an Israelite:—Ner.
h5369.r: The same as נִיר (H5216)|English: lamp, candle, light

h5370.d: נֵרְגַּל Nêrᵉgal, nare-gal'; of foreign origin;  Nergal, a Cuthite deity:—Nergal.

h5371.d: נֵרְגַּל שַׁרְאֶצֶר Nêrᵉgal Sharʼetser, nare-gal' shar-eh'-tser; from H5370 and H8272;  Nergal-Sharetser, the name of two Babylonians:—Nergal-sharezer.

h5375.d: נָשָׂא nâsâʼ, naw-saw'; or נָסָה nâçâh; (Psalm 4:6 [7]), a primitive root;  to lift, in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, absolute and relative:—accept, advance, arise, (able to, (armor), suffer to) bear(-er, up), bring (forth), burn, carry (away), cast, contain, desire, ease, exact, exalt (self), extol, fetch, forgive, furnish, further, give, go on, help, high, hold up, honorable (  man), lade, lay, lift (self) up, lofty, marry, magnify, × needs, obtain, pardon, raise (up), receive, regard, respect, set (up), spare, stir up,   swear, take (away, up), × utterly, wear, yield.

h5376.d: נְשָׂא nᵉsâʼ, nes-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5375:—carry away, make insurrection, take.
h5376.r: Corresponding to נָשָׂא (H5375)|English: (bare, lift, etc...) up, bear, take, bare, carry, (take, carry)..away, borne, armourbearer, forgive, accept, exalt, regard, obtained, respect

h5377.d: נָשָׁא nâshâʼ, naw-shaw'; a primitive root;  to lead astray, i.e. (mentally) to delude, or (morally) to seduce:—beguile, deceive, × greatly, × utterly.

h5378.d: נָשָׁא nâshâʼ, naw-shaw'; a primitive root (perhaps identical with H5377, through the idea of imposition);  to lend on interest; by implication, to dun for debt:—× debt, exact, giver of usury.
h5378.r: A primitive root [perhaps identical with נָשָׁא (H5377), through the idea of imposition]|English: deceive, greatly, beguiled me, seize, utterly

h538.d: אֲמָם ʼĂmâm, am-awm'; from H517; gathering-spot;  Amam, a place in Palestine:—Amam.

h5380.d: נָשַׁב nâshab, naw-shab'; a primitive root;  to blow; by implication, to disperse:—(cause to) blow, drive away.

h5381.d: נָשַׂג nâsag, naw-sag'; a primitive root;  to reach (literally or figuratively):—ability, be able, attain (unto), (be able to, can) get, lay at, put, reach, remove, wax rich, × surely, (over-) take (hold of, on, upon).

h5387.d: נָשִׂיא nâsîyʼ, naw-see'; or נָשִׂא nâsiʼ; from H5375;  properly, an exalted one, i.e. a king or sheik; also a rising mist:—captain, chief, cloud, governor, prince, ruler, vapour.
h5387.r: From נָשָׂא (H5375)|English: (bare, lift, etc...) up, bear, take, bare, carry, (take, carry)..away, borne, armourbearer, forgive, accept, exalt, regard, obtained, respect

h539.d: אָמַן ʼâman, aw-man'; a primitive root; (Isaiah 30:21; interchangeable with H541, to go to the right hand)  properly, to build up or support; to foster as a parent or nurse; figuratively to render (or be) firm or faithful, to trust or believe, to be permanent or quiet; morally to be true or certain;:—hence, assurance, believe, bring up, establish,   fail, be faithful (of long continuance, stedfast, sure, surely, trusty, verified), nurse, (-ing father), (put), trust, turn to the right.

h5391.d: נָשַׁךְ nâshak, naw-shak'; a primitive root;  to strike with a sting (as a serpent); figuratively, to oppress with interest on a loan:—bite, lend upon usury.

h5392.d: נֶשֶׁךְ neshek, neh'-shek; from H5391;  interest on a debt:—usury.
h5392.r: From נָשַׁךְ (H5391)|English: bite, lend upon usury

h5394.d: נָשַׁל nâshal, naw-shal'; a primitive root;  to pluck off, i.e. divest, eject or drop:—cast (out), drive, loose, put off (out), slip.

h5395.d: נָשַׁם nâsham, naw-sham'; a primitive root;  properly, to blow away, i.e. destroy:—destroy.

h5397.d: נְשָׁמָה nᵉshâmâh, nesh-aw-maw'; from H5395;  a puff, i.e. wind, angry or vital breath, divine inspiration, intellect. or (concretely) an animal:—blast, (that) breath(-eth), inspiration, soul, spirit.

h5398.d: נָשַׁף nâshaph, naw-shaf'; a primitive root;  to breeze, i.e. blow up fresh (as the wind):—blow.

h5399.d: נֶשֶׁף nesheph, neh'-shef; from H5398;  properly, a breeze, i.e. (by implication) dusk (when the evening breeze prevails):—dark, dawning of the day (morning), night, twilight.

h54.d: אֶבְיָתָר ʼEbyâthâr, ab-yaw-thawr'; contracted from H1 and H3498; father of abundance (i.e. liberal);  Ebjathar, an Israelite:—Abiathar.
h54.r: Contracted from אָב (H1) and יָתַר (H3498)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h5400.d: נָשַׂק nâsaq, naw-sak'; a primitive root;  to catch fire:—burn, kindle.

h5401.d: נָשַׁק nâshaq, naw-shak'; a primitive root (identical with H5400, through the idea of fastening up; compare H2388, H2836);  to kiss, literally or figuratively (touch); also (as a mode of attachment), to equip with weapons:—armed (men), rule, kiss, that touched.
h5401.r: A primitive root [identical with נָשַׂק (H5400), through the idea of fastening up|English: kindle, burn

h5402.d: נֶשֶׁק nesheq, neh'-shek; or נֵשֶׁק nêsheq; from H5401;  military equipment, i.e. (collectively) arms (offensive or defensive), or (concretely) an arsenal:—armed men, armour(-y), battle, harness, weapon.
h5402.r: From נָשַׁק (H5401)|English: kiss, armed, kissed him, armed men, ruled, touched

h5404.d: נֶשֶׁר nesher, neh'-sher; from an unused root meaning to lacerate;  the eagle (or other large bird of prey):—eagle.
h5404.r: From an unused root meaning to lacerate|

h5407.d: נִשְׁתְּוָן nishtᵉvân, nish-tev-awn'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5406:—letter.

h5409.r: From נָתַח (H5408)|English: cut, cut into pieces, divided, hewed them in pieces

h5410.d: נָתִיב nâthîyb, naw-theeb'; or (feminine) נְתִיבָה nᵉthîybâh; or נְתִבָה nᵉthibâh; (Jeremiah 6:16), from an unused root meaning to tramp;  a (beaten) track:—path(-way), × travel(-ler), way.
h5410.r: From an unused root meaning to tramp|

h5416.d: נָתָן Nâthân, naw-thawn'; from H5414; given;  Nathan, the name of five Israelites:—Nathan.

h5417.r: From נָתַן (H5414) and אֵל (H410)|English: give, put, deliver, made, set, up, lay, grant, suffer, yield, bring, cause, utter, laid, send, recompense, appoint, shew

h5418.d: נְתַנְיָה Nᵉthanyâh, neth-an-yaw'; or נְתַנְיָהוּ Nᵉthanyâhûw; from H5414 and H3050; given of Jah;  Nethanjah, the name of four Israelites:—Nethaniah.
h5418.r: From נָתַן (H5414) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: give, put, deliver, made, set, up, lay, grant, suffer, yield, bring, cause, utter, laid, send, recompense, appoint, shew

h5422.d: נָתַץ nâthats, naw-thats'; a primitive root;  to tear down:—beat down, break down (out), cast down, destroy, overthrow, pull down, throw down.

h5423.d: נָתַק nâthaq, naw-thak'; a primitive root;  to tear off:—break (off), burst, draw (away), lift up, pluck (away, off), pull (out), root out.

h5425.d: נָתַר nâthar, naw-thar'; a primitive root;  to jump, i.e. be violently agitated; causatively, to terrify, shake off, untie:—drive asunder, leap, (let) loose, × make, move, undo.

h5428.d: נָתַשׁ nâthash, naw-thash'; a primitive root;  to tear away:—destroy, forsake, pluck (out, up, by the roots), pull up, root out (up), × utterly.

h543.d: אָמֵן ʼâmên, aw-mane'; from H539;  sure; abstract, faithfulness; adverb, truly:—Amen, so be it, truth.
h543.r: From אָמַן (H539)|English: believe, assurance, faithful, sure, established, trust, verified, stedfast, continuance, father, bring up, nurse, be nursed, surely be, stand fast, fail, trusty

h5430.d: סְאוֹן çᵉʼôwn, seh-own'; from H5431;  perhaps a military boot (as a protection from mud):—battle.

h5439.r: From סָבַב (H5437)|English: (stood, turned, etc...) about, compass, turn, turn away, remove, returned, round, side, turn aside, turn back, beset, driven, compass in, misc

h5443.d: סַבְּכָא çabbᵉkâʼ, sab-bek-aw'; (Aramaic) or שַׂבְּכָא sabbᵉkâʼ; (Aramaic), from a root corresponding to H5440;  a lyre:—sackbut.

h5447.d: סֵבֶל çêbel, say'-bel; from H5445;  a load (literally or figuratively):—burden, charge.
h5447.r: From סָבַל (H5445)|English: carry, bear, labour, burden

h5451.d: סִבֹּלֶת çibbôleth, sib-bo'-leth; for H7641;  an ear of grain:—Sibboleth.

h5453.r: Dual from a root corresponding to סְבַר (H5452)|English: think

h5454.d: סַבְתָּא Çabtâʼ, sab-taw'; or סַבְתָּה Çabtâh; probably of foreign derivation;  Sabta or Sabtah, the name of a son of Cush, and the country occupied by his posterity:—Sabta, Sabtah.

h5456.d: סָגַד çâgad, saw-gad'; a primitive root;  to prostrate oneself (in homage):—fall down.

h5457.d: סְגִד çᵉgid, seg-eed'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5456:—worship.

h546.d: אׇמְנָה ʼomnâh, om-naw'; feminine form of H544 (in its usual sense);  adverb, surely:—indeed.
h546.r: Feminine form of אֹמֶן (H544) (in its usual sense)|English: truth

h5460.d: סְגַן çᵉgan, seg-an'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5461:—governor.

h5462.d: סָגַר çâgar, saw-gar'; a primitive root;  to shut up; figuratively, to surrender:—close up, deliver (up), give over (up), inclose, × pure, repair, shut (in, self, out, up, up together), stop, × straitly.

h5466.d: סָדִין çâdîyn, saw-deen'; from an unused root meaning to envelop;  a wrapper, i.e. shirt:—fine linen, sheet.
h5466.r: From an unused root meaning to envelop|

h5467.d: סְדֹם Çᵉdôm, sed-ome'; from an unused root meaning to scorch; burnt (i.e. volcanic or bituminous) district;  Sedom, a place near the Dead Sea:—Sodom.
h5467.r: From an unused root meaning to scorch|

h5468.d: סֶדֶר çeder, seh'-der; from an unused root meaning to arrange;  order:—order.
h5468.r: From an unused root meaning to arrange|

h5472.d: סוּג çûwg, soog; a primitive root;  properly, to flinch, i.e. (by implication) to go back, literally (to retreat) or figuratively (to apostatize):—backslider, drive, go back, turn (away, back).

h5475.d: סוֹד çôwd, sode; from H3245;  a session, i.e. company of persons (in close deliberation); by implication, intimacy, consultation, a secret:—assembly, consel, inward, secret (counsel).
h5475.r: From יָסַד (H3245)|English: foundation, lay, founded, ordain, counsel, established, foundation, appointed, instructed, set, sure

h5477.d: סוּחַ Çûwach, soo'-akh; from an unused root meaning to wipe away; sweeping;  Suach, an Israelite:—Suah.
h5477.r: From an unused root meaning to wipe away|

h5480.d: סוּךְ çûwk, sook; a primitive root;  properly, to smear over (with oil), i.e. anoint:—anoint (self), × at all.

h5481.d: סוּמְפּוֹנְיָה çûwmᵉpôwnᵉyâh, soom-po-neh-yaw'; (Aramaic) or סוּמְפֹּנְיָה çûwmᵉpônᵉyâh; (Aramaic), or סִיפֹנְיָא çîyphônᵉyâʼ; (Daniel 3:10) (Aramaic), of Greek origin;  a bagpipe (with a double pipe):—dulcimer.

h5483.d: סוּס çûwç, soos; or סֻס çuç; from an unused root meaning to skip (properly, for joy);  a horse (as leaping); also a swallow (from its rapid flight):—crane, horse (-back, -hoof). Compare H6571.
h5483.r: From an unused root meaning to skip (properly, for joy)|

h5487.d: סוּף çûwph, soof; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5486;  to come to an end:—consume, fulfill.
h5487.r: Corresponding to סוּף (H5486)|English: consume, utterly, have an end, perish

h5489.d: סוּף Çûwph, soof; for H5488 (by ellipsis of H3220);  the Reed (Sea):—Red Sea.
h5489.r: For סוּף (H5488) (by ellipsis of יָם (H3220))|English: Red, flags, weeds
