h5495.d: סוּר Çûwr, soor; the same as H5494;  Sur, a gate of the temple:—Sur.

h5496.d: סוּת çûwth, sooth; perhaps denominative from H7898;  properly, to prick, i.e. (figuratively) stimulate; by implication, to seduce:—entice, move, persuade, provoke, remove, set on, stir up, take away.

h5499.d: סְחָבָה çᵉchâbâh, seh-khaw-baw'; from H5498;  a rag:—cast clout.
h5499.r: From סָחַב (H5498)|English: draw, draw out, tear

h55.d: אָבַךְ ʼâbak, aw-bak'; a primitive root;  probably to coil upward:—mount up.

h550.d: אַמְנוֹן ʼAmnôwn, am-nohn'; or אֲמִינוֹן ʼĂmîynôwn; from H539; faithful;  Amnon (or Aminon), a son of David:—Amnon.
h550.r: From אָמַן (H539)|English: believe, assurance, faithful, sure, established, trust, verified, stedfast, continuance, father, bring up, nurse, be nursed, surely be, stand fast, fail, trusty

h5503.d: סָחַר çâchar, saw-khar'; a primitive root;  to travel round (specifically as a pedlar); intensively, to palpitate:—go about, merchant(-man), occupy with, pant, trade, traffick.

h5509.d: סִיג çîyg, seeg; or סוּג çûwg; (Ezekiel 22:18), from H5472 in the sense of refuse;  scoria:—dross.
h5509.r: From סוּג (H5472) in the sense of refuse|English: turned, turn away, go back, turn back, backslider, driven

h551.d: אׇמְנָם ʼomnâm, om-nawm'; adverb from H544;  verily:—indeed, no doubt, surely, (it is, of a) true(-ly, -th).

h5510.d: סִיוָן Çîyvân, see-vawn'; probably of Persian origin;  Sivan, the third Hebrew month:—Sivan.

h5511.d: סִיחוֹן Çîychôwn, see-khone'; or סִיחֹן Çîychôn; from the same as H5477; tempestuous;  Sichon, an Amoritish king:—Sihon.
h5511.r: From the same as סוּחַ (H5477)|English: Suah

h5514.d: סִינַי Çîynay, see-nah'-ee; of uncertain derivation;  Sinai, mountain of Arabia:—Sinai.

h5516.d: סִיסְרָא Çîyçᵉrâʼ, see-ser-aw'; of uncertain derivation;  Sisera, the name of a Canaanitish king and of one of the Nethinim:—Sisera.

h5518.d: סִיר çîyr, seer; or (feminine) סִירָה çîyrâh; or סִרָה çirâh; (Jeremiah 52:18), from a primitive root meaning to boil up;  a pot; also a thorn (as springing up rapidly); by implication, a hook:—caldron, fishhook, pan, (wash-)pot, thorn.
h5518.r: From a primitive root meaning to boil up|

h552.d: אֻמְנָם ʼumnâm, oom-nawm'; an orthographical variation of H551:—in (very) deed; of a surety.
h552.r: An orthographical variation of אָמְנָם (H551)|English: truth, indeed, true, no doubt, surely, indeed

h5521.d: סֻכָּה çukkâh, sook-kaw'; feminine of H5520;  a hut or lair:—booth, cottage, covert, pavilion, tabernacle, tent.
h5521.r: From סֹךְ (H5520)|English: den, pavilion, tabernacle, covert

h5523.d: סֻכּוֹת Çukkôwth, sook-kohth'; or סֻכֹּת Çukkôth; plural of H5521; booths;  Succoth, the name of a place in Egypt and of three in Palestine:—Succoth.
h5523.r: From סֻכָּה (H5521)|English: tabernacle, booth, pavilion, cottage, covert, tents

h5524.d: סֻכּוֹת בְּנוֹת Çukkôwth bᵉnôwth, sook-kohth' ben-ohth'; from H5523 and the (irregular) plural of H1323;  booths of (the) daughters; brothels, i.e. idoalatrous tents for impure purpose:—Succothbenoth.
h5524.r: From סֻכּוֹת (H5523) and the (irreg) pl. of בַּת (H1323)|English: Succoth

h5526.d: סָכַךְ çâkak, saw-kak'; or שָׂכַךְ sâkak; (Exodus 33:22), a primitive root;  properly, to entwine as a screen; by implication, to fence in, cover over, (figuratively) protect:—cover, defence, defend, hedge in, join together, set, shut up.

h5528.d: סָכַל çâkal, saw-kal'; for H3688;  to be silly:—do (make, play the, turn into) fool(-ish, -ishly, -ishness).

h5529.d: סֶכֶל çekel, seh'-kal; from H5528;  silliness; concretely and collectively, dolts:—folly.
h5529.r: From סָכַל (H5528)|English: done foolishly, turn into foolishness, make foolish, play the fool

h553.d: אָמַץ ʼâmats, aw-mats'; a primitive root;  to be alert, physically (on foot) or mentally (in courage):—confirm, be courageous (of good courage, stedfastly minded, strong, stronger), establish, fortify, harden, increase, prevail, strengthen (self), make strong (obstinate, speed).

h5531.d: סִכְלוּת çiklûwth, sik-looth'; or שִׂכְלוּת siklûwth; (Ecclesiastes 1:17), from H5528;  silliness:—folly, foolishness.
h5531.r: From סָכַל (H5528)|English: done foolishly, turn into foolishness, make foolish, play the fool

h5532.d: סָכַן çâkan, saw-kan'; a primitive root;  to be familiar with; by implication, to minister to, be serviceable to, to cherish, be customary:—acquaint (self), be advantage, × ever, (be, (un-)) profit(-able), treasurer, be wont.

h5536.d: סַל çal, sal; from H5549;  properly, a willow twig (as pendulous), i.e. an osier; but only as woven into a basket:—basket.
h5536.r: From סָלַל (H5549)|English: cast up, raise up, exalt, extol, made plain

h554.d: אָמֹץ ʼâmôts, aw-mohts'; probably from H553;  of a strong color, i.e. red (others fleet):—bay.
h554.r: Probably from אָמֵץ (H553)|English: strengthen, courage, strong, courageous, harden, speed, stronger, confirm, established, fortify, increaseth, steadfastly minded, obstinate, prevailed

h5540.d: סֶלֶד Çeled, seh'-led; from H5539; exultation;  Seled, an Israelite:—Seled.

h5542.d: סֶלָה çelâh, seh'-law; from H5541;  suspension (of music), i.e. pause:—Selah.
h5542.r: From סָלָה (H5541)|English: valued, trodden down, trodden under foot

h5543.d: סַלּוּ Çallûw, sal-loo'; or סַלּוּא Çallûwʼ; or סָלוּא Çâlûwʼ; or סַלַּי Çallay; from H5541; weighed;  Sallu or Sallai, the name of two Israelites:—Sallai, Sallu, Salu.
h5543.r: From סָלָה (H5541)|English: valued, trodden down, trodden under foot

h5544.d: סִלּוֹן çillôwn, sil-lone'; or סַלּוֹן çallôwn; from H5541;  a prickle (as if pendulous):—brier, thorn.
h5544.r: From סָלָה (H5541)|English: valued, trodden down, trodden under foot

h5545.d: סָלַח çâlach, saw-lakh'; a primitive root;  to forgive:—forgive, pardon, spare.

h5549.d: סָלַל çâlal, saw-lal'; a primitive root;  to mound up (especially a turnpike); figurative, to exalt; reflexively, to oppose (as by a dam):—cast up, exalt (self), extol, make plain, raise up.

h5553.d: סֶלַע çelaʻ, seh'-lah; from an unused root meaning to be lofty;  a craggy rock, literally or figuratively (a fortress):—(ragged) rock, stone(-ny), strong hold.
h5553.r: From an unused root meaning to be lofty|

h5554.d: סֶלַע Çelaʻ, seh'-lah; the same as H5553;  Sela, the rock-city of Idumaea:—rock, Sela(-h).
h5554.r: The same as סֶלַע (H5553)|English: rock, strong hold, stones, stony

h5556.d: סׇלְעָם çolʻâm, sol-awm'; apparently from the same as H5553 in the sense of crushing as with a rock, i.e. consuming;  a kind of locust (from its destructiveness):—bald locust.
h5556.r: Apparently from the same as סֶלַע (H5553) in the sense of crushing as with a rock, i.e. consuming|English: rock, strong hold, stones, stony

h5559.d: סְלִק çᵉliq, sel-eek'; (Aramaic) a primitive root;  to ascend:—come (up).

h5560.d: סֹלֶת çôleth, so'-leth; from an unused root meaning to strip;  flour (as chipped off):—(fine) flour, meal.
h5560.r: From an unused root meaning to strip|

h5561.d: סַם çam, sam; from an unused root meaning to smell sweet;  an aroma:—sweet (spice).
h5561.r: From an unused root meaning to smell sweet|

h5564.d: סָמַךְ çâmak, saw-mak'; a primitive root;  to prop (literally or figuratively); reflexively, to lean upon or take hold of (in a favorable or unfavorable sense):—bear up, establish, (up-) hold, lay, lean, lie hard, put, rest self, set self, stand fast, stay (self), sustain.

h5566.d: סֶמֶל çemel, seh'-mel; or סֵמֶל çêmel; from an unused root meaning to resemble;  a likeness:—figure, idol, image.
h5566.r: From an unused root meaning to resemble|

h5568.d: סָמַר çâmar, saw-mar'; a primitive root;  to be erect, i.e. bristle as hair:—stand up, tremble.

h5571.d: סַנְבַלַּט Çanballaṭ, san-bal-lat'; of foreign origin;  Sanballat, a Persian satrap of Samaria:—Sanballat.

h5573.d: סֶנֶה Çeneh, seh-neh'; the same as H5572; thorn;  Seneh, a crag in Palestine:—Seneh.

h5576.d: סַנְחֵרִיב Çanchêrîyb, san-khay-reeb'; of foreign origin;  Sancherib, an Assyrian king:—Sennacherib.

h5579.d: סְנַפִּיר çᵉnappîyr, sen-ap-peer'; of uncertain derivation;  a fin (collectively):—fins.

h558.d: אֲמַצְיָה ʼĂmatsyâh, am-ats-yaw'; or אֲמַצְיָהוּ ʼĂmatsyâhûw; from H553 and H3050; strength of Jah;  Amatsjah, the name of four Israelites:—Amaziah.
h558.r: From אָמֵץ (H553) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: strengthen, courage, strong, courageous, harden, speed, stronger, confirm, established, fortify, increaseth, steadfastly minded, obstinate, prevailed

h5587.d: סָעִף çâʻiph, saw-eef'; or שָׂעִף sâʻiph; from H5586;  divided (in mind), i.e. (abstractly) a sentiment:—opinion.

h559.d: אָמַר ʼâmar, aw-mar'; a primitive root;  to say (used with great latitude):—answer, appoint, avouch, bid, boast self, call, certify, challenge, charge,   (at the, give) command(-ment), commune, consider, declare, demand, × desire, determine, × expressly, × indeed, × intend, name, × plainly, promise, publish, report, require, say, speak (against, of), × still, × suppose, talk, tell, term, × that is, × think, use (speech), utter, × verily, × yet.

h5590.d: סָעַר çâʻar, saw-ar'; a primitive root;  to rush upon; by implication, to toss (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative):—be (toss with) tempest(-uous), be sore, troubled, come out as a (drive with the, scatter with a) whirlwind.

h5591.d: סַעַר çaʻar, sah'-ar; or (feminine) סְעָרָה çᵉʻârâh; from H5590;  a hurricane:—storm(-y), tempest, whirlwind.
h5591.r: From סָעַר (H5590)|English: whirlwind, tempestuous, troubled, tossed with tempest

h5592.d: סַף çaph, saf; from H5605, in its original sense of containing;  a vestibule (as a limit); also a dish (for holding blood or wine):—bason, bowl, cup, door (post), gate, post, threshold.

h5593.d: סַף Çaph, saf; the same as H5592;  Saph, a Philistine:—Saph. Compare H5598.
h5593.r: The same as סַף (H5592)|English: door, threshold, bason, posts, bowls, gates, cup

h5594.d: סָפַד çâphad, saw-fad'; a primitive root;  properly, to tear the hair and beat the breasts (as Orientals do in grief); generally to lament; by implication, to wail:—lament, mourn(-er), wail.

h5595.d: סָפָה çâphâh, saw-faw'; a primitive root;  properly, to scrape (literally, to shave; but usually figuratively) together (i.e. to accumulate or increase) or away (i.e. to scatter, remove, or ruin; intransitively, to perish):—add, augment, consume, destroy, heap, join, perish, put.

h5596.d: סָפַח çâphach, saw-fakh'; or שָׂפַח sâphach; (Isaiah 3:17), a primitive root;  properly, to scrape out, but in certain peculiar senses (of removal or association):—abiding, gather together, cleave, smite with the scab.

h5598.d: סִפַּי Çippay, sip-pah'-ee; from H5592; bason-like;  Sippai, a Philistine:—Sippai. Compare H5593.
h5598.r: From סַף (H5592)|English: door, threshold, bason, posts, bowls, gates, cup

h5599.d: סָפִיחַ çâphîyach, saw-fee'-akh; from H5596;  something (spontaneously) falling off, i.e. a self-sown crop; figuratively, a freshet:—(such) things as (which) grow (of themselves), which groweth of its own accord (itself).
h5599.r: From סָפַח (H5596)|English: put, abide, gather together, smite with a scab, cleave

h56.d: אָבַל ʼâbal, aw-bal'; a primitive root;  to bewail:—lament, mourn.

h560.d: אֲמַר ʼămar, am-ar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H559:—command, declare, say, speak, tell.
h560.r: Corresponding to אָמַר (H559)|English: said, speak, answer, command, tell, call, promised, misc.

h5602.d: סֵפֶל çêphel, say'-fel; from an unused root meaning to depress;  a basin (as deepened out):—bowl, dish.
h5602.r: From an unused root meaning to depress|

h5606.d: סָפַק çâphaq, saw-fak'; or שָׂפַק sâphaq; (1 Kings 20:10; Job 27:23; Isaiah 2:6), a primitive root;  to clap the hands (in token of compact, derision, grief, indignation, or punishment); by implication of satisfaction, to be enough; by implication of excess, to vomit:—clap, smite, strike, suffice, wallow.

h5608.d: סָפַר çâphar, saw-far'; a primitive root;  properly, to score with a mark as a tally or record, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe, and also to enumerate; intensively, to recount, i.e. celebrate:—commune, (ac-) count; declare, number,   penknife, reckon, scribe, shew forth, speak, talk, tell (out), writer.

h561.d: אֵמֶר ʼêmer, ay'-mer; from H559;  something said:—answer, × appointed unto him, saying, speech, word.
h561.r: From אָמַר (H559)|English: said, speak, answer, command, tell, call, promised, misc.

h5612.d: סֵפֶר çêpher, say'-fer; or (feminine) סִפְרָה çiphrâh; (Psalm 56:8 (H9)), from H5608;  properly, writing (the art or a document); by implication, a book:—bill, book, evidence, × learn(-ed) (-ing), letter, register, scroll.
h5612.r: From סָפַר (H5608)|English: scribe, tell, declare, number, count, shew forth, writer, speak, accounted, commune, told out, reckon, penknife, shewing, talk

h5619.d: סָקַל çâqal, saw-kal'; a primitive root;  properly, to be weighty; but used only in the sense of lapidation or its contrary (as if a delapidation):—(cast, gather out, throw) stone(-s), × surely.

h562.d: אֹמֶר ʼômer, o'-mer; the same as H561:—promise, speech, thing, word.
h562.r: The same as אֵמֶר (H561)|English: words, speeches, sayings, appointed, answer

h5620.d: סַר çar, sar; contracted from H5637;  peevish:—heavy, sad.

h5624.d: סֶרֶד Çered, seh'-red; from a primitive root meaning to tremble; trembling;  Sered, an Israelite:—Sered.
h5624.r: From a primitive root meaning to tremble|

h5627.d: סָרָה çârâh, saw-raw'; from H5493;  apostasy, crime; figuratively, remission:—× continual, rebellion, revolt(-ed), turn away, wrong.
h5627.r: From סוּר (H5493)|English: (put, take,...) away, depart, remove, aside, take, turn, turn in, take off, go, put, eschewed, misc

h5628.d: סָרַח çârach, saw-rakh'; a primitive root;  to extend (even to excess):—exceeding, hand, spread, stretch self, banish.

h5629.d: סֶרַח çerach, seh'-rakh; from H5628;  a redundancy:—remnant.
h5629.r: From סָרַח (H5628)|English: hang, stretch, spreading, exceeding, vanished

h563.d: אִמַּר ʼimmar, im-mar'; (Aramaic) perhaps from H560 (in the sense of bringing forth);  a lamb:—lamb.
h563.r: Perhaps from אֲמַר (H560) (in the sense of bringing forth)|English: say, commanded, speak, tell, declare

h5631.d: סָרִיס çârîyç, saw-reece'; or סָרִס çâriç; from an unused root meaning to castrate;  a eunuch; by implication, valet (especially of the female apartments), and thus, a minister of state:—chamberlain, eunuch, officer. Compare H7249.
h5631.r: From an unused root meaning to castrate|

h5633.d: סֶרֶן çeren, seh'-ren; from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  an axle; figuratively, a peer:—lord, plate.
h5633.r: From an unused root of uncertain meaning|

h5637.d: סָרַר çârar, saw-rar'; a primitive root;  to turn away, i.e. (morally) be refractory:—× away, backsliding, rebellious, revolter(-ing), slide back, stubborn, withdrew.

h5639.d: סְתוּר Çᵉthûwr, seth-oor'; from H5641; hidden;  Sethur, an Israelite:—Sethur.
h5639.r: From סָתַר (H5641)|English: hide, secret, close, absent, conceal, surely, variant

h5640.d: סָתַם çâtham, saw-tham'; or שָׂתַם sâtham; (Numbers 24:15), a primitive root;  to stop up; by implication, to repair; figuratively, to keep secret:—closed up, hidden, secret, shut out (up), stop.

h5641.d: סָתַר çâthar, saw-thar'; a primitive root;  to hide (by covering), literally or figuratively:—be absent, keep close, conceal, hide (self), (keep) secret, × surely.

h5642.d: סְתַר çᵉthar, seth-ar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5641;  to conceal; figuratively, to demolish:—destroy, secret thing.
h5642.r: Corresponding to סָתַר (H5641)|English: hide, secret, close, absent, conceal, surely, variant

h5643.d: סֵתֶר çêther, say'-ther; or (feminine) סִתְרָה çithrâh; (Deuteronomy 32:38), from H5641;  a cover (in a good or a bad, a literal or a figurative sense):—backbiting, covering, covert, × disguise(-th), hiding place, privily, protection, secret(-ly, place).
h5643.r: From סָתַר (H5641)|English: hide, secret, close, absent, conceal, surely, variant

h5645.d: עָב ʻâb, awb; (masculine and feminine); from H5743;  properly, an envelope, i.e. darkness (or density, 2 Chronicles 4:17); specifically, a (scud) cloud; also a copse:—clay, (thick) cloud, × thick, thicket. Compare H5672.
h5645.r: From עוּב (H5743)|English: cover with a cloud

h5647.d: עָבַד ʻâbad, aw-bad'; a primitive root;  to work (in any sense); by implication, to serve, till, (causatively) enslave, etc.:—× be, keep in bondage, be bondmen, bond-service, compel, do, dress, ear, execute,   husbandman, keep, labour(-ing man, bring to pass, (cause to, make to) serve(-ing, self), (be, become) servant(-s), do (use) service, till(-er), transgress (from margin), (set a) work, be wrought, worshipper,

h5648.d: עֲבַד ʻăbad, ab-bad'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5647;  to do, make, prepare, keep, etc.:—× cut, do, execute, go on, make, move, work.
h5648.r: Corresponding to עָבַד (H5647)|English: serve, do, till, servant, work, worshippers, service, dress, labour, ear, misc

h5649.d: עֲבַד ʻăbad, ab-bad'; (Aramaic) from H5648;  a servant:—servant.
h5649.r: From עֲבַד (H5648)|English: do, made, cut, do, do, worketh, executed, goeth, kept, moved, wrought

h565.d: אִמְרָה ʼimrâh, im-raw'; or אֶמְרָה ʼemrâh; feminine of H561, and meaning the same:—commandment, speech, word.
h565.r: From אֵמֶר (H561)|English: words, speeches, sayings, appointed, answer

h5650.d: עֶבֶד ʻebed, eh'-bed; from H5647;  a servant:—× bondage, bondman, (bond-) servant, (man-) servant.
h5650.r: From עָבַד (H5647)|English: serve, do, till, servant, work, worshippers, service, dress, labour, ear, misc

h5651.d: עֶבֶד ʻEbed, eh'-bed; the same as H5650;  Ebed, the name of two Israelites:—Ebed.
h5651.r: The same as עֶבֶד (H5650)|English: servant, manservant, bondman, bondage, bondservant, on all sides

h5654.d: עֹבֵד אֱדוֹם ʻÔbêd ʼĔdôwm, o-bade' ed-ome'; from the active participle of H5647 and H123; worker of Edom;  Obed-Edom, the name of five Israelites:—Obed-edom.
h5654.r: From the act part of עָבַד (H5647) and אֱדֹם (H123)|English: serve, do, till, servant, work, worshippers, service, dress, labour, ear, misc

h5656.d: עֲבֹדָה ʻăbôdâh, ab-o-daw'; or עֲבוֹדָה ʻăbôwdâh; from H5647;  work of any kind:—act, bondage,   bondservant, effect, labour, ministering(-try), office, service(-ile, -itude), tillage, use, work, × wrought.
h5656.r: From עָבַד (H5647)|English: serve, do, till, servant, work, worshippers, service, dress, labour, ear, misc

h5657.d: עֲבֻדָּה ʻăbuddâh, ab-ood-daw'; passive participle of H5647;  something wrought, i.e. (concretely) service:—household, store of servants.
h5657.r: Pass part of עָבַד (H5647)|English: serve, do, till, servant, work, worshippers, service, dress, labour, ear, misc

h5658.d: עַבְדוֹן ʻAbdôwn, ab-dohn'; from H5647; servitude;  Abdon, the name of a place in Palestine and of four Israelites:—Abdon. Compare H5683.
h5658.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h5658.r: From עָבַד (H5647)|English: serve, do, till, servant, work, worshippers, service, dress, labour, ear, misc

h5660.d: עַבְדִּי ʻAbdîy, ab-dee'; from H5647; serviceable;  Abdi, the name of two Israelites:—Abdi.

h6068.d: עֲנָתוֹת ʻĂnâthôwth, an-aw-thoth'; plural of H6067;  Anathoth, the name of two Israelites, also of a place in Pal:—Anathoth.

h6085.d: עֶפְרוֹן ʻEphrôwn, ef-rone'; from the same as H6081; fawn-like;  Ephron, the name of a Canaanite and of two places in Palestine:—Ephron, Ephrain (from the margin).

h6172.d: עֶרְוָה ʻervâh, er-vaw'; from H6168;  nudity, literally (especially the pudenda) or figuratively (disgrace, blemish):—nakedness, shame, unclean(-ness).

h6179.d: עֵרִי ʻÊrîy, ay-ree'; from H5782; watchful;  Eri, an Israelite:—Eri.

h6181.d: עֶרְיָה ʻeryâh, er-yaw'; for H6172;  nudity:—bare, naked, × quite.

h6184.d: עָרִיץ ʻârîyts, aw-reets'; from H6206;  fearful, i.e. powerful or tyrannical:—mighty, oppressor, in great power, strong, terrible, violent.

h6189.d: עָרֵל ʻârêl, aw-rale'; from H6188;  properly, exposed, i.e. projecting loose (as to the prepuce); used only technically, uncircumcised (i.e. still having the prepuce uncurtailed):—uncircumcised (person).

h6195.d: עׇרְמָה ʻormâh, or-maw'; feminine of H6193;  trickery; or (in a good sense) discretion:—guile, prudence, subtilty, wilily, wisdom.

h62.d: אָבֵל בֵּית־מֲעַכָה ʼÂbêl Bêyth-Măʻakâh, aw-bale' bayth ma-akaw'; from H58 and H1004 and H4601; meadow of Beth-Maakah;  Abel of Beth-maakah, a place in Palestine:—Abel-beth-maachah, Abel of Beth-maachah,
h62.r: From אָבֵל (H58) and בַּיִת (H1004) and מַעֲכָה (H4601)|English: plain

h620.d: אׇסְנַפַּר ʼOçnappar, os-nap-par'; of foreign derivation;  Osnappar, an Assyrian king:—Asnapper.

h6201.d: עָרַף ʻâraph, aw-raf'; a primitive root;  to droop; hence, to drip:—drop (down).

h6205.d: עֲרָפֶל ʻărâphel, ar-aw-fel'; probably from H6201;  gloom (as of a lowering sky):—(gross, thick) dark (cloud, -ness).

h621.d: אָסְנַת ʼÂçᵉnath, aw-se-nath'; of Egyptian derivation;  Asenath, the wife of Joseph:—Asenath.

h6211.d: עָשׁ ʻâsh, awsh; from H6244;  a moth:—moth. See also H5906.

h6212.d: עֶשֶׂב ʻeseb, eh'seb; from an unused root meaning to glisten (or be green);  grass (or any tender shoot):—grass, herb.
h6212.r: From an unused root meaning to glisten (or be green)|

h6213.d: עָשָׂה ʻâsâh, aw-saw'; a primitive root;  to do or make, in the broadest sense and widest application:—accomplish, advance, appoint, apt, be at, become, bear, bestow, bring forth, bruise, be busy, × certainly, have the charge of, commit, deal (with), deck,   displease, do, (ready) dress(-ed), (put in) execute(-ion), exercise, fashion,   feast, (fight-) ing man,   finish, fit, fly, follow, fulfill, furnish, gather, get, go about, govern, grant, great,   hinder, hold (a feast), × indeed,   be industrious,   journey, keep, labour, maintain, make, be meet, observe, be occupied, offer,   officer, pare, bring (come) to pass, perform, pracise, prepare, procure, provide, put, requite, × sacrifice, serve, set, shew, × sin, spend, × surely, take, × thoroughly, trim, × very,   vex, be (warr-) ior, work(-man), yield, use.

h6214.d: עֲשָׂהאֵל ʻĂsâhʼêl, as-aw-ale'; from H6213 and H410; God has made;  Asahel, the name of four Israelites:—Asahel.
h6214.r: From עָשָׂה (H6213) and אֵל (H410)|English: do, make, wrought, deal, commit, offer, execute, keep, shew, prepare, work, do so, perform, get, dress, maker, maintain

h6215.d: עֵשָׂו ʻÊsâv, ay-sawv'; apparently a form of the passive participle of H6213 in the original sense of handling; rough (i.e. sensibly felt);  Esav, a son of Isaac, including his posterity:—Esau.
h6215.r: Apparently a form of the pass. part. of עָשָׂה (H6213) in the original sense of handling|English: do, make, wrought, deal, commit, offer, execute, keep, shew, prepare, work, do so, perform, get, dress, maker, maintain

h6218.d: עָשׂוֹר ʻâsôwr, aw-sore'; or עָשֹׂר ʻâsôr; from H6235;  ten; by abbreviated form ten strings, and so a decachord:—(instrument of) ten (strings, -th).
h6218.r: From עֶשֶׂר (H6235)|English: ten, fifteen, seventeen, ten times

h6219.d: עָשׁוֹת ʻâshôwth, aw-shoth'; from H6245;  shining, i.e. polished:—bright.

h622.d: אָסַף ʼâçaph, aw-saf'; a primitive root;  to gather for any purpose; hence, to receive, take away, i.e. remove (destroy, leave behind, put up, restore, etc.):—assemble, bring, consume, destroy, felch, gather (in, together, up again), × generally, get (him), lose, put all together, receive, recover (another from leprosy), (be) rereward, × surely, take (away, into, up), × utterly, withdraw.

h6222.d: עֲשָׂיָה ʻĂsâyâh, aw-saw-yaw'; from H6213 and H3050; Jah has made;  Asajah, the name of three or four Israelites:—Asaiah.
h6222.r: From עָשָׂה (H6213) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: do, make, wrought, deal, commit, offer, execute, keep, shew, prepare, work, do so, perform, get, dress, maker, maintain

h6223.d: עָשִׁיר ʻâshîyr, aw-sheer'; from H6238;  rich, whether literal or figurative (noble):—rich (man).

h6225.d: עָשַׁן ʻâshan, aw-shan'; a primitive root;  to smoke, whether literal or figurative:—be angry (be on a) smoke.

h6226.d: עָשֵׁן ʻâshên, aw-shane'; from H6225;  smoky:—smoking.

h6227.d: עָשָׁן ʻâshân, aw-shawn'; from H6225;  smoke, literally or figuratively (vapor, dust, anger):—smoke(-ing).

h6228.d: עָשָׁן ʻÂshân, aw-shawn'; the same as H6227;  Ashan, a place in Palestine:—Ashan.
h6228.r: The same as עָשָׁן (H6227)|English: smoke, smoking

h623.d: אָסָף ʼÂçâph, aw-sawf'; from H622; collector;  Asaph, the name of three Israelites, and of the family of the first:—Asaph.
h623.r: From אָסַף (H622)|English: together, gather, assemble, rereward, misc

h6230.d: עֵשֶׂק ʻêseq, ay'sek; from H6229;  strife:—Esek.

h6231.d: עָשַׁק ʻâshaq, aw-shak'; a primitive root (compare H6229);  to press upon, i.e. oppress, defraud, violate, overflow:—get deceitfully, deceive, defraud, drink up, (use) oppress(-ion), (-or), do violence (wrong).

h6233.d: עֹשֶׁק ʻôsheq, o'-shek; from H6231;  injury, fraud, (subjectively) distress, (concretely) unjust gain:—cruelly, extortion, oppression, thing (deceitfully gotten).
h6233.r: From עָשַׁק (H6231)|English: oppress, oppressor, defraud, wrong, deceived, deceitfully gotten, oppression, drink up, violence

h6235.d: עֶשֶׂר ʻeser, eh'ser; masculine of term עֲשָׂרָה ʻăsârâh; from H6237;  ten (as an accumulation to the extent of the digits):—ten, (fif-, seven-) teen.
h6235.r: From עָשַׂר (H6237)|English: tithe, take..tenth, give tenth, surly, truly

h6236.d: עֲשַׂר ʻăsar, as-ar'; (Aramaic) masculine עֲשְׂרָה ʻăsrâh (Aramaic); corresponding to H6235;  ten:—ten,   twelve.
h6236.r: Corresponding to עֶשֶׂר (H6235)|English: ten, fifteen, seventeen, ten times

h6237.d: עָשַׂר ʻâsar, aw-sar'; a primitive root (identical with H6238); to accumulate; but used only as denominative from H6235;  to tithe, i.e. to take or give a tenth:—× surely, give (take) the tenth, (have, take) tithe(-ing, -s), × truly.
h6237.r: A primitive root (ident. with עָשַׁר (H6238))|English: rich, enrich, richer

h6238.d: עָשַׁר ʻâshar, aw-shar'; a primitive root;  properly, to accumulate; chiefly (specifically) to grow (causatively, make) rich:—be(-come, en-, make, make self, wax) rich, make (1 Kings 22:48 margin). See H6240.

h6239.d: עֹשֶׁר ʻôsher, o'-sher; from H6238;  wealth:—× far (richer), riches.

h6240.d: עָשָׂר ʻâsâr, aw-sawr'; for H6235;  ten (only in combination), i.e. -teen; also (ordinal) -teenth:—(eigh-, fif-, four-, nine-, seven-, six-, thir-) teen(-th), + eleven(-th), + sixscore thousand, + twelve(-th).
h6240.r: From עֶשֶׂר (H6235)|English: ten, fifteen, seventeen, ten times

h6242.d: עֶשְׂרִים ʻesrîym, es-reem'; from H6235;  twenty; also (ordinal) twentieth:—(six-) score, twenty(-ieth).
h6242.r: From עֶשֶׂר (H6235)|English: ten, fifteen, seventeen, ten times

h6244.d: עָשֵׁשׁ ʻâshêsh, aw-shaysh'; a primitive root;  probably to shrink, i.e. fail:—be consumed.

h6246.d: עֲשִׁת ʻăshith, ash-eeth'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H6245;  to purpose:—think.

h6249.d: עַשְׁתֵּי ʻashtêy, ash-tay'; apparently masculine plural construction of H6247 in the sense of an afterthought (used only in connection with H6240 in lieu of H259)  eleven or (ordinal) eleventh:—  eleven(-th).
h6249.r: Apparently masc. pl. construction of עֶשֶׁת (H6247) in the sense of an afterthought (used only in connection with עֶשֶׂר (H6240) in lieu of אֶחָד (H259)) eleven or (ordinal) eleventh|English: bright

h625.d: אֹסֶף ʼôçeph, o'-sef; from H622;  a collection (of fruits):—gathering.
h625.r: From אָסַף (H622)|English: together, gather, assemble, rereward, misc

h6253.d: עַשְׁתֹּרֶת ʻAshtôreth, ash-to'reth; probably for H6251;  Ashtoreth, the Phoenician goddess of love (and increase):—Ashtoreth.

h6256.d: עֵת ʻêth, ayth; from H5703;  time, especially (adverb with preposition) now, when, etc.:—  after, (al-) ways, × certain,   continually,   evening, long, (due) season, so (long) as, (even-, evening-, noon-) tide, (meal-), what) time, when.
h6256.r: From עַד (H5703)|English: ever, everlasting, end, eternity, ever, evermore, old, perpetually

h6258.d: עַתָּה ʻattâh, at-taw'; from H6256;  at this time, whether adverb, conjunction or expletive:—henceforth, now, straightway, this time, whereas.
h6258.r: From עֵת (H6256)|English: time, season, when, always, eveningtide, misc

h626.d: אֲסֵפָה ʼăçêphâh, as-ay-faw'; from H622;  a collection of people (only adverbial):—× together.
h626.r: From אָסַף (H622)|English: together, gather, assemble, rereward, misc

h6260.d: עַתּוּד ʻattûwd, at-tood'; or עַתֻּד ʻattud; from H6257;  prepared, i.e. full grown; spoken only (in plural) of he-goats, or (figuratively) leaders of the people:—chief one, (he) goat, ram.
h6260.r: From עָתַד (H6257)|English: make it fit, ready to become heaps

h6262.d: עַתַּי ʻAttay, at-tah'ee; for H6261;  Attai, the name of three Israelites:—Attai.

h6263.d: עֲתִיד ʻăthîyd, ath-eed'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H6264;  prepared:—ready.
h6263.r: Corresponding to עָתִיד (H6264)|English: ready, things that shall come, variant

h6264.d: עָתִיד ʻâthîyd, aw-theed'; from H6257;  prepared; by implication, skilful; feminine plural the future; also treasure:—things that shall come, ready, treasures.
h6264.r: From עָתַד (H6257)|English: make it fit, ready to become heaps

h6265.d: עֲתָיָה ʻĂthâyâh, ath-aw-yaw'; from H5790 and H3050; Jah has helped;  Athajah, an Israelite:—Athaiah.

h6271.d: עֲתַלְיָה ʻĂthalyâh, ath-al-yaw'; or עֲתַלְיָהוּ ʻĂthalyâhûw; from the same as H6270 and H3050; Jah has constrained;  Athaljah, the name of an Israelitess and two Israelites:—Athaliah.
h6271.s: proper feminine noun, proper masculine noun
h6271.r: From the same as עַתְלַי (H6270) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: Athlai

h6273.d: עׇתְנִי ʻOthnîy, oth-nee'; from an unused root meaning to force; forcible;  Othni, an Israelite:—Othni.
h6273.r: From an unused root meaning to force|

h6274.d: עׇתְנִיאֵל ʻOthnîyʼêl, oth-nee-ale'; from the same as H6273 and H410; force of God;  Othniel, an Israelite:—Othniel.
h6274.r: From the same as עָתְנִי (H6273) and אֵל (H410)|English: Othni

h6279.d: עָתַר ʻâthar, aw-thar'; a primitive root (rather denominative from H6281);  to burn incense in worship, i.e. intercede (reciprocally, listen to prayer):—intreat, (make) pray(-er).
h6279.r: A primitive root [rather denominative from עֶתֶר (H6281)]|English: Ether

h6284.d: פָּאָה pâʼâh, paw-aw'; a primitive root;  to puff, i.e. blow away:—scatter into corners.

h6285.d: פֵּאָה pêʼâh, pay-aw'; feminine of H6311;  properly, mouth in a figurative sense, i.e. direction, region, extremity:—corner, end, quarter, side.
h6285.r: From פֹּה (H6311)|English: here, hither, this side, one side, other side

h6286.d: פָּאַר pâʼar, paw-ar'; a primitive root; also denominative from H6288,  to gleam, i.e. (causatively) embellish; figuratively, to boast; also to explain (i.e. make clear) oneself; to shake a tree:—beautify, boast self, go over the boughs, glorify (self), glory, vaunt self.

h6287.d: פְּאֵר pᵉʼêr, peh-ayr'; from H6286;  an embellishment, i.e. fancy head-dress:—beauty, bonnet, goodly, ornament, tire.
h6287.r: From פָּאַר (H6286)|English: glorify, beautify, boast,go over the boughs, Glory, vaunt

h6289.d: פָּארוּר pâʼrûwr, paw-roor'; from H6286;  properly, illuminated, i.e. a glow; as noun, a flush (of anxiety):—blackness.
h6289.r: From פָּאַר (H6286)|English: glorify, beautify, boast,go over the boughs, Glory, vaunt

h629.d: אׇסְפַּרְנָא ʼoçparnâʼ, os-par-naw'; (Aramaic) of Persian derivation;  diligently:—fast, forthwith, speed(-ily).

h6290.d: פָּארָן Pâʼrân, paw-rawn'; from H6286; ornamental;  Paran, a desert of Arabia:—Paran.
h6290.r: From פָּאַר (H6286)|English: glorify, beautify, boast,go over the boughs, Glory, vaunt

h6292.d: פִּגּוּל piggûwl, pig-gool'; or פִּגֻּל piggul; from an unused root meaning to stink;  properly, fetid, i.e. (figuratively) unclean (ceremonially):—abominable(-tion, thing).
h6292.r: From an unused root meaning to stink|

h6293.d: פָּגַע pâgaʻ, paw-gah'; a primitive root;  to impinge, by accident or violence, or (figuratively) by importunity:—come (betwixt), cause to entreat, fall (upon), make intercession, intercessor, intreat, lay, light (upon), meet (together), pray, reach, run.

h6294.d: פֶּגַע pegaʻ, peh'-gah; from H6293;  impact (casual):—chance, occurent.
h6294.r: From פָּגַע (H6293)|English: fall, meet, reach, intercession, intreat, entreat, misc

h6295.d: פַּגְעִיאֵל Pagʻîyʼêl, pag-ee-ale'; from H6294 and H410; accident of God;  Pagiel, an Israelite:—Pagiel.
h6295.r: From פֶּגַע (H6294) and אֵל (H410)|English: occurrent, chance

h6296.d: פָּגַר pâgar, paw-gar'; a primitive root;  to relax, i.e. become exhausted:—be faint.

h6297.d: פֶּגֶר peger, peh'gher; from H6296;  a carcase (as limp), whether of man or beast; figuratively, an idolatrous image:—carcase, corpse, dead body.

h6298.d: פָּגַשׁ pâgash, paw-gash'; a primitive root;  to come in contact with, whether by accident or violence; figuratively, to concur:—meet (with, together).

h6299.d: פָּדָה pâdâh, paw-daw'; a primitive root;  to sever, i.e. ransom; generally to release, preserve:—× at all, deliver, × by any means, ransom, (that are to be, let be) redeem(-ed), rescue, × surely.

h630.d: אַסְפָּתָא ʼAçpâthâʼ, as-paw-thaw'; of Persian derivation;  Aspatha, a son of Haman:—Aspatha.

h6300.d: פְּדַהְאֵל Pᵉdahʼêl, ped-ah-ale'; from H6299 and H410; God has ransomed;  Pedahel, an Israelite:—Pedahel.
h6300.r: From פָּדָה (H6299) and אֵל (H410)|English: redeem, deliver, ransom, rescued, misc

h6304.d: פְּדוּת pᵉdûwth, ped-ooth'; or פְּדֻת pᵉduth; from H6929;  distinction; also deliverance:—division, redeem, redemption.
h6304.r: From קָטַר (H6999)|English: incense, burn, offer, kindle, offering, misc

h6305.d: פְּדָיָה Pᵉdâyâh, ped-aw-yaw'; or פְּדָיָהוּ Pᵉdâyâhûw; from H6299 and H3050; Jah has ransomed;  Pedajah, the name of six Israelites:—Pedaiah.
h6305.r: From פָּדָה (H6299) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: redeem, deliver, ransom, rescued, misc

h6308.d: פָּדַע pâdaʻ, paw-dah'; a primitive root;  to retrieve:—deliver.

h631.d: אָסַר ʼâçar, aw-sar'; a primitive root;  to yoke or hitch; by analogy, to fasten in any sense, to join battle:—bind, fast, gird, harness, hold, keep, make ready, order, prepare, prison(-er), put in bonds, set in array, tie.

h6310.d: פֶּה peh, peh; from H6284;  the mouth (as the means of blowing), whether literal or figurative (particularly speech); specifically edge, portion or side; adverbially (with preposition) according to:—accord(-ing as, -ing to), after, appointment, assent, collar, command(-ment), × eat, edge, end, entry,   file, hole, × in, mind, mouth, part, portion, × (should) say(-ing), sentence, skirt, sound, speech, × spoken, talk, tenor, × to,   two-edged, wish, word.

h6311.d: פֹּה pôh, po; or פֹּא pôʼ; (Job 38:11), or פּוֹ pôw; probably from a primitive inseparable particle 'p' (of demonstrative force) and H1931;  this place (French ici), i.e. here or hence:—here, hither, the one (other, this, that) side.
h6311.r: Probably from a primitive inseparable particle "p" (of demonstrative force) and הוּא (H1931)|English: that, him, same, this, he, which, who, such, wherein

h6312.d: פּוּאָה Pûwʼâh, poo-aw'; or פֻּוָּה Puvvâh; from H6284; a blast;  Puah or Puvvah, the name of two Israelites:—Phuvah, Pua, Puah.

h6315.d: פּוּחַ pûwach, poo'akh; a primitive root;  to puff, i.e. blow with the breath or air; hence, to fan (as a breeze), to utter, to kindle (a fire), to scoff:—blow (upon), break, puff, bring into a snare, speak, utter.

h6316.d: פּוּט Pûwṭ, poot; of foreign origin;  Put, a son of Ham, also the name of his descendants or their region, and of a Persian tribe:—Phut, Put.
h6316.s: proper noun with reference to people

h632.d: אֱסָר ʼĕçâr, es-sawr'; or אִסָּר ʼiççâr; from H631;  an obligation or vow (of abstinence):—binding, bond.
h632.r: From אָסַר (H631)|English: bind, prison, tie, prisoner, misc

h6321.d: פּוֹל pôwl, pole; from an unused root meaning to be thick;  a bean (as plump):—beans.
h6321.r: From an unused root meaning to be thick|

h6322.d: פּוּל Pûwl, pool; of foreign origin;  Pul, the name of an Assyrian king and of an Ethiopian tribe:—Pul.

h6326.d: פּוּעָה Pûwʻâh, poo-aw'; from an unused root meaning to glitter; brilliancy;  Puah, an Israelitess:—Puah.
h6326.r: From an unused root meaning to glitter|

h6327.d: פּוּץ pûwts, poots; a primitive root;  to dash in pieces, literally or figuratively (especially to disperse):—break (dash, shake) in (to) pieces, cast (abroad), disperse (selves), drive, retire, scatter (abroad), spread abroad.

h6329.d: פּוּק pûwq, pook; a primitive root [rather identical with H6328 through the idea of dropping out; compare H5312];  to issue, i.e. furnish; causatively, to secure; figuratively, to succeed:—afford, draw out, further, get, obtain.
h6329.r: A primitive root [identical with פּוּק (H6328) through the idea of dropping out|English: stumble, move

h633.d: אֱסָר ʼĕçâr, es-sawr'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H632 in a legal sense;  an interdict:—decree.
h633.r: Corresponding to אֱסָר (H632) in a legal sense|English: bond, binding

h6332.d: פּוּר Pûwr, poor; also (plural) פּוּרִים Pûwrîym; or פֻּרִים Purîym; from H6331;  a lot (as by means of a broken piece):—Pur, Purim.
h6332.r: From פּוּר (H6331)|English: bring to nought, broken, utterly take

h6333.d: פּוּרָה pûwrâh, poo-raw'; from H6331;  a wine-press (as crushing the grapes):—winepress.
h6333.r: From פּוּר (H6331)|English: bring to nought, broken, utterly take

h6334.d: פּוֹרָתָא Pôwrâthâʼ, po-raw-thaw'; of Persian origin;  Poratha, a son of Haman:—Poratha.

h6337.d: פָּז pâz, pawz; from H6338;  pure (gold); hence, gold itself (as refined):—fine (pure) gold.

h6339.d: פָּזַז pâzaz, paw-zaz'; a primitive root (identical with H6338);  to solidify (as if by refining); also to spring (as if separating the limbs):—leap, be made strong.
h6339.r: A primitive root [identical with פָּזַז (H6338)]|English: best

h6340.d: פָּזַר pâzar, paw-zar'; a primitive root;  to scatter, whether in enmity or bounty:—disperse, scatter (abroad).

h6341.d: פַּח pach, pakh; from H6351;  a (metallic) sheet (as pounded thin); also a spring net (as spread out like a lamina):—gin, (thin) plate, snare.

h6342.d: פָּחַד pâchad, paw-kkad'; a primitive root;  to be startled (by a sudden alarm); hence, to fear in general:—be afraid, stand in awe, (be in) fear, make to shake.

h6343.d: פַּחַד pachad, pakh'-ad; from H6342;  a (sudden) alarm (properly, the object feared, by implication, the feeling):—dread(-ful), fear, (thing) great (fear, -ly feared), terror.
h6343.r: From פָּחַד (H6342)|English: fear, afraid, awe, shake

h6346.d: פֶּחָה pechâh, peh-khaw'; of foreign origin;  a prefect (of a city or small district):—captain, deputy, governor.

h6347.d: פֶּחָה pechâh, peh-khaw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H6346:—captain, governor.
h6347.r: Corresponding to פֶּחָה (H6346)|English: governor, captain, deputies

h6349.d: פַּחַז pachaz, pakh'-az; from H6348;  ebullition, i.e. froth (figuratively, lust):—unstable.

h635.d: אֶסְתֵּר ʼEçtêr, es-tare'; of Persian derivation;  Ester, the Jewish heroine:—Esther.

h6354.d: פַּחַת pachath, pakh'-ath; probably from an unused root apparently meaning to dig;  a pit, especially for catching animals:—hole, pit, snare.
h6354.r: Probably from an unused root apparently meaning to dig|

h6377.d: פִּיתוֹן Pîythôwn, pee-thone'; probably from the same as H6596; expansive;  Pithon, an Israelite:—Pithon.
h6377.r: Probably from the same as פֹּת (H6596)|English: hinge, secret parts

h6395.d: פָּלָה pâlâh, paw-law'; a primitive root;  to distinguish (literally or figuratively):—put a difference, show marvellous, separate, set apart, sever, make wonderfully.

h6400.d: פֶּלַח pelach, peh'-lakh; from H6398;  a slice:—piece.

h6406.d: פַּלְטִי Palṭîy, pal-tee'; from H6403; delivered;  Palti, the name of two Israelites:—Palti, Phalti.

h6433.d: פֻּם pum, poom; (Aramaic) probably for H6310;  the mouth (literally or figuratively):—mouth.

h6489.d: פְּקוֹד Pᵉqôwd, pek-ode'; from H6485; punishment;  Pekod, a symbolic name for Babylon:—Pekod.

h6497.d: פֶּקַע peqaʻ, peh'-kah; from an unused root meaning to burst; only used as an architectural term of an ornament similar to H6498,  a semi-globe:—knop.

h7230.r: From רָבַב (H7231)|English: are many, are multiplied, increased, are more, manifold, ten thousands, multiply

h7231.d: רָבַב râbab, raw-bab'; a primitive root; (compare H7241); also as denominative from H7233;  properly, to cast together , i.e. increase, especially in number; to multiply by the myriad:—increase, be many(-ifold), be more, multiply, ten thousands.

h7233.d: רְבָבָה rᵉbâbâh, reb-aw-baw'; from H7231;  abundance (in number), i.e. (specifically) a myriad (whether definite or indefinite):—many, million, × multiply, ten thousand.
h7233.r: From רָבַב (H7231)|English: are many, are multiplied, increased, are more, manifold, ten thousands, multiply

h7235.d: רָבָה râbâh, raw-baw'; a primitive root;  to increase (in whatever respect):—(bring in) abundance (× -antly),   archer (by mistake for H7232), be in authority, bring up, × continue, enlarge, excel, exceeding(-ly), be full of, (be, make) great(-er, -ly, × -ness), grow up, heap, increase, be long, (be, give, have, make, use) many (a time), (any, be, give, give the, have) more (in number), (ask, be, be so, gather, over, take, yield) much (greater, more), (make to) multiply, nourish, plenty(-eous), × process (of time), sore, store, thoroughly, very.

h7236.d: רְבָה rᵉbâh, reb-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7235:—make a great man, grow.
h7236.r: Corresponding to רָבָה (H7235)|English: multiply, increase, much, many, more, great, long, store, exceedingly, greater, abundance, misc

h7237.d: רַבָּה Rabbâh, rab-baw'; feminine of H7227; great;  Rabbah, the name of two places in Palestine, East and West:—Rabbah, Rabbath.
h7237.r: Fem. of רַב (H7227)|English: many, great, much, captain, more, long, enough, multitude, mighty, greater, greatly, misc

h7238.d: רְבוּ rᵉbûw, reb-oo'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H7235;  increase (of dignity):—greatness, majesty.
h7238.r: From a root corresponding to רָבָה (H7235)|English: multiply, increase, much, many, more, great, long, store, exceedingly, greater, abundance, misc

h724.d: אֲרוּכָה ʼărûwkâh, ar-oo-kaw'; or אֲרֻכָה ʼărukâh; feminine passive participle of H748 (in the sense of restoring to soundness);  wholeness (literally or figuratively):—health, made up, perfected.
h724.r: Passive participle of אָרַךְ (H748) (in the sense of restoring to soundness)|English: prolong, long, lengthen, draw out, defer, tarried, ...lived

h7241.d: רָבִיב râbîyb, raw-beeb'; from H7231;  a rain (as an accumulation of drops):—shower.
h7241.r: From רָבַב (H7231)|English: are many, are multiplied, increased, are more, manifold, ten thousands, multiply

h7242.d: רָבִיד râbîyd, raw-beed'; from H7234;  a collar (as spread around the neck):—chain.

h7250.d: רָבַע râbaʻ, raw-bah'; a primitive root;  to squat or lie out flat, i.e. (specifically) in copulation:—let gender, lie down.

h7251.d: רָבַע râbaʻ, raw-bah'; a primitive root (rather identical with H7250 through the idea of sprawling 'at all fours' (or possibly the reverse is the order of derivation); compare H702); properly, to be four (sided); used only as denominative of H7253;  to be quadrate:—(four-) square(-d).
h7251.r: A primitive root [rather identical with רָבַע (H7250) through the idea of sprawling "at all fours" (or possibly the reverse is the order of deriv)|English: lie down, gender

h7253.d: רֶבַע rebaʻ, reh'-bah; from H7251;  a fourth (part or side):—fourth part, side, square.

h7255.d: רֹבַע rôbaʻ, ro'-bah; from H7251;  a quarter:—fourth participle

h7257.d: רָבַץ râbats, raw-bats'; a primitive root;  to crouch (on all four legs folded, like a recumbent animal); by implication, to recline, repose, brood, lurk, imbed:—crouch (down), fall down, make a fold, lay, (cause to, make to) lie (down), make to rest, sit.

h7258.d: רֵבֶץ rêbets, reh'-bets; from H7257;  a couch or place of repose:—where each lay, lie down in, resting place.
h7258.r: From רָבַץ (H7257)|English: lay down, lay, couch beneath, couched, misc

h7259.d: רִבְקָה Ribqâh, rib-kaw'; from an unused root probably meaning to clog by tying up the fetlock; fettering (by beauty);  Ribkah, the wife of Isaac:—Rebekah.
h7259.r: From an unused root probably meaning to clog by tying up the fetlock|

h7260.d: רַבְרַב rabrab, rab-rab'; (Aramaic) from H7229;  huge (in size); domineering (in character):—(very) great (things).
h7260.r: From רַב (H7229)|English: great, master, stout, chief, captain, lord

h7262.d: רַבְשָׁקֵה Rabshâqêh, rab-shaw-kay'; from H7227 and H8248; chief butler;  Rabshakeh, a Babylonian official:—Rabshakeh.
h7262.r: From רַב (H7227) and שָׁקָה (H8248)|English: many, great, much, captain, more, long, enough, multitude, mighty, greater, greatly, misc

h7264.d: רָגַז râgaz, raw-gaz'; a primitive root;  to quiver (with any violent emotion, especially anger or fear):—be afraid, stand in awe, disquiet, fall out, fret, move, provoke, quake, rage, shake, tremble, trouble, be wroth.

h7267.d: רֹגֶז rôgez, ro'-ghez; from H7264;  commotion, restlessness (of a horse), crash (of thunder), disquiet, anger:—fear, noise, rage, trouble(-ing), wrath.
h7267.r: From רָגַז (H7264)|English: tremble, move, rage, shake, disquiet, troubled, quake, afraid, misc

h727.d: אָרוֹן ʼârôwn, aw-rone'; or אָרֹן ʼârôn; from H717 (in the sense of gathering);  a box:—ark, chest, coffin.
h727.r: From אָרָה (H717) (in the sense of gathering)|English: pluck, gather

h7270.d: רָגַל râgal, raw-gal'; a primitive root; also as denominative from H7272  to walk along; but only in specifically, applications, to reconnoiter, to be a tale-bearer (i.e. slander); to lead about:—backbite, search, slander, (e-) spy (out), teach to go, view.

h7272.d: רֶגֶל regel, reh'-gel; from H7270;  a foot (as used in walking); by implication, a step; by euphemistically the pudenda:—× be able to endure, × according as, × after, × coming, × follow, (broken-)foot(-ed, -stool), × great toe, × haunt, × journey, leg,   piss,   possession, time.
h7272.r: From רָגַל (H7270)|English: spy, spy out, view, backbiteth, espy out, slandered

h7273.d: רַגְלִי raglîy, rag-lee'; from H7272;  a footman (soldier):—(on) foot(-man).
h7273.r: From רֶגֶל (H7272)|English: feet, footstool, after, times, follow, piss, toes, journey, legs, misc

h7275.d: רָגַם râgam, raw-gam'; a primitive root (compare H7263, H7321, H7551);  to cast together (stones), i.e. to lapidate:—× certainly, stone.
h7275.r: A primitive root [compare רֶגֶב (H7263), רוּעַ (H7321), רָקַם (H7551)]|English: clod

h7276.d: רֶגֶם Regem, reh'-gem; from H7275; stoneheap;  Regem, an Israelite:—Regem.

h7279.d: רָגַן râgan, raw-gan'; a primitive root;  to grumble, i.e. rebel:—murmur.

h728.d: אֲרַוְנָה ʼĂravnâh, ar-av-naw'; or (by transposition) אוֹרְנָה ʼÔwrᵉnâh; or אַרְנִיָּה ʼArnîyâhlemma אַנִיָּה missing resh, corrected to אַרְנִיָּה; all by orthographical variation for H771;  Aravnah (or Arnijah or Ornah), a Jebusite:—Araunah.
h728.r: All by orthographical variation for אָרְנָן (H771)|English: Ornan

h7280.d: רָגַע râgaʻ, raw-gah'; a primitive root;  properly, to toss violently and suddenly (the sea with waves, the skin with boils); figuratively (in a favorable manner) to settle, i.e. quiet; specifically, to wink (from the motion of the eye-lids):—break, divide, find ease, be a moment, (cause, give, make to) rest, make suddenly.

h7281.d: רֶגַע regaʻ, reh'-gah; from H7280.  a wink (of the eyes), i.e. a very short space of time:—instant, moment, space, suddenly.
h7281.r: From רָגַע (H7280) a wink (of the eyes), i.e. a very short space of time|English: rest, divide, suddenly, broken, ease, moment

h7283.d: רָגַשׁ râgash, raw-gash'; a primitive root;  to be tumultuous:—rage.

h7284.d: רְגַשׁ rᵉgash, reg-ash'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7283;  to gather tumultuously:—assemble (together).

h7287.d: רָדָה râdâh, raw-daw'; a primitive root;  to tread down, i.e. subjugate; specifically, to crumble off:—(come to, make to) have dominion, prevail against, reign, (bear, make to) rule,(-r, over), take.

h7288.d: רַדַּי Radday, rad-dah'-ee; intensive from H7287; domineering;  Raddai, an Israelite:—Raddai.
h7288.r: Intensive from רָדָה (H7287)|English: rule, dominion, take, prevaileth, reign, ruler

h7290.d: רָדַם râdam, raw-dam'; a primitive root;  to stun, i.e. stupefy (with sleep or death):—(be fast a-, be in a deep, cast into a dead, that) sleep(-er, -eth).

h7291.d: רָדַף râdaph, raw-daf'; a primitive root;  to run after (usually with hostile intent; figuratively [of time] gone by):—chase, put to flight, follow (after, on), hunt, (be under) persecute(-ion, -or), pursue(-r).

h7293.d: רַהַב rahab, rah'-hab; from H7292,  bluster(-er):—proud, strength.
h7293.r: From רָהַב (H7292), bluster(-er)|English: make sure, behave proudly, overcome, strengthen

h7294.d: רַהַב Rahab, rah'-hab; the same as H7293;  Rahab (i.e. boaster), an epithet of Egypt:—Rahab.
h7294.r: The same as רַהַב (H7293)|English: proud, strength

h73.d: אַבְנֵט ʼabnêṭ, ab-nate'; of uncertain derivation;  a belt:—girdle.

h730.d: אֶרֶז ʼerez, eh-rez'; from H729;  a cedar tree (from the tenacity of its roots):—cedar (tree).

h7300.d: רוּד rûwd, rood; a primitive root;  to tramp about, i.e. ramble (free or disconsolate):—have the dominion, be lord, mourn, rule.

h7301.d: רָוָה râvâh, raw-vaw'; a primitive root;  to slake the thirst (occasionally of other appetites):—bathe, make drunk, (take the) fill, satiate, (abundantly) satisfy, soak, water (abundantly).

h7304.d: רָוַח râvach, raw-vakh'; a primitive root (identical with H7306);  properly, to breathe freely, i.e. revive; by implication, to have ample room:—be refreshed, large.
h7304.r: A primitive root [identical with רִיחַ (H7306)]|English: smell, touch, quick understanding, accept

h7305.d: רֶוַח revach, reh'-vakh; from H7304;  room, literally (an interval) or figuratively (deliverance):—enlargement, space.

h7306.d: רוּחַ rûwach, roo'-akh; a primitive root;  properly, to blow, i.e. breathe; only (literally) to smell or (by implication, perceive (figuratively, to anticipate, enjoy):—accept, smell, × touch, make of quick understanding.

h7307.d: רוּחַ rûwach, roo'-akh; from H7306;  wind; by resemblance breath, i.e. a sensible (or even violent) exhalation; figuratively, life, anger, unsubstantiality; by extension, a region of the sky; by resemblance spirit, but only of a rational being (including its expression and functions):—air, anger, blast, breath, × cool, courage, mind, × quarter, × side, spirit(-ual), tempest, × vain, (whirl-) wind(-y).
h7307.r: From רִיחַ (H7306)|English: smell, touch, quick understanding, accept

h7308.d: רוּחַ rûwach, roo'-akh; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7307:—mind, spirit, wind.
h7308.r: Corresponding to רוּחַ (H7307)|English: Spirit or spirit, wind, breath, side, mind, blast, vain, air, anger, cool, courage, misc

h731.d: אַרְזָה ʼarzâh, ar-zaw'; feminine of H730;  cedar wainscoating:—cedar work.

h7310.d: רְוָיָה rᵉvâyâh, rev-aw-yaw'; from H7301;  satisfaction:—runneth over, wealthy.
h7310.r: From רָוָה (H7301)|English: water, make drunk, fill, satiate, bathed, satisfied, abundantly satisfy, soaked

h7311.d: רוּם rûwm, room; a primitive root;  to be high actively, to rise or raise (in various applications, literally or figuratively):—bring up, exalt (self), extol, give, go up, haughty, heave (up), (be, lift up on, make on, set up on, too) high(-er, one), hold up, levy, lift(-er) up, (be) lofty, (× a-) loud, mount up, offer (up),   presumptuously, (be) promote(-ion), proud, set up, tall(-er), take (away, off, up), breed worms.

h7312.d: רוּם rûwm, room; or רֻם rum; from H7311;  (literally) elevation or (figuratively) elation:—haughtiness, height, × high.
h7312.r: From רוּם (H7311)|English: (lift, hold, etc...) up, exalt, high, offer, give, heave, extol, lofty, take, tall, higher, misc

h7315.d: רוֹם rôwm, rome; from H7311;  elevation, i.e. (adverbially) aloft:—on high.
h7315.r: From רוּם (H7311)|English: (lift, hold, etc...) up, exalt, high, offer, give, heave, extol, lofty, take, tall, higher, misc

h7317.d: רוֹמָה rôwmâh, ro-maw'; feminine of H7315;  elation, i.e. (adverbially) proudly:—haughtily.

h7318.d: רוֹמָם rôwmâm, ro-mawm'; from H7426;  exaltation, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) praise:—be extolled.
h7318.r: From רָמַם (H7426)|English: exalted, lifted up, get up, mount up

h7321.d: רוּעַ rûwaʻ, roo-ah'; a primitive root;  to mar (especially by breaking); figuratively, to split the ears (with sound), i.e. shout (for alarm or joy):—blow an alarm, cry (alarm, aloud, out), destroy, make a joyful noise, smart, shout (for joy), sound an alarm, triumph.

h7322.d: רוּף rûwph, roof; a primitive root;  properly, to triturate (in a mortar), i.e. (figuratively) to agitate (by concussion):—tremble.

h7323.d: רוּץ rûwts, roots; a primitive root;  to run (for whatever reason, especially to rush):—break down, divide speedily, footman, guard, bring hastily, (make) run (away, through), post.

h7324.d: רוּק rûwq, rook; a primitive root;  to pour out (literally or figuratively), i.e. empty:—× arm, cast out, draw (out), (make) empty, pour forth (out).

h7326.d: רוּשׁ rûwsh, roosh; a primitive root;  to be destitute:—lack, needy, (make self) poor (man).

h7327.d: רוּת Rûwth, rooth; probably for H7468; friend;  Ruth, a Moabitess:—Ruth.
h7327.r: Probably for רְעוּת (H7468)|English: neighbour, another, mate

h7328.d: רָז râz, rawz; (Aramaic) from an unused root probably meaning  to attenuate, i.e. (figuratively) hide; a mystery:—secret.
h7328.r: From an unused root probably meaning to attenuate, ie (fig) hide|

h7329.d: רָזָה râzâh, raw-zaw'; a primitive root;  to emaciate, i.e. make (become) thin (literally or figuratively):—famish, wax lean.

h733.d: אָרַח ʼÂrach, aw-rakh'; from H732; way faring;  Arach, the name of three Israelites:—Arah.

h7331.d: רְזוֹן Rᵉzôwn, rez-one'; from H7336; prince;  Rezon, a Syrian:—Rezon.

h7332.d: רָזוֹן râzôwn, raw-zone'; from H7329;  thinness:—leanness, × scant.

h7334.d: רָזִי râzîy, raw-zee'; from H7329;  thinness:—leanness.

h7335.d: רָזַם râzam, raw-zam'; a primitive root;  to twinkle the eye (in mockery):—wink.

h7336.d: רָזַן râzan, raw-zan'; a primitive root;  probably to be heavy, i.e. (figuratively) honorable:—prince, ruler.

h7337.d: רָחַב râchab, raw-khab'; a primitive root;  to broaden (intransitive or transitive, literal or figurative):—be an en-(make) large(-ing), make room, make (open) wide.

h7338.d: רַחַב rachab, rakh'-ab; from H7337;  a width:—breadth, broad place.
h7338.r: From רָחַב (H7337)|English: enlarge, wide, large, make room

h7339.d: רְחֹב rᵉchôb, rekh-obe'; or רְחוֹב rᵉchôwb; from H7337;  a width, i.e. (concretely) avenue or area:—broad place (way), street. See also H1050.
h7339.r: From רָחַב (H7337)|English: enlarge, wide, large, make room

h734.d: אֹרַח ʼôrach, o'-rakh; from H732;  a well-trodden road (literally or figuratively); also a caravan:—manner, path, race, rank, traveller, troop, (by-, high-) way.

h7340.d: רְחֹב Rᵉchôb, rekh-obe'; or רְחוֹב Rᵉchôwb; the same as H7339;  Rechob, the name of a place in Syria, also of a Syrian and an Israelite:—Rehob.
h7340.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h7340.r: The same as רְחֹב (H7339)|English: street, ways, places

h7341.d: רֹחַב rôchab, ro'-khab; from H7337;  width (literally or figuratively):—breadth, broad, largeness, thickness, wideness.
h7341.r: From רָחַב (H7337)|English: enlarge, wide, large, make room

h7342.d: רָחָב râchâb, raw-khawb'; from H7337;  roomy, in any (or every) direction, literally or figuratively:—broad, large, at liberty, proud, wide.
h7342.r: From רָחַב (H7337)|English: enlarge, wide, large, make room

h7343.d: רָחָב Râchâb, raw-khawb'; the same as H7342; proud;  Rachab, a Canaanitess:—Rahab.
h7343.r: The same as רָחָב (H7342)|English: large, broad, proud, wide, broader, liberty

h7344.d: רְחֹבוֹת Rᵉchôbôwth, rekh-o-both'; or רְחֹבֹת Rᵉchôbôth; plural of H7339; streets;  Rechoboth, a place in Assyria and one in Palestine:—Rehoboth.
h7344.r: Pl. of רְחֹב (H7339)|English: street, ways, places

h7345.d: רְחַבְיָה Rᵉchabyâh, rekh-ab-yaw'; or רְחַבְיָהוּ Rᵉchabyâhûw; from H7337 and H3050; Jah has enlarged;  Rechabjah, an Israelite:—Rehabiah.
h7345.r: From רָחַב (H7337) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: enlarge, wide, large, make room

h7346.d: רְחַבְעָם Rᵉchabʻâm, rekh-ab-awm'; from H7337 and H5971; a people has enlarged;  Rechabam, an Israelite king:—Rehoboam.
h7346.r: From רָחַב (H7337) and עַם (H5971)|English: enlarge, wide, large, make room

h7348.d: רְחוּם Rᵉchûwm, rekh-oom'; a form of H7349;  Rechum, the name of a Persian and of three Israelites:—Rehum.
h7348.r: A form of רַחוּם (H7349)|English: merciful, compassion

h7349.d: רַחוּם rachûwm, rakh-oom'; from H7355;  compassionate:—full of compassion, merciful.
h7349.r: From רָחַם (H7355)|English: ...mercy, ...compassion, pity, love, merciful, Ruhamah, surely

h7350.d: רָחוֹק râchôwq, raw-khoke'; or רָחֹק râchôq; from H7368;  remote, literally or figuratively, of place or time; specifically, precious; often used adverbially (with preposition):—(a-) far (abroad, off), long ago, of old, space, great while to come.

h7352.d: רַחִיק rachîyq, rakh-eek'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7350:—far.
h7352.r: Corresponding to רָחוֹק (H7350)|English: (far, afar...) off, far, long ago, far from, come, afar, old, far abroad, long, space

h7353.d: רָחֵל râchêl, raw-kale'; from an unused root meaning to journey;  a ewe [the females being the predominant element of a flock] (as a good traveller):—ewe, sheep.
h7353.r: From an unused root meaning to journey|

h7354.d: רָחֵל Râchêl, raw-khale'; the same as H7353;  Rachel, a wife of Jacob:—Rachel.
h7354.r: The same as רָחֵל (H7353)|English: ewe, sheep

h7355.d: רָחַם râcham, raw-kham'; a primitive root;  to fondle; by implication, to love, especially to compassionate:—have compassion (on, upon), love, (find, have, obtain, shew) mercy(-iful, on, upon), (have) pity, Ruhamah, × surely.

h7356.d: רַחַם racham, rakh'-am; from H7355;  compassion (in the plural); by extension, the womb (as cherishing the fetus); by implication, a maiden:—bowels, compassion, damsel, tender love, (great, tender) mercy, pity, womb.
h7356.s: masculine noun, absolute state masculine plural intensive noun
h7356.r: From רָחַם (H7355)|English: ...mercy, ...compassion, pity, love, merciful, Ruhamah, surely

h7357.d: רַחַם Racham, rakh'-am; the same as H7356; pity;  Racham, an Israelite:—Raham.
h7357.r: The same as רַחַם (H7356)|English: mercy, compassion, womb, bowels, pity, damsel, tender love

h7358.d: רֶחֶם rechem, rekh'-em; from H7355; (compare H7356)  the womb:—matrix, womb.
h7358.r: From רָחַם (H7355)|English: ...mercy, ...compassion, pity, love, merciful, Ruhamah, surely

h7360.d: רָחָם râchâm, raw-khawm'; or (feminine) רָחָמָה râchâmâh; from H7355;  a kind of vulture (supposed to be tender towards its young):—gier-eagle.
h7360.r: From רָחַם (H7355)|English: ...mercy, ...compassion, pity, love, merciful, Ruhamah, surely

h7363.d: רָחַף râchaph, raw-khaf'; a primitive root;  to brood; by implication, to be relaxed:—flutter, move, shake.

h7364.d: רָחַץ râchats, raw-khats'; a primitive root;  to lave (the whole or a part of a thing):—bathe (self), wash (self).

h7368.d: רָחַק râchaq, raw-khak'; a primitive root;  to widen (in any direction), i.e. (intransitively) recede or (transitively) remove (literally or figuratively, of place or relation):—(a-, be, cast, drive, get, go, keep (self), put, remove, be too, (wander), withdraw) far (away, off), loose, × refrain, very, (be) a good way (off).

h737.d: אֲרֻחָה ʼăruchâh, ar-oo-khaw'; feminine passive participle of H732 (in the sense of appointing);  a ration of food:—allowance, diet, dinner, victuals.
h737.r: Passive participle of אָרַח (H732) (in the sense of appointing)|English: wayfaring man, goeth

h7370.d: רָחַשׁ râchash, raw-khash'; a primitive root;  to gush:—indite.

h7375.d: רֻטֲפַשׁ ruṭăphash, roo-taf-ash'; a root compounded from H7373 and H2954;  to be rejuvenated:—be fresh.
h7375.r: A root compounded from רָטֹב (H7373) and טָפַשׁ (H2954)|English: green

h7376.d: רָטַשׁ râṭâsh, raw-tash'; a primitive root;  to dash down:—dash (in pieces).

h7377.d: רִי rîy, ree; from H7301;  irrigation, i.e. a shower:—watering.
h7377.r: From רָוָה (H7301)|English: water, make drunk, fill, satiate, bathed, satisfied, abundantly satisfy, soaked

h7378.d: רִיב rîyb, reeb; or רוּב rûwb; a primitive root;  properly, to toss, i.e. grapple; mostly figuratively, to wrangle, i.e. hold a controversy; (by implication) to defend:—adversary, chide, complain, contend, debate, × ever, × lay wait, plead, rebuke, strive, × thoroughly.

h7379.d: רִיב rîyb, reeb; or רִב rib; from H7378;  a contest (personal or legal):—  adversary, cause, chiding, contend(-tion), controversy, multitude (from the margin), pleading, strife, strive(-ing), suit.
h7379.r: From רִיב (H7378)|English: plead, strive, contend, chide, debate, misc

h738.d: אֲרִי ʼărîy, ar-ee'; or (prolonged) אַרְיֵה ʼaryêh; from H717 (in the sense of violence);  a lion:—(young) lion,   pierce (from the margin).
h738.r: From אָרָה (H717) (in the sense of violence)|English: pluck, gather

h7381.d: רֵיחַ rêyach, ray'-akh; from H7306;  odor (as if blown):—savour, scent, smell.
h7381.r: From רִיחַ (H7306)|English: smell, touch, quick understanding, accept

h7383.d: רִיפָה rîyphâh, ree-faw'; or רִפָה riphâh; from H7322;  (only plural), grits (as pounded):—ground corn, wheat.

h7385.d: רִיק rîyq, reek; from H7324;  emptiness; figuratively, a worthless thing; adverbially, in vain:—empty, to no purpose, (in) vain (thing), vanity.
h7385.r: From רִיק (H7324)|English: (pour, draw...) out, empty, draw, armed, pour forth

h7386.d: רֵיק rêyq, rake; or (shorter) רֵק rêq; from H7324;  empty; figuratively, worthless:—emptied(-ty), vain (fellow, man).
h7386.r: From רִיק (H7324)|English: (pour, draw...) out, empty, draw, armed, pour forth

h7387.d: רֵיקָם rêyqâm, ray-kawm'; from H7386;  emptily; figuratively (objective) ineffectually, (subjective) undeservedly:—without cause, empty, in vain, void.
h7387.r: From רֵיק (H7386)|English: empty, vain, emptied, vain men, vain fellows

h7388.d: רִיר rîyr, reer; from H7325;  saliva; by resemblance, broth:—spittle, white (of an egg).

h7389.d: רֵישׁ rêysh, raysh; or רֵאשׁ rêʼsh; or רִישׁ rîysh; from H7326;  poverty:—poverty.
h7389.r: From רוּשׁ (H7326)|English: poor, poor man, lack, needy

h739.d: אֲרִיאֵל ʼărîyʼêl, ar-ee-ale'; or אֲרִאֵל ʼăriʼêl; from H738 and H410;  lion of God; i.e. heroic:—lionlike men.
h739.r: From אֲרִי (H738) and אֵל (H410)|English: lion, untranslated variant

h7390.d: רַךְ rak, rak; from H7401;  tender (literally or figuratively); by implication, weak:—faint(-hearted), soft, tender ((-hearted), one), weak.
h7390.r: From רָכַךְ (H7401)|English: tender, faint, fainthearted, mollified, soft, softer

h7392.d: רָכַב râkab, raw-kab'; a primitive root;  to ride (on an animal or in a vehicle); causatively, to place upon (for riding or generally), to despatch:—bring (on (horse-) back), carry, get (oneself) up, on (horse-) back, put, (cause to, make to) ride (in a chariot, on, -r), set.

h7393.d: רֶכֶב rekeb, reh'-keb; from H7392;  a vehicle; by implication, a team; by extension, cavalry; by analogy a rider, i.e. the upper millstone:—chariot, (upper) millstone, multitude (from the margin), wagon.
h7393.r: From רָכַב (H7392)|English: ride, rider, horseback, put, set, carried, misc

h7394.d: רֵכָב Rêkâb, ray-kawb'; from H7392; rider;  Rekab, the name of two Arabs and of two Israelites:—Rechab.
h7394.r: From רָכַב (H7392)|English: ride, rider, horseback, put, set, carried, misc

h7399.d: רְכוּשׁ rᵉkûwsh, rek-oosh'; or רְכֻשׁ rᵉkush; from passive participle of H7408;  property (as gathered):—good, riches, substance.
h7399.r: From pass part of רָכַשׁ (H7408)|English: got, gather

h74.d: אַבְנֵר ʼAbnêr, ab-nare'; or (fully) אֲבִינֵר ʼĂbîynêr ; from H1 and H5216; father of light (i.e. enlightening);  Abner, an Israelite:—Abner.
h74.r: From אָב (H1) and נִיר (H5216)|English: father, chief, families, desire, fatherless, forefathers, patrimony, prince, principal

h740.d: אֲרִיאֵל ʼĂrîyʼêl, ar-ee-ale'; the same as H739;  Ariel, a symbolical name for Jerusalem, also the name of an Israelite:—Ariel.
h740.r: The same as אֲרִיאֵל (H739)|English: lion-like men

h7401.d: רָכַךְ râkak, raw-kak'; a primitive root;  to soften (intransitively or transitively), used figuratively:—(be) faint(-hearted), mollify, (be, make) soft(-er), be tender.

h7402.d: רָכַל râkal, raw-kal'; a primitive root;  to travel for trading:—(spice) merchant.

h7409.d: רֶכֶשׁ rekesh, reh'-kesh; from H7408;  a relay of animals on a post-route (as stored up for that purpose); by implication, a courser:—dromedary, mule, swift beast.

h741.d: אֲרִאֵיל ʼăriʼêyl, ar-ee-ale'; either by transposition for H739 or, more probably, an orthographical variation for H2025;  the altar of the temple:—altar.
h741.r: Either by transposition for אֲרִיאֵל (H739) or, more probably, an orthographical variation for הַרְאֵל (H2025)|English: lion-like men

h7410.d: רָם Râm, rawm; active participle of H7311; high;  Ram, the name of an Arabian and of an Israelite:—Ram. See also H1027.
h7410.r: Act part of רוּם (H7311)|English: (lift, hold, etc...) up, exalt, high, offer, give, heave, extol, lofty, take, tall, higher, misc

h7411.d: רָמָה râmâh, raw-maw'; a primitive root;  to hurl; specifically, to shoot; figuratively, to delude or betray (as if causing to fall):—beguile, betray, (bow-) man, carry, deceive, throw.

h7413.d: רָמָה râmâh, raw-maw'; feminine active participle of H7311;  a height (as a seat of idolatry):—high place.
h7413.r: Act part of רוּם (H7311)|English: (lift, hold, etc...) up, exalt, high, offer, give, heave, extol, lofty, take, tall, higher, misc

h7414.d: רָמָה Râmâh, raw-maw'; the same as H7413;  Ramah, the name of four places in Palestine:—Ramah.
h7414.r: The same as רָמָה (H7413)|English: high place

h7416.d: רִמּוֹן rimmôwn, rim-mone'; or רִמֹּן rimmôn; from H7426;  a pomegranate, the tree (from its upright growth) or the fruit (also an artificial ornament):—pomegranate.
h7416.r: From רָמַם (H7426)|English: exalted, lifted up, get up, mount up

h7417.d: רִמּוֹן Rimmôwn, rim-mone'; or (shorter) (רִמֹּן Rimmôn; or רִמּוֹנוֹ Rimmôwnôw; (1 Chronicles 6:62 (H77)), the same as H7416; in Joshua 19:13: הַמְּתֹאָר ham-mᵉthôʼâr is mistaken for part of a name; article with the passive participle of H8388; the (one) marked off, i.e. which pertains).  Rimmon, the name of a Syrian deity, also of five places in Palestine:—Remmon, Rimmon.
h7417.s: proper noun with reference to deity, proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h7417.r: The same as רִמּוֹן (H7416)|English: pomegranate, pomegranate tree

h742.d: אֲרִידַי ʼĂrîyday, ar-ee-dah'-ee; of Persian origin;  Aridai, a son of Haman:—Aridai.

h7420.d: רֹמַח rômach, ro'-makh; from an unused root meaning to hurl;  a lance (as thrown); especially the iron point:—buckler, javelin, lancet, spear.
h7420.r: From an unused root meaning to hurl|

h7422.d: רַמְיָה Ramyâh, ram-yaw'; from H7311 and H3050; Jah has raised;  Ramjah, an Israelite:—Ramiah.
h7422.r: From רוּם (H7311) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: (lift, hold, etc...) up, exalt, high, offer, give, heave, extol, lofty, take, tall, higher, misc

h7423.d: רְמִיָּה rᵉmîyâh, rem-ee-yaw'; from H7411;  remissness, treachery:—deceit(-ful, -fully), false, guile, idle, slack, slothful.
h7423.r: From רָמָה (H7411)|English: deceived, beguiled, thrown, betray, bowmen, carrying, deceived so

h7429.d: רָמַס râmaç, raw-mas'; a primitive root;  to tread upon (as a potter, in walking or abusively):—oppressor, stamp upon, trample (under feet), tread (down, upon).

h743.d: אֲרִידָתָא ʼĂrîydâthâʼ, ar-ee-daw-thaw'; of Persian origin;  Aridatha, a son of Haman:—Aridatha.

h7430.d: רָמַשׂ râmas, raw-mas'; a primitive root;  properly, to glide swiftly, i.e. to crawl or move with short steps; by analogy to swarm:—creep, move.

h7431.d: רֶמֶשׂ remes, reh'-mes; from H7430;  a reptile or any other rapidly moving animal:—that creepeth, creeping (moving) thing.

h7433.d: רָמֹת גִּלעָד Râmôth Gilʻâd, raw-moth' gil-awd'; or רָמוֹת גִּלעָד Râmôwth Gilʻâd; (2 Chronicles 22:5), from the plural of H7413 and H1568; heights of Gilad;  Ramoth-Gilad, a place East of the Jordan:—Ramoth-gilead, Ramoth in Gilead. See also H7216.
h7433.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h7433.r: From the pl. of רָמָה (H7413) and גִּלְעָד (H1568)|English: high place

h7437.d: רָמַת לֶחִי Râmath Lechîy, raw'-math lekh'-ee; from H7413 and H3895; height of a jaw-bone;  Ramath-Lechi, a place in Palestine:—Ramath-lehi.
h7437.r: From רָמָה (H7413) and לְחִי (H3895)|English: high place

h7440.d: רִנָּה rinnâh, rin-naw'; from H7442;  properly, a creaking (or shrill sound), i.e. shout (of joy or grief):—cry, gladness, joy, proclamation, rejoicing, shouting, sing(-ing), triumph.
h7440.r: From רָנַן (H7442)|English: sing, rejoice, sing aloud, shout, shout for joy, sing for joy, crieth, cry out, shout aloud, misc

h7442.d: רָנַן rânan, raw-nan'; a primitive root;  properly, to creak (or emit a stridulous sound), i.e. to shout (usually for joy):—aloud for joy, cry out, be joyful (greatly, make to) rejoice, (cause to) shout (for joy), (cause to) sing (aloud, for joy, out), triumph.

h7445.d: רְנָנָה rᵉnânâh, ren-aw-naw'; from H7442;  a shout (for joy):—joyful (voice), singing, triumphing.
h7445.r: From רָנַן (H7442)|English: sing, rejoice, sing aloud, shout, shout for joy, sing for joy, crieth, cry out, shout aloud, misc

h7448.d: רֶסֶן reçen, reh'-sen; from an unused root meaning to curb;  a halter (as restraining); by implication, the jaw:—bridle.
h7448.r: From an unused root meaning to curb|

h7451.d: רַע raʻ, rah; from H7489;  bad or (as noun) evil (natural or moral):—adversity, affliction, bad, calamity,   displease(-ure), distress, evil((-favouredness), man, thing), + exceedingly, × great, grief(-vous), harm, heavy, hurt(-ful), ill (favoured), + mark, mischief(-vous), misery, naught(-ty), noisome, + not please, sad(-ly), sore, sorrow, trouble, vex, wicked(-ly, -ness, one), worse(-st), wretchedness, wrong. (Including feminine raaah; as adjective or noun.)
h7451.s: absolute state masculine plural intensive noun
h7451.r: From רָעַע (H7489)|English: evil, evildoer, hurt, wickedly, worse, afflict, wicked, break, doer, ill, harm, displease, misc

h7453.d: רֵעַ rêaʻ, ray'-ah; or רֵיעַ rêyaʻ; from H7462;  an associate (more or less close):—brother, companion, fellow, friend, husband, lover, neighbour, × (an-) other.
h7453.r: From רָעָה (H7462)|English: feed, shepherd, pastor, herdmen, keep, companion, broken, company, devour, eat, entreateth, misc

h7456.d: רָעֵב râʻêb, raw-abe'; a primitive root;  to hunger:—(suffer to) famish, (be, have, suffer, suffer to) hunger(-ry).

h7457.d: רָעֵב râʻêb, raw-abe'; from H7456;  hungry (more or less intensely):—hunger bitten, hungry.
h7457.r: From רָעֵב (H7456)|English: ..hunger, hungry, suffer famish, famished

h7458.d: רָעָב râʻâb, raw-awb'; from H7456;  hunger (more or less extensive):—dearth, famine,   famished, hunger.
h7458.r: From רָעֵב (H7456)|English: ..hunger, hungry, suffer famish, famished

h746.d: אֲרְיוֹךְ ʼĂryôwk, ar-yoke'; of foreign origin;  Arjok, the name of two Babylonians:—Arioch.

h7460.d: רָעַד râʻad, raw-ad'; a primitive root;  to shudder (more or less violently):—tremble.
h7460.r: A primitive root, to shudder (more or less violently)|

h7461.d: רַעַד raʻad, rah'-ad; or (feminine) רְעָדָה rᵉʻâdâhxlit rᵉâdâh corrected to rᵉʻâdâh; from H7460;  a shudder:—trembling.

h7462.d: רָעָה râʻâh, raw-aw'; a primitive root;  to tend a flock; i.e. pasture it; intransitively, to graze (literally or figuratively); generally to rule; by extension, to associate with (as a friend):—× break, companion, keep company with, devour, eat up, evil entreat, feed, use as a friend, make friendship with, herdman, keep (sheep) (-er), pastor,   shearing house, shepherd, wander, waste.

h7463.d: רֵעֶה rêʻeh, ray-eh'; from H7462;  a (male) companion:—friend.
h7463.r: From רָעָה (H7462)|English: feed, shepherd, pastor, herdmen, keep, companion, broken, company, devour, eat, entreateth, misc

h7466.d: רְעוּ Rᵉʻûw, reh-oo'; for H7471 in the sense of H7453; friend;  Reu, a postdiluvian patriarch:—Reu.
h7466.r: For רְעִי (H7471) in the sense of רֵעַ (H7453)|English: pasture

h7467.d: רְעוּאֵל Rᵉʻûwʼêl, reh-oo-ale'; from the same as H7466 and H410; friend of God;  Reuel, the name of Moses' father-in-law, also of an Edomite and an Israelite:—Raguel, Reuel.
h7467.r: From the same as רְעוּ (H7466) and אֵל (H410)|English: Reu

h747.d: אֲרִיסַי ʼĂrîyçay, ar-ee-sah'-ee; of Persian origin;  Arisai, a son of Haman:—Arisai.

h7471.d: רְעִי rᵉʻîy, reh-ee'; from H7462;  pasture:—pasture.
h7471.r: From רָעָה (H7462)|English: feed, shepherd, pastor, herdmen, keep, companion, broken, company, devour, eat, entreateth, misc

h7472.d: רֵעִי Rêʻîy, ray-ee'; from H7453; social;  Rei, an Israelite:—Rei.
h7472.r: From רֵעַ (H7453)|English: neighbour, friend, another, fellow, companion, other, brother, husband, lovers, neighbour

h7473.d: רֹעִי rôʻîy, ro-ee'; from active participle of H7462;  pastoral; as noun, a shepherd:—shipherd.
h7473.r: From act part of רָעָה (H7462)|English: feed, shepherd, pastor, herdmen, keep, companion, broken, company, devour, eat, entreateth, misc

h748.d: אָרַךְ ʼârak, aw-rak'; a primitive root;  to be (causative, make) long (literally or figuratively):—defer, draw out, lengthen, (be, become, make, pro-) long,   (out-, over-) live, tarry (long).

h7480.d: רְעֵלָיָה Rᵉʻêlâyâh, reh-ay-law-yaw'; from H7477 and H3050; made to tremble (i.e. fearful) of Jah;  Reelajah, an Israelite:—Reeliah.
h7480.r: From רָעַל (H7477) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: terribly shaken

h7481.d: רָעַם râʻam, raw-am'; a primitive root;  to tumble, i.e. be violently agitated; specifically, to crash (of thunder); figuratively, to irritate (with anger):—make to fret, roar, thunder, trouble.

h7482.d: רַעַם raʻam, rah'am; from H7481;  a peal of thunder:—thunder.
h7482.r: From רָעַם (H7481)|English: thunder, roar, trouble, fret

h7485.d: רַעַמְיָה Raʻamyâh, rah-am-yaw'; from H7481 and H3050; Jah has shaken;  Raamjah, an Israelite:—Raamiah.
h7485.r: From רָעַם (H7481) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: thunder, roar, trouble, fret

h7488.d: רַעֲנָן raʻănân, rah-an-awn'; from an unused root meaning to be green;  verdant; by analogy, new; figuratively, prosperous:—green, flourishing.
h7488.r: From an unused root meaning to be green|

h7489.d: רָעַע râʻaʻ, raw-ah'; a primitive root;  properly, to spoil (literally, by breaking to pieces); figuratively, to make (or be) good for nothing, i.e. bad (physically, socially or morally):—afflict, associate selves (by mistake for 7462), break (down, in pieces),   displease, (be, bring, do) evil (doer, entreat, man), show self friendly (by mistake for 7462), do harm, (do) hurt, (behave self, deal) ill, × indeed, do mischief, punish, still, vex, (do) wicked (doer, -ly), be (deal, do) worse.

h7491.d: רָעַף râʻaph, raw-af'; a primitive root;  to drip:—distil, drop (down).

h7492.d: רָעַץ râʻats, raw-ats'; a primitive root;  to break in pieces; figuratively, harass:—dash in pieces, vex.

h7493.d: רָעַשׁ râʻash, raw-ash; a primitive root;  to undulate (as the earth, the sky, etc.; also a field of grain), particularly through fear; specifically, to spring (as a locust):—make afraid, (re-) move, quake, (make to) shake, (make to) tremble.

h7494.d: רַעַשׁ raʻash, rah'-ash; from H7493;  vibration, bounding, uproar:—commotion, confused noise, earthquake, fierceness, quaking, rattling, rushing, shaking.
h7494.r: From רָעַשׁ (H7493)|English: shake, tremble, moved, afraid, quake, remove

h7495.d: רָפָא râphâʼ, raw-faw'; or רָפָה râphâh; a primitive root;  properly, to mend (by stitching), i.e. (figuratively) to cure:—cure, (cause to) heal, physician, repair, × thoroughly, make whole. See H7503.

h7498.d: רָפָא Râphâʼ, raw-faw'; or רָפָה Râphâh; probably the same as H7497; giant;  Rapha or Raphah, the name of two Israelites:—Rapha.
h7498.r: Probably the same as רְפָאִים (H7497)|English: giant, Rephaim

h7499.d: רְפֻאָה rᵉphuʼâh, ref-oo-aw'; feminine passive participle of H7495;  a medicament:—heal(-ed), medicine.
h7499.r: Pass part of רָפָא (H7495)|English: heal, physician, cure, repaired, misc

h750.d: אָרֵךְ ʼârêk, aw-rake'; from H748;  long:—long(-suffering, -winged), patient, slow (to anger).
h750.r: From אָרַךְ (H748)|English: prolong, long, lengthen, draw out, defer, tarried, ...lived

h7501.d: רְפָאֵל Rᵉphâʼêl, ref-aw-ale'; from H7495 and H410; God has cured;  Rephael, an Israelite:—Rephael.
h7501.r: From רָפָא (H7495) and אֵל (H410)|English: heal, physician, cure, repaired, misc

h7502.d: רָפַד râphad, raw-fad'; a primitive root;  to spread (a bed); by implication, to refresh:—comfort, make (a bed), spread.

h7503.d: רָפָה râphâh, raw-faw'; a primitive root;  to slacken (in many applications, literal or figurative):—abate, cease, consume, draw (toward evening), fail, (be) faint, be (wax) feeble, forsake, idle, leave, let alone (go, down), (be) slack, stay, be still, be slothful, (be) weak(-en).
