h7663.d: שָׂבַר sâbar, saw-bar'; erroneously שָׁבַר shâbar; (Nehemiah 2:13,15), a primitive root;  to scrutinize; by implication (of watching) to expect (with hope and patience):—hope, tarry, view, wait.

h7665.d: שָׁבַר shâbar, shaw-bar'; a primitive root;  to burst (literally or figuratively):—break (down, off, in pieces, up), broken (-hearted), bring to the birth, crush, destroy, hurt, quench, × quite, tear, view (by mistake for H7663).

h7666.d: שָׁבַר shâbar, shaw-bar'; denominative from H7668;  to deal in grain:—buy, sell.

h7667.d: שֶׁבֶר sheber, sheh'-ber; or שֵׁבֶר shêber; from H7665;  a fracture, figuratively, ruin; specifically, a solution (of a dream):—affliction, breach, breaking, broken(-footed, -handed), bruise, crashing, destruction, hurt, interpretation, vexation.
h7667.r: From שָׁבַר (H7665)|English: break, destroy, break in pieces, break down, hurt, torn, give birth, crush, quench, misc

h7668.d: שֶׁבֶר sheber, sheh'-ber; the same as H7667;  grain (as if broken into kernels):—corn, victuals.
h7668.r: The same as שֶׁבַר (H7667)|English: destruction, breach, hurt, breaking, affliction, bruise, crashing, interpretation, vexation, misc

h7669.d: שֶׁבֶר Sheber, sheh'-ber; the same as H7667;  Sheber, an Israelite:—Sheber.
h7669.r: The same as שֶׁבַר (H7667)|English: destruction, breach, hurt, breaking, affliction, bruise, crashing, interpretation, vexation, misc

h767.d: אֹרֶן ʼÔren, o'-ren; the same as H766;  Oren, an Israelite:—Oren.

h7670.d: שִׁבְרוֹן shibrôwn, shib-rone'; from H7665;  rupture, i.e. a pang; figuratively, ruin:—breaking, destruction.
h7670.r: From שָׁבַר (H7665)|English: break, destroy, break in pieces, break down, hurt, torn, give birth, crush, quench, misc

h7673.d: שָׁבַת shâbath, shaw-bath'; a primitive root;  to repose, i.e. desist from exertion; used in many implied relations (causative, figurative or specific):—(cause to, let, make to) cease, celebrate, cause (make) to fail, keep (sabbath), suffer to be lacking, leave, put away (down), (make to) rest, rid, still, take away.

h7677.d: שַׁבָּתוֹן shabbâthôwn, shab-baw-thone'; from H7676;  a sabbatism or special holiday:—rest, sabbath.

h7678.d: שַׁבְּתַי Shabbᵉthay, shab-beth-ah'-ee; from H7676; restful;  Shabbethai, the name of three Israelites:—Shabbethai.

h7679.d: שָׂגָא sâgâʼ, saw-gaw'; a primitive root;  to grow, i.e. (causatively) to enlarge, (figuratively) laud:—increase, magnify.
h7679.r: To grow, i.e. (causatively) to enlarge, (fig) laud|

h7680.d: שְׂגָא sᵉgâʼ, seg-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7679;  to increase:—grow, be multiplied.

h7682.d: שָׂגַב sâgab, saw-gab'; a primitive root;  to be (causatively, make) lofty, especially inaccessible; by implication, safe, strong; used literally and figuratively:—defend, exalt, be excellent, (be, set on) high, lofty, be safe, set up (on high), be too strong.

h7683.d: שָׁגַג shâgag, shaw-gag'; a primitive root;  to stray, i.e. (figuratively) sin (with more or less apology):—× also for that, deceived, err, go astray, sin ignorantly.

h7684.d: שְׁגָגָה shᵉgâgâh, sheg-aw-gaw'; from H7683;  a mistake or inadvertent transgression:—error, ignorance, at unawares; unwittingly.
h7684.r: From שָׁגַג (H7683)|English: err, flesh, sin ignorantly, deceived, went astray

h7685.d: שָׂגָה sâgâh, saw-gaw'; a primitive root;  to enlarge (especially upward, also figuratively):—grow (up), increase.

h7686.d: שָׁגָה shâgâh, shaw-gaw'; a primitive root;  to stray (causatively, mislead), usually (figuratively) to mistake, especially (morally) to transgress; by extension (through the idea of intoxication) to reel, (figuratively) be enraptured:—(cause to) go astray, deceive, err, be ravished, sin through ignorance, (let, make to) wander.

h7687.d: שְׂגוּב Sᵉgûwb, seg-oob'; from H7682; aloft;  Segub, the name of two Israelites:—Segub.
h7687.r: From שָׂגַב (H7682)|English: high, exalted, defend, safe, excellent, misc

h769.d: אַרְנוֹן ʼArnôwn, ar-nohn'; or אַרְנֹן ʼArnônlemma אַרְנן missing vowel, corrected to אַרְנֹן; from H7442; a brawling stream;  the Arnon, a river east of the Jordan, also its territory:—Arnon.
h769.r: From רָנַן (H7442)|English: sing, rejoice, sing aloud, shout, shout for joy, sing for joy, crieth, cry out, shout aloud, misc

h7690.d: שַׂגִּיא saggîyʼ, sag-ghee'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7689;  large (in size, quantity or number, also adverbial):—exceeding, great(-ly); many, much, sore, very.

h7696.d: שָׁגַע shâgaʻ, shaw-gah'; a primitive root;  to rave through insanity:—(be, play the) mad (man).

h7697.d: שִׁגָּעוֹן shiggâʻôwn, shig-gaw-yone'; from H7696;  craziness:—furiously, madness.

h7699.d: שַׁד shad, shad; or שֹׁד shôd; probably from H7736 (in its original sense) contracted;  the breast of a woman or animal (as bulging):—breast, pap, teat.
h7699.r: Probably from שׁוּד (H7736) (in its original sense) contracted|English: waste

h7701.d: שֹׁד shôd, shode; or שׁוֹד shôwd; (Job 5:21), from H7736;  violence, ravage:—desolation, destruction, oppression, robbery, spoil(-ed, -er, -ing), wasting.

h7703.d: שָׁדַד shâdad, shaw-dad'; a primitive root;  properly, to be burly, i.e. (figuratively) powerful (passively, impregnable); by implication, to ravage:—dead, destroy(-er), oppress, robber, spoil(-er), × utterly, (lay) waste.

h7704.d: שָׂדֶה sâdeh, saw-deh'; or שָׂדַי sâday; from an unused root meaning to spread out;  a field (as flat):—country, field, ground, land, soil, × wild.
h7704.r: From an unused root meaning to spread out|

h7705.d: שִׁדָּה shiddâh, shid-dah'; from H7703;  a wife (as mistress of the house):—× all sorts, musical instrument.
h7705.r: From שָׁדַד (H7703)|English: spoil, spoiler, waste, destroy, robbers, misc

h7706.d: שַׁדַּי Shadday, shad-dah'-ee; from H7703;  the Almighty:—Almighty.
h7706.s: masculine noun with reference to deity
h7706.r: From שָׁדַד (H7703)|English: spoil, spoiler, waste, destroy, robbers, misc

h771.d: אׇרְנָן ʼOrnân, or-nawn'; probably from H766; strong;  Ornan, a Jebusite:—Ornan. See H728.

h7714.d: שַׁדְרַךְ Shadrak, shad-rak'; probably of foreign origin;  Shadrak, the Babylonian name of one of Daniel's companions:—Shadrach.

h7715.d: שַׁדְרַךְ Shadrak, shad-rak'; (Aramaic) the same as H7714:—Shadrach.

h7716.d: שֶׂה seh, seh; or שֵׂי sêy; probably from H7582 through the idea of pushing out to graze;  a member of a flock, i.e. a sheep or goat:—(lesser, small) cattle, ewe, goat, lamb, sheep. Compare H2089.
h7716.r: Probably from שָׁאָה (H7582) through the idea of pushing out to graze|English: lay waste, rushing, waste, desolate

h7718.d: שֹׁהַם shôham, sho'-ham; from an unused root probably mean to blanch;  a gem, probably the beryl (from its pale green color):—onyx.
h7718.r: From an unused root probably mean to blanch|

h7719.d: שֹׁהַם Shôham, sho'-ham; the same as H7718;  Shoham, an Israelite:—Shoham.

h772.d: אֲרַע ʼăraʻ, ar-ah'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H776;  the earth; by implication (figuratively) low:—earth, interior.
h772.r: Corresponding to אֶרֶץ (H776)|English: land, earth, country, ground, world, way, common, field, nations, wilderness

h7720.d: שַׂהֲרֹן sahărôn, sah-har-one'; from the same as H5469;  a round pendant for the neck:—ornament, round tire like the moon.
h7720.r: From the same as סַהַר (H5469)|English: round

h7723.d: שָׁוְא shâvᵉʼ, shawv; or שַׁו shav; from the same as H7722 in the sense of desolating;  evil (as destructive), literally (ruin) or morally (especially guile); figuratively idolatry (as false, subjective), uselessness (as deceptive, objective; also adverbially, in vain):—false(-ly), lie, lying, vain, vanity.
h7723.r: From the same as שׁוֹא (H7722) in the sense of desolating|English: desolation, destruction, desolate, destroy, storm, wasteness

h7724.d: שְׁוָא Shᵉvâʼ, shev-aw'; from the same as H7723; false;  Sheva, an Israelite:—Sheva.
h7724.r: From the same as שָׁוְא (H7723)|English: vain, vanity, false, lying, falsely, lies

h7725.d: שׁוּב shûwb, shoob; a primitive root;  to turn back (hence, away) transitively or intransitively, literally or figuratively (not necessarily with the idea of return to the starting point); generally to retreat; often adverbial, again:—((break, build, circumcise, dig, do anything, do evil, feed, lay down, lie down, lodge, make, rejoice, send, take, weep)) × again, (cause to) answer (  again), × in any case (wise), × at all, averse, bring (again, back, home again), call (to mind), carry again (back), cease, × certainly, come again (back), × consider,   continually, convert, deliver (again),   deny, draw back, fetch home again, × fro, get (oneself) (back) again, × give (again), go again (back, home), (go) out, hinder, let, (see) more, × needs, be past, × pay, pervert, pull in again, put (again, up again), recall, recompense, recover, refresh, relieve, render (again), requite, rescue, restore, retrieve, (cause to, make to) return, reverse, reward,   say nay, send back, set again, slide back, still, × surely, take back (off), (cause to, make to) turn (again, self again, away, back, back again, backward, from, off), withdraw.

h7727.d: שׁוֹבָב Shôwbâb, sho-bawb'; the same as H7726; rebellious;  Shobab, the name of two Israelites:—Shobab.
h7727.r: The same as שׁוֹבָב (H7726)|English: backsliding, frowardly, variant

h7730.d: שׂוֹבֶךְ sôwbek, so'-bek; for H5441;  a thicket, i.e. interlaced branches:—thick boughs.

h7731.d: שׁוֹבָךְ Shôwbâk, sho-bawk'; perhaps for H7730;  Shobak, a Syrian:—Shobach.

h7732.d: שׁוֹבָל Shôwbâl, sho-bawl'; from the same as H7640; overflowing;  Shobal, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites:—Shobal.
h7732.r: From the same as שֹׁבֶל (H7640)|English: leg

h7733.d: שׁוֹבֵק Shôwbêq, sho-bake'; active participle from a primitive root meaning to leave (compare H7662); forsaking;  Shobek, an Israelite:—Shobek.
h7733.r: Act part from a primitive root meaning to leave (compare שְׁבַק (H7662))|English: leave, let alone

h7734.d: שׂוּג sûwg, soog; a primitive root;  to retreat:—turn back.

h7737.d: שָׁוָה shâvâh, shaw-vaw'; a primitive root;  properly, to level, i.e. equalize; figuratively, to resemble; by implication, to adjust (i.e. counterbalance, be suitable, compose, place, yield, etc.):—avail, behave, bring forth, compare, countervail, (be, make) equal, lay, be (make, a-) like, make plain, profit, reckon.

h7743.d: שׁוּחַ shûwach, shoo'-akh; a primitive root;  to sink, literally or figuratively:—bow down, incline, humble.

h7745.d: שׁוּחָה shûwchâh, shoo-khaw'; from H7743;  a chasm:—ditch, pit.
h7745.r: From שׁוּחַ (H7743)|English: bowed down, inclined, humbled

h775.d: אַרְפַּכְשַׁד ʼArpakshad, ar-pak-shad'; probably of foreign origin;  Arpakshad, a son of Noah; also the region settled by him:—Arphaxad.

h7751.d: שׁוּט shûwṭ, shoot; a primitive root;  properly, to push forth; (but used only figuratively) to lash, i.e. (the sea with oars) to row; by implication, to travel:—go (about, through, to and fro), mariner, rower, run to and fro.

h7752.d: שׁוֹט shôwṭ, shote; from H7751;  a lash (literally or figuratively):—scourge, whip.
h7752.r: From שׁוּט (H7751)|English: run to and fro, go to and fro, go about, gone, mariners, rowers, go through

h7755.d: שׂוֹכֹה Sôwkôh, so-ko'; or שֹׂכֹה Sôkôh; or שׂוֹכוֹ Sôwkôw; from H7753;  Sokoh or Soko, the name of two places in Palestine:—Shocho, Shochoh, Sochoh, Soco, Socoh.
h7755.r: From שׂוּךְ (H7753)|English: make a hedge, hedge, fence

h7758.d: שׁוֹלָל shôwlâl, sho-lawl'; or שֵׁילָל shêylâl; (Micah 1:8), from H7997;  nude (especially bare-foot); by implication, captive:—spoiled, stripped.
h7758.r: From שָׁלַל (H7997)|English: spoil, take, fall, prey, purpose

h776.d: אֶרֶץ ʼerets, eh'-rets; from an unused root probably meaning to be firm;  the earth (at large, or partitively a land):—× common, country, earth, field, ground, land, × natins, way, + wilderness, world.
h776.r: From an unused root probably meaning to be firm|

h7760.d: שׂוּם sûwm, soom; or שִׂים sîym; a primitive root;  to put (used in a great variety of applications, literal, figurative, inferentially, and elliptically):—× any wise, appoint, bring, call (a name), care, cast in, change, charge, commit, consider, convey, determine,   disguise, dispose, do, get, give, heap up, hold, impute, lay (down, up), leave, look, make (out), mark,   name, × on, ordain, order,   paint, place, preserve, purpose, put (on),   regard, rehearse, reward, (cause to) set (on, up), shew,   stedfastly, take, × tell,   tread down, (over-)turn, × wholly, work.

h7761.d: שׂוּם sûwm, soom; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7760:—  command, give, lay, make,   name,   regard, set.
h7761.r: Corresponding to שׂוּם (H7760)|English: put, make, set, lay, appoint, give, set up, consider, turn, brought, ordain, place, take, shew, regard, mark, disposed, care, misc

h7763.d: שׁוֹמֵר Shôwmêr, sho-mare'; or שֹׁמֵר Shômêr; active participle of H8104; keeper;  Shomer, the name of two Israelites:—Shomer.
h7763.r: Act part of שָׁמַר (H8104)|English: keep, observe, heed, keeper, preserve, beware, mark, watchman, wait, watch, regard, save, misc

h7764.d: שׁוּנִי Shûwnîy, shoo-nee'; from an unused root meaning to rest; quiet;  Shuni, an Israelite:—Shuni.
h7764.r: From an unused root meaning to rest|

h7767.d: שׁוּנַמִּית Shûwnammîyth, shoo-nam-meeth'; patrial from H7766;  a Shunammitess, or female inhabitant of Shunem:—Shunamite.

h7768.d: שָׁוַע shâvaʻ, shaw-vah'; a primitive root;  properly, to be free; but used only causatively and reflexively, to halloo (for help, i.e. freedom from some trouble):—cry (aloud, out), shout.

h7769.d: שׁוּעַ shûwaʻ, shoo'-ah; from H7768;  a halloo:—cry, riches.
h7769.r: From שָׁוַע (H7768)|English: cried, cry out, aloud, shout

h7770.d: שׁוּעַ Shûwaʻ, shoo'-ah; the same as H7769;  Shua, a Canaanite:—Shua, Shuah.
h7770.r: The same as שׁוֹעַ (H7769)|English: cry, riches

h7776.d: שׁוּעָל shûwʻâl, shoo-awl'; or שֻׁעָל shuʻâl; from the same as H8168;  a jackal (as a burrower):—fox.
h7776.r: From the same as שֹׁעַל (H8168)|English: handful, hollow of his hand

h7777.d: שׁוּעָל Shûwʻâl, shoo-awl'; the same as H7776;  Shual, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine:—Shual.
h7777.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h7778.d: שׁוֹעֵר shôwʻêr, sho-are'; or שֹׁעֵר shôʻêr active participle of H8176 (as denominative from H8179);  a janitor:—doorkeeper, porter.
h7778.r: From שַׁעַר (H8179)|English: gate, city, door, port, porters

h7780.d: שׁוֹפָךְ Shôwphâk, sho-fawk'; from H8210; poured;  Shophak, a Syrian:—Shophach.
h7780.r: From שָׁפַךְ (H8210)|English: pour out, shed, pour, cast, gush out, misc

h7782.d: שׁוֹפָר shôwphâr, sho-far'; or שֹׁפָר shôphâr; from H8231 in the original sense of incising;  a cornet (as giving a clear sound) or curved horn:—cornet, trumpet.
h7782.r: From שָׁפַר (H8231) in the original sense of incising|English: goodly

h7783.d: שׁוּק shûwq, shook; a primitive root;  to run after or over, i.e. overflow:—overflow, water.

h7785.d: שׁוֹק shôwq, shoke; from H7783;  the (lower) leg (as a runner):—hip, leg, shoulder, thigh.

h7789.d: שׁוּר shûwr, shoor; a primitive root (identical with through the idea of going round for inspection);  to spy out, i.e. (generally) survey, (for evil) lurk for, (for good) care for:—behold, lay wait, look, observe, perceive, regard, see.
h7789.r: A primitive root [identical with שׁוּר (H7788) through the idea of going round for inspection]|English: went, sing

h779.d: אָרַר ʼârar, aw-rar'; a primitive root;  to execrate:—× bitterly curse.

h7794.d: שׁוֹר shôwr, shore; from H7788;  a bullock (as a traveller):—bull(-ock), cow, ox, wall (by mistake for H7791).

h7797.d: שׂוּשׂ sûws, soos; or שִׂישׂ sîys; a primitive root;  to be bright, i.e. cheerful:—be glad, × greatly, joy, make mirth, rejoice.

h7799.d: שׁוּשַׁן shûwshan, shoo-shan'; or שׁוֹשָׁן shôwshân; or שֹׁשָׁן shôshân; and (feminine) שׁוֹשַׁנָּה shôwshannâh; from H7797;  a lily (from its whiteness), as a flower of architectural ornament; also a (straight) trumpet (from the tubular shape):—lily, Shoshannim.
h7799.r: From שׂוּשׂ (H7797)|English: rejoice, glad, greatly, joy, mirth

h78.d: אִבְצָן ʼIbtsân, ib-tsawn'; from the same as H76; splendid;  Ibtsan, an Israelite:—Ibzan.
h78.r: From the same as אֲבַעְבֻּעֹת (H76)|English: blains

h7803.d: שׁוּתֶלַח Shûwthelach, shoo-theh'-lakh; probably from H7582 and the same as H8520; crash of breakage;  Shuthelach, the name of two Israelites:—Shuthelah.
h7803.r: Probably from שָׁאָה (H7582) and the same as תֶּלַח (H8520)|English: lay waste, rushing, waste, desolate

h7804.d: שְׁזַב shᵉzab, shez-ab'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H5800;  to leave, i.e. (causatively) free:—deliver.
h7804.r: Corresponding to עָזַב (H5800)|English: forsake, leave, leave off, faileth, fortify, help, committeth, destitute, refuseth, surely

h7810.d: שַׁחַד shachad, shakh'-ad; from H7809;  a donation (venal or redemptive):—bribe(-ry), gift, present, reward.

h7812.d: שָׁחָה shâchâh, shaw-khaw'; a primitive root;  to depress, i.e. prostrate (especially reflexive, in homage to royalty or God):—bow (self) down, crouch, fall down (flat), humbly beseech, do (make) obeisance, do reverence, make to stoop, worship.

h7814.d: שְׂחוֹק sᵉchôwq, sekh-oke'; or שְׂחֹק sᵉchôq; from H7832;  laughter (in merriment or defiance):—derision, laughter(-ed to scorn, -ing), mocked, sport.
h7814.r: From שָׂחַק (H7832)|English: play, laugh, rejoice, scorn, sport, merry, mock, deride, derision, mockers

h7815.d: שְׁחוֹר shᵉchôwr, shekh-ore'; from H7835;  dinginess, i.e. perhaps soot:—coal.

h7817.d: שָׁחַח shâchach, shaw-khakh'; a primitive root;  to sink or depress (reflexive or causative):—bend, bow (down), bring (cast) down, couch, humble self, be (bring) low, stoop.

h7819.d: שָׁחַט shâchaṭ, shaw-khat'; a primitive root;  to slaughter (in sacrifice or massacre):—kill, offer, shoot out, slay, slaughter.

h7822.d: שְׁחִין shᵉchîyn, shekh-een'; from an unused root probably meaning to burn;  inflammation, i.e. an ulcer:—boil, botch.
h7822.r: From an unused root probably meaning to burn|

h7823.d: שָׁחִיס shâchîyç, shaw-khece'; or סָחִישׁ çâchîysh; from an unused root apparently meaning to sprout;  after-growth:—(that) which springeth of the same.
h7823.r: From an unused root apparently meaning to sprout|

h7828.d: שַׁחַף shachaph, shakh'-af; from an unused root meaning to peel, i.e. emaciate;  the gull (as thin):—cuckoo.
h7828.r: From an unused root meaning to peel, i.e. emaciate|

h783.d: אַרְתַּחְשַׁשְׁתָּא ʼArtachshashtâʼ, ar-takh-shash-taw'; or אַרְתַּחְשַׁשְׁתְּא ʼArtachshashtᵉʼ; or by permutation אַרְתַּחְשַׁסְתְּא ʼArtachshaçtᵉʼ; of foreign origin;  Artachshasta (or Artaxerxes), a title (rather than name) of several Persian kings:—Artaxerxes.

h7832.d: שָׂחַק sâchaq, saw-khak'; a primitive root;  to laugh (in pleasure or detraction); by implication, to play:—deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mock(-er), play, rejoice, (laugh to) scorn, be in (make) sport.

h7833.d: שָׁחַק shâchaq, shaw-khak'; a primitive root;  to comminate (by trituration or attrition):—beat, wear.

h7835.d: שָׁחַר shâchar, shaw-khar'; a primitive root (identical with H7836 through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn);  to be dim or dark (in color):—be black.
h7835.r: A primitive root [identical with שָׁחַר (H7836) through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn]|English: seek early, seek, diligently seek, betimes, misc

h7836.d: שָׁחַר shâchar, shaw-khar'; a primitive root;  properly, to dawn, i.e. (figuratively) be (up) early at any task (with the implication of earnestness); by extension, to search for (with painstaking):—(do something) betimes, enquire early, rise (seek) betimes, seek diligently) early, in the morning).

h7837.d: שַׁחַר shachar, shakh'-ar; from H7836;  dawn (literal, figurative or adverbial):—day(-spring), early, light, morning, whence riseth.
h7837.r: From שָׁחַר (H7836)|English: seek early, seek, diligently seek, betimes, misc

h7838.d: שָׁחֹר shâchôr, shaw-khore'; or שָׁחוֹר shâchôwr; from H7835;  properly, dusky, but also (absolute) jetty:—black.

h784.d: אֵשׁ ʼêsh, aysh; a primitive word;  fire (literally or figuratively):—burning, fiery, fire, flaming, hot.

h7841.d: שְׁחַרְיָה Shᵉcharyâh, shekh-ar-yaw'; from H7836 and H3050; Jah has sought;  Shecharjah, an Israelite:—Shehariah.
h7841.r: From שָׁחַר (H7836) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: seek early, seek, diligently seek, betimes, misc

h7842.d: שַׁחֲרַיִם Shachărayim, shakh-ar-ah'-yim; dual of H7837; double dawn;  Shacharajim, an Israelite:—Shaharaim.
h7842.r: Dual of שַׁחַר (H7837)|English: morning, day, early, dayspring, light, riseth, Shahar

h7843.d: שָׁחַת shâchath, shaw-khath'; a primitive root;  to decay, i.e. (causatively) ruin (literally or figuratively):—batter, cast off, corrupt(-er, thing), destroy(-er, -uction), lose, mar, perish, spill, spoiler, × utterly, waste(-r).

h7844.d: שְׁחַת shᵉchath, shekh-ath'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7843:—corrupt, fault.
h7844.r: Corresponding to שָׁחַת (H7843)|English: destroy, corrupt, mar, destroyer, corrupters, waster, spoilers, battered, corruptly, misc

h7845.d: שַׁחַת shachath, shakh'-ath; from H7743;  a pit (especially as a trap); figuratively, destruction:—corruption, destruction, ditch, grave, pit.
h7845.r: From שׁוּחַ (H7743)|English: bowed down, inclined, humbled

h7847.d: שָׂטָה sâṭâh, saw-taw'; a primitive root;  to deviate from duty:—decline, go aside, turn.

h7848.d: שִׁטָּה shiṭṭâh, shit-taw'; feminine of a derivative (only in the plural שִׁטִּים shiṭṭîym; meaning the sticks of wood) from the same as H7850;  the acacia (from its scourging thorns):—shittah, shittim. See also H1029.
h7848.r: Meaning the sticks of wood [from the same as שֹׁטֵט (H7850)]|English: scourge

h785.d: אֵשׁ ʼêsh, aysh; (Aramaic) corresponding to H784:—flame.
h785.r: Corresponding to אֵשׁ (H784)|English: fire, burning, fiery, untranslated variant, fire, flaming, hot

h7852.d: שָׂטַם sâṭam, saw-tam'; a primitive root;  properly, to lurk for, i.e. persecute:—hate, oppose self against.

h7854.d: שָׂטָן sâṭân, saw-tawn'; from H7853;  an opponent; especially (with the article prefixed) Satan, the arch-enemy of good:—adversary, Satan, withstand.

h7856.d: שִׂטְנָה Siṭnâh, sit-naw'; the same as H7855;  Sitnah, the name of a well in Pal:—Sitnah.

h7857.d: שָׁטַף shâṭaph, shaw-taf'; a primitive root;  to gush; by implication, to inundate, cleanse; by analogy, to gallop, conquer:—drown, (over-) flow(-whelm, rinse, run, rush, (throughly) wash (away).

h7858.d: שֶׁטֶף sheṭeph, sheh'-tef; or שֵׁטֶף shêṭeph; from H7857;  a deluge (literally or figuratively):—flood, outrageous, overflowing.
h7858.r: From שָׁטַף (H7857)|English: overflow, rinsed, wash away, drown, flowing, misc

h7859.d: שְׁטַר shᵉṭar, shet-ar'; (Aramaic) of uncertain derivation;  a side:—side.

h7861.d: שִׁטְרַי Shiṭray, shit-rah'-ee; from the same as H7860; magisterial;  Shitrai, an Israelite:—Shitrai.
h7861.r: From the same as שָׁטַר (H7860)|English: officers, ruler, overseer

h7862.d: שַׁי shay, shah'-ee; probably from H7737;  a gift (as available):—present.
h7862.r: Probably from שָׁוָה (H7737)|English: laid, equal, like, compared, profit, set, misc

h7868.d: שִׂיב sîyb, seeb; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7867:—elder.

h7872.d: שֵׂיבָה sêybâh, say-baw'; feminine of H7869;  old age:—(be) gray (grey hoar,-y) hairs (head,-ed), old age.

h7878.d: שִׂיחַ sîyach, see'-akh; a primitive root;  to ponder, i.e. (by implication) converse (with oneself, and hence, aloud) or (transitively) utter:—commune, complain, declare, meditate, muse, pray, speak, talk (with).

h788.d: אַשְׁבֵּל ʼAshbêl, ash-bale'; probably from the same as H7640; flowing;  Ashbel, an Israelite:—Ashbel.
h788.r: Probably from the same as שֹׁבֶל (H7640)|English: leg

h7881.d: שִׂיחָה sîychâh, see-khaw'; feminine of H7879;  reflection; by extension, devotion:—meditation, prayer.
h7881.r: From שִׂיחַ (H7879)|English: complaint, meditation, prayer, talking, communication, babbling

h7891.d: שִׁיר shîyr, sheer; or (the original form) שׁוּר shûwr; (1 Samuel 18:6), a primitive root (rather identical with H7788 through the idea of strolling minstrelsy);  to sing:—behold (by mistake for H7789), sing(-er, -ing man, -ing woman).
h7891.r: A primitive root [identical with שׁוּר (H7788) through the idea of strolling minstrelsy]|English: went, sing

h7892.d: שִׁיר shîyr, sheer; or feminine שִׁירָה shîyrâh; from H7891;  a song; abstractly, singing:—musical(-ick), × sing(-er, -ing), song.
h7892.r: From שִׁיר (H7891)|English: sing, singer, singing men, singing women, behold

h7895.d: שִׁישַׁק Shîyshaq, shee-shak'; or שׁוּשַׁק Shûwshaq; of Egyptian derivation;  Shishak, an Egyptian king:—Shishak.

h7896.d: שִׁית shîyth, sheeth; a primitive root;  to place (in a very wide application):—apply, appoint, array, bring, consider, lay (up), let alone, × look, make, mark, put (on),   regard, set, shew, be stayed, × take.

h79.d: אָבַק ʼâbaq, aw-bak'; a primitive root, probably to float away (as vapor), but used only as denominative from H80;  to bedust, i.e. grapple:—wrestle.
h79.r: A primitive root, probably to float away (as vapour), but used only as denominative from אָבָק (H80)|English: dust, powder

h790.d: אֶשְׁבָּן ʼEshbân, esh-bawn'; probably from the same as H7644; vigorous;  Eshban, an Idumaean:—Eshban.
h790.r: Probably from the same as שֶׁבְנָא (H7644)|English: Shebna

h7901.d: שָׁכַב shâkab, shaw-kab'; a primitive root;  to lie down (for rest, sexual connection, decease or any other purpose):—× at all, cast down, (lover-)lay (self) (down), (make to) lie (down, down to sleep, still with), lodge, ravish, take rest, sleep, stay.

h7902.d: שְׁכָבָה shᵉkâbâh, shek-aw-baw'; from H7901;  a lying down (of dew, or for the sexual act):—× carnally, copulation, × lay, seed.
h7902.r: From שָׁכַב (H7901)|English: lie, sleep, lie down, rest, lien, misc

h7903.d: שְׁכֹבֶת shᵉkôbeth, shek-o'-beth; from H7901;  a (sexual) lying with:—× lie.
h7903.r: From שָׁכַב (H7901)|English: lie, sleep, lie down, rest, lien, misc

h7904.d: שָׁכָה shâkâh, shaw-kaw'; a primitive root;  to roam (through lust):—in the morning (by mistake for H7925).

h7908.d: שְׁכוֹל shᵉkôwl, shek-ole'; infinitive of H7921;  bereavement:—loss of children, spoiling.
h7908.r: Infinitive of שָׁכֹל (H7921)|English: bereave, barren, childless, cast young, cast a calf, lost children, rob of children, deprived, misc

h7909.d: שַׁכּוּל shakkûwl, shak-kool'; or שַׁכֻּל shakkul; from H7921;  bereaved:—barren, bereaved (robbed) of children (whelps).
h7909.r: From שָׁכֹל (H7921)|English: bereave, barren, childless, cast young, cast a calf, lost children, rob of children, deprived, misc

h7910.d: שִׁכּוֹר shikkôwr, shik-kore'; or שִׁכֹּר shikkôr; from H7937;  intoxicated, as a state or a habit:—drunk(-ard, -en, -en man).
h7910.r: From שָׁכַר (H7937)|English: drunken, drunk, filled with drink, abundantly, were merry

h7911.d: שָׁכַח shâkach, shaw-kakh'; or שָׁכֵחַ shâkêach; a primitive root;  to mislay, i.e. to be oblivious of, from want of memory or attention:—× at all, (cause to) forget.

h7912.d: שְׁכַח shᵉkach, shek-akh'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7911 through the idea of disclosure of a covered or forgotten thing;  to discover (literally or figuratively):—find.
h7912.r: Corresponding to שָׁכַח (H7911) through the idea of disclosure of a covered or forgotten thing|English: forget, forgotten, at all

h7913.d: שָׁכֵחַ shâkêach, shaw-kay'-akh; from H7911;  oblivious:—forget.
h7913.r: From שָׁכַח (H7911)|English: forget, forgotten, at all

h7914.d: שְׂכִיָּה sᵉkîyâh, sek-ee-yaw'; feminine from the same as H7906;  a conspicuous object:—picture.
h7914.r: From the same as שֵׂכוּ (H7906)|English: Sechu

h7916.d: שָׂכִיר sâkîyr, saw-keer'; from H7936;  a man at wages by the day or year:—hired (man, servant), hireling.
h7916.r: From שָׂכַר (H7936)|English: hire, rewardeth, wages, surely, hire out

h7917.d: שְׂכִירָה sᵉkîyrâh, sek-ee-raw'; feminine of H7916;  a hiring:—that is hired.
h7917.r: Fem. of שָׂכִיר (H7916)|English: hired servant, hireling, hired, hired man,

h7918.d: שָׁכַךְ shâkak, shaw-kak'; a primitive root;  to weave (i.e. lay) a trap; figuratively, (through the idea of secreting) to allay (passions; physically, abate a flood):—appease, assuage, make to cease, pacify, set.

h7919.d: שָׂכַל sâkal, saw-kal'; a primitive root;  to be (causatively, make or act) circumspect and hence, intelligent:—consider, expert, instruct, prosper, (deal) prudent(-ly), (give) skill(-ful), have good success, teach, (have, make to) understand(-ing), wisdom, (be, behave self, consider, make) wise(-ly), guide wittingly.

h7921.d: שָׁכֹל shâkôl, shaw-kole'; a primitive root;  properly, to miscarry, i.e. suffer abortion; by analogy, to bereave (literally or figuratively):—bereave (of children), barren, cast calf (fruit, young), be (make) childless, deprive, destroy, × expect, lose children, miscarry, rob of children, spoil.

h7922.d: שֶׂכֶל sekel, seh'-kel; or שֵׂכֶל sêkel; from H7919;  intelligence; by implication, success:—discretion, knowledge, policy, prudence, sense, understanding, wisdom, wise.
h7922.r: From שָׂכַל (H7919)|English: understand, wise, prosper, wisely, understanding, consider, instruct, prudent, skill, teach, misc

h7925.d: שָׁכַם shâkam, shaw-kam'; a primitive root; properly, to incline (the shoulder to a burden); but used only as denominative from H7926;  literally, to load up (on the back of man or beast), i.e. to start early in the morning:—(arise, be up, get (oneself) up, rise up) early (betimes), morning.

h7927.d: שְׁכֶם Shᵉkem, shek-em'; the same as H7926; ridge;  Shekem, a place in Palestine:—Shechem.
h7927.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h7927.r: The same as שְׁכֶם (H7926)|English: shoulder, back, consent, portion

h7931.d: שָׁכַן shâkan, shaw-kan'; a primitive root (apparently akin (by transmission) to H7901 through the idea of lodging; compare H5531, H7925);  to reside or permanently stay (literally or figuratively):—abide, continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-er), have habitation, inhabit, lay, place, (cause to) remain, rest, set (up).
h7931.r: A primitive root [apparently akin (by transmission) to שָׁכַב (H7901) through the idea of lodging]|English: lie, sleep, lie down, rest, lien, misc

h7934.d: שָׁכֵן shâkên, shaw-kane'; from H7931;  a resident; by extension, a fellow-citizen:—inhabitant, neighbour, nigh.
h7934.r: From שָׁכַן (H7931)|English: dwell, abide, place, remain, inhabit, rest, set, continue, dwellers, dwelling, misc

h7935.d: שְׁכַנְיָה Shᵉkanyâh, shek-an-yaw'; or (prolonged) שְׁכַנְיָהוּ Shᵉkanyâhûw; from H7931 and H3050; Jah has dwelt;  Shekanjah, the name of nine Israelites:—Shecaniah, Shechaniah.
h7935.r: From שָׁכַן (H7931) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: dwell, abide, place, remain, inhabit, rest, set, continue, dwellers, dwelling, misc

h7936.d: שָׂכַר sâkar, saw-kar'; or (by permutation) סָכַר çâkar; (Ezra 4:5), a primitive root (apparently akin (by prosthesis) to H3739 through the idea of temporary purchase; compare H7937);  to hire:—earn wages, hire (out self), reward, × surely.
h7936.r: A primitive root [apparently akin (by prosthesis) to כָּרָה (H3739) through the idea of temporary purchase]|English: buy, prepared, banquet

h7937.d: שָׁכַר shâkar, shaw-kar'; a primitive root;  to become tipsy; in a qualified sense, to satiate with a stimulating drink or (figuratively) influence:—(be filled with) drink (abundantly), (be, make) drunk(-en), be merry. (Superlative of H8248.)

h7938.d: שֶׂכֶר seker, seh'-ker; from H7936;  wages:—reward, sluices.
h7938.r: From שָׂכַר (H7936)|English: hire, rewardeth, wages, surely, hire out

h7939.d: שָׂכָר sâkâr, saw-kawr'; from H7936;  payment of contract; concretely, salary, fare, maintenance; by implication, compensation, benefit:—hire, price, reward(-ed), wages, worth.
h7939.r: From שָׂכַר (H7936)|English: hire, rewardeth, wages, surely, hire out

h7941.d: שֵׁכָר shêkâr, shay-kawr'; from H7937;  an intoxicant, i.e. intensely alcoholic liquor:—strong drink,   drunkard, strong wine.
h7941.r: From שָׁכַר (H7937)|English: drunken, drunk, filled with drink, abundantly, were merry

h7945.d: שֶׁל shel, shel; for the rel. H834; used with prepositional prefix, and often followed by some pronominal affix;  on account of, whatsoever, whichsoever:—cause, sake.
h7945.r: For the rel אֲשֶׁר (H834)|English: which, wherewith, because, when, soon, whilst, as if, as when, that, until, much, whosoever, whereas, wherein, whom, whose

h795.d: אַשְׁדּוֹד ʼAshdôwd, ash-dode'; from H7703; ravager;  Ashdod, a place in Palestine:—Ahdod.
h795.r: From שָׁדַד (H7703)|English: spoil, spoiler, waste, destroy, robbers, misc

h7950.d: שֶׁלֶג sheleg, sheh'-leg; from H7949;  snow (probably from its whiteness):—snow(-y).

h7951.d: שָׁלָה shâlâh, shaw-law'; or שָׁלַו shâlav; (Job 3:26), a primitive root;  to be tranquil, i.e. secure or successful:—be happy, prosper, be in safety.

h7956.d: שֵׁלָה Shêlâh, shay-law'; the same as H7596 (shortened); request;  Shelah, the name of a postdiluvian patriarch and of an Israelite:—Shelah.
h7956.r: The same as שְׁאֵלָה (H7596) (shortened)|English: petition, request, loan

h7957.d: שַׁלְהֶבֶת shalhebeth, shal-heh'-beth; from the same as H3851 with sibilant prefix;  a flare of fire:—(flaming) flame.
h7957.r: From the same as לַהַב (H3851) with sibilant prefix|English: flame, blade, glittering, bright

h7958.d: שְׂלָו sᵉlâv, sel-awv'; or שְׂלָיו sᵉlâyv; by orthographical variation from H7951 through the idea of sluggishness;  the quail collectively (as slow in flight from its weight):—quails.
h7958.r: By orthographical variation from שָׁלָה (H7951) through the idea of sluggishness|English: prosper, safety, happy

h7960.d: שָׁלוּ shâlûw, shaw-loo'; (Aramaic) or שָׁלוּת shâlûwth; (Aramaic), from the same as H7955;  a fault:—error, × fail, thing amiss.
h7960.r: From the same as שָׁלָה (H7955)|English: anything amiss

h7962.d: שַׁלְוָה shalvâh, shal-vaw'; from H7951;  security (genuine or false):—abundance, peace(-ably), prosperity, quietness.

h7964.d: שִׁלּוּחַ shillûwach, shil-loo'-akh; or שִׁלֻּחַ shilluach; from H7971;  (only in plural) a dismissal, i.e. (of a wife) divorce (especially the document); also (of a daughter) dower:—presents, have sent back.
h7964.r: From שָׁלַח (H7971)|English: send, go, (send, put,...) forth, send away, lay, send out, put, put away, cast out, stretch out, cast, set, put out, depart, soweth, loose

h7965.d: שָׁלוֹם shâlôwm, shaw-lome'; or שָׁלֹם shâlôm; from H7999;  safe, i.e. (figuratively) well, happy, friendly; also (abstractly) welfare, i.e. health, prosperity, peace:—× do, familiar, × fare, favour,   friend, × great, (good) health, (× perfect, such as be at) peace(-able, -ably), prosper(-ity, -ous), rest, safe(-ty), salute, welfare, (× all is, be) well, × wholly.
h7965.r: From שָׁלַם (H7999)|English: pay, peace, recompense, reward, render, restore, repay, perform, good, end, requite, restitution, finished, again, amends, full, misc

h7967.d: שַׁלּוּם Shallûwm, shal-loom'; or (shorter) שַׁלֻּם Shallum; the same as H7966;  Shallum, the name of fourteen Israelites:—Shallum.
h7967.r: The same as שִׁלּוּם (H7966)|English: recompense, reward

h7968.d: שַׁלּוּן Shallûwn, shal-loon'; probably for H7967;  Shallun, an Israelite:—Shallum.

h7969.d: שָׁלוֹשׁ shâlôwsh, shaw-loshe'; or שָׁלֹשׁ shâlôsh; masculine שְׁלוֹשָׁה shᵉlôwshâh; or שְׁלֹשָׁה shᵉlôshâh; a primitive number;  three; occasionally (ordinal) third, or (multiple) thrice:—+ fork, + often(-times), third, thir(-teen, -teenth), three, + thrice. Compare H7991.

h7970.d: שְׁלוֹשִׁים shᵉlôwshîym, shel-o-sheem'; or שְׁלֹשִׁים shᵉlôshîym; multiple of H7969;  thirty; or (ordinal) thirtieth:—thirty, thirtieth. Compare H7991.
h7970.r: Multiple of שָׁלוֹשׁ (H7969)|English: three, thirteen, thirteenth, third, thrice, threescore and thirteen, stories, forks, oftentimes

h7971.d: שָׁלַח shâlach, shaw-lakh'; a primitive root;  to send away, for, or out (in a great variety of applications):—× any wise, appoint, bring (on the way), cast (away, out), conduct, × earnestly, forsake, give (up), grow long, lay, leave, let depart (down, go, loose), push away, put (away, forth, in, out), reach forth, send (away, forth, out), set, shoot (forth, out), sow, spread, stretch forth (out).

h7972.d: שְׁלַח shᵉlach, shel-akh'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7971:—put, send.
h7972.r: Corresponding to שָׁלַח (H7971)|English: send, go, (send, put,...) forth, send away, lay, send out, put, put away, cast out, stretch out, cast, set, put out, depart, soweth, loose

h7973.d: שֶׁלַח shelach, sheh'-lakh; from H7971;  a missile of attack, i.e. spear; also (figuratively) a shoot of growth; i.e. branch:—dart, plant, × put off, sword, weapon.
h7973.r: From שָׁלַח (H7971)|English: send, go, (send, put,...) forth, send away, lay, send out, put, put away, cast out, stretch out, cast, set, put out, depart, soweth, loose

h7974.d: שֶׁלַח Shelach, sheh'-lakh; the same as H7973;  Shelach, a postdiluvian patriarch:—Salah, Shelah. Compare H7975.
h7974.r: The same as שֶׁלַח (H7973)|English: sword, weapon, dart, plant, put them off

h7979.d: שֻׁלְחָן shulchân, shool-khawn'; from H7971;  a table (as spread out); by implication, a meal:—table.

h8083.d: שְׁמֹנֶה shᵉmôneh, shem-o-neh'; or שְׁמוֹנֶה shᵉmôwneh; feminine שְׁמֹנָה shᵉmônâh; or שְׁמוֹנָה shᵉmôwnâh; apparently from H8082 through the idea of plumpness;  a cardinal number, eight (as if a surplus above the 'perfect' seven); also (as ordinal) eighth:—eight(-een, -eenth), eighth.
h8083.r: Apparently from שָׁמֵן (H8082) through the idea of plumpness|English: fat, plenteous, lusty

h8084.d: שְׁמֹנִים shᵉmônîym, shem-o-neem'; or שְׁמוֹנִים shᵉmôwnîym; multiple from H8083;  eighty, also eightieth:—eighty(-ieth), fourscore.
h8084.r: Mult from שְׁמֹנֶה (H8083)|English: eight, eighteen, eighteenth, eighth, eighteen thousand

h8085.d: שָׁמַע shâmaʻ, shaw-mah'; a primitive root;  to hear intelligently (often with implication of attention, obedience, etc.; causatively, to tell, etc.):—× attentively, call (gather) together, × carefully, × certainly, consent, consider, be content, declare, × diligently, discern, give ear, (cause to, let, make to) hear(-ken, tell), × indeed, listen, make (a) noise, (be) obedient, obey, perceive, (make a) proclaim(-ation), publish, regard, report, shew (forth), (make a) sound, × surely, tell, understand, whosoever (heareth), witness.

h8086.d: שְׁמַע shᵉmaʻ, shem-ah'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8085:—hear, obey.
h8086.r: Corresponding to שָׁמַע (H8085)|English: hear, hearken, obey, publish, understand, obedient, diligently, shew, sound, declare, discern, noise, perceive, tell, reported, misc

h8087.d: שֶׁמַע Shemaʻ, sheh'-mah; for the same as H8088;  Shema, the name of a place in Palestine and of four Israelites:—Shema.
h8087.r: For the same as שֵׁמַע (H8088)|English: fame, report, hear, tidings, bruit, loud, speech

h8088.d: שֵׁמַע shêmaʻ, shay'-mah; from H8085;  something heard, i.e. a sound, rumor, announcement; abstractly, audience:—bruit, fame, hear(-ing), loud, report, speech, tidings.
h8088.r: From שָׁמַע (H8085)|English: hear, hearken, obey, publish, understand, obedient, diligently, shew, sound, declare, discern, noise, perceive, tell, reported, misc

h809.d: אֲשִׁישָׁה ʼăshîyshâh, ash-ee-shaw'; feminine of H808;  something closely pressed together, i.e. a cake of raisins or other comfits:—flagon.

h8091.d: שָׁמָע Shâmâʻ, shaw-maw'; from H8085; obedient;  Shama, an Israelite:—Shama.
h8091.r: From שָׁמַע (H8085)|English: hear, hearken, obey, publish, understand, obedient, diligently, shew, sound, declare, discern, noise, perceive, tell, reported, misc

h8092.d: שִׁמְעָא Shimʻâʼ, shim-aw'; for H8093;  Shima, the name of four Israelites:—Shimea, Shimei, Shamma.

h8095.d: שִׁמְעוֹן Shimʻôwn, shim-one'; from H8085; hearing;  Shimon, one of Jacob's sons, also the tribe descended from him:—Simeon.
h8095.r: From שָׁמַע (H8085)|English: hear, hearken, obey, publish, understand, obedient, diligently, shew, sound, declare, discern, noise, perceive, tell, reported, misc

h8096.d: שִׁמְעִי Shimʻîy, shim-ee'; from H8088; famous;  Shimi, the name of twenty Israelites:—Shimeah (from the margin), Shimei, Shimhi, Shimi.
h8096.r: From שֵׁמַע (H8088)|English: fame, report, hear, tidings, bruit, loud, speech

h8098.d: שְׁמַעְיָה Shᵉmaʻyâh, shem-aw-yaw'; or שְׁמַעְיָהוּ Shᵉmaʻyâhûw; from H8085 and H3050; Jah has heard;  Shemajah, the name of twenty-five Israelites:—Shemaiah.
h8098.r: From שָׁמַע (H8085) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: hear, hearken, obey, publish, understand, obedient, diligently, shew, sound, declare, discern, noise, perceive, tell, reported, misc

h81.d: אֲבָקָה ʼăbâqâh, ab-aw-kaw'; feminine of H80:—powder.

h810.d: אֶשֶׁךְ ʼeshek, eh'-shek; from an unused root (probably meaning to bunch together);  a testicle (as a lump):—stone.
h810.r: From an unused root (probably meaning to bunch together)|

h8104.d: שָׁמַר shâmar, shaw-mar'; a primitive root;  properly, to hedge about (as with thorns), i.e. guard; generally, to protect, attend to, etc.:—beward, be circumspect, take heed (to self), keep(-er, self), mark, look narrowly, observe, preserve, regard, reserve, save (self), sure, (that lay) wait (for), watch(-man).

h811.d: אֶשְׁכּוֹל ʼeshkôwl, esh-kole'; or אֶשְׁכֹּל ʼeshkôl; probably prolonged from H810;  a bunch of grapes or other fruit:—cluster (of grapes).

h8111.d: שֹׁמְרוֹן Shômᵉrôwn, sho-mer-one'; from the active participle of H8104; watch-station;  Shomeron, a place in Palestine:—Samaria.
h8111.r: From the act part of שָׁמַר (H8104)|English: keep, observe, heed, keeper, preserve, beware, mark, watchman, wait, watch, regard, save, misc

h8113.d: שִׁמְרִי Shimrîy, shim-ree'; from H8105 in its original sense; watchful;  Shimri, the name of four Israelites:—Shimri.
h8113.r: From שֶׁמֶר (H8105) in its original sense|English: lees, dregs

h8114.d: שְׁמַרְיָה Shᵉmaryâh, shem-ar-yaw'; or שְׁמַרְיָהוּ Shᵉmaryâhûw; from H8104 and H3050; Jah has guarded;  Shemarjah, the name of four Israelites:—Shamariah, Shemariah.
h8114.r: From שָׁמַר (H8104) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: keep, observe, heed, keeper, preserve, beware, mark, watchman, wait, watch, regard, save, misc

h812.d: אֶשְׁכֹּל ʼEshkôl, esh-kole'; the same as H811;  Eshcol, the name of an Amorite, also of a valley in Palestine:—Eshcol.
h812.r: The same as אֶשְׁכֹּוֹל (H811)|English: cluster, cluster of grapes

h8121.d: שֶׁמֶשׁ shemesh, sheh'-mesh; from an unused root meaning to be brilliant;  the sun; by implication, the east; figuratively, a ray, i.e. (architectural) a notched battlement:—  east side(-ward), sun (rising),   west(-ward), window. See also H1053.
h8121.r: From an unused root meaning to be brilliant|

h8123.d: שִׁמְשׁוֹן Shimshôwn, shim-shone'; from H8121; sunlight;  Shimshon, an Israelite:—Samson.
h8123.r: From שֶׁמֶשׁ (H8121)|English: sun, sunrising, east side, windows, eastward, west, westward

h8125.d: שַׁמְשְׁרַי Shamshᵉray, sham-sher-ah'-ee; apparently from H8121; sunlike;  Shamsherai, an Israelite:—Shamsherai.
h8125.r: Apparently from שֶׁמֶשׁ (H8121)|English: sun, sunrising, east side, windows, eastward, west, westward

h8127.d: שֵׁן shên, shane; from H8150; compare H8143  a tooth (as sharp); specifically ivory; figuratively, a cliff:—crag, × forefront, ivory, × sharp, tooth.
h8127.r: From שָׁנַן (H8150)|English: sharp, whet, sharpen, prick, teach diligently

h8128.d: שֵׁן shên, shane; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8127;  a tooth:—tooth.
h8128.r: Corresponding to שֵׁן (H8127)|English: teeth, tooth, ivory, sharp, crag, forefront

h813.d: אַשְׁכְּנַז ʼAshkᵉnaz, ash-ken-az'; of foreign origin;  Ashkenaz, a Japhethite, also his descendants:—Ashkenaz.

h8130.d: שָׂנֵא sânêʼ, saw-nay'; a primitive root;  to hate (personally):—enemy, foe, (be) hate(-ful, -r), odious, × utterly.

h8132.d: שָׁנָא shânâʼ, shaw-naw'; a primitive root;  to alter:—change.

h8133.d: שְׁנָא shᵉnâʼ, shen-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8132:—alter, change, (be) diverse.

h8134.d: שִׁנְאָב Shinʼâb, shin-awb'; probably from H8132 and H1; a father has turned;  Shinab, a Canaanite:—Shinab.
h8134.r: Probably from שָׁנָא (H8132) and אָב (H1)|English: change

h8135.d: שִׂנְאָה sinʼâh, sin-aw'; from H8130;  hate:—  exceedingly, hate(-ful, -red).
h8135.r: From שָׂנֵא (H8130)|English: hate, enemies, enemy, foes, hateful, misc

h8137.d: שֶׁנְאַצַּר Shenʼatstsar, shen-ats-tsar'; apparently of Babylonian origin;  Shenatstsar, an Israelite:—Senazar.

h8138.d: שָׁנָה shânâh, shaw-naw'; a primitive root;  to fold, i.e. duplicate (literally or figuratively); by implication, to transmute (transitive or intransitive):—do (speak, strike) again, alter, double, (be given to) change, disguise, (be) diverse, pervert, prefer, repeat, return, do the second time.

h814.d: אֶשְׁכָּר ʼeshkâr, esh-cawr'; for H7939;  a gratuity:—gift, present.
h814.r: For שָׂכָר (H7939)|English: hire, reward, wages, price, fare, worth

h8140.d: שְׁנָה shᵉnâh, shen-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8141:—year.
h8140.r: Corresponding to שָׁנָה (H8141)|English: year, not translated, yearly, yearly, year, live, old, misc

h8141.d: שָׁנֶה shâneh, shaw-neh'; (in plural or (feminine) שָׁנָה shânâh; from H8138;  a year (as a revolution of time):—  whole age, × long,   old, year(× -ly).
h8141.r: From שָׁנָה (H8138)|English: change, second time, again, diverse, alter, disguise, doubled, pervert, preferred, repeateth, misc

h8142.d: שֵׁנָה shênâh, shay-naw'; or שֵׁנָא shênâʼ; (Psalm 127:2), from H3462;  sleep:—sleep.
h8142.r: From יָשַׁן (H3462)|English: sleep, remained long, old, old store

h8143.d: שֶׁנְהַבִּים shenhabbîym, shen-hab-beem'; from H8127 and the plural apparently of a foreign word;  probably, tooth of elephants, i.e. ivory tusk:—ivory.
h8143.r: From שֵׁן (H8127) and the pl. apparently of a foreign word|English: teeth, tooth, ivory, sharp, crag, forefront

h8145.d: שֵׁנִי shênîy, shay-nee'; from H8138;  properly, double, i.e. second; also adverbially, again:—again, either (of them), (an-) other, second (time).
h8145.r: From שָׁנָה (H8138)|English: change, second time, again, diverse, alter, disguise, doubled, pervert, preferred, repeateth, misc

h8147.d: שְׁנַיִם shᵉnayim, shen-ah'-yim; dual of H8145; feminine שְׁתַּיִם shᵉttayim;  two; also (as ordinal) twofold:—both, couple, double, second, twain,   twelfth,   twelve,   twenty (sixscore) thousand, twice, two.
h8147.r: Dual of שֵׁנִי (H8145)|English: second, other, time, again, another, more, either, second rank

h815.d: אֵשֶׁל ʼêshel, ay'-shel; from a root of uncertain signification;  a tamarisk tree; by extension, a grove of any kind:—grove, tree.
h815.r: From a root of uncertain signification|

h8150.d: שָׁנַן shânan, shaw-nan'; a primitive root;  to point (transitive or intransitive); intensively, to pierce; figuratively, to inculcate:—prick, sharp(-en), teach diligently, whet.

h8152.d: שִׁנְעָר Shinʻâr, shin-awr'; probably of foreign derivation;  Shinar, a plain in Babylonia:—Shinar.

h8153.d: שְׁנָת shᵉnâth, shen-awth'; from H3462;  sleep:—sleep.
h8153.r: From יָשַׁן (H3462)|English: sleep, remained long, old, old store

h8154.d: שָׁסָה shâçâh, shaw-saw'; or שָׁשָׂה shâsâh; (Isaiah 10:13), a primitive root;  to plunder:—destroyer, rob, spoil(-er).

h8155.d: שָׁסַס shâçaç, shaw-sas'; a primitive root;  to plunder:—rifle, spoil.

h8156.d: שָׁסַע shâçaʻ, shaw-sah'; a primitive root;  to split or tear; figuratively, to upbraid:—cleave, (be) cloven (footed), rend, stay.

h8159.d: שָׁעָה shâʻâh, shaw-aw'; a primitive root;  to gaze at or about (properly, for help); by implication, to inspect, consider, compassionate, be nonplussed (as looking around in amazement) or bewildered:—depart, be dim, be dismayed, look (away), regard, have respect, spare, turn.

h816.d: אָשַׁם ʼâsham, aw-sham'; or אָשֵׁם ʼâshêm; a primitive root;  to be guilty; by implication to be punished or perish:—× certainly, be(-come, made) desolate, destroy, × greatly, be(-come, found, hold) guilty, offend (acknowledge offence), trespass.

h8160.d: שָׁעָה shâʻâh, shaw-aw'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H8159;  properly, a look, i.e. a moment:—hour.
h8160.r: From a root corresponding to שָׁעָה (H8159)|English: look, respect, dismay, turn, regard, spare, be dim, depart

h8162.d: שַׁעַטְנֵז shaʻaṭnêz, shah-at-naze'; probably of foreign derivation;  linsey-woolsey, i.e. cloth of linen and wool carded and spun together:—garment of divers sorts, linen and wollen.

h8163.d: שָׂעִיר sâʻîyr, saw-eer'; or שָׂעִר sâʻir; from H8175;  shaggy; as noun, a he-goat; by analogy, a faun:—devil, goat, hairy, kid, rough, satyr.
h8163.r: From שָׂעַר (H8175)|English: be (horrible) afraid, come like (to take away as with) a whirlwind, be tempestuous, hurl as a storm

h8165.d: שֵׂעִיר Sêʻîyr, say-eer'; formed like H8163; rough;  Seir, a mountain of Idumaea and its aboriginal occupants, also one in Palestine:—Seir.
h8165.s: proper masculine noun, proper noun with reference to a mountain, proper noun with reference to territory
h8165.r: Formed like שָׂעִיר (H8163)|English: kid, goat, devil, satyr, hairy, rough

h817.d: אָשָׁם ʼâshâm, aw-shawm'; from H816;  guilt; by implication, a fault; also a sin-offering:—guiltiness, (offering for) sin, trespass (offering).
h817.r: From אָשַׁם (H816)|English: guilty, desolate, offend, trespass, certainly, destroy, faulty, greatly, offence

h8172.d: שָׁעַן shâʻan, shaw-an'; a primitive root;  to support one's self:—lean, lie, rely, rest (on, self), stay.

h8174.d: שַׁעַף Shaʻaph, shah'-af; from H5586; fluctuation;  Shaaph, the name of two Israelites:—Shaaph.

h8178.d: שַׂעַר saʻar, sah'-ar; from H8175;  a terror:—affrighted, × horribly, × sore, storm. See H8181.
h8178.r: From שָׂעַר (H8175)|English: be (horrible) afraid, come like (to take away as with) a whirlwind, be tempestuous, hurl as a storm

h8179.d: שַׁעַר shaʻar, shah'-ar; from H8176 in its original sense;  an opening, i.e. door or gate:—city, door, gate, port (× -er).
h8179.r: From שָׁעַר (H8176) in its original sense|English: think

h818.d: אָשֵׁם ʼâshêm, aw-shame'; from H816;  guilty; hence, presenting a sin-offering:—one which is faulty, guilty.
h818.r: From אָשַׁם (H816)|English: guilty, desolate, offend, trespass, certainly, destroy, faulty, greatly, offence

h8181.d: שֵׂעָר sêʻâr, say-awr'; or שַׂעַר saʻar; (Isaiah 7:20), from H8175 in the sense of dishevelling;  hair (as if tossed or bristling):—hair(-y), × rough.
h8181.r: From שָׂעַר (H8175) in the sense of dishevelling|English: be (horrible) afraid, come like (to take away as with) a whirlwind, be tempestuous, hurl as a storm

h8184.d: שְׂעֹרָה sᵉʻôrâh, seh-o-raw'; or שְׂעוֹרָה sᵉʻôwrâh (feminine meaning the plant); and (masculine meaning the grain); also שְׂעֹר sᵉʻôr; or שְׂעוֹר sᵉʻôwr; from H8175 in the sense of roughness;  barley (as villose):—barley.
h8184.r: From שָׂעַר (H8175) in the sense of roughness|English: be (horrible) afraid, come like (to take away as with) a whirlwind, be tempestuous, hurl as a storm

h8186.d: שַׁעֲרוּרָה shaʻărûwrâh, shah-ar-oo-raw'; or שַׁעֲרִירִיָּה shaʻărîyrîyâh; or שַׁעֲרֻרִת shaʻărurith; feminine from H8176 in the sense of H8175;  something fearful:—horrible thing.
h8186.r: From שָׁעַר (H8176) in the sense of שָׂעַר (H8175)|English: think

h8187.d: שְׁעַרְיָה Shᵉʻaryâh, sheh-ar-yaw'; from H8176 and H3050; Jah has stormed;  Shearjah, an Israelite:—Sheariah.

h819.d: אַשְׁמָה ʼashmâh, ash-maw'; feminine of H817;  guiltiness, a fault, the presentation of a sin-offering:—offend, sin, (cause of) trespass(-ing, offering).
h819.r: From אָשָׁם (H817)|English: trespass offering, trespass, offering for sin, sin, guiltiness

h8192.d: שָׁפָה shâphâh, shaw-faw'; a primitive root;  to abrade, i.e. bare:—high, stick out.

h8193.d: שָׂפָה sâphâh, saw-faw'; or (in dual and plural) שֶׂפֶת sepheth; probably from H5595 or H8192 through the idea of termination (compare H5490);  the lip (as a natural boundary); by implication, language; by analogy, a margin (of a vessel, water, cloth, etc.):—band, bank, binding, border, brim, brink, edge, language, lip, prating, (sea-)shore, side, speech, talk, (vain) words.
h8193.r: Probably from סָפָה (H5595) or שָׁפָה (H8192) through the idea of termination (compare סוֹף (H5490))|English: consume, destroy, add, perish, augment, heap, joined, put

h8195.d: שְׁפוֹ Shᵉphôw, shef-o'; or שְׁפִי Shᵉphîy; from H8192; baldness (compare H8205);  Shepho or Shephi, an Idumaean:—Shephi, Shepho.

h8196.d: שְׁפוֹט shᵉphôwṭ, shef-ote'; or שְׁפוּט shᵉphûwṭ; from H8199;  a judicial sentence, i.e. punishment:—judgment.
h8196.r: From שָׁפַט (H8199)|English: judge (v), judge (n), plead, avenged, condemn, execute, judgment, defend, deliver, misc

h8197.d: שְׁפוּפָם Shᵉphûwphâm, shef-oo-fawm'; or שְׁפוּפָן Shᵉphûwphân; from the same as H8207; serpent-like;  Shephupham, an Israelite:—Shephuphan, Shupham.
h8197.r: From the same as שְׁפִיפֹן (H8207)|English: adder

h8198.d: שִׁפְחָה shiphchâh, shif-khaw'; feminine from an unused root meaning to spread out (as a family; see H4940);  a female slave (as a member of the household):—(bond-, hand-) maid(-en, -servant), wench, bondwoman, womanservant.
h8198.r: From an unused root meaning to spread out (as a family; see מִשְׁפָּחָה (H4940))|English: families, kindred, kinds

h8199.d: שָׁפַט shâphaṭ, shaw-fat'; a primitive root;  to judge, i.e. pronounce sentence (for or against); by implication, to vindicate or punish; by extenssion, to govern; passively, to litigate (literally or figuratively):—  avenge, × that condemn, contend, defend, execute (judgment), (be a) judge(-ment), × needs, plead, reason, rule.

h82.d: אָבַר ʼâbar, aw-bar'; a primitive root;  to soar:—fly.

h8200.d: שְׁפַט shᵉphaṭ, shef-at'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8199;  to judge:—magistrate.
h8200.r: Corresponding to שָׁפַט (H8199)|English: judge (v), judge (n), plead, avenged, condemn, execute, judgment, defend, deliver, misc

h8201.d: שֶׁפֶט shepheṭ, sheh'-fet; from H8199;  a sentence, i.e. infliction:—judgment.
h8201.r: From שָׁפַט (H8199)|English: judge (v), judge (n), plead, avenged, condemn, execute, judgment, defend, deliver, misc

h8202.d: שָׁפָט Shâphâṭ, shaw-fawt'; from H8199; judge;  Shaphat, the name of four Israelites:—Shaphat.
h8202.r: From שָׁפַט (H8199)|English: judge (v), judge (n), plead, avenged, condemn, execute, judgment, defend, deliver, misc

h8203.d: שְׁפַטְיָה Shᵉphaṭyâh, shef-at-yaw'; or שְׁפַטְיָהוּ Shᵉphaṭyâhûw; from H8199 and H3050; Jah has judged;  Shephatjah, the name of ten Israelites:—Shephatiah.
h8203.r: From שָׁפַט (H8199) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: judge (v), judge (n), plead, avenged, condemn, execute, judgment, defend, deliver, misc

h8205.d: שְׁפִי shᵉphîy, shef-ee'; from H8192;  bareness; concretely, a bare hill or plain:—high place, stick out.

h8206.d: שֻׁפִּים Shuppîym, shoop-peem'; plural of an unused noun from the same as H8207 and meaning the same; serpents;  Shuppim, an Israelite:—Shuppim.
h8206.r: Pl. of an unused noun from the same as שְׁפִיפֹן (H8207) and meaning the same|English: adder

h821.d: אַשְׁמֻרָה ʼashmurâh, ash-moo-raw'; or אַשׁמוּרָה ʼashmûwrâh; or אַשׁמֹרֶת ʼashmôreth; (feminine) from H8104;  a night watch:—watch.
h821.r: From שָׁמַר (H8104)|English: keep, observe, heed, keeper, preserve, beware, mark, watchman, wait, watch, regard, save, misc

h8210.d: שָׁפַךְ shâphak, shaw-fak'; a primitive root;  to spill forth (blood, a libation, liquid metal; or even a solid, i.e. to mound up); also (figuratively) to expend (life, soul, complaint, money, etc.); intensively, to sprawl out:—cast (up), gush out, pour (out), shed(-der, out), slip.

h8213.d: שָׁפֵל shâphêl, shaw-fale'; a primitive root;  to depress or sink (especially figuratively, to humiliate, intransitive or transitive):—abase, bring (cast, put) down, debase, humble (self), be (bring, lay, make, put) low(-er).

h8214.d: שְׁפַל shᵉphal, shef-al'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8213:—abase, humble, put down, subdue.
h8214.r: Corresponding to שָׁפֵל (H8213)|English: ...low, ...down, humble, abase, debase, put lower

h8216.d: שֶׁפֶל shephel, shay'-fel; from H8213;  an humble rank:—low estate (place).
h8216.r: From שָׁפֵל (H8213)|English: ...low, ...down, humble, abase, debase, put lower

h8217.d: שָׁפָל shâphâl, shaw-fawl'; from H8213;  depressed, literally or figuratively:—base(-st), humble, low(-er, -ly).
h8217.r: From שָׁפֵל (H8213)|English: ...low, ...down, humble, abase, debase, put lower

h8227.d: שָׁפָן shâphân, shaw-fawn'; from H8226;  a species of rock-rabbit (from its hiding), i.e. probably the hyrax:—coney.

h8232.d: שְׁפַר shᵉphar, shef-ar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8231;  to be beautiful:—be acceptable, please,   think good.

h8233.d: שֶׁפֶר shepher, sheh'-fer; from H8231;  beauty:—× goodly.

h8234.d: שֶׁפֶר Shepher, sheh'-fer; the same as H8233;  Shepher, a place in the Desert:—Shapper.
h8234.s: proper noun with reference to a mountain

h8236.d: שִׁפְרָה Shiphrâh, shif-raw'; the same as H8235;  Shiphrah, an Israelitess:—Shiphrah.

h8239.d: שָׁפַת shâphath, shaw-fath'; a primitive root;  to locate, i.e. (generally) hang on or (figuratively) establish, reduce:—bring, ordain, set on.

h8240.d: שָׁפָת shâphâth, shaw-fawth'; from H8239;  a (double) stall (for cattle); also a (two-pronged) hook (for flaying animals on):—hook, pot.
h8240.r: From שָׁפַת (H8239)|English: set on, brought, ordain

h8242.d: שַׂק saq, sak; from H8264;  properly, a mesh (as allowing a liquid to run through), i.e. coarse loose cloth or sacking (used in mourning and for bagging); hence, a bag (for grain, etc.):—sack(-cloth, -clothes).
h8242.r: From שָׁקַק (H8264)|English: run to and fro, longing, ranging, appetite, run, justle one against another

h8245.d: שָׁקַד shâqad, shaw-kad'; a primitive root;  to be alert, i.e. sleepless; hence to be on the lookout (whether for good or ill):—hasten, remain, wake, watch (for).

h8246.d: שָׁקַד shâqad, shaw-kad'; a denominative from H8247;  to be (intensively, make) almond-shaped:—make like (unto, after the fashion of) almonds.
h8246.r: A denominative from שָׁקֵד (H8247)|English: almond, almond tree

h8247.d: שָׁקֵד shâqêd, shaw-kade'; from H8245;  the almond (tree or nut; as being the earliest in bloom):—almond (tree).
h8247.r: From שָׁקַד (H8245)|English: watch, wake, remain, hasten

h8248.d: שָׁקָה shâqâh, shaw-kaw'; a primitive root;  to quaff, i.e. (causatively) to irrigate or furnish a potion to:—cause to (give, give to, let, make to) drink, drown, moisten, water. See H7937, H8354.

h8251.d: שִׁקּוּץ shiqqûwts, shik-koots'; or שִׁקֻּץ shiqquts; from H8262;  disgusting, i.e. filthy; especially idolatrous or (concretely) an idol:—abominable filth (idol, -ation), detestable (thing).
h8251.r: From שָׁקַץ (H8262)|English: abomination, abominable, abhor, utterly, detest

h8252.d: שָׁקַט shâqaṭ, shaw-kat'; a primitive root;  to repose (usually figurative):—appease, idleness, (at, be at, be in, give) quiet(-ness), (be at, be in, give, have, take) rest, settle, be still.

h8254.d: שָׁקַל shâqal, shaw-kal'; a primitive root;  to suspend or poise (especially in trade):—pay, receive(-r), spend, × throughly, weigh.

h8255.d: שֶׁקֶל sheqel, sheh'-kel; from H8254;  probably a weight; used as a commercial standard:—shekel.
h8255.r: From שָׁקַל (H8254)|English: weigh, pay, throughly, receive, receiver, spend

h8256.d: שִׁקְמָה shiqmâh, shik-maw'; or (feminine) שִׁקְמָה shiqmâh; of uncertain derivation;  a sycamore (usually the tree):—sycamore (fruit, tree).

h8257.d: שָׁקַע shâqaʻ, shaw-kah'; (abbreviated Amos 8:8); a primitive root;  to subside; by implication, to be overflowed, cease; causatively, to abate, subdue:—make deep, let down, drown, quench, sink.

h8259.d: שָׁקַף shâqaph, shaw-kaf'; a primitive root;  properly, to lean out (of a window), i.e. (by implication) peep or gaze (passively, be a spectacle):—appear, look (down, forth, out).

h826.d: אַשָּׁף ʼashshâph, ash-shawf'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H825:—astrologer.

h8262.d: שָׁקַץ shâqats, shaw-kats'; a primitive root;  to be filthy, i.e. (intensively) to loathe, pollute:—abhor, make abominable, have in abomination, detest, × utterly.

h8263.d: שֶׁקֶץ sheqets, sheh'-kets; from H8262;  filth, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) an idolatrous object:—abominable(-tion).
h8263.r: From שָׁקַץ (H8262)|English: abomination, abominable, abhor, utterly, detest

h8266.d: שָׁקַר shâqar, shaw-kar'; a primitive root;  to cheat, i.e. be untrue (usually in words):—fail, deal falsely, lie.

h8267.d: שֶׁקֶר sheqer, sheh'-ker; from H8266;  an untruth; by implication, a sham (often adverbial):—without a cause, deceit(-ful), false(-hood, -ly), feignedly, liar,   lie, lying, vain (thing), wrongfully.
h8267.r: From שָׁקַר (H8266)|English: lie, deal falsely, fail

h8268.d: שֹׁקֶת shôqeth, sho'-keth; from H8248;  a trough (for watering):—trough.
h8268.r: From שָׁקָה (H8248)|English: drink, water, butler, cupbearer, misc

h8269.d: שַׂר sar, sar; from H8323;  a head person (of any rank or class):—captain (that had rule), chief (captain), general, governor, keeper, lord,(-task-)master, prince(-ipal), ruler, steward.
h8269.r: From שָׂרַר (H8323)|English: rule, make prince, altogether

h827.d: אַשְׁפָּה ʼashpâh, ash-paw'; perhaps (feminine) from the same as H825 (in the sense of covering);  a quiver or arrow-case:—quiver.
h827.r: Perhaps from the same as אַשָּׁף (H825) (in the sense of covering)|English: astrologer

h8270.d: שֹׁר shôr, shore; from H8324; (compare H8306)  a string (as twisted), i.e. (specifically) the umbilical cord (also figuratively, as the centre of strength):—navel.

h8271.d: שְׁרֵא shᵉrêʼ, sher-ay'; (Aramaic) a root corresponding to that of H8293;  to free, separate; figuratively, to unravel, commence; by implication (of unloading beasts) to reside:—begin, dissolve, dwell, loose.
h8271.r: A root corresponding to that of שֵׁרוּת (H8293)|English: variant

h8272.d: שַׁרְאֶצֶר Sharʼetser, shar-eh'-tser; of foreign derivation;  Sharetser, the name of an Assyrian and an Israelite:—Sharezer.

h8274.d: שֵׁרֵבְיָה Shêrêbᵉyâh, shay-rayb-yaw'; from H8273 and H3050; Jah has brought heat;  Sherebjah, the name of two Israelites:—Sherebiah.
h8274.r: From שָׁרָב (H8273) and יָהּ (H3050)|English: parched ground, heat

h8275.d: שַׁרְבִיט sharbîyṭ, shar-beet'; for H7626;  a rod of empire:—sceptre.
h8275.r: For שֵׁבֶט (H7626)|English: tribe, rod, sceptre, staff, misc

h8276.d: שָׂרַג sârag, saw-rag'; a primitive root;  to intwine:—wrap together, wreath.

h828.d: אַשְׁפְּנַז ʼAshpᵉnaz, ash-pen-az'; of foreign origin;  Ashpenaz, a Babylonian eunuch:—Ashpenaz.

h8281.d: שָׁרָה shârâh, shaw-raw'; a primitive root;  to free:—direct.

h8282.d: שָׂרָה sârâh, saw-raw'; feminine of H8269;  a mistress, i.e. female noble:—lady, princess, queen.
h8282.r: From שַׂר (H8269)|English: prince, captain, chief, ruler, governor, keeper, principal, general, lords, misc

h8283.d: שָׂרָה Sârâh, saw-raw'; the same as H8282;  Sarah, Abraham's wife:—Sarah.
h8283.r: The same as שָׂרָה (H8282)|English: lady, princess, queen

h8285.d: שֵׁרָה shêrâh, shay-raw'; from H8324 in its original sense of pressing;  a wrist-band (as compact or clasping):—bracelet.
h8285.r: From שָׁרַר (H8324) in its original sense of pressing|English: enemies

h8286.d: שְׂרוּג Sᵉrûwg, ser-oog'; from H8276; tendril;  Serug, a postdiluvian patriarch:—Serug.

h8288.d: שְׂרוֹךְ sᵉrôwk, ser-oke'; from H8308;  a thong (as laced or tied):—(shoe-)latchet.

h8289.d: שָׁרוֹן Shârôwn, shaw-rone'; probably abridged from H3474; plain;  Sharon, the name of a place in Palestine:—Lasharon, Sharon.
h8289.r: Probably abridged from יָשַׁר (H3474)|English: please, straight, direct, right, well, fitted, good, make straight, meet, upright, uprightly

h8294.d: שֶׂרַח Serach, seh'-rakh; by permutation for H5629; superfluity;  Serach, an Israelitess:—Sarah, Serah.

h8295.d: שָׂרַט sâraṭ, saw-rat'; a primitive root;  to gash:—cut in pieces, make [cuttings] pieces.

h8297.d: שָׂרַי Sâray, saw-rah'-ee; from H8269; dominative;  Sarai, the wife of Abraham:—Sarai.
h8297.r: From שַׂר (H8269)|English: prince, captain, chief, ruler, governor, keeper, principal, general, lords, misc

h8298.d: שָׁרַי Shâray, shaw-rah'-ee; probably from H8324; hostile;  Sharay, an Israelite:—Sharai.

h8299.d: שָׂרִיג sârîyg, saw-reeg'; from H8276;  a tendril (as entwining):—branch.

h83.d: אֵבֶר ʼêber, ay-ber'; from H82;  a pinion:—(long-) wing(-ed).

h830.d: אַשְׁפֹּת ʼashpôth, ash-pohth'; or אַשְׁפּוֹת ʼashpôwth; or שְׁפֹת shᵉphôth; (contraction) plural of a noun of the same form as H827, from H8192 (in the sense of scraping);  a heap of rubbish or filth:—dung (hill).
h830.r: Plural of a noun of the same form as אַשְׁפָּה (H827), from שָׁפָה (H8192) (in the sense of scraping)|English: quiver

h8300.d: שָׂרִיד sârîyd, saw-reed'; from H8277;  a survivor:—× alive, left, remain(-ing), remnant, rest.

h8303.d: שִׁרְיוֹן Shiryôwn, shir-yone'; and שִׂרְיֹן Siryôn; the same as H8302 (i.e. sheeted with snow);  Shirjon or Sirjon, a peak of the Lebanon:—Sirion.
h8303.s: proper noun with reference to a mountain
h8303.r: The same as שִׁרְיוֹן (H8302) (ie sheeted with snow)|English: habergeon, coat, harness, coat of mail, breastplate

h8304.d: שְׂרָיָה Sᵉrâyâh, ser-aw-yaw'; or שְׂרָיָהוּ Sᵉrâyâhûw; from H8280 and H3050; Jah has prevailed;  Serajah, the name of nine Israelites:—Seraiah.

h831.d: אַשְׁקְלוֹן ʼAshqᵉlôwn, ash-kel-one'; probably from H8254 in the sense of weighing-place (i.e. mart);  Ashkelon, a place in Palestine:—Ashkelon, Askalon.
h831.r: Probably from שָׁקַל (H8254) in the sense of weighing-place (i.e. mart)|English: weigh, pay, throughly, receive, receiver, spend

h8312.d: שַׂרְעַף sarʻaph, sar-af'; for H5587;  cogitation:—thought.

h8313.d: שָׂרַף sâraph, saw-raf'; a primitive root;  to be (causatively, set) on fire:—(cause to, make a) burn((-ing), up) kindle, × utterly.

h8314.d: שָׂרָף sârâph, saw-rawf'; from H8313;  burning, i.e. (figuratively) poisonous (serpent); specifically, a saraph or symbolical creature (from their copper color):—fiery (serpent), seraph.
h8314.r: From שָׂרַף (H8313)|English: burn, burn up, kindled, made, utterly

h8315.d: שָׂרָף Sârâph, saw-raf'; the same as H8314;  Saraph, an Israelite:—Saraph.
h8315.r: The same as שָׂרָף (H8314)|English: fiery serpent, fiery, seraphim

h8316.d: שְׂרֵפָה sᵉrêphâh, ser-ay-faw'; from H8313;  cremation:—burning.
h8316.r: From שָׂרַף (H8313)|English: burn, burn up, kindled, made, utterly

h8317.d: שָׁרַץ shârats, shaw-rats'; a primitive root;  to wriggle, i.e. (by implication) swarm or abound:—breed (bring forth, increase) abundantly (in abundance), creep, move.

h8318.d: שֶׁרֶץ sherets, sheh'-rets; from H8317;  a swarm, i.e. active mass of minute animals:—creep(-ing thing), move(-ing creature).
h8318.r: From שָׁרַץ (H8317)|English: creep, bring forth abundantly, move, breed abundantly, increase abundantly

h8319.d: שָׁרַק shâraq, shaw-rak'; a primitive root;  properly, to be shrill, i.e. to whistle or hiss (as a call or in scorn):—hiss.

h8320.d: שָׂרֻק sâruq, saw-rook'; from H8319;  bright red (as piercing to the sight), i.e. bay:—speckled. See H8291.

h8321.d: שֹׂרֵק sôrêq, so-rake'; or שׂוֹרֵק sôwrêq; and (feminine) שֹׂרֵקָה sôrêqâh; from H8319 in the sense of redness (compare H8320);  a vine stock (properly, one yielding purple grapes, the richest variety):—choice(-st, noble) wine. Compare H8291.
h8321.r: From שָׁרַק (H8319) in the sense of redness (compare שָׂרֹק (H8320))|English: hiss

h8323.d: שָׂרַר sârar, saw-rar'; a primitive root;  to have (transitively, exercise; reflexively, get) dominion:—× altogether, make self a prince, (bear) rule.

h8327.d: שָׁרַשׁ shârash, shaw-rash'; a primitive root;  to root, i.e. strike into the soil, or (by implication) to pluck from it:—(take, cause to take) root (out).

h8328.d: שֶׁרֶשׁ sheresh, sheh'-resh; from H8327;  a root (literally or figuratively):—bottom, deep, heel, root.

h833.d: אָשַׁר ʼâshar, aw-shar'; or אָשֵׁר ʼâshêr; a primitive root;  to be straight (used in the widest sense, especially to be level, right, happy); figuratively, to go forward, be honest, prosper:—(call, be) bless(-ed, happy), go, guide, lead, relieve.

h8330.d: שֹׁרֶשׁ shôresh, sho'-resh; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8328:—root.
h8330.r: Corresponding to שֶׁרֶשׁ (H8328)|English: root, bottom, deep, heels

h8331.d: שַׁרְשָׁה sharshâh, shar-shaw'; from H8327;  a chain (as rooted, i.e. linked):—chain. Compare H8333.

h8333.d: שַׁרְשְׁרָה sharshᵉrâh, shar-sher-aw'; from H8327 (compare H8331);  a chain; (architectural) probably a garland:—chain.

h8334.d: שָׁרַת shârath, shaw-rath'; a primitive root;  to attend as a menial or worshipper; figuratively, to contribute to:—minister (unto), (do) serve(-ant, -ice, -itor), wait on.

h8336.d: שֵׁשׁ shêsh, shaysh; or (for alliteration with H4897) שְׁשִׁי shᵉshîy; for H7893;  bleached stuff, i.e. white linen or (by analogy) marble:—× blue, fine (twined) linen, marble, silk.

h8337.d: שֵׁשׁ shêsh, shaysh; masculine שִׁשָּׁה shishshâh; a primitive number; see H7797  six (as an overplus beyond five or the fingers of the hand); as ordinal sixth:—six(-teen, -teenth), sixth.

h8338.d: שָׁשָׁא shâshâʼ, shaw-shaw'; a primitive root; apparently,  to annihilate:—leave by the sixth part (by confusion with H8341).

h8339.d: שֵׁשְׁבַּצַּר Shêshᵉbatstsar, shaysh-bats-tsar'; of foreign derivation;  Sheshbatstsar, Zerubbabel's Persian name:—Sheshbazzar.

h834.d: אֲשֶׁר ʼăsher, ash-er'; a primitive relative pronoun (of every gender and number);  who, which, what, that; also (as an adverb and a conjunction) when, where, how, because, in order that, etc.:—× after, × alike, as (soon as), because, × every, for, + forasmuch, + from whence, + how(-soever), × if, (so) that ((thing) which, wherein), × though, + until, + whatsoever, when, where (+ -as, -in, -of, -on, -soever, -with), which, whilst, + whither(-soever), who(-m, -soever, -se). As it is indeclinable, it is often accompanied by the personal pronoun expletively, used to show the connection.
h834.r: A primitive relative pronoun (of every gender and number)|

h8340.d: שֵׁשְׁבַּצַּר Shêshᵉbatstsar, shaysh-bats-tsar'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8339:—Sheshbazzar.

h8342.d: שָׂשׂוֹן sâsôwn, saw-sone'; or שָׂשֹׂן sâsôn; from H7797;  cheerfulness; specifically, welcome:—gladness, joy, mirth, rejoicing.
h8342.r: From שׂוּשׂ (H7797)|English: rejoice, glad, greatly, joy, mirth

h8343.d: שָׁשַׁי Shâshay, shaw-shah'-ee; perhaps from H8336; whitish;  Shashai, an Israelite:—Shashai.
h8343.r: Perhaps from שֵׁשׁ (H8336)|English: linen, fine linen marble, silk, variant

h8344.d: שֵׁשַׁי Shêshay, shay-shah'-ee; probably for H8343;  Sheshai, a Canaanite:—Sheshai.

h8345.d: שִׁשִּׁי shishshîy, shish-shee'; from H8337;  sixth, ordinal or (feminine) fractional:—sixth (part).
h8345.r: From שֵׁשׁ (H8337)|English: six, sixteen, sixteenth, sixth, sixteen, threescore

h8346.d: שִׁשִּׁים shishshîym, shish-sheem'; multiple of H8337;  sixty:—sixty, three score.
h8346.r: Multiple of שֵׁשׁ (H8337)|English: six, sixteen, sixteenth, sixth, sixteen, threescore

h8348.d: שֵׁשָׁן Shêshân, shay-shawn'; perhaps for H7799; lily;  Sheshan, an Israelite:—Sheshan.

h8349.d: שָׁשַׁק Shâshaq, shaw-shak'; probably from the base of H7785; pedestrian;  Shashak, an Israelite:—Shashak.
h8349.r: Probably from the base of שׁוֹק (H7785)|English: shoulder, legs, hip, thigh

h835.d: אֶשֶׁר ʼesher, eh'-sher; from H833;  happiness; only in masculine plural construction as interjection, how happy!:—blessed, happy.
h835.r: From אָשַׁר (H833)|English: blessed, lead, go, guide, happy, leaders, relieve

h8352.d: שֵׁת Shêth, shayth; from H7896; put, i.e. substituted;  Sheth, third son of Adam:—Seth, Sheth.
h8352.r: From שִׁית (H7896)|English: set, made, lay, put, appoint, regard, misc

h8353.d: שֵׁת shêth, shayth; (Aramaic) or שִׁת shith; (Aramaic), corresponding to H8337;:—six(-th).
h8353.r: Corresponding to שֵׁשׁ (H8337)|English: six, sixteen, sixteenth, sixth, sixteen, threescore

h8354.d: שָׁתָה shâthâh, shaw-thaw'; a primitive root;  to imbibe (literally or figuratively):—× assuredly, banquet, × certainly, drink(-er, -ing), drunk (× -ard), surely. (Intensive proposition of H8248.)

h8355.d: שְׁתָה shᵉthâh, sheth-aw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8354:—drink.
h8355.r: Corresponding to שָׁתָה (H8354)|English: drink, drinkers, drunkards, banquet, misc

h836.d: אָשֵׁר ʼÂshêr, aw-share'; from H833, happy;  Asher, a son of Jacob, and the tribe descended from him, with its territory; also a place in Palestine:—Asher
h836.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h836.r: From אָשַׁר (H833)|English: blessed, lead, go, guide, happy, leaders, relieve

h8362.d: שָׁתַל shâthal, shaw-thal'; a primitive root;  to transplant:—plant.

h8366.d: שָׁתַן shâthan, shaw-than'; a primitive root;  (causatively) to make water, i.e. urinate:—piss.

h8368.d: שָׂתַר sâthar, saw-thar'; a primitive root;  to break out (as an eruption):—have in (one's) secret parts.

h8369.d: שֵׁתָר Shêthâr, shay-thawr'; of foreign derivation;  Shethar, a Persian satrap:—Shethar.

h837.d: אֹשֶׁר ʼôsher, o'-sher; from H833;  happiness:—happy.

h8506.d: תֹּכֶן tôken, to'-ken; from H8505;  a fixed quantity:—measure, tale.
