h8507.d: תֹּכֶן Tôken, to'-ken; the same as H8506;  Token, a place in Palestine:—Tochen.
h8507.r: The same as תֹּכֶן (H8506)|English: tale, measure

h851.d: אֶשְׁתְּמֹעַ ʼEshtᵉmôaʻ, esh-tem-o'-ah; or אֶשְׁתְּמוֹעַ ʼEshtᵉmôwaʻ; or אֶשְׁתְּמֹה ʼEshtᵉmôh; from H8085 (in the sense of obedience);  Eshtemoa or Eshtemoh, a place in Palestine:—Eshtemoa, Eshtemoh.
h851.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h851.r: From שָׁמַע (H8085) (in the sense of obedience)|English: hear, hearken, obey, publish, understand, obedient, diligently, shew, sound, declare, discern, noise, perceive, tell, reported, misc

h8511.d: תָּלָא tâlâʼ, taw-law'; a primitive root;  to suspend; figuratively (through hesitation) to be uncertain; by implication (of mental dependence) to habituate:—be bent, hang (in doubt).

h8517.d: תְּלַג tᵉlag, tel-ag'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H7950;  snow:—snow.

h8518.d: תָּלָה tâlâh, taw-law'; a primitive root;  to suspend (especially to gibbet):—hang (up).

h852.d: אָת ʼâth, awth; (Aramaic) corresponding to H226;  a portent:—sign.
h852.r: Corresponding to אוֹת (H226)|English: sign(s), token(s), ensign(s), miracles, mark

h8520.d: תֶּלַח Telach, teh'-lakh; probably from an unused root meaning to dissever; breach;  Telach, an Israelite:—Telah.
h8520.r: Probably from an unused root meaning to dissever|

h8521.d: תֵּל חַרְשָׁא Têl Charshâʼ, tale khar-shaw'; from H8510 and the feminine of H2798; mound of workmanship;  Tel-Charsha, a place in Babylonia:—Tel-haresha, Tel-harsa.
h8521.r: From תֵּל (H8510) and the fem. of חֲרָשִׁים (H2798)|English: heap, strength

h8523.d: תְּלִיתַי tᵉlîythay, tel-ee-thah'-ee; (Aramaic) or תַּלְתִּי taltîy; (Aramaic), ordinal from H8532;  third:—third.

h8524.d: תָּלַל tâlal, taw-lal'; a primitive root;  to pile up, i.e. elevate:—eminent. Compare H2048.

h853.d: אֵת ʼêth, ayth; apparent contracted from H226 in the demonstrative sense of entity;  properly, self (but generally used to point out more definitely the object of a verb or preposition, even or namely):—[as such unrepresented in English].
h853.r: Apparently contracted from אוֹת (H226) in the demonstrative sense of entity|English: sign(s), token(s), ensign(s), miracles, mark

h8532.d: תְּלָת tᵉlâth, tel-awth'; (Aramaic) masculine תְּלָתָה tᵉlâthâh; (Aramaic), or תְּלָתָא tᵉlâthâʼ; (Aramaic), corresponding to H7969;  three or third:—third, three.
h8532.r: Corresponding to שָׁלוֹשׁ (H7969)|English: three, thirteen, thirteenth, third, thrice, threescore and thirteen, stories, forks, oftentimes

h8533.d: תְּלָתִין tᵉlâthîyn, tel-aw-theen'; (Aramaic) multiple of H8532;  ten times three:—thirty.

h8535.d: תָּם tâm, tawm; from H8552;  complete; usually (morally) pious; specifically, gentle, dear:—coupled together, perfect, plain, undefiled, upright.
h8535.r: From תָּמַם (H8552)|English: consume, end, finished, clean, upright, spent, perfect, done, failed, accomplish, misc

h8536.d: תָּם tâm, tawm; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8033;  there:—× thence, there, × where.
h8536.r: Corresponding to שָׁם (H8033)|English: there, therein, thither, whither, in it, thence, thereout

h8537.d: תֹּם tôm, tome; from H8552;  completeness; figuratively, prosperity; usually (morally) innocence:—full, integrity, perfect(-ion), simplicity, upright(-ly, -ness), at a venture. See H8550.
h8537.r: From תָּמַם (H8552)|English: consume, end, finished, clean, upright, spent, perfect, done, failed, accomplish, misc

h8539.d: תָּמַהּ tâmahh, taw-mah'; a primitive root;  to be in consternation:—be amazed, be astonished, marvel(-lously), wonder.

h854.d: אֵת ʼêth, ayth; probably from H579;  properly, nearness (used only as a preposition or an adverb), near; hence, generally, with, by, at, among, etc.:—against, among, before, by, for, from, in(-to), (out) of, with. Often with another prepositional prefix.
h854.r: Probably from אָנָה (H579)|English: deliver, befall, happen, seeketh a quarrel

h8543.d: תְּמוֹל tᵉmôwl, tem-ole'; or תְּמֹל tᵉmôl; probably for H865; sometimes with H8032  properly, ago, i.e. a (short or long) time since; especially yesterday, or day before yesterday:—  before (-time),   these (three) days,   heretofore,   time past, yesterday.
h8543.r: Probably for אֶתְמוֹל (H865)|English: time past, herefore, beforetime, yesterday, old, late, before

h8544.d: תְּמוּנָה tᵉmûwnâh, tem-oo-naw'; or תְּמֻנָה tᵉmunâh; from H4327;  something portioned (i.e. fashioned) out, as a shape, i.e. (indefinitely) phantom, or (specifically) embodiment, or (figuratively) manifestation (of favor):—image, likeness, similitude.

h8548.d: תָּמִיד tâmîyd, taw-meed'; from an unused root meaning to stretch;  properly, continuance (as indefinite extension); but used only (attributively as adjective) constant (or adverbially, constantly); elliptically the regular (daily) sacrifice:—alway(-s), continual (employment, -ly), daily, (n-)ever(-more), perpetual.
h8548.r: From an unused root meaning to stretch|

h8549.d: תָּמִים tâmîym, taw-meem'; from H8552;  entire (literally, figuratively or morally); also (as noun) integrity, truth:—without blemish, complete, full, perfect, sincerely (-ity), sound, without spot, undefiled, upright(-ly), whole.
h8549.r: From תָּמַם (H8552)|English: consume, end, finished, clean, upright, spent, perfect, done, failed, accomplish, misc

h8551.d: תָּמַךְ tâmak, taw-mak'; a primitive root;  to sustain; by implication, to obtain, keep fast; figuratively, to help, follow close:—(take, up-) hold (up), maintain, retain, stay (up).

h8552.d: תָּמַם tâmam, taw-mam'; a primitive root;  to complete, in a good or a bad sense, literal, or figurative, transitive or intransitive:—accomplish, cease, be clean (pass-) ed, consume, have done, (come to an, have an, make an) end, fail, come to the full, be all gone, × be all here, be (make) perfect, be spent, sum, be (shew self) upright, be wasted, whole.

h8553.d: תִּמְנָה Timnâh, tim-naw'; from H4487; a portion assigned;  Timnah, the name of two places in Palestine:—Timnah, Timnath, Thimnathah.
h8553.r: From מָנָה (H4487)|English: number, prepare, appointed, tell, count, set

h8555.d: תִּמְנָע Timnâʻ, tim-naw'; from H4513; restraint;  Timna, the name of two Edomites:—Timna, Timnah.
h8555.s: proper feminine noun, proper masculine noun
h8555.r: From מָנַע (H4513)|English: withhold, keep back, refrain, denied, deny, hinder, keep, restrained

h8556.d: תִּמְנַת חֶרֶס Timnath Chereç, tim-nath kheh'-res; or תִּמְנַת סֶרַח Timnath Çerach; from H8553 and H2775; portion of (the) sun;  Timnath-Cheres, a place in Palestine:—Timnath-heres, Timnath-serah.
h8556.r: From תִּמְנָה (H8553) and חֶרֶס (H2775)|English: Timnath, Timnah, Thimnathah

h8558.d: תָּמָר tâmâr, taw-mawr'; from an unused root meaning to be erect;  a palm tree:—palm (tree).
h8558.r: From an unused root meaning to be erect|

h8559.d: תָּמָר Tâmâr, taw-mawr'; the same as H8558;  Tamar, the name of three women and a place:—Tamar.
h8559.s: proper feminine noun, proper locative noun
h8559.r: The same as תָּמָר (H8558)|English: palm tree

h8561.d: תִּמֹּר timmôr, tim-more'; (plural or (feminine) תִּמֹּרָה timmôrâh; (singular and plural), from the same root as H8558;  (architectural) a palm-like pilaster (i.e. umbellate):—palm tree.
h8561.r: From the same root as תָּמָר (H8558)|English: palm tree

h8563.d: תַּמְרוּר tamrûwr, tam-roor'; from H4843;  bitterness (plural as collective):—× most bitter(-ly).
h8563.r: From מָרַר (H4843)|English:  bitterness, bitter, bitterly, choler, grieved, vexed, bitterness, grieved him, provoke

h8565.d: תַּן tan, tan; from an unused root probably meaning to elongate;  a monster (as preternaturally formed), i.e. a sea-serpent (or other huge marine animal); also a jackal (or other hideous land animal):—dragon, whale. Compare H8577.
h8565.r: From an unused root probably meaning to elongate|

h8569.d: תְּנוּאָה tᵉnûwʼâh, ten-oo-aw'; from H5106;  alienation; by implication, enmity:—breach of promise, occasion.
h8569.r: From נוֹא (H5106)|English: disallow, discourage, make to non effect, break, misc

h857.d: אָתָה ʼâthâh, aw-thaw'; or אָתָא ʼâthâʼ; a primitive root (collateral to H225 contraction);  to arrive:—(be-, things to) come (upon), bring.
h857.r: A primitive root [collateral to אוֹת (H225) contraction]|English: consent

h8570.d: תְּנוּבָה tᵉnûwbâh, ten-oo-baw'; from H5107;  produce:—fruit, increase.
h8570.r: From נוּב (H5107)|English: bring forth, increase, make cheerful

h8571.d: תְּנוּךְ tᵉnûwk, ten-ook'; perhaps from the same as H594 through the idea of protraction;  a pinnacle, i.e. extremity:—tip.
h8571.r: Perhaps from the same as אֲנָךְ (H594) through the idea of protraction|English: plumbline

h8572.d: תְּנוּמָה tᵉnûwmâh, ten-oo-maw'; from H5123;  drowsiness, i.e. sleep:—slumber(-ing).

h8573.d: תְּנוּפָה tᵉnûwphâh, ten-oo-faw'; from H5130;  a brandishing (in threat); by implication, tumult; specifically, the official undulation of sacrificial offerings:—offering, shaking, wave (offering).
h8573.r: From נוּף (H5130)|English: wave, shake, offer, lift up, move, perfumed, send, sift, strike

h8574.d: תַּנּוּר tannûwr, tan-noor'; from H5216;  a fire-pot:—furnace, oven.

h8577.d: תַּנִּין tannîyn, tan-neen'; or תַּנִּים tannîym; (Ezekiel 29:3), intensive from the same as H8565;  a marine or land monster, i.e. sea-serpent or jackal:—dragon, sea-monster, serpent, whale.
h8577.r: Intensive from the same as תַּן (H8565)|English: whale

h8579.d: תִּנְיָנוּת tinyânûwth, tin-yaw-nooth'; (Aramaic) from H8578;  a second time:—again.

h858.d: אָתָה ʼâthâh, aw-thaw'; (Aramaic) or אָתָא ʼâthâʼ; (Aramaic), corresponding to H857:—(be-) come, bring.

h8580.d: תַּנְשֶׁמֶת tanshemeth, tan-sheh'-meth; from H5395;  properly, a hard breather, i.e. the name of two unclean creatures, a lizard and a bird (both perhaps from changing color through their irascibility), probably the tree-toad and the water-hen:—mole, swan.

h8581.d: תַּעָב taʻâb, taw-ab'; a primitive root;  to loathe, i.e. (morally) detest:—(make to be) abhor(-red), (be, commit more, do) abominable(-y), × utterly.

h8582.d: תָּעָה tâʻâh, taw-aw'; a primitive root;  to vacillate, i.e. reel or stray (literally or figuratively); also causative of both:—(cause to) go astray, deceive, dissemble, (cause to, make to) err, pant, seduce, (make to) stagger, (cause to) wander, be out of the way.

h8583.d: תֹּעוּ Tôʻûw, to'-oo; or תֹּעִי Tôʻîy; from H8582; error  Tou or Toi, a Syrian king:—Toi, Tou.
h8583.r: From תָּעָה (H8582)|English: err, astray, wander, seduced, stagger, out of the way, away, deceived, misc

h8585.d: תְּעָלָה tᵉʻâlâh, teh-aw-law'; from H5927;  a channel (into which water is raised for irrigation); also a bandage or plaster (as placed upon a wound):—conduit, cured, healing, little river, trench, watercourse.
h8585.r: From עָלָה (H5927)|English: (come, etc...) up, offer, come, bring, ascend, go, chew, offering, light, increase, burn, depart, put, spring, raised, arose, break, exalted

h859.d: אַתָּה ʼattâh, at-taw'; or (shortened); אַתָּ ʼattâ; or אַת ʼath; feminine (irregular) sometimes אַתִּי ʼattîy; plural masculine אַתֶּם ʼattem; feminine אַתֶּן ʼatten; or אַתֵּנָה ʼattênâhlemma אתֵּנָה missing vowel, corrected to אַתֵּנָה; or אַתֵּנָּה ʼattênnâh; a primitive pronoun of the second person;  thou and thee, or (plural) ye and you:—thee, thou, ye, you.
h859.r: A primitive pronoun of the second person|

h8590.d: תַּעֲנָךְ Taʻănâk, tah-an-awk'; or תַּעְנָךְ Taʻnâk; of uncertain derivation;  Taanak or Tanak, a place in Palestine:—Taanach, Tanach.

h8593.d: תַּעַר taʻar, tah'-ar; from H6168;  a knife or razor (as making bare); also a scabbard (as being bare, i.e. empty):—(pen-) knife, razor, scabbard, shave, sheath.
h8593.r: From עָרָה (H6168)|English: uncover, discover, emptied, rase, leave destitute, make naked, poured out, poured, spreading

h8596.d: תֹּף tôph, tofe; from H8608 contracted;  a tambourine:—tabret, timbrel.
h8596.r: From תָּפַף (H8608) contracted|English: playing with timbrels, tabering

h8597.d: תִּפְאָרָה tiphʼârâh, tif-aw-raw'; or תִּפְאֶרֶת tiphʼereth; from H6286;  ornament (abstractly or concretely, literally or figuratively):—beauty(-iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), honour, majesty.
h8597.r: From פָּאַר (H6286)|English: glorify, beautify, boast,go over the boughs, Glory, vaunt

h8598.d: תַּפּוּחַ tappûwach, tap-poo'-akh; from H5301;  an apple (from its fragrance), i.e. the fruit or the tree (probably includ. others of the pome order, as the quince, the orange, etc.):—apple (tree). See also H1054.
h8598.r: From נָפַח (H5301)|English: blow, breathe, seething, blown, lose, snuffed, give up

h8599.d: תַּפּוּחַ Tappûwach, tap-poo'-akh; the same as H8598;  Tappuach, the name of two places in Palestine, also of an Israelite:—Tappuah.
h8599.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h8599.r: The same as תַּפּוּחַ (H8598)|English: apple tree, apple

h860.d: אָתוֹן ʼâthôwn, aw-thone'; probably from the same as H386 (in the sense of patience);  a female donkey (from its docility):—(she) ass.
h860.r: Probably from the same as אֵיתָן (H386) (sense of patience)|English: strong, mighty, strength, hard, rough

h8602.d: תָּפֵל tâphêl, taw-fale'; from an unused root meaning to smear;  plaster (as gummy) or slime; (figuratively) frivolity:—foolish things, unsavoury, untempered.
h8602.r: From an unused root meaning to smear|

h8604.d: תִּפְלָה tiphlâh, tif-law'; from the same as H8602;  frivolity:—folly, foolishly.
h8604.r: From the same as תָּפֵל (H8602)|English: untempered, foolish, unsavoury

h8605.d: תְּפִלָּה tᵉphillâh, tef-il-law'; from H6419;  intercession, supplication; by implication, a hymn:—prayer.
h8605.r: From פָּלַל (H6419)|English: pray, made, judge, intreat, judgment, prayer, supplication, thought

h8607.d: תִּפְסַח Tiphçach, tif-sakh'; from H6452; ford;  Tiphsach, a place in Mesopotamia:—Tipsah.
h8607.r: From פָּסַח (H6452)|English: pass over, halt, become lame, leap

h8608.d: תָּפַף tâphaph, taw-faf'; a primitive root;  to drum, i.e. play (as) on the tambourine:—taber, play with timbrels.

h8609.d: תָּפַר tâphar, taw-far'; a primitive root;  to sew:—(women that) sew (together).

h861.d: אַתּוּן ʼattûwn, at-toon'; (Aramaic) probably from the corresponding to H784;  probably a fire-place, i.e. furnace:—furnace.
h861.r: Probably from the corresponding to אֵשׁ (H784)|English: fire, burning, fiery, untranslated variant, fire, flaming, hot

h8610.d: תָּפַשׂ tâphas, taw-fas'; a primitive root;  to manipulate, i.e. seize; chiefly to capture, wield, specifically, to overlay; figuratively, to use unwarrantably:—catch, handle, (lay, take) hold (on, over), stop, × surely, surprise, take.

h8612.d: תֹּפֶת Tôpheth, to'-feth; the same as H8611;  Topheth, a place near Jerusalem:—Tophet, Topheth.

h8615.d: תִּקְוָה tiqvâh, tik-vaw'; from H6960; (compare H6961)  literally a cord (as an attachment); figuratively, expectancy:—expectation(-ted), hope, live, thing that I long for.
h8615.r: From קָוָה (H6960)|English: wait, look, wait for, look for, gathered, misc

h862.d: אַתּוּק ʼattûwq, at-tooke'; or אַתִּיק ʼattîyq; from H5423 in the sense of decreasing;  a ledge or offset in a building:—gallery.
h862.r: From נָתַק (H5423) in the sense of decreasing|English: break, drawn away, lifted up, plucked away, draw, drawn, break off, pluck off, root out, pull out, pluck, burst in sunder, break in sunder

h8620.d: תְּקוֹעַ Tᵉqôwaʻ, tek-o'-ah; a form of H8619;  Tekoa, a place in Palestine:—Tekoa, Tekoah.
h8620.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h8622.d: תְּקוּפָה tᵉqûwphâh, tek-oo-faw'; or תְּקֻפָה tᵉquphâh; from H5362;  a revolution, i.e. (of the sun) course, (of time) lapse:—circuit, come about, end.
h8622.r: From נָקַף (H5362)|English: compass, go round about, go about, compass about, destroy, down, inclosed, kill, round

h8624.d: תַּקִּיף taqqîyph, tak-keef'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8623:—mighty, strong.

h8628.d: תָּקַע tâqaʻ, taw-kah'; a primitive root;  to clatter, i.e. slap (the hands together), clang (an instrument); by analogy, to drive (a nail or tent-pin, a dart, etc.); by implication, to become bondsman by handclasping):—blow (a trumpet), cast, clap, fasten, pitch (tent), smite, sound, strike, × suretiship, thrust.

h8629.d: תֵּקַע têqaʻ, tay-kah'; from H8628;  a blast of a trumpet:—sound.
h8629.r: From תָּקַע (H8628)|English: blow, fasten, strike, pitch, thrust, clap, sounded, cast, misc

h863.d: אִתַּי ʼIttay, it-tah'ee; or אִיתַי ʼÎythay; from H854; near;  Ittai or Ithai, the name of a Gittite and of an Israelite:—Ithai, Ittai.
h863.r: From אֵת (H854)|English: against, with, in, him, me, upon

h8630.d: תָּקַף tâqaph, taw-kaf'; a primitive root;  to overpower:—prevail (against).

h8631.d: תְּקֵף tᵉqêph, tek-afe'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8630;  to become (causatively, make) mighty or (figuratively) obstinate:—make firm, harden, be(-come) strong.

h8633.d: תֹּקֶף tôqeph, to'-kef; from H8630;  might or (figuratively) positiveness:—authority, power, strength.

h8639.d: תַּרְדֵּמָה tardêmâh, tar-day-maw'; from H7290;  a lethargy or (by implication) trance:—deep sleep.
h8639.r: From רָדַם (H7290)|English: ..deep sleep, was fast asleep, sleep, sleeper

h8640.d: תִּרְהָקָה Tirhâqâh, teer-haw'-kaw; of foreign derivation;  Tirhakah, a king of Kush:—Tirhakah.

h8641.d: תְּרוּמָה tᵉrûwmâh, ter-oo-maw'; or תְּרֻמָה tᵉrumâh; (Deuteronomy 12:11), from H7311;  a present (as offered up), especially in sacrifice or as tribute:—gift, heave offering (shoulder), oblation, offered(-ing).
h8641.r: From רוּם (H7311)|English: (lift, hold, etc...) up, exalt, high, offer, give, heave, extol, lofty, take, tall, higher, misc

h8643.d: תְּרוּעָה tᵉrûwʻâh, ter-oo-aw'; from H7321;  clamor, i.e. acclamation of joy or a battle-cry; especially clangor of trumpets, as an alarum:—alarm, blow(-ing) (of, the) (trumpets), joy, jubile, loud noise, rejoicing, shout(-ing), (high, joyful) sound(-ing).
h8643.r: From רוּעַ (H7321)|English: shout, noise, ..alarm, cry, triumph, smart, misc

h8646.d: תֶּרַח Terach, teh'-rakh; of uncertain derivation;  Terach, the father of Abraham; also a place in the Desert:—Tarah, Terah.
h8646.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun

h8648.d: תְּרֵין tᵉrêyn, ter-ane'; (Aramaic) feminine תַּרְתֵּין tartêyn; corresponding to H8147;  two:—second,   twelve, two.
h8648.r: Corresponding to שְׁנַיִם (H8147)|English: two, twelve, both, twelfth, second, twain, both of them, twice, double, misc

h865.d: אֶתְמוֹל ʼethmôwl, eth-mole'; or אִתְמוֹל ʼithmôwl; or אֶתְמוּל ʼethmûwl; probably from H853 or H854 and H4136;  heretofore; definitely yesterday:—  before (that) time,   heretofore, of late (old),   times past, yester(day).
h865.r: Probably from אֵת (H853) or אֵת (H854) and מוֹל (H4136)|English: not translated

h8651.d: תְּרַע tᵉraʻ, ter-ah'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H8179;  a door; by implication, a palace:—gate mouth.
h8651.r: Corresponding to שַׁעַר (H8179)|English: gate, city, door, port, porters

h8652.d: תָּרָע târâʻ, taw-raw'; (Aramaic) from H8651;  a doorkeeper:—porter.

h8656.d: תִּרְצָה Tirtsâh, teer-tsaw'; from H7521; delightsomeness;  Tirtsah, a place in Palestine; also an Israelitess:—Tirzah.
h8656.s: proper feminine noun, proper locative noun
h8656.r: From רָצָה (H7521)|English: accept, please, pleasure, delight, enjoy, favourable, acceptable, accomplish, affection, approve, misc

h8658.d: תַּרְשִׁישׁ tarshîysh, tar-sheesh'; probably of foreign derivation (compare H8659);  a gem, perhaps the topaz:—beryl.
h8658.r: Probably of foreign derivation [compare תַּרְשִׁישׁ (H8659)]|English: Tarshish, Tharshish

h8659.d: תַּרְשִׁישׁ Tarshîysh, tar-sheesh'; probably the same as H8658 (as the region of the stone, or the reverse);  Tarshish, a place on the Mediterranean, hence, the ephithet of a merchant vessel (as if for or from that port); also the name of a Persian and of an Israelite:—Tarshish, Tharshish.
h8659.s: proper locative noun, proper masculine noun
h8659.r: Probably the same as תַּרְשִׁישׁ (H8658) (as the region of the stone, or the reverse)|English: beryl

h8661.d: תַּרְתָּן Tartân, tar-tawn'; of foreign derivation;  Tartan, an Assyrian:—Tartan.

h8665.d: תַּשְׁבֵּץ tashbêts, tash-bates'; from H7660;  checkered stuff (as reticulated):—broidered.

h8668.d: תְּשׁוּעָה tᵉshûwʻâh, tesh-oo-aw'; or תְּשֻׁעָה tᵉshuʻâh; from H7768 in the sense of H3467;  rescue (literal or figurative, persons, national or spiritual):—deliverance, help, safety, salvation, victory.
h8668.r: From שָׁוַע (H7768) in the sense of יָשַׁע (H3467)|English: cried, cry out, aloud, shout

h8670.d: תְּשׁוּרָה tᵉshûwrâh, tesh-oo-raw'; from H7788 in the sense of arrival;  a gift:—present.
h8670.r: From שׁוּר (H7788) in the sense of arrival|English: went, sing

h8672.d: תֵּשַׁע têshaʻ, tay'-shah; or (masculine) תִּשְׁעָה tishʻâh; perhaps from H8159 through the idea of a turn to the next or full number ten;  nine or (ordinal) ninth:—nine (+ -teen, + -teenth, -th).
h8672.r: Perhaps from שָׁעָה (H8159) through the idea of a turn to the next or full number ten|English: look, respect, dismay, turn, regard, spare, be dim, depart

h8673.d: תִּשְׁעִים tishʻîym, tish-eem'; multiple from H8672;  ninety:—ninety.
h8673.r: Multiple from תֵּשַׁע (H8672)|English: nine, ninth, nineteenth, nineteen

h8674.d: תַּתְּנַי Tattᵉnay, tat-ten-ah'-ee; of foreign derivation;  Tattenai, a Persian:—Tatnai.

h868.d: אֶתְנַן ʼethnan, eth-nan'; the same as H866;  a gift (as the price of harlotry or idolatry):—hire, reward.

h87.d: אַבְרָם ʼAbrâm, ab-rawm'; contracted from H48; high father;  Abram, the original name of Abraham:—Abram.

h870.d: אֲתַר ʼăthar, ath-ar'; (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of H871;  a place; (adverb) after:—after, place.
h870.r: From a root corresponding to that of אֲתָרִים (H871)|English: spies

h874.d: בָּאַר bâʼar, baw-ar'; a primitive root;  to dig; by analogy, to engrave; figuratively, to explain:—declare, (make) plain(-ly).

h875.d: בְּאֵר bᵉʼêr, be-ayr'; from H874;  a pit; especially a well:—pit, well.

h877.d: בֹּאר bôʼr, bore; from H874;  a cistern:—cistern.

h880.d: בְּאֵרָה Bᵉʼêrâh, be-ay-raw'; the same as H878;  Beerah, an Israelite:—Beerah.

h883.d: בְּאֵר לַחַי רֹאִי Bᵉʼêr la-Chay Rôʼîy, be-ayr' lakh-ah'ee ro-ee'; from H875 and H2416 (with prefix) and H7203; well of a living (One) my Seer;  Beer-Lachai-Roi, a place in the Desert:—Beer-lahai-roi.
h883.r: From בְּאֵר (H875) and חַי (H2416) (with prefix) and רֹאֶה (H7203)|English: well, pit, slimepits, not translated

h884.d: בְּאֵר שֶׁבַע Bᵉʼêr Shebaʻ, be-ayr' sheh'-bah; from H875 and H7651 (in the sense of H7650); well of an oath;  Beer-Sheba, a place in Palestine:—Beer-shebah.
h884.r: From בְּאֵר (H875) and שֶׁבַע (H7651) (in the sense of שָׁבַע (H7650))|English: well, pit, slimepits, not translated

h887.d: בָּאַשׁ bâʼash, baw-ash'; a primitive root;  to smell bad; figuratively, to be offensive morally:—(make to) be abhorred (had in abomination, loathsome, odious), (cause a, make to) stink(-ing savour), × utterly.

h888.d: בְּאֵשׁ bᵉʼêsh, be-aysh'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H887:—displease.
h888.r: Corresponding to בָּאַשׁ (H887)|English: stink, abhor, abomination, loathsome, stinking savour, utterly (inf. for emphasis)

h891.d: בְּאֻשִׁים bᵉʼushîym, be-oo-sheem'; plural of H889;  poison-berries:—wild grapes.

h893.d: בֵּבַי Bêbay, bay-bah'ee; probably of foreign origin;  Bebai, an Israelite:—Bebai.

h894.d: בָּבֶל Bâbel, baw-bel'; from H1101; confusion;  Babel (i.e. Babylon), including Babylonia and the Babylonian empire:—Babel, Babylon.
h894.r: From בָּלַל (H1101)|English: mingled, confound, anointed, mixed, give provender, tempered, non translated variant

h895.d: בַּבֶל Babel, baw-bel'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H894:—Babylon.
h895.r: Corresponding to בָּבֶל (H894)|English: Babylon, Babylonian, Babel

h898.d: בָּגַד bâgad, baw-gad'; a primitive root;  to cover (with a garment); figuratively, to act covertly; by implication, to pillage:—deal deceitfully (treacherously, unfaithfully), offend, transgress(-or), (depart), treacherous (dealer, -ly, man), unfaithful(-ly, man), × very.

h899.d: בֶּגֶד beged, behg'-ed; from H898;  a covering, i.e. clothing; also treachery or pillage:—apparel, cloth(-es, ing), garment, lap, rag, raiment, robe, × very (treacherously), vesture, wardrobe.
h899.r: From בָּגַד (H898)|English: treacherously, transgressor, transgress, deceitfully, treacherous dealer, treacherous, very  (inf. for emphasis), unfaithful man, treacherous men, offend, unfaithfully

h9.d: אֲבֵדָה ʼăbêdâh, ab-ay-daw'; from H6; Compare H10.  concrete, something lost; abstract, destruction, i.e. Hades:—lost.
h9.r: From אָבַד (H6)|English: perish, destroy, lose, fail, surely, utterly, broken, destruction, escape, flee, spendeth, take, undone, void

h90.d: אֲגַג ʼĂgag, ag-ag'; or אֲגָג ʼĂgâg; of uncertain derivation (compare H89); flame;  Agag, a title of Amalekitish kings:—Agag.
h90.r: Of uncertain derivation, compare with אָגֵא (H89)|English: Agee

h900.d: בֹּגְדוֹת bôgᵉdôwth, bohg-ed-ohth; feminine plural active participle of H898;  treacheries:—treacherous.
h900.r: Plural active participle of בָּגַד (H898)|English: treacherously, transgressor, transgress, deceitfully, treacherous dealer, treacherous, very  (inf. for emphasis), unfaithful man, treacherous men, offend, unfaithfully

h902.d: בִּגְוַי Bigvay, big-vah'ee; probably of foreign origin;  Bigvai, an Israelite:—Bigvai.

h903.d: בִּגְתָא Bigthâʼ, big-thaw'; of Persian derivation;  Bigtha, a eunuch of Xerxes:—Bigtha.

h904.d: בִּגְתָן Bigthân, big-thawn'; or בִּגְתָנָא Bigthânâʼ; of similar derivation to H903;  Bigthan or Bigthana, a eunuch of Xerxes:—Bigthan, Bigthana.
h904.r: Of similar derivation to בִּגְתָא (H903)|English: Bigtha

h905.d: בַּד bad, bad; from H909;  properly, separation; by implication, a part of the body, branch of a tree, bar for carrying; figuratively, chief of a city; especially (with prepositional prefix) as an adverb, apart, only, besides:—alone, apart, bar, besides, branch, by self, of each alike, except, only, part, staff, strength.

h906.d: בַּד bad, bad; perhaps from H909 (in the sense of divided fibres);  flaxen thread or yarn; hence, a linen garment:—linen.
h906.r: Perhaps from בָּדַד (H909) (in the sense of divided fibres)|English: alone

h907.d: בַּד bad, bad; from H908;  a brag or lie; also a liar:—liar, lie.

h909.d: בָּדַד bâdad, baw-dad'; a primitive root;  to divide, i.e. (reflexively) be solitary:—alone.

h910.d: בָּדָד bâdâd, baw-dawd'; from H909;  separate; adverb, separately:—alone, desolate, only, solitary.

h912.d: בֵּדְיָה Bêdᵉyâh, bay-de-yaw'; probably a shortened form H5662; servant of Jehovah;  Bedejah, an Israelite:—Bedeiah.
h912.r: Probably a shortened form עֹבַדְיָה (H5662)|English: Obadiah

h913.d: בְּדִיל bᵉdîyl, bed-eel'; from H914;  alloy (because removed by smelting); by analogy, tin:—  plummet, tin.
h913.r: From בָּדַל (H914)|English: separate, divide, difference, asunder, severed, sever out, separation, utterly (inf. for emphasis)

h914.d: בָּדַל bâdal, baw-dal'; a primitive root;  to divide (in variation senses literally or figuratively, separate, distinguish, differ, select, etc.):—(make, put) difference, divide (asunder), (make) separate (self, -ation), sever (out), × utterly.

h917.d: בְּדָן Bᵉdân, bed-awn'; probably shortened for H5658; servile;  Bedan, the name of two Israelites:—Bedan.

h926.d: בָּהַל bâhal, baw-hal'; a primitive root;  to tremble inwardly (or palpitate), i.e. (figuratively) be (causative, make) (suddenly) alarmed or agitated; by implication to hasten anxiously:—be (make) affrighted (afraid, amazed, dismayed, rash), (be, get, make) haste(-n, -y, -ily), (give) speedy(-ily), thrust out, trouble, vex.

h927.d: בְּהַל bᵉhal, be-hal'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H926;  to terrify, hasten:—in haste, trouble.
h927.r: Corresponding to בָּהַל (H926)|English: trouble, haste, afraid, vexed, amazed, hasty, affrighted, dismayed, hastily, thrust him out, rash, speedily, speedy, vex

h928.d: בֶּהָלָה behâlâh, beh-haw-law'; from H926;  panic, destruction:—terror, trouble.
h928.r: From בָּהַל (H926)|English: trouble, haste, afraid, vexed, amazed, hasty, affrighted, dismayed, hastily, thrust him out, rash, speedily, speedy, vex

h929.d: בְּהֵמָה bᵉhêmâh, be-hay-maw'; from an unused root (probably meaning to be mute);  properly, a dumb beast; especially any large quadruped or animal (often collective):—beast, cattle.
h929.r: From an unused root (probably meaning to be mute)|

h930.d: בְּהֵמוֹת bᵉhêmôwth, be-hay-mohth'; in form a plural or H929, but really a singular of Egyptian derivation;  a water-ox, i.e. the hippopotamus or Nile-horse:—Behemoth.
h930.r: In form a plural or בְּהֵמָה (H929), but really a singular of Egyptian derivation|English: beast, cattle

h934.d: בֹּהֶרֶת bôhereth, bo-heh'-reth; feminine active participle of the same as H925;  a whitish spot on the skin:—bright spot.
h934.r: Active participle of the same as בָּהִיר (H925)|English: bright

h935.d: בּוֹא bôwʼ, bo; a primitive root;  to go or come (in a wide variety of applications):—abide, apply, attain, × be, befall,   besiege, bring (forth, in, into, to pass), call, carry, × certainly, (cause, let, thing for) to come (against, in, out, upon, to pass), depart, × doubtless again,   eat,   employ, (cause to) enter (in, into, -tering, -trance, -try), be fallen, fetch,   follow, get, give, go (down, in, to war), grant,   have, × indeed, (in-) vade, lead, lift (up), mention, pull in, put, resort, run (down), send, set, × (well) stricken (in age), × surely, take (in), way.

h936.d: בּוּז bûwz, booz; a primitive root;  to disrespect:—contemn, despise, × utterly.

h937.d: בּוּז bûwz, booz; from H936;  disrespect:—contempt(-uously), despised, shamed.
h937.r: From בּוּז (H936)|English: despise, contemned, utterly (inf. for emphasis)

h938.d: בּוּז Bûwz, booz; the same as H937;  Buz, the name of a son of Nahor, and of an Israelite:—Buz.
h938.r: The same as בּוּז (H937)|English: contempt, despised, contemptuously, shamed

h944.d: בּוּל bûwl, bool; for H2981;  produce (of the earth, etc.):—food, stock.

h945.d: בּוּל Bûwl, bool; the same as H944 (in the sense of rain);  Bul, the eighth Hebrew month:—Bul.
h945.r: The same as בּוּל (H944) (in the sense of rain)|English: food, stock

h947.d: בּוּס bûwç, boos; a primitive root;  to trample (literally or figuratively):—loath, tread (down, under (foot)), be polluted.

h948.d: בּוּץ bûwts, boots; from an unused root (of the same form) meaning to bleach, i.e. (intransitive) be white;  probably cotton (of some sort):—fine (white) linen.
h948.r: From an unused root (of the same form) meaning to bleach, i.e. (intransitive) be white|

h953.d: בּוֹר bôwr, bore; from H952 (in the sense of H877);  a pit hole (especially one used as a cistern or a prison):—cistern, dungeon, fountain, pit, well.
h953.r: From בּוּר (H952) (in the sense of בֹּאר (H877))|English: declare

h954.d: בּוּשׁ bûwsh, boosh; a primitive root;  properly, to pale, i.e. by implication to be ashamed; also (by implication) to be disappointed or delayed:—(be, make, bring to, cause, put to, with, a-) shamed(-d), be (put to) confounded(-fusion), become dry, delay, be long.

h955.d: בּוּשָׁה bûwshâh, boo-shaw'; feminine participle passive of H954;  shame:—shame.
h955.r: Participle passive of בּוּשׁ (H954)|English: ashamed, confounded, shame, all (inf. for emphasis), confusion, delayed, dry, long, shamed

h957.d: בַּז baz, baz; from H962;  plunder:—booty, prey, spoil(-ed).
h957.r: From בָּזַז (H962)|English: spoil, prey, spoiled, rob, take, take away, caught, gathering, robbers, took, utterly

h958.d: בָּזָא bâzâʼ, baw-zaw'; a primitive root;  probably to cleave:—spoil.

h959.d: בָּזָה bâzâh, baw-zaw'; a primitive root;  to disesteem:—despise, disdain, contemn(-ptible),   think to scorn, vile person.

h961.d: בִּזָּה bizzâh, biz-zaw'; feminine of H957;  booty:—prey, spoil.
h961.r: From בַּז (H957)|English: prey, spoil, spoiled, booty

h962.d: בָּזַז bâzaz, baw-zaz'; a primitive root;  to plunder:—catch, gather, (take) for a prey, rob(-ber), spoil, take (away, spoil), × utterly.

h963.d: בִּזָּיוֹן bizzâyôwn, biz-zaw-yone'; from H959  disesteem:—contempt.
h963.r: From בָּזָה (H959)|English: despise, contemptible, contemned, disdained, vile person, scorn

h967.d: בָּזַר bâzar, baw-zar'; a primitive root;  to disperse:—scatter.

h968.d: בִּזְתָא Bizthâʼ, biz-thaw'; of Persian origin;  Biztha, a eunuch of Xerxes:—Biztha.

h970.d: בָּחוּר bâchûwr, baw-khoor'; or בָּחֻר bâchur; participle passive of H977;  properly, selected, i.e. a youth (often collective):—(choice) young (man), chosen, × hole.
h970.r: Participle passive of בָּחַר (H977)|English: choose, chosen, choice, choose...out, acceptable, appoint, excellent, chosen men, rather, require, not translated

h972.d: בָּחִיר bâchîyr, baw-kheer'; from H977;  select:—choose, chosen one, elect.
h972.r: From בָּחַר (H977)|English: choose, chosen, choice, choose...out, acceptable, appoint, excellent, chosen men, rather, require, not translated

h973.d: בָּחַל bâchal, baw-khal'; a primitive root;  to loath:—abhor, get hastily (from the margin for H926).

h974.d: בָּחַן bâchan, baw-khan'; a primitive root;  to test (especially metals); generally and figuratively, to investigate:—examine, prove, tempt, try (trial).

h977.d: בָּחַר bâchar, baw-khar'; a primitive root;  properly, to try, i.e. (by implication) select:—acceptable, appoint, choose (choice), excellent, join, be rather, require.

h982.d: בָּטַח bâṭach, baw-takh'; a primitive root;  properly, to hie for refuge (but not so precipitately as H2620); figuratively, to trust, be confident or sure:—be bold (confident, secure, sure), careless (one, woman), put confidence, (make to) hope, (put, make to) trust.

h983.d: בֶּטַח beṭach, beh'takh; from H982;  properly, a place of refuge; abstract, safety, both the fact (security) and the feeling (trust); often (adverb with or without preposition) safely:—assurance, boldly, (without) care(-less), confidence, hope, safe(-ly, -ty), secure, surely.
h983.r: From בָּטַח (H982)|English: trust, confidence, secure, confident, bold, careless, hope, hoped, ones, sure, women

h988.d: בָּטֵל bâṭêl, baw-tale'; a primitive root;  to desist from labor:—cease.

h989.d: בְּטֵל bᵉṭêl, bet-ale'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H988;  to stop:—(cause, make to), cease, hinder.

h990.d: בֶּטֶן beṭen, beh'-ten; from an unused root probably meaning to be hollow;  the belly, especially the womb; also the bosom or body of anything:—belly, body,   as they be born,   within, womb.
h990.r: From an unused root probably meaning to be hollow|

h992.d: בֹּטֶן bôṭen, bo'-ten; from H990;  (only in plural) a pistachio-nut (from its form):—nut.
h992.r: From בֶּטֶן (H990)|English: belly, womb, body, within, born

h994.d: בִּי bîy, bee; perhaps from H1158 (in the sense of asking); properly, a request; used only adverbially (always with 'my Lord');  oh that!; with leave, or if it please:—alas, O, oh.
h994.r: Perhaps from בָּעָה (H1158) (sense of asking)|English: enquire, boil, sought up, swelling out

h995.d: בִּין bîyn, bene; a primitive root;  to separate mentally (or distinguish), i.e.(generally) understand:—attend, consider, be cunning, diligently, direct, discern, eloquent, feel, inform, instruct, have intelligence, know, look well to, mark, perceive, be prudent, regard, (can) skill(-full), teach, think, (cause, make to, get, give, have) understand(-ing), view, (deal) wise(-ly, man).

h996.d: בֵּין bêyn, bane; (sometimes in the plural masculine or feminine); properly, the constructive form of an otherwise unused noun from H995; a distinction; but used only as a preposition,  between (repeated before each noun, often with other particles); also as a conjunction, either...or:—among, asunder, at, between (-twixt...and), + from (the widest), × in, out of, whether (it be...or), within.
h996.s: masculine substantive (always used as a preposition)
h996.r: (sometimes in the pl. masc. or fem.) properly, the constructive form of an otherwise unused noun from בִּין (H995)|English: understand, understanding, consider, prudent, perceive, regard, discern, instruct, misc.

h997.d: בֵּין bêyn, bane; (Aramaic) corresponding to H996:—among, between.
h997.r: Corresponding to בַּיִן (H996)|English: between, betwixt, asunder, within, between, out of, from

h998.d: בִּינָה bîynâh, bee-naw'; from H995;  understanding:—knowledge, meaning, × perfectly, understanding, wisdom.
h998.r: From בִּין (H995)|English: understand, understanding, consider, prudent, perceive, regard, discern, instruct, misc.

h999.d: בִּינָה bîynâh, bee-naw'; (Aramaic) corresponding to H998:—knowledge.
h999.r: Corresponding to בִּינָה (H998)|English: understanding, wisdom, knowledge, meaning, perfectly, understand
